Text: Helping Jerry Seinfeld to choose some clothes that had come from an op shop. They were old, colourless woolen cardigans and jumpers. A single static image of myself as a ten year old, wearing my cub scout cap pulled down over my eyes, obscuring my face, I am sitting in the fork of a tree. The image is like a photograph, but is off centre, so you don't see much of my body, but is mainly of the tree and the sky. Something about a very remote beach, where there is no pollution, halfway along one of the coastlines of Australia. There is a sandy track down to this beach, and the wheel tracks of lots of four wheel drives have churned up the sand in the tracks and also all along the beach.

I am on a guided bus tour to the Gold Coast with my partner and her son. I am not enjoying the tour, I don't know why I am there. Someone wants to organise that a few of us break away from the tour and go drinking that night, and they are trying to involve me in the plan, but I am trying to excuse myself. i explain that I used to live near the Gold Coast, so I am familiar with it and it is not new. I say that I used to always drive through the town to cross over the border, but I would never stop there. I am trying to say this while being polite and not put them off their excitement for their night out.
someone is stabbing needles into my brain. I take Mark Zuckerberg to court.

going down into a sewer wearing a deep sea diver’s suit, requiring depressurising. I was having my final night shift at work i asked oncoming shift if they minded I go get some coffee at a shop down the road before we handed over. I went to get coffee, taking about fifteen minutes to walk there—it was a doctor’s clinic, it was by the banks of a river, and all the people around seemed to be engaging in recreation activities, enjoying themselves in boats, having picnics etc. The river stopped at the doctor’s surgery though. There were bluestone-cobbled pavement and street at the end of the river, and I wondered whether the river went underground at this point. I thought I would have to look it up on google maps.  I went into the doctor’s and I sat in the waiting room watching something on television about rainforests. I rang my doctor explaining that I had an appointment with them at 3pm that same day, but could I come for appointment now because I had to see someone this morning, and something about not wanting to pass something on to them if I was infected. I was stuttering and embarrassed on the phone, was lying about something. the doctor couldn’t change my appointment. I went to leave, the nurse on reception wanted to take my blood pressure. I asked if it was too late to change my coffee order to a double shot, no it was ok, they said. For some reason they had touched the blood pressure cuff with a swab that had been used to collect my faeces sample. The cuff was made of material I had been using to make face masks I asked whether they shouldn’t sterilise the cuff, no, they said, it was ok. the nurse said my blood pressure was 100 and i thought, that is very low. They asked what I thought of the tv show in the waiting room. They didn’t ask for payment or medicare details and said i could leave, I thought this was strange. Realised by now that I was late for the completion of my sleepover shift, started to hurry back, but remembered that I had forgotten my coffee, so turned back to pick it up, hoping that they hadn’t thrown it out.  I left without paying or giving them my medicare details.

At somebody’s holiday mansion on the coast, just metres from the surf. It has a wall like a castle, and I am scaling it. I can see in the neighbour’s similarly walled property that they have a pool down right next to the sea. I am a hundred feet up, looking down upon it. The neighbour’s house is higher up on the block, a long way from the pool, a similar height that I am above it, and I wonder how they would even use the pool because it is such a long way from the house. Then I see that they have a second pool, higher, closer to the house.  I get to the top of the wall and look over the top into my ‘target’ house and see their is also a pool area up here. I am not an intruder, these people are expecting me I put my head over the top of the wall and say ‘hi’, but I can’t climb over it. I ask for help. there is a young man there with the person that I am meant to see, I do not know him, he runs and just jumps over the wall, falling 100 feet, i think that he must not be familiar with the house, he didn’t know it was this high up, so I think he must be a gay lover of the person I have come to see. I wait to see if I can hear a splash, in case he jumped into the neighbour’s pool, but I don’t hear one. I also don’t hear a scream. A different scene: a friend who in real life died 30 years ago is in the dream dead and being carried on an open platform on people’s shoulders. She is surrounded by flowers. A good friend of hers is sitting on her chest, grieving. I have a plate of food but I do not feel like eating. There are masses of mashed potato on top, and it makes me feel quite nauseous.

Accidentally bumping into colleagues from university; I am dragging around behind me a very long and heavy motorbike chain. I am ashamed, I don't feel that I belong with my colleagues on account of taking so long to complete my PhD. I am searching for my office in university buildings/colleges/library. i think it is the fifth floor, but I get there and cannot recognize any of the rooms. I see through the windows that a flash flood is happening, and water outside has risen up above the height of the building. People start screaming, it is an end-of-the-world scenario. A phone call happens, I am reassured that the flooding is a system-generated response that has been falsely triggered.

I have a 727 jet airliner that I have parked outside a 24 hour greasy spoon takeaway in Brisbane that i used to frequent after nights out. I ask the shop attendant if it is ok to park it there and he looks out the window at the plane and says that he doesn't have any fuel for it, it takes a special type of diesel. I ask if it is ok if I come back at 3.30 because that is the time of my flight, and I ask how I get the plane to the airport, will a captain from the airport come up and pick it up and drive it down there for me? i have just bought something and have $350 change in my hand. The shop attendant sees someone out the window, I hear a noise, there is something dangerous happening out there. He reaches beneath the counter and pulls out a gun, as if he was expecting it and it happens all the time (it is a late night place frequented by drug users). I panic because I am holding all this money in my hands. Nick Cave is playing "into my arms", I am no longer in the shop, I cannot see where he is, but just him unaccompanied at the piano.... Later: I am waiting for a bus to go to Brisbane. I am with a couple of other people, I cannot see them, but I think it is my partner and her son. We don't have tickets, but will buy them on the bus. There is a feeling of us fleeing, like refugees. Somebody in a van pulls up, towing a trailer/caravan. I think it is the bus at first. I ask him if we can get in the van but he says there is room in the front seat and it will cost $30 each. I suddenly feel unsafe, realising that he is not actually the bus driver, and I don't want to go hitchhiking with my companions.. We decide to wait for the actual bus. We are playing cards on a top bunk when the proper bus arrives hours later. I panic because we are not ready, I tell everyone to get their stuff together and run for the bus, but they stare at me blankly and are slow to respond. I get frustrated. I see the bus pull away because there are no people waiting for it. Later: I am in a car, my partner driving. We are in Brisbane, going down a steep hill, the street turns sharply up between some houses and my partner is driving too fast, she does not see the turn. I shout at her to stop at the bottom of the hill. She stops just before crashing into a house. I ask her if she minds if I drive, because conditions are bad and I don't feel safe. Later: There is something about boarding houses, again in Brisbane. I am in the boarding house.

I am at the house of someone I knew as a teenager who had been to prison for minor drug offences. He was the older brother of a friend and he was kind to us and I liked him. I had a sore on the heel of my hand, I pricked it or squeezed it and masses of solid pus started coming out, and then bubbling and swelling under the skin. It was like a geyser. Later in the dream, the house turned into his mother’s house, who had also been an influence when I was younger, as a political activist and feminist. There were several women there, most of them older, lower socioeconomic status, some first nation. There was a teenage boy there who had done something wrong, it was something serious, but later it seemed to be that he had called a woman fat, or an elephant. i was trying to talk to him about him, to correct him, but everyone kept laughing, as though it were all a big joke, many of them were overweight themselves. I started getting angry at them. The issue turned into something involving another man, who was there as well. It involved calling someone, maybe this person, a ‘bastard’. Everyone was laughing at me, they said ‘that’s impossible, because this man is his father’. I was embarrassed for not knowing, but still angry because they were missing the point. The man was a boy from my year seven class who had been one of the ‘tough’ boys, whom I had half-admired for his easy manner but who I had also felt superior to. I had an envelope with some drugs in it. They had meant to be exchanged for some other drugs, but had been forgotten. a motorbike was involved. I was in a toilet of a public place with garish patterned carpet that covered floor and walls. The keys had been left in the door. i went into one cubicle and the keys were in the door here also. i thought that maybe someone would come back for the keys, so went out and went to the other cubicle instead. The carpet was different in here.

Meeting a friend, a musician who has worked as a radio announcer, on a rooftop of an unfinished building, there are no roofing tiles, and we sit on bare rafters. I ask him why I always meet him on rooftops,but think to myself that it makes sense because he works in radio and it has something to do with ariels and broadcasting. He asks me a question but I cannot hear it and ask him to repeat it four or five times. I am embarrassed about sounding old and deaf. I tell him that I have lost my job recently and there is something about which National Employment Award the job is, and I/he says it should have been a four rather than a three with implication that my experience is undervalued. I go directly from the rooftop to backstage theatre corridors, still elevated, looking down into a courtyard. Corridors are empty (so is the courtyard). I think how much I like backstage areas, their hiddenness, that they hide the inner working of public productions. I think of a recurring dream that I have previously had of discovering a big empy room in my house that I never previously knew was there, and I think that these empty rooms are part of this backstage network of small rooms and corridors. These rooms are old, made of stone, there are doorways but no doors, and there is no glass in the windows. I think it is somewhere in Italy. I think it is such a shame that there are all of these empty rooms when the housing situation is so bad in the city and so many people can’t afford a room. I think I could/should squat here. There is one room with a stove and an old wooden chair and a window looking out over the courtyard. I see a room with many lit candles,I go to it and there is a dead body lying on a table/slab. There is something about a death shroud that becomes an emergency one-carrier stretcher that can be used to drag people away from danger. I am dragging the dead body because I have to prepare it for burial. The body in the shroud is sitting in lotus position. There is somebody else there with me, and their task is to cut the toenails of the dead person.

There was a young boy who had been teasing another boy about being an 'alien'. Then this boy in turn was teased for something and became upset.I was angry with him and took him aside and told him he shouldn't have teased the first boy.

I was with my father on his property by a remote dirt road. He was concerned as to why two vehicles drove past and we hopped into his vehicle and drove a couple of metres to the end of the drive to see where they went. He was relieved to see they had only parked down the road to camp for the night. One of the vehicles was either a campervan or towing a small caravan.  I was amused the he both use his vehicle to do this and be concerned anyone was in the area.
I was in a room and a couple of women who didn't like me were outside my door, trying to break in to get to me. They had syringes and tried to inject me in the neck

I was in my bedroom at my father's home and my sister was in her bedroom next to mine. For some reason a cousin of mine was visiting and wanted to stay over. He then wanted to stay in my bed and after some manipulation I allowed it. I was concerned my sister would find out. I allowed him to try intercourse. Then he was enamored of me. Then the dream changed and my sister was no longer living there. I saw the cousin in the morning and wondered if there would be a repeat of the night before.

I was wearing an evening dress and was with a girlfriend I haven't seen in 20 years. We were in the ladies bathroom and I was also wearing a warm fleece someone from work had lent me because it was so cold. I removed this before leaving the bathroom. Later on, I realised I'd forgotten to bring this with me so retraced my steps to retrieve it. I couldn't see it anywhere.

I was at my father's former home and went into his bedroom and found it really stuffy despite the window being open. I went to close it as I was about the leave the house and realised my father was asleep in the bed and I had disturbed him. This somehow changed to being an office and I was clearing out items from the out tray on a Friday evening before leaving for the day. I saw there were changes to letters with hand written crossings out and additional notes. I noticed that the signature needed updating as a different staff member was temporarily acting in the role while the substantive was away. I spoke to a lady from work about items that needed completion as I was doing it on her behalf while she had a day off. She said not to worry about things and she would do them when she returned. While talking to her I collated some receipts of mine that related to her work and they started to dissolve when they were placed on my home bathroom sink. They were no longer required so I placed them all in the basin with water and swirled them around to complete the process. I returned to the office to see what else was outstanding and Bob Hawke was there although I recognised him as a former boss. He and I went through some changes together and then he apologised for his lack of concentration, saying he had been with someone the night before who drank more than him and he had a hangover. I thought there must have been a lot of drinking to outpace him but didn't say anything. I took the letters and memos with me. I started looking for the documents on a database on my computer as well as my mobile phone so I could correct and reprint them. I saw I had composed some of them

I was working with someone on an art project that was somehow linked to business. We had to submit three slightly different pieces and hoped to gain funding. I was liaising with people from when I worked at a university, an accountant firm I worked for and my current role all mixed up. We were at an enclosed football stadium stand at the bottom and the computer in my office was at the top.  We had printed the details of the project on to three pieces of toast. Each piece was slightly different by applying different flavours of jam.  I had prepared these by visiting my grandmother in her home in the lounge room. She wasn't exactly sure what I was doing and why and was concerned that the butter and bread was being left out. She was trying to put them away before I had finished with them.  I needed some further details for one piece from a customer file and it was quicker to ring my former office than go back up to my current one at the top of the football stand. I called up the office and pretended to be a client to obtain the information. I was surprised they couldn't detect it was me and they politely obliged, providing the details we needed.  The art piece seminar and judging was already underway and we still had to submit our pieces. I wanted to improve our chances by including the new information and preparing new toast and jam. I spoke to my colleague for her input - do we have time for me to do this? What did she want me to do? She didn't respond and was anxious about the seminar. It was at the bottom of the football stand, which now had a room full of seated people in theatre style. You could hear someone giving a talk.  I went to a kitchen bench at the bottom of the football stand and started to prepare toast. My colleague approached and was seemingly going to submit the untoasted pieces we had prepared earlier.   I saw another colleague from yet another place I used to work at and asked for his input. He was on the judging panel. He responded in a slow drawl like he had an acquired brain injury. I wasn't sure if he was drunk and wondered what had happened to him.  In trying to recreate the pieces, it looked at our bottles of jam and saw one was missing. However, the lids had been put on the wrong jars. There was a chance there was enough of the correct jam in one of the lids to complete our submission.  I left it up to my colleague as to what she preferred to do.

I was on a tour bus. The tour leader had a domineering personality. I think my sister and nephew were there. The dream then changed and a tooth crown I have had come loose so I could pull it out. I went to the reception of a dentist to try and make an appointment. I was frustrated that it had been some time and this dentist had still not fixed my tooth and they were indifferent about it. There are a lot of people being served in two different queues at reception. One seems to be for initial inquiries, the other for arrivals for set appointments. I go to the initial inquiry queue. I don't seem to be able to make my predicament appreciated and actually receive treatment, even though I may get to see a dentist in his office.

I was preparing to go camping with my family. We had a couple of vehicles and I was asked to drive a 4WD campervan/caravan.  A friend of mine somehow ended up at my father's house and we invited him along.  The vehicles were already packed with supplies. I had only to pack my own bag. It was taking me ages to do this and I wasn't really focussed. I looked at my drawers and decided there was little point taking my snorkelling gear as it was too cold and I rarely used it whenever I'd taken it before.   It was getting late and I had still to complete my packing. My friend was already in bed in the same room I was doing the packing. I grabbed a first aid kit, underwear and socks. I was longing to be in bed with my friend instead. We were both exhausted and had to get up early in the morning.  I started bleeding period-like and went to the bathroom to clean up. My friend came in to see if I was OK.  I finally went to bed, hoping my friend would snuggle up to me. He didn't.  The dream then changed.  We were in a few tents although it was really a house with several rooms made from tent material. It may have been at my father's former home.  I could see in the distance there was a rampaging moose on fire. He was heading our way and I was trying to alert the others of imminent danger. I can't recall if I was successful.  The dream then changed again.  We were being pursued by authorities for a breach of some kind. My friend was talking to them and then gave them the slip.  My sister and I were trying to get away as well as catch up with my friend. There was a feeling that he had been in trouble with authorities before and was a bit of a smart Aleck. My sister and I hopped over several people's backyards like hop scotch and ended up near a long line of high power lines. It was drizzling.  We looked to the right along the power lines to see if we could see my friend. We couldn't. We were trying to decide whether or not to swing from these to hasten our escape.

I was travelling by bus with a group of people and we stopped at a tourism spot. I was by myself and watched others looking through craft shops and decided to go the bathroom before we recommenced our journey. It then changed that we had been camping there as I emerged from my tent to walk to the bathroom. I passed someone from the bus on the way to the bathroom, possibly someone I know from choir. When I came out of the toilet block I could see people walking back to the bus and followed them as I wasn't entirely sure of the route back to the bus and where it was parked. I climbed an embankment and when I reached the top I couldn't see the people to follow any longer and was unsure which way to go. Rather than get lost going back down, I decided to continue to the bitumen road but couldn't see the bus. I assumed the bus had left without me as I had been angrily warned it would not wait, like I had kept it waiting previously. I was then in the back seat of an older car. There was a couple in the front and I had hitchhiked a ride with them, unsure where they were going. The man was driving. His female partner a passenger. They told me they were going to Newstead and they would take me as far as there. I was heading to Launceston where I worked. I didn't have any contact details on me and wanted to let my work know where I was. I asked the people in the car what the number of the tour company was and they recited the number but every time I tried to put the numbers in I did it incorrectly. I tried to call my sister so she could pass on a message but the same thing happened; I couldn't complete the sequence correctly. The same when I tried to leave a message on my father's answering machine. I had my large backpack in the back seat with me and I kept checking it to make sure my belongings were inside. Next thing all was quiet and I wasn't sure if we had stopped and I had been asleep.The couple had gone and the windows were foggy. I then recalled the driver saying there had been a change of plan, they were letting me out here. I didn't know where I was. It seems the car had been stolen. A group of criminals were looking for the couple and were approaching the unfogged car to search for money the couple had stolen from them. I was concerned they would think I was involved and grab me but I managed to slipped out one door as they opened another and started to look inside. I had the money. It was in foreign currency. I found an abandoned house. I had a shotgun for protection and drew curtains so I could remain undetected although they didn't completely close or stop people seeing inside. Outside a group of people drove along with a dog and guns, firing into the bush. The leader was a woman. I was concerned I would be found. I wasn't sure if they knew I was there somewhere and were searching. They were annoyed as there was a bus full of hippies there, also with guns. A confrontation took place and the brightly coloured bus was pushed over with many hippies still inside. A couple of people still had their thonged feet hanging outside the side of the bus. Others had their arms hanging outside where windows would normally be. I was relieved the group in the car weren't looking for me after all. At some point, someone approached the house where I was and came inside. It was the owner. He looked a little like a friend of mine who is a little hippyish. At times I was him, others I wasn't. We needed to leave because of impending danger. Time passed and I had been trying to make my way to Launceston. I was in a different house and place now. Still with the hippy guy. Now I was an observer. The hippy guy was talking to someone and went to his house. When he came inside, he was talking to someone who wasn't there. It was a ghost he could see as a version of himself, unshaven and younger. When they came to a mirror, the hippy couldn't see the person in the reflection. However, the ghost could see the image of themselves at the time of their death. The ghost was shocked to see it was the leader of the criminal gang. He was trying to find out who killed him so he could take retribution. . The hippy came in again, like he was seeing himself repeat a sequence from the past so he was there in 3 different time periods. The second time the ghost looked in the mirror, it was a different ghost who was also shocked at the reveal of who he was. Next thing we were in a room full of people. The criminal ghost was there chatting to people pleasantly. He seemed to be more kind and genuine in his interaction but still secretly trying to find out who killed him. It was the fault of the hippy guy, yet he hadn't done it. Once again, the hippy guy was sometimes himself, sometimes me. Next thing, the atmosphere changed and we were all prevented from leaving. We were handcuffed/hands tied behind our back and were about to be interrogated. The hippy guy gave a woman there a knowing nod and he created a distraction of smoke, explosion and light like a firework so he could quickly unlock the door to escape. He threw his bag and went after it. But the woman was slow to react and they were caught. Next thing I know there was a celebration of sorts as a couple of people from my work were in the room. They had driven down from Launceston to retrieve me. I was to go home to Hobart with them. I was relieved to see them. I was in a chair leaning on someone from work. I'd fallen asleep. They rose when I awoke and moved elsewhere. They were uncomfortable that I sweated in my sleep on them. People from work were around, chatting and catching up. They assured me I had a reserved spaced on the trip back to Hobart. Before we left, I assisted with throwing out items into a skip. Some of it was film showing evidence of the murder. A policeman was there combing the debris but didn't see it. There was also some jewellery in a box that was found. I spoke to the person who found it and said I knew the person whom that was stolen from, a family friend. He offered to give it to me back but wanted to keep a ring and some other item for himself. I agreed and said the owner would be pleased to have it back. I threw some items out into a boat that was next to the skip. People from work, who use the boat, were geared up and I realised they weren't milling about with the clean up but getting ready for field work. Despite this, I kept throwing obsolete items in there so they would be mixed up with workable ones. I made some cheeky comment to one of the guys there. It was time to depart so I looked for my seat on the coach which looked like business class aircraft cabin. My things weren't there but others already seated handed them to me.

I was about to go on an overseas holiday and a friend of mine gave me a large spray bottle with alcohol and lemonade or similar in it. She said it would be useful for both a drink and sanitiser against COVID-19.  Next thing I was on a public bus with two different friends I lived in London with. I showed them the bottle and they sampled it. One I sprayed directly into the mouth, the other on her hand. I said it was strong as I immediately felt warmer as the contents slid down my throat to my stomach. They weren't travelling with me.  I led a group of people I knew to a dorm of sorts which didn't have beds, just carpeted space. As we were the first, we had the choice of where we wanted to set up our things before others arrived. There were workshops/activities scheduled, the reason we had chosen to come here. Despite being early, out the window we could see that the activities had already started. We hadn't yet decided which ones to go to and we were toying with exploring outside instead. It was Singapore and the temperature was pleasant. I recalled to a couple of my friends that I had been to Singapore before but didn't venture outside as I had decided to sleep in between flights. We had a 12 hr stopover between Australia and New Dehli. My friends had been to Singapore before but were keen to revisit some places. They weren't oppressed by the heat like I had been.  We were in no rush. Some of us read. We lounged about on our sleeping bags on the floor.  The room now seemed to be part of my father's former house.  I was expecting others to join us and warned the others that there may be others coming that were a little, I can't recall exactly what, but they were OK. I opened the door to look outside but there was no one there. I thought I'd leave the porch light on as my father wasn't yet home despite it being late. Then my sister said he was in his bedroom as he wasn't well. He had been there the whole time and I hadn't realised. I was sorry to hear he was sick and was relieved we hadn't woken him. Although he was awake now from me fiddling with the door and light. A friend of my father's I didn't like was due to arrive.  The room switched back to the dorm as before, this time with a deadlocked door. There was an impatient bang on the door at 8am as others arrived, a couple of whom were known to me. This implied that we had been in the dorm overnight. They commenced filling the remaining spaces. The room was open plan with lots of little alcoves like the doors/walls of a house had been removed. These people were not one group but several so they dispersed in different directions.  Through the curtained window, I could see a silhouette. It knocked. I pushed back the curtain and a man of about 30 beckoned me to open the sliding window. He was fairly attractive. I did so and he wanted to know if he could come in. He was looking for someone. Before I could answer his question, he had started to climb inside and next thing was standing next to the window on the inside. I was annoyed and said he could go back out the way he came in. He obliged.   I decided to explore the premises. I think I was looking for someone, possibly the person the man mentioned. I found myself in a room of writhing, interconnected naked bodies. They were silently exploring sensuality without kissing. I stepped over bodies and a friend of mine walked past and wondered if I would like to join? I said no, it wasn't my scene and left her to it. She wasn't part of the writhing mass and was fully clothed but about to partake.  I recalled the scene to someone upon returning to my group and likened it to the statues in a sculpture park in Oslo.  The scene changed again and I was eating a meal with others, including my sister and 12 year old nephew, at a table in a kitchen, presumably at the dorm. There was some behaviour that had incensed my nephew who is a born again Christian. He angrily denounced the behaviour, thanking the host for the meal they had prepared for him and stormed off. I followed him, impressed that despite the difference in attitude, he could still be respectful and thankful.  We were walking along a road to my father's former home, which was really a plank of wood so when we came to the end, it swiveled over so we could walk along the other side. There were items on it I can't recall.

I was with someone in a woman's home. The woman had a strong, domineering personality and we were trying to conceal our true intentions in her home. We were going through new clothing in the cupboards. She was there. At times she would go off searching and find items she thought appropriate to give to us. This was generous of her although the atmosphere was tense as we thought we would soon be rumbled. We discovered two human fetuses and decided to rear them by removing them from where we found them. I kept one warm by putting it under the top of my track pants. At one point we had a Stanley knife to protect ourselves from the woman. She nearly detected it once but we managed to hide it among the clothes and retrieve it later. I cut myself in the process. It then changed and I was in KMart with my sister. She was trying to find clothing or something. We were also trying to restore our damaged relationship. I lost my sister in the maze of clothing and other shelves of goods. I heard a commotion of my sister being mocked and went to see what was happening. She was being followed and taunted by a group of former peers, all women, as she tried to leave them. It had something to do with the fetus. This changed to a corridor of what looked like an airport terminal. There was an unsavoury looking man pursuing my sister, also taunting her. I approached him as a distraction, saying I had heard that another woman was interested in him. He stopped, suspicious. He asked how to spell this person's name, implying it was mine. He then declared he wasn't interested. By this time, my sister had disappeared and there was no danger to her or the fetus. This then changed to a fellow from work who knew about the fetuses and clothing. We were on a bushwalking trail with others travelling single file. He was way behind me. I asked him not to say anything some time ago but he had changed his mind. He was telling others on the trail and it was only a matter of time before it got back to the woman up the front of the trail. He tried to race ahead of me to tell others. He wanted to reveal the truth to protect members of his team. This changed again and another man, some sort of senior management figure, was looking for the fellow from work. He opened the door to a staff/class room, interrupting the lesson and asking about the fetuses. The fellow from work and his partner quickly tried to diffuse the situation and hurried him out of the room. I found my sister in a room and wondered how she was going with the fetus. Someone else there was looking for them. I can't remember if this was sinister or not. It appeared she had neglected the fetus and it had dried out a little. She attended to it and I gave her the fetus I had so they were reunited again. My nephew was there, doing homework on computer. Then the dream changed to one of imminent disaster in the form of an industrial accident. The fellow from work worded up his team in one work place, to move to another. The second place caught on fire, burning to the ground. The fellow from work escaped the blaze but it appeared to the authorities he had died in the fire. Evidence of his signature of approval of an unethical project was destroyed so that the approval lay in the remains but who approved it was burned away.

I was in a dress shop and saw a beautiful gold threaded ethnic dress hanging on the wall. It was like an Indian tunic with long sleeves, fawn/apricot/black colouring, above collarbone neckline with narrow split, snug fit, material belt down past the knees. I wondered if I would be able to afford it and tried it on. I wasn't sure if the colour suited my complexion. Someone came along and suggested I try something else and went away to find me a garment. I was disappointed and looked in full length mirror to see for myself. The midriff tie looked a bit awkward and had large black patches on it I hadn't noticed before. I wasn't sure.

I was in my father's former kitchen with my sister. I was preparing a meal for my nephew which had taken me a considerable amount of time to do. It comprised of crunchy burgers and salad. My sister wanted to use the cookware I was using and couldn't wait for me to finish. I was looking for the burgers and found them in a steamer all mushy. I went absolutely off my head. I can't recall exactly what I said but it was full of vitriol. I looked for my nephew to tell him his meal was ready but couldn't find him anywhere. I was concerned my outburst was inappropriate and he didn't want to be around me. I eventually found my sister and rather than being upset, she was concerned. This was an unusual response from her. I questioned my behaviour.

I had an appointment with my gynae in a hospital to discuss some break through bleeding. I explained it only occurred when I took specific meds and stopped when I wasn't using them.  She was gowned up with a mask. She said the meds had nothing to do with it and further investigation was warranted. She then walked away.  I was frustrated, angry and sad at this response.  I was with my sister. We tried to follow her but lost her in the maze of hospital rooms.

I was living in a home with my sister in the next room, much like when were children. I was annoyed at my sister as she had either the TV or stereo on very loud so I couldn't hear my own stereo. She wasn't in the room itself. She was also annoyed at me. She clambered over my double bed in my room to switch off my stereo when I wasn't there despite it being quite low, saying it was disturbing her. She was very angry.

Repetitive dreams of buildings becoming rocks, those rocks becoming sand at the edge of the sea. Each manifestation was circling, as it did so becoming more abstract till it was another substance. Then the process began again.

A flower. Small. Eye level. Behind, the elegant Californian bungalow in Park St with silvered straight hardwood fence. The shimmering silver of weathered hardwood and the line of the structure disappearing to the near distance. I am on the road facing a second hand shop. Using both hands I lift up hard thick plastic. It is partially embedded in the road. The cheap tough sort that is used on our communal garden, only designed for heavier industry, thickness of a surfboard. It has little flexibility. Once I have ripped the front end from the ground attachment to eye level, I can’t force its mass any further. I have to make a decision as it has its own mass that will behave according to whether I hold it, let it go, or figure out how to force it further.
Girl sitting at the window waiting. She is allowed to go free with her friends. However this means she is likely to shorten her schooling and loose her potential by missing higher education.

I was being productive in some way as if researching, maybe to do with food and feeling rested in my involvement. It was a search of some sort. It was involving and clear. Then I was with Dad, Ken, Alison and others. We were all talking with humour and interest. Someone joked along the lines that I would require a partner with high food standards. Ken offered that he can cook a bit. I was on the ground on my back laughing uncontrollably with joy. I didn’t feel separate from others with my laughter, even though it was such a bodily experience. The others carried on and I felt included in the group. Dad stood with his hands in his pockets and smiled in a genial way in my direction and at the others. I was crossing some paddocks with Alison. They had rounded rises and again the grass tending towards brown, a bit tangled here and there. The environment had a slight abandoned or forgotten quality. Outdoors, open and unattended, somewhere kids might find interesting, but not traversed frequently by adults. Alison had a purpose, I knew what it was In her interested and anxiety-free way she pondered and kept moving and talked leaving lots of silences. I didn’t fill the spaces, I felt like I was learning from her, or she was a guide of sorts or simply it was more her mission than mine. Nor was I being silent. This felt natural, perhaps as it would have in my late teens when there was a more apparent age difference or because I was searching the environment and talking was secondary. I wondered if Alison would like some tuber roses I knew she would have to take the train back to Sale before long. Then it occurred to me that I could buy them and surprise her with them. I would have to find a florist. I found a florist who reminded me of part of the Brunswick St cool scene in the 80s. She seemed too analytical to be selling flowers. I asked if the flowers would last. She said they probably wouldn’t make the journey. I was keen to give them to Alison and wanted to ignore her advice

Reading some lines of Shakespeare I have written by hand. Feel like I have the characters name wrong. Or that it is not all consistent within the one play. I have remembered about six lines and I like the sound of them.   On the same piece of paper are some chords to a favourite song. Below that the words of the song I have hand written. I look at the chords, wondering who wrote them for me, because I wouldn’t know them myself. It is only one line of chords and as I look at them I very slowly realise they are not chords, but some other symbols, like Chinese characters. It takes me a while to realise they aren’t that either, but I can’t place them. They are complex with too many lines to be chords or alphabet characters. They look familiar though, like a franking stamp but finer.   It is late and I should be asleep. I am in bed with my brother Jim. I can hear someone in other rooms or outside beyond. The light is on. I also want whoever is out there, maybe Harry (younger brother), to think we are asleep and I get out of bed to switch out the light. I write, or the writing is on the wall ‘switch out the light’. I press my hand like a cursor after light and wonder why the light isn’t responding then realise you switch it off by pressing the light switch. I think the switch is white but it is an older one like the baker light switches with an obvious up down quality.  In the dark I hop back into bed and my foot lands on Jim’s body. How has this happened? Have I returned to the wrong side of the bed? Or perhaps he has rolled into the vacant space while I attended to the light.

I was sitting at a rectangular dining table opposite a woman. The circumstance had a mixture of formality and the informality of a communal setting like a school camp or spiritual retreat. The woman wore a white scarf. It was tied with a simple large bow at the neck. It was the type children wore as embellishment in the early 20th century and it became her. I don’t remember our conversation, yet I was focused on her and felt a general companionship towards her.  A servant in Victorian livery entered and with professional flourish yet ineptly ripped the scarf from her neck, tightening it as he did so. I could see it unfolding and I cried out to the servant to stop, it is not a serviette. I felt for the woman, her possible embarrassment that her dress was taken as a napkin, and she didn’t seem to be able to defend herself and was clutching her neck in alarm. So I was the person taking action, and I mainly directed myself to her, checking she was okay and recovering her scarf.   The woman settled back and attended to composing herself. Now I was aware of the man beside me and I leaned into him. The more I leaned the better I felt to just feel warmth and someone next to me. He offered no resistance and we simply sat closely side by side in quiet connection. We continued to talk gently with a companionable quality between three of us. I didn’t know the man, or the woman, although I felt connected to the woman simply by the concern I had felt for her. I couldn't detect much of her attitude to me. I felt close to him simply by my own desire to be next to him. Although I couldn't read his feelings either. It was dawning on me, that the two of them were a couple. I wondered if I should extricate myself from him.  He was up preparing the next meal at the stove. I noticed him taking two large fresh carrots and some broccoli from my supplies to add to his chicken and assortment of food. I nodded it was okay and offered to contribute more. I looked for grains and only found a third of a packet of Sunwhite short grain rice with a rubber band around it. I seemed to be pulling it out of some occasionally used camping supplies at the bottom of a small tin storage box and felt embarrassed at such a dismal offering. The makeshift quality of our separate food supplies also struck me. Mine were scattered between different bench tops. Yet he was happily cooking appealing fresh food. I made excuses for the rice, saying I only use it for sushi. He declined the offer casually saying there was plenty of food.   I walked out to look at the kitchen garden. I was going down narrow paths in the underbrush. Gaye and others were there. I felt like getting some bearings. I found an old leather wallet with a few coins in it. Now I was clambering in a sinking sand pit and I put the wallet on a wooden structure, wondering whether to leave it there or hand it in. I continued back to the house taking the wallet.   A young boy sidled up to me saying he could hear coins. I put him off and decided to hand it in rather than give it to him.

Dad and I pulled over in a Hobart street. We were both out of the 1940s car and I found Trace. We swiftly got back in the car, dad and Trace in the back. I hopped into front passenger seat being dishevelled from the urgency of finding T. We had to get Trace to airport. I am not sure if that included me. Being in an urgent hurry I started driving from the front passenger seat then realised how difficult it was to change position. Due to speed and awkwardness I missed empty street spaces to pull in and swap seats. Before I knew it I had to turn a wide arc left into Davey St to take me to airport In mid turn I decided that I must pull over and get into driver seat and I swerved straight ahead to an inclined ramp, taking me up adjacent to the docks. Approaching the ramp, and due to speed, now on the left, I was taken with an extraordinary sight. Two narrow Antarctic ships at the front edge of the docks. There was nowhere safe to pull in and look at them. They were both stationary and yet on a 45 degree lean as if caught in a storm at sea, with high waves between them. There were also sunset colours in slivers, and the cool blue of ice from whence they had come in their immediate vicinity. However this stunning visual that appeared active without any pose of danger was singular to these two ships alone. Apart from wanting to investigate myself, I was keenly aware of a missed opportunity for dad with his deep interest in physics and meteorology. I continued driving the car up and around another broad sweep into a street where I could pull in to the kerb. I had to go to the toilet and raced into a department store. I thought I knew where I was going, but got caught in a terrible web of different departments and staircases. At one stage I was dodging statues of almost life-size elephants in the theatre auditorium. I finally arrived at the very personal toilets, like the ladies at Georges. Not as gracious, but the discreet behaviour had the same feeling whilst the décor was more floral and down a rung or two. It was just about impossible getting back to the car. I didn’t know what street exit I should be heading for inside the department store. None of the stairs down led to anything familiar within the store. I kept going down different staircases and aisles in vain. I found myself in the less public part of the building and found Judy (Trace’s best friend at school) and others. Now Judy wanted my phone number. It was an impossible procedure trying to enter it on an outdated phone, plus I was sure quite unnecessary. By now I realised I had left my bag with all my rent money in the ladies, and there was still the airport to get to. I finally located the personal attendant in the ladies. She immediately presented me with another bag initially raising my hopes. It was quite eye catching in its own way, tasteful abstract floral with a structural form from another decade. I was struck by the coincidence of two handbags being left behind and disappointed at the thought of the money lost besides rent. Back on the street I looked for the car and dad and Trace. The streets seemed to give no clues as if scenery in a gangster movie I was surveying without luck.

A particular friend was being checked by authorities to see if she had complied with covid rules. I knew she had and it was just a case of proving it. Furthermore, it was generally well known so even more apparently, but not obviously provable. What should be easy wasn’t and so there was a lagging feeling of incompletion. This magnified and lacked boundaries when it was broadened to more people. Although they were known, and again appeared achievable, it turned into a repetitive sense of working on something and not getting anywhere. This was accompanied with a disturbing familiarity of something apparently achievable becoming a troubling inescapable mounting mass of the unattended as if under a microscope I couldn’t pull my eye away from. This was the uppermost feeling and the authorities were never visible or present and I woke up. Someone was being blamed unfairly. Feeling panicked I texted a message requesting an overnight stay at Chris and Gina’s as I walked along. The second I pressed send I regretted doing so. I wondered if the wording I used was sufficiently obscure to not be taken as a request. I hurried along, feeling a bit like I was in a western film set, all being empty. It was if a teacher of good standing who had given us a lot was being blamed, was it Assunta? I needed a place to stay for the night, or to pass time so I wouldn’t be noticed. I saw an unexpected friendly person from the past. She offered help immediately without fuss. We walked over to some sauna bathing cubicles. As we walked along the line they were all occupied. One just being vacated raised hopes. A young man who looked trustworthy and relaxed claimed next in line. It struck me that he was prone with his old clean towel on top of what looked like a coffin rather than a place of rejuvenation. I continued on searching for a solution to the wrongly blamed teacher, culminating in something now hazy.
There was a ball. I just remember sitting at a long table with my friends. The boys on the table were from my primary school and not actual partners.
My dream was romantic in nature but also a bit wild as I had been drinking alcohol in my dream.

My mum’s neighbour had a big modern house renovation so we were taken around on a tour of it. My parents were a bit critical of it and comparing it to what their future renovation will be like. But it was a polite enough experience.

My partner and I went for a road trip about an hour out of Melbourne. We pull over in the middle of nowhere as it seems really beautiful and we go for a walk. It’s a warm summer day and we can smell the aroma from grass and eucalypts. We walk over a small hill and the eucalypts are so nice with gum nuts and swaying in the gentle breeze. We decide to lie down on the grass beneath the trees on this small hill in the shade. It’s very comfortable and we feel relaxed. Then we hear some noise nearby and realise there are some young girls playing in a swimming pool nearby. We realise we must be on someone’s property. The girls get out of the pool and notice us. They are chatting to each other and we get up to leave casually. One of the girls realises we must have just been relaxing and says we will have to have a swim next time. I say thank you, that’s very kind. We make our way back to the car. We notice their Dad too who must have been wondering what we were doing on his farm. We walk back over some mounds until we return to the car. It’s a shame we have to leave so soon as we were hoping to take a nap but it was nice whilst it lasted.

I was at my parents house. There was a severe bush fire in the news and coming in our direction potentially. We just had to watch and wait overnight. The electricity was out so we kept an eye out on our app. My uncle and cousin came to our house too. My Dad has lavender in his hair? We played cards to pass the time. The bushfire never came

I was trying on my wedding dress. There was the dressmaker who has made adjustments to my dress and two female housemates that lived with them. One of them was assisting me. My fiancé accompanied me but waited in another room. I stripped down but was struggling to get my socks off. I kept losing my balance so needed help staying upright. I tried to get the dress on but was still finding it difficult to stand up. I kept tripping over the dress and was worried I’d rip the delicate lace. I felt very clumsy and was concerned that I’d be like this on my wedding day. I was trying to get up to look at myself in a mirror. I couldn’t stand up long enough to get a good look at it. Most of it looked good but there was aiming i could see that was way too small so I wanted to speak to the dressmaker about that. It’s important to note that the dress I saw in my dream is not the actual real life dress thatI have purchased but waiting to try on until lockdown finishes so I can go to my parents to try on since we had it delivered there. The housemates had just been listening to the news that coronavirus lockdown restrictions were going to be extended and the way out over the next few months was going to be worse than expected. This would really jeopardise the wedding. I was anxious but expecting that disappointing news. I kept trying to look at the dress but still couldn’t stop tripping over. Then my fiancé nearly saw me in my dress from the doorway which I didn’t really want for him to see me in my dress as it’s bad luck. I felt slightly let down that they hadn’t closed the curtains to the room and prevented him from seeing the dress. But I was also a bit ambivalent because I was thinking there might not even be a wedding in January. I felt despondent to the whole situation. I also didn’t really like the vibe of the dressmaker and the housemates as they were too relaxed and not focused on my needs.

I was with my best friend and another person unknown except he had dark skin in my best friend's home, except his home wasn't any place I know. All I know it was on the beach or by the seaside. We were just listening to music. I didn't feel anything much, except that the unknown friend was like an intrusion, not unwelcome as such, just not really supposed to be there.

I was at a community radio station I used to work at 30 years ago. I was doing an on air shift but it was at a makeshift panel on the floor instead of in the studio. There were some people around but I only recognized G. and B. I was my real age and so was G. I remember noticing he'd aged well. I was anxious because nothing seemed to work right and I was constantly panicking because I didn't have the next song queued up in time. I couldn't find the aux line on the panel to plug in any inputs etc. But magically the next song always seemed to start up by itself. I couldn't figure out where they were coming from. After the 3rd song I woke up.

I was at primary school except as an adult attending class. But the classroom space was actually like a supermarket with narrow aisles formed by shelves with products or books on them. The task at hand was some kind of coin tossing game. We were put into groups of 4 and I was in a group with my classmates D &G and someone else. The door at the back room was slamming in the wind and I was trying to stop it from doing so but not very successfully. My grade teacher Mrs V teacher told me off for being disruptive by making noise with the door. I told her off sharply in return that it was the wind, not me causing the noise. I remember the sense of being in a very bad mood. Then I was outside with my brothers and my mum was there too. The school was right next door to some top level military facility run by the Iranians. This was somewhat disconcerting. I said to someone if there's ever a war we will be the first ones to be killed. Suddenly a modified jumbo jet doing military training exercises game flying down very close to the ground. As the pilot tried to clear a residential building he missed his mark and crashed right into it. We were shocked. The plane crash to the ground in pieces but the pilot walked away. It was 10 to 4 and we were on a break. I decided it will I was going home even though there were still 10 minutes of class left. My brothers had to hang around till 5 their school day was longer. We were trying to organise it so that we could all go home with Mum together but I didn't want to hang around. I walked to the bus stop with a friend. It was in a residential Street that looked like a war zone filled with rubble and Middle Eastern people. I studied the timetable but there was no bus scheduled for 4pm. You had to ring a number for the bus to come. I had a Bible and was ripping pages out of it for some reason. My friend was worried that the people on the street would be offended.

I was at an unfamiliar house in Footscray and this guy was going to kill me over some drug deal I think. But somehow I managed to take him down temporarily which gave me time to run out and down the street. I was looking for the police station as he had a gun. There was someone else with me. He was starving and just desperately wanted to get something to eat. I made a wrong turn and ran into a cul de sac which gave the bad guy time to catch up. There was a bakery there so I told the hungry guy go to the bakery. He was really thankful that I pointed out the bakery. I couldn't find the station, it just always seemed to be around the next corner. Finally I ran into a grocery store. There were 3 security guards there. The guy chasing me had caught up. I yelled at the guards he's got a gun but they just laughed. But then suddenly they took him seriously and overpowered and shot him dead. I didn't need the police anymore.

A counsellor, it may have been another version of me, phoned me. Whoever was on the other end of the phone began questioning me to see if I was a suicide risk assessment. I explained to them I just wish I had never been born at all.

I was at a festival on a big outdoor oval space. I believe it may have been a writing festival, and I was trying to have some writing workshopped or the like. I saw an old university friend. In the dream, I was suspicious of him, but he seemed to explain away our past as a misunderstanding, and I felt safe with him again. Then there was a fire that was consuming the entire oval. I knew my car was in one of the many car parks, which in this case were interspersed among the tents and festival activities. There was a slope, and on the incline the field was ablaze, I was on the decline, a road next to the oval. I kept trying to run to the car park where I had parked. I was panicked that my car was going to be incinerated. I was distracted by various people and detours, but I was focused on finding my car. I got there and my car was clearly on fire. I got there and my car was OK.

I was in the United States. I was sleeping in very poor accomodation. There were two single beds. On the other bed was an older lady whom I knew as a public defender. I had some business to be here but I was finishing up. There was a feeling of unease. There was an older man somewhere in this hotel or share house that I knew as a bad man, and he was connected to why I was there. It was late at night and the woman told me I was no longer needed and I must go. I thought that I would be able to sleep one more night but she insisted I leave.   I was at a bus depot and I needed a bus to the airport. I knew I had to go home to Australia. Several buses passed me, somtimes it I was too late to hail them and I just watched with frustration as they passed me by with "AIRPORT" written on the front. I saw a bus with "AIRP" or something a little off but I was feeling desperate with a flight to catch so I hailed it and got on. I was with my ex partner. I was trying to win him back in some way. There was some knowledge that this was "the last chance" as once we got back to Australia we would be going our separate ways. There was some knowledge I had made a mistake and I was begging his forgiveness. He flirted with other girls in front of me, whom he knew from the local university. He was cold and cruel to me. I was losing hope.   In the midst of this, I tried to check with the bus driver that this bus was indeed going to the airport,  still conscious of a plane to catch. He explained to me that there was a strike at the airport, the workers had been exposed to an unacceptable level of risk, they were exposed to "Covid droplets" and the entire airport was closed down as they had walked off the job. I was beginning to feel really confused and unsure what to do. I thought perhaps this delay would give me more time to "win back" my ex partner, but I also felt this was a hopless endeavour. We entered a tunnel and I saw all this men who I understood to be the workers at the airport, with their signs. They were dressed in blue and other clothing to suggest they were the baggage handlers or other types of labourers.

I am with my maternal grandmother. We are on a busy street or road. To my horror, she has an accident and rolls onto the road. There is a giant truck. The event happens in slow motion and I struggle between looking and looking away. I hope she won't be run over by this truck, but when I notice her cardigan is caught under the tyres, I know all hope is lost. My grandmother and I are in an ambulance helicopter. It is shaking and rocking constantly. I feel intense fear and I try to keep my grandmother's body still in case she has a head injury. She is completely unconscious/ dead like. I am afraid and question if the pilot is safe. We weave and zig zag through mountain tops. In the helicopter with us there is a politician, I think of him as former Australian Prime Minister John Howard but this man looks nothing like him. I wonder why the politican is accompanying us, I don't believe he does anything without a cynical self serving purpose, but I cannot find a cynical reason for why he is with us here. I think could he care? This is a challenging thought, I despise John Howard. At a point in the helicopter I am also fiddling with three identical Christmas gifts, may be jars, candles or angels?, I am looking through the messages. I am trying to sort by which gifts have religious messages and non-religious as this will determine the best recipient. There is a feeling of rush and hurry and anxiety.

I am a room of a house with my cousin and her new baby. I notice I am not interested in the baby, and this is unlike me. I am not coo-ing or smiling or wanting to hold the baby. I just want to leave the room. There are other people around and I feel distinctively anxious. I want to use the bathroom. I exit the room into a hall and then walk over to the bathroom opposite the room my cousin is in. I go inside and try to lock the door but the lock is not working. I feel desperate as I try to fix it. A strange man (I think it may be my cousin's partner) notices my struggle and intervenes. I feel intensely uncomfortable as he takes over trying to fix the lock. I want him to go away. I struggle to say or do anything, but I know I can't use the toilet unless I can lock the door. I am getting irritated with the man.

I may have been a child. I was with some other children I recognised as childhood friends. We were having a sleep over. I got the other children set up in my room. Meanwhile, I was also attending to my sister. She appeared as a child as well. I followed a written instruction from my parents to administer some liquid laxative to my sister. I was afraid this would lead to fecel smearing but I followed the instruction nonetheless. Later in the middle of the night, I discovered she had smeared feces everywhere and across multiple rooms. I was embarrassed that my friends would find out so I went about cleaning it as quietly and as quickly as I could, but I only seemed to increase the mess. I saw my pet rabbit hopping around and I noticed he was cleaning his paws by licking them. I was afraid he was licking up feces and this would harmful for him but I felt overwhelmed and stressed and like I did not know where to begin. My friends would peep out the bedroom door now and then as well, increasing my stress. I yelled at them to stay in the bedroom. My dad appeared and I was so incredibly relieved. He made jokes about the mess we had found ourselves in, and I felt my stress decreasing, I was so incredibly glad he was there to help me.

I was in a big room organising boxes of groceries into lots for people to use. There seemed to be some people sitting on tiered seating above the boxes. The groceries had something to do with being provisions for the Covid lockdown.

I needed to go to the toilet. Where could I pee? Would it be ok if I just sat astride the cardboard core of a toilet roll? People can see. That’s no good. Now I’m on the bunk bed. I’m on the top bunk. The pee goes on the bunk and down the side onto the carpet. “An” comes in and I try to pretend it didn’t happen. I pour water all over everything to hide the pee. I’m sitting with B (husband) on a metal bench, outdoors, waiting to board a plane.   Our bench is under a tree, looking towards the outside of an the airport terminal, sort of on the tarmac, so we could see the plane.  A flight attendant came up to our waiting area and said, “Your flight is delayed for one hour, two hours... actually, I don’t know when your flight is leaving.” So we sat and sat for a while longer, and then we saw a vehicle drive in with a tall pole coming out the roof with something large and horizontal on top. The vehicle moved in between the nose of the plane and the upstairs part of the terminal building. The object on top of the pole started extending to connect between the plane and the terminal. I said to B, “That’s an air bridge. It must be so the captain can board the plane. He doesn’t want to get on with everyone else.” Soon after, there was an announcement to move forward. I gathered all my stuff from the seat, including a small laptop computer and a couple of paper notebooks with stuff scribbled on the pages and then we and the other passengers headed towards an open-air area where there were long counters with rollers or conveyors and staff standing behind. I asked, “Is this security? Do I have to put my laptop in the tray?” An official said, “No, that bit comes later,” and we realised we still had a long time to wait.

I was sorting through videos of B’s 1976 bushwalk in Tas. I found some files from 1976, but not the right ones so I was-trying to work out where else to look. I was putting names on the files and arranging them in chronological order as well as I could.
Something about ancestors’ (names.) arranged in a circle...

I was in as small room, changing into a swimsuit, and preparing for some kind of indoor activity, but somebody drew my attention to what my family was doing outside, so I went looking for a window where I could look out and see them. There was a window. I tried to get the window open wide enough to lean out to see what the family was doing,and I saw them in the distance, in the water, near a shore/beach, swimming or playing or something, so I decided to join them. Somehow I was then outside and crossing the water. Don’t know if I was wading or actually walking on the water, but I seemed to be trying not to get wet. Not sure that I was swimming at all, until when I got close to them.  I don’t know what happened after I reached them.

I was at a building with someone else. It had an amazing, very old lift. The lift had ornate, cage-like walls with curly bronze metalwork. It was manually operated in some way, but I was explaining to my companion that it wasn’t a “paternoster elevator” because they run continuously, and passengers have to step in and out of the moving cage. This lift did stop at each floor, but had an elaborate mechanism where two operators were required to slide the cage sideways along metal tracks out of the lift well before the doors could be opened. My companion and I went looking for the toilets. We couldn’t find any in the ground floor, so we walked round the back of the building, where I’d seen a couple of doors that might have been entrances for ladies & gents, but they turned out to be very battered old wooden doors, locked and barred, which looked more like doors of storage areas, so we continued round and back into the building, where we heard an announcement that the lift was ready to take passengers upstairs (the mechanism being so slow and complex, and the cage so small, that passengers needed to book ahead to go up or downstairs.) My companion and I discussed whether we should take the opportunity to get onboard. I don’t know if we did. I was discussing whether something was real, or just something people said in dreams... I was trying to choose the right kind of clothes for some obscure event... Last bit I remember, I was with Al, and I was teaching him how to buy petrol. We were in a white or silver car. Because I wasn’t familiar with the car I asked for help filling it from a service station attendant. He said he would choose the best fuel for this car. I was worried that he was taking advantage of us, and would deliberately choose the most expensive premium fuel, but when I went round to the other side of the car, following the very long hose from the car to the pump, I was pleased to see that he had actually chosen the cheapest appropriate fuel. When it came time to pay, I explained to my son that we needed to go in to the pay desk office/convenience store section.  We told the woman behind the desk the car’s registration number, which she entered on her keyboard and issued us with an invoice, which we took outside. My son wanted to go and pay cash to the man who poured the petrol, but I told him we needed to take the invoice to another cashier and pay by card. When we got to that desk, the transaction would not go through because I’d got two digits wrong in the car’s number, so we had to go back out, copy the number down correctly, take it back to the woman who issued the invoice and hope that she would agree to issue a new invoice with the correct number. I had a lot of trouble copying the car’s number in legible handwriting, and made several attempts, with a lot of crossing-out.

I was out in the bush or the desert somewhere, looking at the landscape of hills & valleys of red dust, with ridges in the bare slopes like contour lines, and a voice either inside my head or nearby  was saying, imagine how this place would look if the water level rose - this would all be like a sea or a big lake. Looking around me I saw that water really had risen up to fill the landscape, spreading out like a silvery sea with dark red-brown peaks and ridges poking through its shiny surface . Somebody came riding up on a horse  wanting to bring news to the knight who defends this area. I told him the person he sought was checking defences at the far end of the kingdom, and it would take some time to reach him, due to all the water, but not to worry because that same body of water was protecting us from invasion, like a moat.

I was in a place with tables and chairs, either a train dining car or a bar, or a folk club, with 2 seats either side of small tables. I had left my chair to do something and when I came back someone had taken my seat and there was nowhere for me to sit. I was upset and looked around me murmuring, “That was MY seat!” and while I was looking around somebody I vaguely knew moved a long table aside and a whole row of new seats seemed to appear from nowhere alongside it. I congratulated her on her problem-solving skills and sat down to chat with people I knew at the next table.  One of those people was Jeanette, who was standing nearby. I told her about the dream I’d had earlier last night about writing advertising in different musical keys. After that conversation I got up to either leave or go buy a drink, and thought for a moment that I’d lost my phone, but it had just slipped out of its cover, and I was holding it mixed up with a whole lot of other stuff.  I was coming back into a multi-storey apartment building I’d been into earlier, where someone had a grey kitten that looked like a baby version or our cat, except that this kitten was grey all over and didn’t have any of our cat’s white markings. I found the kitten sitting outside the building and picked it up and cuddled it, and it snuggled up to me, just like our cat used to do, and, even though I was disappointed that this cat’s markings weren’t as pretty, I really wanted to keep it, and was wondering if I could persuade my husband to welcome a new cat right away. The people in that apartment had a golden-type coated dog that had some kind of problem preventing it from eating, so they had some arrangement for feeding it.  I had a drink with a friend. Even though it was really early in the day, I joined her in drinking some kind of sticky, sweet liqueur, served in a pink bowl, with bits of fruit in it. My friend said she now wanted a cocktail, and insisted it would be easy to make. I hadn’t finished my drink, and as I was lying on the bed drinking it I realised it would be hard to sit up without spilling it, but I managed to twist around and hand the bowl to my husband, who was lying beside me. I followed my friend back to the kitchen, thinking she seemed to be a pretty big drinker. There was another woman in the kitchen. She was very neat, with an immaculate blonde pageboy haircut and a grey suit. I offered her a drink and she politely and rather primly said, “I hardly ever touch alcohol“ and then added, “except for my white wine in the evening”, in a tone of voice that suggested that the white wine was very important to her.  The cocktail woman was looking around for ingredients & saw a big plastic bottle of clear brown liquid on the bench. She asked what it was, and I told her it was vinegar - which was clearly written on the label.  At some point I was pouring some kind of lumpy grey breakfast cereal into a bowl. It was a strange sort of bowl, blue china, very deep and hollow-walled, with small holes either side, just below the inner edge of the rim.  As I poured the cereal in, it seemed to disappear somewhere, so the bowl always looked nearly empty. Then I bumped the side and bits started falling back into the bowl from one of the holes in the side, and I realised that the cereal had found its way into the hollow walls. The more I tapped on the sides, the more fell back into the bowl until I was afraid it was going to fill up and overflow before I could manage to pour the milk in. I did pour in the milk, but don’t remember drinking any.  I was helping my husband to vacuum pack some clothes. I didn’t get the plug in quick enough, so air started getting back in so he had to vacuum it again, and while he was doing that, I was fascinated by the complex bayonet-style locking device I noticed inside the plug.  I was so distracted by this that when the vacuuming was done I tried to put the plug in upside down and back to front, so we had to do the vacuuming all over again.

In an English-looking country town. I’m talking to a woman behind the wheel of a car. Her hair or part of her clothes is stuck together with a staple. A little later I see the car moving erratically, rolling backwards, driverless, and sort of ricocheting from one side of the road to the other. It needs to be stopped, and I do stop it, but there’s some sort of crime committed in the process. A little later I’m talking to the female driver about how to cover up the crime. We’re in a country lane and I’m leaning into the car window talking to her. I notice a man in the distance looking at us. He’s down the road, on the other side of a small wooden bridge, close enough to see us but not to hear. I warn the woman in the car that this man had seen us earlier,  and might link us to the crime. How do we eliminate him as a risk, without resorting to murder? I stroll across the bridge to chat with the man, acting nonchalant, and hoping to convince him that I’d run into the car woman by chance just now, and if he’d seen me with the woman earlier, it was a coincidence. I’m not sure how convincing an act I put on. He was a youngish man, maybe in his 30’s, thinnish, with a beard and long light-brown/dark blonde hair.

I was standing with a group of people, mostly men, in a toilet. We were wiping our bottoms. One of the men looked like Hugh Laurie in a pale blue-green tweed suit. He got a bit of poo on his suit. Nobody seemed embarrassed at all. I was at a nursing home visiting my grandmother. I was on the phone to my aunt about how Gran was going. Aunt was concerned that Gran wasn’t eating. I told Aunt that I’d seen Gran eating a sort of custard in the morning,and some omelette, and she’d had a few protein drinks, so she wasn’t starving & the nursing home people were looking after her ok. While I was on the phone Gran came into the room in a wheelchair. I didn’t want Gran to know I was talking about her, but hadn’t finished reporting back to my aunt, so I gave Gran a kiss and quickly and quietly told my aunt the rest of the news. Looking at Gran I noticed that even though she was so old and small, she still had the face of an intelligent and alert woman. I could see her younger self behind the wrinkles. I was at our children’s primary school and one of the teachers told me that “Mrs Troy” was on sick leave because she was having trouble with her ear, due to something she’d caught from one of the kids - possibly one of ours. I was meant to keep this information to myself & not spread it around. I was chatting to other parents in the school ground. The school was preparing for some sort of concert event where groups of children from each class were preparing presentations where they would talk about words starting with different letters of the alphabet. I was with my Dad, watching the presentations. A group of kids got up doing presentations about their set of letters - maybe D,E,F,G. A boy of about 10 took his turn, presenting his words with such style that I said to Dad, “I think I can see where he’s headed as an adult,” (imagining the boy as a stand-up comedian). I told Dad I recognised this boy - maybe I’d taught him - and tried to recall his name. I was pretty sure it was Daniel. I was in some concrete garage-like building with husband “B” and a big suitcase/backpack full of clothes on the ground beside a car. I needed a shower and went rummaging through the luggage to find a towel and shampoo. Then I started gathering clothes to wear. Realising that I was getting dressed for a performance of our Bolivian pan pipe band, I pulled out my poncho and a selection of black pants, top etc. to go under it.

I’d gone with my husband to my favourite local cake shop, & wanted to order a birthday cake for our son. We passed a street stall outside stocked with all kinds of beautifully packaged, interesting loaves, but it was closed and dark. The cake shop was open, but their display window was bare. I wasn’t sure if this was because they were stocking less stuff die to Covid, or if it was just late in the day & they’d sold out. There were lots of people in the shop, but people were trying to keep their distance.  At the counter I was served by a woman with a nice black & white polkadot mask. Admiring her mask, I realised I’d left mine at home.
