Worrying about being seen in public without a mask, I rummaged through my handbag for a substitute, and pulled out a long pink & orange handwoven scarf, which I tried to wrap around my face, but it kept slipping off. The shop woman’s mask also kept slipping below her nose. I asked if I could order a cake to pick up next Saturday, and she said, “Are you allowed to have people over for a party?” I explained that it would be just the 4 of us in our household who would be eating it, so she took my order.  At some point in this process I noticed that my husband had also forgotten his mask, so I had another look in my handbag and found a big square orange-toned shawl/scarf with fringes and flower embroidery. I offered it to my husband but he said he didn’t want it - that he had something else he could use, and dropped it on the floor.   I picked it up, feeling a bit disappointed, and saw it had dirty marks on it. I tried to fold it up neatly, but it was very big and hard to fold.  I wanted to distract my husband to go outside so I could secretly buy a “matchstick” cream cake.

There was a music session & I was playing along with other people,  They were playing a tune that I thought at first was a folk tune, but turned out to be”Colonel Bogey” march. I did my best to join in though I couldn’t see the music properly. I was playing the flute and the others were playing all kinds of brass band instruments. Someone gave me some sheet music but it was for a different tune. Then they were playing a tune that was by some modern classical or jazz or something composer. It was a really nice tune that I’d been wanting or trying to play on the piano in the past and I was interested to hear how it sounded.  I was with B (husband) somewhere and remembered that he needed to move our car to somewhere safer because the parking time limit was running out and I didn’t want  to get a fine. I said I’d already parked our son’s car in a residential area where there were no limits. It was a long way back to where our car was, but we needed to move it.  Later on we were at someone’s house and I realised I’d left a musical instrument behind when we moved the car. I was relieved that I still had my flute with me. I could see the flute case was open and empty, but because I’d just been playing it, I knew it was ok.  At some point I was involved in acting in a movie. I was supposed to stand very still,  while some female character came up and made a speech in front of me. She was only knee high, so I leaned over to hear and sort of sobbed in sympathy with her pathetic words, wondering if it was ok to show any emotion in my standing-still role. Then there was a gunshot sound, like a starting pistol, and I started to run a lap round the room, but the director told me to stop, and asked why I always ran in these movies. I apologised and said I thought I’d been told to run when I heard the signal. I continued the run round the room, noticing bits of the polished floor that had been damaged. I was in a house with someone like Gerard and chatting about stuff, and then left to go next door, and he followed & rushed through the door ahead of me, gabbling some excuse to the people who lived there.

I was with people making a movie or a recording and noticed we were overlooking  an old folks home, and right in the middle of whatever we were recording a woman came into the yard repeatedly calling out someone’s name in a plaintive, shaky voice.    I was now somehow involved in relocating the old folks home into new premises. The residents weren’t all that happy with the move, and we were trying to convince them of the benefits. It had a pool in a sunny yard, & we got them to go in the pool - which at times looked only the size of a bathtub. We were trying to get them to agree how great that was, while uncomfortably aware that the yard was not all that big & looked out on a not very attractive street. Then a noise started. It sounded at first like a very loud rock band and then I worked out it was a Mr Whippy ice cream truck with its music too loud and distorted and I said to the people, it’s ok, that noise is just passing through. It won’t happen all the time.  Glimpse of making a cup of instant coffee, where the coffee powder was very fine, looking as if it had a little powdered milk mixed in. It was thinly scattered and partially sticking to the sides of the cup so I couldn’t work out if there was enough.  I was with a child who was in my care, possibly one of my students, and he/she needed some medication that had to be given “under parental supervision” or some rule like that. It was a clear liquid and I had to measure 4 spoonfuls of it as accurately as possible, but on the 4th spoonful the part where the bowl of the metal spoon met the handle went floppy, so the bowl of the spoon kept drooping down and spilling the contents. I tried all sorts of ways of holding the spoon in place with one hand while pouring the liquid with the other, realising that this was a job that really required 3 hands, and was calling out for help. The liquid was to go into a bathtub like the one the pool/ bath at the old folks home described above. The child was in the bath/pool, and I was telling her to “swim, swim”, miming the action as I said it.  I was with people in several vehicles driving fast along a dirt road. The vehicles, fairy rugged 4-wheel drives, kept either colliding head-on or having near misses because of one of the drivers unwittingly driving on the wrong side of the road. It was a very rough, dusty and stony road with poorly defined edges, and I heard a man’s voice saying that going so fast, “these things bounce around a lot”, implying that a driver could easily drift to the wrong side of the road without realising it.  At some point I was in a movie set where they were filming an episode of something where scantily clad women were reclining in what were meant to be glamorous poses. I think one of them was Essie Davis, playing Phryne Fisher, and I was looking at her, wondering how they make her look so much younger than she really is. Somebody explained that it was all about lighting, and tricks like oiling the skin so it looks shiny. For a moment I saw the women under bright, cool lighting, with pale, slack, slightly puffy, ageing skin, and then it switched to dim, warm light, and their skin glistening with oil, giving an illusion of youth.  I was getting dressed for a party “with my lovely aunt Beryl”. This Beryl was the sister of my Dad’s brother’s wife. While I dressed myself up in a pretty dress and lots of jewellery, Beryl appeared, dressed in some sort of satin tuxedo, because, after years of marriage & children she had come out as a lesbian, and wanted to wear masculine clothes. We were going off to a dance.

I was to find the past addresses of some celebrity or significant ancestor through directories on some kind of genealogy website. 3 different entries, the last one giving the most detail, but I can’t remember what the detail was. I can dimly picture images of the pages with ads for different stuff. At some point I was talking to someone about currencies and what things would have been worth. Somebody asked me which notes I would use if I was buying things in the musical key of G. I said that the letters G, B and D would definitely be in the advertising because they’re the notes in the tonic chord & therefore very positive, and wondered if you would find notes from the relative minor anywhere in an ad. Would they use a minor chord to advertise something sad like a funeral director? The person I was talking to was surprised that one would be expected to pay for hire of a hearse as part of the service & I insisted I’d heard on the radio that they come under the “Taxis and Hired Vehicles Act”.

I get chicken out of the freezer to make tonight’s dinner. It’s meant to be 400g chicken breasts, but the package is all messed around and appears to have a lot of wings in it. That’s annoying, but I think I’ll just have to make do with wings. I’m now eating the meal, with a baby, about 6 months old, on my lap. The baby is interested in my food, and grabs a piece of pumpkin, biting a bit off one corner. It’s a bit hot and the baby spits it back onto the plate. I tell the baby, kindly, “It’s not nice to spit food from your mouth onto someone’s plate. It will get germs on it.” I’m looking at a sea scene on a TV screen, and keep noticing creatures. “Oh, look, a seal!” I reached out, through the screen somehow, to give the seal a cuddle. I knew it could be dangerous to get so close to a wild animal and risk a nasty bite, but the seal seemed to enjoy the cuddle & then went on its way. I’m at a ball. Dancing in a small room. Doesn’t seem to be anyone else there. I say, “Pity I’m not wearing a skirt,” thinking I’m wearing grey slacks, but then look down & see I’m wearing a calf-length skirt made of 3 or 4 tiers of fabric, each one with gathers where it attaches to the tier above so the whole skirt flares out when I spin around. Similar to a skirt I do own, but darker, in shades of reddish brown. I’m wearing the skirt as I walk down a street, maybe Lygon St in Carlton, & people somewhere behind me are talking derisively about hippy wannabe throwbacks wearing folksy skirts. I’m getting dressed opening a cupboard that has doors within doors, about 3 layers of doors covered with greenish wallpaper, & then shelves or drawers inside, and I’m wondering if I can take a shower right there, with water running all over the carpet or if I have to go to a bathroom to get changed. I’d really like to stop for a cappuccino, but I have to get to a meeting/get-together with some of my old work colleagues. First I have to find where I parked my car and then move it near the meeting place. I see a parking area, but the ground is covered in thick, red mud & I don’t want to walk there because it would mess up my shoes, so I follow the road further in & find a drier area with lots of parking spaces, so I decide to walk the shortest way back out to the street and park there. This involves climbing a very steep embankment & getting round the edge of some deep ditches to get back onto the footpath. I’m at the get-together, talking to my friends. I still haven’t had the coffee I wanted, but at the end of our meeting, “Ella”  hands us all plastic bags containing food we hadn’t finished from earlier. Mine had something chocolatey in it. As we were leaving, someone was talking about mental health issues related to Covid & suggesting that the virus caused changes in the brain, and I was trying to explain that the mental health problems were caused by anxiety about the virus, rather than through actually being infected, and that this was causing a lot of the problem in aged care. I went to find my car, which was now supposedly parked on the street a few doors away, but I couldn’t find it. I walked a block or two one way, remembering I needed to cover my face, pulling a scarf over my face while I felt in my pocket for a mask. Once I had my mask on & still hadn’t found the car I turned and came back up the middle of the street, through a kind of market area where I noticed that no-one else was wearing a mask. I was really angry and started saying louder and louder, “Where’s your mask?”, until finally I was standing in the middle of the street, shouting, “It’s because of selfish idiots like you that we’re stuck in this lockdown for longer and longer. Why can’t you be bothered doing a simple thing like wear a mask?!” And the people just looked at me with this “Who does she think she is?” kind of look. I got back to near where the meeting had been and still couldn’t find the car. I thought I could see a red Corolla like our real-life one, but when I got closer I could see it was a little dark red sporty thing. I felt a bit panicky, thinking our car had been stolen, or if I’d simply forgotten where I parked it, but then realised this was a dream & then I woke up.

I was walking along the road with B, and singing along with a song we were listening to on his phone while waiting at a pedestrian crossing. The song went high and my voice soared up with a beautiful, sweet note that was perfectly in tune. It was such a beautiful note that a man waiting on the other side of the crossing gave me an appreciative look with eyes wide open. B looked at me & said, “See - you CAN sing really well when you get a chance!” We were at a gathering, maybe some kind of concert in an upstairs room. We were sitting near the back on seats like wooden pews, and there were all sorts of clothes & other things scattered on the floor, including my handbag & iPad. When we were on our way out of the building after the event I remembered that I’d forgotten my things. It was quite a long, difficult way back in, so B offered to go back in and get my stuff. I said, “Make sure you get my iPad and the little notebook!” When we got home, or wherever it was we were staying, I looked at my handbag and realised that my iPad wasn’t there, and I was worried and angry with B who insisted he didn’t remember me saying anything about looking for the iPad. I replied angrily that the last thing I had said before he went back in was to make sure he looked for it, and why hadn’t he listened to me? He tried checking if it was nearby by making FB Messenger call to the iPad but we couldn’t hear it ringing, so we knew we’d left it behind. B said not to worry. We were the last people to leave that place, and we’d go back first thing in the morning, so the only people likely to have seen it would have been cleaning staff or organisers, & we could phone the organisers to let them know we were looking for it. I remembered that I’d put a label inside the cover with my name and contact details, so I felt reassured. We did go back next morning, and it was there, just where I’d left it, lying on the floor just in front of where we’d been sitting, partially hidden under a black cardigan. My notebook was also lying on the floor near where I’d been sitting, so everything was ok.

I was in a small, windowless wooden cabin with a bench long the end wall, facing a door at the front. There was a pile of children’s scrapbooks or school workbooks on the bench. I could hear sounds outside, behind my cabin, and wondered if someone was smuggling children to safety aboard a boat, and whether the books on the bench belonged to those children. I wanted to remind them not to forget the books, but was afraid that if I opened the door of the cabin it would draw attention to their activities and put them in danger, so I stayed quiet inside, waiting and hoping that they would remember the books. I was in a darkish room with Aliena, (one of the central characters in the novel I’ve been reading at bedtime) and she had just given birth. She was talking about the umbilical cord and the placenta, complaining about pain and bleeding, and I could hear midwives reassuring her that everything was normal. I was observing the scene with interest, thinking to myself how strange it was that in the story there had been a 7 year gap since her first two children were born, with no more pregnancies, so here she was with another child that hadn’t been mentioned in the book. Somebody, who sounded like the narrator of the book, said that this child created a “triumvirate burden of responsibility” for Jack, her partner in the novel.

There was some kind of big 5-yearly religious festival due to happen  - “Festival of the Holy...(cross? crown?)”, and authorities were worried about crowd control and social distancing. I heard a news report that support troops would be coming from Poland to help out, as the event would be taking place in Vilnius, Lithuania. Last thing I remember in the dream is an aerial view of the square outside the cathedral in Vilnius.

I was organising some sort of party, and decorating the fridge door with jokes I’d printed out. There was a cartoon joking.about the contents of some story I’d already stuck there and I was looking for somewhere to fit it. There was a small note on the side of the fridge that I’d stuck up long ago ad I tried to move it but it was stuck so firmly that I couldn’t move it without damage. I went to the other side of the room to check out how things looked and some male nearby made a really lewd joke about a raunchy woman. I called him out for the comment but turned around to see a picture of an orange armchair where she’d bitten a big chunk out of one side of the back, so it had one corner bitten right off with springs and stuffing sticking out, & I thought, “That guy’s got a point - she really is a “goer”!”  I went out to take a shower and came to a really tall sort of staircase or metal climbing frame and climbed to the top, where I could only get to the bathroom by climbing across a perilous gap & I realised that I was doing this in the wrong direction. Normally I’d be climbing across from the other direction and heading downwards, which would be much easier. I realised that at my current age & fitness level I couldn’t get across the gap from here & was scared to move. There was a mirror beside me and when I saw myself in it, the reflection was a quite good looking teenage male, about 17 or 18 years old, & I thought, “I’m not a bad looking young man, but I do need a shower.” B (husband) and I were having dinner with Cathy. She was looking very slim and well, dressed in a smart plaid shirt in shades of brown & orange that went well with her blonde hair. Although I didn’t actually like the shirt, I complimented her on how well it suited her. She served us a stew out of a big pot. It had lots of vegetables and good ingredients, but was a bit disgusting and slimy to eat, but B & I were polite and said nice things about it as we ate. Cathy said this was a dish she really liked to cook for guests, and I agreed that it’s really good to have a signature dish that’s tasty and easy to cook. Thinking about my own family favourite “Syrian Chicken”, which is tasty, but a lot of work, I wondered if this would be my version of Cathy’s “go-to” dish.

I was involved in a dangerous secret mission. I had to get a key to someone. I had a special box with compartments in it, and there were several keys in the box, of two different shapes. It was hard to be sure which was the right key. They were copper-coloured, and one set had big round ends where you grip them, with transparent amber-coloured glass/plastic inserts. It was important to give right keys to someone in secret way. There was a man watching me, and I couldn’t be sure whether he was an enemy agent or someone I could trust, so I didn’t know how much I could safely reveal to him. There’s a lady offering tea, other foods. I accept, he doesn’t.  Olga is sick in Perth. Dad goes to WA see her. I’m amazed to realise that this is his first time ever in a plane, and wondering how the trip is going for him. What to wear? I put on a pale green top under long, patterned cardigan that I usually wear over a dress with a grey long-sleeved T-shirt underneath for warmth. I never normally wear this outfit with the green top but it looks good, and is warm enough if I wear grey cardigan on top. For some reason I need to dress nicely. I’m somewhere near a river in ?London, south of wherever B & I are staying. We want to go back a bit farther north up the river, to a spot where we had a very romantic interlude. It’s nice going along the river. Decoying someone  so we could get away from them back to where we wanted to be. How to get there? I can see a bus or tram in distance across a very busy intersection. Trying to plan route using a timetable on my iPad. B points out that I’ve chosen the wrong route, so I hurriedly try again, afraid of missing the bus/tram. We need to get home. The route on the iPad seems very indirect. I’m wondering if we can even get there from here?

Builders appear to have started work on the planned units behind our house. I can hear heavy machinery, see above the fence bits of large machines working. They’ve broken part of their back fence down. I’m standing in our back gate, looking across the lane and screaming, “Go broke! Please go broke!” as loud as I can. An older woman with bleached blonde hair – looking like an elderly Italian-Australian grandmother – hears me and asks why I’m shouting. I shout passionately, “Because I don’t want them to build those horrible, ugly units.” I believe at this stage that the woman is connected with the builders, and want to be as insulting as possible. She asks why they’re so bad. I go into detail: “They wanted to put 10 on the block – at least they’ve had to reduce that to 9, but it’s still too many, and some of them will be 3 storeys. Our next door neighbours will have no privacy at all in their back yard. And they’re really horribly ugly.” She asks what’s so ugly about them, and I say, “They’re really sterile flat roof, flat front, white boxes with nasty panels of grey cladding.”  I realise that the woman is actually a neighbour, standing on stairs at back of a house next door to that block, and she’s agreeing with every word. I’m walking downhill along a dirt driveway towards a road with my sister, stepping over an earth ditch or drain along the way, talking about wanting to be a grandparent, and how it’s really down to just 2 of our 4 sons, both of whom have female partners, but are not married and as far as I know have no family plans. I said to my sister maybe the son who told us he’s bisexual might adopt one day if he stays with his male partner, because he does seem to like kids – or maybe somewhere down the track he’ll find a female partner, but his brother who is gay definitely doesn’t want kids, so, I said to my sister it’s up to the other two boys!  I’m in a place where there’s a kitten or a young rabbit running around in a yard or a room. I lean over a wall or a fence and pick the kitten up and start explaining to our youngest son “The female has a very complex reproductive system because of the shape of its uterus/fallopian tubes” (seeing a mental image of the organ in question, which as far as I remember looked like a cat’s horned uterus), thinking that this would be of interest to him as a student of reproductive biology. I was serving bowls of ice cream topped with dollops of cream for me and B. We were about to drive somewhere to meet someone.  I started eating mine and said to B, “Why not enjoy the ice cream now because it will melt by the time we get there,” & give B his share. He sits in the car eating it.  We’re driving somewhere for a picnic following friends/family in another car. Car ahead of us pulls over into camping spaces beside the road and we pull over behind them. There are no tents pitched there, but there are things lying around in the camping spaces that suggest people might already have claimed them. We park there anyway, explaining that we’re not camping here, just parking for a little while. Other families in a row of tents behind these sites, a little farther off the road are having a picnic, sitting on tartan rugs. We walk past, saying hello. There’s a red, hammock-like synthetic fabric swing nearby, belonging to their kids. I swing on it, and realise as I swing, that I’ve peed right through it.  Embarrassed, I keep swinging, hoping the air movement will dry up the evidence quickly.

I was in the jungle, supposedly required to help some local indigenous people who were picking bananas. These bananas were hanging in bunches from vines really high up in the trees, and the men were skilfully scrambling up and down the vines like rope climbers, cutting down the bunches and bringing them back to me, where I was supposed to be helping out somehow, but all I could really do was tidy up the bunches by pulling off any dead bits & rubbish. I thought I’d get in trouble if I didn’t look busy, but they were all so high up in the trees that I didn’t have any bananas to work on, so I sat down on some concrete steps to watch them. It was very hot and sunny so I started applying sunscreen that was really white, thick, sticky and greasy, and I commented to someone who was with me what revolting stuff it was, but I had to smear it all over my neck, face and arms. I was wearing my dark purple top with the matching amethyst pendant, and was worried that the awful sunscreen might damage the pendant. I was no longer at the banana picking, the scene somehow having kind of transitioned into a garden party where I was being introduced to a sister of my real-life nephew’s wife, Catherine. This woman introduced herself and her husband, and I introduced myself to them, but I didn’t quite catch their names. I went with the woman to do something - either get some drinks, or get stuff from a cloakroom - and while we were waiting at the counter I quietly apologised to the woman, saying, “I’m sorry, but I’m really terrible with names and I need to practice so I get this right. Can you please tell me your name again.” She said her name was Katinka. “And what is your husband’s name?” I asked. He appeared beside me, saying in a very posh English voice, “My name is SIR Jeremy Throssington-Smythe. A lot of  people call me Thross.” Apparently just calling him Jeremy would not be acceptable and I was a bit put off by the SIR thing, but was embarrassed to call him Thross, and felt the whole name was a bit of a mouthful, so I said, “If you don’t mind, I think I might end up just calling you ‘Hey!’”   By this time we were back at the tables in the garden and I was explaining apologetically to  Katinka that I often feel socially awkward, and she pointed down at a book that was lying on the ground under the toe of her shoe, that was full of stories about how to cope in socially awkward situations. I thanked her and started looking through the book. Then I was back with my husband B, who remembers lots more people than I ever can, and told him about the encounter. When I mentioned Sir Jeremy etc etc, B said, “He’s the British foreign secretary!” I was a bit embarrassed that I hadn’t known that, and felt rather ignorant, but I really am very bad with names.

I needed to go to the toilet. For some reason I thought it would be more environmentally sustainable to do it in a hole in the ground, which must have had a bucket in it, because then I was carrying the bucket and its contents into a toilet block in the hope of flushing the contents away and washing the bucket, but I had to wait behind a whole lot of people. At some other point I was on white/grey sand, possibly near a beach, and explaining to B [husband] that I could pee in the sand and leave it looking as if nothing had happened. I demonstrated, brushing dry sand over the wet patch so that it was soon hidden. Our friends “John & Jenny” had a fourth baby who was toddling round a room. I was watching her round face, blonde hair and stocky physique and commenting that she reminded me a lot of one of their 3 other now adult daughters. Someone was disagreeing and suggesting that she was more like another of the daughters.  I had met a woman I really liked and wanted to get to know her better. She was lonely because something had happened to her husband but she was wary of becoming too friendly with someone new. We enjoyed each other’s company for a while, but I could see that she was a bit suspicious of my motives so I decided to go for now, but wanted to swap phone numbers so we could get in touch later. I found an old scrap of paper that already had my name and address on it, tore off that part of the page for her, writing my phone number down the side. I asked for her number. She gave me the name of a website, saying, “You can find me here.” I said it was lucky she worked for a small business where I could find her on the website, because if I’d given her the Victorian Education Department website she wouldn’t have had a hope of finding my name there. After leaving it occurred to me that I hadn’t given a moment’s thought to my own partner. This partner was in jail for some reason, and I realised that I hadn’t seen him or even asked about him since his imprisonment. Whoever this partner was, I really disliked him and wanted to be rid of him, thinking the prison sentence might be grounds for a divorce. I was talking to someone about this and then realised angrily that no one in the Justice Department, no social workers or any support agency had reached out to me to guide me in how to behave under the circumstances. I was ranting angrily, “not a single word of guidance!!!”  and similar grievances - not that I really had any interest in that partner or his wellbeing, but it made me feel better about it having someone else to blame for my ignoring him.

About people suffering effects of poisoning like the people we saw in the series we were watching last night on TV about the Salisbury novichok poisonings. Main character in the dream seemed healthy enough but there was some question about whether  she had signs of having had the poison in the past, or whether it was going to have delayed effects. I was talking to Gavin about his retirement plans. His wife and his cat were there, just like we see them on Zoom rehearsals.  I was with a friend listening to a recording of some man playing a piano piece famously badly, and I decided to play along, using some old sheet music I had, but taking so long to find the right page in the battered old music book, that the piece was pretty much over by the time I was ready to join in, but saying to whoever I was with that I’d have a go at playing it anyway.  I was walking in the country on a path along a ridge above a very green forest. A beautiful bright yellow cockatoo was on the ground. It was rather flat, sort of 2D & folded in half, but alive and healthy. I picked it up so that its wings opened out, and stroked its long beautiful feathers, and encouraged it to fly away, which it eventually did, but rather reluctantly.  I was trying to show people a quick route to a house where we were going to stay, but kept being prevented from getting there by no-entry & one way street signs.  I was in an old, derelict-looking building, maybe some kind of science lab or factory, with a chunky framework of hollow metal beams, painted red, with blue cladding filling the spaces between the framework  beams. The surface under the red paint was lumpy, as if the metal was rusting. I realised that those hollow beams in the walls were full of boiling water under high pressure, and I was rushing around warning people that the boiling water was about to come bursting through any weak spots in the rusty framework . We kept escaping corridors and rooms just in time through doors with really dodgy, rusty-looking locks that might not open. The rusty red framework had uprights either side of those doors, so as we struggled to open the doors I had my eyes on the door frames the whole time, expecting to be drenched in boiling water at any moment .
Putting groups of names into piles. Grouping together ones that had something similar happen to them - broken bone? The names are written on something that looks like postage stamps.

I’m in a room where there’s a man threatening violence to someone I’m with. I look for a weapon. All I can find is some sort of toy - either an old BB gun type thing my Dad used to own when I was a kid, or some toy that fires clear plastic pellets. I fire it at the man, but it’s very weak and the pellets fall short. The man laughs at my attempt to attack him, but I keep firing, getting closer, but the pellets just bounce off him and he continues to laugh at my efforts. Then, unexpectedly one of the pellets hits his neck and draws blood. At first I think he’ll just shake it off, but then he falls to the ground in a pool of blood. Later on I’m in a train in a foreign country, maybe South Korea. I’m on my way to meet someone, probably my son R, & I think husband B might be with him. They’ve given me instructions on how to get there. I’m supposed to get off at stop 4 - or is it 5 or 6? There’s an electronic information display in the train, but everything is written in a foreign script except for a number at the end, and I’m confused about whether this is a stop number or a zone number, and before long I’m confused even about which number I’m looking for. The compartment I’m in is extremely private, clean and comfortable, with curved walls and seat all lined with a matt black fabric patterned with a large diamond-shaped grid of thin gold lines. I remember someone telling me that the Koreans take enormous pride in their trains, and am impressed by what I see. I sit in my compartment, watching the urban scenery flash by, and trying to make sense of the display on the sign as the numbers on the end go up 1, 2, 3, 4... Am I supposed to get off here or at the next stop? The PA announcements are no help to me as they’re all in Korean or something. Then I notice to my horror that the numbers on the sign are going back down again, so the train must have reached the end of the line and be on its way back. Soon I’ll be back where I started! If I ever get to where we’re meant to meet, I’ll be really late. And now I can’t remember at all which stop it was meant to be. I wish I’d written the instructions down on a bit of paper instead of trusting my memory! Can I just stay on the train and head back the other way again and get off at Number 4, whatever that means? Would my ticket still be valid or will an inspector notice that I’m travelling on an expired ticket? How do I even buy a new ticket? Can I use a card or does it have to be cash? All I have in my purse is some Australian money - about $35 in notes and a handful of coins which I’d have to exchange for local money. In the dream I remember a terrifying real-life experience 2 years ago with B and our youngest son, Al, on a bus in Poland where confusion over how to buy tickets led to a menacing ticket inspector threatening us with a huge fine for fare evasion, and although I eventually managed to tearfully plead our out of the fine, during the argument with the inspector, images flashed through my mind of ending up alone in a foreign prison. The situation felt frighteningly similar to the Polish real-life nightmare, and I was beginning to panic, again feeling the fear of being in trouble with foreign laws. I felt helpless and afraid. Could I phone our son, R and ask him for help? He lives in Korea and knows the system. I start looking through the contacts on my phone, unsure whether I have his Korean number saved on my phone.

Explaining where I caught some illness? Not the normal way - different route from normal. Eg, through skin? Touch? Instead of breath? “Tell Brother Remigius!” I have mental images of crossword puzzle grids and green vegetables, - Brussells sprouts or cabbage?  There’s nothing bad going on. It leaves me with a positive feeling.

I was making lists of, or counting, daily Covid cases, and sorting them into one of 3 categories. One category, I think it was children under a certain age, didn’t require any restrictions, so I felt pleased if I could include a name in that list, but also anxious about getting it right. A second group was a bit ambiguous - maybe with limited restrictions, and the third group was fully restricted. The lists were piles of pieces of lined brown/manila paper, written on in pencil.

Woke up about 4 am didn’t get back to sleep properly again. I have vague images of long legged insects like mosquitoes but not mosquitoes swirling around my hand and head. There is a sense they are more than they seem. Perhaps some type of hive mind.

I’m working in film editing under the editor I used to assist, Paul. I keep on coming into work and find him tinkering on the flat top bench using parts from an ancient editing machine. I nit sure why he has done this as the steenbeck seems to be in doing working order. He tell a me it has to with the black tape around the screen edge. It’s preventing him from being able to look at the machine correctly.  I’m in the production office doing work and  in another office across the entrance way other members of the team are signaling to members in our office - and back and forth. I think this is to do with a romantic connection but I’m not sure. I’m also in the middle of it all, somewhat amused and somewhat exasperated.  Now I’m in a big old wooden Victorian building with lots of corridors leading all over across many floors. The section I’m in is like a domestic area - an old home but with much of the domestic elements pulled back.  There are however plush red velvet curtains which brings warmth to the wooden features everywhere else.   I go through many of the rooms and interact with the people  around me but can’t remember how. I also f gd ave a strange/interesting device that seems to a robot or automaton. I’m not sure why I know this because  I only remember vague snippets of it being in human form.  Later I’m trying to explain the automaton to someone but the are uncertain I’m telling them.  I pull the thing to be bits to make sense of it but now it seems to be a clever but simple contraption resembling an old fashion heater with a flame with in its small frame - not human-like at all.  Inside their is a metal contraption about 25 cm long and quite fine -I remember grey metal and brass , with one end being thicker and layered.  I pull the device out of its frame and then attempt to pout it back in. Flames keep emerging from the device and I wonder if I’ll burn myself but I don’t. My hands are just warm.  Again opposite myself is a fire place with a black metal frame. It isn’t on but I remember turning it on earlier - perhaps in another space - and having a warm gas flame appear in the grate.   The next part if my dream takes place in a university context. Myself and a group of other students are talking. The space is line a combination of older Goerge street in Sydney and Melbourne with paved areas fir us to congregate in the road.   A woman with shoulder length straight straw coloured blond hair is having a difficulty solving a problem she is engaged with. I suggest approaching it from a different angle. She’s immediately gets excited and stars describing a solution that comes to her. She’s thankful for the help and I’m pleased to have been if assistance and sprites because I appears this is a specific math problem - not my area.  I’m then in the pub beside the outside area and am having a drink with her. She starts to become enamored with me which I’m not comfortable with. She is now male with a long blond mustache.  I go to another section of the pub across the road - again an old Victorian era space with vey sigh ceilings and lots of glass windows . I speak with someone I can’t now remember and soon leave going into the other space. The nan with blond mustache is there and us surprised to see me thinking I had left. I pretend that was the case , having avoided him, and move on.

I’m on holiday with family in a small town, possibly in a skiing area, but it’s not ski season. It feels like New Zealand and Australia. The wether is overcast and may have jus stormed. It’s cold. The house is expensive but not that well furnished. There are mattresses but no beds. I think we are there with another family. It’s dark in the house and the rooms are in a strange configuration one leading onto the next in an usually lay out.   It makes me think of Tarkovsky’s Nostalgia, the witches house and the main house where the camera tracks through the space as if fl paying. There’s also the memory that there is something haunted or uncanny about the house. We try to subtly convince  either my son or someone else they shouldn’t sleep in a room but they don’t pay attention.   I try and lift them out of the room while they’re asleep picking up the whole mattress with them in it. It isn’t heavy but has a closet enveloping feeling.   I also find myself in a work environment in a two story building in a commercial street. It feels like a combination of two different jobs I have had - in Telemarketing and Education both to do with vocational training.  Things are going on but I’m not quite sure what and I feel somewhat disconnected from the others - this is not upsetting but more an observation.  I go walking because I need a good coffee. The street feels like a mixture of Wellington, NZ, Melbourne and Marrickville  Sydney. Again the weather is darker or twilight-ish I’m walking along the café strip looking for some where open but most of them are about close.  A woman counting up lets me into one cosy space and I have a coffee. The aroma and taste a rich and flavorsome - and dominate my senses and experience.  Back in the sky town. I’m leaving I think but am riding on a mountain bike and taking an unsayable route across country. This is an arid rocky place with sandy yellow/white coloured shale, rocks and hills.  I hear a signal ahead and bike harder trying to get i point  past the signal without stopping. As I come in line with signal I see an antique steam train, with out steam, heading towards me out of a tunnel. I bike out of its way but am amazed by the archaic style of the train - not yet a quintessential Victorian steam train but something with odd carriages and boilers perhaps even constructed together out of wood. It’s very dusty and feels like it is part of a western movie.   I ask a man if it us an antique and he says it is.  I keep biking and the dustiness soon gives way to amazing vistas ahead. Green forested fills to the left and sheer red rock cliffs and buttress-like  mountains to the right (like monument valley) but towering high like mountains. The sun is on the red rocks and the vista us very moving.  I find myself in another town by the mountains and bike past an area that seems like a record. It feels European like Chamonix  mont blanc. I ask a man possibly the same man from the train what the buildings are. They are a ski resort but the town is very quiet with current circumstances. I want to help out.

I’m at a house and we have a guest. We are going to go outside for drinks but the guest doesn’t want to be in the sun so she sits a little way off.  I’m fine with her doing thus but worried we don’t have any food, cheeses or olives.  The house we’re in transforms a little. It has an L shaped back wall with doors on both sides of the l junction to go out to the courtyard. I seem to remember blue new weather boards but the change makes it more palatial.  The doors outside are now long open walls with large round reddish beams holding up the roof above us. It’s airy. The floors inside are still the same a dark reddish stained new floor boards - very nice and clean.  I’m now returning with olives and for some reason encourage the cat to take olives from my mouth.   I then see my father in the yard eating olives and drinking. He then seems pleased with himself and shows us all how he can do what I just did, feeding the cat olives in the same way.  I’m annoyed and think he’s being competitive and dishonest. I’m also annoyed that the car that did thus with me is doing this with my father. I then find myself at a function at a big house with extensive courtyards. Im with a group of people and I remember being dresses in jive trousers and a white cotton shirt. The fabric is crisp and the shirt is airy.  The house is airy with extensive sliding doors that bring the outside in.  A friend comes over to me an architect I know from skateboarding. He’s angry at a mutual friend Angel. I ask why he thinks he the friend is duplicitous. He is adamant that nothing the friend says is true. That he is lying about thus that and the other, also about his family. I don’t think what he says adds up. I Enter somewhere airy in the same grounds where a lot of young women are arriving in ornate and structural architectural dresses. The young women enter a modern building and go up the stairs where the look at the dresses in a mirror excited to have got to wear these elaborate constructions.  I go from observing to being one of the dress wearers but I don’t see myself. I feel the fabric. Coming up around and out throw my waist to my shoulders - it’s warm but airy.  There’s also an inner part that comes up inside the cone that I feel against my chest - it’s silty but layered as if padded. One of young woman in particular stands out and is enamored with the dress she wears - in a sweet and endearing way. She’s pretty with long blond ringlet hair.  I mention how cumbersome theses architectural dresses are and she laughs in agreement. I used to like her a lot and I had a chance with her but turned it down as I was friends with her boyfriend. She turned up in the media latter married to two prominent sportsmen. I’m then at a suburban sports ground. A feeder team in the Canterbury Bankstown Bulldogs are upping the ante.   They want to keep the earnings from their games, as they are doing well unlike the top team in the main competition.   I’m not seeing this as a partisan but more as an outside observer.

International Rugby League teams Australian and NZ play or gave played. Then the English team walk up the field, a Neighborhood sports field. I’ve had this dream before. I’m then with my old work boss. We’re all out for lunch.I have to change to change for an appointment. My suitcase is spilled open on the back of a flat deck truck. I change for meeting on the truck. Not sure about my selection of clothes or about getting changes in front of old boss. I put on a white shirt over a white t-shirt . Not me. I’m not embarrassed about changing in the open it just feels a bit off. I find myself in a building and some guy is setting up to pitch a script to some dim execs. It feels like Hollywood I think it’s a Robin Hood script and the writer has rolled it up tight and is trying to nail it to the wall - I assume to make it seem like an arrow that he will reveal to be the script at some point. I laughter at this because it us funny and misguided. I stop him and suggest I’ll help him. I’m then in a cinema complex with my partner and we are taken by our son in to see a movie but he’s a toddler - as he was when he was little. My partner is putting him in a line. We’re in a rush and are Late with getting him in. We have tickets, and some stranger recorded nexus formate of the film. I’m worried the ticket seller will think we’ve bought the film and not tickets to see it in the cinema so I rush us through. Again my partner has our son in the line. I go to join them but find the way I go up is separated from them by a large concrete walled corridor. I go back to find them but and as I turn into an intersecting corridor I walk in the way of two white American teenagers or early twenty somethings. The yell in fright when they see me walk out in front of them. I try to flippantly calm their fright by telling them not to worry, “I’m an Australian and we sometimes we done times walk at strange angles”. The nervously laugh at this explanation. I then find myself outside the line area in the complex wondering how I’ll pick up my sone at the end of the film when the film I’m going to see will run longer. The space I’m in is like a mezzanine level below where I was. Under the floor where I was is a wall of blue windows with glass framed by thick aluminum. I can tell if their us an aquarium behind it or a fun parlor. I then from bd my self I the pitch meeting building and a dark haired attractive woman is suggesting I pitch my script - possibly a fictional espionage conspiracy script. I’m not sure what happens but the woman who is possibly a manager or producer in the film business sits on my lap and puts her arms around me. This all feels a little weird even though i find her attractive but also familiar - a bit like someone I know but not her. The hair is more asymmetrically cut and black and she is more serious and focused than the person I know. While she’s talking me into pushing g my project she just starts kissing me. I like that she’s doing but also feel a bit controlled and nervous and that I’m going to be caught out by my partner. I also have the weird sensation of our tongues connecting in our mouths - the connection feel as if they are their own beings somehow disconnected and the mouth it’s own slippery universe or biological cave. I withdraw and stop our kissing. She looks at me seriously, apprising me. I’m then in a mother level of the building and the two American guys I walked in front are standing with rifles on another level of the pitch/cinema building. There is a glass wall and the room beyond seems to be at the bottom of a large flooded space or an internal building lake space. The Americans guys seem to be part of a militia or are conspiracy believers - though are dressed normally. Things start to get funny. There is a dead man/drowned in the deep watery space behind the glass. A script he was holding floats beside him. I laugh. The title, I can’t remember, suggests a conspiracy script and contains all the answers to unravel that conspiracy. It us of course fiction - the script I was going to pitch earlier- but I know the guys looking in think it’s real. I’m not sure how it got there but gave a memory of an amusing series of events. Any way the American guys decide they are going to shoot the glass out to get the script and what they think is proof. As the work out witch glass pane to shoot out I wonder what they will do when millions of meters if water rush out. I know find myself outside walking down a glass area with family friends. My son, still a toddler is walking along the opposite side of the grass lined street a bit behind us. The couple are seeing me off I think. As we walk and talk the wife, a tall woman, hugs me very close and cries that no one thinks she’s pretty. I say she is but thin she’s more attractive. I pull away and see here with deep etched in winkles and exaggerated features as if she is wearing stage makeup - similar to that in the Charlie Kaufman film final I just watched on Netflix. Her huge is also strange. In real life she is tall but her I had crouch down to be able to hug her. I look back and see my son is missing and that worries me.

Several Peers with Wooden buildings on them on a black, troubled night time sea. The sea is high and tumultuous  as it was by the peers where the boat was moored, and black for a lack of stars or moon. It feels like there is a storm. But I don’t sense wins or rain.  I see two of these boats like I’m looking at them in a wide shot. There’s danger but I don’t seem affected by it.  When I’m at sea I feel like this on the Kapiti Coast in NZ our by the island but it also seems different- somewhere else.  I’m on the shore in the day, again on a Kapiti coast beach. In my mind I’m with some one but I’m not sure who. The notion that someone important has died is in my head - someone like the queen mother. I’m riding around an urban space on a mountain bike and find my way into a school area. I thinks it’s a primary school and the buildings are modern and single story. I bike around one building and find groups of people siting on the ground in the shadows. They are maybe homeless but I’m not sure. This is not where they should be.   I bike up past them and the find myself  at a modern glass café that feels like it is part of a university. I think it might be raining. I go in for a coffee and I’m waiting in line with some other people. There is a woman with a few other people waiting. She has a sandy blond bob - a bit of gray showing through and feels older than I am, even though we are a similar age. I get my coffee and food. She isn’t impressed and will go elsewhere. I tell her that I’m here at the university and that it’s convenient.  After she’s gone I’m talking with the woman who runs the café - I think she’s one of the woman from Ralph’s café at Sydney uni in real life. I now gave more things and ask if I can pick up my trestle table tomorrow morning. There is a lot of wind and I don’t want to carry it while holding the other items I have and looking for the car.  The trestle is a white gray plastic tucked in behind some tables.  While one of the staff is confused by this the manager/owner seems to understand.   I head off and have to remember where the car is. I have a good idea but am a little unsure. The streets feel like Melbourne but are hillier like Wellington or the Easter suburbs of Sydney.   I must find the car despite my confusion and find myself at a development sight/junkyard. A large scale project us about to begin soon and my father, whose name is actually Ralph,  is in charge of the project. I’m looking at the scene unfolding from on top of a high stack of scaffolding steel that has not been assembled maybe 2 meters above the dark brown  muddy ground where a large group of people wearing white hard hats and lab coasts are being spoken to.  I’m more worried about the cats. One of them our Burmese Coco is below the scaffolding and is annoyed, biting and scratching me for some reason.   I picked her up, cautiously because of her mood and go back to the house - a house where we gave been staying temporarily. There’s dark brown set soul around the house too. I go inside and find the cat. There are now two of them. One annoyed and the other compliant. We leave the house and a black Staffordshire Bull Terrier starts parking at the placid cat, now on the ground beside it. I rush in and tell the dog off and get the cat. The dogs is just surprised by the cat who says sorry for causing the dog a fright. I note that it’s interesting the placid cat can speak English.   I’m now drinking around Melbourne possibly to find the car and my life partner gives me some directional instructions. I start driving off and she thinks I’m heading in the wrong direction. I assure her I know what direction I’m heading in and point out the window towards the city. We are on the East side of the river and can see the city. It’s nit actual Melbourne but a constructed version of the city that often appears in my dreams. It’s built up and denser than the real city.  I’m now in bed waking up but wanting more sleep. I can feel the cat moving in the bed and I’m a little annoyed.   When I open my eyes I see it isn’t the cat but our son but as a seemingly fetus like baby in a crawling position. I realise from his eyes that he’s still asleep so I settle him down and cover him up.  I can get more sleep

I’m standing in the sea at about waist depth with my son. The water is a silty greenie brown and the sky is cloudy. There is the sense if there being a shark in the water. It’s big and may have already tried to come at us. I have impressions from under the water of the sharks body. It’s close and rubs past me with it’s side, white and large in the murky water. Strangely I’m not nervous. I gave an aluminum poll. I thinks it’s an extendible painting roller handle to reach high walls that I’m using to ward the shark off - but it doesn’t seem to come back or if it does it’s staying away.   Then I’m meant to be going out with a friends friend who has just had a break up in a relationship. I’m not sure if I want to be there or not. She is attractive but in a handsome and character filled way. She has black shoulder length hair and is wearing a rusty red silk shirt and a three quarter length fitting skirt white/off-white. We have a coffee in a café, with red brick floors and walls and wooden tables. I think our Maltese Australia friend is monetarily there. The woman as I said is quite striking, possibly Maltese as well, or perhaps of Spanish or even Indian origins.   We walk through a plaza  in a cross between a Sydney space and another European space, again made from dark red bricks.  I want to ask her about her break up but don’t, not finding the right time. I wonder when we are going to the films and what she wants to see. She suggests we watch two films but I’m worried that will take too long and I have to get back to my own partner who is waiting for me at a wedding.   I walk some more with her along a road and railway line. A child , male and 10ish, has a skateboard and is ushered off. I wonder if there is a Skateboard park somewhere near by and think about going for a skate myself.  We then find ourselves at the house where the wedding is taking place . A large group of people head out into the garden where I find my partner. Again as with the entire dream the weather is cloudy and overcast. We are all waiting for something to happen but before it does the crowds are gone and myself and my partner look around the house which it seems we gave moved into. It is an older weatherboard house, 1940’s or 50’S-ish and needs a bit of upkeep. It also has several buildings, a studio, with pallets of produce laid out by its front veranda attracting a gust of beetle-like insects. Apparently the previous owners grew the produce and have to pick them up. I think the insects will make that a futile task though I’m not overly concerned.  My partner and I are out and about in a an inner city Wellington NZ suburb like Berhampor. I think we get a call that their is trouble at our house. Our son’s party seems to have got out of hand with a mass of gatecrashers. We go hone and go into the garage, which has no roof and big glass doors onto the toad and a bunch of twentyish young men come in. My sons friends who have seemingly resolved the situation and removed the troublemakers. The police will not be needed to  be called.  Again my partner and I are elsewhere in a small shopping area line Erskineville in Sydney but again either buildings in dark red bricks. We walk into a shop on our way home, to take a short cut and find we are slowed down because of Covid restrictions.  Not sure what the restrictions are because we are still allowed to moved Fi ward through the long skinny space with its cream plaster walls with the a warm painted concrete floor that may gave some straw laid on it in places.  The restrictions it seems involve walking single gone through the people in the café until the tables a bustle give way to a shop area with lots of good strewn on the floor. Thus makes our progress difficult as we have to pick past very delicate objects on the floor and the display cases.  At ones stage I reach into my pockets and find a handful of clear rounded crystals which I drop one of when I bring them out and hear a glass like crash when it falls on what appears to be a beautifully colored stone filled with green, blue, purple crystals (Paula shell colors). Broken crystals are everywhere.  I brush them under the draws and display units not wanting to be discovered but they’re everywhere and crunch u Der foot. The shop owner Gomes over but doesn’t seem to VFX see the breakage or be concerned. I however feel guilty but continue on. I tell my self this is a dream and not happening but it doesn’t assuage my guilt.

I was in a big living room / terrace outside deck space with my grown son, 21,  my younger sister, now dead for ten years, and my oldest friend. My son and I were looking at a book together and discussing it. I’m not sure what it was about but it was a discolored paperback and may have been academic. My son sat on the edge of a seventies style couch while I sat on the floor leaning against it. For some reason it seemed to be of danish design but was upholstered with an unstylish and drab speckled brown fabric. The kind of furniture that might sit in an old family beach house.   Any way my sister walked past us out of the room and seemed happy. I then noticed that my oldest friend was having sex in the same space on the floor. I couldn’t see who he was with clearly because of the furniture between us. An older armchair, not danish, covered in the same fabric as the couch, a big chunky wooden coffee table, 1970’s or 80’s and a green lush plant in a bronze shining pot.   Any way I could see my friend having sex moving backwards and forwards like a jack rabbit. He was wearing a faded button shirt sleeved shirt I remembered him wearing before and a set of white brief shorts.   My reaction was one of annoyance and embarrassment at the fact he had chosen to have sex while we were in the room. I tried to ignore him but found his physical actions too distracting/irritating to do so.   The annoyance was then amplified when I thought... “ he’s not having sex with my sister is he?”. He then stopped and his partner got up off the floor which seemed strange as she had been in New Zealand, where they live, not Australia, and I wondered how she had appeared here.   I wasn’t relieved though because he proceeded to walk around the room with a clear erection under his white shorts underwear.

When I work I remember an internal discussion about language and communication. Some thing I was doing would be problematic  because the students/ those involved be confused about what I was asking of them. In my mind I saw three people together walking down a street on a sunny day in shirt sleeve crispy button up shirts. In my mind the associate was that they were Greek but there were no visual clues to suggest that was so. Perhaps it was an “it’s all Greek” play with words going on in my head.
I do remember spending a lot of money transferring it via my phone to some one else and feeling a bit unhappy or worried about this.

I was staying in a mass accommodation venue like an army base with lots of small cabins for sleeping and communal bathrooms. I was trying to move through them to locate my bedroom. I kept bumping into people and getting swept into their dramas. We were creating documents of useful information to give to people on where they could go for help. People seemed to cooperate toward a common goal. I was running across the crunchy stone pathways in between the cabins in the darkness seeing my breath condense in the cold night air. I was still trying to find my cabin, running along the pathways trying to get back so I could go to sleep.

I had a strong sense of trying to get home. Walking and driving, bumping into random people who asked where I was going. I saw other people being arrested by police and bundled into cars. I saw a woman I knew a long time ago, she tried to help be but it was no use. I was travelling through grassy areas with people standing, no-one was sitting, I went past check points. Some people were not convinced I had enough papers to get through and get home, I kept driving.

I dreamt that I was in a beautiful ocean front house with a lot of people from my work and my mum was there too. It was quite dark but we could see the powerful ocean from the deck. I was amazed to see these beautiful massive sailing yachts all lit up in with their full white sails going past with a full crew. They looked stunning. One of my colleagues saw the boats and jumped off the balcony and was bouncing from the house over to the rocky point, to get the best vantage point. We just watched on as we didn’t have hopping powers like she did. Later when we were tidying up my mum came in and said she doesn’t want to go home yet because she wants to watch the dancing. I said of course, as I know she loves music and socialising. I stayed back at the house and waited for mum. I was playing with my colleagues little grey kitten on the floor. The kitten later in the dream turned into her four year old daughter, who I was also playing with outside. She was making me laugh with her inquisitive observations and I was impressed with how smart she was.

Dreamt I was staying in a beautiful modern home filled with indoor plants. When I got ready for bed, I prepared blankets to lie on the concrete foot path outside. Then some people strolled past and were looking at me. I decided to move indoors and sleep there. One of the plants was ‘perpetual spinach’ like my dad grows, I felt so happy as I thought we’ll have a great supply of spinach no matter what happens! I saw a little girl taking some medicine by herself, it was pale blue liquid in a syringe. Near my bed I found bags and bags of chocolate, jumbo sized blocks, I was giving it away to people, asking them what is their favourite. There was a white man delivering training online about Aboriginal culture, he used a ‘welcome to country’ from you tube, so I didn’t think that was genuine. My relative found a wonderful op shop full of great secondhand toys for kids, we were buying them for all the kids in the family. Back on my bed, it was dark, people still milling around collecting their chocolate. I wanted them to go home. I was waiting and waiting in the darkness, wondering when we can go home.

I was in a share house with lots of people I didn’t know, but I seemed to have a role to help guide them and groups of children home from school. I went downstairs to the kitchen with no fridge but noticed the impressive stove and wok, and magnificent mushrooms sitting under the sink. I went to the bathroom to try to wash my hands but the tap was missing and I found it flimsy, attached with some sticky tape. I tried to move it to pour water over my hands but it only trickled a few drops. A gorgeous young tall man entered breathing heavily like he’d been running and wanted to use the enormous pink bath. He had a heavy hormonal scent and was covered in city grime & dust. I wondered if his smell would improve after his bath and what the dirty ring around the bath would look like.The house owners were two gay men who were happy to have us all there in their home. It was a house full of squeaky floors like the ones I’d rent while studying. I wondered what the cafes were like nearby, as it felt near the CBD. I wanted a coffee!

Returned to the site of a tragic event that happened long ago. The place felt like Australia but could have been Vietnam. There was a delegation of people visiting the site, which is now buzzing with activity and people getting on with their lives. We were expecting a woman to tour the site who was an original witness to what had occurred. There was rubble and new parts of buildings. No- one was wearing masks but it felt good to socially interact again, despite lack of social distancing. A big delivery of fresh fruit and vegetables had arrived, boxes and boxes of top quality produce, there were young people on mopeds helping to deliver and cold storage trucks waiting to deliver the boxes. All the people around the produce broke into a big round of applause. Others were giggling at my exuberant clapping... i joked that I’ve got a Grad Dip in Applause! Inside  The building where the food was delivered some rooms felt like Vietnam decor, light green walls, sunlight, potted bamboo and small paintings over the walls. Other rooms felt like Australian decor from the 1970’s, large chunky colourful glazed pottery, against long wooden side tables with dimly lit lamps. A woman was strutting around giving her critique of the interior, I thought her comments were pointless... just observe the differences I thought.... People were celebratory and excited. Another delegation arrived with the female witness. She gingerly stepped through the site and lifted her gaze to see the changes. There was a hush waiting patiently for her to respond, but everyone watched waited for her reaction to unfold.

helping a little girl with a stack of colourful books in a bookshop. She was so happy and was telling me all about the characters. Her mum saw her and was so happy that she had chosen the books and we were enjoying the moment together. Then I left the shop and I was walking through a board room full of young women in business suits, they had just been elected to local council wards. I was happy to see so many women represented. Outside there were many pens set up on a large grassy area filled with dogs, my sister was there amongst the crowds. Then later the dog pens turned into caravans and tents and everyone went to bed. We were given noise cancelling headphones and were told they were only for emergency, we were not to misuse them.

I dreamt that I was trying to navigate this uber rich world and there were all these rules that I was unaware of. Everyday life seemed to be so ridiculously complicated if you weren’t part of that society, just an observer. I was trying to pay for some food and had to go to several counters before my credit card worked. Houses were so grandiose and over sized, lawns immaculate, sprawling balconies and elaborate interiors. Facades spoke of a long history where buildings were modernised over centuries. I was trying to walk away and realised all these homes were built near a site of stunning environmental beauty and significance. Walking on the other side of the houses I found a path out where suburban landscapes were more familiar. I sat down on a brick fence looked up and the tree was full of the most wierd, cute and amazing creatures. I was desperate to take photos for my kids but couldn’t find my mobile. I just looked up and they were all looking back at me, different shapes colours, but all furry, gurgling with big eyes and cute fluffy ears! I was frozen looking at them but realised if I moved to get my mobile they would be scared off.

I had to fly to Iran. There was chaos at the airport my bags weren’t packed properly. I was looking for somewhere to get changed. My family had left on an earlier plane, my partner wasn’t fussed about the whole deal but I was so scared. I had to fly by myself into an unknown country and no visa for entry.

I saw a dog falling from the sky, bound by masses of tape and unable to break free. It was plummeting, rocketing towards the ground much faster than gravity. Behind the dog was a dark storm approaching. The dog looked at me and kept falling, it was terrified.

I had fallen asleep in a house, woke up and realised all the doors and windows were unlocked and there were loud noises and people all around. I felt really unsafe snd locked the house up. I started to cook a meal on this elaborate gas stove twice the size of a normal stove, just marinated tofu. I had spilt flour all over it and was thinking it’ll be do hard to clean afterwards. I was mad with my partner cause he was cooking on a much simpler stove, but I said he wasn’t trying. Then later I was walking to another house and realised every path I wanted to take was problematic, either the water was too deep or road too steep and impassable. People were shouting at me to turn around go back, look for another way. I kept walking down this grassy path trying to find a way.

I dreamt that I could see clearly into my neighbours house across the road. It was dark but I could see her moving around in her garage, then she was on the floor so I was worried she was attacked or dead. So I walked over to see if she was ok, but when I got there, no-one was there, so I let myself inside the storage area of her garage. It felt safe, so I noticed all her boxes snd children’s toys. I saw an old child’s bed, so I put it together and fell into a deep sleep on the bed. Meanwhile her car pulled up in the garage and she entered the main part of the house and started preparing dinner. I was trying to wake myself up, so she wouldn’t find me and get a fright. But I was so sleepy I couldn’t move. Eventually I managed to sneak out and she didn’t see me. I tried to run back home.  But on my way I was lost again, couldn’t get home.  I was with a good friend and a group of strangers walking across sand with lots of crabs and sea creatures, there were owls loudly hooting in the trees. I felt embarrassed that I was in my pyjamas in public.
I was back at work in the office. There was some controversial situation and I seemed to be caught up in it, with piles of work building up, along with the stress.

I remember sitting at a tiny table in a dirty restaurant in a corner. A group of 6 people approached and were trying to be seated. I was trying to explain to them that there was not enough space. It was disgusting and cramped, I was not sure why I was there. No one wore masks or was distancing. Later I was walking through the empty displays at the Royal Melbourne Show.  I found a stall selling shampoo and I was looking at their products. Nothing else was around and there were no people, it was completely abandoned.

I worked for the government and we were announcing grants for the community. We were talking them up saying how much they’ll help the community deal with the pandemic,  but in reality they were useless and everyone was angry.
Cooking, low, cookies.
I have the visuals of both the corn field and the bucket in my dream but not wider context

I had a square fish tank, full of water, fish and gravel. I flipped it on it's back then over once again. It was watertight but the gravel moved and buried some of the fish. The large white one was floating upside down but was still alive. The small tetras were still in the gravel and I tried to dig them out with the end of the tank cleaning sponge which is on a long stick.   It then there was a face in a clear box/container and it was getting smaller and smaller. Somehow this connects to understanding why I have my waking dreams where people are watching me sleep, or shadows retreating in the hallway. It is if the people are my alters and there's a little army of them all looking like little cowboys and indian or army figurines but backlit inside my head.

Tank was at the back of the house but it was made of glass and clear. Our tropicalfish were swimming in it, and their fish food was at back of the tank, sitting on a ledge. It was on the top of it so could have easily walked around to get it but I had to distract the fish and reach over. There was a round cob load so I asked my husband to break it into pieces to give to the fish to distract them. There was at least one penguin in the tank, but it looked like the purple Bank of Melbourne toy penguins.  It kept bobbing at the surface and ducking up when I tried to reach over.
I remeber someone other than myself saying "if you want to become a fully fledged member" and a visual of me cleaning large white buckets and plastic take away containers.

I was in an office. It used to be my office but was now used by Matt. He wasn't there, and I was going through the drawers looking for my stuff which I commented to someone that it had all been left there. I found face masks that were exactly the same as the ones my husband had ordered that day in real life. In my dream I knew that my husband had ordered them and I was surprised to find them there and questioned whether we had doubled up or if they had arrived already.

My brother was about 3 or 4 years old. He put his arms up for me to pick him up and carry him. I picked him up and he had a booger in his nose. I tried to get it as it was at the entrance of his nostril but it was super stretchy and once I got it a few cm away from his nose it snapped back far in. I then picked my nose and it came out like crumbly fetta.

I was looking for a found a large wooden serving board while I was at work.  It was at least 60cm wide, and had a large handle. I found it on a shelf above my eye leavel and had to take it through a crowd by holding it over my head. It had something to do with muffins - maybe that we were going to use it for or had used it for serving muffins. As I walked through one of the doorways it turned into an ocean but it was a straight drop at the door way like as if it was a pool. I was now in the ocean with the board, and it turned into a cylindrical shape like a barrel in kids playgrounds that goes round and round. Gordan Ramsey was in the ocean treading water and asked me if I would be his date for a dinner that evening. It then switched to a restaurant space, and I was at the head of a long table that was seating about 10 people. I was dressed nicely, and Gordon was to my right and about 3 chairs down. Everyone was there for some special event and was super dressed up. This then had another switch and turned into inside a house which I slowly realised in my dream that was my grandmothers house. There were a heap of girls and I was in charge, or leading them. We were looking through the big windows that faced the road and were hiding from something or someone. We had to try and escape without being seen. The windows kind of vanished/morphed into we were just outside the windows and all the girls and I had to run through the trees to get to the road. It felt as if it was in the moonlight as the girls and light were all shinnery and silver. Once we got to the road it was then normal light and there was a car, maybe a ute coming to get us. From the house boundary line someone started shooting at us and I was ducking low screaming at the girls to keep running to the car. I popped my head up and it was my dad shooting. I somehow had a riffle and took 3 shots at Dad but kept missing so gave it to the person next to me and said to shoot. He asked if I was sure and I told him just to shoot him in the hand. Dad seemed relaxed, as did I about the fact that we were shooting and I think at that point I realised it was a dream as the urgency of the situation disappeared.

I had a package that I had to drop off. I was with my mum and sister. The drop off point was the corner my high school was on. Mum or my sister was dealing with the drop off and was on the phone with a DJ who was the one meant to be picking it up. The phone got cut off. The DJ eventually came and got the package.  There was now 3 of us in addition to mum, think it was my brother who joined. We were sitting at a table in front of the school, and teachers kept calling out to us to see if we were okay or what we were doing. I yelled out that we were waiting for mum.  I had the bag that whatever the package was in which was like a big Country Road duffle bag type. There was plastic bags in there as well. My best friend from high school - Bianca was now there. She ducked behind a car to change into a bright red dress but she looked like the actress Caitlin Fitzgerald when she's in Masters of Sex. She was smoothing down her dress especially over her stomch as if she was pregnant. I had to find a plastic bag in my big bag for her to put her change of clothes in. Bianca and I were walking up to the school, and we were starting back there after a significant time away. Not sure if it was actual time away, which would be 15 plus years or if we'd missed just a term. Mum and my sister were back in a car leaving, and hadn't said anything to us so as I waved with a big smile on my face I was sarcastically saying "Have a great first day back girls, hope it's a good day, bye!" and Bianca was laughing as Mum and my sister had no idea that's what I was saying.

I was getting a massage in a room with two massage tables and I was there with someone else I know. Large room, brick walls and benches running along the back of the room. Well lit, and big glass doors. Male massuese. I remeber being in the room getting ready to lie down and a female employee putting a basket of something on the table. Think it was for towels, robes etc. there was something between being standing and then now. I was speaking to the male massuese and I asked where he bases himself, and I knew that I was getting at where he live. Either he or I wanted to make plans for that night. Very sexual tensiony.   Jumps to my bother Andrew, in the same environment but it wasn't a massage place now. Felt like they had packed up. Andrew had a small esky filled with bottles of Great Northern.   We were discussing dad going on holidays by himself. Think my other siblings joined us at that point. (another brother and 1 sister). He was planning or was already on holidays in Mexico. Jumped to me being the one that was going on holidays and I was buying/had bought a new set of headphones even though I already had a set.
