Dad was there and was telling me off saying I shouldn't be spending money right now. The headphones had coloured attachements that looked like the flat lids of highlighters and in all those colours.

I was in the car with mum and we were driving to Morwell. She took the furtherest exit and then once we were in she looped almost all the way back up so she easily could have taken the middle exit. We had to see the Nardones as they were doing some printing for us.  We got to a place that looked like dads school. I was sitting at the end of this large inside space, at a trestle table that was like the top of a T with another long table. I was speaking to an Asian man and he said he couldn't do the bulk printing I needed as his English wasn't great and my stuff needed attention to detail. I called over to mum and Kat who were sitting next to each other half way down the long table. I was asking what we actually needed to get printed/if we really needed to get things printed. Kat rolled her eyes and had a bit of a go at me saying "of course you don't need printing, and table decorations "  as if I was putting down her choices. I knew that I already had candles maybe as the place name holders and didn't think we needed a ceremony printout. I knew it was a religious ceremony as the printout was going to have the prayers of the faithful in there. I became aware that this space was a restaurant, and I had a feeling that my sister Kat worked there but she wasn't working now. I had ordered a steak, but was annoyed as I hadn't been asked how I would like it cooked. I was with my other siblings on the table, an they had ordered lentils or something similar looking that came out in little stacks on a plate, as if they'd been unmoulded. They were eating this with their hands. Kat was now speaking to the staff at the neighboring shop which was a book store. The two staff working at our venue had to go to the back through a coutyard and secure things as there was a storm coming. I remember seeing washing hanging on a line across this courtyard. There were tons of old school sports tube socks. The staff had to secure black plastic that was flapping in the wind. The rain started which I could see running down the large window behind our table.   it was more senses than visual. It was the same space, but I think we were all laying on the floor with doonas and sleeping bags etc. Felt like a party in your late teens/early twenties where you all crash at someones house. I remember having sex with someone, but only the feeling. It was spooning, and he was behind me. I have the feeling of him pushing inside me and then the angle changed and he couldn't get back inside me. That sensation was now missing and I could still feel it and was trying to get him back in frantically.   I was at a big function space, but back in Melbourne. It had pews like a church. I was thinking about how I'd have to set it up and how much access we had prior as I had to get ready in between. This felt like a wedding but with the fight I was having with my mum I was thinking "this is overboard, it's not even a wedding".

I was with Jason in a store. It wasn't a bookstore, more like a homeware, gift, knick knacks place but there was one shelf full of books. We were looking at the new Yotam Ottolenghi cook book. Jason pulled it off the shelf and it was the distinctive onion on the front cover.  I walked into an adjacent room and was looking up as there used to be a way for you to drink water that came down from the ceiling. I was hunting for something like an old school lamp or fan chain that you pull to turn it on.   - I was examining a square of mesh, that you could see through one way only.   - I was walking around at Dad's place, looking for somewhere quiet to masterbate but found no where.   - I was on the landing of a building at uni that I used to work in. I was telling someone that there was another toilet further upstairs.   - The usual wake up confusion with the shadows from the skylight looking like people in our hallway.

I was at work. My 2 bosses were there, asking me to read a print off of something and asking me what was wrong with it. The text was super small, then I realised that it was a black sheet with white writing rather than the usual black writing on white, and because it was a photocopy rather than a print its clarity was the reason the text appeared too small. One boss was asking me how to reverse it on the photo copier and I was hunting through the settings menus knowing that I'd seen the right setting before. It then jumped ahead and I was still in the same place, but talking to our head chef. I remember being seated at a low table with her and we were talking about something semi serious work related but I can't remember what specifically.

Brown water, like a muddy dam. I was jumping in, and sending a best friend off for he day in a boat   The bown water now had a rock wall breaker on either side, like going into a mariner channel. It was a festive fun day out, everyone sitting on the rocks with deck chairs on the opposite side and brightly coloured umbrellas and towels. I was sitting on one side, a person to my left, and then the person sitting to her left was dark purple and black. On the opposite bank was mostly older people in their 60's and 70's. One of those ladies was trying to figure out if purple person was a guy or a girl. We could see her trying to be subtle and pointing in our direction to her neighbour. They were gossiping. This was happening at the same time as purple girl was trying to count how many of them there were on the old side. I told her to stop, I was laughing and told her what they were trying to do.   One of the ladies was Jenny. She wanted to go home and I was ready to leave. Can't remember if I or someone else told her that I'd take her home. I was getting my things together and had to jump back into the water. Once I was in the water I suddenly was back on the rocks, and big fresh blue ocean waves were rolling in from behind me. I could see them coming in the reflection of a window, like a big shop front window, so I could prepare myself each time. I was still sitting, and had my fingers latched onto something and in the dream I was thinking I should hold onto something else because my fingers would snap if I got swept off the rocks. As these waves cme over me they turned into a tunnel around my body. I felt anxious as I wasn't sure how to time it to start holding my breath. I knew I should leave it til the last moment so I had less time to hold it but I was scared of leaving it too late and the wave engulfing me.   The waves stopped. I was now wearing a green dress. I jumped, like a dive in, but it didn't go like a normal dive and I kind of floated down to meet the water like when you try and throw something light like a tissue or feather. There was the push of the leap, but it didn't equate to any force hitting the water, and when I did I didn't go in properly as if my dress was buoyant and wasn't letting me go in.   By this time Debbie had already walked back to the wherever/whatever was at the end of the marina channel, maybe a car park and had gone home. Jason was there with me and said that she'd gone home. he said her husband had been there and taken her. In the dream I didn't see the husband and Jason didn't use his name but I knew it was David. Jason made a comment about him. I can't remember what It was but it was equally nasty and nice. Something like "Despite what he looks like he can be a good husband". It was odd as David wasn't there at the beach/lake but turned up by accident at just the right place and time to take Jenny home.

There was a group of people, maybe via zoom/facetime etc. I knew I was part of this group but I didn't see them. We were going around the outside of a house and we're taking turns voting on something that seemed to be very important.  it's like you're doing something very important and should have been listening but for some reason I've missed the start when I've been explained to what is happening or what I need to do. I'm uneasy because I know I should know what's going on but don't want to let 'them' know that I have no idea.   We were voting, and I was voting on behalf of Australia in this group of people.  The shadows and light from the skylight had me convinced that was the office or computer screen that the voice was coming from who was in charge of this voting. I moved my hand and this caused me to accidentally vote twice. The person in charge told Australia/me off because I'd not voted properly and this is where I felt uneasy because I hadn't realised that the hand gesture meant a vote.

I was in an open, airy restaurant/bar with an actor who looked like Kevin from Backstreet boys. He was upset, and I think I was his employee in some way as I was in charge of looking after him. There was some heavy talk and he wanted to go to his room so it must have been a hotel. The waiter/staff runs out to stop us and I explain that we're taking the rest of his plate of food u to his room. I asked for the bill or it was given to me, but it was in a green diary/daily planner. We got to the steps of the restaurant and Kevin/nameless actor took the bill from me but someone behind us said that he shouldn't look in there as the staff had written some pretty negative reviews about him. / This was like a memory scene on TV where it's narrated. Kevin was complaining that the scene he got negative reviews about was hard because he and his co star Jennifer Anniston had to do a sex scene straight away. The visual was he and Jennifer on a large corner balcony at night rehearsing for this scene and they were dancing, but it was them individually doing almost a waltz and crossing each other as they practised. I was very anxious as it was my job to look after him.

I woke up and instinctively knew that I was being watched. I was sleeping topless and I rolled over and got further under the doona so they couldn't see my breasts. Once I was over and adjusting my pillow I had the ah ha moment and rolled back onto my back and went back to sleep unworried.   It's always an uneasy feeling. It's not towards them however, but a guilty feeling. It's like I should know what they are doing but I wasn't paying attention when it was being explained and now I'm trying to catch up without revealing that that I was being rude and not listening.

I remember being in water with 2 little girls about 4 years old who were Asian - maybe Thai or Korean. They were one on either side of me, and were struggling but I didn't seem to think they were in much danger. Maybe a wave pool where the water comes and goes rather than an ocean or deep pool. I had string on my foot so kind of kicked my foot out to the girl on my right so I could drag her back to me. Got her, and grabbed the other one and they were both fine.

Precocious little children. I was going through a box of old photos and towards the bottom of the pile there was a photo of little girl of about 3 or 4yo with wild unkempt matted blonde hair and dressed in colourful three piece ensemble. Flared pants and and overdress. I knew it wasn’t right because of the era that the photo was taken. It should have been black and white and she should have on clothes that suite the time. The subject of the photo started moving, like those Harry Potter paintings and I knew instantly that she was the right one for my (it felt like I was making a movie or needed her for something). Someone removed her overdress and was going to change her outfit and I insisted that the she stay the same. My friends Alanna and John from Queensland turned up and we were going to drive somewhere. John in a separate car to Alanna and I. I told them about the photo and the child and I think we were going to collect her?

I appeared to be in an outdoor truck stop. There were rows of stalls selling food and an open dirt area of ground. I think our car was being filled with fuel. I was wandering around with my friend - don’t know who it was but I think it was a girlfriend. A guy approached me to ask directions. He had a bag slung over his shoulder and he was his mobile phone. He ask about number 101 and where it was. I looked up and down the street and then asked what was he looking for and he said it was an insurance office. I suggested we look at the map on the his phone but I needed some reading glasses to see it clearly. He dug around in his bag and pulled out a large plastic syringe - it was filled with black solution. I recognised it as a drug and said to my friend and kind of to him too, “its bong water and really dark “ with the inference that it was good quality. Apparently the reading glasses were somehow in or attached to this? And he had to empty the contents to get at them...He went into the road house. Next we were inside a room together in a separate area - not the road house. It was an office space with carpeted floors and and tables and chairs. The were a bank of windows covered in white sheer curtaining/blinds that slid sideways. The sun was glaring and coming through. The guy was sliding the blinds to try and block our the glare. I looked up at his face and it was tanned and rugged but not handsome, I didn’t know him. One of the windows was slightly ajar and was letting in a cool breeze. I said it was lovely and fresh but my friend was cold and shifted herself away from the gap and turned her back. There were stacks of files and paperwork all over the table and we were there to help him find something in them. My friend who had her back us was attaching tubes  to her nipples and the when the guy walked in he kind of acknowledged this but ignored her and walked behind. We were back in front of the stalls and and woman was at the counter. She was tall and masculine and wearing bikers boots and had a jacket over her arm. I said to the guy that I recognised here and he confirmed he did too and that she was the chef/bar attendant from the bowling club but it was now permanently closed and she was unemployed.

I opened a wooden door to enter a foyer where another wooden door was closed. Both the doors were old and dark wood and shabby. The second door opened onto a large open room with high ceilings. It was a waiting room for a doctors surgery.The were some chairs and people sitting and standing. On top top of a small podium there was a sign in book and a lady was standing next to it. She seem to be over seeing the signing in process. She had next to the book a pile of undies. Small bikini bottoms with coloured graphics printed on them. Along the top edge, across the back of each pair, there was some kind of slogan. Mostly to do with porn. I picked them up to look. I moved over to the main desk which was shoulder high. There was another lady there with another sign in book. There was someone in front of me. I looked at the counter and to the left there was a medallion of meat. It was pale and surrounded by a ring of thin fat. I said it looked like a lean piece of pork. Then I noticed to the right that there was an open packet where it had come from and the barcode and words said pork.

I was tossing my shopping, all loose paper bags of product on the seat of a car. Next thing I was in the passenger seat and my ex from 6 years ago was driving. He’d picked me up and we were driving home. But home was my family home from my childhood. There was a woman standing in the middle of the road. Dressed in black with long blond hair, I was prompted to say to him, something like, “Did you call Lisa this morning?” I said yes, and I asked why he did and what he wanted. I just said “you love her and want to be with her” he looked forlorn and nodded. Then I asked did he want to try and and sort things out and work on being with me. He nodded silently and I said we don’t have to go home yet and drove past my old house.

Starting outside at some event. It was evening and we were all getting ready to go back to a house. There was a Dutch? couple with a little child. A young man in his 20s and a younger boy. They were not related.There was food and I was with the young man watching him eat. He seemed a little drunk like we we had been at a party or something. He was sitting on some kind seat that had a round white table attached. He was naked and the table top was hiding his lower half but it had tilted up and bottom half was exposed. When I looked down at him his genitals were blurred out. He wasn’t concerned and we talked about where he would stay at the house. We all ended up at this big many roomed house that appeared to be a permanent residence I was familiar with. The asked the boy to change his sheets on his bed so the young guy could sleep there. It was really messy. The couple with the child appeared and I asked the little girl would she like to draw. I took her by the hand and we went in search of a jar of textas and pens and pencils I knew I had. But when I got there they were missing and I yelled out to someone to ask where they were and he said he’d lent them. I was annoyed. I was then in the bottom of an empty swimming pool with a sloping side. I was trying to lift the little girl who was now naked up to her parents but as much as I tried I couldn’t get her past the edge and they couldn’t reach her. No one was concerned.  I remember being inside a room looking out at a deck and some trees. There were two pigeon/dove type birds as large as chickens moving about in the branches. They were extremely bright and colourful lots of rainbow colours. One bird had its tail feathers all fanned out and it was beautiful. It seemed to be trying to attract the other bird. They came down on to the deck and one came through to the door into the house. I called for my partner to come and look at how beautiful they were but the birds wouldn’t put on the display. I thought if a scratched in on the back near its tail it may spread its feathers. I was rubbing and scratching its tail but the bird had turned into a naked woman on all fours and I was rubbing her tail bone.

I was at a pub and there were many people in the dining room part. I seemed to be alone, my friend having left earlier. Don’t know who he was but I think that he was extremely drunk and I worked out that he actually drove himself home. I saw another friend there and went over to say hi. It was a lovely warm encounter. Ben hugged me and we left the pub in a warm, friendly arm in arm embrace. Nothing romantic. Just friends. Laughing and chatting about having something sweet to eat and cup of tea at his place. Our houses were close to the pub, as was the other guys house who left early. We walked by there to check if he got home and that’s when we saw his car. He’d been putting together /building a coffee table of sorts for his wife and we were looking at outside the house.It was pretty shonky and looked like one those slot together pre cut things. We went inside. Next thing I was in bed and next to me was another old friend, Robert. He was groggy and half asleep. But got out of bed and was naked. He pulled on a pair of black socks before heading to the bathroom... I then was in my mum’s house in the middle room. I was trying to sleep on a makeshift bed on the floor. There was someone else with me and I knew that there were many other people asleep in the rumpus room a couple of rooms away. I knew that my mum was out there too. I hear a car pull up in the driveway and said to my friend that it was my cousins with all the children. They were noisy. I looked at the time and it was midnight. Shocked that they turned up and expected to stay. They came in the house and kids were noisy and went and woke everyone out in the room. I was worried for my mum.I tried to ask them to be a quiet.

I found a baby seal. Not too sure about if it was a seal though. It was small. Arms cradling size. Grey and brown smooth and silky skin/fur. It could move around easily but seem to have no legs.It had no teeth. I know because I put my finger in its mouth and it sucked on it. All pink and gummy. There were other people in a the house were I was living but I even though I had a relationship to them, I don’t know who they were. The home was a facsimile of my family home. The little seal needed to be wet occasionally but I knew it wasn’t crucial. He got into the bathtub. I had to go away and needed someone to care for him for a few days. I knew that my neighbours would probably do it but had to go and see them. I left the seal in the house and went next door. My neighbours were my actual old neighbours from 20 years ago. Phil and Sue. Their daughter Megan was there too she was the age she would have been 20years ago. They were busily doing jobs and huffing and puffing at each in frustration and not really speaking. It was a bit awkward to ask. But I sat and talked to them for a bit. Then the seal was there and Sue said that Phil didn’t like them. Especially their mouths? There was a big kitchen island bench with shelves below and the was a plate with cat biscuits spilling over. The seal started trying to eat them and I got down on my hands and knees and  tried to clean them and stop him from eating them. I then found myself in front of a closed door that was supposed to be a pub or some kind of venue. I had a brown paper ticket in my hand that was printed with some offer and I was going to redeem it at the pub. There were three men standing outside, waiting too. We all though the place was closed but I opened the door and the pushed another door with my knee to swing it open (conscious that I didn’t want to touch the door with my hand). Inside were hundreds of people sitting at long wooden tables. It was kind of like a theatre restaurant and they were all brandishing large shiny knives. They were all wearing black face masks. These  people were on the left side of the room and on the right were large chunky wooden tables that were empty and had nothing on them. I ran and jumped on top and tried to slide on my butt towards the bar. The table wasn’t slippery enough and I got stuck just before the end. A bar maid came to me and said to get off that I wasn’t allowed to do that. She kind of half smiled at my antics. I gave her the ticket in my hand and she read it and laughed and showed the other barmaids. It apparently was an offer that didn’t start for another year. She threw it away. There was a master of ceremonies who was yelling instructions and everyone stood up with their big knives and swung them at the same time to cut something on their plates. I then remembered I didn’t have a face mask. There were other people walking around and I noticed a lady pushing a pram. She had a nurse’s outfit and there was a mask hanging from badge/pin/watch on the front of here clothes. I looked towards the door and now it was glass. There were many people trying to get in and there was a man giving out black face masks. There was one policeman who pushed past him, intent on getting inside. I knew he would fine me for not having a mask. So I found the nurse and lent over and hooked the mask from her chest. I put it on in such a hurry that it twisted-upside down and inside out. I turned around to face the policeman and mumbled  and kind of laughed my clumsiness. He looked at me and with a sad smile and said his name. He said “it’s me ??” And I knew him. He held me and kissed me very gently but firmly on the lips. I could feel his face and skin that was bristly. My left nipple went stiff and he brushed it. He said something about the seal being missing and I got very upset and started crying. My head pushed into his shoulder and left ear. I said I love him so much. He hugged me and said he knew.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: Espionage. I was sitting at an outdoor cafe in another country with a group of people. We were there to gather information, I think. I had a camera/phone that could take images of things not seen with the eye. I was trying to take a photo of the scene away from the cafe out towards what we said were the pyramids. The left side of the screen was not in focus and was showing something that wasn’t physically there. Among the trees was something mysterious and I felt that it was slightly scary. I kept trying to focus it and I think it worked.

I was with my friend Alanna. We were in a field on a lake. There were many people and some I seemed to know. It was some kind of celebration, like a community picnic.We were part of this group and there were other groups set up beside the lake.The terrain was typical grazing land and there were some fences and the ground was uneven - no flat areas. Next thing Alanna and I were back at a hotel where we were staying the night - it was a two day event. We were going to go out but we were both tired. I fell asleep on the end of one of the beds with pillows stacked around me. I awoke  and looked out the window to see a biplane flying low and dragging behind a banner. There were other aircraft doing similar things. Even a helicopter towing something too. It was really early but we decided to walk back to  picnic ground. I was wearing cut off denim shorts and an old blue  t-shirt with no bra. I had strappy flat sandals on my feet. I remember it being really hot as we walked along the street and into the paddock. I kept adjusting my shorts and pulling at the legs to pull them down as they were a bit tight. We passed other groups all set up for the day’s activities. It had the feeling of a competition or event. I was concerned about not wearing a bra but I kept skipping and hopping through the rough paddock grass.I seemed to be a lot younger. Alanna said something about me being capable of playing basketball even though I wasn’t tall enough. We arrived at ‘our’ patch and there was no one there. It was too early for them. Then Robert arrived and other people slowly started to turn up. I really wanted to get changed and have a shower so Robert decided to walk back with and Alanna stayed. A young guy in burgundy -very short- shorts and sleeveless tshirt walked across in front of us.He was blonde and thin and walked with an arrogant confidence. Robert said that was “Spencer”. We walked up a rise to a track and followed the dirt trail.To our left and up on a little rise there were some boys  on a flat trolley/barge  that was laden with boxes and supplies. One boy was rowing the thing to propel it along the ridge but there was a drop off coming up and he didn’t slow down even though I shouted to stop. The wheels went over the edge and tore off the front boards of the trolley. The kid was really angry and started pulling off the broken bits and flinging them into the grass.I could see the wheels underneath. We decided to keep walking past.

I was in a huge metal shed. It had a really high domed roof. There was a loud crashing of a storm and large amount of rain dumped in one big crash on the roof. There were many animated bright blue creatures in the front on the shed and they were moving. After the crash they were all lying on the ground. It was kind of like one those sheds where refugees are temporarily house.

I was in the ocean. It was big,expansive, black and heaving. No white wash, just a huge swell. There are other people with me, but I don’t know who they are. We are talking about the Chinese and some illegal activities that they are doing. I said to someone “do you know how many car bodies are at the bottom of the ocean?” We weren’t struggling in the ocean, we were kind of bobbing and riding the swell, up and down. There were other people in another cluster a bit further away and a friend was in the group. He yelled to me that he had let go of the camera and the way the swell was moving, meant that it would float passed me. I was watching for it and saw a red strap coming in my direction, but out of reach. I tried to tread water and push toward it to grab the strap but the swell was too powerful and I couldn’t reach it. I knew that it would come back towards us on the next heave of the waves, so I wasn’t too concerned. The ocean was really black and an unnatural wave was building up over to our right and it rose up a few metres in a long line - no peak or white wash just a big wall of water. I was on top of huge heaving swell watching it curling up and moving toward us. It didn’t smash into us, it just merged with the swell that we were in. No one panicked or struggled.

I was with my mum and dad at the family home. We were preparing to leave. Next thing I was in a store like a big hardware store and in the centre isle the was a display of tall - 3mt high - cauliflowers and broccoli. They were displayed standing in a bucket and on top of the long stalks were the head of the vegetable. I picked out two and checked the heads. The sign said they were $2.50 ea. I took them back to mum and dad’s.  Mum was asking questions about something and she was agitated and being quite forthright.

I was painting a room. Rushing to get it done for some reason. It was only painted down to about a metre from the ground. The was protective plastic taped up all around and splatters of paint everywhere. Someone came to take me to a night club but said that there had been a fight. Two young guys had had a vicious punch up. One guy was a handsome tall slim Arab Muslim called Cain and we seemed to know him because I commented something about his temper getting him into trouble and not being able to control it. I was back in the paining room and there was new pale blue carpet on the floor. I was a bit annoyed as I hadn’t finished paining and this meant it would take longer because I had to be careful not to get paint on the carpet. I knew I had promised to go to dinner at and people were waiting for me. It was 9pm and the phone rang. It was a old landline style phone and when I picked it up I knew it would be Sue my old next door neighbour from 30 years ago but the voice was my sister. She asked was I still coming to dinner as it was so late.

I was with a man - he was a kind of amalgamation of a few partners I’ve had. He offered to massage my back and he kind of rubbed it a little and squeezed and stopped. Very unsatisfactory and quite useless. It turned out he was also not good at other things. There were lots of plants in the house and all needed watering. I filled up a bottle and was watering a few that were in a flat display tray. It had little notches on the edges and as the water filled the plants it overflowed into the tray and quickly rose to spill out the notches. I used the bottle and dipped it into the water to try and remove some water before it made a mess.

I think I was in the back of my family home. The rooms were all slightly different and the configuration was wrong, but it felt like the home. I could hear a small scuffling and fluttering sound coming from another room and went to investigate. There were two peewee pecking and attacking something. When I bent down they flew away and there was a small blue and green budgie. It crouched down and allowed me to pick it up. It was very scared but seemed to be uninjured. I shouted to someone to get the old cage from outside. They appeared with a bird cage that used to be pale blue, but the paint was mostly gone and the rust was taking over. I opened the lift up door at the front and put the budgie through the opening. It immediately hopped up on the rusty swing that was in the centre of the cage. I found two of the food and water dishes that hook over the bars of the cage. They were filthy and full of old food. I started to clean and wash them, but they morphed into large stainless steel dog bowls that were covered in bird poo. I ran them under really hot water and they cleaned up, shiny and bright.

I was at my house and emus were looking in the window Playing an iOS game set in a museum, where you needed to save points or money to fix holes, open galleries etc - the museum was closed to the public and so there little income - I made some tweak to get enough points to close a hole in the roof, then closed the game for a while to let my points build up again over time

I had to a film a presentation for work, which involved actually going on site and into the collection store. I had to log into a security system and enter codes to the coin store remotely. I got some coins out for the presentation, and then recorded something - but watching it back I could see how it could be improved, parts to rephrase or leave out etc to make it better (e.g. I'd used some footage from a colleague from a previous workplace, using a big chunky mechanical stitching foot to sew baskets onto their display supports - the stitching foot squashed the top of the basket briefly as it pressed down so it wasn't really a great method and shouldn't be promoted). Plus I thought I hadn't expressed the benefits vs risks of displaying objects well enough, so that people watching would be able to make an informed decision. But then a textiles conservator showed up (two, actually - one a current colleague and one I'm not sure about) and said they would record the presentation instead. Also they had a kit of storage and display props that showed mounting methods for textiles really well - much better than what I'd used. So that was very good, button I was wondering about what to do about the coins, which shouldn't be left with 'unauthorised' staff. The coin store was also still open so the coins could be put away after filming. I wondered if I should close the store and leave the coins with the two conservators, but decided I needed to stay for the filming and lock the coins away properly afterwards. Then a security guard used the same remote security log in system to open the coin store remotely, knowing he'd be onsite later while a big stadium rock concert was on. So while he was on site the guard snuck up to the store, which was now unlocked, and stole things - though it seemed more like software and not coins after all. Also the software was on old three and a half inch floppy disks. The guard slipped out with the crow as they left the gig. The gig-goers also took software as they left, from an unattended table that seemed to be full of free merchandise. There were also free straw hats on the table. Then I was back in the collection store, eating pad thai. Food isn't allowed in collection stores normally but this didn't seem to worry me. As I was finishing the meal I realised there was a disposable nitrile glove caught up in the food, which I'd nearly put in my mouth. I put it in the bin.

I was back in the shareed house I lived in in Norwood, Adelaide - I'd 'interviewed' someone as a new flatmate but my other flatmate was still out. I liked the person I'd interviewed and was going to give him the keys but then thought oops I should let my friend meet him first.  Then there was an announcement on the radio that an earthquake was 20 minutes away so we all went out to sit on the grass in the backyard. There were four of us - me, the new flatmate and two of his friends, a woman and a teenager. Someone brought a mosquito net with us.  The garden was looking both chaotic and lush - lots of vegetables growing. Bindies and prickles were growing in the lawn - some of them in narrow rows, a bit like they'd been sowed properly but I had an idea the rows were made by something scratching or dragging across the dirt and they'd just settled in the furrows. The old lemon tree was still big and gnarled. The new flatmate was involved in music biz and had light brown skin. The three of them were talking about a song. The teenager started to tell me something about it quite earnestly, implying I would know this thing 'if I was older than 18', which I assured him I was, and we all laughed a bit because I am obviously older than 18 but he'd seemed not to notice. The thing I should know at my age was that if I worked in a museum I should have to sing his song in front of a mammoth specimen - I said I already did work at a museum and I hadn't thought to do this. The woman still wouldn't tell me why we needed the netting. Then the Manager of the Museum called me from work and said things were pretty rough and could I come in to either work in Dispatch or stand guard in front of the 'Wiggles poster'. I asked what was involved and he got all annoyed and said he had no time to explain and reiterated help was needed. I said sure, I'll come and help at Dispatch and hung up on him before he'd finished speaking. As I was getting ready I realised I hadn't asked if this would be paid overtime. It wasn't clear if the issues at the Museum were connected to the expected earthquake.

I was running along the top of a cliff by the sea - on a path - assessing the safety of it and discussing this with someone At my grandparents' old houseman Olympic running event had been set up inside, kind of an obstacle course going through number of rooms and hallways. I remember thinking that there was a decent chance that the most previously unlikely of things could happen - I could win an Olympic running race I was singing something at the same time (quite well, I was very pleased with my pitch and tone) - and as I walked the 'course' I glanced briefly into an unfamiliar room I didn't remember, off the hall with the bedrooms and study - there were two strange men wearing coveralls sitting in there - I wasn't alarmed by this, I knew they were meant to be here and they didn't seem hostile - but I was briefly self-conscious that they'd heard me singing. Then I was trying to manoeuvre a tall, triangular-shaped box through the crowded aisles of an Asian grocery - I kept stopping to let people pass, or wait for them to move etc - but eventually I just kind of pushed my way through, around the end of one aisle and into the next, and people had to stop for me because the box I had was so big. I laid it down on its side under the glass doors of the frozen or cold storage area - it's highest point fitted 'just so' under the door so it didn't prevent them from opening and explained this to a few people as I opened it up briefly to show it held many partially eaten containers of ice-cream flavours. Then I left quickly before anyone could protest. I noticed my hair was getting very long but I thought it looked quite good, from what I could see of myself in Zoom calls - it was curling under at the ends instead of sticking out. Then I was back at an old workplace and one of my old colleagues who's usually quite lovely was being very snarky comments about my old boss and where she'd put a couple of trollies. I was a bit worried she was losing her marbles. Tidying up in the labs, someone else opened a cupboard and saw an old jar of yellowed resin and just tossed it straight in the bin - I was slightly in awe because I'd been dithering about whether I should throw it out and the proper way to dispose of it and she just DID it. I was kind of relieved, and vaguely surprised she could act so decisively. Then I was looking through some old notes of mine one of them had found - possibly old plans or notes for a talk, and some colour photocopies of pictures of family members that looked as if I'd laid them out so I could draw around them to make a calendar for my grandmother. I threw them out and wondered why they'd saved them for so long instead of just throwing them out themselves. Someone saw me looking through the old photos and came over to look at them over my shoulder, which I thought was very nosy and I wished the wouldn't, also they weren't very good photos. I didn't say that though. Some of them seemed to date to the birth of a friend's baby several years ago but they still looked like a baby now.

Ben Mendelsohn was on a car that had been ejected up into the sky and was falling back to earth. It landed on top of a tall building in the middle of a city and blew up. But then we saw scenes from a different angle, before the impact, where he had put his hand through the driver's seat window to activate the airbags. At first it looked like it was just the fact of having an airbag underneath him (but with the car's roof in between) that saved him during impact, which I thought was pretty lame and unlikely, so then it altered again to show that he'd somehow managed to pull the air bag out and use it as a parachute to steer himself away from the car as it fell and to land safely on top of another building. The car might have been a helicopter now? Anyway it still crashed.  Then my friend Kate, one of my aunts (Sue) and my Mum were appointed temporary 'royalty' at an event with lots of people. Two bakers wheeled in two cakes and asked which one they'd like to try first - the plum cake or the pumpkin pie cake. They dithered a bit so the head baker made an executive decision and served the pumpkin pie cake, which they declared was delicious and ate enthusiastically.  A little snippet remains of me talking to my sister and taking a sample of red wine from her barrel. It was only 9:15am though and I thought 'uh oh is this the slippery slope I'm starting on, drinking in the morning' plus also my Mum was around somewhere and I thought she'd see and disapprove.

I was on site at my real home, while the renovations were in progress. The builder had found some problem and was calling an expert to come and look at it urgently - I think it was structural. There was some problem with the fences also - they pushed over an old fence to hold up another old fence from behind while they worked on the other side. I was expecting a delivery of some kind - stuff for the renovation - but the builder said HE wasn't expecting anything - I got a bit made because I'd had the schedule from them (the builders) and had been following it, and it had a delivery marked on this day (a Friday). Then I was talking to elderly neighbours about some issue that seemed related, so we all went over to look their place - they had a complicated set up in their (large and spacious) roof cavity for a security system - it involved a dedicated iMac and some video cameras. Somehow we created a static electricity charge that traveled around the wiring for the system, with a blue glow. It was strange - the builders had never seen anything like it before - and also bad, in that it wasn't something that was supposed to happen and indicated a problem. Aside, I was talking to another person about the elderly couple, who were reclusive and paranoid. But the wife had struck up a relationship with another neighbour and they chatted often over the fence. The couple had taken the opportunity of having specialists on site to ask about their issue.

I was talking to someone who was going overseas (the UK?) about how they’d have to stay in quarantine for two weeks—where they’d stay, whether they’d be ok etc  In an antique shop full of fantastic pieces of furniture—wardrobe innards and shelving that seemed a bit Tudor era, solid and large and complex. I was sad because I wanted to buy one but couldn’t ship them back home My belongings were all caught up in the branches of a really big tree? As if a flood had carried them past and they’d got stuck? Though I was pointing out one box-shaped object (an old cathode ray tv?) and noting it had moved branches—so it proved SOMETHING had happened but it must have already been there

I was setting up a treasure hunt for a friend's younger son - it was dinosaur-themed. The hunt started with a zine that was pinned to a post in a grassy strip of land between two sides of a residential street. If you read the zine there were instructions to find the next clue. I think there were four clues all up and I was trying to figure out the last one - deciding perhaps I'd post something to be waiting at his own house. The penultimate clue led to a place that was quite remote though - down a dirt road out of town - I'd been there already and also left a litre for milk there for some reason - and I need to get back to place the written clue to the final destination. I was trying to finish but my sister came along and said Leigh Sales wanted to talk to us about something and I didn't tell I could say no - so I started getting stressed about finishing in time. I was also talking myself into leaving what I'd done so far in the form it was in - I could see a better way of drawing/presenting it but now I didn't have the time to re-do it. I kind of stomped off in a bad-natured way with my sister to find Leigh Sales, past an office that my workplaces' HR manager was in. So now we were at my workplace, which had an audiovisual display set up to play short films by Indigenous film makers. As I left that space I passed a display that was something to do with Ned Kelly, which the HR manager was standing next to - he asked what I thought about Ned and a plan we had about doing something about Ned at the museum and I launched into my Ned Kelly rant from my previous workplace - "Ned Ned Ned, always Ned, why do we even have his armour here, we're a library, also he was a murderer"

I got out of my car, which was parked in the street - there was a man lying on his back with is arm flung out. He looked like he was pointing across the street to something else. Or was he sleeping/dead? If you followed his hand, he was pointing at a building with four big rectangular cement blocks, which had been cast above a doorway and were still drying. (A two by two grid, short ends parallel with the ground). A wooden plank sat underneath them, holding them up. It was bowing just a little in the middle. I pointed this out to my companion just as people above these blocks (in a flat) started to have a massive fight. I'd been thinking it would be interesting to watch the blocks fall but now there was a second thing to watch, though I didn't quite like to. Then, I was in a boat or maybe a rocket ship - watching another ship (owned by the government) founder or get into trouble on the bay. The captain of our vessel decided to go and help them even though technically they could arrest us. He pulled up alongside and went in. The ship was a long tube on an angle, with people strapped into chairs, looking a bit wrecked. We found their captain and siphoned some of our oil into their supply (using two very narrow flexible plastic tubes). The two oils were slightly different (one of them was darker and thicker) and we were a bit worried it would cause more problems, but their captain was able to get the ship going again so they could get proper help - and also very honourably didn't try and detain or arrest us, for which we were thankful. I was looking for a cat in a garden.

I was in a store looking for things I needed to buy for the renovation (kitchen and bathroom fixtures etc) - I started to talking to the shop owner, and I could tell he was disappointed I already knew what I wanted and was just looking for the best prices The shop owner somehow had an email response I'd sent previously in answer to a questionnaire - he figured out it was me from my name and the email address - and made a note of it to link the two queries (email and in person). Then he connected it to another query he'd had from someone who lived in a street in Werribee where I used to live as a child - and I exclaimed 'oh I used to live there!'. This query related to a subscription service that was offered for kitten and cat owners, I think where you were sent monthly supplies (food etc) and included benefits like checkups etc. I confessed to him I WAS interested in the deal - I thought it was good value - but I didn't sign up for it at the time because I was feeling cheap. Then I was looking at a dance routine I'd recorded of myself, and thinking I should save it to my phone (maybe for TikTok?). I was imitating a 'known' routine. Now in a lab - and playing with an overhead fixture that allowed you to 'mist' your work surface (you could control the water flow and pressure, this was the lightest setting but you could make it rain if you wanted to). This was annoying the people I was working with. Some Soviets came by and objected to a cap one of us was wearing - one of our party knew this was because the cap 'presented' as Polish but was made from a Soviet cap that they'd put a bit of plastic decoration on (the use of plastic was very insulting to the Soviets, so the Polish made all their caps this way). It seemed to have a pull string fitted - when you pulled it a recorded voice said something.  Then I was in a house, I think my sister's, which was linked to the house of a couple who she doesn't like (and who aren't very nice). We walked through their house to get to one of the living areas, which was a big room set up for building with LEGO. We might have been looking for someone there? Next, a professional of some kind was proposing to treat someone's ear condition by using a Stanley knife (but cutting something in their ear canal). I was horrified and offered them one of my scalpels, which they accepted - but then I had to go into a filthy, cluttered garage to fetch out by toolkit. The garage was full of old crap - a car, a grotty mattress etc. Somehow a quote I'd prepared at a previous workplace came back to me in my current job at the Museum. The client wanted me to write them a Conservation Management Plan for a small museum, and my quote had been based on not being able to visit the museum in question - I'd have to base my recommendation on their notes and pictures. I originally thought they'd only sent me a couple of pages which wasn't going to be nearly enough, but I flipped through the notebook they'd sent again and it was full of observations, details and pictures. I was pleased because it would be a really straightforward job and I'd be able earn $2000 for my museum. Then I was leaving somewhere and went to the toilet - another person came into the toilet with me to talk on their phone and the cubicles weren't really separated from each other properly - no doors. So she could hear me going to the toilet - but she flushed hers to make some disguising noise, which was thoughtful of her. My toilet had no seat and the toilet roll holder was in the way of where you sat, plus the whole back window was made of regular window glass so there was nothing to stop anyone from looking in PLUS I totally undressed before I sat down. I tore up some strips of spongy fabric that just happened to be lying around to put over the rim of the bowl before I sat on it. None of this repulsed me or made me anxious as much as I expected - I was just kind of resigned.

A new education entrance was under construction at my workplace. As you entered the big foyer/atrium, school groups would turn left into a room with lots of big computers, then into a classroom area screened from the rest of the museum by big fake flowers. I was involved in some kind of test of the new program, and was sitting on the ground in the main foyer (wearing loose linen shorts, that I worried were a bit revealing). Someone was reading from a 'scenario' sheet, and then a group of dancers started performing and moved up very close to the group - they were looking at us as they danced and making faces, and we were smiling and laughing.  Two senior staff from the museum and a more junior staff member appeared to address us - they were all wearing green and purple crocheted cardigans. The junior staff member was a ring in for their boss and made a joke about having checked the dress code first.  Then the museum morphed into a space that contained a kind of 'alt-world' or space, that you could only reach by passing through a number of special, significant trees (different varieties of large gum tree). There were proper ways through - when you had permission - but some people were finding their own ways in. One couple used a chainsaw to open up the trunk of one tree and pass through (the tree sealed up again).  Another couple found a way to open up a tree and went through, but it sealed up again before they'd completely emerged to the other side. They'd had their arms around each other in an embrace as they passed through the tree, and now they were mostly in the alt-space but one arm each was caught in the trunk, with a hand out in normal space. This was a known danger of passing through the trees, and could send people mad. One of the couple did panic and went momentarily mad, her head changed into the head of monster with lots of sharp pointy teeth and she bit off her lover's head. (It wasn't bloody, it just sort of disappeared in a puff.  She almost immediately returned to normal and realised what she'd done, and cried and despaired. Her lover's spirit was still present though - and in fact she herself seemed to be able to slip in and out of her physical body into a spiritual one - these looked like little peg dolls with faces made of felted wool or cotton. The surviving woman could look down and see her spiritual form sitting on her shoulder.  The junior staff member from before approached from the other side of the tree and 're-set' it - this involved zapping some little electrical points) - which healed the tree gateway. I think the body disappeared and the survivor was no longer trapped; she tried to call out to the archivist as she returned the way she had come (visible from inside the alt-space, and up some stairs) but the archivist couldn't hear her.  Then there was another part in a large rectangular or square building, with many many identical wood panels off the internal corridor, which lead into rooms around the edge of the building. We watched a sequence of short stories, gradually learning who was in each room and how they had got there - many had been lead into their rooms under false pretences. As we watched, we realised we were seeing different sides of things that were happening at the same time, or stories repeating themselves to accomodate actions others had taken (which then changed the outcome of the second story). There was a young man in one room who seemed separate to everything going on, and told other people what to do to affect the outcome of the stories. One man always became obsessed with a small figure on a shelf behind him, whenever a story had cause to bring him into this room. Another woman was instructed to put on a red dress and push-up bra. Another woman (who we hadn't really learned about yet) was wearing a fabulous sculpture dress and somehow had been drenched by the sea. She was shut into another room but we didn't learn her story.

I was somewhere remote - I'd travelled over water to get there - someone had all the power and I think me and a younger girl were working to free us from the person in charge.  I passed some test somehow which meant I could put her on a train out of there - it was designed just for her. Somehow the train engine turned into a horse who had to pass over a terrifyingly wide and powerful river by crossing a narrow log.  The horse couldn't fail though - it was programmed to travel across the log - bu the entity had tricked us, and the log was too short - it stopped short of the other bank. We could even SEE the other side. The girl realised there was no way out - the train-horse couldn't return, and she knew eventually the log would fall into the river, which moved at frightening speed and power underneath her - she could see things in the water, cars and logs and other chunky debris - so she jumped into the river to get the end over faster. As she hit the water she turned into a tea towel, which went all limp and flowed with the current without any resistance. I realised the river was what we all came from and what we all returned to. Earlier while the train-horse was traveling over the log I'd had a view of going over huge waves in the river - like we were on a roller coaster - and even got the same sensation in my guts you get on a roller coaster - the river was so huge and furious, like an ocean. Meanwhile I was working to detect the entity in power by working on some kind of 'spell' - to release a sequence of things to set in place e- like a key - that would somehow 'deactivate' it. Then I was in a hotel with a friend of mine (Kate), except the hotel looked a lot like my grandparents house in Werribee. We went back to the room we'd been staying in and realised we'd left the open fire going. Logs had fallen onto the carpet in front of the fire but mysteriously hadn't set everything on fire, though there were some large chunky embers near the door. Also I'd left the window up so I remember thinking that the combination of cold air and the fire had probably made the piano go out of tune. I was a bit cross Kate had left the room without screening the fire or shutting the window - I'd left the room before her. I didn't say anything though. I was given words to say about our / a breakup. I was watching a ball-shaped thing get rolled in hundreds and thousands, so it looked like a delicious donut but in fact they were spiders being sent out into the world (to infiltrate or kill). I was looking through a glass 'machine' that was both a nursery (where the spider balls were raised) and the machine from rolling them in hundreds and thousands. Then they shot off through tubes to wherever. Some kind of captured scientist had set it up and ran it. I wondered why he'd never been tempted to sabotage it. Then I was packing things and I had all this crap, notebooks, books, random stuff - I still had to finish packing and get off site before a due date - but it wasn't going well, partly because I couldn't concentrate and apply myself to the task. I came across a book that would help us escape.

My workplace was still closed to the public, but some professional colleagues were somehow still allowed to visit and asked what they should see - I couldn't remember what exhibitions were still up. Meanwhile someone at work had discovered an ancient elephant specimen preserved (intact) in an old bog - everyone was very excited because this was an amazing find and everyone would want to come and see it (once it was excavated and prepared) and thus save us financially.  Then I was at Parliament House in Canberra, looking at six sculpture's a friend's partner had made around the perimeter - supposedly recreating much older sculptures that used to be there. Five were figures made of stone, and one was a small three-story tower which I first described as made from smooth wood and metal, but when I got closer could see it was made out of two different metals - coppery on the outside and silver on the inside - in very organic shapes. I was just visiting, and as I left a friend and her sisters danced a goodbye song to me as I walked away, which I imitated. They were wearing strange balloony paper dresses.  I came to a house were I was staying with others - it was very messy, we were 'squatting' there while the owners were away. We had to pack up and leave very quickly because the real owners or tenants returned unexpectedly - we scrambled out the back door as they came in the front. One of the returning people called for her cat and worried because she couldn't hear her meow - I wasn't sure where the cat was but I knew she'd lost her tail (not violently, like she'd 'shed' or moulted) and felt bad.  Then the six of us were racing around the aisles in a store like Big W (sort of a lowbrow department store) - the store was empty of people (except us) but there were dinosaurs outside trying to get in. We knew that after six dinosaurs showed in a window, another would try and get through a big door into the store. We didn't have much of a plan to stop them getting in - just physically trying to hold the door closed.  Then this morphed into a musical, where the same people were ghosts and re-enacting the crucifixion. Then a live person came in the door (someone from TikTok who I'd been watching) and started watching and enjoying the performance too - the ghosts were surprised he could see them but pretended everything was fine. They gradually got closer and closer (the ghosts and the TikTok star) and I could see everyone had different teeth, the type of teeth showed what type of monster they were. I thought the TikTok star had pointy vampire teeth and wondered if there was going to be a fight.  Then I was sitting on the edge of bridge with someone unfamiliar to me and we talked and had a bit of a cuddle and smooch. A woman flirted with me and flashed her breasts and vulva - we smooched too. It was all quite lovely but in the back of my mind I was worried (for both of them) that they'd realise I wasn't very good at relationships.

Someone in our party or community had made a new device that travelled at super speeds - faster than the eye could see. It looked like a silver metal ball - maybe billiard ball size? Smaller than a tennis ball - and it was kind of like a mechanical virus. It travelled until it hit a person, embedded itself and then exploded, which sent out a number of new balls. A younger woman essentially became a suicide bomber by carrying on into a market or public shopping space, to deploy the first one. The resulting 'blast' flattened several people and then the little spheres lodged in them like bullets - so the people were definitely dead. Needless to say the spheres spread very quickly - they moved so fast there was no time for people to react or even realised what was happening My 'view' followed them as they spread down the road, at one stage reaching people at the snow and people on a ski lift, who started dropping off the lift seats as they were affected. I can't remember why we'd made this, let alone released it - though I do seem to remember the older woman hadn't really asked anyone else before she let the first one go. And I don't think we realised just how fast and deadly they would be. Modern transportation networks meant they spread even more quickly. When you got very close to the spheres and slowed them down it turned out they actually looked like hairy spiders. Eventually of course they came back around to our town - two citizens who'd left town previously came home, fearful of what was happening, and brought the 'virus' back within them. One of the pair was the younger man from 'The Boys' TV show. We were trying to figure out how to protect ourselves from the devices, which seemed a bit hopeless as we'd seen on TV they could cut through steel and space shuttles - but we'd found a narrow 'windshield' somewhere and aligned ourselves in a row behind it and waited A TV interview had somehow revealed what they 'wanted' - but I don't remember what this was We waited but the 'attack' didn't happen - but then, we thought, would we even know if it had? They moved too fast to see. A random extra snippet - I was having trouble connecting devices to a 'display' unit, to play music - they parts didn't quite look the same but similar to casting from a smartphone to a TV using a Chromecast. Eventually I got it to work and was playing a really interesting band. I had to leave but left it playing for a couple who were there

I made a dress in a gorgeous soft teal fabric - a kind of A-line shape with three-quarter-length sleeves - I sewed it really well and was very pleased with it but when I tried it on it was completely the wrong size and I couldn't pull it down properly over my bust. I couldn't figure out how I'd got it so wrong (though I hadn't made a toile). I was showing it to an old school friend and looking at the pattern again and realised I'd used some of the wrong pattern pieces in putting it together - there were pieces for a 'B cup' dress and pieces for a 'D cup' dress and I'd used a couple of each without realising there were two sets in the packet.  I thought about giving the dress to my Mum, though it wasn't really her style - I thought she'd look good in it. I'd also knitted a jumper, which I was showing to the same friend. She'd made one from the same pattern and though I'd done a good job and was pleased with mine but I liked hers better - she'd incorporated narrow vertical strips of colour into it that looked really good and also knitted three-dimensional mushrooms that came out of it (mine didn't have any mushrooms so I don't think this was in the pattern). Here's was sort of freer and more creative - mine was more 'by the book'.  I was trying to find some songs and videos on my phone but was unresponsive to my taps, or responded in the wrong way and I'd lose the song I just found (I wanted to add ones I'd found and liked to a playlist). I was getting really frustrated and was pretty much hitting my phone in anger (which in the back of my mind surprised me because I love my phone so much)  Meanwhile my sister had muted what was playing (I was casting it to the TV) - we were back in the living room of our childhood home in Canberra. She was using an app on her phone to try and learn more about the nightmares she was having. I was troubled she was having nightmares. We had a conversation about whether they 'crossed timezones', meaning that if you had a regular nightmare at 5am, in another timezone you'd have it at the time that aligned to 5am in your local timezone - or a panic attack if you were awake.  Then I was at a friend's parents' house who were arguing about staying in the town they were in. It was a new 'pioneer' town - her Mum didn't want to stay in a place so small but her Dad was adamant he wanted to stay, because he wanted to practice his father's trade and do things for the dead - build a place where they could rest, or make coffins, where they could be at least and where their family could bring them (while they were talking he was tracing some kind of machine pattern which had a feeder belt).  Later I got up (late) and went out and said happy birthday to my friend's Mum, who hugged me for a really long time - apparently the rest of her family (except my friend) had forgotten or not bothered. Her other children (I think there were three of them) were leaving with their Dad, so it would just be her and my friend left in the house. I knew she needed a lot of looking after.  Then I was watering vegetable garden plots. I had an excess of the special fish juice fertiliser in the watering can, so I watered someone else's seedling trays too.  Then I was trying to pack up a whole bunch of stuff of personal stuff I had at work - plastic bins full of boxes, a whole dolls house, bits of china etc - and I needed to get them back to my regular house. But because work was closed this would be tricky - I couldn't put all the boxes near the front entrance doors because they'd be visible to everyone through the glass and moving vans couldn't drive onto the plaza outside. So I negotiated to take them down to the loading bay instead. The security guard was reluctant, and told me there'd be a fee, but agreed to do it. Somewhere here we pulled two other guards out of a class they were in to help me - it was a spy class and they were really interested in it, so reluctant to leave - but they did come and help me. None of my stuff was packed properly, by the way, there were bits everywhere. I faffed around getting things downstairs and eventually one of the guards asked me very politely if I was finished and could they go back to spy class - I said yes of course and felt bad because they'd been missing such a great opportunity.

I was at work looking for the 'nice' toilets - they were new with very tall wood or faux-wood doors - and they'd been off-limits for a long time while some building works were happening in one section of the building. The works were supposed to have finished last month but the toilets were still closed and locked - though I tried the door anyway, it was bent inwards a little at the bottom where others had obviously tried to force it too. So I went looking for the least horrible of the other toilets that were open. There were all very open, small, cramped and dirty - e.g. I found one that had four toilets to a 'cubicle', and the sanitary bins were full to overflowing. The walls were kind of half-height so everyone could see everyone else. It looks like the toilets drained onto the floor and then into a drain in the middle of the floor so you couldn't put toilet paper into them because everything would clog up and get even more disgusting. So I put my toilet paper into the overflowing sanitary bin instead and touched some of the paper that was already in there as I did, which was disgusting. I was thinking of writing a letter to the Executive team about how bad the toilets were and how they really needed to be replaced - I started writing the letter in my head to form the argument - e.g. visitors would also be disgusted, so we needed new facilities and more regular cleaning - but at the same time I knew we had no money for upgrades so it'd be kind of futile.
Somehow I'd betrayed or really let down my old friend Kylie from high school / college

walking along somewhere and having a v short drive-by convo with Greg Davies as he passed by the other way. - being in a big sprawling house somewhere, late at night, and leaving my housemates to go to bed, before deciding to shower instead and playing with a dildo.

Being at a socially distance gig at an Albert Hall-like venue. Just remember being there and walking thorugh with other ppl at interval. Think we might have walked past a place getting refurbished. Remember there being a white sheet and maybe some scaffolding. Seemed like a lot more people than they were, but we were all walking in single file in two directions going somewhere. Might have been with someone. Remember seeing someone on a balcony/upper floor as we passed by. Lots of red and white and gilded things in terms of decor.

- Dara O'Briain just ... idk being there - something about space and telescopes - a large lot fo dried instant ramen noodles sitting outside a house in the rain, getting soaked. - some health expert saying things might get tough again and we really should have at least a week of non-perishable food available as a stock - Al Murray was also there for some reason - being in a(nother) house somewhere idk idk

There was more before this but I don't remember it. What I do remember is being in this wide open parkland somewhere, and watching two young blonde girls running up some sandy banks to a limestone castle where there was a athletics track, clearing seeking out someone I couldn't see bc they didn't want to be part of some kind of running race bc they didn't want to catch covid in prison if they lost.   This then switched to being in a hotel somewhere where I was with maybe three or four others for a small BDSM/kink party, one of whom was my partner and lover, and I'd had sex with them, but not penetration bc I'd forgotten to bring a dildo with me. They'd gone off after that, with my parting words being, 'my bed is always open to anyone who needs it', and I was with someone else who was less experienced, but she did have a vibrator with her, and for whatever reason, we decided to just flop down on the bed and wank off, which was fine. I offered to help her, and she agreed, so I used her vibe on her, and ate her out.  Then I'm going home later on, and I'm in a bit of a hurry bc I know I have a couple of Little Britain pictures I want to take down from my room bc they're not cool and actually offensive and I should have taken them down years ago but didn't and it won't do if I'm creating a safe space for everyone.

I was visiting Pompeii, but Pompeii was in Germany. I had been there before, the previous year. I was staying at a guest house nearby, and was planning to leave later that day and had a ticket for a 7 pm train. Before catching the train I had to go to Delmenhorst to pick something up. I caught sight of a clock and saw it was ten past four, so decided I had to leave Pompeii, go back to my guest house, then get to Delmenhorst and back before 7 to get my train.  When I got back to the guest house I was packing up and the landlady came in with a sandwich for me in a white roll. The sandwich had raw onions in, which I don't like so I tried to pick them put without her noticing, but the onions kept multiplying so the whole sandwich filling was onions. In the end I picked them all out so I just had a plain bread roll, then I noticed a piece of bacon stuck to the top half of the roll so I ate that. I started to realise that I might miss my train, and wondered whether I could go to the station and change my ticket before I went to Delmenhorst.

I was walking along a road with four other adults and a child - a boy of about 4 or 5. We were walking side-by-side holding hands. The boys was between two of the adults who were swinging him as they walked. I didn't recognise any of the other people, but in the dream I felt I knew them. The road was open, in the countryside, cobbled and had no traffic. I felt that it was in Europe somewhere.

I had booked tickets for an event at a winery for myself and some friends, but couldn't remember whether I had told the others the details of what time it was and where. So I was looking through a leaflet from the winery to try and find the information, but there were several events listed and I couldn't remember which one I had booked. I was also trying to find some information about the dress code for the event. I thought I'd found the event and decided the dress code was 'smart casual', so I dressed in jeans and a smart top, then decided to check again, but this time I couldn't see the event I thought I was going to listed at all. And I still wasn't sure whether the others knew where to go. So in the end I just went to the winery. When I got there I found a large room like a wedding reception venue, but it was being renovated and there obviously wasn't an event there that day. So I carried on walking through this room, and at the other side I met Amanda. She was very smartly dressed, in a white blouse with sort of swathes of material the went round her neck. I thought this outfit was too old for her, but definitely made it look as though she had made an effort to dress up, unlike me. I told her I was really glad she had made it as I had been trying to call her to remind her, and we then decided to go and look for the correct location.

I went away for the weekend to stay with some friends. "Catherine" was mentioned. the reason I was at this house was that they had invited me to a hen party, but I said I couldn't go because I had some other friends visiting, but they said to come anyway and my other friends could come and stay as well. So I was in this house, sitting by the window waiting for my other friends to arrive, while people around me were getting ready for the hen party. I thought I was in Kinglake, but the view outside the window looked nothing like Kinglake. There were cobbled streets and the street lights were on. It looked more like an English town actually. Then the bride-to-be announced that she couldn't go to the hen party because she wasn't feeling well, so her finance said he would go instead of her, and put on her dress. It was a white silky dress (more like a wedding dress than a going-out dress actually), and it fitted him perfectly! I realised then that the bride-to-be was one of my former colleagues, Megan. Then everybody left the house and a few moments later I saw a minibus go past the window full of people going to the hen party. The bus had been decorated and it looked really good fun. My other friends still hadn't arrived, and I wasn't sure whether they would want to go to the party with people they didn't know. I had decided that I didn't really want to go myself, but when I saw the bus I changed my mind and decided that when my friends did arrive I would persuade them to go to the party.

All I remember is eating a pie. It was quite a large pie, square, maybe 20 cm by 20 cm, and I cut it in half diagonally to share it withe someone - I don't know who. It was a beautiful pie - buttery, perfectly-browned flaky pastry on top with a rich meat filling. It steamed as I cut into it.

I found a printed credit card statement that showed payments for flights to the USA and some accommodation, for a holiday that I had been on with my ex-boyfriend Jeremy. I remembered that he had never paid me back for the holiday and decided I would contact him to ask for the money. I told my current partner that I was going to do this, thinking he might not want me to, but he said it was up to me. When the dream finished I was still trying to decide what to do and how to contact Jeremy. Part of dilemma was trying to decide whether I really needed the money or not.

I was in a classroom. There were maybe 20 people in the class, and I was sitting in the second row so could see what the people in the first row were working on. The tutor asked a question about whether anybody had brought anything with them to talk about. I felt that some people must have been in this class before, as they seemed prepared for this question but I wasn't.  The person in front of me had a printout of an email that was something to do with the environment and a copy of an advert that was something to do with the Adani coal mine. The advert was two pages and was coloured a deep blue colour. It looked as though it had a picture of an oil rig on it, though I thought it was about the coal mine. The tutor seemed very pleased with the person who had brought this. Then at the other side of the room, I recognised Steve, an acquaintance of mine, whom I haven't seen IRL for about ten years. He had also brought some material with him, which the tutor looked at and became very animated about how wrong it was. it was something environmental.

I was at work and was at a presentation where our organisation was presenting some new software we had bought. I must have been part of the team that was presenting as I was sitting at the front near the podium. The "software" was in a box, about the size of an old-fashioned blackboard eraser.  Someone gave a summary of what the software did, then Mel was asked to present on where we had got the software from (ie. the vendor). She pushed back on this and asked why she had to do that. I said "well I'm interested to know so maybe other people will be". I couldn't decide whether she thought talking about this was beneath her or whether she was just tired.  Then one of the other presenters, who was wearing a dark blue jacket and white open-necked shirt then asked her "how long does it take to get a Masters degree" to which she replied "about two hours", which he and I found very funny. Then Mel sat down next to me and agreed that she would present after the coffee break was over.

I was in a town somewhere - there was snow piled up at the sides of the road but it didn't feel cold and I wasn't dressed in warm clothes. It was night-time and the street lights were quite atmospheric. I was with a group of others - I felt I knew them. I needed to get somewhere and wanted a lift, so one of the group was nominated to take me. I don't think I knew the guy who was chosen. He had blond hair and was wearing a white shirt with the sleeves rolled up despite the snow. My driver got into his car, which was a white car and looked quite old, and turned the car round. Then he leaned out of the window and started vomiting, loudly. I felt that I didn't really want to get in the car with this guy, but was trying to convince myself it was OK. The others in the group seemed to find the situation amusing. After turning the car round, the driver drove slowly towards where I was standing, whilst still leaning out of the window vomiting. I stood beside the road, trying to decide whether I was going to get in the car. Now I was in a restaurant or reception venue somewhere.
