I was standing in the centre of the room on my own, and the was a big circular table, with a large cake on a cake stand in the middle of the table. Part of the cake had been eaten but about two-thirds of it was left. It was a chocolate cake, with a thick layer of cream in the middle and more cream on top. I heard a voice telling me that I could take a slice, so I cut myself a slice of the cake, put it on a plate and started eating it. I could taste it and feel the texture of it. It was delicious.

I was visiting somewhere I used to live, which seemed to be on the outskirts of Sydney. I decided to walk to where I was going from the station, though it was 2-3 km away and I was carrying a large backpack. I walked along a country road that was parallel to the main road. At some point I decided to cut back onto the main road, so I walked down a side-street, passing a church. I remember that there were fields around me which were very lush and bright green. Then I decided to stop and get a kebab at a cafe that someone had recommended to me. There wasn't a menu except for a piece of paper on the counter that basically said choose chicken, lamb or vegetarian, and select your sides from the cabinet. I ordered chicken and the woman behind the counter put some chicken into a large takeaway container. I had wanted flatbread with it, but once she had put the chicken in the container I didn't like to ask, as I thought if I had bread it should have gone into the container first with the chicken on top.  I then went to choose my sides, but I couldn't see anything in the cabinet except tzatziki, so I asked for tzatziki. I really wanted hummus as well, but didn't know whether I was allowed to have hummus as well as tzatziki and for some reason didn't want to ask. The server then handed over my container and  took it to the till to pay. There was a generous amount of chicken, but it really just looked like roast chicken with tzatziki, not a kebab. Some slices of tomato had mysteriously made their way into the container as well. The girl at the till rang up the price which was $6.50. Since the pandemic I have been paying for everything by card, but when I looked in my wallet I saw there were a lot of coins in there so I decided I would use some of the coins to pay the $6;50 and I asked the girl on the till if that was OK. I then started counting out the coins. I wanted 3 $2 coins and a 50c, but every coin I took out turned out to be a foreign coin. I had an Indian coin and a Ugandan coin, and others. The girl on the till got bored with waiting for me to find the money and wandered off. While I was still looking for coins I glanced out of the window and saw it was pouring with rain, so I thought I might eat my kebab inside instead of going out and looked for a table. Then the girl came back and I gave up looking for coins and paid by card. The girl then asked me if I wanted to work over the weekend, delivering kebabs for the cafe. I seriously though about it for a while, but decided not to as I didn't really know the area and thought I would be too slow doing the deliveries. By then the rain had reduced to a drizzle so I went out anyway. I was just leaving when I realised I had forgotten my backpack, which I had left behind the door, so I picked it up. For some reason I didn't put it on my back properly, but carried it in a very awkward way by the strap. I walked back the way I had come, and saw the church again. Whilst walking I met a family with two or three grown-up daughters, who seemed quite well-heeled and were very loud. They were going to their holiday house, which I walked past as they went inside, and I heard one of them say "be careful, this used to be our dentist's". I started to think I was getting lost, so decided to cut back to the main road to get my bearings. On the way I saw a sign to Donnybrook. I thought that was odd as the only Donnybrook I know is in Melbourne. I then reached the main road, by a Shell petrol station, with a big red and yellow sign.

I was in a church and was cleaning one of the ornaments. I don't know what it was - it was a grey stone or concrete artefact, about 1 m high and with a square cross-section, about 20 cm across and tapering to a point at the top. Not really phallic - at least that's not how I saw it. It looked very dull at first, then when I put water on it, I saw lots of colourful abstract patterns on it. Someone who I couldn't see was telling me to work harder to get it clean.

I was on a skiing holiday in Japan. For some reason I had gone out that morning without eating my breakfast. The breakfast was chicken and chips. I had left my chicken and chips on a table in the corner of the room and was planning to go back later and eat it. But when I went back, it had gone. I felt very annoyed about this. So I asked a woman who was serving meals if I could have another breakfast, but she refused because I was supposed to have a ticket for a breakfast. I started to argue with her, and told here that I was entitled to a breakfast, but someone had taken mine away before I'd had chance to eat it. She kept refusing and I kept explaining what had happened. Eventually she said 'Wait', and went into the kitchen. She came back a with a plate on which was some sort of stew and boiled potatoes. I remember thinking that this wasn't really what I wanted, but thanked her anyway and took it to a table to eat. I don't remember the taste of it, but the stew was very hot.

I arrived in a city in Central Asia by ferry - I think it was in Azerbaijan. After getting off the ferry I got a taxi up the road, but the taxi was open-air and I found myself breathing fumes which seemed to come from a factory or chemical plant somewhere. The fumes were very acrid and made it difficult to breathe, and got worse as I went up the road.

I was at my ex-boyfriend’s family home for a family event. I wasn’t sure why I was there as we have not been together for a number of years. I had arrived on time, and there was almost no one there, so I was sitting on some older style furniture reading while I waited for others to arrive. It was a chaise longue with a carved back and it wasn’t comfortable. Whilst I knew I was in the family home, the actual house was much bigger than in reality and was like an extended Mediterranean villa with archways, and covered colonnades. There were outdoor areas and a lot of vegetation. I was sitting inside on the chaise longue, and was aware of others outside. One of my ex’s cousins, Nick, arrived and greeted me, but otherwise people were distant and I did not feel welcome. They, like me, seemed unsure why I was there.

I was in a shopping centre in Scotland. It was quite small and run down. I met some lads who were quite geeky but nice. Ended up chatting to then and having a beer. I think they were asking about suggestions for films to see as there was a cinema in the centre. There was another girl with me, who kept making stupid comments. I don’t really know who she was - not someone I’m conscious of knowing even though I knew her in the dream. One of the lads bought a small box of beers which we shared while we were sat around an old Formica table in the food court of the centre. I recall the beer box was cherry red and it had cans in, which was a contrast to the bottles we’d all been drinking previously. I was conscious of liking the lad who bought the beers, in a ‘teenage crush’ sort of a way, rather than anything sexual.

I was in Davos , Switzerland, which I visited regularly to ski when I was a child. I was coming down the road from Wolfgang towards Davos, with the lake on the left. The road stretched out straighter than it does in reality, and I could see the town ahead. Evidently it had been raining heavily, and there was flooding on either side of the road, but in separate places so the road was still passable. we were in the left lane. The closest flooding was in the right lane, and it stretched maybe 10m, encroaching almost to the middle of the road. The flooding in the left lane started just the other side of the right lane flooding, so about 160-165m ahead. The shape of the flooding was curved, with each flood being kind of like a seperate half of a yin and yang image. Two motorbikes approached the flooding, one in each lane, one from each direction. They were at different speeds or distances, so there wasn’t any concern they’d crash, I was just conscious they were both on the road. It appeared that they tried to avoid the flooding, and moved towards the centre of the road which seemed logical as that’s where you’d expect the flooding to be shallow. However, it proved wrong, and the motorcycles each fell into deep water. the rider in the right lane, who was closest to me struggling to get out of the water - the motorbike itself had disappeared. Then there was someone on the pavement alongside the rider, and they started shouting ‘Steve Cram! Steve Cram!’ repeatedly, kind of in the same was that the kid in The Shining shouts ‘Red Rum’.  I became conscious of dreaming then. being on the ski slopes above Wolfgang and skiing back to the Kulm  hotel, and there was very little snow. I took off my ski boots at the door of the hotel and they were full of slush - really full, in a way that would be uncomfortable and wouldn’t allow room for your feet. I entered the hotel and there was a woman working there who was really hostile and unfriendly, but this didn’t really bother me. I left and got on a bus somewhere. It was dark, and I think I was missing a shoe/footwear on one foot.

I went to rugby training. It had been raining and there was only one other person there, which was disappointing. We abandoned the plan for training and decided to meet others at the pub. I left to change and came later to the pub by myself, it was on a narrow busy street with busy bars on either side. I felt a bit stressed about the number of people. I found my friends and another good friend joined the group at the same time as me but from the opposite direction. She was wearing almost the same thing as me - a casual, fitted, khaki shirt-style dress with epaulets and pockets on the chest. It was awkward, especially as I felt she looked better than me. I left and wandered in a park for a while, before running into another friend who said she had a spare ticket to the Barbarians rugby match that evening. I declined.

I was flying in a capsule to the moon as a tourist, with 3 or 4 other people. We got there really quick - it was meant to be about half an hour but we got there in a minute. There was a station there that we could eat some food and enjoy the view. We were there for around 24 hours before heading back to Earth. We came back and landed at the same area that we took off from. After landing, I waited around for another capsule, there were a lot of people watching. From the next capsule, only one woman landed, she had pressed something causing the capsule to divide up into different smaller capsules and everyone else was landing somewhere else on Earth. She was talking to her partner telling him that if they left now, they could run off and hide somewhere in New Zealand, as in the chaos they wouldn't even realise she had gone.

I had heard that there was a shooting in a post office, and it was a really young kid who did it, and there was not many survivors. Myself and a few other people for some reason decided to 'experience' what it was like for the survivors, it was like a virtual reality thing. I was lying on the ground, could feel the brush of bullets past my skin and clothes. The kid who was shooting was a boy, only around 10 - 12 years old.

I was helping out with COVID-related things at my old primary school - I remember remarking that the slide was still in the same place. I don't really remember what exactly I was doing but I was in the science lab

I was going for a swim in an indoor pool. When I got in, most of the pool was taken up with games and so there was one little slither of the pool for me to swim in. I put my phone at the side of the pool and tried to swim, finding it really hard due to lack of space, but also I just can't swim very well. I spoke to a woman who was playing a water polo game, but not about anything too important. I'd noticed that there were some kids who were hanging around where my phone was - there were other phones there also - and I kept swimming for a little bit longer. When I got out of the pool, I realised that my phone was missing along with all the other ones. I managed to corner one of the kids - a boy around 12 years of age - and yelled at him aggressively for him to give my phone back. I went away for a little bit, and when I came back, my phone was there. When I unlocked the phone I'd seen that the kids had downloaded all of the these cartoonish, kiddy apps that I didn't recognise and I started to delete all of them

I was flying back to Melbourne after a trip somewhere. I was with my mum and we were walking through the airport to get a bus into the city when I needed to go to the toilet. I walked in and there was a queue for the cubicles which included a male manager I used to work with. He said that he walked into the wrong toilets and couldn't be bothered to leave so he stayed in the queue.  I walked back out and then waited in a queue for the bus. It was taking ages and everyone was really frustrated. It was meant to arrive every 20 mins or so but it felt close to an hour or two. We thought about getting a taxi but eventually the bus came and we got on.  When we got close to the city, I realised that there were storms brewing all around. Looking out to the bay, I realised that there were cyclones brewing. I then looked around me to the other side of the city and there were dozens of cyclones all around. I started to take a video of my phone so I could send it to my friends interstate saying, 'Great, look at what is happening in Melbourne now.' A cyclone began forming in front of the bus and we managed to hold on and drove through it, but looking back at it, it almost seemed to catch fire and take out a few cars travelling behind us.

I was working as a police officer and we had a member of the public acting up, but as it turned out, he was an undercover cop. I became friends with this guy even though we didn't know much about him. A similar kind of thing happened again, and it also turned out this person was an undercover cop, and my fellow police officer also became friends with him.  I was then at a concert on a boat. I met up with some friends, but it was a really hot day, so we stayed inside, but when the band started, we all ran outside anyway. We were now not on a boat but in a park. We kept changing places. We initially were in a good spot, but my friend wanted to move up the back. We were stood next to some unenthusiastic people sitting at the back, while we were dancing around. The Bee Gees then came on, played two songs and left. Because it was hot, I sprayed some deodorant on, and felt bad for doing so and apologised to the woman next to me sitting down, who just kind of ignored me. We then moved again, to some seats that had been barricaded off, but my friend removed the barricade in a bit of a rage, and insisted on sitting down, while the rest of us stood up. She then felt a bit sheepish and decided to move again. We ran into another friend that we hadn't seen in a long time, and we sat with her friends way off to side of stage. I then noticed a dog shelter in the park, so I went over to say hello to the dogs, and I got chatting to the woman who ran it. She asked if I could take a photo of her with a koala that she had adopted, and another friend came along and kept getting in the background of the shot and ruining it, because she was mad that she wasn't asked to be in the photo.

I was in flat and that my mum was with me, and it was late at night. Some big planes started flying really low overhead and landing somewhere nearby. We were watching them as plane lovers and really enjoying the spectacle. Suddenly a jumbo landed in my small inner-city street and started taking out everything with its wings. It hit my apartment block and it cut it in half horizontally, and so the building collapsed but my apartment and my mum and I were okay.

I was at a retreat with work - there was a really large house with a lake nearby. I remember hanging out with some of the guys from work and we were catching a bus somewhere to do a day trip, and I was really enjoying everyone's company. I got talking to one of my work friends when we were wandering around a mechanics, looking at all the different parts on the shelves. He said that he just broke up with his wife despite them just having another child together. We then all got on another bus and were travelling through a city, and I saw one of my friends, who I used to also work with, running to get on the bus, so I yelled out to the bus driver to wait for her. She managed to get on the bus and the friend sitting next to me stood up for her, and I started wiping her brow.

I was in a house, waiting for my sister in law to get ready. My mum, my brother and I were all waiting to go to a winery in the country, and it was getting late in the day, and she had still not got ready to leave. I was going to knock on the door to tell her to hurry up, because the sun was beginning to set and I wanted to see the scenery in the daylight. Both my mum and brother looked at me as though it would be a stupid idea for me to hurry her up.  There was someone else there but I can't remember who he was. I knew that he was a traitor of sorts, and so my mum and I managed to lure him outside of the house and lock the door. He came back with an emu that he wanted keep as a trophy, but couldn't get in to the door. I remember thinking that there were lions outside too and that they might take him. When the dream ended the sun was still setting and we still hadn't got out the door.

I was at my friends house in Tasmania and she said that she was going to have to sell up and move. She said that she was sick of people doing renovation work around her. Her house included a shed that all of her other friends had scrawled graffiti in and it was falling down. I know that there was mention of a war coming because I remembered thinking that she should be pretty safe in Tasmania and it probably wasn't a good idea to move.

I was in what looked like a flooded building, a ruin, block of flats maybe that was under water.  Two men were nearby, dressed in everyday clothing, and one was giving the other a lesson on how to use diving kit. The one learning was having a bit of a hard time so they moved to an area where he could surface for a break.  I was just observing, oddly seemed like we could speak under water.
A sexual dream with a younger man and I appeared to inhabit a younger version of myself.

I was in a large indoor market with all sorts of stalls, mostly bric a brac or crafts, clothing rather than food.  I went to one clothing and found it huge, and as I went in it became my home which turned out to be an apartment.  I went in and started to get out clothing that I no longer used to be able to add it to the market stall but could not find place for the items.  Most of the clothes for sale had handwritten stickers with size and other info on.  The place was very busy.  I have the impression it was in New York, though the atmosphere reminded me very much of Hong Kong.

I was walking in my locality with my two sons and a two of their friends and they were planning a small get together.  Then we were back home though it was not my actual home, it was a very much older rather lovely house and I was asked if I could help out at short notice, ie right then cooking for a community event organised at the local church, so I was in the kitchen looking at what I could do.  The kitchen was full of mosquitos and not a lot of food I was puzzling over this.

I had gone to à consultation with a dermatologist because my hair was falling out.  The docs office was really muddly with piles of paper everywhere and when the doctor wanted to write a letter to the hospital where she wanted me to go for tests she could not find the correct notepaper.  First I agreed that I would return and pick up the letter from her secretary but apparently the secretary might not be there for some time since she lived far away, then the doctor asked me if I could pick the letter up from her home, I said sure.  She then asked me if I liked carrots since she had lots from her garden and did not know what to do with them all.  I said yes because I eat carrots daily.

Was at docs feeling unwell. In the surgery was a drug rep who was discussing with my GP what might be a good thing to try and my doc prescribed something called Nemmi.  I was uncertain because it did not seem to me that the GP was certain of what the issue was so I looked up this 'Nemmi" and found that not only did it appear to have many unpleasant side effects was unproven to be efficacious and was for men.

I was in hôtel quarantine with Ron my husband but had left my room without a mask and the hotel was operating normally with plenty of people about without masks and distancing.  I then found the hotel was huge with wide red and yellow carpeted  corridors that I could run along that seemed not to end.  I then found myself lost, unable to remember the room number or even the floor

I was at a holiday resort, and had arrived at breakfast time, had a bit of difficulty finding reception, wandered around through various places then found someone who told me I could go and have some food before checking in.  It was a buffet with many choices I took coffee and wanted simply bread and jam but could only find pastries, croissants etc, then found some interesting savory bread, foccacia style so chose that.  It was busy with guests and noisy. Went to sit down and a group invited me to sit with them.  Seemed very friendly, weather was awful, the resort had indoor facilities and activities so no problem, looked good for a short break I thought.  The guests all seemed to be older people.  It was Pre Covid - no masks. One lady had been to the doctors in the resort and was telling me about her complaint--constipation!  She had a long list of suggested helpful foods :).  I told her travel often gave me the same problem and I recommended prunes! Then I noticed a friend from a book group I belong to and I was surprised to see her.

In my garden I could see two neighbours walking along the fence between our houses looking at something.  They saw me and rushed away.  I went over to the fence to see if I could work out what had interested them and found myself in their house and I WA de red in their à bit until I heard the neighbours returning so quickly went back home where an estate agent and two people I terested in buying the neighbours house were drinking coffee on my terrace.  I then we to find my husband who was working by the river at the end of our garden. I found him in a massive red rock and sand river gorge with a trickle of water running down and we spoke of working on a retaining wall before the river came down in spate in the winter.  The atmosphete was oppressive and I think with river in flood the landscape would have been scary.  I then noticed the body of a woman partially hidden by silt washed out by the last flood.  Trying to phone police no signal, realised there was a road further down the river valley, so went down, past a construction site, and the landscape changed again to a graffiti covered run down area, where there was a person being threatened, then shot by an armed man who went on to menace another person with an iron bar, it was frightening.

I and others I do not know were completing the building of a tree house.  Nothing unpleasant happened, it was quite high up.  Basically we just worked on construction and putting furniture around which appeared without needing carrying up. The area was wooded with large trees all round.

I and a friend were flying two planes and were taxiing to the runway.  My friends plane developed a tech problem and she stopped. I taxied on through what seemed to be a rather odd mix of airport and supermarket car park and finally had to stop. It was very weird and confusing, kind of orange dusk, I got out of the plane and went to a building to get paperwork checked so I could continue and found myself in the home of a couple, the lady could not walk and had a strange contraption a cross between stilts and a scooter to get around.  The atmosphere was heavy, it was dark, raining. The guy then turned out to be some kind of vampire and I managed to get away buy hurling a baseball at him, the baseball was a bit like a  boomerang and came back.  This part was scary and I felt very afraid, it was nasty and opressive I left the building, and found myself back on a plane, this time as a passenger with my husband waiting  for take-off.  The overwing emergency door popped open and flapped.  The pilot announced the plane was ready to go but they were airing it a bit due to three coronavirus cases on board.
My husband Ron and I were playing some kind of board game on a very large board. My husband was moving his counter and was irritated saying I had pushed him, that I always pushed.

I was picking two children up from school, I do not know whose kids, they were 6 or so. It was a busy area, in a town but not anywhere I recognised. It was a silent dream, some street and background noise no speech. It was daytime. This dream morphed into a fairground, by now I was alone, nighttime, noisy with fairground sounds, not many people, not at all scary, quite bright colours.

I was at a large and bizarre funeral of the mother of a friend There was a sound and video system being installed and I was helping set up.  The cables between speakers and amp got tangled and it was impossible to untangle them, then the video monitors would not work.  I got very irritated and frustrated with this. The person was buried in a black formula 1 car.

I was in a very built up area, which was very degraded and run down, abandoned and was going to be rebuilt and redeveloped.  I was looking around with others.  Then I was sitting beside a very old grey stone well, with moss all over the stones, with a friend who was telling me about the death of their child, and the friend went away, angry.  I think I may have made them angry but did not know why.  I was crying.
I was in a crowded place, some kind of event was going on. There was quite a strong sense of unease. The dream was very dull coloured, it seemed like winter, people dressed in coats.
I see from the road my son  walking along the beach followed by a large rabbit.   I’m walking parralel to him but some distance  away, on the road next to the beach. It’s Brighton.

I was in the corner of a room with purple tables and chairs. My friends or maybe people I didn’t know came in and started walking towards me. I moved towards them, then remembered that was not right, I must not go near them, so I left the room.

A strange looking man was supervising my work. His face was interesting, with a long twisted nose and a twisted smile. I said, I’m taller than I look, taller than you think I am. He said, yes, but you really are taller in your dreams.

I was making a huge collage, a map of the world, sticking large chunks of torn paper down with PVA.  It was so big I had to go and lie down on it, and then look up & see the reflection. It was mostly blue & white , and shiny. I decided it needed some curved orange bits stuck on to make it look more 3D, so I got up to do that, (I was wearing my mum’s black and white spotted bathrobe) but first I had a break in the pub with my husband.  There was a rack of leaflets in the pub , he kept getting me to look at them. The third time he did this I got annoyed, I said you keep saying the same thing, those leaflets are really not interesting.  Then I had to wash of the glue. I was sleeping in the bath, in the flat we moved out of when I was 5. Every now and then I would be woken by stories from my tape player which was running in the bathroom, there were very long periods of silence during which I’d go back to sleep, my head sank back in the water but my face stuck out.

I was in a cafe with my friend Julie. We were looking after a little girl around 1-2 years old with a ribbon on top of her head. The girl had a birthday card to open, inside was a book, a present, the wrapping paper had come off, it was black tissue paper with a letter written on it with black shiny pen, too dark to read. She wasn’t interested in looking at the book.   I was teaching the girl how to take photographs, first I was getting her to take photos of a single colour, we took pictures of solid yellow, one that was pure purple and one of plain orange. We sat in some chairs, nobody else was in the cafe to start with so we moved chairs a couple of times to be closer to the window. We ordered two soft tuna rolls and one can of drink, the bill was £17.50. Julie’s sister Susanna had send her a wheely case, inside was my purple jumper which I must’ve left at her house, I haven’t seen it for years. The girl was gone now, and my friend was a different one , Amanda, now. Or was I talking to her on the phone? Then it was Thompson’s, the local hardware shop. But it was mostly a posh old fashioned clothes shop, I had never looked around the clothes part before, but had to wait a long time as one of the women who worked there was trying on everything, blue and pink shiny dresses, there were also lots of folded up boxer shorts in beautiful colours. Then my friend was waiting for me to go to lunch. We were students in Paris. First I had to look through lots of papers to find the drawings I had started so I could work on them at home later, he waited patiently while I sorted through a huge mound of sketchbooks, flicking through all the blank pages, until I found the papers. Then we walked through the streets of Paris to the restaurant. I was worried about paying, I think I was invited but not sure, I would offer to pay but felt shy. I was worried that we would drink wine and then I would not be able to work properly that afternoon.

I’m at my studio in London. Rebecca said they needed 4 new people to bring a piece of work for an art discussion group every Saturday. I agreed to take part but wondered how that would work as I’m away from the London studio, shielding in Wales,  but decided I could see how things worked out, maybe I could participate by zoom. I was surprised to be asked , together with a person who was partly my old friend Gail, partly a younger artist called Rachel Figuera. Most of this dream took place in a wide queue around a courtyard full of colourfully dressed people many of whom were studio neighbour artists. Helen had put some work up for our group exhibition. One piece was a long stick with a beautifully carved large head at one end and a tiny one at the other. There was a little bit of ink not coloured in properly, so I took a dab of ink on my finger and fixed it. I realised I had changed it, completely ruining it by painting a crude girl’s face on it, the girl looked a bit like Katherine, helen’s daughter. I wondered how to explain/apologise to helen , she was far away in the queue though so I didn’t have to explain immediately. I also moved another piece of Helen’s work, bamboo in a bottle with the root facing upwards- I turned it round so that the root would be in the water. I didn’t think Helen would mind. For the Saturday work discussion, I started making work, a painting on brown paper. I wanted to attach a small portrait to this and searched around for copper coloured pipe cleaners, or some copper wire or even some brown wool to attach it to the main work, but failed to find any of these. I went to look for Rachel to ask about logistics and found she had printed large beautiful black & white posters, and put a copy in everyone’s pigeonhole. My work was   going to be ok to talk about in the Saturday group though. Since it was autumn, and I would be making a presentation on a stage, I looked for an orange dress to wear. I only had a green one, but thought that would do. I was ready & prepared for the event, and had decorated the stage orange, now happening on Monday morning. I turned away from the stage, and opened a door to a small brightly lit cubicle off the main courtyard, where I had to clear up some rubbish. There was a sink and a toilet, I put some of the rubbish in each and poured buckets of water on top, but most of the rubbish stayed, so I looked around for scraps of paper to wrap it in, everything I found was too small or unsuitably shiny. I pulled the rubbish out, it was disgusting, smelly & slimy but not actually shit, more like rotting beetroot peel. I wrapped it up as well as I could, but couldn’t think of anywhere to put it.

I went to America. I met my friend Abbie in a big shop,  she was buying art materials, and then met some new people who took me to where I was going.  I had to teach a class in the morning, then work in the studio, then teach again in the afternoon. I bought a record player online and applied to get a rescue cat. I was a bit worried about my flat, I lived there alone and it there were a lot of dark bushes near the entrance. Also I was unsure of how to get there. It was fun working with the other people, I cancelled the cat because I would not be home much. QUADRANTE appeared in a big lit up Perspex sign , blue and yellow, it was perhaps the organisation I worked for. I wore Levi’s and cowboy boots, I felt strong.

in the form of a manuscript which I could read as it scrolled past, from right to left, in a slow continuous band about six inches high and eighteen inches wide. It was on soft white paper with pale brown marks all over it, like a pattern, I could understand what the marks meant. It had been drawn with coffee. It instructed me to do detailed gardening work. I should work in sections, devoting each small area to a different herb, creating a garden which would be a mosaic of herb patches. For specific information on how to plant and grow each of the individual herbs , I should do an internet search for each of around 25 different herbs. After the paper had finished scrolling past, I could see the bright green patches of the garden I was beginning to construct.

I was waiting for a German man, I was upstairs in the museum. The museum had just opened and hardly anyone was about. He arrived and asked if I had all the things we needed, I did. I was pleased to see him, he was very helpful. He was much taller than me, or perhaps I was sitting on the floor. He had long greasy blond hair. I got a coat, a big old army type coat out of my bag and he helped me sew a lining into it. We were very focused & concentrated on our work. Then he helped me sew two bands of fabric onto the back of a red blanket. The strips were very uneven but it didn’t matter. I had a big duffel bag with pieces of fabric in, and a flat bag, like a tool bag for the coat. I was glad the sewing worked so well and that everything had gone smoothly. He said goodbye when we’d finished our sewing. Then I waited for my friend Julie to arrive. She came upstairs to the room I was in with three or four other people. Julie was wearing a skimpy dress that looked like she had made it out of a sheet. A very muscular Cuban woman started doing ballet poses and Julie commented how shiny and strong she looked, she did look as though she was made of polished wood, like a sculpture come to life. I said we shouldn’t stand there staring, it’s rude to stare at people and make comments on what they look like.

I called Honi on my mobile phone, the screen view was life size. I felt a bit awkward, not sure why I’d called, or what to say.  There was a blue background to the screen I was looking at and a bright shining gap through which I could see her face. When I looked lower down on the screen I could see an identical bright gap , a stranger’s face was visible through that, I said oh you’re with your family, it’s fine she said, I’m just outside Marseilles, I’ll send you three photos of where I am. We chatted for a while, I don’t know what was said. She posted three images but the screen was so close to my face that I could only see some indecipherable writing.

I was on a ship, inside, not on deck. It was very dark and wet, and I saw everything contained in a tall rectangle. The ship was old and wooden. The darkness had spots of pale light scattered across it. My father was the ship’s doctor. Somebody died of scurvy, maybe my father, not sure, anyway I wasn’t sad nor did I feel anything. I had to write a record of the death in a large hardback incident book. The book was on a big lecturn, I had to sit on a high chair to reach it. Someone said “be sure to write it down as the other kind of scurvy, we don’t get any funding for the ordinary kind”.  A bright pink pig with a few blue splashes ran past me into the distance, it was raining, visually everything was still very dark with splashes of light and in the long tall rectangularlarly framed format.

I was standing outside a house at the top of a very steep slope.  It was very modern , brutalist architecture, and the front was completely flat concrete with ridged vertical lines running down like corduroy. I held on tightly to the ridges to stop sliding backwards and falling down the slope. There were no windows or a bell or door knocker but I knew there must be a door because I had to get in, perhaps my children were inside? The front of the house was a uniform grey but there was one little mark of purple chalk on the concrete, so I knew children lived there, perhaps it was my next door neighbours. I knocked and called, I could see the faint outline of a keyhole and a line which may have been a door. Finally the door opened and I could go in. They were expecting me to come. My friend lived in the house which seemed big and old fashioned on the inside. She said she lived upstairs with “her people” and her mother lived on the first floor, her father on the ground floor. They shared the sitting room, I could see part of a pale blue patterned carpet and a glimpse of the mother who had pale hair, she was shouting something, telling my friend to do something, or not do something. I went into a bedroom and picked up lots of coins from the white sheeted bed, the money was all mixed up with sharp pins so it was difficult to pick it up. It was my money, it had fallen out of my pockets when I’d been lying on the bed earlier. I was really pleased and relieved to have found it. I tried to open a drawer to put the money away but it was stuck a little bit open. So I just pushed the coins through the gap.

I’m in a big beautiful house in the countryside in a room with huge windows and a table with chairs around. I don’t live there. It’s sunny and green trees are outside. Then I’m in my house in London. I have to go out to teach my evening class. I have to get ready. I’ve got all day, I can have a bath, get dressed, then get my things together, then go out. The time moves fast and it’s time to go. I wander around the house, starting to become anxious. It was getting dark outside, nobody was around. But I wasn’t ready. What did I need to bring with me? The house was dark and I was alone. There doesn’t seem to be any furniture or lighting I my house. I don’t have a car, my husband is not around, I would have to come back by bus. But I can’t walk fast on the way back from the bus stop, in the dark, because my leg is injured. I would need to dress in dark clothes and a leather jacket so nobody would attack me. I can get an uber or a taxi home. But I will have to stop at a shop on my way home because I have no food. I’m hungry but what shall I buy? Sausages? But where are my clothes? Maybe in a bag downstairs in the hall. I haven’t got a leather jacket, I can wear a coat, but have I got one? I need other things too, for teaching. But what? I must not bring my laptop or a big bag in case I get attacked for it. A small bag then. It’s getting really late, I must go soon. Who will be there, at the studio? I haven’t been there for a long time, why am I going now? I’m scared to go and scared to come home alone because it will be so dark. I have to leave now.

I was with my friend Kevin walking around. There was a trolley bus/ tram track line close to the side of the road. I tried to hold on to some railings because a tram was coming, but my grip was loosening so I managed to flip over and throw myself over onto a slatted wood shelf. I settled down comfortably & Kevin sat facing me. I felt very attracted to him. Maybe we would have sex? I thought  that would be really nice but I probably shouldn’t. I felt aroused. I said I don’t think this is a good idea. I hate my boyfriend and can’t stand living with him but I’m in a relationship and if he found us naked together it would be difficult for Colin - no, wait actually it would be a good thing, a way to get rid of Colin. Suddenly he made a direct crude move on me but there was a small Perspex box next to me which he pushed into me, it hurt so I pushed back. Kevin became angry about the box, I told him that clearly it was an accident. He told me off. I said , I’m glad I didn’t have sex with you, because you are being so horrible now, now I see you would have been horrible to me afterwards.

I  had to make a book with a picture of something like a car, or a tortoise, or a hut, for each village, all the places around where I live, to protect them from harm. All the books were the same,the making was repetitive and time consuming,  each time I made one I experienced acute pain.

being in a house with all our trivia friends. It was one of their houses and we were talking about her rug. There was lots of laughter. Then I was in another house on my own trying to work out if it was haunted or not. Then I'm at a railway station with my husband. I think it's in Europe somewhere. There is a man protesting about getting on or not being able to get on a train I'm not sure what his deal is and there are police there apprehending him. Then we walked away from that scene, our kids are with us now and I get excited because I see and advertisment that is for a new snack. The snack is just a tub of Vegemite with some crackers in the lid for dipping.  Then I'm with a friend of mine and a director and were examining a cliff face for a scene in an upcoming James Bond movie that we've been cast in. We climb to the top then abseil over the edge. There's ancient rock art that's been desecrated, "fucking Rio Tinto" we all say. Then I'm in some sort of out door classroom with my daughter. There's sewing machines and her teacher and all the kids in her class. Then my husband and my kids and I are all out about to start of on a road trip. I have to adjust my daughter's back pack which turns into her car seat.

I was in the garden doing some work, my neighbours we out in their gardens too. Then I remember taking my daughter to school and talking to another parent who's child went to a different school but the school was nearby and had similar values to my daughter's school. We were discussing th merits of both schools. Then I'm hanging our close to my parents house, it doesn't look anything like their actual house. My husband and I are leaving the kids with them while we go somewhere. Before we go out eldest son shows us a small hovering ball he's found, he thinks it's alien. Then our daughter comes to us and has a whole fleet of small hovering objects around her. They look like paper airplanes but made out of metal.  Then I'm present at the birth of my friends son. My husband is there too and two of our other friends. Then for some reason my mum is there. I tell her it's not appropriate as she do any know Sarah and Sarah probably doesn't want her there. But she doesn't care or is oblivious and just wants to watch the spectacle. I remember getting quite angry with her for being so oblivious. I can't recall the rest.

I'm in the city with friends. Talking about the new apartment they are living in now and reminiscing about all the fun times we had at their old one. We then go to a bar to dance but the music isn't that great and there aren't many people there. I leave and go to Chris and Krystal's house where I am staying. I am on my own without my family. The next morning I stay while they leave for work. There is much fussing around with showing me how to lock the house up. Then they walk off down the street. I can hear Chris practicing his Spanish. being in a house show like Grand designs but we're looking at a house after its built. It's my neighbours house it's got a Day spa out the back with an indoor pool. And the host of the show who I think is Steven Fry is criticising the shoddy workmanship on the tile laying in the pool room. There's two girls the who work in the day spa. They're saying that the pool is nice despite the bad tiles. Then I'm at my house with my family and we're having a big party. There's at least 100 people here. My sister Erin and her family are here. We're standing in the front yard and she brings over I guy who's come along with them and introduces him to me. "This is Tram" ste says. It's a nickname. I've heard her talk about him before and say "oh your Team" and he says "yeah the one who smells all the time, but I don't smell today" and he laughs. He doesn't smell. The party continues. Then it's the next day and were saying goodbye to everyone who's stayed over. Tram leaves and my sister feels the need to explain why they always say he smells as she feels responsible for him smelling. She starts explaining.

I was back in highschool, there were people there I did go to school with but the physical school was different. We were in an amphitheatre type auditorium. People were being called to the stage to assemble a team or group for something. I was sitting midway up in the middle with my friends and I was heckling the teachers and the kids being called forth. being on a train with two guys who I'd just met, I think we were going to a party. Then I was living in a small town sometime in the past. I went to a tiny little speak easy in someone's house with a man is just met recently. There was live music and dancing. I'd been there before and I found my baby's clothes on the floor where I had dropped them at my previous visit.

I was a passive observer of a couple who's marriage was in turmoil. I was just sitting on their couch in their very fancy house watching as they fought and their marriage broke down. The were some links to organised crime that was making the marriage unstable. next my family and I were having dinner with a friend of ours. He served is a meal which included a steak that was a piece of his dead wife's body. He explained it was a way that he and his family honoured her and he had a dwindling freezer full of of steaks made from her. it wasn't disturbing. I was going on a road trip with a bunch of friends in convoy. We were down on the coast and we stopped at a road side attraction. It was a large tower that we all climbed up. At the top was an old friend from school. I turned to him and said "I haven't hugged you in so long, can I please have a hug" he wrapped me up in his arms and gave me a big long hug. Then we walked back down the tower. a friend giving me coffee and a pair of overalls.

I was younger like a young teenager. And I had been kidnapped or was running away from something/someone. I was hiding in public toilets. Then there was a cop who has either kidnapped me or was trying to help me and also my little sister was with me. Then we were hiding under a bed in the cop's house and  all these other kids came in and got under the bed to hang out and play with us. They were the cop's kids and his friend's kids and my sister and I had to hide from the cop's friend when he came in. I was having lunch with Zanna's family. We were sitting at a big long table and talking about how they had moved house. I'm in Melbourne at Amber's house it's an old share house and I'm standing with my other friend Andy. We're reminiscing about all the places we've lived at and who lived there. We're laughing lots. I am walking down a city street. I stop and get some food from a Lebanese shop. Then I keep walking and run into Andy again and someone else. We keep walking and see a closed down shop front with a for lease sign on it. I know that place and I tell the guys I'm with that it has a huge house out the back that has all these unexpected and creepy rooms. It's open so we go to have a look. I lead them through the shop to the house. The front part looks fairly normal-kitchen, living area, bathroom, two bedrooms. Then through a big barn door that looks like a cupboard I lead them into more of the house. There's another living sort of area and a couple of rooms. We hear a strange noise and then I remember my other dream about this house and in that dream we moved into this house and it was haunted. I make us all run out of the house. I'm in a beer garden with friends. I'm sitting at a table with a girl. Tom is sitting next to me. He's drunk and acting inappropriate. Laying across my lap and trying to kiss me. But I'm not put out by it, I kind of tease him back but then tell him very firmly that I am very fond of his wife and I think he should sit up and stop being an idiot. He does. I'm with Tom's other brother Heath and we're looking for their older brother Steve. We're worried about him. I'm on a video call to my friend Dot's sister Eliza who's just had a baby. Her and her husband are showing me the fruit trees they've planted that we sent to them as a baby gift. Somehow I'm not on video call anymore but physically there at their house. There's other people too and I become concerned that no one is wearing masks or socially distancing.

I was staying in a building on the main Street of the town I grew up in. At least two of my kids were with me, the third may have been there but he didn't feature much. My eldest son who's 16 was making a reverse lentil Sheppard's pie for dinner with the lentils on top and the potatoes on the bottom. He was using three types of lentils and arranged them in stripes across the top like Neapolitan icecream. There was another family there who I think we're my son's girlfriends family, in any case his girlfriend was there too. There were younger kids playing with my six year old daughter too.  Then it jumped to the next night where my son offered to make lentil pie again but I sad no let's walk next door to the burger shop and get burgers tonight. So we did. Then we walked around the town for a bit while we waited for food. It was a dream like version of my home town, recognisable but also different. Then the dream jumped and I was with my youngest two kids and my daughter's school class. We were crossing a river in the dry season up north I was very nervous about crocodiles but the teacher was assuring the children and me that there were no crocodiles. I was carrying my 2 year old son and holding my daughter's hand. I woke myself up before we crossed because I am terrified of crocodiles and they always appear in my dreams so I shut that shit done before anything could happen.

My family and I are about to leave to go on a road trip. My eldest son has lost one of his shoes at school. He thinks he left it at the bus stop, it had $45 in it and something else precious to him and needed for the road trip. We take a bus back to the school to look for it. We're asking people if they've seen it  Then my family and my sisters family have broken into this apartment complex. We're outside and start to scale a wall and climb across roofs. We find a spot and break in. We're in an apartment looking for something. Were searching around. Suddenly we realise there's two men in the bathtub. We go to leave before they see us. We're sneaking across the lounge room that has a big plate glass window looking out onto the walkway that leads to the from door of this apartment. A women who lives here is walking up and sees us. we all run to a window to escape. Then I'm walking down a hill I think at a festival, I see and old friend and chat to her. She looks younger, like she did in highschool. There's a stream running next to us, I stumble into it as I walk away. Dream skips to being inside a big hall, there's a fundraising event going on. Another old friend from high school is there running the show. She looks like her older self and I can tell right away because she is wearing a hijab and she never wore one while we were at school (except in the mosque) only when she was older.  Then my family and I are in a big building with lots of rooms. We're in one room and in the room next to us is another friend from high school he's there with two other people (who are teenagers) I don't know. They have a big cabinet full of these fluffy robot toys. I know my daughter and youngest son really want one. I also know these people won't sell me one. I go back to our room and get a stocking to put over my face. Then I go back into the other room the two teenagers I don't know are frightened. I apologise and say I just want one of the robot toys and I'll give them money but I'm not taking no for an answer. They flee with the money I was offering and leave all the toys behind. I bring my kids in and tell them to choose one each. They do. Then we all go back to the car we were packing and get in ready to start the road trip. We never found my oldest son's shoe.

helping a woman post cesarean birth and helping her to breastfeed then express. Then I was in the tea room with an old colleague of mine who I greatly respect. And we were both complaining about some of the care birthing women receive and how the system is broken.  Then I was in a house with another woman who I didn't know. We were trying to work out how to get out but it seemed as though the house was conspiring against us.  Then something is with my family in it. It felt a bit like a suspense movie, it was a little scary but mostly exciting. I think we were running away from someone or something.

I was within a group of people and we were exploring an underground tunnel system. We had drone mad cameras and were filming it all. A smaller group and I split off and entered a spiral staircase. When we were on the staircase a woman and her young son climbed onto it and started walking upwards, I was below them so watched as they walked towards the people above me. We all knew they weren't human so the people next to me and I started formulating a plan to knock them off the stair case to save the other peopl above us. There was more but that's all I remember. Something about remastering Degrassi high.

camping with friends. I was with my best friend and her husband and her husbands friend. There was sexual chemistry between the friend and me. We were all sitting around drinking and laughing. Then somehow I was sitting on the friends knee showing him some video clip. He started kissing my neck and suggested we should have sex. I kind of laughed it off. Then I was kissing him back and said okay let's have sex. Then he asked if he could fuck me up the arse and I replied "only if I can fuck you up the arse" her smiled. Then we were in the campground shower locks looking for a free shower stall to have sex in. We found one and went in and locked the door  I was with Keris trying to buy pizza from this road side stall. I tried twice to buy one. But each time I bought one I set it down to cool for a minute and then I'd go back and it was gone. I finally bought one and took it back to keris and we ate it quickly so it wouldn't disappear. It was too hot and burnt our mouths. Then keris and I were watching a movie with Kirsty. She was getting really annoyed at me when I'd get up to answer the door to put the kettle on and we'd have to pause the movie. She told me I wasn't good enough to watch the movie and got really angry at me. I got angry back and told her this was why she was so miserable in life because she had such exacting standards.

I had teamed up with a bunch of Misfits fighting off zombies and other paranormal phenomena after the apocalypse. I was roaming around with two of my friends. The apocalypse hadn't happened yet. Then after the apocalypse. We'd been taken prisoner by another group of survivers. The leader was Sam Neill. Then we were in a house battling ghosts and demons. Wed sort of teamed up with Sam Neill at this point. I was being attacked by a demon and I was screaming for my husband to help be because I thought Sam Neill was controlling it. He was in the other room talking to his mum on zoom. Once I'd freed myself i went in and unplugged the computer and yelled at him from not helping me.  Then we were in a mine with robots, we'd found a valuable mineral that could be used to make explosives mad were trying to mine a lot for profit. I was still suspicious of Sam Neill. Then he cornered my in an elevator as we were going back to the surface and told be h was the devil.

conversation with my son. We were discussing how one identified the houses where infected people live. I was in a small area of wasteland and there was a large flat blob of plastic glue being created on the ground, about twenty feet across and round except for a pointed extrusion like a speech bubble. The glue was opaque and textured with a mesh of random fibres, it transpired in my dream that that was to reinforce it so it could stand upright. Then I was on a bank of grass and looking at a long terrace of white painted Regency houses. Random houses had these big flat blobs of glue suspended above them, the point like a speech bubble touching the roof. These indicated where the infection was.

I was in a London tube carriage which was home, it was all fitted out like a gypsy caravan and there were a lot of people, who were my family, hugger mugger inside with me. There was an old lady who was my grandmother and she had wiry grey hair and a shawl and she was speaking to an oldish man. ‘He sent the card to number 13,’ she said. ‘He must know about the move to Scotland then,’ he said. I reached for my big shawl and fetched it down from a peg. I could paint it for you now. It was a mixture of red, green, blue and yellow and mid range in tone, a very sunny feel. The blue was an opaque sea blue, the red slightly watery and the yellow a splash like sunflowers, all in the same colour range and no defined pattern, just a lovely mix of colours. The fabric was that slightly shiny part synthetic material and there was a fringed edging which was slightly ratty and the fibres were that twisted modern fabric and weren’t hanging down, just a bit of a muddle. The tube was parked at a side platform in a very big smoky old main line station with a huge old arched iron roof, like Euston or King’s Cross in the old days before the platforms and the concourse were modernised, so when I was a teenager. The station was very quiet and echoey, it was as though the noise and the trains were in another area. The tube door opened and there was a big gap to the platform of about five feet. I hovered in the doorway and thought I cannot jump that. A male voice, and I think it was Lawrence Fox the actor, said ‘come on you can do it’ and I was walking to the end of the carriage feeling trapped and looking for another way out and hoping the platform would be closer at the end of the carriage.

I was in a big green fuel tanker, not driving and we drove into a large yard, very muddy with pinky grey clay and with a row of petrol pumps. We drew up alongside one and I got out. There were several men there working. I was with some other. Then I was with K my daughter on S Road, just by the House where Pam rented a flat in M and K was driving a generic farmyard tractor and we were across the road from the yard, she had to drive across that blind slope before the railway bridge where there is no visibility and cars come over there fast. I was saying ‘It’s clear, go’ and she was hesitating and she didn’t have the speed to cross without a potential collision if anyone was coming so I was panicking and saying go go and she drove across and went down the track into the yard opposite, the same yard again. The yard had been very busy but now there seemed to be no one around. The yard was like a big muddy farmyard and was part covered by a tin shed. Then a man in overalls and a visor like people wear now suddenly appeared. It was one of the men from the previous visit and no one I know but he was similar to T my old policeman friend. The tractor was roaring and tugging like a horse and I had got down and was holding it by a doubled back rope, like a horse. The man had a smudge of the mud on his visor and the tractor was mostly red, with pinky cream and grey. I let the tractor lead me and pull me down the yard to a place under the tin roof with bits of metal beams and I held it there and he said hitch it up to this and produced an old tire. He was mocking me for not being a country person and asked for my phone number for the paperwork on the clipboard he was now carrying. I gave him my old London number from when I was a child.

There was a camera attached to the end of a ski and a skier was taking off high in snowy mountains. It was a place I have never been, I’ve never been skiing, but it was as though I were in that camera. The sky was a brilliant clear blue and it was sunny with that weak sun of cold places. The skier took off and went high in the air then a bird became visible flying high in the sky. I focused on the bird from the end of the ski and followed it as it began to do an aerial display. It became obvious it was a heron, soaring and diving, twisting its neck around as it flew down and pointing its beak up as it soared. I must have been craning my neck to follow it.

I was in the country at a big house with people I know but I can’t recall who. I was shown a sample tile and asked by Avon Barksdale from The Wire to pick which blue to use for his swimming pool. The tile was one of those North African ones I like, textured and hand made. It had a line down the middle and the left hand side was glazed a dark azure blue and the right hand side a paler clearer turquoise blue like the sea at Comino and I preferred that one. I got in a car with Kevin the local taxi driver. he was driving and said he had a Norton now and I remember querying that because it’s a motor bike I think and I was musing on whether you could DRIVE a Norton. We came around a corner and the right hand side of the road had a large square hole in it, about five foot square and lined with concrete and about two foot deep. I said that’s very dangerous, it was just past the corner and there were high grassy banks. We drove past and I saw in a lay-by a fruit and veg stall on a cart, like those all over Malta. I said to Kevin ‘oh look, that fruit and veg looks good, it’s so difficult to find in lockdown’ and he said ‘it probably isn’t very nice’ but stopped the car and reversed and drew up next to the cart. The fruit was all jumbled and packed in sweating plastic bags sealed at the top and I said ‘you’re right, it isn’t very nice’.

I was walking with a man called Sam. He was one of those tall, rangy explorer types I admire but have never met, very focused and remote. He was wearing a long duster coat which swirled behind him and a canvas hat pulled very low. We were walking in a strange desolate landscape. It was a ochre light and the land was  vast and with dark compacted sand, no vegetation, very empty. Maybe it was a desert in India not Arabia because it wasn’t hot. Suddenly Sam started to walk faster and took off alone on another track which led him to disappear off to the right and quickly become a distant figure who didn’t respond to my calls. I carried on and a strange man-made feature appeared ahead of me. It was a high terraced construction about the area of a football pitch, slightly rectangular in its footprint. It stepped up in big stone walled terraces with flat sandy walkways as each travelled up, leading to a final terrace with a Parthenon like temple. It looked more like one of those ancient Indian palaces abandoned in the countryside than anything European or Arabic. I walked around the right hand side and as I did so, the sky became dark yellow and I couldn’t see at all. I had a yellow fog in front of my eyes and I struggled to find my way around the end of the temple complex and back towards the place I had started from. I was aware of the sound of water from the top of the construction. I had reached the end and there was nothing but an eery yellow glow when I bumped into an older man, bluff and hearty, who said he knew the way. We walked on and came to a hedge and could hear the sound of a busy road. We left the landscape and the fog cleared. A party of Indians followed us onto the road, they were heading for university. We stopped outside a house and a kindly older man with grey hair and an intellectual look invited us in. I was struggling to understand where we were and he said some place of two syllables beginning with M and I asked him to spell it out. The word ended in ‘cuit ’. The inside of the house was Natasha’s house, with lots of her things around, very cluttered but lovely things and I admired and picked up a miniature painted metal Victorian rocking crib with pink flowers on. The man was joined by another nice slightly younger man and the new one said we were outside a junction and you could go left or right for the town where I was staying. I said I’d rather take the right hand road and he said that would lead round to join the left hand road, waving his arms for emphasis. I was back in town, which was M. It was dark outside and I was on the High Street, then I was inside the hotel I love there. There was a woman with a young girl about 10 with Down’s Syndrome and she was holding a hard back book, quite old and she had found a letter in it which was from the hotel to her. She said she loved the hotel and when she played there she lay on the floor and they brought her smoked salmon and anything she wanted.

I was an observer watching a scene from The Wire. Jimmy and Bunk lounging on the balcony of a modern riverside apartment. Jimmy is scrolling down on his iPad making an order for Tesco Direct. Bunk says ‘Jimmy is going to increase this order as though that will lessen the virus.’ The screen shows different collages of graphics associated with Covid-19 arranged in dramatic Brutalist art works: face masks, medical packaging and equipment instead of Tesco products. ‘That’s just like what Jimmy’d choose’ says Bunk.

I was in the middle of a huge road junction, a sort of vast crossroads with great wide roads sweeping in four directions. It was a space rather like one you would find in a city centre, roads wide enough for ceremonial processions. It was completely empty. There was a big painted spot in the very centre of the junction and I was there bending over and patting it.

M. I recall going to meet him in the city, and him not being available. I think I was angry, at the predictability of it. I also recall feeling a sense of life in my previous home city of Wollongong as lots of colour and feeling and depth. I wondered why I would ever want to leave this place.

a sombre, serious, business-like mood. I was in a taxi in London and one person told the driver to go to Room 102 and someone said ‘that’s Daniel’s office, right?’. We arrived at an office in a large shabby building with bare iron struts to the ceiling. There was a job and choosing menus, it was something to do with food supplies, I wasn’t in a restaurant. It was to do with the pandemic, something important and sacks of chickpeas came into it. I woke up thinking oh no not chickpeas, I hate chickpeas.

I was in the garden of my old house in London, down by house. The miserable sterile garden of my childhood, small and pruned to the ground by my father, kept becoming the lush beautiful garden of a hotel in the Cotswolds I have known for sixty years, a bit manicured now, but I dreamt it as it was back then. I walked up the garden and it was back in London and there was the nasty rockery at the end. On the rockery were two huge chicks, bigger than seagulls, less aggressive, quite sweet really, with white fluffy feathers and the odd black one and soppy faces. Maybe like albatross chicks in size, though I doubt they smile. There was a small brown round bird like a partridge rushing around between them feeding them. I exclaimed ‘oh these are cuckoo chicks, she thinks she’s their mother.’ I went back to the house, it was London again and I was in my old bedroom looking out and the birds were still there but I was trapped inside as usual.
someone accused me of not being myself.

I was at a gathering of writers and people in the industry, where I was alone. I met another writer I know and we talked about an event that she was speaking at. Someone interviewed me for a newspaper article, which was quite favourable.

I was one of three bikies dressed in leathers etc and I think I might have been male. We were parked in what looked like the main street of a largish country town with shops on either side and a fair number of people. We saw another bikie approaching and when he saw us, he quickly turned into a side street. My two companions said we had to chase him, but I didn't want to and stayed behind. Suddenly I wasn't on my bike and was walking across the street feeling unwell and dizzy. I could see a van approaching fast and I didn't think I could move fast enough to get out of its way because I felt so weak, so I dropped to the ground and rolled out of its way. Then I was in a large room with a coffin at one end and a few chairs arranged in a diagonal line away from the coffin. I thought it was my mother who had died. My sister was there. We discussed how beautiful the flowers on the coffin were and how mum would have loved them. They were enormous oriental lilies whose petals were frilled. I moved up to get to the seat next to the coffin to get a better look, but mum came along and sat on my knee as through she didn't know I was there. It now seemed to be that it was my grandmother in the coffin and that we were in a church with floor to ceiling glass windows behind our chairs. I looked out and saw people arriving including my sister's sister-in-law, Judy and her family, walking passed as though they were coming to the church. Judy was carrying a book as though she was part of a procession. Then she walked back and this time she was carrying a chalice. I realised that she was going to be part of the offertory procession. A priest came over to us and asked mum and my sister to take an item so that they could be in the procession too. I knew he was about to ask me to do the same so I put my head in my hands so that he wouldn't ask.

I was wandering around a village that seemed to be in the Dandenong Ranges. I was with someone from overseas who kept saying that she had always wanted to come here, but it was a lot smaller and less interesting than she's imagined. My partner was there somewhere. He'd bought a new bright red car that I thought was ugly but he loved it because it was powerful. Then I was talking to Helen, a woman I'd once worked with, but not seen for 22 years. She also had a bright red car but hers was a ute. She suggested that we drive to the top of the mountain in it. We got part way, but the mountain was so steep that we kept rolling backwards. After the third try, I got out to do something and she didn't notice so began another ascent. I thought that she'd be back in a few minutes so started walking in that direction. Soon I saw a series of wooden gates and people streaming out of them going downhill. Someone told me that they were tourists who had been to the top on buses. I saw a familiar car park and crossed to wait there and as I did, Helen's car came back and she waved me to a spot where she could stop and pick me up. Nearby we saw a woman we both knew, who asked us to come back to her new house for coffee and the three of us drove off.

I was with some people and trying to find something - a file? . I was looking in an office and a dentist walked in. It seemed that she was my dentist and asked me to get into the chair so that she could examine my teeth. I complied. While she carried out her examination, he told me that her husband had the thing I was looking for. I wandered off to talk to him and he was with a number of people I knew, but haven't seemed very much over the past several years. They seemed to be getting ready for an event. A man came up to me and seemed to know me, although I didn't remember him, yet there was something vaguely familiar about him. I changed by clothes for this event, but wasn't happy with what I had on, so changed again, this time taking off my top in front of several people. Although I was still wearing my bra and faced away from them, both they and I appeared to fell this was inappropriate.

I was at my son's all-boys high school graduation which was held in partnership with a girl's high school. A very young woman made a speech about having to leave school early because she had been pregnant but that in spite of that she had continued to study and was now happy and successful.  I was very impressed. When we got home I understood that it was a year later and there was a friend of my daughter's staying at our house. She told me that she had just been to the next annual high school graduation at the same school and that this time three girls had told a similar story in their combined speech. Suddenly they were all in the house so there were several mothers and babies/toddlers staying with me.   They all went to the shops and I went to different shops wanting to buy fruit pies and I met my friend, Catherine. She told me that I was being too welcoming of all these children - that I should put my own children first. We walked to a nearby beach and had ice creams.   Then I was in the car park of a large shopping centre and one of the young mothers was there, trying to get her little girl of about 18 months into a car seat. I helped her but the child was facing backwards as though she was a baby and I felt sorry for her because all she could see was the back seat. I asked if she could have one of the teddy bears I could see in the front seat but her mother said no, so I found a green frog hand puppet and asked if she could have that. The mother agreed that she could, but I remembered that it was a dog's chew toy and probably had dog saliva all over it. I was too embarrassed to tell the mother and gave it to the child.

I was at home and my cousin was visiting. I was telling her about the first dream I had, but at the time it was not a dream - it seemed to have really happened. She joked that the woman public servant might have been having an affair with my husband. I said, no that that was a different woman.  Then my granddaughter, who seemed about four, although she is actually 13, asked me to read a book called "The Worst Witch" to her. I started to read to her but then I went outside and there were three women in the street, which was some sort of cobbled laneway. They were scrubbing three old baths. I took over scrubbing one of them and it was a pleasant, communal activity. Then they went inside leaving me to it. I stopped scrubbing and saw that, on the corner of the lane there was a tiny key-cutting booth. It occurred to me that when I give workman the key to my house, they could easily come down to the booth and make copies, leaving me vulnerable. My son-in-law Rob was standing beside me and I told him about my concerns. He agreed and we considered how I might avoid this. Then he offered to drive me home and I got in. As he was backing out of his car space, an old Rolls Royce car was also backing out. The old man in it took ages to turn his car and get passed us. Rob knew him and they talked across me through their windows. The cars were almost touching and I couldn't believe they were not scraping against each  other. When we got back to Rob's house, I discovered that they were neighbours and I went in to visit. The old man was now an old woman who told me that she regretted never having time to have children.

I seemed to be some sort of journalist trying to find out about a government secret. I was waiting outside a government building with someone else and a public servant smuggled us in. She took us to a corridor where we sat and I had lunch as some sort of cover - even though it seemed a really inappropriate place to stop and eat. A senior-looking person asked what we were doing there and she said that I was there to translate and showed him a small doll dressed iin a yellow silk dress. He seemed impressed so let us go. She took us down another corridor where we entered a dark office and I started taking notes. rom some papers written in Chinese. Suddenly someone came in and caught us and we ran, splitting up. My friend and I got out about the woman who had let us in was caught.

I was some sort of design expert and I was asked to design something for a national project. I was really please, but then I discovered that they wanted me to do something extremely nationalistic. I felt that rampant nationalist at the moment can be devisive, so said no to the commission. Then I met an old boyfriend, Greg. He asked me to help him teach a photography class, and I thought that might be fun, so agreed. The students were all young adults or older, such I am used ting, so I felt quite confident, but when Greg asked me to compile and number of photographs showing how one might frame individuals  and groups for the most pleasing result, I found old photos from my family and earlier life which were not particularly good examples and I knew it. When I began to run off enough copies for the class, I found that the photocopier was spitting out different sizes of pics and when I wanted a group photo duplicated I was getting just one person in the group. When I wanted an individual's photo duplicated, the photocopier was cutting off their heads. Two photos of my daughter had her head cut off. I didn't have nearly enough copies for the whole class but hoped that I  could get everyone to share. I knew that the class - and Greg - thought that I was hopeless so I was embarrassed, but tried to talk the class through the pics anyway.

I was at some sort of talent quest as a judge. One of the contestants had a superb voice and we wanted to make comment on it, but we were unsure of what pronoun to use. The person was large-framed and tall, wore jeans and a flannel checked shirt, had a low voice and a name that did not allow us to know gender. I was arguing with someone that we needed to go back to the entry forms to see if his/her gender was recorded there so that we could speak to this person without insulting him/her. While they were looking for the form, I wandered outside and found myself watching the performance of a young Asian girl, possibly 8-10 years old. He was in a brightly-coloured, possibly traditional dress. She was in a small shop that had no front and was very shallow. She was brilliant - so graceful and technically perfect, but had no facial expression, as though she was a robot. I spoke to her parents about her and told them how fantastic she was and how she should go in the talent show. They were thrilled.
