Then I suggested that she be coached in expressiveness and they agreed, but there was a man in a grey suit walking with us and I somehow decided that he must be in the Australian government who must have a vested interest in the girl.

I was at a house that seemed to be mine. It seemed to be renovating it. There was a man who appeared to be a senior tradesman and I was telling him how, although my son is not a qualified tradie, he is an extremely precise worker and that when he cuts materials he allows only a one millimetre tolerance although his boss allows three. The older tradesman seemed really impressed by this. I walked into my bedroom and saw my husband there. It seemed that he had been away for a long time and I wanted him to notice the changes I'd made to the en suite, but although he walked in there, he didn't notice. There was a tension between us and not a great deal of affection. We went to another room and he was telling someone, that he was going to have a bet on a horse. I was really angry saying that he knew what happened when he gambled but he told me that he was over that.

I am at RMIT University, going to an orientation lecture for the new students. I am a lecturer, but it is mandatory that I attend. As I am leaving, I bump into my closest friend, Sharyn, who lives in a different city and whom I don't often see face to face. She is there with her husband, brother and sister-in-law and has delivered a talk about her charity and the extraordinary medical research it is enabling. We are both dismissive of RMIT saying that its flashy signage is not only a waste of money, but is misleading. I start to tell her a long story about how when I was doing my Masters there, a sign indicating where to go for the library actually lead me back into the city to the State Library of Victoria instead of the university library.  As I'm telling her this, she is exhibiting signs of exhaustion and we still have a fair was to walk. The others have disappeared, we walk much more slowly and she tells me that the serious chronic illness that she has has been particularly painful and debilitating in recent weeks. We talk about how she should cut back on her workload, but I know she won't.  We finally reach an apartment that she and her husband are staying in while they are in Melbourne and as soon as we get inside, she sits back at her laptop and starts working. Her husband is worried about her and so am I. she has a cavoodle and it is jumping all over me and I can't get it to settle down. Finally, it is driving me so crazy that I leave.

I had come home from somewhere and my daughter was there. She was telling me about something that seemed important, but I was not really following her. There was a knock at the door and an old boyfriend of mine was standing there - my daughter asked him in. As our relationship had ended badly, after two years, I did not want to have anything to do with him. He offered me some very scraggly flowers which I put straight into the rubbish. He told me that he had heard that my current partner was in England and that he thought I'd like to "have fun" while I was on my own. I told him to get lost and walked out. Then I found myself driving into a car park of a large shopping centre and decided to park right near the back so that I would have further to walk to the shops to get fit. I walked with a spring in my step, feeling good about getting rid of the old boyfriend, and found myself in the forecourt of the shopping centre. I looked very deserted. I walked up to a square retail outlet in the middle of the forecourt. I had the sense that it usually sold coffee, sandwiches, cakes etc, but there was nothing on the shelves and no one serving. Someone working at a nearby butcher's shop called out that she was looking after the coffee shop, but it was closed. Two women were standing behind me and as I left, they moved up as if to order from the empty shop. The woman at the butchers called out the same thing that she had told me, and they listened, then ordered coffee and buns. T walked away.

It seems to be early afternoon and I am sitting in a car in an inner city shopping centre with my daughter and a friend from outside the city. We are opposite the hairdressers where I have an appointment. I'm telling the others that I am feeling that I don't want to go in because my hairdresser has recently been married and it rained heavily on that day. I know how much trouble she went to in organising the wedding and that she had hired an open carriage made of crystal to take to to and from the church. I know that she would have been wet and terribly disappointed and I can't bear to hear about it and hear how sad she would be. The friend in the car asks me to book her an appointment for later in the afternoon. I go into the salon and notice that my hairdresser has changed the style and colour of her hair and that there is a table set up for lunch with four woman sitting around it eating. My hairdresser isn't sad about her wedding and seems quite happy. She tells me that her mother is one of the ladies at the table and that they are celebrating an anniversary. I ask about the appointment for my friend but she and another hairdresser explain that there won't be enough time because they need to strip her hair right back then rebuild it.

I am overlooking a classroom in which I need to be and it is filled with very young boys and girls in ballet constumes doing ballet drills. Their is a block of about 20 boys on one side of the room and about the same number of girls on the other side of the room. I comment that they look cute to whomever it is I am with, but feel vaguely impatient for them to finish and leave.  I am with a group of people fighting some evil force. I am either Buffy the Vampire Slayer or she is our leader - the point of view seems to shift.. We identify where we can find the "monster" we need to eliminate  and it is below us, so Buffy/I decide to go down to engage it and to do so, will nned to become one with it. My/her eyes goyellow, but everyone knows that I/she will be okay.

I was at a place that seemed to be a sort of cafe/sort of workplace. A woman I know slightly (Mary) came in and we greeted each other. I wanted to ask after her children, but could only remember her son's name, not her daughter's. She seemed aware that I was struggling and gave me hints. Suddenly I realised that this was a polling booth and that I was second in charge. Then the woman in charge left and I had to take over. It was late in the day and I had to make sure that all the polling place staff had taken their breaks and voted themselves - which is something I should have done hours ago. I started to feel a bit panicked, though not too much. I asked everyone if they had had their lunch and voted and they said yes, so I felt relieved. Then Mary asked if I could tell her where to find this beachside town in West Gippsland. I was trying to show her on a map. It seemed very simple to me but she wasn't getting it. Someone was annoyed with me about a purse or wallet.

I am having drinks with friends at a bar - it appears to be champagne with a lot of fruit in it. We're having fun. Someone who I didn't know that well is hurt or sick and asks me to take her to a doctor. I don't really want to leave the fun, but I find a doctor and keep calling to make an appointment. Finally someone answers and I am told that we must wait about six hours before we can seem him. The sick/hurt person is really not that sick/hurt and I believe that she can wait on her own. I explain that I can't wait around that long and intend to leave, but somehow I'm there for quite a while and the surgery asks me to go back to my car and move it from an ordinary parking space to a loading zone spot. As I go to do so, I see an elderly woman who appears to be a parking inspector leaving the car park and I think I have a parking ticket.

I was being chased, along with several others by someone who was on a killing rampage. I think that we were all law enforcement types, not police though, more like security agents. We ran into a chirch and I ws hiding under a pew, covered in my dark red electroic throw rug. People kept coming up and talking to me, so I was sure my hiding place was poor. Eventually, the killer found me and we had a talk. He said that he was not interested in killing any of us, so I was not scared of him. He explained who and why he was killing, so I felt it was all under control.
I was running a stall selling something. There was a menacing presence in the form of the people visiting the stall.

Drinking with my friends in a pub. No social distancing between us. It wasn't one of our usual pubs.The same familiar in jokes were in play, Lee going to the bar and asking everyone except his partner if they want to a drink.
I was with a friend and we were at an outdoor market.
I was trying to arrange something that needed social distancing and people were not behaving.

I was working in a large stately home, doing my current job. I was sorting out conflict and personnel problems. HR were trying to ignore them and not investigate but I was insisting we had two.  After normal working hours on the Friday a wedding party turned up to hold a wedding in the stately home. I should have stopped it, we make pharmaceutical and are a controlled site, but I was too busy dealing with the disciplinary issues.

I was at a conference. Several old classmates were there from more than 30 years ago. I was standing talking with some other directors from my company, when it became clear they had all been invited to a meeting which I had not. When I asked why, I was told it was because I could not be trusted to keep confidences because my husband works for the same business. I left the conversation very upset.

Staying in a house with a couple of friends. Had a lift and visitors kept getting stuck in it, but there was a trapdoor so they could escape.  One of my friends was acting weird and went off by himself so I had to go and find him.

I was on a night out with friends from work. One of the group decided to cycle home and was hit by a car and killed. We found the accident as we were walking home. we went back to someone's house after the accident. It was the house of someone I have never worked with but who  was I old friend I have not seen for more than 10 years. A group of us stayed up all night drinking, when the sun came up I was surprised I had managed to stay awake as I thought I could not do it anymore. Then my sister turned up with a load of babies to look after, they started crying and I woke up.
I had a dream about poo! I was covered in it, some pointed it out and I was really embarrassed.

Me and my family were in an Italian country and we were walking around through the streets, noticing things like this famous drug house painted pink or this museum with a famous sun balcony. We went into that museum and suddenly it was a house that needed renovating and it felt like the sims but real so I was in charge of it. We went into the bedroom and there were loads of clothes there and me and my friends who were there started picking out things to try on and wear later and there was a disney section with all the little heels and dresses and dress up things so we chose some of those. Then all of a sudden we were taking the Disney stuff in bags downstairs to this massive open hall with raised seats and a stage and when me and scarlett found our mum she was like "hurry up and go get ready itll be your turn soon". We took our bags and went backstage and I had apparently decided to sing "Once Upon a Dream" from Sleeping Beauty and be dressed as her so I got changed and these dancers came in to help me do a dance and practice what the choreography would be. Scarlett was getting ready to do a Snow White one too and we were both excited and then I went and performed and it went okay. After we all had to sit in this long hall and listen to a speech and then suddenly we were in St Ives with tea cups that theyd gifted to us and we had to order from a cafe so I got a scone and everyone else got eccles cake

I was watching a musical about a school but it was all mystical and stuff. Then I was in this whole anime except to me it was real life and Molag Bol from Skyrim was there and I was tiny compared to him and there were lots of subplots

Went on holiday to a dirty horrible place in a little village and it was originally just me and mum but then olly arrived to surprise me so he stayed with us too and my dad arrived at some point cause he was there after a while and then we were packing up to go home but it took like 3 days and the Pikes arrived to spend time with us; me and the boys were upstairs on our Nintendo switches and I was making a scrapbook about Pewdiepie, a woman from Thailand who comes to the pub, and another Youtuber. Eventually we were done packing up and mum sent me and scarlett to the co-op to get some salami or ham but when we got there there wasnt any, just bacon, so we got that instead, and Katie joined us for some reason and picked up some banana peels that were 50p because she wanted them and later called the banana the "Jason Bourne banana" but I never understood why. We also ran into Libby who was looking for mint sauce but couldn't find any so we asked the shop assistant but they said they were busy and to ask the people in the new pirate section so we did and they showed us the herb aisle. When i got back to the cottage Anneliese invited me to stay at hers for a couple of days before uni but that would mean moving in a day later than i wanted and also not seeing olly for an couple days longer than planned so i said no but she said she would sleep on the couch and my mum was pushing me to go so i said yes

Me and my friends were at some kind of farm and we were just walking round, there was a barn first with chickens, kittens, and owls in that one of my friends got distracted with for ages. When we moved on it got a bit weird cause there was a shed with monkeys in really small glass cages like fish tanks and then snakes just roaming loose. My dad got bit and apparently a million other people did too according to him but it wasnt toxic. We kept going and there were these things called Lobs that were like really slimy seals covered in green goo and they were friendly but disgusting. As we walked on we ended up merging with a National Trust property that we weren't supposed to be in but we followed the crowd and ended up with everyone anyway. Me, Scarlett, and my parents were then in a little village with really heavy traffic and we kept trying to buy pizzas but they turned out horrible so me and scarlett sat in the car eating the left overs while mum and dad tried to find some nice pizzas, and Gary from next door was sat in a camping chair just down the road laughing because we had made mistakes with the pizza. Then the car wasnt held by the hand brake so rolled down the road and crashed into another car called Brian but no one really cared. We had to follow mum and dad into a park and down some stairs and then suddenly I was in an underwater cliff place and there were loads of people drinking and the alcohol was in pools everywhere like rock pools so I had a shot of tequila and people were running around with gummy bears and telling me to eat them but they had drugs in I was sure so I didnt. There was a huge octopus singing and it kept asking us to suck its tentacles and Olly was there but not and I kept thinking I could see people I knew but it turned out they weren't real.

Me and my friend were in jail for some reason but we managed to organise an escape plan with a few of our friends and then executed it. We took the grate out of the floor and hid in the space beneath and then when the guards were looking for us we snuck out the door and into various rooms that looked like classrooms. Then we had to sneak into a school and meet up with some people to help us escape but my friend ended up killing someone and we left a trail of clues behind accidentally so we were caught. Everyone at school blamed me and I was lying in bed waiting for my trial and I got a letter from uni saying I wasnt allowed to come anymore or go on placement. I was lying in bed crying for a long time and then I had to go to school and everyone was horrible to me and wouldnt let me near them even though I wasnt the murderer. Then for some reason I had to relive the whole thing again but in more detail, and this time it was Holden from Mindhunter who was driving us to the school after our initial escape and we were making sure he knew that he would be in trouble if we were caught too. We managed to get into the school by pretending to be doing a writing piece for another school and then we snuck round the back of the school and found their vault full of money and jewellery. For some reason I put a diamond necklace on and the caretaker found us and noticed the necklace so was trying to get it off me and my friend killed him by cutting off his head. Then we had to hide the head so we put it in a pram and pretended we had a baby which would have worked if the receptionist hadn't wanted to see it and the wind hadn't moved the blankets. We drove away back to our house which was in the desert and all sat around waiting to be arrested but when I went to go and meet Holden again outside, one of my gang put balloons out the chimney like in Up and tried to make the house fly but instead it just carried him (and the head cause he had it) into the air and away and the house fell down and was destroyed, leaving us all there for the police to find.

I was back at high school but at Tadcaster not Hanley and there were people from.primary there and Richard and Dominic kept hitting on me on the bus and at school and it made me super uncomfortable. Then it was prom and I had this purple and gold tight dress on and I was the last to walk into the room and when I did everyone gasped and said my dress was the best one. When I left the room the dress was now red and like a princess dress and I took a picture in th3 mirror cause I looked like queen elizabeth I. At some.point there was a lesson where I was 5 minutes late and we were tasting sausages and learning about nefertiti. A girl called Felicity came in late and was told off because she had been at the pub with her family in a group of more than 3 which wasnt allowed anymore so everyone was worried about going near her

In English class and we had to write a story as part of an exam so I went and sat outside to do that but everyone was distracting. Wrote a story about a man who escaped some mobs and the mafia or something and went abroad. Then I was going on a plane with my primary school class plus a couple people I know now and my old sixth form tutor was in charge and made fun of me for falling asleep

Olly cheated on me and then we went for a drive and crashed the car by accident and then my parents were mad at me and I had to decide in 2 days whether to stay with olly or not even though he didn't love me anymore because we were living together

I was knitting blanket squares or thinking abut knitting them - they were blue and off white and I was using different knit stitches and patterns on each square to create the whole. I was trying to decide between one pattern and another. Either a flecked diagonal single stitch in each colour or a striped effect. Then suddenly I already had a lot of small squares and was trying to work out how to piece them together to make the blanket pattern work overall. The blanket was being made to go in our new campervan. Some of the blanket squares were a bit thicker than others so the blanket was looking a bit bumpy and I was considering starting again using different techniques.

I was travelling in our new van. It was much bigger than the actual van - like a bus but easy to drive like a car. instead of sleeping in the van I was sleeping in a tent. My son and daughter were with us. It was a happy trip.

I was interviewing asylum seekers in the hostel where they lived. the woman has two young children - a boy and a girl - but they were not hers. She was looking after them but I didn't know why. It was bedtime and she took me from the downstairs room in the hostel to one upstairs. She explained she did not feel safe sleeping in her room downstairs because if the risk of fire. The children were about six. They got into a double bed together and the woman git into a single bed. The room was brightly coloured but the bedding looked rumpled and not very clean. One if the children remarked there were no headboards in the bed but I could see there was one. It was the old fashioned curved type in wood effect Formica and wobbled back and forth as the children jumped around in bed. Then I was due stairs again explaining the research to a man I had interviewed. He was laid on a sofa and didn't seem interested. The woman was back in this room and I was explaining that she had the right to check the write up of the interview and agree it. She told the man it was important and he should listen.  I had the sense I had been there before and then the dream changed and I was telling someone about my experience at the hostel. We were wondering why the woman felt safer upstairs if the risk was fire and I wished I had asked her more questions. I realised I hadn't asked her she and thought about contacting her again. I momentarily appreciated that I was dreaming and decided to go back and ask both the man and the woman more questions but to be very tsctful.

I was camping or in a campervan. With my children who were young again and my partner. The purpose of our trip wasn't a holiday. We were staying somewhere to attend an event. It was cold and we hadn't brought enough bedding. The space we were in was unfeasibly vast and rather damp.

The van was involved. We arrived somewhere in it. There was a birthday cake which I had brought with me. It was very similar to the one I really made for my son yesterday. It was bigger and had white chocolate flakes on top of a dark chocolate buttercream frosting. We were about to eat it but something intervened to stop us cutting the cake. Don't know what.  I remember feeling as if I should be somewhere else doing something but didn't know what.
I was cycling with people. I was trying to remember someone's name but it was always just on the too of my tongue but I couldn't quite get it.
van - I am driving.

I was at a party and also this developed into me retelling events at the party to other people.  I went to a party in a large old house. I experienced the other guests as older than me but they looked middle aged - in their 50s and 60s - so I guess I was younger than I am now. I felt like an observer rather than a participant. As if I had not been invited as a friend but arrived by accident somehow. There was an atmosphere of sexual tension - one woman had auburn hair pinned up and was dancing with an older man. She was wearing a dark rich red/maroon coloured skirt. She slumped on a sofa and let her hair down then lifted her skirt so I could see her upper thighs then her pubic hair. I knew she was masturbating but I didn't see her touch herself.  Then I was on the shore in Argyll & Bute speaking to a young man. He had something to do with the ferry to Bute. He was wearing a mask so I could only see his eyes - they were blue but with very dark lashes and eyebrows. I thought he was handsome. He was wearing a very old fashioned light brown duffel coat of a type I  once wore. He spoke with a Scottish accent and misunderstood me for a tourist from England. I explained I had lived in Scotland for many years then started reminiscing about the party. He remembered stories about what used to go on in the big house on Bute and laughed about it. I showed him a book I had with pictures of the people at the party and we laughed at the clothes and poses.I told him about the Auburn haired woman and he said she probably thought you were gay. I was surprised that he didn't expect me to be and that he thought that was a joke.

I was looking for something in a small northern English town. Not sure at the start  if it was someone or something, I walked along a street of terraced houses and found a shop was open. It seemed to sell secondhand goods - there was old furniture and decorative items such as vases in the window. I went in. There was a young woman smoking, She had her back to me but I knew she was not the person I was looking for but guessed she might be their daughter. There was a portrait of the person I was looking for on the wall. I knew who it was but also that they were dead. I wasn't upset or shocked. The woman was talking to another woman at first as if she was a customer but then I asked to see her work and it turned out she was an artist. The first woman turned to look at me - she was tall with dark short hair and she looked like her mother - the woman in the picture n the wall which was now a photo of a woman in Victorian dress. I told her that she looked like her mother and she laughed. Se was wearing a khaki coloured military jacket and looked quite alternative/punky. I realised I was trying to buy a gift for someone and that I was late for something, I decided I should look at the art.

I was starting a residential course in something to do with writing and/or filmmaking. There was a common room type area with quite a few people in it some of whom I recognised as people from my past. They looked the same as when I knew them although what any of us looked like did not matter in the dream. I knew I had to do something to enrol on the course fully but kept getting distracted by people. Eventually we were asked to sign our names in different colour pens on a large flip chart sheet - one per tutorial group which was going to go on the door of whatever room we were in. I was wondering why I was there and felt a bit as if I had made a mistake - enrolling for a course I had already done. But I was also excited to be going back to learning in a group.

I was trying to get somewhere but was riding a broomstick which was new to me but not surprising. There was a woman with me I knew her. She was a more accomplished broomstick rider than me. I was practicing my  flying skills in a car park but she went ahead and I decided I needed to catch up. I found that if I lost concentration the broomstick dipped towards the ground and slowed down. I had to really focus to make it fly fast, straight  and fairly high - even so we were flying only about 8ft above the road and this seemed normal - as if everybody did it. A woman joined us. She was known to me. I didn't like her but I felt a connection with her. She was upset about something and I comforted her by putting my arm around her as we flew. She was wearing a soft black jacket which felt like sheepskin or some other warm soft animal skin type fabric. I decided I might like her more than I thought. I also was surprised that I could fly fast while talking to her and thinking about her instead of focusing on flying.  We both caught up with the other woman and realised we were being pursued by a man on a motorbike. It became clear that we needed to get somewhere before we were caught. I was confident that we would get there. The flying felt exhilarating.

I was involved in a journey which seemed to be some sort of driving competition. We stopped our van and I was showing someone how easy it was to sleep in the van. I stretched out sideways across the van which was much wider than it is in real life and was pleasantly surprised how wide it was. I then showed the person watching how I could sleep on the parcel shelf which was surprisingly comfortable. I thought I had been very clever to find such a comfy spot but when I got off the parcel shelf it was sagging and looked a bit broken. There was definitely some driving action after that

I was working for Pete again and so was my son Anthony.  It was something to do with catering but we had accidentally got involved in something illegal - possibly smuggling as the dream included unpacking boxes. I was warning Anthony to be careful and not to get involved.  The builder mg we were in was very bare and clean and clinical looking with great shiny floors and plastic looking walls. We were talking to each other in a stairwell and I was leaving as he was entering. Then the dream switched to outdoors. I was talking with Lauren, Anthony's girlfriend. She was working in Dunbar. I was surprised as that's a long commute from Glasgow but she said she enjoyed the driving. I was a bit envious because she had a job writing and I wanted a job writing. I felt I was better qualified than Lauren but didn't say do as I wanted to be nice to her. I looked up and saw Pete walking away from us down the street. It was sunny and warm. I decided to catch up so I could talk to him.

I was catching a train with my partner Cam. The livery was pale mint green. It was an old fashioned design with individual compartments linked by a corridor. We were carrying very heavy old fashioned suitcases without wheels. The seats were filling up so Cam rushed to put the suitcases on board while I found a compartment for us. After the train pulled out of the station we wanted something from our cases but when we went to get them there was a locked door between our carriage and the next. The door was green, scratched with graffiti. I kicked it in anger. The dream switched to home but not the home we live in now. We were talking about having to rent somewhere in London because I had found work there. But Cam had agreed a lease on somewhere tiny where there wasn't even room for a table. I was cross with him and we had an argument. I was worried about being stuck somewhere depressing - dark and cramped for months and paying for storage on our large table. I felt like crying but shouted at Cam instead. Then I was in a car travelling through Edinburgh. But I was also watching a film in which Alan Rickman was driving a car. I was both in the film and watching a film. It was unmistakeably Edinburgh but it was wreathed in smoke wafting in layers like mist. Over to the west there were twin plumes of very dark smoke spiralling up - I seemed to know why that was and what had happened and started explaining it. It had something to do with deforestation. Then I was telling a funny story to a friend about bumping into Emma Thompson and her mum having tea in a cafe. But while I was telling the story I was also in the cafe reliving that experience. Emma Thompson was wearing an off white woollen coat and matching dress. Her mother was elderly and looked like her but wasn't anything like her real mother. The cafe looked like someone's sitting room and I joked with Emma that the woman standing by the door who was dressed as waitress (apron, black skirt, white blouse) looked so surprised to see us that perhaps it was just her sitting room. At that point I realised this was a dream and found myself back in the role of telling the story of when I met Emma Thompson rather than being there.

I was driving along a country road looking for a small country home - an off grid hut. Saw it - it was Nissen hit style - an arch of corrugated metal with a brick front. It was nestled in a very bright green grassy field with a slight hill behind. Inside it was much bigger than it looked on the outside. It was cold but there was a woodburning stove but I did not understand how it worked. It was dark black metal box in the middle of the room with a very big metal chimney running up to the ceiling. Behind it there was a glass box with a fire in it. My partner seemed to know how it worked. He turned a handle and the fire in the glass box grew bigger and then he explained that the heat would trigger the fire in the more normal looking black metal stove. He warmed me to keep away from the heat and then a jet of hot air was released with a whooshing noise and I felt very warm. The room was well-furnished and very neat. I felt like I was there by mistake - I was anxious about the owners coming back as if I shouldn't be there.

I was in a village with some grand large stone houses. I headed for one set back from a sharp bend in the road. There was an open day or village fete type event on. I was with my partner Cam. We stepped into a student be portico/verandah area where a woman wearing old fashioned country tweeds was talking to other people. There were homemade cakes which she invited us to try. One was still being baked. It was a  flat chocolate sponge - a rectangle like a Swiss roll sponge but it was being baked under a silicone sheeet with wires leading to it which I understood to be a new way of baking cakes.  We didn't eat any and went inside. We seemed to know why we were there and now I felt like a detective looking for something and solving a mystery.  We went down some steps and opened a door. The room was only partially visible from the threshold. It was large and laid out like a gentlemen's club with deep brown leather sofas and armchairs. There were men in there but I could only see one. He was wearing a dinner jacket - black tie. He wore a mask. It was black and metallic green and covered his whole head like a ball making him look a bit like a fly - a shock by greeny blue blowfly or similar.  I felt afraid. He told us to leave and implied I was obviously in the wrong place because I was a woman. He didn't acknowledge Cam.  Cam and I retreated, turned a corner and stood with our backs to a wall. I said something derogatory about the man. I also said something about how we could come back and get into the room later. Then I heard the man's voice through the wall. There was an old metal grill in the wall crusted with yellowed paint and dust. I knew he had heard what I said and felt annoyed with myself for being caught out. The voice told us to leave and warned us not to try getting into the room again. I was frightened and remembered thinking this was something to do with dark magic. I realised that even if I left they could get me using spells. Cam and I hurried away but were surprised nothing bad happened to stop us leaving. I was scared but also planning how to return and get over the problem posed by the evil man.

I was staying at a holiday shack and it was my birthday. Seb came in early in the morning to give me my present. It was a book and scattered throughout the book were postcards and cards. I wondered why he had to wake me up so early. I checked my social media to see who had wished me a happy birthday but nobody had and I felt disappointed. Someone had given me a kitten for my birthday - a ginger kitten. I asked what the cat's name was and a woman I used to work with said 'Otago' but I wanted to call the cat Pablo. The kitten was exploring all the nooks and crannies in the shack and seemed to grow bigger by the minute. We had to leave the shack and I was with a man I didn't know in a small bus. We went down a very steep hill at Wollongong and went to pick up this guy who lived on a wharf. The guy who lived at the wharf told me that he had once wanted to be really muscly and bulky but he'd had an accident and realised it wasn't worth it. Now he lived in a shack by the wharf because he didn't care about money and possessions and the shack had only cost him $2000 to buy. He had covered the outside of the shack with old Persian carpets to keep it warm. He said the council came to visit twice a year and he had to make sure the shack was in good condition then otherwise they would say it was uninhabitable.

I was in a shopping centre with 2 other women I didn't know. We were looking for the exit but got stuck in a tunnel that seemed to go forever. I could see other people leaving the shopping centre via the automatic doors but for some reason we couldn't do that - we were stuck in the tunnel and hoping that if we kept following it, we would find our way out. We eventually got a room like a commercial laundry. The tunnel had ended and there was nowhere else to go. I was thinking, 'we can just walk out the way we came' but then I thought, 'I bet the door behind us has closed' and when I turned around, the door we had come through was blocked off with a giant black metal panel. It was frightening to think we were stuck in this room but at the same time I was thinking, 'I knew this was going to happen. It's happened before in other dreams.' Beside the giant black metal panel was a set of metal stairs. There were 2 Asian men sitting on the stairs. We told them we were stuck in the room but they didn't care. It was as if they knew we were coming and they were somehow involved in the fact that we were stuck there.

At swimming pool in changing rooms. They were busy. I had forgotten to come swim ready. It slowed me down. I had two new swim hats to choose from. Went into pool. It was packed. I was expecting two other people but there were over 20. Had to ask lifeguard which lane to swim in. Got in but really hard to swim. People congregating at end of lane chatting. Swimming felt hampered. Discovered tiny boy clinging on to me. Got to end of lane and he belonged to a good looking guy. Tony, very old work colleague was there too. Headed back off to swim but like swimming in sludge. Stopped midway and my husband was there. Moaned to him about how busy it was. Carried on. Tried a few more lengths. Saw other side of pool was quiet so went over there, I was swimming but only in really shallow water. Like a solid shape under the surface. Moved over to find better deeper water. It was empty. Thought to myself where is everyone, Realised my time was up. Heard someone say they are looking fo a swimmer who hasn't got out in their 45 min time Got out of the pool to find myself in London street scene.

I was with my ex-girlfriend, about age 19, and she was going on a date with a man. She was all dressed up. I was surprised because I thought she (like me) was gay. I was upset that she going on a date with someone else and got the feeling she didn't want to be with me anymore. In the dream I was wondering if she would have treated me that way if we were a heterosexual couple, and I expected she wouldn't. At some stage, she was sitting next to me in a cinema and she was naked and she realised the usher was going to come and chastise her for being naked.

I carried out a supermarket sweep type run in a strange dress shop.  Then I was in a hall of a grand house and a posh man said ‘let the lady keep the dress sir.’ It was like a period drama.  Later I was dog walking with my friend H.

I was chatting with a man I know called Ed.  Then it turned all ‘sci fi.’ I was hunting down a gang of ‘Custom bikers’ armed with a strange staff like weapon, under orders from my favourite singer. It took in some fantasy landscapes, underground tunnels, rivers, boats.

I was in a dome and someone was fighting.  Then I was using facewax strips.   Then my best friend and I were running away from someone unknown. Our car blew up so we hid in a petrol station. Then we were on a bizarre farm that people can visit but the animals weren’t real. They were a cross between lions and wild boar but bizarre colours and friendly. Then I was in a hotel or big old house and had a massive sack of apples with me. I was waiting to meet my favourite singer. I moved to a room where I was waiting for some people I didn’t know to finish preparing whatever they were working on - cotton buds, gherkins and hair dryers.

I was texting someone called Mark to say that I didn’t think we should see it each other anymore. It had been a long distance relationship with little communication and I hadn’t seen him for months but had remained faithful. It was like a switch - I went from being invisible to being really fanciable and it felt like such a relief. Various people said if I was up for it they’d like to take me out - including people who I’d worked with in real life and also blokes kept confiding in me that they were in sexless relationships and could I help out. I was invited to various parties, met celebrities and then the action shifted and I was at work. It was a big sort of call centre and we were all crammed in and I can remember being okay with that - feeling popular and safe and loved. People gave me presents and I was toiling the garden outside and cooking dinners and flirting a fair bit with various people and someone I really liked was offering hints that they’d like to take me out but in a push me pull me sort of way. And then I was putting on the jewellery and faffing with courgettes

heading to the cinema at what felt like the end of term. I was sitting next to M who was an old lecturer of mine and he was dropping various witticisms throughout the film - several of the which appeared in a review (“he doesn’t think with his heart but with a different part of his body altogether” - this seemed incredibly witty At some point we weren’t at the cinema but in a lecture theatre and L - a not very nice manager from my work place was giving a talk on something or other. My Mom appeared and said how she’d worked with him in the past and didn’t like to speak ill of people but she’d make an exception with him. We were told to evacuate the lecture theatre and some kids leapt to it and converted the steps into a sort of ramp thing and then D also from work started handing out sandwiches.

I was at college and Russell Howard was too - he wanted to help me with my writing because he had been published in the past although the subtext was that we were going to get off with each other. Other blokes turned up at my house - they were like a really nerdy bunch but also not very nice so RH told them to do one but not before they’d made a mess of the lounge - it was the lounge at the house I’d grown up in and I knew my Dad would be cross if we left it. However me and RH were a bit distracted. He was giving me a hug and he had an enormous erection. He gave me a wink and a nod ‘yep I’m blessed’. We laughed. I really liked him. He was nice, suburban  - Dad was back though and cross about mess and that I’d bought a boy back. He’s helping with my writing I explained. Dad shot me a look. Later RH sent a card saying he loved meeting my hippy parents and this smoothed things over. I waved him off in the rain. I felt like I was on the verge of something; felt popular and liked.

I was working as a lawyer - there was a big meeting looming and an evening dinner and I joined the table to find my friends P and K were there. They’d saved me a place and I was pleased about that. We started chatting and swearing - I kept saying bastard really loudly and got the impression people were not very happy. I showed P a crayon I had purchased - it was double ended and red one end and sort of ochre the other. He wasn’t impressed and I can remember feeling a bit cross. I decided to return it to the shop where I’d bought it - it was late opening and the man working there was wearing all these badges - all smile, it’s a beautiful day and don’t be moody etc. I found this irritating. I was late getting back to work myself then - but it was okay because R was there and gave me a hug. Around us young women in states of undress or older women in 1980s clothes were sort of hanging about. My boss said he was casting for a play - the lead part went to someone called Sam - we were aware that Sam was destined for great things. I started looking through my briefcase and there was talk of medical examinations - someone had been scratched and we (me and R) needed to trace it. The women started saying how it was self inflicted and showed me there really long nails.

I met Sean Bean at some sort of gig or backstage party - it was late and I was wanting to get home but he was about to leave and said I could meet him at 4am. He let me stroke his arm and was spraying aftershave around and I felt daft because I thought he wanted to share a drink with me. Anyway he left and I was conscious I had to stay awake so I ended up mooching around an art gallery - I was doing a jigsaw at one point and shoplifting stuff and I got lost at the back of the museum - in this really ornate part and a builder had to direct me outside. But I still had time to kill so I went back inside and saw my mate Cathy. She was doing an exhibition about Greek art and then my Mom turned up and started making dodgy comments about Cathy and her gay friends and I was like hissing at her to be quiet. Cathy heard and was cross and told me she didn’t want to go for drinks and I was knackered but still had time to kill. I ended up looking for a bus stop and bumped into someone I used to work with and she was lost too and panicking. Then Sean Bean turned up - he had a funny haircut and was being stupid and showing off and I remember wondering if he was just acting the part or if he was like that in real life.

I was moonlighting and doing some work for BT. It was a fairly rubbish admin job not much above a work experience role and my boss was useless. The team leader was lovely though and was in charge of lifts. We were evacuated because there was some police training going on and they were worried about them being targeted by a knife man - I wasn’t so much scared as quite excited by this. She decided to take me on a tour of the other buildings and I was introduced to various Union people wearing lanyards. Nice lady seemed dejected - she couldn’t join the union something I vowed to sort out. We bumped into WA - he was wearing a shirt tucked very tightly into high waisted trousers and looked a bit fat. Nice lady sensed an atmosphere and wondered if we had history. I mumbled yes and WA proceeded to explain that we had shagged in the past and I was more into it than him. I was dead embarrassed and started worrying about this but with an immense sense of relief realised I could just leave this job. I told nice lady I wasn’t coming back and there was talk of how she didn’t blame me but could I please return any cooking utensils I had used. WA was cross and asked who would bring his Mom into work now but I was like, “see ya”

So I was working at a school with people from work - there was some sort of inspection looming and tensions were high, particularly amongst I and M. I was stressed out but being really amusing about it and M was adopting a sort of Mr Chips demeanour - patting young lads on the head and being chummy. D also worked there - D was someone I worked with ages ago at a not very academic college and he’d decided to produce some literature to show what a fab place we all worked at. Only said literature made it all look very sexist and 1950s and me and I thought this was hilarious. It was a mixed school and my task was to make sure the girls were all dressed in proper school uniform - they totally weren’t and I had to go out and buy regulation bras which the girls who all seemed to have 1980s big hair refused to wear. A kind of riot ensued in the playground (which was very vividly depicted - all slate grey stone and surrounded by Victorian buildings) and I had to deal with that - but I wasn’t scared more thrilled at the prospect.

I was visiting the home of a man I was interviewing for a journal, it was the home where his mother had grown up, and his parents still lived there. It was a big estate on the Mornington Peninsula, and it was on a lovely sprawling bushy property. The bedrooms were spacious and colourful, and they'd furnished the house with lots of beautiful antiques. I thought it was really beautiful and special, and I was wandering around imagining what it would be like if my ex-boyfriend and I lived there in the future. I felt really happy and full of love and excitement for the future, trust in the future, and hope for the future.

I was at a festival of some kind with a group of people I didn't know well, and I felt self-conscious to come across as cool. The look of the festival was quite "circus-grunge", and there was lots of graffiti around. One of the people I was with was showing me his tattoos. We sat at a table and ordered chips and fried chicken, and the layout of the restaurant was designed to make the wait staff bump into the patrons anytime they got up to move, so it was cramped and a little stressful. After we'd eaten, we went to another area where there was a haunted house experience, and we walked through a pitch black underground dirt tunnel. I was terrified, as I often am when in the dark, and was grabbing onto the person in front of me even though I'd just met them. There was a doorway partway down, and we entered and it looked like a clinic room, lit with blue-white lighting. There were two sleeping cats in there, and I realised that my very close work colleague/friend was with me, as well as a best friend from high school. our task was to take care of the cats, but the room was uninviting and dirty with cat poo on the carpet and I was really eager to get out. I'm also not hugely fond of cats. I was feeling quite anxious to move on, but the other girls were enjoying themselves. We eventually went back into the dark tunnel, and when we got to the other side, we were in the foyer of a theatre. The doors to the stage were open, and I could see that there was a Harry Potter musical being performed by a ballet company. I loved the music and felt inspired to dance, so did some ballet in the foyer watching in. It felt very freeing and relieving to dance. I spotted my parents with an old family friend in the crowd, and I was so happy to see them, but for some reason I didn't say hello.

I was in a Japanese restaurant with my best friend and a girl from high school, and she was giving my best friend a going away present because she was moving overseas. It was an iPad, and it was the second iPad my best friend had received as a going away present. We needed to order but I was getting stressed because there was so much on the menu and I couldn't decide. I went to go to the bathroom, and all of a sudden I was in my parents' house in the bathroom attached to my old room. I masturbated with a bottle of face wash. Then I went to use the toilet, but it flooded, and I had to clean it up with towels. It was stressful.

I was packing up to leave college as I was graduating. My friendship group was with me, packing up too. I was putting rubbish and old food from the kitchen in big black garbage bags, and containers of feta were spilling and leaking everywhere. It was sunny. I felt kind of neutral, pleasant but not particularly happy. My ex-boyfriend was with me, and we were together. We went to our last class, and the premier of the state I live in was our lecturer/tutor, and he was really frustrated at us because we kept talking and weren't listening to him. I was being cheeky and quite rude, but then I felt really bad and wanted to show him I respected him.

I was walking through the snow with two other people, and walking through the town, it was clear that society was very poor and there was a lot of crime. I felt a bit tense and out of place and unsafe. I saw two women squatting on the side of the road to pee, in the middle of the day. We got to a sheltered, hidden spot behind a brick wall and I was sexual assaulted by the two others (male and female), but I was watching the scene as an on-looker. Eventually I walked off through the snow, and I realised I was being searched for by police for some crime, I think it was drug-related. I arrived at a cafe where I worked, and my sister was also working there. My mother was a customer, sitting at a table eating a toasted chicken schnitzel sandwich while she was babysitting a baby in a pram, who was my sister's baby. I was really busy at the cafe (even though there were hardly any customers, and the manager kept asking me to do this, but I didn't really know how to do anything because I was a new employee, and I realised I was still in my pyjamas. I ran outside where there was a tent and tried to find clothes to change into, and I did, but was frustrated because they were equally inappropriate, I think just a rain jacket with nothing else. I went back to the cafe and I looked at the television and saw that police were on the hunt for the CEO of the company I work for, because he was involved in a sexual assault. I realised that's who had assaulted me earlier. But I felt compassion for my CEO, I think he's a really wonderful person, so I felt worried for him. But he handled it gracefully and resigned. I felt a sense of loss. There was a scene of police interrogating him in my old primary school.

I'd stayed the night at a friend's apartment, although I didn't recognise the apartment, and was packing up the room, folding the bed sheets and even taking furniture down to my car. On the way to the car, my mother surprised me by giving me a favourite silver tea set of hers and some pistachio biscotti. It was Easter and my auntie and uncle were there. After we'd left the apartment, we drove off and it lit on fire. There were lots of babies and young children with their doll houses and toys being protected from the flames by their fathers. There were scary beasts coming out of the flames and naked women riding them. It was sexual but I was scared. We drove off and then it was just myself, Amelia and the body of a man in the car, who was the 'third man' in a list of people we needed to kill. It was sunrise, and we saw dinosaurs coming over the hill. I felt terrified, but having Amelia there stopped me from freaking out. It was a very apocalyptic scene, with big fire balls appearing off in the distance. As the dinosaurs approached I realised they looked quite silly with googly eyes and I became less scared, but felt a little nauseous.

I was at my old primary school, and there was some kind of night-time event happening. There were lots of kids there and we were playing pass the parcel. I got the parcel and decided to give it to the cutest kid there, and then she got the prize inside, and I felt really guilty for choosing the winner just because she was cute when the other less cute kids deserved it too. Then there was a performance, and I was in the audience but had to leave early because I had to go back to my ex-boyfriend's house to stay the night. I was trying to quietly sneak out, but I had a lot of belongings to carry, including a mattress, pillow and blanket, and I was really frustrated trying to juggle everything. I was also anxious because I was running late. I decided to carry half of my belongings, but then I lost the other half and was stressed. I went to the principal's office to say goodbye to my auntie, who is the principal, but she was playing piano and couldn't hear me say her name. I waved vigorously, and she was looking right at me, but couldn't see me and kept playing. It was really creepy and I was scared. Eventually she waved back. I ran out to get to my car, which was parked really far away, and I was running because I was late, but I couldn't run. It felt like I was running in honey, or likely my muscles had no energy to do it. I realised I had a roller blade on one foot, so could just glide there, and it was really freeing and relieving. I got to my car but then a friend grabbed me and reminded me that we were bridesmaids in another friend's wedding, and that the wedding was happening in 5 minutes. I was really stressed because I hadn't done my hair or makeup, I didn't have a dress and I was hot and needed a shower. I ran back to the school and was helping the other bridesmaids get ready but I still wasn't ready. I realised my dress was back at my car, so I sprinted there, but by then my car was a tent. It was really hot in the tent and there were three dogs in there who were really hot. I felt guilty and worried about them in there, but had to get back to the wedding. I realised the only dress I had was a white sequin dress which looked too much like a bride's dress. I was really stressed and sweaty and dusty and running late.

I was in the backyard playing jump-rope with my dad, and I was yelling and screaming at him because he was doing it wrong, but it was like he couldn't hear me. I was so mad that he wasn't listening. I stormed off and went working down the street, which was a dirt road, and eventually I was travelling in a cart being pulled by people along the dirt road. I think slowly I transitioned to being in Cambodia, and the people pulling the cart were local people. feeling awkward, and I just kept my head down and read my book. It was really hot, and I kept losing my place in the book. It was frustrating and I kept getting interrupted and re-reading the same passage of text. Eventually we arrived at an outdoor kitchen where a woman was teaching a class on how to make dumplings, and the time was up for the class so everyone started trickling away, but she wasn't finished making the dumplings yet, she had 5 more minutes until they were done. I felt awkward and embarrassed that the other classmates were leaving, which felt rude since she wasn't finished, but also I needed to leave because my sister was waiting to pick me up. I felt torn between staying and being polite and respectful to the teacher, or leaving and being respectful to my sister who was waiting.

I was on a balcony talking to a man about how he and his wife were going to commit suicide because summer was over and there was no reason to live if it wasn't warm and summery. His wife jumped off the balcony first, down the centre of a stairwell, and it took 8 seconds for her to land. The husband counted down the seconds, and then covered his ears with his hands and yelled out "SAFE" when she landed to cover the noise. Her body was seriously distorted and I thought she was the dead, but then I saw her moving a bit, and I realised she was still partly conscious but the top half of her body was detached from her legs and hips. It was horrific and terrifying and I felt disgusted and shocked and scared. The husband was going to jump next.

I was on a small plane and it was flying erratically, doing big dips and turns and at one point threatening to go upside down. I was really scared, and we were flying quite low. The plane descended to land, and landed briefly, but then took back up and eventually crashed. We were stranded, and I was with an old family friend who was crying about missing her teenage daughter and not being with her for Christmas. In this place where we were stranded, there was a man who was trying to be the leader, and he said he was going to banish school for the children among us who were stranded. But I was the tutor/teacher and I was really worried about the effect that may have on the children. People seemed to be supporting this man though, and I felt isolated and fearful.

I was being held hostage by two men, but mainly one man. I was terrified, and kept trying to get through locked doors and run through the house to get out without being seen. But at the same time, I was hosting guests and had to cater for them and talk to them, so that was really stressful and I felt torn between trying to get away and fulfilling my duties. I eventually got out one of the doors to the outside and my heart was racing. I sprinted across the property, which looked kind of like the garden and outdoor area of my primary school. I was jumping over wire fences and hiding behind rose bushes. I thought I'd almost got out off the property but I turned a corner and the two men were there. I felt sick to my stomach and terrified. I felt nauseous with fear even. The main one had an evil smirk on his face, and said something to me about me trying to get away but not being able to because he was smarter than me. Then all of a sudden, I felt intense attraction to him, and we were standing close, and all of the terror dissolved and I realised I had Stockholm Syndrome, where you fall in love with your captor. Our faces were close, and I really wanted to kiss him. He had beautiful hair and lips and I felt good. We kissed and it was wonderful and soft and slow. I felt amazing.

I was walking through the streets in my nightie, it was morning and I was really really exhausted. I had to climb and crawl around all these concrete obstacles to get home, but I was so tired. At one point I had to squeeze under a slab of dirty concrete, in my nice silk nightie, and it was really cramped and barely big enough to fit through. I eventually got home and there were people over at the house, which felt strange and exciting but uncomfortable because that's illegal at the moment. I was really turned on and wanted to watch porn on my laptop but people were there and I kept trying to conceal it and it was uncomfortable and frustrating. Eventually I gave up and started to get dressed for work, it was a hot day so I picked a revealing outfit with strap sandal heels. When I got to work my manager shamed me for my outfit (with her eyes), and pointed out that one of my buttons at my breasts was undone. I feel awkward and embarrassed. I realised I wasn't at work yet, I was actually at some kind of awards ceremony and my manager was there. So I left the venue to catch a cab to work, but the cab that pulled up had a driver that was in the back seat, asking me to drive, and she looked drunk and really dishevelled. I didn't want to get near her, so I ran to a bus stop to catch public transport to work, but couldn't work out the streets and the bus numbers and felt really overwhelmed. I jumped on one that I thought was right, but it took me to this outdoor amphitheatre that was famous for it's beautiful greenery and garden. However when I got there, all the greenery was gone and it was bare and there was lots of concrete. I felt sad that they'd decided to get rid of the garden, because it was so beautiful and full of ferns, which I love. I was still trying to get to work, so I decided to walk, but ended up at the beach. There was a girl there who was trying to plant a rose bush, but of course there was only sand, so she planted it in the sand but it was so hot and dry and unsuitable that the rose bush dried up and was crispy and dead. I followed the girl back to a house where she started to make a chocolate smoothie, and I realised I was at my ex-boyfriend's mother's house, and the girl was my ex-boyfriend's mother's young daughter. I started cleaning the young girl's dishes, and I felt anxious to impress my ex-boyfriend's mother with my cleaning skills and by doing a proper job, but in my anxiousness I used too much detergent and then felt tense because my ex-boyfriend's mother doesn't like to waste things and is really frugal with things like detergent.

I was in my childhood bedroom with my dad, and we were talking and joking about something, and suddenly he seized up and grabbed is arm/shoulder and fell to the ground with this horrible haunted look on his face. I think he was having a heart attack. I was absolutely terrified, I love my dad so dearly and the thought of this happening breaks my world. I realised I didn't have my phone on me to call emergency services, so I tried to call out for my mum but the shock made it hard to speak/yell. Eventually I was able to yell out to her, but I don't think it was loud enough. It was so disturbing

I was with a small group of people in a modern mansion, and we decided to take a bath, but the bathroom was full of damp dark leaves. The colour scheme of the bathroom was very dark, it was unwelcoming, and the bath itself was black. One person dived into the leaves and it took them to a place where they were surrounded by their worst fears. They didn't come up for a long time and there was a little bit of thrashing around in the leaves, and I thought they were drowning. I was really stressed and worried, but they eventually came back up. Later, another person dived in. I was too terrified to do it.

Me and some other guy were a team in a tournament that was like a strategy/battle, and the last team alive won. I was really attracted to my teammate, and I was kind of flirting with him and he liked me back. There was a battle with five different types of werewolf, which was really scary. There was also a challenge where you had to swim through the murky river in London, which was particularly scary because I hate deep water or water that you can't see through.

I was stirring this pot of broth, and a few friends were with me, and I realised the pot of broth was going to bring Voldemort back to life. But I knew I had to do it and then destroy him again. I was terrified. He came back to life, and we started battling, but after a while my wand stopped working. I kept trying to throw spells at him but it would work, it was frustrating and scary. One of Voldemort's side-kicks got hit in the spine and was in a lot of pain on the ground and I felt really bad and guilty because I didn't want anyone other than Voldemort to be hurt or killed, so we made up a milky herb tea and gave it to her to soothe her. Then we all tried to run away and escape because I couldn't keep battling if my wand didn't work, and we were running through the city, there was so much concrete everywhere and there was a lot of damage and trash. The city felt very apocalyptic and abandoned, except there were still lots of people around but they were very anxious and scared as they ran around the city. I felt really unsafe. We finally made it to a building and went up to an apartment where my high school best friend lived, and it was more calm there but I still felt anxious about the outside world. We were trying to decide what to have for lunch. When we looked out the window the city looked so damaged and there were plumes of smoke and destroyed buildings. It was mayhem and I realised it was because of COVID-19. We turned on the television and the journalist was interviewing two flight attendants on a crowded tram, and the attendants were explaining that there are only a few flights out and they were encouraging people to get out quick. I felt anxious and torn about what to do.
Was with a colleague, who said that he had come straight from the airport to work

Was with some friends from university who I haven’t seen in years. For some reason I sat on my friend’s boyfriend’s lap and he started touching me inappropriately in front of everyone, including her and my husband
a house, it was a big house that I didn’t recognise, maybe somewhere in mountains or hills. I think it was my house.

I was in a yoga teacher training with one of my teachers and one of my friends, and we were talking about my friend, who is very strong and flexible. Then, either in the same dream or a slightly separate dream, I had to rush to a lecture theatre for the next session and my husband was with me. But I really needed to per and was on the look-out for a toilet. When I found it I realised I wasn’t wearing any shoes and was grossed out by walking barefoot in a toilet. But the ladies’ toilet was closed so I had to wander around a bit more and when I came back lots of people had arrived, as if from a festival. I’m not sure if this makes it a lucid dream but at that point I said to myself that I should just wake up and go to the toilet.

We were on a big house, I was in a large group of people and I think pretty much everyone was familiar. There was conversation etc for a while and then some people left and I was left with a couple of guys, one of whom wanted to kill me. So he was chasing me around the house, in the garden, I did some acrobatics at some point and hid somewhere for a while.
I had to protect something so I had to kill people but I had to keep my leg immobile somehow

the story of Alice in Wonderland but I was Alice The most vivid scenes were where I was "not the right Alice", explaining to Hamish why I don't want to marry him and realising it is my responsibility to save the Jabberwocky but not knowing how to wield the Vorpal sword when I try.

I was observing myself go through my day at work. There was no dreamlike qualities, it was like watching my own memories play out. The order of events was the same and I was standing at the shoulder of the other person so I watched myself in all the interactions. When nobody was there I was in the corner of the room still watching myself type or make calls.  The conversations sounded like they had in my real day. When I was observing text message conversations I was looking over my own shoulder sty phone on my desk. The song "watermelon sugar high" was playing all through the dream.

I am at an old work place. A single story building on farm land with a number of rooms. There is deep snow. Two of the service users from my current work are living there. I am explaining that I can't go to sleep until I take the puppy out for a toilet. They are telling me not to go out in the snow and showing me tracks from other animals walking around the property.  I am talking with them about vikings. They look after my dog and I go outside and see a large stag walking away. I try to follow the tracks. It is dark but the moon reflects off of the snow.  I have to try to stop the death of residents in a nursing home. Running through corridors that are blocked with hospital beds - a boy, aged around 12, is leading the way. He has learned the sequence needed to get through the automatic doors.  There is someone else running alongside us but I think only I can see her. I am talking to her about something bad and the boy is telling me not to because "you don't know what's coming" We enter a room and there are 5 old fashioned metal hospital beds all in a row with their headboards against the opposite wall. The men in the beds are all on their left side and all are dead staring at us with dead eyes. I recognise the man in the middle, he is the only one with glasses. It looks like something was poured in each of their right ears and that's how they died.  I am running out the front door of the care home, it is a single story bungalow with beige bricks. It is snowing heavily and there is a Victorian terrace of houses ahead of us. I can see a lot of black cabs parked with headlights shining at a building and an old lady is coming up from cellar stairs onto the street. She is frail, naked and with long white hair pinned up on her head. One of the men waiting at the black metal fence wraps a kimono around her. There is something written on the back of it, a warning to others of what type of woman she is. I am crying and I try to go her but I can't move or speak, I watch them drive her away. She turns and looks back, I know she saw me. I know this will happen to me one day.

Someone had died and there was an argument going on about the will. Two sides of a family who both thought they should have a certain item  I was not a part of the family but was working for one side.  Something happened on a bridge, I remember s row of bodies. A boy I knew in primary school was an adult in the dream. He was explaining to me what was happening, he was wearing an over-sized chunky cable-knit beige jumper and the sleeves fell down to his elbows when he moved. We had been having sex and were laying in a make-shift bed on a paved area on a courtyard talking about what had happened with the other side and how we would get back what was stolen.

service users, at the supported housing for adults with mental illness and addiction, where I work.  The accomodation was my secondary school building. There was a conversation with one of the service users who is a gambling addict and paranoid schizophrenic. I was trying to help him with a task but I don't think I could. At some point during the conversation I became aware that I was dreaming. One of the female service users had two small children. When I collected her from Gravesend and took her back to the home we were talking about schools. I was saying that if you can afford it then you should send children to schools where they have freedom to develop at their own pace and more outdoor learning. There were 2 other women on the train with us who agreed. The baby was sitting on my lap, the 3yr old on the service users. I ended the conversation saying I hadn't been able to afford it but my sons had a Montessori nursery before school and that was the best for them if anywhere they've been. I was regretting that I couldn't do better for them for statutory schools. Then I was phoning the same service user for welfare checks, she had left the baby at the seevice and wanted someone to bring him to her. I was explaining that I couldn't bring him to Tunbridge Wells because I wasn't at work and there weren't enough people in the office to spare someone for the journey.

I was in some kind of a water kingdom where everyone moved about on long narrow boats or swam. It was sunny and warm like a giant pool party. I was there for a family meeting, it was to do with a business. I was related to the family.  The head of the family was an old, fat lady with black horn-rimmed glasses. There was my brother and his 'wife' who were in cahoots with the old lady to try and take the business and all its equity. They were having an affair that was an "open secret" within the family. We were in a meeting room when some kind of natural disaster happened which devastated the kingdom. The waters were turbulent and the sky was dark. I was looking for survivors in what was now a palace largely underwater.  From a window, I saw the old lady, brother and wife jet-ski to a tower. I followed and came into a long hall, everyone else from the family was seated around a long oval table. The three I had followed were missing. There was something that looked like a golf club bag at one end of the table. A tall man motioned for me to check an upper room. I went up spiral stairs and from there could see the threesome having sex. The "wife" was not on an equal footing, she was a slave of the couple.  I returned to the room and waited for the meeting.  When they came down they were trying to tell me that there was no bad feeling and they had brought my share of the family business in the bag at the end of the table.  As I turned to look toward the bag, the old woman jumped like a frog and pulled a sheet off the bag  I saw that it was full of spears. I was trying to escape.

I had covid and was choking slowly, my lungs were getting tighter like they were filled with glue. I was trying to get my sons from a neighbour's house. There was a maze of full bin bags to try and get into their back garden. I had my puppy with me but she was distracted by their lurcher and wouldn't come. I couldn't move and I had no voice left to call for help.  I just slumped down in the piles of rubbish to die

I was at the psychiatric unit where I used to work. The math teacher was being really unkind to me. I was trying to find the nice TA who had been kind to me but she wasn't there and I couldn't get to where she was. I was getting more and more upset and feeling more humiliated and alone when a girl I had done textile class with at secondary school came to hug me, she introduced me to her girlfriend who was a girl I knew from the village I grew up in. They both looked the same as they had as teenagers except for having really beautiful dreadlocked hair. Naomi's was purple with small silver bands through it and her girlfriend's was silver with small polished black bands. Her girlfriend was sitting talking with someone.She smiled in acknowledgement but didn't speak. They were in the main area of the unit, where the dining area usually is. It was full of people though and very dimly lit. As we weaved through the crowd, the woman I was with was trying to explain what had been happening and inviting me to join their resistance movement. I was scanning the crowd looking for my old boss to tell her what was happening.

A big building, looks like a shopping mall crossed with my secondary school building  I am there with my sons, the lights are really bright outside the shops and its hurting my head to look at. At some point I can't find them and in my frantic search I go to the basement level which is a water park. I can't see them, the water is really blue but the lighting is only around the wall. There are two babies in the water park, one is a small white boy and the other a Filipino girl, they are given to me to keep safe. I can't see by who, I can see a large group of babies tethered together. I am trying to make sure they keep their heads above the water but the depth keeps changing and the wave machine comes on intermittently. I am panicking and scanning around me for a way out. I see a group of year 11, I used to support, at the side of the pool. I am then in a classroom with them and they are telling me they've been in more trouble and asking for help.  We are all then at a churchyard. It is gothic and there is heavy snow on the ground. I don't have the babies anymore, they are with an old woman who has them in a victoriana style pram. There is an old man coming towards us but his face keeps changing. I can't place the faces but I know he wants to hurt me. We are trying to leave and then I have a girl in a wheelchair that I am trying to take to the cinema, she doesn't have enough oxygen left if we are delayed.  She is really happy and understanding when I say I can't get through the procession across the road. There are protesters but I can't see their signs. Then we are flying straight upwards and she gives me flares to send up so the students can find us

Theatre shows had all moved to street performances.  I was supposed to be in comedy piece but the performance started without me. The lead's sister had taken my place.  I was in the audience with people from my work. It was staged outside my work but the building was different. Dark wood with a balcony overlooking the street.  The service users were all on the balcony looking down on the performance. It was early evening so was lower visibility. I was sexually assaulted in the back of a pick up truck parked at one end of the building. I was aware that service users could see me. They were jeering and encouraging the man as they thought I was into it.  I couldnt walk after, I was trying to get out of the truck. A group of young Irish women lifted me down. I was laying in the middle of a huge crowd still trying to get to the play I was supposed to be in. I was in a lot of pain in my back. One of the women was a nurse and told them how to lay me as she thought my back was broken

I was in a big cinema and headphones were being given out to watch the film on phone screens. I was trying to get away from someone. The people around my cinema chair weren't quite human, they had really big, sharp teeth but somehow they still fit in their mouths. I needed to escape and had to climb over other people as the seats were tightly packed. I gave my headphones to someone in the chair next to mine as she didn't have any. They brought refreshments and that was like a date rape drug, I was conscious but my body felt like it wasn't my own. I couldn't move properly or speak There was a Christmas church event but the building was an old small bungalow so not many people could fit in. Lots of people were parked outside, there were people coming straight from their Christmas Eve parties who were still drunk. Nobody noticed I had been drugged.  Eventually I got to the inside of the church but by this time I was coughing badly and everyone thought I had Covid. I recognised some of the people in the room, they were all seated on flowery sofas. It looked like they had suffered strokes or brain injuries and they couldn't move so were being served by family members. I saw a door to an inner room. It was a church service run by my old pastor.
