I didn't want to see him but ended up next to him. I still couldn't talk. He was holding my hand but talking to the person opposite in Romanian. There was a long table in this room, made of dark wood and set like a tea party.  I couldn't move to leave but then I was in an electric wheelchair trying to get down a corridor which had been blocked by people's luggage. I went out into a garden and saw they were unloading a paddle steamer. The people here looked like they had suffered strokes or brain injuries but I thought maybe they had been drugged too. I was trying to get back to a particular room. Whichever way I travelled the rooms were blocked. It was like being in a maze. I am terrified of mazes. The dream got louder and louder as people were playing instruments and laughing when I turned corners. Nobody would help me. The last room I  remember had an old Jamaican man in it, he had the big sharp teeth but was on a life support. He turned his head and smiled at me as I was trying to move his luggage from the path

I was in a large group,  at a building site. The group is all people I know - my family and friends and people that I don't speak to anymore. There are workers on the site but I don't recognise them. My friend Phil is telling me that he has arranged job interviews there for my step-dad and brother-in-law because they need work after their injuries.  Step-dad and mum say they will wait behind for the interview. My sister and her husband get angry because she is my partner for the next check and she doesn't want to leave him there. They are accusing me of trying to separate them. We are supposed to be taking precautions against dieing so a pair of us are responsible for checking if everyone else is ok periodically. After this we are going to drive to the next site. We are late leaving because the younger children want to do a show. I am getting anxious as I know we need to be on time. I offer to take others as my boyfriend has a car. My sister that I should be partnered up with is saying that my boyfriend is a murderer. This is a running joke but neither me nor him thinks he is funny. I tell my mum we will check everyone and then my sister can find her own way there.  We check everyone and the final check should be that we ask each other. I have asked her but she won't ask me unless we drive her and I've said no. There is an argument with my sister again saying that I am deliberately making problems for her and her husband. I leave. We arrive at the next site and go into the nurse to be checked. It is the nurse who looked after me when I was in hospital for my heart in July. She says she needs to check my blood pressure but I am already losing consciousness. I can hear her shouting for my partner and telling her she should have checked. I am on the ground and I can't breathe, they are attaching me to machines. I was dieing

there was a family event in a large stately home style hall that was on the site of my primary school Banqueting tables were set and my whole family including grand parents on both sides were all sitting at the table There were other people there too, residents from care homes I have worked in and people I knew from university.  It had kind of doubled as a "house meeting" for residents that evidently lived there in the upper rooms.  I had been given a repair to log by one gentleman and when I came to report it I was told that "he always makes a fuss so don't worry about it". I was arguing that we needed to do something as I was uncomfortable to pretend I didn't know when I did. I got into an argument with all of the people on my table. My Dad was sitting at the head if the table and I had been given a space on the corner next to him - it looked like they had miscalculated as it wasn't a proper space - but as I was clearing items away and taking them to wash up, everytime I came back to sit down, my place was further away. Until eventually nobody else was sitting at the table anymore.  Then I had a pain in my hand, there was a blister. I squeezed it and a small bug that was striped like a zebra came out.  Then I was in a small parlour room with my mum, her husband, my step brothers and sisters and the police with social workers. There was a large bird cage.  The police were sent to check the suitability of my Mum to look after Alan's children. My younger step sister was giving a good report, my older one wasn't. I was asked for mine and was trying to explain why the things the older was saying weren't true. The social workers were more bothered about the bird cage and how this was a bad example for one of my step brothers as it would make him swear. Then my real brothers were there and we were sitting on the floor, my older brother had me held in a restraint and wouldn't let me speak again. I closed my eyes and when I opened them I was back in a room with 3 of my current residents who all have the same name and one was talking about his gambling addiction and how he felt he could never stop. He was really upset about selling his phone again

I was a prisoner being held as a sex slave, I never saw the perpetrator, only heard his voice.  It was like a travelling human circus, I was naked and chained up in a wagon with bars. The visitors to the "attraction" would pay to see me do what they wanted  It was always dark and raining. The wagon was sinking in mud and potholes frequently. I managed to escape with other prisoners. The rest of the nightmare was trying to avoid getting caught again Camera flashes at some points. A tall building, looking up a turret from the inside which had metal branches protruding from it. Realising we couldn't go that way because one of them fell.  I was facing being caught again, he wasn't going to kill me but he would make sure I never ran again

I am in a viking longboat racing towards a shore line. Ahead of me a village burns, I can hear screaming over the sounds of the waves. Jumping from the ship and running ashore, there are bodies everywhere I woke up turning over bodies, I was looking for someone, fear and panic

I was in a sort-of heritage park with lots of antique shops. A man I know from church was there and he was talking about his attempts to train for the priesthood. Some of the antique shops had better antiques than the others.

I was living in France. It was raining a lot throughout. I was with my mother in a house when two men (who were black; my mind kept saying don't include that detail!) walked in and started looking around, as if they were pretending to belong there. One was looking through a back room (maybe a pantry) and the other was looking through the cupboards. I walked towards the second one and asked him to leave. He backed up towards the stove and walked around it (it wasn't attached to the wall and there was space around it). There was a carving knife on a magnet behind the stove and he grabbed it and started to come towards me with the knife.

I was walking across a sort of square when a police officer called out my name. We sat down on a bench. And using the sort of tone of a clever TV detective he said "We've just realised that yesterday you couldn't tell us where you were at the time of the take-away delivery". The implication was clear, I had committed some sort of crime.
I was in a short of desert, but more like a 1950s movie soundstage version of a desert, my parents were on either side of me and I took their hands and said "I've started my period".
A old lady was going on a trip and her suitcase was so full that things were hanging out of it and she couldn't zip it up. I offered to do it for her. In was happy to be helpful.

I was in my house with my partner and an old colleague was staying on our living room sofa. She had aged considerably, looked run down, and was leaving that morning. I asked where she was going and she said "places". Then I offered her some of the many lotions and facial cleaners I had inherited from my mother after she died. They were expensive and I didn't want them to go to waste. The colleague thanked me for them.

I was stranded in a small town on a lake. The weather was terrible and it was flooding. It was similar to a place we used to spend time in the summer but not exactly the same. My mother was there and she made a few sculptures out of black plastic. A friend from high school was there too and he was there with his wife who wanted everyone to pay attention to her. Then she disappeared and we found out later in the dream she had got on a plane to go home without telling anybody. She was on the fourth flight out of "town" that day. Then I went to my friend's cabin and he introduced me to a friend of his. He was funny and good looking, laughed a lot with our joint friend. But he only had a few months to live because of a cancer diagnosis. But he continued to be in good spirits. I told him "I wish I had met you years ago". Then we found out we could go home so I asked someone if I could take one of the plastic things my mother had made because it resembled a tombstone and I could use it as a Hallowe'en decoration for the yard.

taking a group of students on a school trip to a sort of holiday park. It seemed to cover huge amounts of space and included things like multiple swimming pools, ocean front, wave pools, buffets. Along side this, I was supposed to be writing an assignment which the children were preventing me from writing. I was getting frustrated because I could not seem to complete what I needed to. my father and brother turned up too and tried separate me from the group so I could write (the location of this was down the road from the house I are up in). Eventually I started to yell at my family, other colleagues and students that I needed space. In one instance though I was supposed to be helping serve food to the students but instead I jumped into a swimming pool fully clothed. Some of the students joined. At another time, students were distressed and told me their problems. The dream finished with me standing and talking to a former student of mine who had made a doll of her favourite English teacher, and she told me about her huge crush she had on him and she wished he'd worked at the school for longer.

My husband and I had accepted teaching jobs at an international school in the Indian Ocean on an island. This was a source of stress because there were a few instances in which I realised I had jumped head first into something without doing any research. When we arrived they gave me and my husband separate accommodation, which wasn't what we thought we had agreed. On the first night I just wanted to go to bed and sleep but the room I was assigned was filthy, with mould on the walls and water leaks. So I had to move furniture around to stay dry. But before that I had said to another teacher I didn't want to go driving because I was tired from the journey but they wouldn't accept that and I went drinking in a group. The next day, my husband asked the headteacher why we had been assigned separate accommodation and he seemed too busy to be interested so he said we could move into mine or his. His room was much nicer than mine, with a floor and walls and a proper roof. But it was smaller and there was a sort of living room area at the end of the bed which other people could use at any time of night or day. So we didn't like the lack of privacy and decided to go to my "room". But when I went back to sleep, there was a boy in the bed who said "anybody can use these beds, it's not yours". I started to feel frustrated and decided to focus on the job itself, maybe it would be better. But no one would tell me what I was hired to teach. The island was beautiful and the students were often playing in the surf. So were the adults and no one seemed to do any work. Our friends from home had also taken a new job at the same time on an island in the Carribean. She asked if she could come to visit us and I said "no" because I didn't know the name of the island where I lived. There was a lot more playing on the beach.

I was working in a school.I walked around the school and a number of things happened. First, I got lost in the school building. I ended up in the boys' locker room and there was no way to get out except by going through a door that went outside. I knew I shouldn't be in the locker room but unless I wanted to get lost by going through the door to the outside, I would need to go back through the locker room. There were no boys in it but I was still shielding my eyes.  A coach saw me and yelled at me so I ran the rest of the way. I also had a lot of work to do at the school and was very tired, so tired I couldn't think properly and I walked into a school assembly wearing just a bra and a skirt. A Catholic priest yelled out like a school boy something like "look at her, she's naked!!: and I ran back to my classroom to get a shirt. I was angry at the priest so when I came back I sat beside him to try and see if we could talk about something different. A small boy came up to him and asked him to "do what you did before". I made a mental note of what he said and decided to report it to the child protection officer. I didn't know who was in the role so I asked someone else and they said "Lisa". So I went to find Lisa and I was told she had gone to hike the Himalayas. I was annoyed but then remembered I had made two trips to the Himalayas myself that school year. Then I went outside and walked along a sort of stream and to make sure I could jump over part of the stream, I had to hand my phone to a girl I had known from high school. She held it while I jumped across. After this, I was given a gift by someone to congratulate me on my pregnancy. I hadn't told anyone so I don't know how they knew.

I was living in a dirty and polluted city where I felt very stressed out (it felt like a strange mix of Istanbul and Bangkok with  a river in the centre). I was supposed to go home eventually but it felt like this was a long way off. My dad suggested I get a massage to make myself feel better but I got stuck on one side of the river and couldn't get back. I got an airplane back to the correct side of the river but I was very worried it was going to another country so I was clarifying this with the pilot many times. Eventually I got to the massage shop and it was dirty too. A previous customer has left mud on the table and sheets. So we rescheduled again to the night before I left.
driving with Mr Toad from Wind in the Willows and Toad of Toad Hall. It was an old fashioned open top car and we were driving through some woods, singing.

I was both walking and driving, sometimes alone and sometimes my partner was with me. We kept passing animals on the road in the dark and couldn’t be sure if they were cats, rats or hedgehogs. Mostly we thought they were rats but a bit too big.

I was travelling in a train up Snowden in Wales, looking at mountains all around. Then something got stuck in a pipe, like a tin can, and we had to bash the pipe to get it out, but it wouldn’t come. I was not alone. we had to free the pipe to put something else in to keep it either warm or cool.  Then I went to toilet and it wouldn’t flush, so I had to chop the stool up to get it to go down. I used scissors and threw them out off train window.

I was at some kind of training course or protest organisation and we had to split into groups to brainstorm tasks. I ended up in a pair with the actress Caroline Quentin. We had to analysis reports in newspapers and on a flip chart- don’t remember what about, but for some reason we needed to have bras. We both had very large cup bras, don’t remember where they came from or what they were for, but hers was white, and I was using my favourite, most comfortable dark brown Triumph.  Then we had to move all our stuff to another room, which took a lot of trips, and then we had to tell someone what we’d found, but I don’t remember the details.

I was looking at shoes and someone was telling me to buy some with heels, but I said I couldn’t because they didn’t look right on someone who was ‘short fat and barrel like with little stubby legs’ which is how my sister had described me in my late teens. I tried to demonstrate to them with some little plaster models I picked up, and turned them upside down to show painted black high heels on very short stubby legs.

I and my partner went on holiday with two friends we used to go away with for Christmas- though strangely rarely at same time, also neither had their partners with them.  We were in a cottage mil s from anywhere, along a very rough and waterlogged track. After settling into our ‘rooms’, as cottage turned into barge at this point, we spent a long time debating going to a pub for food and drink, and working out with a map where we could go that would have good beer without taking car out again.  After planning route through countryside we suddenly arrived in a small Asian looking market place with several restaurants and bars. We went in one with a good menu and stood waiting to be seated even though it was obviously full. After 10 minutes, I said we had to look elsewhere. We went next door, which was much more sophisticated looking, and had extra room upstairs. It turned out the chef in both was the same, but I don’t know how we knew that. There was no real food for vegetarians, but I ate rice and nibbled some other bits off other people’s plates. Another friend, had joined us by this time. We drove back, in a very large jeep type car, crashing into other cars on the way back.  Then we found tickets for a concert in Glasgow, to celebrate one of our party’s birthday.  We talked about how to get there, but I don’t remember us going.

There was a big party - someone's birthday. I was outside the party with some people including my boyfriend and his brother. Someone had told me it was a wild party and people were taking drugs. I said this to my boyfriend's brother and he thought that was just normal. We all went in. A lot of people in large rooms but not like a party atmosphere, more like a fair, people milling around. My boyfriend was reprimanded for having drugs and I thought this was quite unfair since lots of people at the party had taken them and it wasn't something he would normally do. He had to go upstairs. I was in a small room now with a smaller group of people and trying to decide which film we would watch.

I appeared to be working in an air force possibly with some current colleagues from my hospitality job. the force was downsizing. Don't remember personnel being make redundant but more so equipment and plane changes. The company was reverting back to previous setups and not continuing contracts that had expired.

Had a car with similar problems to my own. It was parked in a car park with a grass overflow area. The car was parked half on concrete and the rear on grass. There was a problem with the tyres and had reason to believe the owner of the car parked next to mine was involved. Tracked down the father of the owners in a generic country pub setup. He agreed to come have a look later. We met outside the pub later and he had bought his wife along. We walk to the car and they get inside. They don't see any issues but I'm convinced the rear tyres are a little deflated. Before I get a chance to show them they asked me to push the car to avoid a Landover trying to maneuver past. Didn't do it in time and the corners of the cars lightly scrape together. The couple again ask me to push the car. Complied but didn't mention another problem with the car battery. Despite this the car started moving quite rapidly. The car turned 180 degrees in a small arch then forward towards a chain link fence. Inexplicably the car launches as if going up an invisible ramp and crashes sideways into a bushy area outside the car park. Work up shortly afterwards and went back to sleep.
I appeared to be in a position of power or influence. Possibly aristocratic but did not appear to be interested in whatever my role was.

being at an airport terminal with my parents, can't remember if my sister was with us. My father was being off and in a hurry but it didn't appear to be going anywhere other than different corners of the departure terminal.

I was sneaking around an unknown city trying to find supplies to replenish my health. Shops and restaurants were either closed or out of stock. Found a cafe that was closing but still had some snacks that I stole. No one appeared to notice. A little later similar to what happens in the game Fortnite, a purple fog surrounded the area I was in. As in the game once a location is cordoned off with this fog one can't return otherwise it will damage your health. At one point I was in a office block partly blocked off but instead of a fog it was split by a purple curtain going from ceiling to the ground. Focus was more about me surviving.

I was in a house I didn't recognise with family at first. I had to share a bed with my sister but she was irritating me and I left.  At another point I was riding a bicycle to this home. Missed the turn in to the drive way and carried on up the street, slightly uphill until I reached a roundabout junction. Managed to turnaround through this junction with minor traffic around me and headed back down the street where my "home" was. Tried to park my bike as if it were a car but realised I didn't have to.  me in my home with an old friend of mine. We were preparing to go on a night out but I needed to get ready. This appeared to be difficult to me with my first attempt being a neon pink Adidas t-shirt, black trousers which later revealed as another Adidas branded product and a pair of neon pink trainers. Noted to my friend and a another person that I was a walking Adidas catalogue and said I would change. Walked into another room and found my black jeans to wear instead. a large amount of a cocaine like substance in the room where my friend was waiting. I think I spilled it on the floor and the table it was on. On closer inspection it appeared to look more like granulated sugar. We tried collecting it all in a jar but it wasn't big enough and a lot remaining on the floor. We did not seem to be overly alarmed by the situation. Whilst I was getting ready to go out my friend was indicating an intention to take some and was asking around if anyone would join him. Lastly this house had quite a few other people in that I either couldn't remember or didn't recognise. a group of friends and friends of friends all waiting to go out for the night.

myself avoiding and running away from a troll like figure who around the size of two story house. This was in an urban area but mostly taking place in a car lot. I was with another 2 people. looking for keys for a vehicle for us to escape. I found some and threw them towards one of the others who promptly started the engine. This was an oldish Mercedes that had different coloured body work between the front and rear. Silver and red I think.

I was with someone that I considered a biological brother. I remember him being black but don't recall if that was my skin colour as well. He had lost his legs in some form of conflict. using strange science fiction like tools and equipment to move him around. there wasn't a wheelchair around at all. He was naturally unhappy about the situation perhaps close to giving up. I think I was trying my best to improve the situation.

Two rival teams competing in an outdoor area, mixture of grass, hills, concrete and water. Not reminiscent of anything I have visited before. I was in one of the teams. Do not recall anyone I knew in either side. The general public was present but not in spectator stands. It escalated with the other team boarding a helicopter with an array of weapons. They proceeded to attack everyone including the general public and then turned their attention on me. Attacking with miniguns, propellers and a barrels on chains. I laboured but managed to evade their attacks to a point when the opposition abandoned the helicopter and headed back to their base somewhere else. Still armed they come across me in their path and try to shoot me. I run away from them and hide behind rocks and derelict buildings. Afterwards I return to the arena where my side appear to be preparing for another game or attack. Spoke to a former colleague called Lauren about how ridiculous it was. Didn't see her previously and don't recall seeing anyone get hurt.

A woman had given birth. She Needed to have a bath or wash before having sex again. She Disappeared. Searchers were looking under water stored in old containers. Someone was using torn up sheets as ropes to dredged the bottom of old water tanks. Sheet rope got stuck, then it starts moving and being pulled back into the water. The woman was hiding under the water and was pulling the sheet rope. She emerged unharmed.

Living in a house next door to my mother. Hers had moss on the thatched roof. We walked to the town centre and found an attractive building which used to be a department store as we could see the old crests and stained glass windows with initials on. Then it became Leathleys department store in Wimbledon. I got stuck in a loop researching details of the building.

I was dropping a balloon off a high balcony and miraculously was able to land it in a small metal bucket 40ft below.  My best friend T was with me and she congratulated me enthusiastically. Next moment I was swimming lengths of a pool at Madonna’s house.  She was admiring my rings but said I should take them off for safety reasons.  We swapped book recommendations and I was reading a collection of short stories. Next my feet I think, were fitting into daughter’s first shoes as a toddler and my niece as a child was there too. I was choosing artwork but painting was similar to one already own with large rock formations. Next I was being shown a way to commit suicide using a hose pipe and a bucket of water. Then I was in a train with lots of brown paper parcels.  The rock painting was there. I remember praying.

I made a new friend who shared a lot of childhood experiences and lived in same part of U.K. as me. Chatting made me late for a big Awards Dinner. Her husband called a taxi but I ended up in a decorators van full of Chinese people. Then I was involved in organising export papers for my daughter’s boyfriend who we don’t think is a nice person. Pleased to receive phone call from official department saying his deportation arrangements are confirmed for 6 days time. Then find myself In New York eating Chinese meal with husband, grown up son and girlfriend plus gown up daughter and this boyfriend. He is complaining about wine my husband A has chosen. A reacts quickly and suggests he buys a good one himself then! This feels like the bad atmosphere we had when both of them had to live with us during lockdown.

We are in a new house and I am planning how to furnish with curtains and artwork.  Then I was back in my childhood home but my grown up daughter was there in the garden in a cocoon shaped garden chair playing music really loudly, which I asked her to turn down.  A group of us were in the front garden trying to fix a leaking house pipe which was spraying water everywhere.  There was a huge pile of junk there too.  I tried to get back into the house but couldn’t until husband opened door.  He had discovered flies in the freezer buzzing inside some frozen bread packaging.  He didn’t shut the freezer door properly again.  Then we were in a large DIY store trying to buy a broom.  My younger version of my parents appear with a trolley and my grown up son as a toddler. I am confused and pick up someone else’s trolley by mistake and it has a pink toilet seat in. We all proceed to check out and see grown up daughter with her current boyfriend.  My father remarks that he is typically ignoring us.

I had had sex with this strange man with blonde red hair. Afterwards he made me dive into the Thames in London docks with him to swim to his friend’s yacht. The water was filthy and dead fish heads were bobbing around us. We reached the yacht but I was cross with being tested like that. We sailed to a hot and sunny place.
A little recollection of driving and parking a car next to an old van. But my car’s steering had a mind of its own and kept turning into the van and smashing its side.

Staying in a tiny room in a big old house, like an Agatha Christie novel. Actor Peter Dinklage was there and I was chatting to him.  I was a guest, not a servant, but I was chatting with the servants as friends. There was a dinner party and I was going to attend, but a young woman  came up to me and was grabbing me by the cuff, trying to take me somewhere else.  My clothes weren’t right for the dinner.  Then I might have been a servant, wearing a black maid’s dress with white lace cuffs.  Peter Dinklage was trying to get me to go with him and smoke marijuana, and i was laughing with him, saying ‘I’d love to, but I’m working’, even though I didn’t want to, I didn’t want him to think that i was boring. We were standing with lots of people in a hallway with deep Turkish carpets.  In another tiny room where i could see that the walls weren’t quite connected at the corners, so i could see through into next door.  There was no one in there.  I could see some of the garden from he window, but it was dark. I was meant to go somewhere, but I couldn’t leave the room.

I was in an hospital facility where mothers were with tiny or premature babies.  One woman, that i was aware of, but didn’t know personally had a baby that was wrapped in a film like an amniotic sac.  At one point i held the baby in my hands. I knew that i had to get the baby away from this woman.  It was very quiet everywhere. I was talking to lots of people, i think i was staying there.  I went into a room to look at different people, all in their white hospital beds.  It was very white and sparse. I was talking to nurses and patients, but being careful about what i said, and i had to find out information.  I wasn’t frightened.  It felt like I was on a mission, like a spy.  I was walking on shore line at the beach, with Sand and water bubbling between my toes as i walked, the sun was shining and the beach was busy.  I was following a man.  He was walking too, ahead of me.  Everyone around was happy nad on holiday.  He was just walking.   We were inside a country house with many paintings on the walls of people who worked there, because it was a film studio, but this was the boardroom type of area, not where the films were made.  The man was here.  He was some kind of boss.his painting was on the wall. Again I was asking questions.  At one point i spoke to him, but i was all casual.  I was then working in costume, The man was handing me his suit, which was a dinner suit, with bow tie, his costume to hang up for the next day.  I was writing his name on the label around the neck.  He asked, ‘why are you putting my name on it.  They usually just write on numbers’. I replied that it was easier this way, but i wondered if I’d made a mistake.  He might guess that i was a spy.  He was going to get on the train, which was across the beach.  He had a long journey ahead of him.

Travel to tell my first husband that I wanted to get back together with him.  He looks about twenty, so thirty years ago. I have a suitcase and arrive in Liverpool, To a flat he was living in student style.  He was clear, no way. But I could stay the night, I slept in tiny room that was full of box room stuff. The next day I was at a train station busy, couldn’t get served queue kept moving, people moved ahead coz they saw other workers come on. Eventually got to buy a ticket. I was at a counter in the station. It was like a city of stores within the station.  I ordered breakfast with lots of meat, I had the same as the guy before me. He knew what to order, but I didn’t.  It seemed good to do this, so I wouldn’t look like I didn’t know what I was doing.  It was a good breakfast.  Had to take dogs from the flat that was now a caravan after breakfast, before the others came home.  The others were my ex-husbands friends from years ago.  I didn’t want to see them and be embarrassed that i had come here and been rejected.  I had to leave with our dogs I had to carry them up a very impossible slope of derelict house, It was virtually vertical, with lots of falling rubble.  I got to the top and need to get the into canoe one at a time down a massive drop into the sea.  There was a lift for the boats like for lifeboats on a liner on side of the house hill, then I realised that I had to just through myself and the dogs in the boat into the sea.  Then at a party Craig Charles, the actor claimed that has wasn’t horrible to women, but he would shove beer in the face of a girl who was drinking a bottle, just for a laugh, but he wasn’t a misogynistic he called it doing a ‘beer-au-saurus’.  I was going to the party, which was like an end of college party with a very short dress with bra strap top, like all of the party girls.  The bottom half was intentional super short so it showed my knickers and I had emerald green Chrismas baubles tucked out the back and the front to look like a penis and testicles, but I had to ask myfriends if it was funny, or if I was just going to look stupid.  Would everyone think it was the hilarious joke that it was meant to be. Trying to get served as we went in, you only got a tiny drink and there was one of the caretakers of the college at the bar with a big stamp on his hand, the kind you used to get in clubs. It was so intricate, I thought it was a waste as no one would ever read all of that text

I was walking somewhere outside.  There were lots of people around. It was like a countryside beauty spot where people would come to walk.  It was a grey day. I was perhaps following someone, but pretending that I wasn’t.  I was certainly keeping an eye on a person with a child ahead of me.  It was probably a man, but I’m not sure.  They had walked off ahead, up a sandy slope.  It was then kind of like a canyon walk in Los Angeles, but still grey skies.  At the top of the slope, i heard the child cry out, and I knew that he was going to harm her.  Confidently I started to run towards them.  I could hear the  people around me, who knew me, they were not strangers, Saying ‘she’ll never do it.  She’ll never get that far’ and i was running in really tiny steps, almost on my tip toes, but i was going really fast.  I could feel the air move past me.  I was going to get there.

I was on a film set, it was in a kind of disused factory, so we were undercover, but open at the sides to the outside. There were lots of crew milling around. My husband was directing. He grabbed my arm and said ‘don’t stand there’ as he rushed me though all of the people. They were obviously feeling embarrassed for me. He then went on to explain what everyone did. He had forgotten that i used to work in films when i met him.

I was in a large fancy modern house, with a fully glass top floor, so you could see the gardens below.   It wasn’t my house, I either worked there, or was a guest.  I found a broken piece of plastic, like the arm of a pair of glasses, under the sink unit.  I threw it in the bin, but then found a toothbrush as well. I realised that the piece of plastic must be from the casing of this toothbrush, and that made it a travel toothbrush. I was cleaning my teeth and looking down to the gardens where the woman who owned the house was talking with her husband when she saw me.  I pretended not to see her, but that i was just looking around the gardens.  I turned away. Outside of the door to the bathroom, there was a nanny or a maid who was taking care of the children of the house.  I stayed in the bathroom. I was then with Seth.  I knew that we would have to go on the run. I had this pet that was either a mouse or a guinea pig, with furry round brown feet.  We were laughing and joking together, sitting in a car.  Then all around us people started arriving and setting up stalls for an antique or junk market.  We knew it was time. We looked at each other and nodded, Thelma and Louise style. We knew that we wold either go to jail for ever, or be killed.  We smiled at each other. We slammed the doors of the car and Seth started To drive backwards up the street, really quickly.  A cop skidde to a halt in his car in front of us, shaking his head.  I had to Make Seth stop half way up The street.because i had to put food down for my dogs.  Would they have enough water if i was killed?  Who would take care of them? We set off again at speed.

I was at a drawing class and doing a drawing in ink. It was an indoor scene of some stairs coming down and the purpose was to look at the light and shade. I was drawing from another drawing but also positioned myself in the room where I could just about see the scene from the same angle, although there were some kind of room dividers or very large chairs in the way. As my drawing wasn't progressing very well I took a break and went to a bathroom. Under the handwashing sink was a kind of a low down sink and there was a cat's drinking vessel. I cleaned the vessel and the sink and thought I was procrastinating. I went to another room to show my work to someone else but the drawing was now completely different, like a protest poster with large letters on it and I couldn't find the original one about the room. There were a lot of rodents running around, each one was different, like fancy pet mice and rats in different colours and with different kinds of fur.
There was a new forest path - it was circular.

In a small courtyard garden. A group of people were playing a piece of music. There was a flowering tree near them, and I knew it was an oleander, and it had been given to me. I had some gardening shears and while the music was playing I was trimming the tree, to cut off those flowers which were dying. The flowers were white and very large, and the tree didn't have many leaves, it was mainly a smooth trunk and branches and flowers. As I cut one of the flowers I realised I accidentally cut through the trunk and the whole top of the tree fell down. Once the music was over one of the people commented what a loud noise the tree falling had made, and also said that the music they played was called the Latin name of the oleander. I explained to the musicians that I accidentally cut off the whole top of the tree and wondered whether the tree would still continue growing.

Was at a drawing class and working on drawing a building on A2 size paper using charcoal. I was drawing either by looking at the building or a picture of it, not sure. I framed my drawing very tightly to the page, making a dark line at the top of the page at an angle, and another about two thirds down the page. I then thought I had got the proportions wrong but when I looked at the source again (a picture I think) it looked all right and I went on adding some detail. Until now I had been indoors and at an unknown location but was now outside Blackheath Halls along with the rest of the class and the teacher. I thought that if the teacher was working on this course three days a week as well as evening ones, that was probably nearly a full time job for her and I wondered if I could do something similar for a job.

I was rushing to get to an airport and also to watch a film. I thought I was always running to be on time for the airport. I was running up a dark rainy road past bus stops, up a hill. Finally I got to the airport and went to a machine to book tickets for the film and the flight. I thought about sending a message to the people who were coming with me to ask if they wanted me to book for them as well, but then thought T would be too slow to reply and it would just make things more difficult. But then they arrived, T and two of our friends, and I went on to book tickets for all of us. The film was Snowpiercer and it would end only a few minutes before the flight was leaving, so I said we should leave a bit before the end, which didn't matter anyway because I had already seen the film.

I was driving a car in my old hometown. For some reason there was a cardboard box in the driver's seat so I was trying to drive from a position of crouching down on the passenger side and just about reaching the pedals and the steering wheel and reaching my head up to see out of the window. The car was difficult to control but I was trying to get it to the car park of the old petrol station at the top of the hill near my parents' house. The car was veering all over the place but didn't crash.

There was a kind of underground cell - maybe a sort of prison. Quite crowded with people. There was a barter system for food and I was helping set out the food and take payment but I wasn't at all sure how to calculate payment. Small porcelain animals were quite valuable but some people were also paying in small jugs of cream which had a certain value.

I was walking along the street somewhere in London, a bit like Shaftesbury Avenue. The road was mainly closed for traffic, with just one line for traffic and that was under a kind of canopy. I crossed the road and went into some shops. There was a Holland & Barrett and there was something I wanted to buy so I was going to go in, but the shop shelves were almost completely empty. I went through a doorway into the next shop, apologising to a person in the doorway as I went in. I briefly realised I was too close to them for social distancing and also wasn't wearing a mask but then as soon forgot about that. In the other shop I was meant to work at the till. A person came to the till and wanted to buy three items. One was soap. One was something I had to weigh and put in the price for the weight. I was having a lot of trouble with operating the till because I didn't know what I was doing, and the customer was getting irate and was annoyed that I wasn't being friendlier and more helpful. I thought that I wasn't feeling very well but that wasn't the right thing to say because not feeling well could make others uncomfortable if they thought I was ill. So I said I just wasn't in the mood for being friendly and could I just try to deal with the till. The shop manager came over to see if I was doing OK and I said it was the first time I had used a till like that and I was struggling a bit. I had to delete some items I had put in twice but finally got to the right total and the customer was able to pay.
there were a lot of dogs, like i was working in or visiting a dog shelter?

leaving food outside my door for anyone to take. I didn't know if anyone would take some but then it was gone and I read some reviews online or social media type posts which said they thought this was a good thing to do. So after that I kept leaving food outside and then someone with a vacuum would come and hoover it all up, maybe to take to a food bank or something? leaving some sort of food outside my door, and then it being hoovered up, and then I'd have to leave another sort of food out there.
dating a friend, dating someone i didn't know.

I was at some sort of party in a mansion or maybe a hotel, and I was in a room full of people and that was kind of fun, but eventually i decided i needed to leave that room, and i was trying to get to another room. I got stuck behind a couple on my way and that was a bit awkward but eventually i got past them, and made it to this room which had a man in it. we both went to the window intending to jump out. we were very high off the ground. the man went first and he could fly, and then i went, squeezing through a window to get out, and i could fly too. I knew all that was going to happen because i'd seen that last scene play out earlier, but at that point i was looking from afar, whereas at the end i was in the body of the woman i'd watched earlier.

I was in love with this woman and we kept going around different locations, like in a shopping centre, one was a comic book shop. Then eventually we came back home and there was pizza everywhere and some other people there and all of a sudden I wasn't together with the woman any more and the dream turned quite scary, like there was something trying to get in the house

I was in my Taekwondo class in a school hall - I was meant to be instructing the kid's class. There were lots of kids running around, they felt too close together and like there were too many of them in the hall for corona times. Some were wearing masks, some weren't - that made me feel nervous. I also wasn't sure if I should be wearing a mask - one kept appearing in my hands and I would put it on, but then I'd lose it or have to take it off. Other instructors were also milling around but none of us seemed to know what to do to run the class. Eventually, Gerard Way was there, looking how he did about 10 years ago, and started to given a sort of stand up routine on American politics - I couldn't really hear the content because at this point I was at the back of the hall with the other instructors maybe trying to form a plan - but I don't think it was very funny or interesting for the children in the hall who were listening. My general feeling was 'what on earth is he doing up there?' After a while, we brought him down off the stage and he disappeared.  I was again at the front of the class trying to work out what to do. A parent who I'd never seen before, of a child I'd never met, talked to me in a friendly voice but she was complaining that the classes were a mess now, that we didn't know what we were doing, that she understood we'd probably taken a big financial hit cos of corona, but that was no excuse and she wondered if she should pull her daughter out of classes. In my head, I was thinking about all the planning and scheduling we as an instructor team had done for classes in the last few weeks and how this parent wasn't accurate in lots of the things she was saying about there only being one class a week etc, but I was so unsure of myself I couldn't saying anything back to her. Eventually she left and I just said like thanks and smiled even though I should have said lots of stuff to her that would have addressed her concerns. Immediately afterwards my own instructor came over and was like 'what did you say to her? I hope you told her she was wrong etc etc' and I said i hadn't because I wasn't sure what to say and then I felt like a failure. the daughter came up to me and said something like 'don't worry about my mum, she's always like that', and also being stressed that class still hadn't started and we were running late.

lots of chases. i was part of the Umbrella Academy and so were a couple of my friends and we were being chased by assassins over and over again and having to escape. having to escape down this series of rooms which went down a hill and we had to clamber over lots of furniture to do that, but it was quite fun. eventually we all collapsed on some sofas laughing. we hadn't escaped

i was panicking because my friend had set up a survey with some rude questions on an organisation i work with's website and i couldn't convince them to take it down or rephrase it and then i felt like a terrible person.

Strange masturbatory practices. A cock/dildo - made of real flesh but not a man. Sleepover with M and his friends. A hospital bed. It's too hot. Need to open windows.  Dream with K, M. and others. K has these leaves from Croatia. They are thin cells of a plant that traditionally they would have dressed in the winter but they now bring indoors. 1000$ for the bowl. They have a very delicate umami flavour. I'm unconvinced. I ask if they have health benefits. Then I notice they're also in a magazine so have become fashionable.
I said 'all I want from a husband' and then caught myself

Train tunnels and long walks and wetlands. I have to avoid the trains rushing in to this final stop. There are standing pools of water I need to walk through. Me and S are out walking. I'm naked. She's just topless and in hiking trousers. She falls off train because of trick ankle, onto her face. I rush to help. We come to a house. Light through window. Shadows of seagulls flying on walls. It's beautiful. I say it's like a film. There is a pristine bathroom on the ground floor. I realise this is for the air bnb. Some rooms unfinished. In one, I have to walk along planks. There are open sewer pipes that I have to unblock with chemicals. There's going to be a party. Fill the footbath with gel for a fun splashing experience. But I wonder if maybe sand would be better? Less chance of a mess? Curators TT and BB are there. I think I'm meeting them for lunch to talk planning. Then am talking with young artists about setting up a film processing studio in the house. They are snooty and don't want to talk to me. A couple sort of do some floor cleaning. But no one wants to work long enough. My dad is here. He says 'You should really get on TV. They need you'. I'm plastering and tell him it's not that easy, I'm too old and I don't have the expertise. Then I'm having a big shouting thing with some other old guy about what I've done as head of department. I'm jabbing my finger at him and yelling about how in 2 months, in the face of of in year budget cuts I've secured a 33% increase and protected my staff.

My cousin E is here. So is my mum. We're in a house, going through my grandad's things. E picks up a bunch of objects and suggests that we put them together for a display: a pouch of tobacco, a shell of a lighter, the  interior workings of another lighter and an old film viewer. I agree this is an excellent idea because the whole family has a right to access his archive.  Then I'm on an old boat on a body of still water under an overcast sky. It's my Vancouver waterscape of childhood. Maybe Kitsilano. The boat is wooden, painted red and brown. There's a large family on it including a girl called Marjoline. But there's space for me too. We go chug chug chugging across still water. When we dock I try to get off but I use the wrong door. It's a sliding wooden screen that's carved and old. The father days oh no that's not the exit. I see behind me on the other side that there's another way off the boat but I choose to force the sliding one and try to squeeze out. This breaks some kind of mechanism so the door now won't stay closed or open. The father has to fix it by be wedging wicker fishing baskets into the frame. On the dock someone gives me a bag of almonds to eat.

We're in New York. Rockefeller center. Lincoln center. There are bridges with lined with bronze sculptures on insects and fancy carvings. With S's mum and other family members but also my colleague K. There seem to be 6 of us. I don't really like K but S's niece is here and she seems to love K and is carried around by her. There is an amazing train system. Part funicular lift, part elevated subway like the one in Wuppertal. We go from a very high elevation with a bird's eye view. It's sunset/dusk. There are islands and sculptures and amphitheatre. We keep stopping in shops and art centres to ask directions. I apologise but say we've come to New York on a whim and I've never been before so don't know how to get around the city.  S's mum really wants to go to the opera. We eventually all wind up in the foyer of Lincoln center. A Native American welcoming ceremony is taking place. It's also a celebration of queer, disabled athletes. Two lesbians are singing songs in white outfits. One is in a wheelchair and has no arms. She's blonde and pretty. The other woman is more of a power ballad singer. Big hair and jewels. They sing in Christian evangelical country style and then kiss passionately. A boy we're with is wheelchair. He might have cerebral palsy. He excitedly says 'yeah, girls!' S's mum says 'oh but he's a bit old for that isn't he?'  Then I'm in a mountainous area, heading up ghost trails with my son M, and friends L and D and others. Haunted spaces. Intertwining gravel paths. Dark buildings made of wood with lots of rooms connected by hallways. M walks on in the building and disappears. We call and call for him in a sing song way. He then reappears as a 4 yr old and holds my hand. But I'm sceptical that it's really him. I keep questioning him. He insists but then refers to himself in the third person and I know it's not him. I pick him up and he becomes like a jar of peanut butter. I shout to the powers that I'm going to smash this unless the real M is released. We sing again in various voices and tones. I smash the jar and he eventually emerges as himself. We continue up the mountain as it starts to rain. If we stand still the ground turns to quicksand and we lose our shoes.  M is then in the office with me as I work. He sleeps on the floor under a coat. Strange hangings in the window  I leave the office and head outside. It's all archaeology now. I want to teach students basic excavation techniques. I want to open up the pits in the hill. The main one and the one further up where the rabbits are. I talk with the archaeology officer who tries to mansplain it all to me. Then I tell my story about how I'd done this myself in the rain before and how it was terrifying with the mud but I'd managed it. Then I'm in an underground mall complex. With a woman who also researched the Celtic images and identity. We're putting together very cool horse sculptures out of plastic elements. They are like the marble horses that were in the gallery show at Arnolfini. We discuss this and my history of research. The space is built of dark stone, brick but it's lit brightly. Like a 1970s mall.

I was in a field holding two sleek black hamsters. They had shiny eyes and were soft with almost oily fur. I was cleaning a disgusting fridge that my lodgers had messed up, with nuts and mold everywhere. I looked up to see the hamsters racing through a field of tall waving grass. They were holding leaves in their mouths and were coming towards me from a long way away. I returned to my fridge cleaning. When I looked up again I couldn't see the hamsters. So I whistled and whistled for them. One came back to me and beckoned me to follow it back into the field where we found the other one motionless underneath a bit of cardboard. Some overenthusiastic children had squashed it but it was still breathing. I picked up both hamsters and stroked them and brought them down the hill. I built them a beautiful hutch so that they could convalesce. I was worried about them but felt very happy to hold them in my hand and happy that they had survived.

High tide. Muddy water lapping at my feet. All the young lesbians hanging out. Leftover Thanksgiving dinner that I have to chew to keep. I know that people will be disgusted by that but I have to do it. A pyrex dish from childhood is in another dish. It cracks but that's ok. An English Department in a 1970s building. Amphitheatre steps and water. Seattle I think. Talk of Boeing factories. I'm back in the city but it's changed since I was last there.

Taxi to Bristol Temple Meads railway station. I have to get a train to London to get to a meeting. The taxi is driven by a woman with learning difficulties. The road by the station is blocked by traffic and diversions and a large set up of tables and emergency services people. We chat to them and they guide us through. I'm trying to find my train ticket on my phone but nothing happens when I search for Eirini's name or the journey. I'm anxious about missing the train. I head into the station and it's filled with Eastern European people who have taken shelter on the benches because they have nowhere else to go. They are dressed in layers of textiles and most are sleeping but some are arguing in groups in doorways with station staff. I pass a group of Polish soldiers who are wearing 19th century uniforms in pale grey blue, with hats with feathers in. I need to find a ticket machine to print my journey. I climb a tall ladder to access a complicated machine with lots of buttons. None of it is intuitive. A blonde woman with her two small blonde children pass. The little girl asks me questions about science and architecture and I remark how clever she is and encourage her to find out more about these subjects. I think I finally find my tickets and push the blue 'print' button but when I look at what the machine spits out it's just generic information. I come down the ladder to see if I can find help and I wake up.

The Cube is being sold. The exterior is being painted all jolly. Hogge asks if we want to come in and see it. I'm with Jem but not Milo, I think. We talk about taking photographs but I say I've never been able to although other people have. We go in through an outbuilding I don't remember. It's a stone room lined with a strange concrete plaster board with circles. There are no windows.  We leave through that room into a hallway and are about to walk through but Jem gets frightened at a door that's flapping open and closed. He grabs my hand and we run at lightening speed through this part of the place. He's saying there's bad energy. We wind up in a magnolia painted living room with peach coloured furniture.  Marvin and Euan are there. We talk about the haunting. Hogge doesn't sense it. Only me and Jem. Then things start appearing on the floor which then float up to the celling. A green fish. A head. I say 'can't you see these?' They say no. Then I see an animated Pokémon card. I know that the spirits are trying to communicate with us via the kids' childhoods. Though Hogge can't see this he now believes me because I'm describing it all in such detail. Other images appear on the floor and float up. A yellow sun visor. When I touch them they materialise so that now others can see them.   The haunting intensifies in the room. We discuss what's to be done. Something about a large biscuit and having to cut thin slices into it to increase its surface area. Something about preventing it from getting out into the community. To do that would be impossible. So what do we do? My laptop has been splattered with grease so I put it in a bag. We have to get out of here. I suggest that something must have happened here since we last came. I think we need to return to the strange stone room. I suggest that it was built as a safe room to protect the previous inhabitants from the ghosts. I think the place has only become haunted after some major building works have taken place, releasing the ghostly presence. I say we should go outside and enter again rather than walk through the terrifying space.  There's a woman on the sofa. She must have been there all the time but I'm only just seeing her. She's all in green. Big skirt and two types of green top. She keeps saying how stupid she's been and is. I tell her not to say that and it will all be ok.

I was in holiday with M and A and B. This involved driving a camper van around at night and then parking up at a house. Much conversation about making dinner. Then I was with S and BT. I had a bubble making machine that I filled with concentrated green washing up liquid. The machine made delightful farting noises as e made big bubbles and bounced them around the kitchen. I was a surgeon in a medical team with other women surgeons. We talked about our breasts and how unfair it is that it's not acceptable for women to be public without wearing bras. We then took off our clothes to scrub up for the surgical theatre

A table filled with food - individual plates of raw veg. Cucumbers, radishes, tomatoes. BA, A and N are there. But BA won't eat and the adults are angry with her. I say 'I know I always go on about Britain but, maybe we need to feed her proper delicious adult food and then maybe she'll eat it' Then I'm with my son M, who's wearing a light pink blazer with the sleeves rolled up.  We're record shopping. There's a posh young man who's in a relationship with an older social worker type woman. I remark on how odd they seem

I am in a living room with many sofas. An English bull terrier is on one. I'm playing with it with a small rubber ball. The ball is translucent. I'm worried that it might be too small and the dog might choke. A cat is sleeping on its back on another sofa. It's laughing in its sleep and it's body is shaking. There's cupboard with many drawers, all filled with tiny things and bits of shiny paper. The dog starts playing with me and then bites me. I'm then on an airplane with S. It's empty and we get our choice. The seats are more like the ones in business class so we can recline together. I'm struggling with lots of things, including half finished cakes and bits of cheese. I'm trying to get it into our out of the overhead lockers. I also have to get changed so I go to the men's toilet because I'm wearing men's clothes. I look at myself in the mirror when I'm in my bra and pants. Several baby boomer heterosexual couples come in and tell me off for being in the men's toilet. That it's not ok for me to be there. I say triumphantly to them 'but look, your wives are in here!' Then there's something about animals and laughing and I say 'help us Obi wan you're our only hope'. Then I'm in a large gathering of people with S and expartner B. B is being charming and flirtatious. I recognise that but I am not interested. I can see S across the room watching us. She's jealous and I wish I could let her know there's nothing to worry about.

Wandering topless to get the milk. But where I usually go there's been a drug bust. Police lights flashing. People in handcuffs. Playing solitaire. A pub. Outside space and am no longer with people. I sit inside waiting for people to arrive. Fairy lights and evergreens. E has made sourdough bread. More Spanish language. I'm in a cinema auditorium. Being mansplained about video projections. J is doing this? Melted butter running into the floor. I don't have my glasses so finding hard to see. Being blinded by the light and my eyes watering. Driving at speed in a crowded car through tunnels. I'm on the basement floor of something. Speaking Spanish. Trying to find a socket for my laptop and having to crawl aross a huge soft bed. Something about inefficient facilities management. Then S's mum, J, N. A telling us she'd heard from Jago about what rude , and ribald things they got up to in the island. Something about sausages waving around. N looks terribly embarrassed. I realise I'm not meant to have this knowledge.

My bedroom window looks out into the neighbors rubbish skip. They just throw things out the window which is above me. There's an ironing board. I try to talk to the guy about it but he is defensive and says he pays his rent. He's weaselish and has a scraggly beard. Then I'm in a house haunted by 2 murdered children. An enameled iron fireplace with smelly Voodoo dolls and all the children's personal effects. Swimming goggles, folders. We want to get rid of things and my friend throws then in a corner but I say we can prosecute posthumously. Call the police quickly! Garage door. That's where his ghost is - the dead father of the children. There's a finger pushing through the vinyl, like in an Ingmar Bergman film.  Door opens. Empty. I know he's coming in his Rolls Royce. His disembodied head is there at the café, in a blonde wig. It also stinks. Running through shops and cafes. Then suddenly, he's a squirrel in a perspex box. I hold him in the sunshine to burn him alive.
Jack Nicholson thin with illness. Far right tattoos. A coming energy crisis

I was walking around a city in the rain, i said it was Brussels and the person I was walking with I was describing how much I hated Brussels to them and how it was a rubbish city. I compared it to another similar city. We were walking through building sites and it was raining a bit. Then I was outside an apartment, it was now nighttime and I went to buzz on the doorbell, I had a bit black coat on with a hood. My sister was in the apartment.

escaping from the police or someone - I knew I needed to run away. I remember climbing over a balcony of a grand room, having to balance and get to the ground covertly. I was escaping Someone like mr burns from the Simpsons. I remember I was with someone else, but I don’t remember who. We went into a small bakery and hid under the tables. Though we were trying to hide, I still felt exposed like anyone could see me. We weren’t caught, and we sped outside where some women from the bakery were waiting to give us some food. It was baguettes and then a kind of crispy rice Roll. At some point I was driving my dads car, a bmw, in the bright sunshine and it was really hot. I kept getting out of the car, I think the road was like a procession at Notting hill carnival - there was music happening and dancing around me that I was aware of but couldn’t see

my family were hosting a party, but the party didn’t start until really late at night. We had been shopping somewhere during the day and come home really tired so we all went to sleep. The house was a strange warehouse, and I slept on a mattress on the floor. There were some boys sleeping nearby as well. Before I went to sleep I took some vinyl out of my shopping bag. They were to play at the party later. I think i felt I was trying to impress the boys with my vinyl collection. One of the boys was Zayn Lowe, the Radio 1 DJ. Then when I woke up after a nap, I went to the toilet to wash my face and wet my hair. The toilet was clogged with poo and also sausages which I had to break apart with my hands because they were really big and wouldn’t flush. There were also  disposable face masks In the toilet and I had to start fishing them out of the toilet with my hands as well. I was really angry that someone had done this, and I went to tell my mum. She didn’t listen, and I realised I was only wearing a T-shirt and the tattoos I have on my thighs which she doesn’t know about were showing, so I quickly moved away and told my sister about the bathroom, she agreed that was gross but good mum didn’t see my tattoos. The party started and we were waiting for a family friend, Oona, to arrive. When she did arrive she looked angry and started walking away. One of the other guests went and intercepted her and then she came back smiling. The party was half in my old junior school, half in an overgrown warehouse.

I was travelling alone, and I remember being in the Netherlands. I was on a train or bus, and there were people getting on who looked like immigrants from India or Pakistan. They sat very close to me so I tried to get up and move and then wasn’t sure which seat to sit in. The train then seemed to become a boat, and I was sitting by the window with my bag of things. Then my bag fell into the water and I was super distressed as it had my phone and passport in it. I somehow jumped into the water and got the bag back. I then spoke to a male passenger, and I was looking on my phone for a place to stay in the small Dutch town I had found myself in. I said to him that I had a friend in Eindhoven but I wasn’t sure I could get there. I was writing a report for school or university, not clear what exactly. I was working with a girl I used to go to secondary school with and we were frantically trying to complete the project. We were also watching something on a laptop, it was a bald man in a pub and he was the bartender, and one point he was threatening one of the customers, but then the customer put ten pounds in his shirt and that diffused the situation. I was stuck between watching this, and rewinding the clips for my friend to watch, and then also focussing on writing the report. It was hand written and messy, and I was saying how we would have to rewrite it because it also contained some of our early ideas we weren’t using anymore.   At some point I recall being in Virunga National Park and for some reason they were building some large walls around the place we were. Then they built a strange fire escape attachment with ladders. There was no gate.

I was throwing things around and my parents and boyfriend were watching. I was standing in front of an oven / cooker and hitting it with a frying pan. I was crying and grabbing my face quite a lot. At some point I was punching my boyfriend in the face - he was my boyfriend in the dream but didn’t look anything like him. He tried to hold me down on a bed to stop me hitting him and I screamed. I think he may have managed to calm me down. I also remember driving to buy wine in the middle of the night, I think I was drunk and going to some kind of party. I bought lots of bottles and then put them in my backpack. I also remember being in some kind of shop or restaurant and tasting a mix of spices, and someone was asking me how many cloves of garlic were in the spice mix. I said 12-15, and they said yes, the packed said 15-12 garlic cloves. The was also another moment where I was in the back of the car with two others who were maybe children, and these adult men in the front were going to assault us in some way, I tried to fight them and then they stabbed one of the other victims. I remember being distressed by this, but more in a way that I was fighting all these people around me. There was another part of the dream I remember being on a big escalator down into the tube in London and then being told to put a face mask on, and I was struggling to put mine on.

I woke up and wrote down a list of the contents of my previous dream in order to remember them to put in this dream log later. It was very clear and very realistic. I wrote on paper with a pencil - just single words or phrases to help me remember.
there were a couple of former pupils in it. I remember their faces - but nothing else.

I had a clear dream that my dog had a tick on her leg - so clear I had to check this morning that she didn't. The tick was small and beige and right in the middle of her leg, very obviously. I don't remember trying to remove it.

I dreamt about a Victorian house and I was in the house with somebody else and there were many rooms, but the one that worried me was the one that should have been locked and wasn't. There was somebody else with me - a man - and he tried to lock the door but also couldn't. Inside the door were more rooms and a staircase leading up to somewhere I really didn't want to go, and there was a creature we were scared of waking up - like a bear I think, but I never saw it. The man ate these plates of lichen in order to help him move quietly around the room, and there were circles and sigils carved into the wooden floor and on the cupboards. These had some great significance that I couldn't quite fully understand. I tried to follow him in but was frightened so didn't see all I could have. I also had to stop people going in and getting hurt - I did this quite violently at times. Next door there was an arena with many people that I knew but did not recognise and I moved between the two. The rooms were beautiful but dusty and neglected.

Text: being in some small northern coastal party kind of town. I was with some females. Perhaps we were all younger. There was someone there I was interested in. But perhaps because I was getting drunk or I could see things weren’t going well and I took some kind of break to let things play out for a bit without me there. Soem guy drove me around the town in a taxi or some kind of hire car past dawn. Out on the main street and up to a car park.
