Text: I was telling my sister in law Chanele, must have been on the phone, that the kitten was dead and she was saying ‘no it’s not.’ I said ‘it was before, it was rolled into a ball.’ There was some conversation about it growing front legs. We joked about how if she came over it would come to life. The grey kitten was on the ground rolled into a ball, like the pattern on a sea shell.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: I was a journalist, I had the job of hanging around or near Trump and writing 30 second vignette pieces about him. In depth descriptions about what happens with him across any given thirty second period. I was in the backseat of a limousine with him. He was about to get out to go to a rally. I wasnt feeling hostile to Trump. I felt quite friendly. We had talked earlier, and I knew I had a really strong 30 second vignette from earlier I could write. I said ‘have a great speech’ or similar (slightly friendly because we had talked earlier) I was by the rigt window, he was at the left, there was someone between us - Melania? - as he stood up (you could stand up in the limousine) he said in response to me “I….” but then got distracted checking his reflection in the driverr’s rear visiomn mirror, then he said ‘well you take care’ and crossed in front of me and got out of the right hand side of the car. It was a ramshackle rally at night time, only a couple of hundred people, wasn’t very rowdy, it was just on the broder of Marrickville and Enmore in Sydney, near The Factory Theatre, specifically Smith Street. Then I got of the limosuine and went to the public toilet where my friend Scott was there with my son Jem. Scott was holding his hand. I said to Scott ‘what was the last thing Trump just said? I need to write it down. Did he say (and I gave two slightly different variations on I think the ‘you take care’ line.)?’  Earlier there had been another scene of Trump I was watching on camera, like a vhs or cctv, the camera zoomed in on Trump from well above as he was waiting behind a couple of other people to get into the back of the limousine, he jumped up and down twice, excited like a little kid.

I could not turn a small car to the right out of an indoor car park where there were sliding glass doors like in a supermarket. There was also some kind of small pole there I had to avoid. It should have been easy but I kept doing the turn too late and the car was very unresponsive and heavy even though it was a very small car. There were quite a lot of people watching including Richard Vidler and I knew it was getting to the point that they’d start laughing, I didn’t look at any of them, I tried to stay in good humour and get on with what I was doing, I tried two or three times, backing up and trying again, trying to keep my head about me but there was a rising anxiety that I just couldn’t do this and I couldn’t think of any way that I could. I was wondering if someone was going to push me or whether I should get out and push the car myself. Knowing vaguely that it was kind of weird to push a car through something instead of driving it.

Dream 1  I was with Kurt Cobain. He wanted to play with me a song I wrote called ‘Lapsed Person’. I was fairly chuffed. There was some kind of revolutionary activity happening in the chemist warehouse in Surry Hills. Water or flooding was involved.  Dream 2 I was sleeping underwater in a series of different clips of underwater footage, there was one with a shark coming out from behind a rock.  Dream 3  I was running in a long distance running race. A dreary city’s backstreets. The guy running in front of me turned left but I climbed up over some kind of ledge through slabs of cement in disarray and into an old motel, high ceilings and dreary, backwater. I was directed to a room somehow where there were some older Middle Eastern Muslim men in a group watching something terrible that was happening on TV in a far off Middle Eastern country. They had their heads in their hands and couldn’t belive these people had done whatever it was that they had done again. It was catastrophic. On the TV some journalists tried to fly away in a helicopter and some middle eastern man propelled himself about 50 metres into the air to try and drag a journalist out of the helicopter. This was filmed from above the helicopter looking down, with a large group of rowdy people on the ground. I went upstairs to another room and my girlfriend Kelli was in there sitting on the edge of a bed at the far end of this big dreary room. She said it seemed to be raining inside and indeed there were puddles forming at her feet and water coming down in various spots. She said she was going to go to the bathroom. It was on the far side of the room to the left on the wall where I’d come in. When she was gone I quickly went to the old deep built in wardrobe to secretly check, although I was pretty sure there was no ritalin in there. The wardrobe was between the bathroom and the front door. To my surpise there was quite a lot in one long pack. As I was grabbing one, she came out of the toilet, I carried on what I was doing and pretended I wasn’t up to anything suss. She stood over me and said there was a woman in the bathroom, an older woman. I said ‘what?’ and i stood up, thought right this is my job to deal with and noticing i felt no fear i went in to check. I went into the old grey/green bathroom, with shower curtain and maybe steam from the hot shower but there was no one in there. I came back out telling Kelli that and the ritalin tablet I thought I had i must have dropped and it turned out to be an old brown partly shrivelled grape on the floor. I walked across a backyard that had similar old style stone work to that which appeared in the park, from one group of people to another part of a house, or a stand alone done up shed. In there was Nikki. I was surpised to see her here and I decided to go straight to the heart of the matter and said ‘how did your IVF turn out, did you get a baby?’ She said she would answer in the style of one of my answers and began singing something. I think she meant offence but I decided to join in the singing and came in at the end, to my pleasant surprise, in perfect harmony. Kelli’s mum was sitting at the table eating and I made a joke about ‘what it would take to take those potato gems off you’? She was laughing and I felt the warmth of an easy connection and was suprised how natural it was.

There was some kind of big gig being played at The Hunter on Hunter, a small 90’s pub venue in Hunter St Newcastle, with outside areas. My old friend Nick Roberts was wandering around in his distracted way. Kind of wanted to be there but also had something more important he wanted to do. Something intellectual. I was on a moving sit down escalator going slightly down. My friend Scott travelled past me going up. He was perhaps on a bluetooth phone I couldnt see and was listing Forever Since Breakfast song titles. ‘Ginchy Woo Woo’ he was saying. I said something like ‘classic Blackley’ to I think his friend Ernie who was somewhere near me. Then coming past on the elevator was Jeanette Moore, my son’s grandmother on his mum’s side. Jeanette has been dead about 4 years. I sat up a bit straighter when I saw her and she saw me and said ‘Matty’ and smiled at me and I smiled at her and I thought ‘My God what does she think of me.’ I was walking through a park. A big city park with stone work around gardens, an old ornate park. There were i think three hugely muscular guys doing some kind of aggressive training where they were throwing something at a tree. They were very serious and intimidating but I wasn’t in timidated by them and was going to walk between them and the tree even though the biggest guy was looking at me aggressively, but then I decided to walk around behind them. There was soemthing to do with my brother’s sixteen year old daughter’s birthday party going on. I was walking behind some midlle aged guy and I cut through the bushes on a corner to get ahead of him and hoped he wouldn’t find that offensive. Then I was sitting with famous Australian comedian Dave Hughes to do some video or sound editing. He asked me to put an effect on soimething and joked ‘have you got the budget for that?’ And I said ‘yeah, I topped up my account last night…or well I asked my dad to actually and he did’. And Hughesy was laughing and I couldn’t remember how to put the effect on beause I was distracted because I was making this famouys comedian laugh. The effect software was a silver box with four buttons or switches on it. Very old school.

In the middle of the street of my street where I grew up, a few hundred metres from my ouse, the corner of High and Bridge street was my white VW camper van, the van I've been fantasising about buying for over a year. A woman I was in a relationsip wit was in the passenger seat. I was returning to the van to drive. The van was surrounded by about seven or eight high school students, male, seniors, 17 years old or so. They WERE all looking trough the window of the van. My female partner was playing a game of some description on her phone. I'd been making a video clip for a famous indie folk singer previously. Someone asked me what I was doing it for - the same woman who was playing the game in the car. I said to her 'just let me do it my way.I'll do it for the reasons I want.' One of the schoolboys said to me a little smartly in reference to the clip -'what are you doing? You like the band do ya?' Trying to patronise me as being I guess old and not with it. I took the friendly approach and jumped into the driver's seat. I was aware there was a lot of these kids. One kid wit curly black hair was flicking a lighter at some exposed mechanics of the car under the steering wheel inside the car where my driver's feet would go. I said 'just leave it alone mate and get on with your own life. There'll be repercussions and stuff, you don't want to do this.' I didn't pull the door but I let him stay licking is lighter at the hole where my feet were, he thought there was something in there e could light that could blow up the whole car. I was deciding whether or not I'd let I'm go. he didn't do anything in the end. But I was also aware that the woman in the car ad kind o provoked this situation and I was assertive and dismissive of her while not being hostile to her - I wanted to do it my way. if I get into trouble I get into trouble. and I'm happy to avoid trouble just to keep the peace.

some black and white television documentary or news show, a photo of an old prime minister in parliament, a zoom on the photo, a slight grey haired man gesturing, but who by name didn’t actually exist in real history, voice over saying it was the most corrupt government in Australian history. Then two middle aged men walking in a paddock in conversation looking down tv overlay news/current affairs style, filmed on a long lens, one of them with curly more white than grey hair, the other the reporter in a suit. The curly white haired man saying he learnt a lot from the animals. He said at the age of 48 he had found himself wearing a snout. A snout was a brilliant thing animals had devised to filter things. the snout he had was made of hard grey material with felt on the outside, stuck out maybe 15 centimetres, covered his lower face in much the same way as a face mask. And he said it is also of course known by it’s other name ‘a Seminar’. This was like the Latin technical name, or what the experts referred to it as. It had ceased being a tv show somewhere along the line and I was on his property or involved. It was night. Maybe 4am. I went out to see his cows. There was soemthing remarkable about them. They’d learnt something. To think as a group or work as a group or something. I got out to this paddock. I was with girlfriend Kelli who I think was in a shopping trolley I now had to the side in front of me. This group of black cows, maybe 12 of them or so, all of them standing perfectly still maybe three, four metres or two cow lengths of me, they were so black only their silhouette could be seen in the night. There was perhaps a light mist. They were silent also. Still as a painting. A formation. They were different sizes, and not in a straight line but a group, some of them back slightly further so that the outline was uneven but also composed like a painting. I said ‘they look like a gang’. This stillness started to vaguely intimidate me and I realised I’d slid in behind the trolley as protection. I thought that’s not a good look and I decided to come out from behind and move us both back a bit. As I tried to drag the trolley back my back almost immediately pressed against a barbed wire fence behind me, a panic started to rise in me, there was no room to move, I was looking down and then with a swishing of tail a huge black bulk of a cow was upon me.

Kelli is not confrontational and she doesn’t want to be the queen. Some particular thing she said about ‘doing the job for something bigger’.   An art gallery. my old guitar teacher possibly from teenage years was doorman. There was a girl who kissed Chris Mcdermid and when she finished kissing him she said ‘we have a problem’ because her son sitting right next to them really liked Chris. That’s why she had kissed him. In the dream I got a close up of his facial features which I had never seen so close and looked at them through the eyes of someone who was admiring him.   Carolina was staying in Glebe, walking down the street and she wasn’t happy with me.   I was driving through Sydney and swerving out of my lane, finding it hard to drive normally.   My son Jem was walking through a park and he said ‘it gets heavy’ and he fell on the ground and sneezed four times.   We were sitting upstairs at a warehouse. Several in a group of people I didnt feel that comfortable with. Grey, dark, shadowy. Tamara was there dressed very elegantly in black, a kind of wrap around shawl. She was going to rap at a funeral the next day so I did some very bad beat boxing as a joke, but regretted that I’d started as I was going to need to keep going. She was walking up and down a plank and I was thinking how confident America had made her how it had turned her into an extrovert. I noticed she had pockmarks circling right around the edge of her face.

I was friends with Donald Trump. I was with him at my family home where I grew up. He’d completely lost his shit. He stole my mum’s car. He was completely wild. A wounded animal, steaming with sadness but at the same time utterly dangerous and unpredictable, totally in motion though, changing by the second. Me and him had some kind of falling out or I was just like enough’s enough. He was sure that anyone who fell out with him was losing out. He was more like a gangly sinewy teenager than a man. We had been working together on something for awhile and I said ‘you’ve taught me some stuff, but now you have to get out, now fuck off, fuck off Donald get out of here!’ I told him No Donald you can go. He tried to smaash evberything on the way out of the house. He picked up the antique purple lamp from the hallstand that was the only thing my mum ever told me not to touch in my childhood, and he stole it bending it in two somewhow, breaking it. Out of everyone I’ve ever known, Donald was definitely behaving most like my son when he was a teenager in real life. He went on to the neighbours lawn, it was night now, I think the neighbour was a well respected person from the industry I work in, Karryn, she had some other men with her, around her. Donald’s eyes were bright white with red rings around them. Totally crazy. Karryn went to call the cops on her mobile and Donald suddenly lashed out and stabbed one of the guys in the chest with I think a fork. The guy went ‘wo’ and stumbled and then fell on to his back on the lawn Donald started gloating saying he had no feeling at all, no regret, he was going to kill everyone on the way out. He was getting right down low, no friends in the world. There was something very sad about the scene. And then one of the guys lashed out and stabbed Donald back and Donald fell down on the lawn. I think he was goingto die.   My ex Kate, the mother of my child, was there too and she was saying ‘the house got sold that you didn’t buy and now it was getting sold again for way more money. What an idiot you’d  been for not buying it.’ It was the house nextdoor to my childhood that she was talking about, the one Donald was stabbing someone on the lawn in front of. Both the houses were empty. I tried to get my mum’s lamp off Donald but he wouldn’t let it go. We had been friends for awhile but if it looked like things were going to go bad Donald would just destroy everything. He just wouldn’t take no. It was really sad.   in town at night in Newcastle and people were just attacking each other everywhere, skateboarders, teenagers, just sliding into violent conflict at the slightest opportunity.

Baby twins, wide round faces of beautiful olive skin, apparently Brazilian, and one baby face spoke to introduce himself - "I'm Max, the one with the curly top lip"!.. Fail to remember the other's name, but the talking child introduced his twin brother too. I believe there was a footballer connection, parent/father, definitely famous.  Then I recall a pavement, but looking down through toughened glazing over an interior of a home, very stylish artistic architectural owners, elegantly relaxing in this environment, whilst being watched over by me from above. The scene was a mix-up of this fancy lower ground space, against a backdrop of street kids eg near a favela in Brazil. Then all change, to a park near my teenage home, running through back streets to take a short cut through that park, to get to a particular destination. There was possibly an old love-interest merged in there somewhere, very vaguely. There's a small humble cafe scene too, with very friendly owner, treating me like a regular, other people around with prams but sparse, and talking about the absence of a scheduled trip to visit family in Chile.

Partaking in slicing steak-cuts, and comparing the different cuts available, but they were being made from a mountain-side! There was a restaurant setting too, I recall working, and table-spacing.. Then a pub setting too, with familiar face talking of GB. Working offices in the neighbourhood, with some electrical or computer issues, I seemed to be involved in saying that they were very old systems and too clunky. Birthday planning also, maybe a party

Jumping into the sea, from a wooden yacht, clear turquoise water, though not so deep really. I was one of three and with my feet & toes I was trying to position a ladder underwater, from the sea bed to base of the boat. Inside we were sorting cupboards and food supplies, old items. My mother and I also separated the chairs in the room, as we tried to plan ahead with packing food, for future meal/picnic perhaps. An old friend was arriving to join us on the boat and he was proposing to bring a kayak and other water paraphernalia - he needed to phone ahead, to another mother figure friend of ours, so as to arrange the unloading of his car. Meanwhile my friend & stylist was due for a go-see appointment with lovely potential agents in south London, old trusted friends/colleagues from the past, Claire, Kate and Catherine. He needed to get there at quite short notice, all the way from north London, using northern line tube and then changing over to on an overground train for many stations. Alas, he would be better to cancel and reschedule as the hellish tube journey was way too busy and super risky/packed with people that late in the day. We would call to notify them.
there was a 'contract' document in my hands, which represented something solid/certain, and the sense of keeping one's word being important.
me with two pairs of high heeled shoes, one pair possibly white - not on my feet, but being carried/presented to me, ie into my hands, perhaps by or with my mother standing nearby.

there were old colleagues from various places, mixed together, women perhaps mainly there was an office environment, where new & old things were getting sifted/ sorted - but some food preparation was going on too, for sharing & presenting to the others for their opinions. then I was nervous about returning home, to a flat, on a large complex/estate which was in party mode, very loud, masses of people seen in various open windows. then very strong alcoholic drinks were being put in front of us, but I had to try and prevent my mother from taking & drinking them. yet overall the location was somewhere with a sea, not a holiday, more a familiar setting, definitely sea within touching distance, visually land met sea, but not quite the same as previous re-occuring dream setting by coast, different to that one.  Curiously, I also remember a friend telling me that I dropped/left my oyster travel card on the back seat of her car, but fortunately I had not needed it.

An old client/photographer is visiting for some printing services, he presses the buzzer and I say "3rd floor" and let him in. I'm with another man, a colleague, we're calm but distracted by radio or tv, something very interesting. But before arriving at work I'm at a small table with a take-away snack & drink, and there's an issue with some fellas nearby. Feel a sense of being taunted, or certainly apprehensive about staying any longer in such proximity to their very unfriendly talk/actions, and possibly a car.. I leave prematurely.

a road near my home, quite a significant route in the city, really clearly present by name.  Though there was another scene where I lost a shoe, it accidentally slipped off between platform and tube train.  An old employer friend of mine was around too, I was pleased to have her appear I think...  And some driving around too, nearby, within my neighbourhood, I was helping to navigate as I knew the streets better than the person/friend driving.

Scene of shared home/workspace with dear friend and her young family, was a little difficult, too many occupants, proving over crowded for normal family activities. I was offering some pasta to cheer them up, cute little shapes, like beautiful delicious ringlets. The space then became more airy and very modern, more of a home, with smae friend preparing a soup with broad green leaves, for a new pet/creature which was acclimatising to its new surroundings, possibly in something resembling a tank in the house. We had to remain calm/quiet in our rooms and just wait for the creature to feel at home. But the soup was causing puddles on the floor, and I was concerned that my mother would be displeased. Yet she was driving + arriving to the house with her arm in a sling, so I was trying to coordinate the various cars in/out of a congested driveway access area.

Definitely a pandemic situation, sort of lockdown scenario. There was a vast store, but also a small friend's shop, and a very long long wee!.. I seemed to be providing some make-up support, but also assisting with parcels for delivery. Friend's business was good and happy.  Mother's home was another setting. Strange activities, felt slightly in limbo, all very uncertain. Pub setting also, with some familiar faces there, but there was a strange floor, which was the main focus. I recall then hiding in my bathroom to avoid some nonsense rules and the noise.  Lastly, a bizarre arts & crafts moment, where I was creating an artwork/object on or beside the wall of my neighbour two doors down the street, and intensely pressing the material (soft dried apricots) between my fingers..

A strange place, environment, not a home, I felty as if I was passing through.. In one sense it felt like a shop, and I had a basket for while, and I recall sandwiches,.. a public space I guess. But very odd, almost like a museum/novelty town but certainly without much 'business as usual' going on, almost 'on hold', like a vast airport lounge. I visited a public bathroom, which had showers too, and this area had very large glazing which was alarmingly overlooked by a very busy bar/pub next door..

very busy, I thought I felt exhausted.. a sense of everything being entirely colourless. I was definitely engaged in my usual production work, and I felt that there was a great deal of stuff & detail going on

chasing, involving an old boyfriend, and another scared woman also appears.. there's a phone warning, then for a moment I'm kneeling very carefully onto a folded piece of cloth. I can say it was a some kind of foreign land, not home, though a little familiar. But the whole thing was somewhat of an exercise, not leisure, it was difficult.  In another part, it's all deep tube lines, with very long access tunnels and stairs.  Then there's a shooting venue, large stages with drive-in facilities, and I'm trying to coordinate vans arriving, dropping off equipment perhaps..

Virgin (airlines) was in operation, flying to Chile no less.. Our flights were booked, but the airport was a different & unknown location. My folks and I were in a strange town/city, madly searching for the essential airport-transfer bus, but in the chaos & panic of not knowing where we were, we missed it. So then we were stressed, wildly seeking a private car/taxi option, with only 15 minutes before the flight departure. Finally we did pile into a car, thanks to some generous help from some strangers, very friendly people. Bags, cases, sweat, not sure if we made it really, but I recall some vague seating detail that wasn't going to be great (due to our delay), for the uncomfortably long journey. Stressy and exhausting.

A large, rented property, poorly maintained and depressing to look at, an awful mess. There was struggle and subtle conflict with many other tenants about their irresponsible attitude to rubbish, which was making the building & grounds even more atrocious, and my life miserable. Suddenly, maybe a third of the front of property was sliced off, like a cross-section, and it was done (by someone else/superior) to reveal the dreadful extent of abuse by tenants fly tipping in their own yard as it were. It was stressful as I tried to bring things under control and restore calm.  My aunt and uncle were in another scene, it was an uncomfortable subject/situation, at a table, where I was silently listening, but then I exploded and swore, directly at her. Immediately sensed it was awful. In a separate scene, dear friends of mine (several generations) sat around their usual family table, voicing their religious commitments to their very valued & particular 'Sunday' fixture (possibly just a programme on the radio), and revealed that the father had not been taking part as he should have been, for some time. This moment was terribly emotional and moving for the first daughter and he, and I was inconveniently wedged between them as they tried to embrace and reassure each other.

I was making paper kites that were more like Chinese lanterns with elaborate tops that flared out. My dog carried one and another person. Gradually all sorts of different people took one into the garden. Some of the people I knew, some i didn't.  There were discussions about how they should be held, should the string have a handle or just a loop. I also remember walking through a shop that was being refurbished trying not to tread on all the tools lying around. Also remember  when I stepped into the garden i hadn't any shoes on and the ground was wet and muddy.

In a pub with friends who were working there. It was after hours. I had belongings in the pub- language teaching materials, wood I was going to carve. I needed them home i think I was moving. There was a woman there as well who had just got a mixed spaniel . Said the dog was called keeter. They helped me put things in my friends car. They would take them back and I would get a bus home. I started to walk but went the wrong direction so I went back to the pub. I knew I would miss my bus. Then the car wasn't working so we had to carry everything out again. They said they would come back and tidy before opening the next day.  I tried to ring a taxi but the phone wouldn't work.  Then another couple came out said they needed a taxi. Then I got a phone call from someone who I think had phoned me in another dream offering me a job. I was impatient and said call me back in five minutes as I need to use the phone. He said that was your last chance and cut off.  It seemed that one of the couple had collapsed and I had been trying to get paramedics to the scene. I knew I was dreaming and felt I was changing the story. Then somehow I got the job and it was a million a month, that it was some kind of games show giving people their dream jobs. It would mean going to the US to live.   getting on a plane but then somehow we we were  back in Cambridge. It was however futuristic in appearance. I was showing the American woman I was with a new hospital and talking about how good the transport was. We would get on and off these kind of trolleys as we moved around.  Then we were in the countryside. In front of me was a steep incline. I coiuldnt climb. Under the soil were pieces of velvet. I picked up different coloured scraps and squares planning to make a bag with it.   When I realised we couldn't climb the cliff of earth we found ourselves on level ground, lots of stalls around us with pieces of fabric on them. I spotted a yellow piece of velvet and took it.

I went next door. There was a stream and a lake. Not  many houses . She said she wasn't  going away until later and would now be back Monday  My ex lodger was there I was annoyed that he seemed so much happier  than before. I noticed how damaged the ceiling was. She seemed to have lots of cats so i offered to look after them and then I started to go home. I didn't have cats but lots of young birds that were miniature and kept  being washed  down a drain.  Someone I knew now wearing  workman clothes was waiting at my house.   Then I was cycling. I stopped  because I hadn't any lights and it was getting  dark. I paid £36 for some very complex lights. I couldn't work  out the instructions so the shop owner helped me. I think I knew him from somewhere.  His wife started talking to me about where I lived and how dry and barren it was. I said no there's a lake and its beautiful at this time of year

I am standing by a swimming pool thinking I might like to swim. I think I am in some kind of college. There is a statue embedded in the ground and is lying prone. But later it moves so I realise its a person. Someone is making a speech but I ca recall what is said. I go up to a room i share but keep opening the wrong room room 31.  I bump into  someone, maybe a work colleague and he asks how my holiday was. I said that was weeks ago but I am going away again next week.  My room mate and I only have one key to the door so I accidentally lock her in. Someone says some about me being vague today but again I can't remember what was said.

i was in a huge house which I owned. I woke and people chattering outside my  bedroom window. One was a girl that i recognised. I got dressed putting on lots of different layers. There were quite a few people about. I said there's always people about. I felt a little irked. I wanted them to understand  it was my house. Then I started a conversation with an elderly man about a previous lodger. I took him on a tour of all the rooms. Some i recognised or remembered some i didnt. In one room he pulled back the curtain halfway and i glimpsed a city. He said what was my favourite view. I struggled to recall anything but remembered and said when I lived in Sheffield I loved the view of the city at night with all the lights on so i suppose its the Isame.  I said i had the time to show him round because I didnt have to start work if I didnt want to until ten.  Then we were outside walking past  different buildings and appeared to be in the countryside.. We walked on and came to a children's school and then turned back. Then there was a ymca building, then a wood with keep out. I said it was probably  used for military training. He went in the wood and after a few minutes some territorial army asked him to leave. We continued back to the house. I had an idea for the house. I said I would like it to be a craft centre where people would stay for a short while work on their crafts. We would have a visitor centre where they could sell their work if they wanted, the man said I would have to work out the finances, make a plan . He said he knew people we could approach for this.  We got back to the house. There was conversation about someone going to a wedding  of the man whom she had loved. Then i suggested that a murder mystery might be fun. I said you can download it for free. We went into a room with lots of strange old keyboards that were difficult to use. My friend Carole. The letters were tiny and odd. I struggled to write the search terms and Carole was irritated with me but eventually  managed. Then we went towards the house again as I needed to  get some money. I told him and another that they should go into Darlington and get a printer and some A4 paper. There was some blue paper by the keyboards but it wasn't ours

some mechanic fixed some ethings he had found. One was a car. They said they were for me. I didnt want to tell them I had crashed the same type before, the other thing was rectangular but inflated and was like some kind of electronic skateboard. I used this as we headed towards where we were going.. we were in someones home. We went up to their garden which was an extension of their apartment.  It was hexagonal and on the roof, somethingwas buzzing and flying outside and a saucer shape piece of metal smashed into the garden, about the size of a dinner plate. They continued to bombard us in the garden. The couple had two monkeys which when we looked down to a lower garden were there.  One of the monkeys was hurt and we went down. Fur was falling off and his skin was bright green. The monkey kept saying I'm dying. The monkey died and his terrified mate jumped up and clung to me.  We went back up and now the fliyng vehicle swooped lower over us. The size had somehow  changed. I grabbed it and flung it towards the ground. They crashed and the guy in it said he was going to report me to  the police. I was just angry.   Then some sort of device in the garden apartment let out the voice of the monkey saying I am dying. I said you have recorded it all, you must let me have the recordings. I think they were reluctant to do so and I was trying to persuade them.

Iwas in my flat. There was a budgie. It laid eggs on a flower pot saucer balanced on a stand. I said they would not hatch that she was feeling broody. They hatched. At first I thought there was one dead but when I turned back it was OK. There were 3cchicks fluffy and yellow. I went upstairs to tell my neighbours Maureen and Chris. I also tol ad them the snake was twisted round a stick attached to the flower pot, that it was dead and the skin stripped away. I said i thought the budgie was feeding the chicks with this. I felt repulsed. Chris was concerned, said he was going to bring some chemical to ensure the snake was dead.  next I was in the kitchen trying to keep the chick's in the kitchen away  from the  cat. One chicken had lost a leg.  I wanted Chris to take the budgies away. I felt uneasy and uncomfortable   somone not liking me and she taking everyone away for several days. I was supposed to go but was left behind.

In a kind of church hall...having an evening to prepare for...tho it was a bit like a large bathroom. Some people were helping too.I went back there in the evening...a black female was there already Everything was beginning to look really clean.John Platt was there too.  I told the female I had come by bike, so I'd had another friend to bring me there by car. She was really surprised. It was all either for a parents school evening or for people coming to stay. I saw close details of the surfaces and cleaning materials, they were all shining white.  People were expected soon. I think Abbie's parents were coming too. Lots of other people were involved but I didn't see them. It was a place we used in daytime and needed it to be ready for something in the evening.

We were trying to support Mary and persuade her to move ...it involved a lot of phoning different people. We were almost persuading her...I had to pack a lot of things I needed...especially my heart medication....and food for the journey. We'd arrived at our destination...there were 8 of us...children playing on the floor were part of us...one adult male wasn't happy about it. I was looking through a whole heap of programmes, looking for tickets for the right ones.There were lots of different people coming and going and merging in and out.I was hoping all would be ok. Timescale was really important ...I thought it would all be very good for Mary.

I was in a large indoor space, like a church or sports hall, trying to sort out covid arrangements....who had caught the virus, what questions did people have, what should people of. My son Barney was helping to organise it. There was a lot going on, I felt ok about it and glad that things were being sorted out.

In a doctors surgery, waiting for diagnosis for Peter. P was sitting at a desk reading and every time he looked up his face kept changing to that of a US senator with bright white teeth. Another doctor came in . P is writing a lot, he looks up again with a different face and said in an American accent that he's finding titles for his poems. The doctor clearly says he feels "very tender" about what he's going to say. I said whatever it is we'll be positive and face it together.
I was in a new lifedrawing class and I'd made the best black and white drawing I'd ever done in my life...it took 10 minutes and I put the date on it.

In my daughter in laws new flat...kind of basement. She wanted me to meet her two flatmates They were women, one blonde ish who just passed through the room.The other entered the room but I couldn't see her well...she looked fuzzy ..so I asked her to come forward which she did and I could see her clearly..very smiley tall thin with long black hair. I had a good feeling about both of them and knew my d-in-law would get on well with them. There was a lovely atmosphere in the room and I could hear my grandchildren playing happily outside.D.in law was lying on top of the bed..I was sitting next to her. It was summer and warm. She told me their names and I thought they were hard to remember and I might get them mixed up.

We were in a seaside holiday house/hotel...Cornwall/Wales...the female owner was very warm and welcoming..I was aware all our family were there too...I was looking out of the 1st floor window on to the beach..saw a preteen girl standing in the sea holding what I thought at first was a large fish, then saw it was a seal pup and could see its shiny brown eyes and black and grey speckled skin very clearly...she put it carefully back in the sea.Back in the room there was a male teenager trying to mend my large gold watch...gave it to me then I lost it having searched everywhere...the room was very untidy. I called to my youngest granddaughter to come and watch a man dancing on a rock on the beach who was wearing a pink tartan shirt and white shorts.When she came in he had gone. I talked to the owner about how she needed more wardrobes so she could put things in and sell them..she agreed. I could smell the sea and feel warmth in the room. I watched more people having fun on the beach. Kept searching for my watch. Then walking in the country and finding granddaughters shoes and putting them on her. Felt it was a happy holiday..talked to the owner who said she'd been there 2 years. I met a female guest who came out of the loo and was putting sanitizer on her hands.Then she joined me at the window..the sun shone directly on her and I thought it could be a good place to sunbathe. Kept thinking what a gorgeous place it was and how I wanted to stay.Same holiday but we were going to it by train and met US male..found he'd been to the place where I grew up.We were then walking along the beach..thought about a swim..but not yet. I was walking upstairs carrying 2 of my paintings and watched a white and ginger cat undulating across chairs in the sunlight. I sat with the man and we talked about similarities and differences of GB and US words. Peter came in with large,good bottle of red wine and we wrote postcards. I saw it was 4.40 on the watch I was wearing. We walked through other guests rooms which were open, some were really tidy some messy

I was with my friend Annabel in a house by the sea.She hinted she had health problems. We sat at a table indoors -lots f comfortable silences.Other people were in the house. Wanted her to speak but didn't want to press her. Then another woman with dark hair was at the table.Annabel said have I read the book she gave me,  sad what book as I felt bad that I couldn't remember it.The woman opposite said she had got it and it was the best book she had ever read.I asked if I could have it when she'd finished. I was staring at the table and there was a brochure...maybe a food one...and the wordsDELVER ROSE stood out and felt meaningful, I thought it could be someone's name. I tried to tell Annabel but then I couldn't find it. Still silence. I suggested a walk then she said shall we have more tea, and then Ill tell you and be completely honest, and you can tell me everything too. I said ok.I couldn't think what she meant, but guessed it was everything she'd been experiencing in lockdown.

We were in a holiday house by the sea with several different friends. We were travelling in a car with two friends who had changed into their younger selves, one started crying and his dad said not to worry he's ok.We were then walking in the country side and seeing other children and I said to Peter imagine our grandchildren being as tall as that. Our oldest grandchild said very clearly "Damn the Dust". In the holiday house we were making sure the food would last the week, tho we were eating a lot. In the car again I noticed P and a friend's hair looked exactly the same length., and a dark grey. Back in the house I was reaching up to put oil into 4 large frying pans which had frozen potato cakes in but as they were so high up I couldn't quite see so a friend offered to help. There was a feeling of open air.

I was returning from a place where things hadn't gone well.Arrived at a deserted railway station, one train there, and asked a middle aged man if this train goes to Birmingham.He replied in a foreign language that seemed like a no. There seemed no one else to ask. Then I found Sophia in a big hangar.She seemed older, she'd been talking to a young boy she'd just met, they were not getting on well, he was making her cry. I tried to tell her not to be upset by someone she'd just met, she tried to cling on to him but I could tell it wouldn't work out.I looked back and saw the train just pulling out, I thought it must be the Birmingham one.I saw very tall bright green weeds growing up through the tracks, and realised how deserted it was, and to remember to tell Soph's mother what had happened. Then I was half at home and half at friends in Hereford.Jess was there and I was getting ready to go to a Samaritans shift at 9am. I was getting dressed putting on 2 pairs of trousers, one thin, one thick, and arranging a big bowl of salad . I tipped it up and carefully put it on my head like a hat looking at myself in the mirror..everyone thought it looked great but I thought it made my head look too big so I removed a few leaves still looking in the mirror and thought it looked better. I had to leave and catch a bus or train, and Jess asked me how she thought her mum was I found it hard to answer as I didn't want to worry Jess, so I made it seem that I thought she was better.

Cycling down the steep hill near the house I lived 20 years ago. Aware that a woman was driving behind me and being sure I was signaling left . In a house half in London and half in my old house I was looking after a collection of children. They were all playing together well even though I didn't know them very well. I was aware their parents would be home soon.....they were making a huge mess and I worried it would seem bad for their parents to come home to. I walked up shiny wooden open stairs and helped a young girl to tidy up...she was folding her dolls clothes really beautifully then we were about to go downstairs when I realised I couldn't because I had strong vertigo...started to panic...told the girl and she put her doll at the top of the stairs and slid it down what I realised was a slide. They both went down and I then had confidence and was able to walk down easily. The father then came in the door and said Hallo Greta to me, and I told him my real name. A young boy came in with him with blond curly hair and was instantly smiling and pleased to see me and I recognised him from a dream I had a while ago.

We were with close old friends Peggy and Graham and their 2 daughters who merged from between being children and adults.We were aware of covid and once I got too near them and said sorry. I could sense there was something wrong between them which they were hiding and not talking about.Summertime.We all sat in our front room, I gave them drinks and one big bowl of fruit that I'd carefully arranged. I could see lots of people outside the window. Peggy said I looked very tired and I told her I was doing  the dream survey, and she waved her hand and said not to tell her but to tell Graham, that it would do him good. We went for a walk..took food..and instead of our city it turned into a lovely countryside..dusty ground. I noticed their daughter was crying and unhappy and saying she had a bad headache. I told Peggy and she said she'd be fine and to keep on walking, but her daughter lay on the ground, so we went back. We moved to the side of the pathway to let other people pass. Back in the kitchen I overheard Graham saying a few years ago he'd found a bad smell under our cupboard...turned out it had been a dead cat...he said only female cats smelled like that...said there was hardly anything left of it.I said I remembered a friend's cat disappearing and wondered why we hadn't smelled anything. They were uncomfortable. I wondered what it was.Graham was making strange jokes. I showed him my paintings which he said he liked. Lots of different conversations going on...I wanted to know what was wrong with them but didn't know how. I looked in the mirror and saw how tired I looked, bags under my eyes,and put on tinted foundation. I wanted to remember how lovely our walk was and why we hadn't known about it before. I exchanged very meaningful glances with their daughter.Theyd bought me a very nice present....also costumes for us all to wear.

I was with a group of good friends in a beautiful old beamed house in the country..many of us wère staying there. Someone said "listen to how quiet it is here compared to the city" we all listened and really could appreciate the silence. There were 2 large shiny wax- looking stains on the pale carpet.There were two very large beautiful dogs in the room. There was a couple who had just broken up and one went off to sleep in another room.It was night time, the big room was fairly dark. I felt I was younger than the others.There was a fire in the grate.Someone brought in  "something special" from the outside. I was lying in a large bed...the atmosphere was growing very spooky. One dog leapt over me...I said I can't sleep here. Then the other dog leaped over me and it was obvious they were both looking for the waxy stain.Everyone was looking very knowingly at each other as if they knew this place was haunted/scary. I had definitely felt the heavy weight of the dogs as they leaped over me.

It was like a tense adventure film...I was doublecrossing two men in affairs...one was very frightening...tension was building up all the time..I was about to be found out...night time..it was like we were all following a script though it was real...we were outside and everything was going wrong...would I get found out? the scene was lit up with a single bright light

Walking along creek near the primary school I attended. Theres some boats there. Kids are catching a fish. They pull it up on the road and a car is waiting for them to finish collecting it. I walk down to the creek. There a long boat there, the kind that travels through narrow canals in Europe. It's trying to turn the corner but the water is too shallow. I think that that would be an interesting way to live, just on a little boat.
Dreamt I was playing VRchat.

Everything whites out. A chant fills my head. "I'm an the divine and I am here to manifest it in this world. " Everything around me is filled with bright white light. I feel a strong surge of energy. My whole body is filled with bliss. Everything whites out til I can only see my hands. Then I am standing in front of a girl, she is laying on a table. She is unwell, I will intuitively know she has lung problems. I realise that I can heal her with hands and energy. I almost do it without asking but realise I need to ask permission. She agrees. I instruct her to breathe deeply and relax. She is blabbering about something unimportant.

I can still breathe through my nose so the reality check failed, therefore I must be dreaming. I'm fully lucid now. I fly out through the window over and into the front yard. There's some very strange looking plants with large yellow pom pom flowers on the end of white stalks. Very bizarre. I look up ahead and can already feel the dream fading. I rub my hands together as hard as I can to anchor myself in the dream, it works! I fly down to the creek and take a look, its flooded and the water is very high and brown. I consider going in but I don't really want to get wet. I feel a little splash as the water laps against a tree trunk. Hmm that's enough for me, I keep flying. Suddenly theres an underpass and a weird circular white building that looks like it belongs in a James Bond movie. I go and investigate. The door is frosted glass and there's a plaque next to it. I can read it clearly 'Beren Maintenance Facility'. "Hmm, seems suspicious" I think. I've never heard of it before. It certainly doesn't exist in waking life. I float through the glass door without any resistance. There's a reception desk but no-one there, and a spiral walkway that leads up to the higher levels. There's an office with a frosted glass door, it looks like two women are behind it and I can just make out their sillouette. I decide to go in. There's no one inside, must've been an illusion. There are a few desks with many items, looks like medical equipment but also there's a section with children's toys like a wooden colourful play area. I leave the room and explore more. I start walking up the walkway to the next level. There are some nurses about and some patients on wheeled beds. Was this a medical facility or maintenance facility? Looks like a specialist hospital or something on the inside. The dream starts fading again, so I start rubbing my hands together but it's not working as well as I'd like. I go down on my knees and rub my hands into the carpet, it's quite thick and a dark navy blue colour. I can feel the threads running through my fingers like thick strands of wool. It works and the dream stops fading. I look up and a really cute girl walks past, she isn't wearing a uniform. She walks up and into the toilet, and I soon follow behind. She's already sitting on the toilet with her pants off, legs spread. "Wow is she keen", I think. I go up to her and kiss her. With Friend H, walking neighbourhood I grew up in. Big passionfruit vine, there's a monster sized passionfruit, about the size of a small rockmelon. Both in disbelief. I say I'll be rich because i have created my own variety of huge passionfruit. Cut it open, mixture of passionfruit and cut kiwifruit inside. We're both confused. Go to the shop, there's seeds on the shelf. Relieved that theres finally seeds on the shelf again

I am with my girlfriend, I fear that she is cheating on me. I confronted her about it. She says I've already told you that I would never cheat on you. The dream unfolds and I am still worries she is cheating on me and I have to ask her again.

I was part of a lage crime family who had apparantly made their money by stealing it in some way from aontoher family - I think I had 10 siblings the youngest of which was at one point my stepdaughter, we were sitting in a restaurant and then we sudenly had to dsappear 3bause the other family had discovered we had nicked their money - so we all piled into a taxi, but the taxi sped off to quickly and me and the youngest sibling were left behind - (the car sped off before we were propery in the cab and so we kind of fell out. We walked after it for a while, on a long, narrow street which I thnk was in London - My'youngest' sister couldn't phone them because only certain phones could call certain networks - my phone worked, but it took me ages to dial the number and it didn\t work. We were sitting on the pavement when a guy came looking for us - he was talking on the phone to the father of the family. He had been sent to find us - then we were with th family again and my stepdaugher ha turned into a differnet person but still my youngest sister - we got into a fight with the mother and. I wasn't me in this sdream as such - I felt like I was playing the part of this other person.

I'm in a film set but I know all the plotliines - as well as being part of it - this one was a family tye drama I thiink, there were servants, one of whom disappears upset because her 'boyfriend' seems uninterested in her - tere was a party that finished at ten o clock and it was in a house that was massive and had loads of corridors and a dodgy lift. Then a white tiger turned up later. the tiger was almot a family pet - and was happy to be hugged and petted, although I felt very nercous when I did it.  This seemed to take place in a different house.

I dreamt I was in my granny's old house for a night on my way somewhere, mr granny is dead I was supposed to be there alone, but then my uncle turned up and some other man I didn't know who was also staying - I was a bit nervous about stayng in a house with a man I didn't know, but then my uncle decided to stay the night too. I was then in my hometown and in two of the houses I;d lived in when I was younger - my dad  was there (in the second house) and we were waiting for my mum who was out somewhere - it was after midnight and we were in the hosue where i grew up as a teenager - someone came in (a girl) and we were going to chase her away but hten she said she lived here once and she was being chased - I was both on a bike and driving a car - and I was wored about mum because she'd been so tired. Then m y stepdaughger was there and she was wrapping up a cat to take home.

I was in prison, although I don't know why - it seemed to be quite an open prison, even though the place looked liked a dungeon - although quite a large one - we could walk around a lot of the time, but a lot of the time were were in cells with iron bars. I had my cat with me. I was being released that day, and my mum and aunt came to collect me. On the way out I say my young cousin wh had just been jailed for 12 years - I told him he'd be out in 8, then I procedded to tell him wher he;d find the best clubs and stuff in the place - I told him there were ways of enjoying yourself if you know where to look. The cat kep disappearning but always reappeared again. Then suddenly I was in a resturant/canteen type place, but with other inmates - think we were out for a trip? thinking I should be sitting with another group of people who I'd usually sit with, but because I was in prison, I should stay with the group I was with.

it was the 1960s and I was following the life of someone - she was always in trouble, losing jobs, - it was like the plot of a film or book - she kept moving flats and I'm not sure if she was me or not...she had a baby at one point, there wereparties going on and friends that kept chaning and coming nd ging because she was so unrealiable...then I was away on a trip with a bucnh of peole - I knew most of htem but they were all from differnet parts of my life - there were sports going on at some point then we all left in a bus, but it might have been a plane? It was relaly hard to climb into..

I was on holiday somewhere and the people I was with varied from moment to moment - firstly my husband and mum, later a childhood friend. One minute it was a snowy place, the next it was somewhere sunny. The bedrooms were basically just the chairs in the lounge part of wherever we were and they just got pulled out and everyone slept where they were sitting. At one point I lost my freind, and felt that she was ignoring me so I decided to go home - when I did find her and tell her, she was upset, but I as angry with her and said it was just the same as when we were 15 and she belw hot and cold with who she wanted to be friends with. She insisted we were 14 and this took up quite a bit of the dream. Then I was back in my childhood home again, in the amusement arcae where we all used to hang out. It had changed and was really busy and I just wanted to get out, but I htink I was looking for someone.

I was in Vietnam, only it wasn't - helping people escape, as the country was in a mess and had a dangerous regime. Someties it was a group of people, other times it was just a couple or me and one other person. I'm pretty sure Sandi Toksvig was there ...We hid in an underground 'bunker' at once point I think, and one we got somewhere but there was not eough food for everyone? So we had to hide... I helped a vietnamese couple escape and took them to Ireland, through some kind of underground system, then I popped next door to tell my neighbour I was carrying a large pick and dragging a heavy black bin bag, whcih I had made heavier on purpose by filling it. My neighbour called me Sara instead of Sandra, and made me tea, but I didn't have time to drink it as I had to give someone the bin bag on a hillside. I dragged the bag up the hill to ive this person, a young man, who I seemed to know. He was amazed I'd made the bag heavier than it needed to be, but that seemedt be the end of - he was pleased with what I'd done.

I was in a college or universty, and was sitting a a desk covered in paperwork to sit a final exam. I didn't feel like Iknew anyhting, ad I think one of the questins was about Shakespeare - The lecturer was there, and sat down to chat to the class - There were aother people around, and none of us seemed to feel very stressed - I felt almost meh - I remember thinking that I could probably blag, and there wre documents that I could refer to when I was doing it. Then I was on a boat...

I was in a big audotorium, which looked a bit like the european parliament (curved chairs etc) but there was a stage, well, a few stages. But I was watching everything on a screen while I was there...I think...First there was some kind of dance performance, but the dancers fell, but it was fine because they got up and carried on (this was replayed a few times). One of the dancers was someone I'd worked with when I lived in Budapest.  Then Michael Gove turned up because an incident was being investagated where he attacked someone with  a big stick...I think the aim of the investigation was to find out if  he really did hit the person or whether he missed/was pretending. I remember thinking that surely it shouldn't make a difference if the attack took place anyway, and then I felt quite pessimistic because I knew he'd get away with it. Then the person he attacked appeared next to me, and was loudly cheered by a group of people, including Barack Obama. He was doing a kind of victory dance...

I was at work and redoing a couple of days of a course that finished a few weeks back, then I was the student in a class, and left as I wasn't feeling well. I went to the doctors to try and make an appointment - my doctor came to see me in the waiting room and I told her I was feeling bad - very depressed and did I need my tablets adjusted - she didn't want to do that but gave me a herbal remedy to bathe my feet in. I was a bit pissed off because I didn't think they would work. I asked her about stopping the tablets - mabe they were making me worse, but she said no. I left the doctor's and went into a shop - I rememebr feeling really ill and unbalanced - I bumbed into someone who started shouting at me - I told her I didn't feel well and she apologised. Then I was at home my mum was there and my dad had apparantly gone to berlin to talk to a bank who had sent a plane for him. I felt very depressed and mum was also upset and was crying a bit.

I was in a house that I didn't recognise though I knew who was there - 2 old friends (a couple) and 3 of their 4 sons, including my godson, the boys now all in their 20s. The boys were upstairs in a loft, in bunk beds, but now they appeared much younger. I was happy to see them. I climbed up the stairs and gave them presents - they were surprised. I also gave them a huge spray bottle of orange juice and another one of champagne! I think the idea was they would spray each other with the bottles, a game.  The scene shifted to outside - a sloping headland looking over the sea. I was aware it was public land. I think I was annoyed that the headland was now covered with people camping in a variety of things - tents, swags, caravans, etc. They were quite crammed in. I could hear complaints about the number of people all together.

I came across an old friend in the bush, who I think was protecting an old growth forest. I passed on some recent environmental news whereupon we ended up in a cafe/meeting place where people were eagerly waiting to hear from some others about similar news events. I was annoyed when my sister and mother walked in as they wanted to have coffee and chat instead of listening to the presenters. I was dustracted with them and i think ended up having to leave.

hearing some noises that indicated to me there was someone in the house. I wasn't sure if I was imagining the noises, or exactly what they meant, I was just lying there listening. i was lying on my side and then I felt a sharp nudge on my back. our dog had come in and nudged me firmly.

I was at a mostly empty airport, in London I think. I was supposed to be flying home to Australia. My father had died. The staff couldn't find my booking initially, and I was upset. Eventually it was found, but the only way I could travel home was by Africa.
a series of fragmented dreams about homes and schools

Text: theft
being in a large castle and running up and down stairs. My parents and in-laws were there and we were engaged in a playful hunt for each other.
my youngest son saw an advert for Sea World with a picture of Godzilla and so we went there.

I was in a car with my husband late at night at the bottom of a hill in a rural area. He was in the driving seat and I was sat behind him. We had a lot of equipment in the car and we were on our way up the hill to a large wooden castle. A lot of people were dying there and we wanted to help. The mileage dial on the car dashboard kept moving up, indicating how many more people had died; it just kept rising and rising. My mother in law wanted to travel with us but there was no space in the car. She said she could walk and so we drove off. But then we figured out how to make space and so at the entrance to the grounds of the castle we stopped. There were many other cars making the same journey and many people walking. My husband went to look for his mother but she had caught up with us as we had travelled so slowly. we prepared to enter the castle.

I was standing on a round table in the middle of a large room that could have been a cafe; it was my parent’s house although I didn’t recognise it. I was fully dressed and taking a shower but there was no water. There was a fridge in the room. My mother had been out shopping and bought a few things I would like. As it turned out, they were all made of glass and functional such as an ornamental brush and pan, ie, not food but because they were made of glass I could not use them either.

There was a woman. She was tall with short brown hair and not slim. She wore a regular skirt and top and flat shoes. She was different to the people who had come before her, more honest. She was in our home but when we spoke about her we were standing on a stage in a theatre and she was in the audience. We praised her for not trying to make a show of everything, for being real.  Then there was Napoleons kake. I cut it up and tried to do it fairly but that wasn’t possible. My fourth son came later than the rest and couldn’t decide which of the final slices to take.

We must have been in school because we had an assignment where two pupils had to draw together on the same piece of paper. My friend took the lead and wanted to draw with me. I agreed. But then another friend came to me with most of her paper filled in and told me that I had to complete the blank areas she had left for me. I said nothing about my plans with the other student.

My husband I had to choose a school for our youngest son. There wasn’t much choice – only four schools and no information about them. I took my youngest to his first day. I could see it was a nice school and thought about getting a job there. There was a large colourful classroom and many children sat the floor (perhaps 40), but the problem was that these children all had special needs. I had a slightly heated conversation with my husband, but he said we had no information that it was a special school and I knew this was true. We decided that our son would have to stay there whilst we made an application for him to go to another school.

My husband and I were in a train travelling across Oslo. There was a woman and her young son. The son was very smiley and I kept talking to him. She said a few words to him and I guessed she was Finnish. She said that she was actually an anthropologist and used words from many different cultures.

I was living in London, in the same borough. Somehow, there was an old school friend there. We spent a lot of time walking around the town and I showed her my old house from 3 years ago. We talked a lot about our children, especially our eldest who are both of university age. I wanted to know what her daughter was now studying. Her daughter was in my mind, I had an image of her wearing a plain beige dress that just hung on her like a sack. I did not see her face.  Later, we were standing by my old house and I was playing a recording of two of my children playing with a friend in the snow in Oslo. The recording must have been 12 years old. I felt the presence of my eldest child at his current age and we laughed a lot.  Suddenly, my two children were young again and in my dream. We were still in London, but it was covered in snow and looked like Oslo. A woman and child were with me and I guess they were my friend and her daughter. Then we bumped into another old friend and his son. the child had a massive piercing on his lip and in his ear. He was, perhaps, 12 years old. I made a big fuss of him and told him how cool he looked. I also told my friend that I was envious that he had been brave enough to do that and that I wanted my children to have piercings. But at the same time I was really feeling that my friend had issues and should not have done that to his child.  I felt very close to my male friend. He is very tall and he had put on a little weight.  we stood very close to each other and there was some energy between us.   My female friend and all the children were sat on a bench, but my male friend was trying to organise something else. I walked back to speak with him. We were alone and I felt happy. We walked back together to arrange the children and implement his plan.

My family and I were watching a new game show on the television. It was essentially about general knowledge questions with a choice of six answers that were flashed up on the screen. One of the questions was ‘What was special about a set of mountains that were called the Giant Mountains?’ I made some smart joke that was clever and everyone laughed. But then my eldest son knew the real answer and said they could be seen from space. Suddenly, I was in space with a group of astronauts (4 or 5). We were floating very far away from the Earth and I had a sense that I had joined an ongoing conversation. They were discussing the answer to the Giant Mountains question and trying to identify where it was on Earth. They pointed it out and then started showing me other landmarks on Earth that could be seen from space. One of the astronauts (a man) said that what he liked most about being on the moon (I suddenly noticed we were floated near the moon but not standing on it) was that he could see the whole of the Earth. It was then time for us to return to Earth. We did this through a free fall. At first this was exhilarating but as we got closer, I started to worry about how we would pass through Earth’s atmosphere. I thought to myself that the body I was in had gotten out to space and so there must be a plan for getting back (I was aware it wasn’t my body). So I just relaxed and suddenly we were approaching the ground. I decided that I would trust the body to know what to do as I saw the other astronauts pulling at parachute straps and landing on the ground. My body did the same thing. Then as we all took off our helmets, I saw that the astronauts were a group of men and one woman. The dream suddenly became black and white. Three of them were presenters of the children’s program Blue Peter from the 1960s.

I was taking my son to school for the first time after the Covid lockdown. He had forgotten how to get his clothes ready for school and so had a sports top on instead of a shirt and jumper. We got to school and realised I had to run home and get his clothes. We discussed his timetable and which teachers he needed to speak with. I spoke with the school secretary and we decided he should walk around with his trousers but not his sports top and so he went to his lessons late and half dressed. When I was outside the school, I bumped into someone I hadn’t seen for a long time. She wanted to show me three tattoos that she had on the back of her hand, but they had gone wrong (they looked like a small cluster of round scars). She wanted me to advise her but my mind was on getting home to collect my son’s clothes. (I have a sense that I returned to the school and all was OK with my son)

I was in hospital and had had a baby. Someone thought I wouldn’t know how to feed the baby but it was easy. My parents visited me there and we all sat on the bed together. Later, I was at as swimming pool.The people there thought I wouldn’t be able to swim so gave me two short time slots and told me to come back later. I needed to drive home. I used my mother’s old van except it had been altered and half of the boot had been removed. I hadn’t driven for a long time but I knew I could do it. Then one of the staff from the pool came and sat with me. Both at the pool at the hospital, I recall a lot of unwelcome attention from authorities.  I drove back to my parents home town but when I got there it was dark. My eye sight seemed poor but I decided I could still drive. At one point there were some bright lights as I had to pull out into traffic. I managed it but I knew I wasn’t safe. I decided to get help the next day. my parents I could see in my mind. They were not together (my father was at home but my mother was stood at a bus stop) and they were struggling because they had to wait so long.

I had just started at an office. They did a lot of research. I spent time looking around and meeting other staff (all white females). The main focus was concerning a literature search I had done and the criteria I had used for the search. In particular, the synonyms for life and daily living. I was told I could get help from a younger PhD student who was very helpful and shared her paper document. I remember being very grateful and although apprehensive in my new role was happy.  I was on a bus on the way home (I think it was on the way back from the university). There were a group of young white men towards the back of the bus. They were lively but not threatening and I believe they might have been a sports team. I was on the bus but more as an observer. I was not physically present. They were going to have their photo taken and so one of them stood in the aisle whilst the others all flung themselves in different positions to smile.  One of the older guys (white hair, a little overweight, perhaps late 50s) sat on the floor near me. He had a blanket around his shoulders. I could see that it had got caught on the wall below the seat. The seat must have been above the wheel because the blanket was getting dragged in as the wheels of the bus turned. The man did not notice what was happening at first but I could see it tightening around his neck. Then he realised that he was been dragged through the mesh and to the undercarriage of the bus. Everyone started shouting because they did not know what to do. The driver (male) stopped the engine but we were now on a hill and the wheels would not stop turning. The man was now almost completely outside and we knew that he would die if the bus was not allowed to come to a standstill by itself. But the thing was that we were on a hill and heading towards other people. The driver was going to have to put the brakes on. At this moment, another man appeared. He was a white male, taller, perhaps in 40s. He was a reflection of the first man and also half trapped between the inside of the bus and its undercarriage. They knew each other and there was a lot of anxiety because they knew that saving one meant that the other would die. They could not both live. One had to sacrifice himself when the driver put the brakes on.

My husband and I were looking for a new house. We had visited one property but there were lots of problems with it. We went to a second house but unfortunately the landlord himself showed us around instead of an estate agent. This house was even worse than the first but he kept trying to persuade us. We even had to go back for a second viewing as he promised to make changes. As we stepped on the carpet (which was made of grass) it felt wet because he had just cleaned it. Outside, however, there were large lumps of bird poo all over the patio. Although I felt my husband was too fussy about the houses, the sight of the poo decided me that this was not the right place for us.  We drove away in a large double storey lorry. My husband wasn’t used to driving it and drove too quickly. We entered the motorway and he didn’t notice that other vehicles were gathering to leave on the sliproad (all travelling on the right hand side of the road). There were a lot of transporters and I didn’t feel very safe. My husband had to veer out into the fast lane and travel faster than he should because he was inexperienced. When passed the slip road, I could see ahead that something else was happening. I told my husband to slow down even though we were in the fast lane. Then we saw a motorbike skid and crash into a car. The cyclist leg snapped off like a piece of lego. The driver of the car got out. He had long hair and no teeth. The cyclist was ranting at him. The driver was very sorry and I felt sorry for him. Lots of other drivers had stopped and were also criticising the long haired guy. I felt they were picking on him because he looked so dishevelled. A woman who also looked a little worn, got out of her car and hit the long haired driver with a stick. Then suddenly I could see her in a booth. She had make up on and a pink dress but still looked as though she had had a hard life. She was being filmed in the booth and was moving sexually. She then put her hand in her underwear.
