Text: I was at college with my tutor Viv. I was in a new classroom with lots of new students. Viv was at the front of the class arranging her papers. She gave little attention to the class and everyone else seemed busy and excited. I didn’t know if I was meant to be there but was nervous to ask. We hadn’t finished our course because of Covid and I didn’t know if this was a catch up lesson or something new. Eventually, I went to the front and asked Viv and she said it was new class.

I was a white female and I had been suffering with myeloma. I was probably in my late 20s. Myself and another woman (Asian, in her 20s) were setting up a new office. Our roles were administrative. Our boss (an Asian man in his 30s) was away for the day. The other woman assumed a dominant role over me and was planning on asserting her position with the boss when he returned but she was a little deceitful/disrespectful in the way she did this. I did not like her at all. At one point we could not get something to work and we had to press the button on a control. She pressed it many times with her nails which left indents. There was nothing else she could have done.  The next day the boss was at his desk and I was alone with him for many hours. He was very good looking and a nice man. I liked him a lot and felt bad for the approach the other woman intended to use with him. I knew that I should show him loyalty and not her and that in being honest he might like me even though she was apparently more superior to me. So I deliberately did not mention her when we discussed how the office had been set up the day before. It was clear that a romantic connection was developing between us and at one point when I had to get changed I did so in front of him. As the day progressed, he began to realise that the other woman had been deceitful in some of the things she had done. I didn't need to point it out, but I never defended her. But then at one point, he was cross about the control that had been damaged. At this point, I felt I should have defended her because this was just an accident but all I said was "Oh, it must have been damaged somehow" (ie, I didn't let him assume she was to blame but I did not defend her either). When she came back to the office, he challenged her about everything. She became really nasty when she realised that there was a romantic connection between myself and my boss and started being very personal including commenting on my health. Still, she was demoted and the romance between myself and my boss continued; I felt very excited.

I went into Marks and Spencer and up the escalator. going there but this time with a friend. We looked around but I knew there was nothing there that I wanted because I had already been there once. We took the stairs instead of a lift and then saw that we were in a very old stone building and had entered a half level staircase. It was damp and cold. We walked down the stairs as though we were trying to find our way out. As we got near the bottom, I told my friend I had lost a letter the last time. She said maybe I would find it now. But by this time, we were on the bottom level and up to our knees in water and so I dismissed the idea but said nothing because I didn’t want to spoil her enthusiasm.

I was in a school in which I used to teach and just walking through the corridor. I suddenly saw a member of staff and a child I recognised. The child was being difficult but I just stopped, called him by his name, and started talking to him which calmed him down. The assistant was surprised I knew the child and my respect for him.

sitting a maths exam in a large school. I had spoken with someone in depth about the exam before with a friend and they had been very confident. I thought the practice questions I had seen were OK. However, when the teacher came in and we all sat the test, the questions suddenly became very difficult. I sat looking at them blankly and not knowing how to start. I did one which seemed easy and didn’t really require any mathematical knowledge, but I felt I was probably missing something obvious because I lacked so much confidence in myself. I spent a long time just staring at the question even though I thought it was easy and so did not really make any progress onto other parts of the exam. Also, the question paper was just some folded paper and so I didn’t realise how many questions there were; I misjudged the timing and did not finish. I spoke with the teacher afterwards and it all seemed very serious. He told me to finish the questions at home. I was surprised and upset at my poor performance.

I was in my 20s and with a girl I knew from university. We were not friends but could have been with time. We were in her father’s living room which was small but very cosy with an open fire. I felt a little tense as though I knew them both but not very well. I thought he was good looking although he was a lot older than me  and wearing a cardigan. We were talking about finding a new place to live. I had lived in many places and had to keep moving. I said something about learning from all the moves that I should choose a property that could reflect my identity rather than for practical reasons. He challenged me and said I had once described myself as “regressive”. I came out with some long argument that my current view was not a contradiction with an earlier expression, somehow linking regression with identity. There was clearly some tension between us but it wasn’t clear if this was positive or negative. As we were talking, my friend left. Then something happened on the rug that needed my attention. I was on my knees and the man knelt next to me and physically close. Then his daughter returned, and it was clear something was going on between us so she left again. I sat up and leaned against him and it felt good.

An ex-colleague was telling me all the plans about how schools were going to keep children safe on their return next week. She described how the children had to line up. We also talked about another colleague/friend. She had a disease which made her vulnerable to Covid-19 and I was worried about her returning to school.

The two main characters were a very good looking male who was a bit of a rogue. Very fit, dark hair, stubble, dressed in black. The other character was a female (tall, slim, long dark straight hair) with two roles – one as a local girl, and one as a kind of superhero with the power to see into the future, although she doesn’t know the full extent of her powers at the beginning. The male hero has a relationship with both female roles but does not realise they are the same person until the end. He develops a romantic relationship with the local girl, but has some sexual tension with the hero female. He does not realise that he is escaping lots of dangers because the female is using her powers whilst in her local girl persona.  The male had escaped from a gaol and thought all was well. The female in her superhero role (and to her surprise) had, however, been imprisoned and put in a pit. She realise that for once she needed his help. The male suddenly noticed a flashing light and curiosity got the better of him so he followed it and it took him to the imprisoned female. Some guards came and restrained him. Then the pit turned into a large basin with a plug hole and started to fill with water. The female indicated to the male that they must swim down the plug hole. He pulled away from the guards and dived into the water. They went down the plug hole. Then a big plug came down and filled the plug hole but was then pulled out again. The two heroes held on tightly inside the giant plug and as it rose into the air, they managed to escape. At this point, the female told the male who she really was. As they rode away on a horse, she suddenly got another image of the future in her mind. This time it was clearer than the last, and it was an image of the two heroes getting married.

I remember I lived with a family. The first husband had an abusive father but they managed to leave him. Then the mother got a new husband but he was abusive as well. However, he challenged my role in the family. I had changed the mattress on the bed whilst he was away and this was a big deal. I was standing in a stream. Three girls, around the age of 14, passed me, walking on large stones. All had long brown hair that was tied back. The tallest one reflected on everything being a phase in life.

I was in the body of a younger woman (20s). I might have been Asian or Black because everyone else in the dream was non-White.  I was going to meet my boyfriend. I had two male friends with me. We travelled on the underground. We had not been at our destination long when my boyfriend turned up. He was heavily into drugs and street crime. Then a car turned up with two young men in it (20s). My boyfriend and these two men knew each other and I had a sense that there was conflict between them. They started shouting at him from the car and then pulled out a gun and started shooting. The four of us ran down into the train station but there were no trains running so we had to run back up the stairs. My friends ran down another flight to look for another train but my boyfriend dragged me off in another direction. We were soon safe and hiding in a housing estate with lots of apartment blocks around us. But there was still shooting and lots of young boys (14 year olds maybe) running in and out of the blocks threatening people. I tried knocking on someone's door but they were too frightened to help us.

In the dream, my husband and I decided to return to Oslo to live as we thought we would feel safer there than living in London. We were searching Oslo for dangers. I recall walking the streets and visiting the harbour.

I was an adult but living with my parents. a young boy who was probably my brother. started with them telling me that a letter had arrived that described how each year I had to go to China and look after someone for a week. It was a bit like jury service – I was obliged to do it and there was no warning. The instructions were on a long letter – several pages of typed light blue paper. I told my parents this was ridiculous. No one could expect me to drop everything and travel half way around the world and so it must be fake. Plus, who types letters on paper these days anyway. Still, we were worried about it especially as my parents didn’t want to get into trouble.  I was convinced it was something underhand. I monitored people who were watching my house at night. When someone official came to the house on other business, we asked him about the letter. I also imagined what it would be like in China and thought I would have sit still next to someone’s bed so that the people who looked in through the window thought I was caring. Someone was standing behind me, marking out the spaces I had wriggled into because I was uncomfortable on the low chair they had given me. I also imagined seeing a weird kind of animal that shed its skin and from within the skin came a caterpillar. a young friend wasn’t convinced the letter was a fake and wanted to try out part of the route in case it gave us a clue about how realistic a journey it might be. driving through parts of Norway.

I was working in a school. I felt I had to be there. One of the jobs I had to do was clean the kitchen fronts and I was very bad at it. I could sense my mother encouraging me to just try my best, she was not physically present. Another thing I had to do was keep a small group of children occupied as regular school had been suspended. I didn’t want to keep them occupied although I knew I could if I put the effort in. I created painting activities and directed other staff who were far more enthusiastic than me even though I was in charge. I felt guilty but bored. At this time we also had training about how to use medical equipment and that we must not touch it with bare skin.  Later, I got the courage to go driving. I had a very old car and soon discovered I hadn’t forgotten how to drive and I could go up hills. There was an obstruction in the road. I was suddenly on foot and walking through someone’s living room. I felt guilty and hoped they would not notice me. A middle class woman was sat on the floor with three young children and a cat. The children and cat saw me and I started to play with them. They liked me and so she didn’t mind me sneaking through her living room.  Then, when walking up the hill, on the way back to the school, I saw a young woman struggling with a young child. The child was having a tantrum and the woman was reacting to the emotions. I went over and took the child by the hand. I spoke soothingly but assertively and the child walked with me. The young woman was happy and felt I had taught her something.

An old school friend decided in the morning that later we were going to eat dinner together but it wasn’t a good day for me. The kitchen was chaotic and overrun with dirty dishes. Two of my children were cooking. The one was trying to cook a slab of beef in a saucepan with egg soup and wondered why the soup would not solidify. I was making my own lunch whilst I stood with him and trying to ignore the mess in the sink. We decided the beef needed to finish cooking before the egg would cook. I didn’t have the courage to ring my friend to cancel.
an apartment block, gunmen, and me trying to get into the building. I felt excited rather than scared.
involved sexual advances but were not quite what they seemed and there were confused feelings.

Text: dividing food into portions, by 'the usual' system of elongated diamonds and dashes.
There was a wooden bar, shaped with right angles at each end like a drawer handle, but body width size, it was a restraint for people having a mental health issue. Harry pointed it out to me
i had woken up, and noted the time
working out fingering for viola so that all the fourths are reachable. I think it's for an ensemble.

In the middle of some ongoing task required for work, kneeling down doing things at a notcieboard. The voice of the boss over the intercom says see if Lily is bringing to put on the noticeboard before we finish up. 'Lily' shakes her head, no, she isn't bringing it, she's bringing me sth else, i can put it on my noticeboard. I pin it on.

i was tryingout a study subject, in anthropology or similar. i didn't like the person running the class but it was too crowded to get into a different class. i wasn't serious anyway. the coordinator contacted me and said she cld get me into a class with the tutor of my choice next semestser, which is next year. i was surprised they were trying to look after me, and also surprised that they assumed i was serious about continuing the course. The class was going upstairs with one of the teachers, who was Uncle S.. He gave out rubber bands with the kind of plastic square on the end you get on packets of crackers etc. we were supposed to flick them at people. I understood, this was like one of those Mary Douglas exercises about what is taboo and why. I said i was going to save it and flick it at my brother but i saw George coming down the stairs, so i flicked it at him because i knew he would find it fun.
someone who was my wife. she was very small, very thin, with dark hair and a strained face.

an AfroAmerican woman and her son. He's about 8, sitting at a table and colouring with great concentration. She's standing behind him, opposite me. she's tall and slim, maybe 35, with classic 'Afro' hair, wearing a yellow blouse. He asks her something; she avoids answering clearly because it would have sexual reference and he's too young. She looks straight at me. I'm hot for her.
i was playing viola.

Ian was getting ready to go up in a monoplane as the single permitted guest passenger. The pilot in real life is a composer and academic who i studied with once. It wasn't a monoplane, it was bigger and more complex than that and covered in - possibly a zeppelin, with an engine? but anyway it was being called a monoplane. It had mayb 20 people in it but they were all part of the team in some way. Ian (like the others) had a full white suit on that covered body, hands and head, with a solid mask (like the suits used for working with hazardous chemicals) and had a large yellow working model helicopter taken apart to carry with him. This appeared to be compulsory. He and the pilot weren't wearing the headcovering and mask section yet but the rest of the team were. Ian was filling in a form to be able to go and wanted me to help with a couple of sections. I couldn't see to read the form and there wasn't really time, so i was telling him it was fine, he didn't need me. I was also telling a friend about it, who was there, and i that i had taken this trip myself once. I was saying Ian will be ok, he's been up in various planes often. I went over to the airfield with him, non-flying people weren't allowed very close so he had to go off with the pilot and team, turning around a bit anxious but excited to go. The guest passenger sits in a small bubble near the front of the plane with the pilot, everyone else sits in the back.

working for Vi. Vi is with a couple of grandchildren, and I catch a glimpse of her partner Richie, esp. his mane of long white hair. i have obtained a couple of classic books, one i forget, the 2nd is called Queen's rights by Frank Willoughby, which is about the labour movement. I'm aware that the title is misleading. We talk about the best second-hand bookshop in Australia, which will source anything you need quickly and easily. i travel to a university in Sydney for some sort of major gathering of social and historical significance. I am directed around campus and eventually find a huge quadrangle covered in lawn. There is a big market under tin roofs like Victoria market. I am directed to Shed 4, where this famous bookshop is. I am surprised that such an important bookshop is nothing but a stall in a market. I go to the stall, which is run by a couple of old men, and ask for the Willoughby book. The man serving locates it immediately. It is an old hardback, its cover is in very rough condition. My copy is better condition and has the title in big plain capitals on the cover. It is $12 - cheap. I buy it. I go to a place where they are serving food and two old women have cleared at a room and made up beds for me and my lover. There are 3 of different sizes all joined together. Everything is very old and basic but their care makes me feel special and looked after. The room is otherwise empty except for a noticeboard.

There was a group of 9-10 friends, with 4 key people that link three groups within that. i forgot 2 of the people - the other 2 are a friend i play in ensembles with and a long-lost friend. Both gay men but that doesn't appear significant.  We are trying to go into a full auditorium. not clear what it is - like a big church but not a church. We all want to sit together, because of the links between the 3 groups. We try to go in when there's clapping but sth doesn't work and they come out again. Some go out through the hinge side of the door. i'm surprised by this but i see from a woman ahead of me doing it that it's just wide enough when the door is open. Someone comes up being like an usher, trying to help us get in. I think that's the point when Kay joins us. She seems to be about 16.  We're outside at tables on grass, some of the group are different now. One of them is asking a question of everyone, repeatedly because Kay won't answer. She is fiddling with a big tray of tiny containers with tiny things in, like for a craft project. She has dropped it, the containers have scattered and one or more have broken. Stuff has fallen out under the table including some broken red&white striped rock candy cane. I think it's rude that she won't answer and prompt her. She says it (the tray of containers) was for a guest. I'm coaxing, I say it still can be, it doesn't matter if one is broken.  We're setting up to watch an iconic film. It's a musical. A young person in the group dresses up as one of the actors in white overalls with thin straps and a white sailor's hat. He's also dyed his hair and moustache. I laugh and clap and say all you need is to grow another foot. This is a joke i've been making about this person. He says Only an inch. We smile indulgently. Kay is, or before this was, painting hundreds of minute wooden flowers manufactured together on a rack, you can break the flowers off when they're done. The painting is extremely detailed - bearded iris, orchid etc.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: i was at some sort of meeting that i was central to, maybe i was the guest, people were asking me questions etc, but there was shit all over me, soft yellow smeary shit, and it was getting worse, not sure where it was coming from, maybe out through my pores??? i was trying to clean it off with a shirt or jacket but it was all over that too so i had to leave went back to where i was staying and got in the shower to try and clean up someone came in, there was something in place, sort of magical, set up to kill her within 4 hours. there was the image of a man in a mirror on the wall winking at her and being attractive and she was getting sucked in by this, not realising it was part of the system/bewitching? leading to her being killed i was warning her about this and we decided to try and subvert it so we got in a car and drove away through some unknown route, i was following some kind of directive which took us through grassy vegetation way higher than the car. Someone else was with us, possibly my younger daughter. My passenger got out of the car in the middle of this vegetated area. We left her, i tried to go back but i wouldn't have been able to find the way. So we went back to the meeting place and she was there - so we thought maybe we've succeeded, she's still alive, but maybe we got tricked and maybe the man who was going to kill her was there too and us bringing her here was part of the plan. When i was leaving someone went in through the security door before it closed. i was worried about this, it was potentially dangerous, so i was trying to find someone to phone who was a member (i wasn't). Took a while to find my phone. i thought i'd ring the leader of the group, or maybe my ex. There were a couple of other people in the car at one point.  someone was asking me about this meeting, i said it was monthly and anyone could go but i didn't really know about it - i gave them some vague information that i half knew about when what and where, then realised they could ring the council or the church where it was held, i could see a sign on the outside of the building, possibly Bendigo community centre?? Or they could also look in the local paper, it would be advertised.
i had got up. i filled in a form about a film or MIFF. a little paragraph, again featuring robert redford. Ian read it and was impressed because he said he had studied under robert redford.

i'm watching a film, a dramatised version of a historical discrimination case in which a man who is both gay and disabled is treated systematically so badly by his employer that he becomes injured and this gets worse and worse. The employer thinks he has no chance in the case because he is gay and because their child is more valuable. The man wins the case and is awarded damages of possibly $75,000,000. There is historical footage of the actual man and his partner. The film seems to be somehow about his partner not him. The man is in a wheelchair in the footage. By the fashions it may have been in the 60s or 70s.

A letter arrives and someone's memory is triggered of a long ago racist event against a Black girl. Two people, a man and a woman, are planning a way to thro her in a pool from a height in such a position that she woudl be injured. They are folding paper to work out where to throw her. They fold coloured paper in symmetrical shapes dividing it in 3 and in 6. At the time of the event i'm a horrified helpless onlooker, also a young girl. the injured person becomes the daughter of a friend of mine (Indigenous).
wetsuits and library

a man Keeping watch at the edge of the sea to prevent something happening, then him searching in this isolated place, bur something to do with colour as well it was very important. From time to time I seemed to become aware. Towards the end of the session the colour part centred on a balance between light pink and  light blue. It all ended with me seeing a small boat going along on the Thames in the distance.

I take a job  where im preventing something happening but its all very abstract, I think it is something like preventing people arriving somewhere but it is looks like charts, a big interactive chart on a table With symbols like little cylinders . Then the scene becomes real people, and they are holding the cylinders by wire handles. They glow red, and are lamps. I realise they are either refugees, or else climate activists. Either way I immediately swap sides to help them instead. We drive up into mountains, it looks like the lake district, and then climb up crags. I am on top of one and its all beautiful, colourful, with blue sky, the short grass and mossy smell, I want to stay but we have to go down. There is a woman just ahead of me carrying a baby.
We are living in London and I suggest instead of staying at home we could go to the cafe around the corner. I say we could take some biscuits and tea (!) . M agrees that would be a good idea.

swimming and rescuing , someone was trying and failing wearing a wetsuit. It goes on for a long time, then I had a wetsuit on. Then im in a small library looking for a specific small book, I find it but its an ancient brown volume and looks a bit mouldy and stained so I leave it. I see the  librarian is unpacking a big stack of brand new paperbacks , I realise they have been given a lot of money for a specific reason and bought them . I want to get some of them but a big crowd gathers around them so I don’t. At the entrance I find a man I know, he’s sitting putting on some shoes which he says he made. They are black and pointy, I say they are extremely tiny! But they fit him.

I am at my grandmothers house and about to have a bath. I put on a dressing gown but i dont bathe, i go and lay down on the rug in front of the fire , the light is off and I know there is someone in the bedroom, I don’t know who. I feel warm and comforted. I am in a sitting room, im looking at my big table which is used for dining on but also everything else. I realise I have ruined the surface sewing on it a lot, its all blackened and stained. I say to M do you think I could sand it and refinish it and then keep it covered up? Then I realise that was just a dream, unless i ordered two pairs and sent two left feet back. Then im lying down in that room reading a book, but I fall asleep. I wake up and see I’ve left the ironing board up, and three irons switched on . I then find myself going down the steps at the end of my terrace to catch a bus. At the bottom I try to put on sandals instead of my shoes, although theres snow on the ground. I find i have two righ foot sandals ,so give up and put the other shoe on. I want to take them back home but I see M running for the bus so I have to take them with me. At that point i realise I don’t have 2 pairs of those sandals , there cant be two right feet so this must be a dream.   Then im making dinner , cooking fish, but ive prepared too many vegetables , peas, carrots, allsorts, so there would be too much with potatoes.

a concept. Im in bed half asleep when I sense a large animal in the room, then a little boy in the next room ( he comes out of a film yesterday ) calls  out theres an animal in my room . I go in , he‘s afraid, and see an animal dash behind the wardrobe, I look behind but can’t find it.  Then someone is carrying a person outside, the person can’t breath properly, there is a wheezing sound. Im with them , we are at a zebra crossing when I see two young women. They are my friends ( also out of the film), I go to  them. There are two small girls at the crossing. M say to me, would you save those girls , or your two friends instead? I said what do you mean, as in a disaster?

I am in an isolated house in the countryside , there are other people there. The house is surrounded by soldiers, Nazis. I decide to escape and get help, and I must take the animals with me. a dog. I get out of the back but don’t have time to see about the animals, I go through a wood, and run and run, up hill and down dale . I see behind me the dog is running too, and I think, what shall I do for a lead? I think ,  I didn’t have any dream tonight so I’ll have nothing to report. But wait a minute, there was that Nazi dream, and I start going through it in my mind.

I was in a busy wholefood type of cafe, there were several toilet rooms and I was trying to find one with no one in it, I felt a little uneasy, as if I had something to hide. I give up and im in the cafe room, I’m thinking I’m wasting my life working somewhere like this,  but then looking at the faces of the other young peoples working there I realise I don’t think that about them, so why think it about me. I remember one womans face particular.

I am in an art gallery, it is a scruffy room a bit like one in an old art college building. A tall woman brings in a huge painting , its all done with heavy brushstrokes in deep rich colours, even the frame, and her dress, long and narrow has the same pattern as the painting all over. Then I see another painting , the same kind of colours but it is of someone wearing an intense green football jersey. Then I see a work that is a cabinet with flat cloth covered objects on it. I notice the artist belonging to that one is wearing the same fabric as one of the things.  I say to a woman about the artists matching their work , she tells someone what I said but gets it all wrong, and its too noisy for anyone to hear when I try to correct it.   I helped M with having a small exhibition at a scruffy art gallery shortly before lockdown

I was in some kind of Institution, a school I think,but then I went to sleep at my mothers house . My younger brothers are in bed in the other rooms and im in my mothers room (we are all young). My mother comes in and says she feels very ill, and coughs right in front of me. I realise it’s THE virus. I get out of bed so she can get in and i go and snuggle down somewhere else with the bedclothes over my head worried I caught it. Then I am back at the school . I walk around and teachers look at me, im very sleepy and not properly dressed , and am trying to find out the time which I find is 11. 0. I have overslept but I am no longer worried about having caught Covid .

Me and another young Japanese woman are travelling to school, sixth form, and we don’t want to. On the way we say, why are we going to school when we already left and been to college? We agree it’s wrong and that we will go to a cafe instead.

I’m in an industrial cityscape and it’s dark. There is someone standing in the shadows, but otherwise deserted. I’m walking down a rough road with gloomy warehouses on one side and wasteland on the other, bordered by a stone wall with gaps in it. Out of the gaps come a few feral dogs. I feel a bit frightened but act cool and ignore them, and they don’t attack. I go right to the end of the road which turns out to be a dead end. I walk back up the road and alongside me appears a dog, it has a rough wiry coat, a short tail and about 24” - 30” tall, but the horrible and abnormal thing about it is, its body is about 6 feet long.
swopped identities, worrying about whether I will like the fabric I’ve ordered
My and my middle brother were racing around the old cricket field at Spen Victoria. Every time I overtook him he pulled back. I knew he was going to beat me because my legs were moving really slowly.

I was travelling to various destinations in Europe, always in hiding. Someone or something was hunting me down. I was scared. I eventually found an estate agents in a small town near the coast in Italy. They let me sleep in the upstairs restaurant. At night I stared at the stars. When I closed my eyes I could see what was trying to find me, but I couldn't describe it or put a name to it.

One of my ex-girlfriends got in touch to say she'd been to Spain and seen Maria, the wife of my late friend Terry. We then got a lot of friends together to talk about it but it took place in the back of a van. The van was then a hospital waiting room and all the people were therapists. I asked them if they were therapists for animals. They said no, just people. I then said that it was probably easier to tell if dogs were unhappy because you could read their expressions, whereas cats gave nothing away. The therapists laughed. Then I saw our old dog was curled up in a corner looking sick.

I was on holiday with various members of my family and numerous other people, seemingly all staying in a big house together. A man was making a meal for us all - I could see he was cooking loads of pasties and Findus crispy pancakes in the oven, along with various other things. I saw that he was grilling something but was resting the hot grill pan on one of my pillow cases whilst cooking. I shouted at him, how dare he use my pillowcase to cook something hot on. At some point I had opened windows in various rooms, but then there was a thunderstorm which became a hail storm with massive pieces of hail, so I had to go and shut all the windows. It was the last night of holiday and we were planning to go out. My nan said she wanted to go to the pub, where there was live music or karaoke, so she could sing along. I think she had already got dressed up. I was surprised because my nan had dementia and rarely even talked, and hadn't dressed up for years, but I thought she might enjoy it, and that I might also take my aunt.  Later I was in a theatre awaiting the start of a show. I was there with my mum, my sister and someone else. I had arrived at the theatre on a bus. I was with someone on the bus. We had to get the bus one way past the theatre, then wait for it to come back the other way; I wondered whether it would still be the same driver and whether he'd notice we'd just got off the bus in the other direction. When we got to the theatre we had to ring the bus bell at exactly the right time, then the bus stopped immediately; it stopped in an exact place between 2 of the huge letters outside the theatre that spelled the name of the production. Inside the theatre foyer there was a big U shape of red comfortable seats; the walls were black. We had a long time to wait before the show. I ordered something from the person serving - they said there was a good offer on 4 drinks, which I planned to get later - and asked for a programme. They said the programme was only 2 sides, it was just a piece of pink paper printed double-sided in black and white. On it there were very short, scathing reviews about all the previous plays that the actors had been in; I mentioned this to mum when I gave her the programme to read. At some point, Barbara was there and decided to show the foyer staff how she would perform the lead role - I think the play was My Fair Lady. She flounced dramatically up and down the foyer, explaining how she would have got the part and/or doing some lines from the play, and gave all the staff a flyer/resume about herself. For one of the staff, she produced and handed over a larger folder or book full of big photos of her in previous productions. I had intended to change my clothes once I arrived at the theatre but by the time all this had happened I didn't have time to change before the play started. I looked down and was wearing a long dress over some smart trousers, so looked ok but a bit odd. I asked my sister whether she still intended to change before the play.

I was, somewhere with lots of youngish people, possibly a gig. I met a young man and got talking to him. He was the sort of guy I would have fancied in my 20s, very skinny, dark hair  - sort of tousled and messy and sticking up a bit, cheeky face, I was aware at the time he was a bit young for me. I was wearing a t-shirt from a festival with a list of the bands that played. He was looking at it and knew all of the cool bands that were on there, including one called 'Gul' which I had never heard of It wasn't the cool bands that I had been to the festival to see and he must have guessed this, so he said he also liked the Stylistics, who were also listed on the t-shirt. I thought I was well in there with this guy but then he started to talk to another girl and arranged to meet her tomorrow. She went off somewhere while me and the guy went and sat down at a dining table, which seemed to be in his house. The other girl came over and I thought the guy was going to lie and say I was someone from work, and that I would leave if he did. We put some paperwork onto the table anyway to give that impression. However, he very honestly told the girl that he was seeing me today and her tomorrow, and they both seemed fine with that but I was less convinced, although I  thought that must be just what people do these days and I should go with it. During his conversation with her, I accidentally knocked over a glass of his homemade pink lemonade, which went all over the paperwork and I hurriedly tried to mop it up before he noticed. The guy came back alone. We had been playing a board game of some sort and I presumed we would continue with that. But he said he had only pretended to be playing, or had just set the board up randomly, so he put the game away. He obviously didn't want to waste time with board games. I moved to a rocking chair and he sat on my lap. We started kissing, which quickly became very passionate. With my arms around him I could feel how skinny he was. We continued and it got very exciting

I was with my friend Vanessa wandering around a town. We had various shopping bags with us. We randomly arrived at a ferry port and Vanessa suggested we should just get on a ferry and see where we ended up. We got onto a ferry with no idea of where it was going. We felt very excited and impulsive, although I was a bit anxious because I remembered that I hadn't changed my clothes since the previous day and I also hadn't cleaned my teeth. I looked in the shopping bags I had with me and saw there were some clothes I could put on, although they weren't clean either. We enjoyed the excitement of being on a ferry to an unknown destination and speculated about what country we might end up in. After a while the ferry pulled into a dock where it would be waiting for an hour and we got off to go home and pick up more stuff. Around this time we found out that the ferry was actually going to a lake in the UK, we looked up some information about it and it looked nice but obviously not as exciting as going to a different country. I went home to get some clean clothes etc then headed back to the ferry port to continue the journey. When we got back on the ferry, a woman with a child had taken over the area that we were sat in before and the child was setting up to take over the floor area to play in. I felt annoyed that someone with a child had presumed they were entitled to take over the best seating area on the ferry. I pointed this out to them and showed them where I had created a pretend lake and castle on the floor, to indicate that adults may also want to have a play area and they weren't just for kids.

An evil man was controlling a young woman and making her do things she didn't want to do. Not sure if I was the woman at some points, definitely most of the time I was watching her - she was blonde, perhaps looked a bit like Britney Spears. At one point the man made her lug around a load of really heavy stuff that was tied to her back, so that as she walked she was stooped over and could only move very slowly. All the time it was dark, late evening in a seedy cityscape. She lugged the stuff to outside a cinema or theatre. At this time my viewpoint changed to seeing the city and characters as if they were on a board game. To help the woman, I put 3 lengths of spring onion in various places outside the theatre as barriers (on my board game version) - from the woman's perspective these were big, like bollards. The woman lugged the stuff round into a different street, where there were several contortionists. One female contortionist was demonstrating a new technique to make yourself pretty much flat, possibly to fit inside a flat cardboard box. It involved kneeling on your own shoulder so that it became flat - it looked very painful. Other contortionists watched and tried this.  Later, I was part of a whole group of people lined up who had to do a physical task - I think to avoid something bad happening. There were about 20 of us - some of whom were my friends - lined up side-by-side. In front of each of us was allegedly a set of monkey bars and we needed to cross from one side to the other and back within a certain time. The bars were different for everyone and mine was not a set of bars at all, it was just one hand ring on a very short rope placed quite high up and a long way from me. I tried to figure out how I could get to the ring to swing off it - I would have to leap from where I was and hope to catch it - and how I was meant to go anywhere during the task with only a single ring that didn't swing anywhere. I asked a friend next to me to ask the people running it whether that was correct. They brought me a big paving slab up on its side and put it in front of the ring as if that should help me to do the task. I saw that my friend Suzie was preparing to do the task after me and was dressing up for it with lots of jewelled accessories. I went over and gave her a jewelled hairband to wear for the task.

I was at a train station with 3 other people. One of them was my manager (Jo), another possibly my sister, or a couple of friends. We were waiting either at Northampton station, or for a train to Northampton. We had luggage with us and it was a bit of a walk to the platform. When the train arrived, Jo had started speaking to someone and I was worried we were going to miss the train. Eventually all our group were ready to go to the train. We had to run and go via the ticket office. The person at the counter made me crawl through a low tunnel through the back of the ticket office to get to the platform. Jo was sitting next to me on the train and talking to the strangers opposite me about something to do with work that made me feel like I didn't fit in.

I was at a big party - I think a family party, although there were lots of people there I didn't know. I think my mum was hosting. There was a big room like a restaurant but I think it was my mum's house. There was a big long raised table in the middle then loads of other tables around the outside. All of the tables were laid very meticulously with fancy place settings, cutlery and very particularly-shaped matching wine glasses. I had to get another wine glass for myself for some reason and went to a big cupboard with loads of wine glasses in it, all different shapes, sizes and colours. There weren't any the same as the ones on all the tables so I picked up a yellow one that was a bit bigger. Some other people were also getting new/more wine glasses but they all picked a dainty little orange one so I thought I should do that too so I didn't look greedy.  Possibly in the corner of the same room/party, but possibly not, my friend Rach was running the wine bar. All the wines were French. Rach was finding a wine to go with the meal and asked someone how long it would take to get a particular wine ready. It would be too long a wait so she said "we'll go with les bananes" instead - I was horrified at the idea of a banana wine because I hate bananas. I saw some huge wine bottles in the bar area (probably 8x normal size) and at some point some posh teenagers came in who were staying in the vineyard. Later I was on holiday somewhere exotic, or at least somewhere novel. I was staying in a fairly rudimentary, possibly wooden, lodging with numerous other people, a mix of my friends and some strangers - possibly all sleeping in the same large room. everyone decided to get up at 2am to see the light at that time of day - it was either approaching dawn, or somewhere where it barely got dark. We all stood up and looked out of our lodging across to the village and could see the buildings silhouetted against a pale light - it was very pretty, although I was not impressed to be up so early. We all walked into the village to appreciate it some more. I then presumed everyone was going back to bed, which I wanted to do, but all my friends intended to stay up and out for the rest of the day now. I wanted to go back to the lodging as I wanted more sleep and wasn't properly dressed or with the stuff I needed for the day. I was wandering around trying to find transport back to the accommodation. At some point someone I was with started talking to a man who said he had found some transport back to wherever we were going. It was leaving in 3 days' time but would cost only £200; I was tempted to ask if I could share the transport with him, as it was very cheap, but it was leaving a day later than I needed to so wasn't ideal.

I was in a group of friends on a city street going past a grand building. We were being quite lively and talking loudly. A man came over and told us we needed to be quiet, as if the whole building was having an exam - he particularly said this to my friend Kate, who is generally pretty loud. As we got to the doors of the building, it became clear, ironically, that Kate actually worked in this building, which I think was a university or college. Kate took us into the building to show us where she worked. I spoke to some of her colleagues, including a young woman who was very nice and friendly. At some point she ended up wearing my shoulder bag, just before we had to leave.  We were outside what I think was the same building but there was a commotion going on. It was dark and people were crowded, moving along the street in a big mass and it was clear something dangerous was going on. We either saw or became aware that someone we knew called Jesper had been killed in the commotion - not sure if by someone else or an accident. I was at my drama group. I could hear the chair of our group, and his wife, keep telling people that they needed to ask me about things, even though I had resigned from my position of responsibility. I was annoyed that people were still being told to ask me about stuff. People were talking about who was doing all the roles in the play we were rehearsing and one of them was due to be Jesper. I said very bluntly 'but he won't be doing it because Jesper is dead isn't he'.

A group of us were creating some sort of escape room or adventure game. In this part we had to make a tunnel that someone could go through. I was standing at the top of some steps that went down into a darkish room. From the other side of the dark room, Amanda from my drama group appeared. She threw me a roll of black cloth with something like a big hula hoop attached to the end. When I opened up the hula hoop end in front of me, I could see that the cloth now formed a tunnel that went down the steps, through the dark room and I could see Amanda at the other end. I could feel fresh air on my face that was coming through the tunnel; I was surprised and pleased about this because I didn't think the tunnel would be so convincing. Amanda said to send someone through the tunnel and that they would be surprised to find themselves in Parliament Street at the end of it, with their bag mysteriously beside them. Someone started going through the tunnel; I think it was an actor from Casualty.

Two people (one of whom might be me) were investigating a woman who was behaving strangely. We/they kept encountering this woman at various points around a town. She was an older woman, intelligent-looking, perhaps with glasses and hair in a bun. I think she was well-known locally, possibly had been a person of influence or maybe a spy/secret agent; there was a reason why we/they were paying attention to her anyway. At various times, we noticed that she seemed to pause in the middle of something, as if frozen in time. We/they observed numerous instances of this - in the dream I watched these as if they were video clips of the woman. We/they thought that either she was freezing time, or travelling in time, or that some evil person/enemy was controlling her, or moving her through time. We/they decided to investigate and find out what was going on.

I was at my mum's house. I think I had been staying there over Christmas but I was leaving that day and had to get to the airport by 7.30pm for a flight. I needed to find a long blue holdall of mine that was at mum's with some Christmas presents in it - I needed to pack the rest of my stuff into this ready for my flight. There were lots of people at my mum's house, including my sister and possibly other people I know, and it was more like a big party combined with a shop, or an airport in fact - there were various areas with stands of stuff for sale, e.g. souvenirs, also artisan food and drink that you could sample. I asked my mum a couple of times where the blue holdall was but each time she told me, there was a lot of noise going on so I couldn't hear. Mum was totally different to how she is in real life, she was buzzing around the party chatting to people and getting irritated by me keep interrupting to ask her about the holdall. At one point she was sampling some red wine from one of the stands and passing it to me to try. It was getting anxious because it was closer to my flight time and I couldn't pack. At one point, my mum or someone else brought some food around - it had come from one of the stands or a cafe, there were very small rectangular boxes with mini meals in, more like a taster than an actual meal; one I had had some lovely but tiny bits of beef with some other stuff. I had been intending to drive to Nottingham before driving to the airport, but it got so late I decided to drive straight to the airport. I tried again to ask mum about the blue holdall but she got annoyed with me. I realised/remembered that I was pregnant, possibly with twins, and was actually going to the airport to give birth. I was puzzled because my belly wasn't any bigger than in real life but felt both excited and afraid by the prospect of having children. I said to my mum 'next time you see me I might have 2 babies!'

I was looking around a museum with an older couple who I didn't know well. Something reminded me of the Titanic museum in Belfast. I said to the man that he should definitely go to the Titanic museum and he said he had already been. We ordered a snack from the museum cafe but when mine came it was a huge plate of mac and cheese/cauliflower cheese), plus chips plus peas and more cheese sauce. It was delicious but then I noticed it was already 1800 and remembered that I was going out for a restaurant meal that evening, so I shouldn't be eating so much now. I remember thinking I would just style it out and pretend I fully intended to order such a large snack but would still manage to eat a full meal later; I was thinking about the smallest thing I could order at the restaurant without looking suspicious and having to admit I'd eaten too much beforehand. We went into the museum shop/bookshop - initially just a small room. Then it opened up into a bigger bookshop which I recognised as being the bookshop attached to a different, bigger part of the museum (or possibly a university) in a different part of town. I asked someone whether this was in fact the larger bookshop and how come it was attached to the smaller one in a different part of town - I found the geography puzzling but interesting. Later I was driving around the university looking for somewhere to park. All the parking was in courtyards surrounded by old university buildings. I found somewhere with lots of spaces free, but when I got close I realised the parking spaces were on a severe gradient (approx 25%) and I didn't dare park there.

I was going to a school reunion. I wasn't aware of any specific dress code or requirements. I arrived in a group of about 6 friends but most people had arrived ahead of us so we had to split up over several tables. This part of the reunion was in one of our old classrooms, as if we were recreating an actual class. After I had been there for a while, I realised that everyone else was wearing our school uniform and I felt I was the only person who wasn't. By coincidence I had chosen to wear a yellow checked shirt, which was similar to the blue checked shirt of our uniform. My old school friend Miranda delighted in making fun of me for not realising we were all meant to wear the uniform and suggested there were other things planned that I had failed to prepare for, e.g. that we were all going to have a class photo. At some point after that we had a karaoke session in the classroom. A few people I didn't recognise stood up to sing. I noticed that they weren't wearing the uniform either - they were wearing very bright shirts, perhaps African or Caribbean-style designs. They gave me an approving nod or other gesture for not wearing uniform so I felt less alone. A very small girl/woman also wanted to sing, and I recognised that she was Nicky from school, who had always been tiny and unfairly picked on when we were at school. Miranda or someone else showed me a timetable with all the things we were meant to be doing that day - there were various different groups of classmates indicated by 4-letter codes but I wasn't sure which one I was meant to be in. We visited a haunted house attraction. When I went in I recognised one of the people working there as a real ghost, apart from here he looked more normal and less scary, like a normal human, so I told him so.

I was at work. I kept wandering around the building. There were lots of people but I couldn't find anyone that I liked or that liked me. I seemed to be in everyone's way. At one point I managed to get myself stuck between people who were either getting plates, or passing plates between them - people were having to get plates out of somewhere and pass them to another person, and I seemed to be sandwiched between the 2 people making it very difficult for them to pass the plates but I was stuck and couldn't move. I carried on looking for someone I knew and at some point saw a colleague I knew from a long time ago - he looked like a cross between Sasha from Holby City and Dave; I was pleased to see him and went to chat to him whilst walking alongside him. He had gone up in the company since I last saw him and whilst walking with him I accidentally walked into the Board meeting he was going into. I got told off by a Board member and asked to leave. At some point after that I saw Helen. I trailed her around for a bit but she didn't say anything to me. When I left her, disheartened, I overheard her say to someone else "I wish she'd leave me alone!" I felt lonely and tired. I sat down at a cafe table and fell asleep with my head on the table. When I woke up, I looked at my phone to see something to cheer me up but my phone just kept playing videos of shower heads, which was very distressing - I felt even my phone was against me. I was about to leave when I saw my friend Anna, she had just been at or in a theatre show and dressed up glamorously - old-style Hollywood glamour. Anna insisted I went out for a drink with her and I felt cheered up at that prospect.

I was in a big house where I was staying with numerous family members, although only my sister was there with me currently. Evidently we'd all decided to take turns to cook and had each bought stuff to make a dinner one night. I had bought mini kievs and chips. For some reason I'd taken the mini kievs out of the freezer but then not cooked them straight away and had left them in the packet intending to cook them later. I could see in the packet that some of the filling had oozed out and they weren't looking too tempting. My sister told me in no uncertain terms that she would not eat them. I was angry at her criticism and I made a rude comment about my family (with a bad swear word). My sister gloated at me criticising the family, whereas she would never do that. She showed me a cupboard where she had bought about 20 jars of curry paste, presumably to make dinner when it was her turn. Later I was driving into town. I stopped at a T junction in the middle of town but it was very difficult to see if it was clear either left or right. I had to edge forward slowly and quite a long way to be able to see. Meanwhile there was someone in a black car over the road revving the engine as if they were getting bored and going to drive straight at me. When I turned right, there were pedestrians walking all over the road, who were out and about in town. I thought town didn't look very safe with all these people and felt a bit nervous. I arrived at a cafe and put my coat on a seat then went to order at the counter. I was first at the counter when I got there, but while I was looking at the menu, another woman came up next to me and got served ahead of me. Then more people kept arriving, queued behind the woman next to me and kept being served ahead of me. The servers were asking 'has anyone ordered cake' and everyone who had was served ahead of me because I hadn't pre-ordered and didn't want cake. The menu I was looking at had lots of interesting mini lunch options but then I saw that this menu was for "MM Club" members only, so I didn't know what stuff I could order. Eventually I got fed up of people being served ahead of me, said something about it angrily to the server and walked out. I found my friend Rach and she suggested we went to a different cafe/bar. At this point I was starting to feel a bit unwell - dizzy possibly. Rach took me to a bar that I thought I recognised in my dream. You had to go into at the bottom/lowest level of the bar and it suddenly opened out above you, a bit like a theatre with raked seats. I remember the paintwork was a very unappealing mid-brown colour. At some point Rach showed me a photo where someone had put lots of makeup on her, it was very glamorous but looked odd because it was a sort of Indian-style makeup look, e.g. a bit Bollywood, but Rach is white.

There was some sort of emergency/crisis going on. I was in a large building and everyone had to pack up their belongings and leave, seemingly permanently. I had just come back from somewhere else and already had some stuff packed into a large wheeled suitcase, but I noticed I still had lots of other belongings unpacked, including some birthday presents, so packed some more bags, overflowing with stuff, as quickly as I could. One bag was an open shopping bag full of books; a random man said he was offended by my books because he was Jewish and tried to spill them or get me to leave them. Once I'd gathered my stuff I went to queue at a lift with other people to get out of the building; we were pleased that this lift was not as busy as others in the building. I looked over the edge of the lift - it was an open lift and it was a very long way down, it looked like you could fall out of it and possibly some people were. I got in the lift, when it got to the bottom it started travelling horizontally, more like a bus or train, taking us away from wherever we'd been. I stayed on the lift/bus until it stopped, which was sooner than intended. I got out into a strange town with a friend, who at this point looked like Jenny. We walked through the town trying to look inconspicuous, everywhere there were people looking dispossessed or threatening, it was very apocalyptic. I thought we were being followed by someone who wanted to hurt us but realised it was a local beggar, who was either lame and/or blind. My friend found a local monument, a big brown stone monument that had a fountain and a pool and I recognised it from a holiday guide as the highlight of this town. But now it was full of dirty water, with homeless people/refugees sleeping around it and bathing in it. I said to Jenny to get out of there. We made friends with the blind/lame beggar, although he couldn't really speak. I worked how to ask him, in simple language and gestures, where to go when you want to hide and we followed where he led. I had to run after him and jump onto a bus/coach as the doors were shutting. The coach driver said I could stay on the coach if i filled in a whole bunch of surveys, which I was happy to do. The beggar took us (via the coach) to an obscure cafe. The beggar was now magically female and possibly had turned into Jenny B, whereas Jenny B had turned into my friend Vanessa. I was following them into the cafe and looking for them. I passed some men who were talking about Dubrovnik but it quickly became apparent that they were on the lookout for newcomers/refugees to harass, so I moved on and found Jenny B and Vanessa at a table. Jenny B had got us all food - one plate was breakfast, with eggs etc, another was something else - she'd also got us 2 bottles of wine.
A consignment of vegetables was delivered to my house - by truck I think. Mostly root veg. Then appeared some delicious veg soup.
I was acting in an Italian film, while simultaneously watching this film - it was in black and white, with English subtitles. there were the usual chic types looking cool.
I was at my college in Cambridge where I was a graduate student. I had to deposit some clothes in a dry cleaning service. Then I was picking it up, and my graduate academic gown was missing...

I was teaching a literature class to a group of young adults. The book being studied was set in world war II: Germans were occupying Czechoslovakia. The class was interrupted several times by untimely events. At one point we all broke out into another room, I'm not sure why. I asked the group what they thought of the writer's depiction of the Czechs and Germans. Before they could answer a young woman came into the room holding a new baby and with a toddler, a little girl of about two, beside her. One of the female students said that this was her sister and her new baby. I said hello to the new arrival and greeted the baby. The toddler said she'd been weighed the previous day. I asked her what she weighed. 'A Roman number,' she replied. A male student, I noticed, had a nasty swelling and bruising on the side of his face - his cheek. He said his mother had made him come to class and had given him some soothing liquid to put on it when it hurt. He did this then, and I was surprised at the way he doused his face.

I was vacuuming the bedroom, as the floor looked dirty. The usual attachment with the broad head for vacuuming carpets wasn't there, so I had to use the small one with a brush, usually for smaller areas. This made the cleaning process painfully slow. After a few moments the cleaner stopped sucking, and starting blowing air out. I looked everywhere on the machine for a button to reverse the air flow, but without success. I turned the machine upside down, and found it clogged with fluff - that was why it wasn't working. Initially I was using the present cleaner, a cylinder with hose and attachments; when I found the fluff, it was an older style upright vacuum cleaner which sucks in dirt from underneath.

Paris Hilton was running for office. She kept pulling her top down to reveal one naked breast like that Italian ex-porn star politician from years ago. 2. The dream had a recurring music sound track that heavily featured the song, "One Night in Bangok"
I was travelling on a boat to Indonesia, and that I was focused on reaching a certain set of island - there were some other people on the boat, and I was particularly close to one of the men on board
adventure quest, I was very focused.

Couple walking away from me hand in hand. She had blonde hair, he had brown. I didn't recognize them. They turned and walked past me. It was all in silence. Walking my dog on the lead in a field that I normally walk up and a woman comments on the dog. I replied, "If I let him off the lead he won't come back until the next Apollo."  I was driving along a road, near where I was brought up, towards Prenton during a howling gale, where debris was being blown across the road. The sky was dark with clouds. I drove up to a house, which I think was my cousin's old house, and there was a builder outside. I spoke to him. I walked into the house and an old woman with blond curly hair was sitting in an armchair. I felt that she was my dead auntie though she looked nothing like her. She showed me a conservatory that she had had built which I looked through the glass doors at and saw that it was very narrow.

I was on some kind of quest to save somebody, and most of the dream occurred whilst travelling along a river. It was very sunny and beautiful, and along the way I did something that meant that I acquired a young, early teen female sidekick who was able to fill me in on things that I did not understand.

I own this cute leather handbag that is like a cat's face. In my dream I was carrying this with me, and I kept getting admiring glances, and people stopping me and telling me how much they loved my handbag!

I was doing a lot of searching for something. I was in a place set up somewhat like the University of Queensland St Lucia Campus, but it was not a Uni but a museum of sorts, with different buildings covering different eras. My state of mind was perplexed - there was some mystery that I was trying to solve, and I was constantly on the move.  I was joined by S. She was somewhat of a sidekick in my searching. This search had narrowed down to finding some missing fossils, and we were moving from building to building. At each building she would have another alcoholic drink - a different kind at each building.  We entered one building and she passed by a tall man who she knew from the past. At the last minute she said hello. We came to another building, the inside of which resembled an old building I am familiar with at the Uni of Melb, This is a two-story, labyrinthic building. It was full of boxes, and being emptied out/packed up. By now, S had a large tumbler of beer in her hand.  Someone came up to her and asked her if she was drunk - and I realised that she was.

I am still on some kind of quest, and still travelling along a river system. I still have the young female sidekick I acquired the night before.  There seemed to be a lot of rules, that I was unaware of, but that my sidekick could negotiate for me.  At the end, she and I were in a large wooden cabin by the side of the river, and the sun was going down. There was a fire to the far left of the cabin. It was quite dark, but it was not gloomy. She handed me a token, which was the currency for the region that we were currently in - it was a small wooden guitar and it was mostly yellow and green in colour.  I was quite happy that this token was something I had an affinity for - guitars and wood. My sidekick and I sat down to plan the following day.

I was in and around water, and was spending time on a small island. I had a raft that had been made by someone else. my physical positioning was below that of other people. Most of the time I was thinking about things that had happened in my life (a little) and about things that were happening to other people (a lot).  A man unknown to me commented on how nice my perfume was, and called it Blue Rose. My recent ex was there and also commented on the perfume. He was perfectly fine and not in any way mean or snide. I looked down, and saw some boxes and he told me that he was packing my stuff up. most of the time I felt content and placid, and occasionally curious.

I was on a roadtrip (in my home state), and I was alone for most of the dream, occasionally interacting with others, but not in a meaningful way as far as I can recall. The only thing that stands out is that I was doing this for the purpose of protecting a 'secret friend.' I did know that there was nothing bad going on, and also that I did not actually know who this secret friend was, but that what I was doing was worthwhile and necessary, and that if I helped them, than a lot of other people would be better off.

There were some hangover narrative elements - I was still travelling with purpose, and had special powers - I knew that I had them, but did not think about them or use them, and no-one else knew about them. I was sitting on the floor in a living room; Seated on the couch, and looking down on me was my recent ex-partner (M) and one of his 13 yr old twin girls (G).   M and G were talking about a visit that they had just finished with the rest of their family, and how they had shared the fact that M and I had broken up with them. There was a strange energy about them. I asked directly if they had said bad things about me, and they looked at each other in a funny way, and I knew that they had even though they attempted to minimise it. I felt a little bit sad, but did not have to struggle to let it go - something I consciously told myself).  M and the twins, G and H, and I all went to a venue that night. It was a long hall type building, and had an upstairs room as well, where bands played. I used to play in a band, and it was very much the kind of vibe that used to exist in the 1990s in Australia. I walked in well ahead of M, G and H, and immediately sas J - another ex partner with whom I had a long and sometimes emotionally draining relationship with. He looked like he used to look - and he was arguing with someone. The room was very dark and he could not see me. Almost immediately upon my seeing him, he finished his argument, spun on his heel, and stormed off in my direction. We came face to face and he looked very shocked to see me.  When I had first seen him, I thought, "Good. It has been a long time, and we were very close once, and great friends, so this is a chance to clear the air." We just stared at each other for a moment, and I smiled and he walked away and went upstairs to where the band was playing. I thought, "Oh well, that is a shame," but did not feel particularly upset. thinking that he should not be surprised to see me, since we had both ended up in the same city, and the bands playing were faves of both of us.  I went outside, where inexplicably it was daylight and a rural setting (the band venue was in the inner-city), and sat in a garden talking to a lady who was well known for her wisdom. Here also, I sat on the ground while the other people there were seated on chairs and looking down on me. There were a lot of flowers and it was very beautiful. I was surprised to see that there was a black cat standing upright in a small stone alcove next to the chair of the wise woman. I was not paying attention to what anyone was saying, and was focused on the cat.

My brother and Peter and I are waiting for my Dad, and feeling very bored.  I have to go to the toilet, and pee standing up, and am able to direct the flow like a man could - my Dad catches me doing that and rolled his eyes. There was a place called Fordian. I was back at my old house in Melbourne. I was on the road, and looking up at the balcony of the house. My brother P was there, along with my cousin N, and with them was a small male toddler. He had a massive rock and threw it down on the road, and it smashed into the person I was standing next to - I tried to warn them, but it was too late. I walked down the end of the street to talk to my old neighbour - the house where I had lived had moved to the bottom of the hill. When I got there, my neighbour was not there. There was a couple in their 40's and they were standing in the ruins of the house - it had burnt down. I explained that I used to live in the house next door, and pointed up to it - it looked beautiful, and I felt sad that I had left Melbourne. I also noticed that the couple were very resentful of me.

I was on a quest of some sort. for the majority of the dream, I was exhilarated and focused.  Then, just as things seemed to be heading towards a thrilling climax of some kind, I was waylaid by having to teach a bunch of international uni students (mostly from China). They were seated in about three rows that went a long way back in a hall-like wooden room - it was in another country (where I had previously been adventuring). at the conclusion of the lesson I had put up a sequence of physical props to make my point, including a green dress. Then an older man was in the room - he was trying to take over the lesson and was very annoying. He was telling them incorrect information, and I had to step in and reiterate the major points.  I was to the left hand side of a weird room - somewhat like a caravan. There was another woman in the room to my right, and some mirrors were placed around the room. The man who had been in the classroom was very condescending and sexist. He went to take a shower, and I could see him (naked) in one of the mirrors, and thought it was gross.  Then, I was talking to my Dad. I had sniffles, and a sore throat and felt very tired. I thought that maybe I should go and get tested for Covid-19, and I told my Dad that. He pooh-poohed the idea, and said that I was being melodramatic. I told him about my symptoms, and that the advice was that I should get tested. He again dismissed the idea - I realised that it was because he did not want to take responsibility for taking me to get tested, because it would upset the plans that he had for the day.
One of my clients at work took their work away from us. I was desperately trying to see if I could get another client but couldn't.

very determined and capable and I got a lot done. I went out of character briefly to worry that someone had forgotten my phone number. set in the present. I organised a lot of worried people and allayed their fears.

I was going to see a beach house I thought I might buy, but it was a very "hands on" look. There were no other people and I got changed into my bathers there, so maybe I was actually holidaying there. The approach was gorgeous, down a sandy track with tee trees on both sides. The house was small, a nice kitchen, a nice bedroom upstairs with views of the beach and a lounge room that had a moat in it. I thought "well that looks good now, but if I buy this place, that will have to be covered up during winter" Although it was small there were two sort of "lean-to" rooms which I was happy to see bc. it meant that the council would allow me to build rooms there as it would be in the existing footprint. I walked down the track to see what sort of a beach it was. It was quite a boring little "lagoon", and not too pretty but you could swim across the lagoon and there was quite a rough beach. I decided to swim to that and catch some waves. I went and thought "oh, I wonder if I am too old to swim in waves like this?" but I did. I caught a big wave in, a girl came and helped me back to the shallows she said "what are you doing swimming in this area? You don;t even have your Level 1, do you?" I said "Yes I do!" although I knew I was lying. For some reason I couldn't be cross with her bc. her heart was in the right place trying to assist me.

I was sitting in a meeting. All of the participants were lined up in single desks and there was a facilitator in front of us. The participants' desks were in water. We sat up to about our waists in water and the facilitator was raised above us on the edge of the pool. It was an interview session about people's voting patterns. There was quite some discussion and somehow the group came to the conclusion that only "high-vis" workers came to these sorts of things because they were the only ones that had the time and that as they were highly unionised then they were more likely to vote for labour and hence all opinion polls were skewed strongly towards labour and the liberals were probably  a lot more popular than the data showed. It was then time for all particpants to leave, we all walked to the front of the pool and climbed out. We were dry when we got out. I was happy to see a an old friend of mine, A, there and also a colleague, S. We walked together to where we were going to have some refreshments before leaving. We left the pool building and walked past a building that looked strange, somehow we knew it was a detention facility.  We went into another building that held the refreshments. They were absolutely awful. There was no vegetarian. The attendant pointed out something that was vegetarian but when I ate it, it was meat. It tasted DISGUSTING and I had to spit it out.  Also, we realised that somehow we had been transported somewhere without our knowledge, to another country. We were dependent upon the orgnaisers of the session to get back. We didn't have our passports so we needed them to help us get to Australia.  Everything was old and dilapidated.  The bus was awful and the city we drove through was really run down. We realised we were in Spain We realised we would have to fly back to Australia. A said "don;t worry, I will get us upgraded with my club membership, you can be my guest" I was somewhat relieved, but I felt bad that S would be left behind. However, when we got there it was a charter flight and there was NO Qantas Club, no business class or equivalent.  I was suddenly worried that my family would be worried if I was late home for dinner so I wanted to call them. I had a moment's panic because I didn't know mum or dad's mobile numbers off by heart, but then I realised I remembered their land line number. As I looked for a phone, I saw dad in the boarding lounge. He was calling mum to advise he would be late home for dinner, I was asking him to tell her that I'd be late too, but somehow he couldn't follow what I was saying.  We arrived back in Melbourne. A. was absolutely furious about the whole affair and decided to take a leave of absence form her job. She arranged for a very high profile lawyer (who was also a famous actor) to take her place. IN my dream we both worked at Goldman Sachs. I was telling mum about it and she laughed, she said "oh that X will shake them up alright! Isn't A marvellous having the spunk to shake them up like that?"

my sister "found" a person. Initially we thought the person was "Barry C----" and this person was a missing Essendon (AFL) player.  My sister (P) and M and N were very pleased that my sister had "found" barry. However, when I spoke to "Barry" I relaised that he wasn't Barry really. he quite happily admitted he wasn;t barry but he wouldn't tell me his real name. When I raised this with M, N and P they weren't too concerned at all. which I found confusing and there was a feeling of frustration and consternation.  I needed to be "found" by ME. To be found I had to go to a jungle and we were both blue - like the beings in the film Avitar.
travelling in the countryside by train with my friend Jane and encountering a group of people with strict and eccentric religious views

I was travelling by train along the line from Charing Cross to London Bridge, which I always love because of its views of London and its Victorian atmosphere. There was complicated trackwork and the the lines going off to Blackfriars and Cannon Street. I was being told about the benefits of Artificial Intelligence with thee possibility of being in two places at once, or in one place and not there at the same time.
