I was in a kind of restaurant with bookshop and musical venue in Clapton, serving rich and aromatic Balkan stews. It was run by very talented and creative people, who were also friendly. They were not famous, but there was a long review of them in The Times from the 1980s. It was a warm and colourful and lively place.

I was in a small town in Germany. I was visiting a museum or old castle, but by the time I came out in was pitch dark and I couldn't find mat way about. I was by a riverbank in the darkness, feeling my way along with hands and feet and in danger of falling in. A local inhabitant appeared and helped me, taking me kinfdy by the hand. We walked through the darkness together, and we passed, on the other side of the river, a large and beautiful Gothic church still enveloped in darkness.  We reached the lights of the town and a bright little souvenir shop. I thought my rescuer was encouraging me to buy, but he bought me a small souvenir of the town, and then took me to the bus station, put me on the bus to Munich, and waved goodbye.
I was leaving my job of over 30 years ago in Vienna and was experiencing anxiety over this separation, and travelling to work by tram but the transport was disrupted and I couldn't get there.

I was taking a university exam, but writing very slowly, and I wasn't pleased with my answers. What I wrote was brief and inadequate. Also I couldn't find any blank sheets of paper, and I was going round asking for blank sheets, but in vain. What I wrote was eventually just enough to pass.
I was in the town of Glastonbury, and a vast historical pageant was being organised. There was a lot of marshalling of crowds, noise and hubbub, and worry whether it would all go well, but it did.

the former Yugoslavia, where I worked many years ago. I was trying to find my way home in a city, with complicated concrete housing estates of apartment blocks that I was getting lost in, sometimes clambering over dangerous concrete blocks, and many streets deserted, but some full of lively markets.  I didn't reach home.

I had just back at an old job of thirty years ago, in which I translated media material about the wars in the Balkans. I was about to leave the job, and felt a pang of guilt at somehow deserting the cause. Then I revisited the office after leaving and saw my colleagues working hard and in a dedicated fashion and I felt regret, as if I had abandoned them, and I missed the work. I didn't feel emotions of this kind at the time.

I dreamed of Russia. The country was ugly and threatening, with dark and sinister nineteenth century people, and a general sense of people being obstructive and unpleasant. But my guide was an old school friend, my first love, who has no connection with Russia. He was showing me round a bit.

Scenes replaying from programmes I watched in the evening, literally just as though I had my laptop open to view them again. Between scenes names of people to contact or lists of work issues occasionally interjected but would go when the next scene started.

I am watching fireworks then realised that they are colours you see behind your eyelids when your eyes are closed. I open my eyes and I am underwater, gazing upwards towards the surface of a gentle river, on a summer day with trees bent over it. The water is deliciously cool and the play of sunlight on the water is indescribably beautiful. I can clearly hear happy voices playing in the stream, and I just drift there, listening and looking.

I’m in a large room full of jumble - walls, floor, ceiling are wooden and it’s backlit by natural light although there’s boxes and school chairs obscuring the light source (probably a window) from me. Architecture is Victorian era, colonial style, potentially a school or church hall from when I was growing up but not one I recognised as such. Someone offstage, who I know to be Diego from The Umbrella Academy that I need to find/clarify/decide something - this is very specific. I  am then outside the building with it behind my back and although the building appears large and in an urban setting on the inside I am now standing on what appears to be a Hebridean island in summer evening light. It is not what I am expecting but feel quite calm about it.

I am walking at night across an old, wooden railway bridge, across a narrow but deep gorge, with my team. We are all dressed in black and are silent as we move. We have a handwritten note from a team member saying they are leaving, and we are trying to find them.

the situation I am in is playing out in a glitchy way, as though two or three old-fashioned super 8 films are overlapping each other, although this is does not feel unusual. What I can see looks archival and autumnal, a boulevard or park with heavy old trees, but there is no sensation of cold or wind, which does feel odd.   I'm approached by a woman in a trench coat, who asks why I'm there and what I'm hoping to change. She's says that I can't help them and I turn around to see an institution I know to be full of people. It looks similar in style to the Lincoln memorial and has the word "spanakopita" engraved across the front.  I turn back and the setting has changed slightly - trees have shifted a little, light is different. The first woman is gone and a second approaches, same hairstyle but darker hair and different trench coat. She asks me why I think I'm there, and tells me that I can't change anything. I turn around again and see the institution which this time is much smaller and looks like the type of grecian temple folly you get in georgian formal gardens. I know that it still has as many souls in it as before.  There's a clicking like an old film ending.

Just impressions piling on top of each other like photographs or short gifs: walking through an office building, it has showers and an common room, it’s actually a residence; it’s in wide spring meadows with Frisian cows and bright yellow buttercups; back inside everything is monotone. I am very familiar with it, I might be going home. Someone in a lounge tells me to check my phone and there is also a message written on a page torn from a spiral bound book. I have to ring my new boss, Ayesha, who was expecting me to call earlier. I am slightly puzzled and slightly irritated by this. I am in my room which might be my office or my dorm, there are lots of books on the walls and it is long and narrow. Another message arrives on my phone, chasing me, it seems strange that my boss is so insistent in knowing where I am and what I’ doing so I ignore it and collect my things to go for a shower.

I am at work but not in my usual office - my desk is like a cashiers office in an old bank, with dark wood, a glass screen with foil lettering, brass, piles of paper. I'm aware that this is not normal.  Each time I look up, a different applicant is there, and they are all from one family, the Hargreeves from the Umbrella Academy Netflix series. Each one pleads their case, but there is an issue with all of them. I am getting frustrated as I have explained this to all of them before.   At a certain point I look up and the light has changed, it's the next day. The same applicants come to the counter, but as I can hear from the news playing in the background, there has been a change to the rules and we are now able to accept them.

I’m walking up to the spot where I left extra water and provisions after several days walking and camping in a national park. I’m not tired or seem to be carrying anything. The ground and outcrop I’m on are red dirt and dusty like the outback or desert Mesa, but the trees are European alpines and are tall, slim and give almost canopy cover. This seems strange as though it has changed since I was last here.   I’m collecting my things together when Gough Whitlam approaches with a small entourage and chats amicably, asking if I have enough water. I’m cautious replying as one of the two 5 litre bottles I have stached has been opened and half is gone. There is no sensation of heat but I have been very, very hot in the past few days.   The minibus arrives to collect me and I get my things.   We stop off at an underground, literally, printers. It is in a long, low tunnel with stacks and stacks of revolutionary posters crowding the sides and printing machinery partially blocking the way. Looking more closely at the posters they are actually glossy commercial prints for a mishmash of things, which disappoints me.   Pushing past the machinery as staircase takes us down into a gigantic cavern that is avast reading room, brightly lit and with tables, chairs and thousands of books.

The impression of numbers (serial numbers, phone numbers) and names (of things rather than people eg boats, types of bread, animal species) being projected in front of me as I walk, obscuring my view. Some are handwritten in blue copperplate, some typeset, some digital, some scrolling. They are in blues, greens, browns and dark reds. There is no obvious link between them and this irritates me.

We are investigating a case an Diaz is leading. I am not a detective but an observer to see how the team works. At all times I am at the centre of the action to be investigated so I know exactly what happens but am often not with the team. I do not tell them what I know because I am simply observing and it doesn’t seem relevant. At different times I see Lara Palmer’s boyfriend heading out his family house - a 1920s New Zealand villa - in the evening and roaming quiet suburban streets with his friends then waking up soaked in beer before heading sheepishly home. Another time I see a youngish woman, probably a uni student but dressed like a pensioner in loose jeans, roll neck and hand knitted jersey, grabbed by a man in clean work overalls and forced to march to a traffic island cover in trees. He throws her to the ground to attack her - it is clear that rape is intended by there is no sense of urgency or concern - and she produces a piece of baling twine and tells him to do it properly, clearing meaning him to strangle her. He is horrified although I never see his face. The last scene is a gigantic, corrugated iron building on fire and people fleeing, with Diaz and her team helping them to escape and trying to find the source. It seems likely that it was caused by a door-release mechanism that has been broken in the entrance to the mill, although I know that this device was broken by another detective earlier for other reasons.
Thought an intruder had left a big dead mammal in our bedroom like a wombat or something.

I was getting ready to go to a big festival, like Glastonbury. We were taking a dodgy limo to a weird scruffy hotel to stay in the night before. Time jumped forward and we were at the festival, there were a lot of boys there I went to secondary school with and haven't seen in years. One of them somehow had a pair of my pants that were clean but a bit stained from being old, he commented on that and I was humiliated and told him off.  Suddenly back at the strange hotel the night before the festival, I have packed my stuff and get in a huge comfy car ready to go, waiting for the others. Someone's mum is driving us? I am watching a friend, Sarah's, instagram story. She has lots of freckles all over her face.

There's an island, big house on it. Someone wrote a book about a shark attack. There is a group of attractive girls, we are going to have a sleepover on in the big house on the island and strip. We are swimming around the island. They are going to build a football stadium on the island and bridges from the mainland so the stadium on the mainland can be moved. My partner was there somewhere and someone was punching him. My brother was there?

In a house with my parents and my brother (Tom). I realise that Tom's wife Abby has given birth to their baby, a boy named Kai. I didn't know the name and they are keeping him from us. I find a huge photography book (at least A1 size) with photos of the baby as a newborn and as I turn the pages they get creased and some rip and I am unable to stop causing the damage. My mum tells me Abby will be angry and blame us, just another thing to strain our relationship. We are on eggshells. In the same photo album there are pictures of the actress Kim Raver getting married, my mum features in the photos as the witness/signatory.

I am trying to vacuum a room where a family (2 parents and 3 children) had all been living together. There is no furniture, multiple overlaying strips of carpet that are filthy with dust, debris, crumbs etc. I'm hoovering for what feels like a long time but it's barely making a difference. The family has moved out. Later in the same building, I've been staying there on holiday with my partner, his older sister and his parents. I think we are all packed to leave and then discover my partner and my clothes are all still in a drawer unit, someone comments they won't fit in our bag which I can see on the floor is already full, I start panicking.

I was at someone's house, they had a double garage with a skylight over one of the cars that they showed me. I went to a woman's bedroom, I think she was my friend. In her bedroom she had two armchairs with cushions on that had ribbons tied on them in memory of her four dead siblings.  I was then at the fairground depicted at the start of the film the Notebook with actress Rachel McAdams. She was hanging from the ferris wheel like Ryan Gosling does in the actual film. I was aware she was acting, and I was there with her. Me and Mark were then the main characters in the film in the abandoned house stripping to have sex. Mark commented that even though we were doing it somewhere interesting we were doing it how we always do it, and I got annoyed and left. Big strips were peeling off one of my fingernails and the remaining nail was painful and tender.

I was at a summer camp type learning workshop. Deirdre is there, we sit in offices. My brother is there, both his adult self and him as a ten-year-old child. We watch a video of my brother's child self, he is getting in with a bad crowd of kids and is in trouble with security. The bad kids are racist and misogynistic. I get dressed in black jeans and boots to look more formal.

I was researching a large tree, it was an oak tree but produced conkers. There was a pearl hidden in one of the conkers, it was an old myth. I was opening up a particularly large conker to try to find the pearl.

I was coming back home and wanted to talk with the neighbours and rang their bell but I couldn’t hear it ring, then I noticed their front door was wide open. I wondered what had happened but didn’t go in to find out,  Then I was at home and we had a builder working on the living room. my partner David Was there and when I asked him what’s happening, he said well, the holder is working and he didn’t bother me even once with a question or a request, he is just doing his job.    I was talking with a woman, she bend down and I saw that she had a huge bold patch in the back of her head.

a man dressed in strange clothes, I think fairly futuristic as in a sci fi film, he was tinkering with something, like a wrench, screwing something but I could t very well see what exactly.  I thought to myself I must remember this dream so I can describe it later.

I was cleaning a toilet bowl and trying to scrape at the limescale at the bottom of it with a toilet brush. Some of the limescale came off but then I noticed the brush itself was dirty with excrement and was leaving streaks all over the bowl, it was impossible to clean with it.

My husband, a male friend and I volunteered to help out at a pub - setting tables, clearing, collecting bottles and litter. My role was to prepare tables by putting cutlery and napkins. The landlords were grateful and welcoming. They offered to come and pick us up the following days but my husband and I decided we would cycle through the night.  A young girl was bullied by three local girls (all school girls in uniform). The bullied girl was very strong and a bit of a tom boy (in the dream, I saw a video of her holding on to the back of a moving freight train with one hand and holding a flag with the other).  I saw several people running on the side of a mountain in reddish mud. Some pieces of mud fell and an anti personnel mine detonated. Someone shouted the others to be careful.

I was interpreting for a lovely group but then it was chaotic and I wasn't sure whether we were supposed to continue. My colleague told me to stop because the speaker was easy to understand but I thought it wasn't up to her to decide what the delegates could or could not understand and I said that I was being paid to interpret so I would continue.  I fell asleep as there was a break in the event. Some (African?) delegates went to a state-of-the-art IT room to do some work and I went for a stroll near some kind of park, where I was hoping to see D&E. On the way up to the park, I had to crawl at some point as the path was very narrow and bordered with water, which I was scared to fall into. I didn't see my friends but sent them a picture from my new phone. They didn't seem to receive my picture and didn't get back to me. I can back down from the park, saw a lovely dog on the way.  I then had to carry the mummified skull of one of the delegates, which had been decorated and surfaced with some shiny metal. I was very careful with it but it rolled over when  I put it down. Finally, I saw an old friend whom I haven't seen in years. She told me she had a disabled son, whom she left in a specialised institution. I told her I was surprised that she'd never mentioned it and when she said he was 30 I thought it didn't add up as she's about 35 in real life.

A friend and I were interviewing groups of people to select who we thought would be appropriate to rent out a house. At some point she and a man (who at tha point was intervieing with us) argued about the number of rooms in front of a group, which I thought they shouldn't have done. The question was to know whether there were 3 or 4 rooms, as you had to go through one of them to access the other ones, questioning if it did count as a room.  One of the group was composed of 2 men, one cis-woman and one transgender woman (who reassured the other woman that she wouldn't be alone as there were 2 of them).   Another group was made up of Cambridge Univerity students and I thought that although they seemed trustworthy, it wouldn't be doing them a favour to let them rent out the house as it would mean they would do their Masters' Degree at a much less prestigious university.   There was a whole wall at the back of the house (outside) covered in whiteboard surface, and I thought that this would be trashed as I walked by.  there were suddenly dogs, including my own. I stroked him and he was really enjoying it (and me too).

I was part of a secret organisation. I didn't really know what the purpose of it was but I was sent to work abroad. There was a woman there to supervise. I didn't want to be there and I demanded to know more.  I was sent to a nurse because of my headaches who injected me in the arm. I realised too late that it wasn't for my headache and I knew there was something wrong. I think there were 2 "colleagues" there with me. I escaped.  I found myself in my house and I wondered if I couldn't move the big fridge-freezer out of the living room to make more space and maybe put up a projector and screen to watch films.  It was an old stone house and I looked into a passage into the stone wall. It was narrow and there was an opening on the other side, I could see the light. There was supposed to be a window but there wasn't one. I crawled through, felt a little claustrophobic but managed to see outside: it was the neighbour's garden. I was back in my house and the neighbour's dog came through the passage. I either had my 2 dogs or had to arrange to collect them from somewhere.  I saw a video of someone filming my ex's house: it was very untidy, with piles of clothes, tools and bikes everywhere.  Back to my house, I also noticed a pile of neatly folded clothes that I had to put away. I saw a colleague-friend giving an interview. He spoke in English at first but then he switched to an Indian language.

There was some kind of international homeless camp - including a New Zealander who made it back home after years having to be a sex worker. I saw some stunnning landscapes - Azores?   I was on a work "mission" of some sort and had to make my way back home. The receptionist was found to be a spy. I left the building where my colleagues (in the dream) were and walked towards what I thought was "Gare du Nord" (North Station). I witnessed the burglary of a kiosk, a man threw away a bike D-lock on the floor (it looked like he had just cut it off) and his accolytes were busying themselves in the kiosk already. I wanted to tell the Police but there was none around and i felt impotent (the word "impotency" came up vividly in my mind and I thought about this word in my dream, and about how it was a perfect description, and also, I like the sound of it).  I entered what I thought was my station but ended up in a very crowded pub. The tables and armchairs were so close together it was difficult to walk through. The were people sleeping or chilling on them. I had to climb over some tables to come back out and as I did, I realised I wasn't wearing any shoes. An older woman pointed it out to me too.   I took some stairs with a weak-looking rope as a railing, wentdown and realised it wasn't the way I had come in as it was only going down towards the cleaners' quarter. There was some kind of box and plastic on the floor. I saw a cleaner and she had a very bushy moustache. I wondered how she managed to grow a moustache.  I went back up as I still coulnd't exit the building.   I realised I was in fact in another station and asked a young woman for the North Station, adding that I couldn't check myself because my phone was broken. She said to go to another station but that there was one change; or to walk to Magenta Station, which was further but direct. She smiled when she repeated "Magenta".   I still had no idea how to get there and I wanted to cry but then I thought to myself that it would be fine and that I would be happy once I would get home for the weekend.

I was worried about not getting enough work. I found myself near some kind of (train?) station and saw a colleague. I wondered what she was doing there. We had a quick chat and I carried on walking (with my husband?). There was some sort of workshop and other interpreters/translators were attending (all women). We were standing in a group and someone asked us to split into voice ranges to sing a song. I and another woman were stood in the middle not singing because we didn't know the lyrics.  Later I found the colleague I'd met before again and she said she'd bought a bag for £5,000, which was cheap to her. I thought that was insane money and that she must be very rich. Later, I bumped into another colleague, she'd stayed in my room and left a (green?) gummy bear on the floor, which I found later.  Later, I saw an old very good friend whom I haven't seen in almost 20 years. I asked him how to attract clients and find work, I said that I would be happy with 2 times 4,000 words to translate a month (he was also a translator and I wanted him to understand I wouldn't steal his work), but that I would rather do a lot more interpreting. He gave me the name of an agency to contact: "Sherwood". Then another friend from that time in my life rang the door, I let him in. He was taller than I remembered. He told me about his daughter and his difficult relationship with the mother. I asked him how old his daughter was and he said: "Four. I thought I'd already said that!" (in an inpatient way). They'd both brought some odd orange wine, reminiscing that we used to drink rose together. I wondered how to repay them for the wine but there was a shop right opposite where we were that sold the exact same wine. My mother arrived (it was her flat) and I reminded her of who my 2 friends were. I went to my room, noticed I'd bought a set of bra and knickers (they looked too small) and saw the gummy bear that my colleague had left on the floor.

I was in trouble and needed help. My oldest and best friend from France came and I wondered how she'd managed to make her way from France at the drop of a hat to help me. She only had a couple of carrier bags with her. I took her to the neighbourhood where I live in the UK as there was a fair/market of some sort. I think she wanted to buy something or go back to see someone we had seen at the fair/market and we agreed she would come back later. I know that more happened but I cannot remember what.

My uncle was living in Lyon. He was racist and made a promotional video to sell a ground floor flat (for €/£ 350,000), featuring a woman representing French "values" (through being some kind of mayor or elected representative).  I was talking about his racism to someone and how absurd it was.  A. and I were visiting. We (A., my uncle, my mother and I) walked into town. It was very busy. A. talked to a couple eating at a restaurant table and they recommended some vegan cheese. Their friends told us we could just have googled it but I said it was nice to have some human contact and recommendations this way.  Later, there was a kind of parade, with old women dancing and singing. There was a black woman in the group and I thought it was good to see. They announced the Director (Mayor?): an older woman with short hair.  I ordered some pizzas but when I bit in the first one, I realised there were pieces of ham, a creamy base and cheese. I spat out the ham, scraped the other bit off and thought I should eat the rest anyway so as not to waste it.

I was travelling through Algeria but it was difficult to get around.  I was coming back from somewhere and had to walk on a high up path above a beach. At some point, there was a boat blocking the way that was moving high up like a pendulum.   I saw a colleague I used to work with (again, higher up) and he was talking about how much he used to drink when he was in France: first in the South of France and then near Lille, where he would down up to 10 pints of beer a night.   My friends were meeting up in town to celebrate one of our friends' birthday. I didn't want to go, I thought to myself that I had closed myself off so much that I couldn't even see my friends anymore. I bumped into some of them but one especially didn't acknowledge me or say hello, which really hurt me and reinforced the feeling that I was unable to meet them. A girl who apparently knew some of my friends was pregnant, but I already knew because a close friend of mine had already told me. It didn't show yet and she alluded to it without saying it clearly so I didn't know if I was supposed to know and how to react.   I understood that my husband was meeting my friends so thought I should too, but I wanted to go for a run before. I was wearing some track suit bottoms but spent a long time trying to find my shoes in a big bag, but without success. I went via a shop, people were queuing at the checkout and as I walked nearby, a female security guard just shouted me to lower my trousers down (she suspected I'd stolen something). I refused to do it in front of everyone and suggested going to the back of the shop. We just walked to the end of the aisle and I lowered my trousers down so she could inspect that I hadn't stolen anything, but all the people from the till arrived and it was very embarrassing.   I then saw different friends and told them in turn what had happened. I also mentioned this study to one of them and she said with irony/scepticism: "are they going to help you realise that crisps are made of potatoes?".

My husband (A.) and I were at Sainsbury's. I was queuing and we had to social distance but no one really did. There was a family in front of me with a mother and  maybe 2 grown-up sons. She was talking to them in English but then she said "je vais parler français". I don't know what she said as I stopped hearing them. There were some reduced items. I took one pack and asked A. if I should take the other one too, green beans with onion and a dressing. He couldn't make up his mind, which annoyed me. I think he told me what he'd planned to cook and it didn't seem to fit with his plans but I got it anyway. One of my best friends (J.) called but my husband picked up, talked with him while I was doing the shopping and when I came back, he'd hung up and said that he'd told my friend that we were expecting some guests, so I couldn't speak on the phone. I thought it was very rude, disrespectful to me and dishonest to my friend. A. said that J. had told him he was on a "hypochondriac rice cakes" diet.  We started making our way home. My husband started rubbing himself against me and we were both aroused. I understood that he'd lied to my friend so we could spend the evening together alone.  On the way back, we had our dog. We turned into a narrow winding pedestian street and one of the men of a gay couple asked: "you live on doggy lane too?". The narrow path was boarded by houses with big sliding windows on the right, very close to where we were walking and the dog was off the lead. He escaped into one of the houses,the sliding window was open and there were only thin curtains to go through, to run after a Guinea pig. I followed him, hoping he wouldn't kill the Guinea pig. Thankfully, I managed to get him back and we were back out on the path. A tree had fallen over the path but we made our way through/over it. Further, I saw a big chow chow and the dog ran to meet the dog, who was with a man. As the chow chow was also off the lead, it was fine to let them meet. The chow chow immediately humped Terry and I said to the man "that was quick!". They stopped humping quickly and our dog started running away. He found a bike and started pedaling away. I was running as fast as I could and was shouting his name. I shouted to a man on his bike to try to stop him but he didn't. I kept yelling, getting more and more agitated. I caught my finger in a fence so our dog was getting away. Further on, still running, I asked a family if they'd seen a dog on a bike and someone said no but someone else said no. I couldn't see our dog anymore and thought he was lost for good as this was in the city and he could have gone anywhere.

I had a cruch on a neighbour. His house/flat was windowless and it was difficult to make out how it was inside. I had a suspicion he had a crush on me too because I managed to see inside his house and I saw that he'd put up some notes (post-its) I'd written for him all around the house. It felt like a bunker, close to a motorway and one back door opened to a restaurant's kitchen.  Several of us went to the cinema and I was hoping I would sit next to him. I was late because my card wasn't working but there was a seat left next to him. I gave him a present. I knew he had a half-sister. He had a difficult relationship with his mother but she helped him financially. I knew that because we'd talked about it once and we both opened up to our family history. I told him about my difficult relationship with my father but he seemed more interested in talking about him.    A friend was studying "firefighting techniques". I was telling someone about her and her studies but I said: "I've got the French word for it" as the English word didn't come but then it did.  She gave me a pint of beer, which she got a good deal for through her studies. As a thank you, I went to some kind of till and asked to get a £20 voucher, but the cashier got it wrong and wrote "£30". I had to rectify but felt like a cheapskates.  My friend showed me some new machine they used in her studies, called "The Butterfly". Someone demonstrated by going in and got swept up in an angel-like movement. My friend mentioned something about Romania. I told the neighbour about it and gave him.a piece of paper with a geometric heart on it. I had a paper too and we both started to colour in the square-lined heart in red. He showed me his and there were two :( smileys. He said that they were the reason he couldn't study firefighting.

I was at my husband's family estate and I found out more about his 6 brothers and 3 sister, most of whom were quite a bit older than him. They were very wealthy and I felt out of place. I knew they disapproved of his choice to be with me and thought he could do better. We stayed the night in one of the cottages, saw one brother there. Were were in another part of the estate the next day with another brother. There was a little boy (no older than 2) and I looked after him for a bit. My husband (A.) and I were looking after N.'s dog. The dog was black and handsome. I can't remember his name and in the dream, I was trying to remember his name too. We went to some kind of football training grounds where A. was working/volunteering. I lost the dog and was very worried, but we found him again. As I had no work, I decided to come to training with A. every day. The was a good spread of food, including a big ring/wreath-shaped cake, all made by A. 2 women (one older white, one younger black women) worked as dinner ladies to help the boys/men get food after the training. I was always trying to keep and eye on the dog as I was anxious he would escape again and I was thinking about putting a tag with my name and phone number on his collar. A. and the football trainees were queuing and A. shouted to me something like I wasn't pulling my weight or I was lazy or something to that effect, and everyone heard. I felt crushed that he thought that and that he ridiculed me in front of everyone so I thought it would be best to leave (with the dog). I went past the table with the dinner ladies, they were smiling and laughing; they didn't look like they'd heard what A. had said to me so I just said something like "he'd rather I went so I'll have to go". I knew/thought A. fancied the younger girl and would end up with her.

I looked at the watch and it was 1:15 pm. I thought my husband would be very disappointed as we're on holiday but I'm stuck in bed with a headache.   I asked my mother how much inheritance she would get. She said €5000 but that she'd lost 36 years.

I was staying at a hotel by an unidentified seaside. The majority of the dream was in the restaurant, which seemed to be mostly outside, wrapping itself around the building. There was much moving of things to make the place the best it could be in terms of appearance and functionality. Like moving trees in pots and relocating other bits and pieces like lighting. We wanted to make it look and function the best it could be and were happy when something worked. I was with someone I don't know in awake life, but we knew each other well and there seemed to be lots of other people in the restaurant that I knew, or was talking to. Everyone seemed to be happy. I was asked about adjustments by someone at a table but I can't remember what it related to. I think it was something to do with their life rather than the place. I went out for a walk with my friend down to the beach and we were singing and laughing. The road to the beach was full of people. I was wearing a cropped top and someone in the street touched the skin on my stomach. It didn't seem to bother me.

I drove to see a very old friend and his wife. He was in a grand but crumbling mansion in Wales, which he was very proud of. He had a drone but it looked like a Kindle, and he'd flown over and around his house and grounds, and I was very impressed with what it had achieved. I wanted him to teach me how to use it so I could do the same at mine The drive seemed important and I was following a map.

I moved to a large modern house on a cliff right next to the sea, which had huge crashing waves, but far enough away that it was beautiful to watch and not any danger to me. The house was all vast windows facing the sea, so it was like being outside inside. Someone came to visit me. We sat talking and she was quite close to me. While we were talking I noticed that there were a lot of people playing in the waves, which would have been dangerous, but they were right at the edge and were jumping up and down and making a lot of noise. I found their presence slightly irritating, that they were spoiling the view and feeling of the place.
The internet wasn't working but Tom found clever ways to fix it.

I was living somewhere with fruit trees. There was a lot of fruit ready that had to be dealt with. I was freezing it to have with yoghurt. I was also stealing a peach the size of a melon from the neighbours. There was a little girl in the neighbourhood who had become national champion playing a car race game. The game was very realistic with gear changes etc. so it was very impressive she was so good at it.

I was practising to be a wizard and given various cherry trees to try out my skills. The one they finally left me with was a cherry tree with a freckle. The freckle was causing problems for its growth and fruit bearing.

I was in the town where I was born. There was some festival and my mum, dad, sister, her partner, my husband and my uncle were on a boat cruise. We had to duck down to go under a series of bridges. We went on land again and there was a band playing at the harbour. They played a carnaval song and we all started dancing, together with other people who where there.
We were doing a second viewing of the house we want to buy. We asked some questions, but somehow it became clear that the owner was trying to rent it out instead of selling.

I was visiting a friend from secondary school and during the visit my bicycle got stolen. I didn't know how to get home and walked to the town centre. There I met a friend from primary school, who was there looking for prostitution work. She was going to drive me home and she had a very big car, utility vehicle but a brand new one. As we were driving 4 cars suddenly blocked us on the road, driving from the opposite direction on both sides of the road and behind us. We were trapped. Their cars were also big, new utility vehicles. Suddenly they turned into big robots and my friend was going to do the same with her car to fight with them.

We bought IKEA outside furniture and it had some asbestos in it. We were reluctant to get rid of it and we're thinking of other solutions, like covering it with other material. I was then volunteering to take samples of dust off people's clothes, these would go to a lab and be tested for asbestos. After this I washed to take the train home. The platforms had been changed and I couldn't find mine. Ran all over the station in a rush and it wasn't there. No signage either. we were in South Africa. We were crossing a border by car and everyone in the car, including the driver had to build their arms up to cross. I was driving and this made it very difficult to change gear.

Going into an iron mongers choosing knobs for chest of drawers but being unsure how many were needed.  The shop was a long way from where the car was parked.  It was a tiny shop.  The drawer knobs were metal but when you picked them up they were terracotta.  There were no prices.

I was in St Ives Cornwall - was going to a spoken words and music gig in Penzance. But I’d planned to walk there and realised it would be dark and Id only walked the route once plus it was over fields.  Called a friend to see if they were going but they weren’t.  Couldn’t drive as I’d had two halves of cider and was over the limit.  So I phoned St Ives taxis but needed to know not only if they could do the trip both ways but how much it would cost as I didn’t have that much cash.

Filling in online activity tables for someone - keep going back to check everything is done.  As I think I’ve finished I realise I’ve left out info on Tricky - the musician - and have to add it in.  Next people are waiting for a meeting with me in a hallway of a large house.  There are other meetings going on so as well - so lots of people sitting around.  The one person I’m waiting for doesn’t seem to be there - a woman says she thinks that the missing person did come in and looks out the door and sees her going by - she’s says she’s the one in ‘high heels’ I go outside and call the woman’s name as she is trying to go into another office.  Then I realise I’m in the street where a friend of a friend is selling their house.  I look to the other side of the street and see them - dressed flamboyantly- saying goodbye to what must be a prospective purchaser. I call my friend to tell her.

I’m with someone we are in a room with 2 doors. We are tired and decide to lie down knowing that we’ve got to let people in shortly.  We set an alarm for 4:30 and curled up fall asleep. At 6:00 we wake up as the people we were due to let in earlier are still banging on the doors.  Next thing I’m outside in Leytonstone High St looking at a market stall selling junk,  trying to talk to the stall holder but it doesn’t work.  There’s a bloke pan handling customers for cash and as he moves round my way I move off. Stand outside a drs surgery on the corner where the bank used to be.  It’s not taking any new patients - and I say as much to the person I’m with.

At a front door and am shown into a room by a woman and I sit at a table.  Large, bright room mainly pale colours. Rooms leading off it. I’m there as I’ve been asked to do a podcast for the comedian Sarah Milligan. She sits down opposite me and says what the fee is.  I don’t feel it’s enough and say so - I offer to take her dog for a walk which she reconsiders.  I’m Given a lead and small puppy.  Her assistant and I go out into the streets and the puppy tries to get into every shop.  We turn to go back. Inside she says she has reconsidered and has increased the fee by 75%. We shake hands and I leave.  Outside I meet a friend who wants to show me something so we enter a big building and go up and up escalators.  It’s a sort of hospital. We stop and walk through double doors and are in a reception area.  I’m told to take my shoes off and am given paper type slippers.  We walk through a series of treatment rooms with carpeted floor. Like a pub carpet.  It’s cramped and busy but I’m given no explanation or introductions.  We leave by a double door and as we go down a staircase I ask who funds this and was it the yoga centre?  My friend heads down a flight of escalators and I struggle to follow her as my slippers fall off.  Eventually I catch up and say my shoes are still upstairs.

Was in a 70s type building with a group of people waiting for an event to start. Sitting on a selection of hotel like sofas.  The format of the event which was some sort of fashion show had been agreed and was about to start when someone took over and re-arranged it all. This person wasn’t pleasant and got what they wanted by force of personality - it felt hugely embarrassing as there were external people there and it was a bit like doing your dirty washing in public.  We went upstairs to relocate and again were to start when whoever it was in charge wasn’t available - at this point I walked off and the soundtrack was ‘Bank Robber’ by The Clash and I was walking downstairs behind Mick Jones from The Clash - and I was beside myself with delight - Mick Jones!   Then I was outside - it was in Wanstead E London - opposite the pub outside the charity shop.  I had some sort of fabric bubble that I was playing with - it was a dark green feather light structure.  I was walking to my destination when a little girl called out and wanted a go. She always breaks things so I kindly said no but then pulled off some of the material and made her a bubble of her own.  I kept walking till I got to the venue which was hugely busy with lots of cars and coaches arriving and dropping people off.  No one I knew was there yet.

Had to buy shoes - was in Watford High Street. Partner had my bag with purse but I went downstairs into a busy show shop.  Didn’t get help from any assistant- a friend worked there but she wasn’t around.  Found a pair of shoes - platform/flat form clogs and although was worried that they think I was stealing them, headed upstairs to pay. My partner was there so I got my purse back. The shoes were (24.99).  I had the right money but the cashier insisted on showing me how to cash up at the end of the day. He wouldn’t use a calculator - did it all in his head.

Cleaning the deck of the boat - it’s a wide beam. Working with someone.  Look ahead and there’s a boat midstream but ahead is a small metal structure that looks like a motorised pontoon with a neighbours small son at the wheel.  We see the child at the same time and I call his father David.  David recommenced that we block off the exit roots to make sure the boy doesn’t try to escape.  We get the boy off the pontoon and his parents have arrived.

In an exhibition space - the exhibition was on water usage.  To get to the displays you followed puddle shaped signs on the floor which started off shimmering gold then turned to water colours when you stood on them.   Next in a workshop - cutting out a rectangle from cream coloured metal with oxyacetylene.  It was a protest piece of artwork against rigid definitions of art and I was writing  ‘F your perceptions this is art I’m making’

Started off on a cliff edge looking over - there was remedial work going on to shore up the erosion.  Next I was on the steps of a hotel in central London - talking to the men who open the doors for guests.  I go in and head to the 4rd floor - it’s a spa area and there’s lots of women in fluffy gowns - as I head through one asks me about an individual.  I say they aren’t in and then in case I’m thought rude - say  they are In Devon. Next I’m in bed with I guess my partner - I want to sleep but they have a hugely important meeting and insist on trying out the shirt, jacket combo for the meeting.  It’s awful so a rethink is needed. Finally I’m outside again - this time in Watford High Street - waiting for my father.  It’s packed and busy and he finally finds me - he’s annoyed as he couldn’t find what he wanted so we head into the shop together

I’m in a large car with family and we are getting out passing stuff to each other.  We’ve been food shopping at clearly expensive shops.  The house is open and we start putting things away,  Friend Kate has bought a selection of meat for herself - she opens  the package to show - hugely expensive cuts.    It’s time to sort out my son’s dinner - he’s having pasta & cheese sauce. While it’s cooking I call him in.  Get him settled at the table & he starts to eat.  Then there’s shouting outside - I go out.    The landscape is different - at the end of the garden there are fields and on the skyline, trees with mountain gorillas in them.  The gorillas are angry & there’s lots of chest beating going on.  There’s one very large male silverback leading the aggression.  My son comes out and is taken back indoors but not before the silverback throws a toy dog into the garden.  Our real dog escapes into the first field and runs around excitedly before being caught.  We go inside and secure the house.

There was a baby riding a cow bareback. Her nappy was slipping off as she stood up on the cow. She was controlling the cow expertly. The cow was stretching out, growing longer legs and back and neck, changing shape as the baby stood on it holding the reins. She moved around the cows body. The cow was gigantic. they were riding along a country road very fast. She rode it all different ways, even on its hind legs.

An open truck full of stinking muck went by (either human or animal) and I heard someone from the next house shout "shut all the windows!" the people I was with tried but failed to shut the windows so they reached out and tried to throw a kind of hinged flap on the top of the truck over the muck. It didn't work. they got covered in the muck, and everything inside the house got covered in a layer of the muck as well. We had been trying to paint the walls of a room in the house, but it had been a disaster becasue we didn't have the right sized brush and the spray for the paint was malfunctioning and making the paint land in blobs and runny streaks all over the place. I was trying to paint the place white, but someone else was using black paint and it was contaminating the paint i was using. we were arguing about who had taken the big brush. I could not buy a new one as i was as broke. the people I was with morphed into my mother, and my ex partner of 20 years. He was annoying the hell out of me. It was the worst decorating job i had ever done. I got the impression that this was a job, not my own house. Paint was going mainly on the newspaper i had laid down rather than the walls. It was impossible to clean up. Earlier I had been running up a hill with two girls i had been at school with, who could really run. they were still girls, not grown women. it was night. we came to a very very busy road. it had been raining. there were a lot of big lorries thundering by. I thought i would never be able to get across. then some horses came by and i was cinvinced there was going to be a messy pile up becasue of the horses and the amount of lorries not taking care to slow down. it was really hairy. the horses were covered in lathery sweat, like overrun racehorses. but the horses were ok, and eventually we managed to run across the road and carry on running up the hill. We took a lane between high hedges, the terrain was lumpy, full of stones and rocks, the ground was muddy from the rain. There was another girl behind me, and I looked back, and waited for her, but she sped past, and didn't wait for me.

I waas refusing a drink in a crowd of people at a bar, it was some kind of party, everyone was really dressed up. Someone said what's that you're drinking? They looked into my glass and wrinkled their nose. I said it was water. I was an alcoholic, I said I needed a night off drinking, and that most people had a night off sobriety. I needed a change. But I doubted the truth of what I was saying though I did not drink anything but the water. Everyone around me looked confused at what I was saying and I realised that everyone there was an alcoholic but didnt KNOW that they were. There was a juke box playing a song, but the record was scratched and stuck on the intro. It was To Cut A Long Story Short, by Spandau Ballet. It was frustrating because I wanted to hear the whole song.

I was in a wonderful library full of old books, towering overhead, lots of little passageways, it was polished wood and leather bindings. I was so happy tp be there, but my excitement was echoing around the place much more than it would in real life. I had to be quiet, my voice was bouncing around as if it was a massive empty chamber. There was a large clock/writing desk. Its main drawer was full of brand new mid brown closed zips in bunches, and loose, tumbling about the drawer. amongst the zips was a tacky watch, it was plasticky and jewelled, slightly broken, someone had stuck a glittery bindi on it. I shut the drawer. Outside the library it became confusing, a country village that morphed into a place I used to live in another european country. There was a minor celebrity there, a woman who was very fond of dogs. Someone said she was a bit silly, and thought that if she whistled, a dog would come to her. But she really did have this gift, and lots of friendly happy dogs started to appear, and she was very happy. But one of the dogs was an old one that remembered me. It had a grey muzzle, and was on a rope, tied to the side of a building. It growled and snarled at me, and I could't go anywhwere near it. It's owner was dead, and had died soon after our affair had ended, and he had his grave on the same land, buried by one man, alone. I struggled to recall his name, but after a moment or two i did remember it. A quayside appeared, with deep water all around, lots of people drinking and eating at benches. I stepped onto the jetty, over the water, but it was unstable, and a pod of whales swam right underneath, causing a wave and i fell into the water with a girl. she might have been my daughter when she was younger. we sank down, but were ok, we could breathe under the water and i remember thinking that this was not usual, and being aware of each breath i took, and feeling it in my lungs and being cautious. we saw a strange fish swimming, and then a mermaid swam toward us and i was disappointed because it was not a real mermaid, but a sort of disney cartoon type character. she caught the fish and ate it from the head down, and offered us the tail portion. we tried to eat it but it was disgusting. the mermaid laughed and swam away to her mermaid friends who also laughed at us, but it wasn't malicious, they were just playing around. Then we saw a whale with a long nose - a bottle-nosed whale i think, moored to the side of the Rainbow Warrior ship. But the whale also became an animation and we were part of a strange animated movie about the whale who took the Rainbow Warrior on a quest to save the planet. There were also two little boys, identical twins, on the ship, messing about, almost going overboard, but i knew that this was written into the plot. I was annoyed that the twins had been cast as white, then I looked carefully at them, and it seemed like they were chosen because they might have seemed dual heritage east asian/white to some people, but I knew this was a cynical move by racist directors and i was annoyed about it. There was a strange soundtrack throughout.

I was trying to coax news out of a man who said he had started a new business. He had bought a place in a tourist town, somewhere in Cornwall. he was ill with a terrible migraine and was lying down. I lay down next to him and offered him a pain killer, but his wife was there, and thought that i was trying to seduce her husband and lay down next to me, and reached out to her husband who would not respond to her. I tried to gt information out of him but he was obtuse.
I was a hobbit putting a flatpack bed together, but it was complicated and the end result was so awful you could not have slept on it.

I was with my 13 year old daughter whom I have not seen for four months. She was agitated and crying, the room we were in was unfamiliar. Then suddenly a man broke through the wall of the room with his finger and started trying to push his way through and I knew that he as trying to get to my daughter. I screamed at him to stop and when he didn’t, I called the police, but I was put through to an answering service. He was breaking through the wall and my daughter was crying and I understood then that he had sexually abused her when I was absent from her. I was so disturbed and distraught. I was apologising over and over, and the emergency services turned up just in time to stop this man breaking right through the wall. My daughter was wearing hideous lacy white knickers, and I was equally disturbed by seeing her bottom in these knickers. She was sprawled across me, and I was holding her and crying that I was so sorry
working on the paper somewhere a sense of being in the middle of writing, maybe sharing ideas seeing myself working but glimpsed as if through an open window

Just awake in the middle of more bikes- in the peloton on bike cam- not actually riding- just continuing with the TV coverage of the Tour de France that I've been watching for almost three weeks- continuing progress/effort up the mountain!  I can see the riders just behind the bike where my camera is- concentration looking up the road and then all the array of colours in the teams that go with the Tour  a nice day in the Alps but definitely going up a slope! love the perseverance!
images of being in a series of short encounters- with others- a few unfamiliar/vague images of people-not really engaged or doing much. little snippets of events- of something happening.

sense of breathing peacefully- I see myself (from the front- eye level, about two metres from the seeing me) standing still, looking ahead- being held, comforted, nestled back against a known  man looking into somewhere behind me- not seeing me or looking at anything in particular quiet, peaceful- both of us taller, thinner, fitter than any current actuality. (a sense of safety rather than romance)  almost a sense of being relieved, relaxed, understood, in tune- strength against my back in being lightly supported/held   walking diagonally to the right and see a long envelope (4 x 8?) with an address on the front that I'd written- lying on a low table on the left-maybe admin of some kind- an enquiry- concerned/ telling someone that I needed a reply from someone-    while slowly moving with others diagonally to front right-a sense of pause-looking down at the letter on the way slowly past- feeling of other adults around in a reasonably confined indoor space- just noticing people from shoulders down- just presences nearby- not heads or faces  feeling a little puzzled/concerned as image went past me lower left as I looked down/back and was awake...

people standing/milling about on my left someone advising about something people working to complete a puzzle at some distance going in a lift but still being in a bigger space with a sense of lots of other people nearby jostling but seemingly working together on the problem  someone to my left and behind me mentioning Sunweb

I was in a large grassed open park like space - not familiar to me, but Inoticed a few people pulling out weeds. My husband pointed out (on our left as we were walking away - perhaps having been on our dog-walk) two young children near a bus shelter with their mother, eagerly contributing to the process.
I was writing a report- concentrating quietly- perhaps on my own, sitting and hands moving i was slightly tilted forward looking forward

firstly adults milling about- sort of crowded and darkish  then outside walking to something on a pah between big apartments with grassy lawns- Ian alongside and walking behing/accompanying older large lady with bluish skirt just past knee and uneven gait-large  calves and low sensible shoes. She had some issues walking. Two others were with her.  the group seemed sort of unsure of destination, heading in slightly diff directions with Jenna confident- long hair flying behind her as she ran off to the right to an apartment building. Ian and sort of dithering between heading to the left or the car in car park between the two buildings and then turning to join the others as they moved towards building where J was headed.  Ian seeming a little confused, not knowing where we were supposed to go. Others chatting, no sense of rush or urgency. Me frustrated. Clear day- space around.

I dreamt I was a woman who had a job interview. that interview was to take part at my parent's house in the conservatory, and I was dressed as you would for a professional interview.  A woman was interviewing me - older, distinguished. She brought her dog which was a black alsatian who played with my parent's two dogs. I remember the interviewer's dog vividly. we sat next to each other with our backs to the door to look into the conservatory, and throughout the conversation there was this powerful draw to her, like a magnetism. I do not remember her asking any specific questions, nor do I recall what this woman looked like.  The last bit I remember is us leaning in for a kiss.

Last night I dreamt i was an american serviceman in WW2. I was based in a town called Boulougne which was in North West Brittany, right on the coast. I'm 99% sure this place isn't real. We heard that the German's attacked amphibiously and took the harbour, so we had to go in and repel them. We jumped on a coach like you would get on for a child's school trip. It was old and dirty, and somehow was able to drive right into the harbour and park, going past several German soldiers who didn't seem to notice. When we got out we all hid behind a small hill and open plain and began shooting at German soldiers on the far side against a wall. They were moving back and forth so it reminded me of the game Duck Hunt. Then two tanks arrived and so I said I would deal with it. I ran around the tanks so they kept trying to follow me, but they couldn't see me properly and eventually one drove off in frustration.

I was at an indoor water park with my partner, Leanne. I had a distinct feeling of her leading me around the water park and having to hurry to keep up with her. We didn't interact other than her leading me and going first down the slides.  There were 5 slides in total. All were long - longer to go down than they looked like they should be. All but the final slide were tunnel water slides and had twists, turns and drops to keep on edge. There was a feeling of slowing down and speeding up randomly. On one slide we (Leanne and I would go down simultaneously with her just in front) caught up with a loud, middle aged man at the bottom of the slide.  The pool areas were very busy and we had to dodge people as we walked out of the shallow areas of them. It seemed that the water park was on the border between England and Scotland. One woman was apologising to her child and explaining that she had to go back to Scotland in an ominous way, before handing her child over to a nanny in a full Mary Poppins outfit. The nanny then began wading into the pool asking if the child was having fun.  The last slide had a huge queue and I remember there being two small children behind us. They knew my name and kept asking me questions. Eventually I saw that the slide was a huge toilet bowl with 32 large, black slides next to one another down to the drain in the middle which took a sharp left turn and then dumped you in the pool. I was worried that we would all hit into one another in the middle as the slides went straight down into the drain.  We got to the front and the slide operator was overly familiar, telling me to pick a slide. I was the 31st and assumed the two children behind me were together so thought I would be the last allowed on but apparently they weren't and one of them was next to me. I lost sight of Leanne. I looked up and apparently every slide was name after a type of foodstuff and I was on the Bovril slide.

I am with someone I used to work with at an event, as we leave I decide to go to someones house. I am followed by a man who is friendly and asks me to go to dinner. I get to the house and as I go in the man who is talking to me gets in the owner of the houses truck and starts to reverse out the drive. They tell me to close the front door and get in. I tell them they can't steal a car. They say the owner will nevr know and they will return it after dinner. At this point the entire family who live in the house all come out the front door. They don't see the truck being taken they are just walking as a family.

I am with my mum and someone else, we are in a house I don't know whose house.  I need to catch a flight to Corfu but I keep forgetting about it and I am not sure what time the flight is. A flight time screen is in the corner of my dream view and has two flights on it. One ar 16.30 and one at 21.30.  I can 't check the times because I don't have a smartphone, only a really old Nokia. I am going on holiday with my now ex who hasn't called me to see why I am late. No one has called me.   I need to get home to check my flight and pack. I grab an old bike, but it is really old fashioned and I am peddling hard up a big hill but I cannot get very far. People / strangers keep distracting me. I feel like I am in a video game.  I go into the Coop supermarket and am walking around looking for something, I can still see the flight details and I am really starting to panic now about having missed my flight. Still no one has called me. My optician is in the Coop, he is filling up the fruit and veg scetion and he shouts something funny over to me and I wonder why he is working here as he told me at my eye test how busy he was over lockdown. I have a trolley and I have piled it with shop stuff and boxes and I am trying to get out but I don't want to shoplift and I don't have time to pay.   I am now sat opposite a guy with a smartphone. I ask him if I can borrow it to check my flight, but I can't get onto the website, I keep launching apps and being unable to close them down. I get onto the fligth website and I see I have completely missed my flight. I am not sure why I keep forgetting things.

I am walking up and down and around the lanes of the village I live in. I see people and talk to them but it’s not very clear. They are telling me different ways to get comfortable to sleep.  I am hanging washing onto a washing line with my daughter. It is really windy. Suddenly I notice that with each piece we hang up a poo (dog poo, long poo and some green poo) appears under the washing line. I tell my daughter to stay away. I’m still hanging up the washing, the wind is blowing and the clothing is flapping across my face, I feel like I am barefoot and I don’t want to step in the poo. I feel grossed out

A grandfather had died and I was attending a dinner and drinks party at a big hotel like a wedding. In the lead up to the party I was in America with huge crowds of people watching cars about to race. We were all standing on a bridge looking over the edge. Piers Morgan was in a convertible and Tommy Lee Jones was on a BMX bike watching the car rally. There was an explosion but no one cared and then people on the bridge started to jump off into the river to cool down. They were having fun. Someone wanted me to jump off the bridge, they were in the water looking up and asked me if my shoes were leather. The woman next to me said hers were leather converse and I said mine were too.  Then I am at a hotel getting ready for the party, it feels like it is my party but I know it isn’t. Guests are made up of university housemates, people from my current and previous companies. I feel very nostalgic, but I am not engaging with any of the people. I’m nervous as an ex will be there and I don’t want to see them and I don’t want anyone else to meet them.  I’m trying to get ready, and I’m scrolling through a long playlist on a screen looking for music. For some reason I’m scrolling a list of Bon Jovi songs but I can’t get to the song "keep the faith" I want, the list keeps moving about and I lose my place repeatedly. I am wearing a big dress but with timberland boots. The laces are really long and I just keep pulling at them. On one boot the laces are a black ribbon, it’s so long and I just keep pulling it. I put some of the excess in my hair.  Then I’m in a bar, and old work colleague I haven’t seen for years walks up to me, I go to hug her but she walks past me, she’s talking to me but I can’t seem to hug her and when we do, it is awkward like when someone goes for a double cheek kiss and the other a single cheek kiss. She asks me who has died and says she’s sorry and then we are standing at a bar. Waitresses are setting a long table for dinner and all the places are so close together. I am told I will be at the head of the table and then the waitress splits off my part of the table and spins it on its wheels and I am just following her watching things fall off it. I’m still trying to lace the boot with the long black ribbon in it. People are walking in to join and I don’t want my ex to walk in, I see lines of people I know but they are straight faced, no expression. I’m so nervous and I am pulling at the ribbon and breaking bits off, tying it into bows and sticking it in my hair, but it’s not my hair and I want it all to stop.

I was hanging out with my daughter and her friends and the mums at school, and then I was at a flat viewing and 3 small people ran through and were showing me round. I was sat at the table and my mum and dad were there. Next thing I am in a garden with a widing path and I am feeling anxious and JLo is standing in front of a small group talking about how she suffers from anxiety. There are tall plant pots all round and for some reason they are filled with water with ice on top and I am walkig up to them and punching through the ice as she talks. Then I am looking for some tables and I see a friend over the fence in a garden. He asks me if I want to come over for a dinner party but I don't and I find myself on a small speed boat with someone I used to work with years ago. We are looking for a spot to go diving and the sea is clear and turquise. He stops the boat under a bridge in a type of sunken city and it is dark. He has a wetsuit, flippers and a mask and snorkel and I only have the swimsuit I am in. We climb up a high wall and jump straight off, him feet first and I dive. As I enter the water headfirst I see a sunken concrete platform that I only narrowly miss. I am not scared, it doesn't bothern me.

I’m with my ex at their mothers house for Christmas but it’s more like a hotel. I feel uncomfortable because the last time I was there it was not a good experience at all. I feel very aware of myself and my surroundings and I’m trying to stay out of the way without being rude. My ex is doing what they always did, acting casual, knowing I am uncomfortable. I go out to get away and my ex goes shopping. I get back to the house/hotel first and I am trying to keep myself to myself. I am avoiding the family members and moving around parts of the house and in the garden. My ex gets back to show off what they have bought (a black top hat).  We need to get ready for the family meal. Other people are now milling around which makes me think we are in a hotel. My ex comes to speak to me. We decide to head up to get ready but as I start to move a elderly woman comes over and stands in front of me. She looks at me and it’s my grandmother (my dads mum), but she looks just like my Nan (my mums mum). She smiles at me and I hug her, and then I hug her hard. I ask why she’s here and if she knows my ex’s family as they live up north and my dads mum lived up north. I keep looking at her face, it’s my Nan. She says hi to my ex who is looking confused and then she tells me in a voice that keeps fading and I have to lean in to hear, that it’s ok, she knows what’s been happening. I’ll be ok. We go up to get ready and I feel very calm. We pass guests on the stairs and in the hall and I’m not sure how my Nan is here as she died years ago. My ex asks if I’m ok and is talking to me, but her voice is like background noise as we go into the room. I am just thinking about my Nan and I know I have seen her face so clearly for the first time in years.

I am with an old work colleague and we are talking on a porch of a house. There are two people sat behind us but we don't know who they are. Suddenly there are noise, choking, gagging noises as someone next to me is being strangled. I can't see them, I can only hear them and there is a pool of flesh and blood next to me. As I look around trying to work out what is happening one of the people behind me is strangling the other with a rope, I can't stop it and I can't get away from it.  My old work colleague has disappeared inside the house, it is pitch black in there and I can't stop looking at the pool of blood and flesh next to me. I go into the house and my colleague is in there, as I walk towards him, someone runs from the shadows behind me with a mask and facepaint on. I completely freeze already traumatized by what I have just seen outside.  The stranger removes his mask and starts laughing...my colleague is laughing, I am so confused.

Chapters of a book, seeing pages and words On a motorbike but don’t know whose riding it. I have no helmet on. Stop at a house go into the garage, speak to a girl with long dark hair and ask to take back the bicycle. I get on and I’m cycling. Another chapter another page. I’m in a town centre and I’m cycling through it. There are big signs everywhere. I speak to some people, they are talking about if Marks and Spencer’s should sell a dvd which explains strange phenomena. A young guy says he won’t stock it as it puts ideas which aren’t true into people’s minds. I ask how he knows the content isn’t true. He says because he doesn’t believe to be. I argue that he has no right to decide what is true or not. He says that if it can’t be proven it’s not real. I get really annoyed, I’m so bored of people thinking they personally know everything and have the right to voice their opinions but blanket reject or block others. I say, just because HE can’t prove that aliens exist, a cannibal wouldn’t eat another cannibal or there is or isn’t life after death doesn’t mean that it isn’t real. I ask if he exercises and he says he does Pilates. I ask him to prove that Pilates is good for him. Show me that it stretches the muscles, lengthens the body and makes the organs healthier. He said he can’t. I tell him if he can’t prove it but he does it because he “feels” better and healthier then he has no right to stop a dvd being sold which asks strange questions on unusual topics. I am suddenly following a group of people marching and protesting against a nightclub. Another chapter and another page and I am on a boat but really high up above everyone and I am taking pictures. I am in Florida or somewhere. There are fancy boats everywhere, young people are dancing and partying. Police are busting drugs cartel boats. I float higher and higher above the scene.
I am standing in a large field and fire and smoke has swept through it. I am just standing there amongst the smoke staring blankly and suddenly panic rises through me.

I was going to London to pick up good food in the evening and was getting changed in the middle of the street. I was so excited to go. I was at the fish counter at some sushi place and asked when they discount the fish? I then got some amount of the salmon, some other pink fish, and scallops mixed together. I then walked the streets and came back. My son was having a headache.

I was traveling in Syria on my own. I was by the coast and someone mentioned that there are so many people by the beach even though they shouldn't be because the water is being "treated". I went closer to see over the little hill. There were people sitting on the beach and some with their feet on the water. The bit of water that touches the sand was looking like it had some tar/black oil on it. I was thinking how when it gets really hot and  I need to swim to cool down I can't do it here and therefore must carry on traveling until I find another country where I can swim. I also thought about how when I meet Syrians in the future I can tell them I have been to their country and its beautiful. I then walked away from the water.
I had a dream about vaccinations. It's quite hazy but I knew that I need to be in line to get my vaccinations. Except he waits was so long and I was waiting on the street and it was getting dark.

I was on those streets, driving in a car with someone, seeing the working women. Stopping occasionally, getting out of the car to speak to them. One of the women had a pretty long gash across her finger. I asked if I can dress it with the plasters I took with me. I also told her that she needs to go to AE to have it stitched or it will take longer to heal and you cant stick after 24 ous anymore. I didn't think she would be open to going there. Hence the dressing. I an still see the darkness of the streets, the shady street lights, the warm air and cars driving past, occasionally dropping.

I was working in the nursery with small kids through the COVID era. The dentist was next door or even several dental practices. One of them had always customers when I walked past. There was a receptionist in their room and another lady with a lot of makeup. They always seemed to be taking payments and people were hovering by the doorway. Appeared to be waiting for the anesthesia to kick in. I spoke to the lady taking payments and she said they have been busy all the way through. I said the other dentist next door was doing a discount for the nursery for about £20 an hour. She mentioned, "so they went that low". The corridor where you walk out of the nursery is long wit a few doors and opens up to a bigger waiting room. I can't remember much about the nursery now except that there was something bad that happened, either a child got ill or went missing. This then transforms me straight into another recurrent very vivid dream I had a while back where I was looking for a child on this beach that was so beautiful, quite deep fast and so big waves. When I think of this location, I see everything so clearly - the beach, waves, sand, the shore, buildings by the beach, people walking, and swimming. And I was still looking for a kid who seems to be missing. Meeting those people along the way. The saltiness of the wind and warm sea air. The noise of the beach.

Me and my son were traveling with our caravan to Estonia where I am from. We stopped at the roadside restaurant. I parked the caravan and went inside. Heard the hissing noise and smelled gas. Got so scared and opened the doors and windows, told my son not to go there. Went inside to the restaurant and approached a middle-aged Estonian man and asked for help. He went and solved the problem. I asked what was it, he said a button with a man who wears a white coat as it means someone who changes gas canisters. He just switched it off. I thanked him. He asked if we towed all the way from America. I said we came from the UK but are on holiday in Estonia. Otherwise will take the caravan to the south of France where we have our holiday every year and leave it there. He asked whether there really are places where to leave the caravan. I said yes, the storage. Me and my son then went to order the food that looked so good. There was a semi-open BBQ counter where he ordered meat as he does not get it often. I had some vegetable dish. After I really wanted to fo to the toilet. I couldn't find one although there were so many. I was so desperate and opened one door where it had the disabled wheelchair sign on but something else written in Estonian. Not a toilet sign. I really needed to go.

I was in a crowd of people and the job application process was going on. There was a lot of talk about it being in three "processes". The first one took a very long time and then we got to the second stage but it was really confusing about what I need to do in order to be considered. There was still another round left but it seemed so far away.

Me, my son and ex-partner were in my childhood home for a visit. I was watering the garden. We then heard that Justin Bieber came and I was worried he wants to hurt us. I wanted to go into my secret hiding place in the house and old my son, but he refused,  went to another room instead to dig out my old belongings. I begged him and shouted at him but he wouldn't. We heard him coming up the stairs and asked, "what is this room?" regarding the room, we were in. I tried to climb up the storage area and found some old children's surfboards, thinking of how we can use them for our next holiday. I then went back to the garden and carried on watering it and we noticed one of the watering hose's came from next doors garden. It was open and water running out, we tried to put it back from under the fence. The lawn was recovering fro the dry spell and the grass was starting to grow back. Suddenly my babysitter was there and told me about the patch where some plants were growing that its "Weetabix" that is growing there. I said that I never saw Weetabix grow and it's great.
