I was walking around a home that was a mix of my childhood home and my current home. I walked around and saw different rooms and thought of extra places where I could make beds for people if they were visiting. The floors were wooden and light in color just like in my childhood home. Then I somehow got together with my good friend and her stepdaughter as well as her son. Her son was being looked after by her ex-husband and he did something detrimental for him. The stepdaughters told her about it laughing and were glad he got in trouble.

I was in a forest that was dark and had scorched earth. There was a darl small lake or more like a pond. IN the middle of the lake there was a hole. Inside there was a person but it wasn't a real person, it was "personified" Twitter. It was like a ghost that tries to get people to stay on Twitter and influences them badly. It occasionally gets out of the whole in the water to fly around and to get people. I was near the lake and looked from the trees, trying to get away from the ghost. I was so scared and seeing the ghost get another victim, but I was also reassured as I could hardly fell the victim for understanding the ghost for what it was and therefore not so much of a danger for me.

I was living in a big historic building that looked like my old high school building. In the garden, there was a summerhouse for a Russian gangster where e was murdered. The house was mashed into rubbles of wood and covered with snow. Journalists and the public came to see the house as the guy was famous and asked me all sorts of questions about it. I had only read about it in the newspaper myself and didn't know what to say. I was worried whether it's safe for me to go out of the house and opened the large grand doors to peek outside. Somehow my old lecturer from uni was involved in it and now in a lot of trouble. He asked me for help.

Some men need to put the scaffolding up inside a room but are unable to for several days as the room is filled with disposable nappies for refugee kids. It feels like they come back every day and are unable to do the job. And it feels like this has been going on for a long time. I can see the scaffolding really clearly as well as the plain packets of nappies but I can't see the faces of people. Then the hot water tank starts to make a lot of noise, I am aware that I am still dreaming and I am a little worried that it will explode. Then after a while, it stops.
I was in a log badly lit corridor and was going to in front of my regulatory body for fitness to practice hearing. feeling paralysed by fear and shock. shady dark colors.

someone was preparing a meal which involved adding a snake (skinned) to a pot of other cooking ingredients.  A woman from my Spanish conversation group seemed to be doing the cooking.  I was observing the scene, rather than actually present.

The setting was a meal, a banquet, really, and the main guest was Ernest Hemingway, although it wasn't actually EH, but someone pretending (claiming?) to be him.  There was lots of food.  It was a boisterous occasion.

I was watching a television programme.   It was hosted by pop star and writer, Jarvis Cocker.   He was choosing record albums and talking about them (identifying themes, what he liked about them), and then invited 3 guests to talk about each album in turn.   I didn't recognise either the albums or the guests.

I was with a male friend in a house which was similar to the small terraced house in which I grew up in the 50s and 60s.  One of his daughters was there.  I used the toilet which was little more than a cupboard. Then he and I were on a tortuous journey to catch a flight from Heathrow Airport.  It looked like we were going to miss the flight and when we arrived at the check-in desk (which we couldn't find at first), there was no-one there.  When someone appeared, she was doubtful that we would be able to get on the flight.  But she changed here mind after my friend spoke to her.  I started to look for my passport in a capacious inside pocket of a white raincoat I was wearing.  I couldn't find it, but the check-in clerk had it and handed it to me with my boarding pass, My friend and I embarked on a tortuous journey, on foot, to the boarding gate.  I had to go back and clarify the directions with the check-in clerk.  The route involved walking up an ordinary street with houses and turning left.  Then we were in a kind of corridor off which escalators rose.  We got on one and were in a bus station, but our bus had left.

My wife and I seemed to be going on holiday.  We were at some sort of check-in place and we dropped off 2 cabin-size bags.  I was bothered about why we'd done this as we walked away towards somewhere. Then we were on a bus, perhaps being taken to a terminal for a flight, with other people. I felt that we had another larger bag in the hold of the bus, and that was also bothering me.  When the bus drew to a halt, I stood up immediately, but that didn't seem to be the right thing to do so I sat down again.  A man two seats in front of us stood up so everyone else, including me, did the same.

I was in a pub, meeting a male friend I used to work with many years ago.  He said I was half an hour late (it was 17:00 and I should have been there at 16:30, he said).  We bought a pint of beer each.  A woman appeared.  I used to work with her, but never knew her very well.  She started to seduce me.  I was unsure.  We seemed to meet up again later.
my Mum.  She was in some sort of hospital.  I went into a room and saw her in bed.  She smiled at me.  And then started to get up.  I was pleased.

There was a party where lots of my daughter's old school friends were, plus some parents - and me. Then I was in a university and found my way to the library where my daughter was with friends. She wasn't pleased to see me and then spoke loudly - out of place in a library. Next I was sat on the very front row at a football match (seemed to be Anfield where Liverpool play) - no barrier between me and the pitch. My daughter arrived and sat on my knee which didn't seem right - she should have had her own seat. The referee blew for half-time when Liverpool were about to take a corner kick and the crowd behind the goal to my left were not pleased and surged forward.

I was on a coast, possibly in northern England, with a group of my friends.  There was a fish and chip shop.  We had to walk along the coast, rocky and right next to the sea,  We cut inland and my friend, Bob, who likes to do this kind of thing, guided us to the fish and chip shop using his mobile phone.  When we got there, we had to decide whether to have large or small portions.  We all lined up to have a photo taken - I was next to Bob's wife, and had my arm around her.  The scene switched to sitting down at tables, eating the food.

I was at my creative writing group in a room I didn't recognise.  I seemed to be the centre of attention.  I hadn't done any preparation/writing and I kept getting my papers mixed up.  I was asked to read other people's writing..  As I was about to read one piece, my legs started to bleed and some blood dripped onto the bag of one of the women,  She was angry.  I told her to soak it in cold water.  She seemed ok then.

I was in what felt like an official building and seemed to be in Eastern Europe. I was in a queue to show my passport, but people kept pushing in front of me (you had to wait until one of the officials was free - they were sitting behind windows).  My wife was in a different queue and was getting served. But when I eventually managed to push my way to a window, I hadn't got my bag containing the passports (I had my wife's as well).  I was angry and upset, and started complaining and described the bag as a small white one (it was like an suitcase-type make-up bag that my sister had when I was young).  It had lots of other travel things in it (books, maps - and sandwiches for the journey). I was very upset.  Then my wife appeared with the passports.  I was relieved. Then I found myself in an office where my wife's Spanish and Catalan language teacher was sitting with his feet up on a desk.  He had several carrier bags which it turned out contained all the contents of my bag, including the bag itself (which was a small canvas shoulder bag - blue, not white). He pointed to a nearby room with porters/messenger staff who he said gave him the bag.  My wife was also there with the sandwiches she'd made. The teacher said that someone had criticised one of the books in the bag,  Then I was suddenly in another situation where a woman.  She criticised the fact I had a book by David Lodge.  I wanted to defend him, but couldn't find the words.  I tried to say he had writtten a highly-regarded creative writing book.
I was in a theatre - it was at this time of Covid-19  We had to evacuate the theatre.  Outside, we were near the railway station in Sheffield.  I was on my own.  It was raining.
an ex-boss of mine featured, I was suddenly in a 'spy scenario'.  Myself and 3 colleagues were exposing a traitor.  We hatched a plan and then confronted the traitor.
A depot with a huge lorry and a not very successful conman trying to steal stuff. Later making food for a friend at home,

I was going to do a training session and I wanted to show a clip of a film, which I played in my forearm. It was about a work setting - a modern one as people could break off work and bop in a disco and 5he cleaners had little electric vehicles ton drive around in. The clip was very funny and illustrated perfectly what I wanted to show - that people at different levels were treated differently and that there were mostly women at the bottom. But it was in French without subtitles and I didn’t think the English speakers in my audience would understand it.
I was in Spain with a couple of women friends and we got friendly with Rod Stewart and went to his home which I had a key for .

I was clearing out the boot of my car to drive to work in Guildford. I was with my parents though Indon’t recall seeing them just being aware of their voices. I think I was leaving them things that belonged to them. There was a metal shopp8ng trolley which I said belonged to Joan. There was a sundae with whipped cream and red berries which looked perfect to eat but my dad said the sell-by date was before lockdown so I put it on the dashboard of my car to throw away later. My mum said ‘ aren’t you eating that, is it too big?’ ‘No,’I said ‘It’s too old”

I have been asked to participate in a choir and to play the piano accompaniment. I manage very well despite the fact that I haven’t played the piano since I gave up lessons at the age of 11. My brother who is a musician praises me saying he never realised I could play. I am surprised to and remember I was put off by a horrible music teacher.  Afterwards we are at a fair and I am on a stall selling alcoholic drinks with a friend and trying to work out how much to sell each drink for as we have a wide range of bottles ( not just wine but obscure things like eau de vie ). I suggest £1 for everything. A man comes up and asks if we have ever done money laundering training as he needs to train us.  Later I am at home with my father and I find an old camera which still has an undeveloped reel of film on it and there is a video on it of me and my boyfriend messing about.  I try to work out when it was taken - it was a long time ago as my hair was short and dark but I can’t see any other clues. I am surprised how dark my hair is.

I was returning home At nights from some where in London that I hadn’t been for a long time. There was a warehouse and the outer wall was completely covered in clock faces like an art installation. I said goodbye to my friends. They asked if I needed any help getting home.  I said ‘ No I would take the bus’ I knew the bus route and that it was direct. I started walking in one direction looking for a bus stop but there wasn’t one for ages and I was beginning to feel very tired and cursing myself for not having asked someone where the stop was. Then a realised I had veered offf to the right and was walking in a pedestrian area ( a bit like a promenade at the seaside with lots of people out enjoying themselves). There was a gate to the left that lead through a type of allotment. I asked a man if it lead back to the main road and he told me the name of the street it led to,

I was printing off etching plates - very large plates and three colours. I was trying to work very quickly as it was some type of competition and I was trying to get finished in a particular time frame. I had an assistant to help me but they didn’t really know what they were doing as they hadn’t prepared anything in advance. I used one plate by mistake and I thought that the result was quite interesting and I was using parts of plates using a newspaper stencil and I wondered if that was a pochoir technique as I don’t usually use it. I never saw the final prints - I could only imagine what they looked like.  Later on a university campus I was in a department with the engineering academics and they were planning to convert the basement into a large workshop with equipment so they could work after hours. They said they would put some art equipment for me. In too - like printing presses. It was going to be absolutely for staff only or it would change the atmosphere. I thought it was really interesting to Have a combineD space for artists and scientists like that and that I might learn some interesting skills. I thought I’d probably be the only woman using it.  Then I was wheeling my mother in a wheelchair as she was going to be an external examiner- she asked me what was wrong as the wheelchairwoukdn’t move but the whee was stuck in an enormous ball bearing. The staff member in charge was asking me if she could manage to put her responses in on a tablet if the letters were enlarged sufficiently as she was blind. I thought the letters would have to be very large.

I was in a hotel In a city on a work trip with 3 colleagues and we wanted to do something that evening. Somebody said it was difficult Because we had already done all the obvious things. One of the three said “I know it’s cheesy but I ‘d really like to see the William Tell chorus”. So we decided to get ready and do that. When he came out of his room my ex-colleague had an extremely short pair of shorts on which I thought weren’t really appropriate. We were also in a train station and I was trying to get a young boy to run down a platform shouting ‘train, train’ so we could film him but he didn’t understand what we wanted him to do.

My mother in my best friend died quite suddenly when I wasn’t there. Am talking to my best friend’s daughter about the funeral as I can’t go. my best friend is alive and with a group of patients who are complaining about her as they are having tto wait while the nurse brings her a second hot water bottle. I think they are being racist as she is black and they are all white. The nurse quietly tells them that my friend’s mother has just died and they are more sympathetic.

I was in a university and we needed another more comfortable chair and someone said I could swop an up rate chair for one of the comfortable chairs in the engineering staff room so I went over ( with someone) and there were some but I didn’t feel happy stopping them then and thought it was unfair to do it without checking with someone so Inwould come back later. There was a young Chinese couple (PhD students ? Very attractive). I was suspicious that they had done something I was at the other side of the campus and checking on a tablet about what was happening in the engineering staff room and saw 4 dots ( representing people);moving about and was convinced it was the Chinese couple fighting with another couple so sent the security staff to investigate. Followed after them but when we got to the staff room there was no sign of anything. The Chinese woman had left some make-up which I took as I thought she wouldn’t need it any more. I felt guilty for the make up and for setting the security staff on people who may have been innocent. Another woman ( PhD student? ) came in and said ‘ You’ll never guess what happened here”

I dreamed of my sister who died in 2003. In the dream she was alive, well and happy. She had a dog, who would often go and sleep next door, and a cat upstairs with a litter of kittens. The dog came home and was stretched out sunning himself in the garden, so Val went upstairs to get one of the kittens to show me. She came down with this dear little dark marmalade kitten, who was stretched out fast asleep across her chest. I was enchanted and moved over to stroke her. We both admired the dear little creature!

I was in bed covered by a duvet that had a French navy flecked with white cover. I thought it was quite striking. There was a woman standing above me wearing a wrap around dress in the same materiel. She gave me a small gift wrapped in the same fabric, but I can’t remember what the gift was. Then she appeared on the left hand side of the bed and gave me a bar of soap, also wrapped in the same fabric. My overall feeling was that it was a happy occasion.

I was with a female friend walking along a high street looking for a particular little shop. I knew  it was sandwiched between other larger shops as I had been here before. The previous time I had searched for ages, walking up and down and presumably passing it several times without finding it. That time I had found it eventually. On this occasion the same thing happened and I couldn’t find it again. Eventually I saw the item I was looking for but it was simply in another shop window not in a different shop. Then I was moving house. Another woman was with me and the removers had arrived. They were a friendly and efficient bunch and were engaged to do all the packing. Eventually the boss left them to continue. They were four young men who immediately starting flirting with us. I knew they would take all day to pack up the house, stay somewhere local overnight and drive off the next day. My friend was flirting back and I felt I ought to join in. It was clear this was going to lead to having sex with them. I was going along with it, albeit with misgivings. I then decided that I would have the courage to stand up to them and put a stop to it.

I had returned temporarily to a group I used to belong to. We were queuing somewhere for a meal. I knew that only the committee went to the front of the queue but chose to ‘forget’ it. No one said anything to me but I knew they were all aware. I got in and chose a table for two, reserving both places, for me and a friend, with my gloves on the table while I went in search of food. Everyone else tended to ignore us and I didn’t feel good, although I put on a don’t care attitude. I was in another place serving food, but there were no tables. A friend and I were singing excerpts from Mozart’s Requiem to ourselves. We came to a particularly beautiful and poignant movement but I couldn’t remember how the melody started. There was a piano and I knew that if I could hear the first few notes I’d be away. However, the piano was hidden under a lot of rubbish. Eventually the woman serving food stopped what she was doing and handed me a dustpan and brush, but they were very odd and not very efficient. I managed to clear the rubbish away though!

I was in France and arrived by train in a large city. My journey from the train station on foot is always a tortuous one and each time I worry that I won’t find my way to the city centre and back. This time I was looking for a CD and decided to stop at the first shop that sold them. My route, as usual, took me along a street with towering buildings, then up a steep flight of stairs. I put a sweet wrapper in a waste bin at the bottom of the stairs. Arriving at the top of the flight I found a shop that looked likely and went in.  The people, a man and a woman, were really helpful and friendly and we chatted away but I couldn’t remember the name of the CD I was looking for. I thought it might be by Bing Crosby or Frank Sinatra. We chatted for ages and they brought out all sorts of goods, including a doll’s house quite flimsily made and various pencils. We had been joined by Laurence, a friend from when I lived in France. It was lovely to see her again and I felt very happy. I didn’t buy anything, the shopkeepers congratulated me on my French and Laurence and I left the shop together. I was dying for the loo! I realised how happy I was to be back there and felt I should visit more often, and how lovely it was to practise my French once more and not lose the fluency.

I got on a train that was relatively empty. I had one large suitcase and two smaller bags, as well as a handbag. I put the three bags in a space between seats but didn’t sit. The train filled up very quickly and was crowded. I think it was an underground train as opposed to a main line. When it câme to my stop many people poured off, which prevented me going against the flow to retrieve my luggage. When the train had emptied a lot I went to get my bags, but couldn’t carry them all together. I picked up a smaller one, gave it to a young man by the doors, asked him to put it outside and to let the guard know that i was getting off. He put the bag outside and, as I approached the doors, they started closing. I called out and they half opened again but the train was slowly moving. People on the platform were telling me to jump, those in the train counselling against doing so. In any case, I decided I couldn’t jump safely with all the bags, so threw a smaller one out, but it landed on the track instead of the platform, where it was buffeted to and fro

We had taken Jack to College where he was starting today, only it became Bob who was there. There were 17 newcomer students. Lots of photos of the group were taken but I found it difficult to get a good group shot as they were strung out in a long line. Bob did his usual thing in a social situation of distancing himself from me, although I realised he would want to get to know fellow students. We walked to another part of the campus and I fell into step with a young woman who was most interesting and lively to chat to. We were joined by a young man whose back was sore as, he told us, he’d sat down abruptly the other day and injured his coccyx. But it was simply the connective tissue, he told us, and would eventually heal itself. I thought that he had clearly studied his Biology before coming to College! Then we were in a room with lots of other adults including senior staff of the College. Among them was a woman whom we had known when we lived in France. She came over and gave Bob the bisous, then turned to do the same to me. I moved back slightly and reminded her of social distancing, although the room was very crowded, and that we shouldn’t be doing the bisous. She shrugged good naturedly like it was no big deal. Typical of the French, I thought, where COVID numbers are rising and where we still have many good friends!

I was at home with another family member, a younger female I think, but this person is shadowy and indistinct. We are due at my son and daughter in law’s for dinner. It’s already time, 17.45, but I’m not dressed. As a stickler for punctuality I feel stressed. I quickly get dressed, am dying for a wee but somehow don’t have time. Put my make up on but my mouth feels furry as I haven’t cleaned my teeth. Quickly clean my teeth but then we have to go into town to get a lipstick. Dash into town, rush down the street, get to the shop and, without going in, I pull a lipstick out of my handbag and apply it. We are now 30 mins late and my companion is getting anxious too. We try to rush up the road to get the bus, but everything is in slow motion and an effort.

I was in a very large bed with two other people. They were both work colleagues and were at one end next to one another. I was at the other end so I was facing them. I was asleep but gradually became aware that the man was making advances to the woman. She responded to begin with but then thought better of it as she had a husband and children and withdrew. He was furious, it all got unpleasant and I was terribly embarrassed but couldn’t pretend I was still asleep. In the end she got out of bed and went to another bed in the room. He flounced up, got dressed and lit a cigarette. I asked him to go outside to smoke it. He was going to comply but she intervened, sat next to him, took the cigarette and held it in her own hand so that it was further away from me, and then they proceeded to have a discussion to try to resolve matters between them.

I was with a diverse group of people on a training day on Philosophy. We each had to choose an aspect of Philosophy to discuss and were assigned an individual tutor for an hour or so. We all waited in a big hall. Bob was claimed quite quickly by his, Professor Kersey, very renowned  , to discuss something which we all thought quite esoteric.  I waited and waited but my Mr Brand never showed up. The organisation was pretty chaotic and the organisers angry with us. I was pretty angry too at having a no show, but was told airily that his car had blown up in a gas explosion, but nobody had thought to inform me. There was one comedian student who led us all in a sing song, which was great fun. After much hanging around we gathered we had to reconvene in a hall somewhere, but it was a tortuous route disturbing other groups to find it. I was also with a group of about 6 youngsters. They wanted me to go to the shop and get them some paints. These paints were in bottles like ink bottles, so quite small. I tried to write each of their names and colours but was having real trouble holding my pen and forming the letters. The colours were: black, yellow, navy, and an assortment of all the colours. We set off but they became discontented with me as they reckoned we were going to the wrong shop.

I decide to take Toby for a walk in town where we were likely to meet other dogs. I was a bit nervous as he doesn’t relate well to other dogs. We were about to go down a narrow, dark alley when I saw that there was a dog and walker coming towards us. We stood to one side at the top of the alley and I kept Toby on a short lead. He pulled on the lead as they approached and showed too much interest in the other dog but didn’t bark like mad at the other dog, as he usually does. I felt pleased with him and felt that we were making progress with his behaviour.
I was preoccupied with Michael. I was trying to find out when the funeral was an who his extended family were.

I suddenly started thinking of me elderly mother and wondering how she was and how she was coping. I felt terribly guilty that I hadn’t thought about her during the pandemic but had been too busy taking care of myself. How was she coping with wearing a mask? How was she doing her shopping? I was just assuming that the neighbours were looking out for her. How could I be so selfish and uncaring?!

I was in a house somewhere and people kept coming and buying different supplies (notebooks etc) even though this wasn’t a shop. At one point a man wanted to buy some books and there was a library at the back of the house where we could take books and sell them. I was then lying down on the floor of the house with a friend of mine (male) and we were watching a cinema screen. A female friend then came along and lay next to us.

going to a lettings agent. It was on a hill and the building was on a corner with a glass front. I couldn’t see many people inside, but went in and asked whether they had found many places to live. A man gave me some gifts and possibly some info about some properties. I said I must go more often if they give me gifts. The agency was in Archway. walking down a hill away from the agency.

I was near my work (I work next to a large church) there was a glass building with an escalator in it. I was at the top of the escalator and a colleague was coming up it and we hugged and said it was nice we could hug again. I was then in the courtyard of the church. seeing the director and another colleague.
Robots and TV characters chasing me

I was running as a refugee, having to hide from people chasing after me. I managed to meet up with family on a train but authorities with weapons caught up with us. We ran into a forest and were then attacked by magical beings until the authorities caught up with us.
I was part of a group made up of friends/family and tv characters that were being chased by/fired upon by a group of people. We were being thoroughly overpowered and we were finding places to hide.
A large group of tanned, oiled, beautiful young people were mingling in a disco - sliding around and over each other.

I was standing in the middle of a country crossroads talking to a couple (male and female). A large quarry lorry came up the road and went past us and turned left. Then a tractor came up the same road but went right. The driver then started to lean back until he was driving the tractor horizontal. He then quickly picked up speed and drove away at high speed.  I gave the female a hug to say goodbye but it became sexual and we kissed. The sexuality remained as we crossed the road and we wanted to take it further. On the other side of the road was a gate leading to a large country house but I became aware I was dreaming.
I was in a large, light blue, 60's style American Cadillac - very shiny - and drove it into a room with a pool table. Someone shouted "Nice car, Geoff"
I was driving on a snowy mountain pass when it narrowed down to a thin strip and I couldn't go any further.

I was in the upstairs office of a police station, standing in front of a desk with the desk covered in single sheets of paper. On the right side was a particular pile of important papers. A woman came in and said it all had to be cleared away as it was untidy. I said that it was police work and all relevant. She started to pick up the pile of papers and I shouted at her to stop: that I'd had enough and was leaving her.

There was a telephone pole with the support wire covered in 3 or4 separate round protection sections made of straw. A BT operative was near the top, pulling himself up by straw straps attached to the round sections. I followed close behind as I was in charge of the job. We climbed down. Standing on the road I saw that we were below a motorway slip road and the operative showed me his telephone which showed the number plates of all the cars going past overhead - I showed him mine which did the same thing.

It was Christmas and I was in a busy department store. Each section had a person in charge of letting people in and out. A woman wearing a Nordic woollen hat with tassels, and a baby in a back carrier plus 2 other children asked me where something was. We became very attracted to each other and gradually mover closer until we were touching. I held her hand and it was a very pleasant feeling but she turned and walked away. Then I was coming down a crowded staircase when everyone came to a halt because there was a barrier at the bottom with no-one in charge of letting us out. So we all crashed the barrier. Next, I was in the street looking in a store window and I saw what I wanted to get my father for Christmas - a pair of red and green, tartan, waterproof, padded gloves. I went inside and decided I would get some for my mother as well but couldn't find the right department. Then I was outside with my partner and she said to get where we wanted to go we would have to wade through the river. I said no it was too deep, it would be over our heads. I said we will get the bus.

Decided I wanted to go to watch ice-skating. Cut a long strip of blue polythene to pay for the tickets.Thought I would wear my Parka as it would be cold but thought that the hood would block others view so wore my black woollen bobble hat instead. I could picture myself sat in the ice-rink.

I was at the bottom of a hill with a wheel barrow that I needed to take to the top of the hill. I went through a gate but the field was waterlogged. I tried to get round the flooded area but got wet feet. Next I woke up in a room and could hear voices outside - I look out and see a mayor in his robes addressing a crowd of villagers. I know I should be with them so don't want to be seen and duck down. They are discussing the village fete and I hear that I will be collecting donations. Then I am out in the street with people all around. A man with 2 children approaches and wants to give me money but I don't have any change. He says it doesn't matter and gives me a cheque for £15. Someone else gives me a £1 coin and then someone else does as well. I put the money in my shirt pocket. I walk past stalls looking for food. It gets very crowded with people having to squeeze past each other. Out in the road I see my eldest daughter with friends running a bric-a-brac stall. I ask where I can get food and they point all around but all the food is up-market and I am looking for something plain. I ask someone else and they show me a chippy. I go in and the owner is coming out with a pile of fish and chips. When he comes back I ask for fish and chips - he truns round and picks up a banana and a stick of celery. I shout no - fish and chips which he gives me. I go to a table and try to put salt on but it comes out fast and covers everything so I scrape it off. A man says it does that. 3 old men are sat round the table, very scruffy muttering Welsh.

I was in the lobby of an old fashioned hotel with lots of wood panelling. There were 2 lifts and a staircase to the right. I had read that I needed to do 15 minutes of running so decided to do it running around the corridors of the hotel. After I started I realised that there was someone running with me - an older woman. After 1 circuit it was not 15 minutes so I went again. When I got back there were several people milling about one of whom, Howard welcomed me. He said did I want to try Elaine's hat - it was a large floppy felt trilby but as I tried to put it on it flipped inside out. Elaine said "no, it goes like this" and put it on her head where it changed to a tight fitting latex skull cap in the shape of a mortar board. Next, she announced that she was having drinks on the 22nd but people started to say they couldn't make it but I thought I could.

I was in a hotel room with my daughter and granddaughter. I said it was time for me to go so I got my suitcase from on top of the wardrobe but it was heavier than expected. I opened it and there was another full bag inside. My mother said that I had left it on my last visit. I said that I would leave it again as I had enough to carry. My daughter took a phone call and said that it was alright as my other daughter had arrived safely in Italy. I started putting on my shoes which were like ballet slippers and bright yellow but with the lace area having a white background and covered in small coloured flowers. The laces were silk and also bright yellow. Than I tried to find my trousers but there was pile of trousers, all of them black but I found mine because I recognised the belt.

the first part of the dream involved booking in at an hotel. Next, I was in an airport where, by chance, I met an old friend from school (David). He suddenly went floppy and I stopped him falling to the floor. Then his sister appeared and we started walking down a corridor with other passengers but I was carrying him. When we got to the entrance. she asked me if I wanted a lift and I said yes. We went to an old Morris traveller and I put David in the back seat and she asked me to drive. I adjusted the driving seat which was too far back - I looked at her and thought she was not very tall for the driving position. Next, we were driving along a road close to where I was born and lived until I was 8. We then came to the railway station at Bush Hill Park but the whole road junction was much larger but with no road markings. I did a big U turn and headed back. Next we were driving by the end of my old road and asked if I could get out there. When I walked towards my house I realised that I was actually in a seaside town which was very crowded and all the hotels and pubs were heaving. I was looking for the hotel where I was staying but couldn't find it. Eventually, I found an old hotel but couldn't find reception. I went up and down different staircases and stopped at a bar and asked for reception. She told me that the bar was reception. I told her my name and and older man with a large hearing aid asked me a question but I couldn't understand him. He gave me a small, plastic covered card with the number 90 handwritten on it. I then went to the top of the hotel where room 90 was but there was a family in the room and blocking the doorway. I said this was my room but they said no - I looked at their card and it was a badly written 40 which I showed them and they went downstairs. Next. I was in the bar and asked for a Guinness and the bar staff asked if I wanted real ale. I said yes and she started to pour it but lost concentration and it overspilled. I took the beer onto a veranda overlooking the sea.

I was staying at a house in the country with a group of people who I didn't really know. I went outside and saw some young people in the woods lighting a fire but they weren't supposed to be there. Then I saw other people hanging around and a white horse lying down. I wandered away and there were 3 people playing with a tennis ball that they threw to me which I quickly returned - this went on for a few throws. Then I moved to a bigger group that included those I was supposed to be staying with who were also throwing a ball around. A large figure in grey arrived - Gandalf - but a ball hit him on the head and he collapsed. He was taken indoors. We all went in and gathered in a room when a Gandalf figure walked in but when he took off his cloak it wasn't Gandalf but a much shorter, fatter figure with a bald head - a bit like Phil Collins. He said something  and walked away and I followed.

I was desperate for a shit so found a toilet in a house. After, for some reason, I didn't have time to wipe my behind so stuffed toilet paper in my pants. Something missing here. Again, I needed the toilet but this time I am on the toilet when a man comes in - my father in law who I haven't seen for over 40 years and who has been dead for over 30. When I flush the toilet, it fills up almost to the brim. He tells me to get the plunger and clear it, which I do. Something missing here. Again, I am on the toilet when my mother calls out that there is a leak in a water pipe and she is going out. Somehow I am aware that she is going out with a girl shopping. I start taking up floorboards and there are a lot of pipes and some wetness. I go downstairs and I am in the house I grew up in until I was 8. When I go to go into the front room I know that it is full of elves, dressed in red and green, climbing over everything. But when I open the door there is a whoosh and I see nothing except an awareness that in the sky is a father Christmas type sleigh with all the elves on board. The room is empty of all the furniture. Again I start taking up floorboards when a young woman comes in who I don't know but I do know she is the sister of the girl who went out with my mum. She says she is training to be a plumber but I tell her I have called my friend. My friend, Rik, arrives but takes up a panel in the floor using a special screwdriver. When he looks at the pipes he says they'll all have to go

I was walking through a city inappropriately dressed in felt slippers, sloppy trousers and no shirt. I knew I had to find my way to White Hart Lane football stadium but wasn't sure of the way. I walked through a market and asked a couple in a cafe - he was a bit aggressive but told me anyway - go down there, then left and left again. Next, I was standing on a small hill overlooking the city but could not see the stadium. On my left was a father and son playing together and the son, fully clothed, slid a concrete path which was like a water chute. I carried on walking when I was stopped by 2 policemen and their dog - big, black and hairy - they let the dog go and he ran up to me and licked my face.

I was in Germany at my work place where I had been sent from England. It was a warehouse type building but more like a big empty church. I was with 2 colleagues who were making fun of me about something to do with my shoes. Our boss arrived. She was complaining that someone had spilt soup on her. Then we were standing together and she asked where my lunch was "Oh fuck" I said I've left it at home. She showed me the sleeve of her blue coat that had soup on it - I said "Don't expect me to lick it off". Then I went out to buy lunch but didn't have any money. So a woman and her son from work went with me carrying a red box and called on houses for donations using a phrase like Merry Christmas but it was something completely different. We crossed the road and went past a house where a woman was sat in an armchair facing an open window that was large and an up and over. By this time they had money in the box. I took some money and went to a corner shop but didn't know what to get but smelled cooking. I went to the other side and that was a sort of fast food shop but also a butchers. I only had coins in my hand and I wondered if I had enough but also wondered how they would explain that the donations were used for my food. The shop was small and very crowded - the counter was 3 sided with people all round. The woman next to me said "Wie viel?". Someone came to serve me - I said could i have chips please - she grunted yes. I asked for a small piece of meat too - she grunted no - what about a chop? - she showed me a piece of meat but it was very fatty so I asked for 2 sausages instead. I thought that the woman would have eggs at home so I could have sausage, egg and chips. Then I just waited but nothing happened.

It started in a workplace, possibly my old college with colleagues. I told them that I must do some shopping. I am carrying an old style blue supermarket basket. I buy a roll in a white paper bag and 2 other things also in white paper bags plus a tin of home brewing kit. I stop at a shop and put the basket down and go off, when I come back the basket has gone. I search on the floor and then in a greengrocer's shop where I think a woman has it but I am mistaken as I notice that several people have similar baskets. Next I have acquired 2 children - 1 a toddler who is a relative and a baby. We start to walk home, me carrying the baby. The toddler points out an owl on a garage roof but as I look I can see it is a small dog but then a large black dog comes running out of the house barking but we run into the street and it stops. Then the owner and 2 other members of the family come out and ask me what I was doing. I explain about the owl and he says yes there is a baby owl just hatched being looked after by the animal. We then start wandering away and after a time I realise that I don't know where I am although I do have a general idea of the direction we must go. We go along several streets - very normal terraced or semi-detached houses - I see some street names - one is Marchioness and the other 2 Latin words beginning with V written in unusual lettering and high up on a house wall. After a time the toddler starts to complain that her feet hurt and begins to cry. I sit her on a chair that is there and take off her shoes. I then take 3 pairs of shoes from my rucksack all boot like without laces. They are black leather. As I try to put one on I see that she has claws instead of nails that scrape on the inside of the boot. Finally, I get them on and we set off. We have to climb a fence and go through someones garden and come out at the top of a road where there is a large red brick building with lots of windows. I tell the child it was my old school.

I was cycling downhill on a very wide road but with no road markings but the bike was clapped out. Next, I was on the other side of town but cycling uphill and struggling.  Then I was in the flat of a family I know but the mum, Bethan, was not there. As I was leaving I noticed a small patch of what looked like oil by the front door. When I got to the ground floor I saw that there was a steady thin stream of oil  coming straight down. I texted Bethan and she replied that she knew about it and had told the landlady several times but she didn't do anything about it. At this point 2 men arrived and started wiping the oil but making a mess of it. Next, I was back in the city centre but all the road surface had been taken up, there were no road markings and traffic was coming from several directions. As pedestrians we didn't know which lot of traffic would come next. Finally, I crossed to the pavement and knew I had to get to the other side of town again but now there were new buildings and I didn't know how to get through. I went into a cafe and saw a friend, John, sitting with a stranger who seemed aggressive. We chatted for a while but then I tried to find my way out but finished up in the kitchen. I took a towel from a door and opened up the outside door which had a security number lock but was open. Outside a chef came after me and asked me what I was doing and I explained I was trying to find my way out.

I was in Spain and decided I had to park my green minivan out of the way. The best way would be to hang it in a river where it couldn't be seen. I drove looking for a gap in the fence and started to drive through but realised that the drop over the kerb was too much and stopped with the front wheels hanging over the edge. I got out and looked down to the river where I saw that it was much further down than I had realised and my rope would not have been long enough and that I wouldn't have been able to pull it back up again. Next, I thought I would catch a ferry so looked for the loading area. I drove in and thought I had the first spot but saw another car in loading bay 1. Then I saw another in bay 2 so went to what I assumed was bay 3. Some time passed and I wondered if I was in the right place when the first car drove off, followed by the second. I tried to follow but lost the way. I stopped the car alongside a lot of other parked cars and walked towards a large building with a big sign above saying AEROPORTO. In the building I asked someone if they had change for parking and they pulled a large quantity of 2ps out of their pocket.......

I came down the steps of an end of terrace Georgian house with a light green door. I went to the next house and decided to dig up a small, green succulent plant on their gatepost and replace it with a hyacinth. After I dug it out the door opens and a man asks what I think I am doing - so I tell him and he shuts the door. But I decide I need to explain so go and ring the doorbell which is an old style ivory press button inset into a carved circle in the stonework. The man opens the door - he has a friendly face and when I start to explain he insists I come in for a drink. However, in the background has been another man muttering angrily. Once the first man has gone into the house the other comes out and starts kicking at me but is very uncoordinated and his movements are amusing. I leave the house and walk down the road where 2 boys are kicking a football. One miskicks and it comes to me so I kick it back to the other.  I cross the road into a railway marshalling yard where there is a group of people who are squatting in the yard but someone shouts a warning and they roll out a sheet of canvas to direct a flood of water coming into the yard. This water then rolls away covering the tracks but avoiding the squat. I walk further in, past an engine without wheels placed on a platform. As I walk on I see a guard in a long blue coat with a yellow stripe in the collar obviously looking for people who shouldn't be there so I turn around back the way I have come but I see more guards to the left so head right towards a large open gate. However, 2 more guards come towards me and I start to run - one of the guards slips over which is funny - but I wonder if I have started running so fast too soon and will I make the gate.

I was in a field with 2 others and some more further away. We then started throwing something to each other but it became somewhat aggressive so I moved away when a red ball was thrown at me. More red balls appeared and I threw them at some girls who threw them back. We then all went into a small room and sat on the floor together, snuggling. Next I was in a refectory with the man from the field who was very unhappy about something. Food appeared on the table but water started coming up through the floor. Someone said it was because of the stuffed shark under the floor which then became visible. I went out of the room because I thought I knew how to stop the water although the caretaker was dealing with it.

I WAS DRIVING UP A NARROW LANE BETWEEN 2 HIGH, STONE WALLS WITH A SCHOOL ON THE RIGHT AND A DETACHED HOUSE ON THE LEFT. THERE WAS VERY LITTLE LEEWAY ON EITHER SIDE. THEN A CAR APPEARED OVER THE HUMP AT THE TOP AND I REALISED I WOULD HAVE TO REVERSE WHICH MADE ME NERVOUS BECAUSE OF HOW NARROW IT WAS.

I was in a classroom with a group of young boys - some I know, some strangers. I am trying to get them to complete a project they need for their qualification. One or two won't settle at all and then some older girls join us. They are frustrated by the boys behaviour but also start chatting. Things deteriorate until I send them all out and tell them to play tag - I nominate one of the girls as 'it'. They don't play but hang around while I have a cigarette in the porch of the college. The weather is dismal and older people are walking by towards the sea.

I am in my bed and I need to see the time but the alarm clock is not there. I look on the floor and it is there but broken - it is black. I worry about replacing it. The dream continued with my being in a different house but on my way out. Just after leaving I saw my daughter and a friend sat on a bench with a naked boy baby beside them on a white blanket. I went towards town but the next scene is immediately after. I came back but it was now very dark and I had trouble finding my key in my duffel bag. Next. I am inside the house but out in the back room. The house is in total dark but I need to find my way to the front but I know I must be careful of a large oblong pond in the middle of the room. I make my way to the door but hear a noise in the corridor which worries me so I decide to open the cupboard beside the door when a dreadful presence comes out and I scream and wake up although I also know my son is in the room on the other side.

I was on a football field but not in kit whereas all the other players were. They were all milling around the centre circle and I was between them and the goal but an opposing player left them and ran towards me and thundered the yellow ball into the net. Next, I was in the kit over near the right hand corner and the ball was kicked high in the air, it came down and hit my arm and went over the line. There was an argument among the players as to whether it was a corner or goal kick.
Scrabble tiles on a wooden stand SLAUGHTER which changes to LAUGH(S)TER
I squeezed into a room but there was a mattress standing on edge in the doorway which I went past

I was going to a spa resort for the day with my daughters. The building was a grand country house and we had to crawl through an ornate concrete arch in one of the garden walls of the country house in order to enter the spa. The arch was oval-shaped like a mirror and even the ridges around the opening resembled the frame of a mirror. What was beyond the opening was unclear. It was just a black space.

I’m in the local Post Office/shop and I’m at the counter buying two packets of sandwiches. I know the lady behind the counter. Outside there are tall, dark pine trees. I’m taking the sandwiches out of the wrappers, not to eat them, but to carry them like that. The sandwiches keep falling apart. I keep trying to hold them together, but all the fillings keep falling out.
I was sunbathing with my daughters by a pool, somewhere hot.

I’m with my daughters. We wait to receive the vaccine. There is a delay and the nurse tries to pass it off as nothing, but I realise from her expression that they’ve run out. We wait to be told that we have to go home.

I’d gone to my hairdresser the previous day for a trim, but was back in the salon again today for just a blow dry. As she was brushing out my hair, I noticed that she was cutting my hair again, when she’d not told me she was going to do that and had trimmed it the day before. When I questioned her, she said ‘it needs doing.’

I was at a venue, some of it was outdoors and some inside. It seemed to be a kind of restaurant and I was with a group of people, some of whom were my children i think, waiting for a couple to arrive. I seemed to be waiting a long time and kept going into the toilet and checking myself in the mirror as if I wanted to impress the man we were waiting for. I was dishevelled and my hair was messy for some reason. My clothes were not ideal, but I don't know why that was. Eventually, the couple arrived and the man seemed to morph from a person I had a fling with twenty-five years ago into a man I had an affair with in the last twelve months. The woman seemed unknown to me. We all sat and ate at a  large table.

I fled from a man, leaving him alone in my room. I don’t want to go back, but I don’t want to leave him alone in my room either. After some time, I return and suspect that he’s looked at some of my stuff. This man gives me the creeps and I just want him gone.

I was wearing white knee length socks that had become like plaster casts, then they started to disintegrate and became chalky. I was then trying to get to a place, but I was late and couldn't get there on time. I was becoming increasingly frustrated.

I was in the kitchen, stirring a big pot on the stove. It was full of minced meat and kept bubbling over. It smelled and looked unpleasant. My daughters, Rebekah and Sarah, were at the kitchen table, talking and chatting.

I notice something on one of my daughter’s legs. It’s halfway down the side of Rebekah’s left lower limb. It looks like a dark stain. I wash it and wash it, and even exfoliate it, but it won’t go away.

a photograph I took when my children were little and we were on holiday in Barbados with my mother. We were in a sea cave and the rocky entrance had been formed into the shape of an X. it reminded me of the Xs people painted on the doors of people who had plague.
I was on holiday with my daughters and there were lions prowling around us. I was scared of them, but also felt that they were vulnerable.
being on Mitcham Common

I am working as a part of team with the people from Borgen, the Danish political TV drama. I am not sure whether I am part of the staff attached to Birgitte or part of the TV news team. But it feels good to be part of a team, working together, each playing our part. like a snapshot in time.
I am with my late wife.  We witness a robbery taking place and are waiting for the right time to catch the robbers.  There is no conclusion.

I am in Leeds waiting to meet her at the central library which has been redesigned: to maximise circulation space, the books are kept on 'cliffs' of shelves rising up fifteen or more feet, and are accessible only by climbing and swinging on ropes hung from the ceiling.  Outside, in the Square, my wife has still not turned up so I go home. I drive through the once familiar Sheepscar gyratory system and see that it is being changed with new kerbs and lanes.  I enter the house to find her on the phone. She is talking to someone about a  'wheelchairing' holiday in the Cairngorms.

I am with my late wife and young son in a shopping centre. I go off somewhere on an errand but cannot find my way back to them. I wander through a seemingly endless variety of spaces, some below ground with flights of steps that lead nowhere. I meet strange people, in strange shops and cafes. I take in a variety of architectural detail as the scenes change rapidly - one scene is set in an orange brick cavern-like basement area with brick steps leading upwards but I don't know where - I am completely disoriented.
My late wife and I are working for a local authority housing department for reasons unknown and we are housing large families.  It all feels normal and natural .

I am in a criminal gang (my late wife is also a member and we are working together ).  We are planning a robbery and are given a boxful of woollen balaclavas or masks to choose from.  All are in two shades of blue. I choose the one that is supposed to look like me but it is not a great likeness.  There's another which is meant to look like Prince Charles.  But I am not sure which one is more like me.  The question is not resolved ...
I am discussing the death of a school friend - maybe my late wife.

I am painting and decorating a block of flats which are clad in black and white panels. The flats are located near a  wild piece of common land where I used to roam as a child.  I manage to finish the job.  I am not sure if my late wife is with me or whether I am on my own. But she is at least in he background, maybe at home.

I have volunteered to search for people who have an infection. But they won't let me go out to look because I am not able to cope with the technical side.  So I hang around in the office with nothing to do.  Then I am contacted by The Guardian newspaper about an article they want to write about me. I don't know why, though I am a little flattered. They assign the interview to a very young journalist called Joelinton but my wife wants them to send someone older and more experienced, she thinks that is what I warrant.  But I have no idea why they want to write about me. I haven't done anything much...

It is wartime and overhead I am in the street watching a dogfight between a Spitfire and a German plane which I can't identify.   Then I am indoors, in the house where my wife and I and family used to live. My wife is with me and we have friends with us. I don't know who they are. Outside in the street and on the drive people have gathered. I don't them either. They are all talking to each other, about what I don't know but I do know that we are all gathered to discuss town planning and are waiting for the guest speaker. Eventually she arrives. She is vaguely familiar but I can't place her.  She carries a briefcase.  I need to go to the toilet. It only has a curtain for privacy - no door -  and I am sitting there when the speaker pulls the curtain aside.  I am embarrassed and feel very vulnerable.

I am in London with my late wife and our two young children.  I don't know what we are doing there or where we are going.  There are crowds everywhere.  It is London as it was years ago.  We find ourselves in the East End in an area of picturesque decay.  I become separated from them and I want to photograph the local buildings and streets but  I have forgotten to bring my camera and cannot get my iphone out of my pocket.  Then I am back with my wife, but without the children, in a kind of wilderness.  I pick up a large stone and we see a strange lizard-like creature coloured white with elaborate lines of markings in blue the length of its body.  It is a salamander we decide but I am not sure. I try to take a picture but once again fail.

I am involved in planning a redevelopment scheme for an area of wartime anti-aircraft gun placements on the common near where I lived as a child.  This is a revamped plan and the new buildings are painted in camouflage.  My job is now to 'sell' the scheme to Ruth Bader Ginsburg the (now late) great US jurist and campaigner for women's rights who stand alongside my late wife. It feels good to be doing what I was trained to do, as a town planner, and I think I have done a good job on a worthwhile project.   But it has taken such a long time to obtain the necessary agreements and approvals.  If it all goes through I will have achieved a great deal.

My late wife and I are in bed together, I feel very secure - all is normal and safe.  We are living in our old house in Leeds. Earlier I was watching something happening outside from the bedroom bay window and making notes, in fact we are watching together.  But this is forgotten because we are involved in working, or testing, a method of measuring hugs and holding but it is too hard to do and we decide not the bother because we have taken a lodger, a soldier who we think should not be here. He is in hiding in our spare room, after acting as a whistleblower, making public government or military secrets. We become anxious for him and for ourselves.

I find myself in Stockport for some kind of course or conference which is cancelled while I am there. I think my wife is with me but cannot be sure. I need to get somewhere in the town but cannot find the place. I wander around and begin to marvel at the tall red ruined buildings which dominate the town. It is like a war zone. I want to take photographs. The streets and passageways are steep, some are just long flights of steps. I find I can rise fro the ground and float up and down these over the tops of crowds. I enter a large high roofed garage building and witness a man presenting his wife with a cherished registration plate on her car. I leave and enter another building and find myself in a kind of social gathering - community or social workers of some kind. Above the general hubbub of conversation rises the loud, dominant voice of a woman protesting on the phone to someone about being refused a grant to repair a community building. I try to find her to offer my assistance or at least to offer advice or impress her with my knowledge and experience. At last I see her across the room sitting at a table. But when I eventually reach her she stops talking and vanishes. The room is suddenly quiet: everyone is just eating cake.

I am in the middle of a big family showdown. I don't know what it's about though.  There is a large gathering of the clan. I am a member of the downtrodden side of the family. We are looked down on.  Something happened in Australia but it is not talked about, it is just part of the family's backstory and colours everyone's attitudes.  A scandal of some sort was exposed, with an element of criminality.  My wife and I leave and we end up waiting in a bus shelter for a bus that doesn't come.

I am in the process of looking for a university which will boost my results given enough money.  I think my late wife is with me but can't be sure, though I know somehow she supports me in this.   I know I am only mediocre and others might want to take me down a peg or two.   I am spending a lot of time on the computer and a lot of money on this.

My late wife and I are late for a song recital. We sneak in and find seats. We listen to a tenor with a rather weak voice singing a song called 'Heartland' by an English composer who may be Roger Quilter. It seems to be the last song of the evening but the audience claps halfheartedly and not for very long - the singer isn't very good. When the singer has disappeared, the audience chatters. One voice stands out above all the rest a few rows behind us. It is a loud, throaty voice and one with an astonishing depth and resonance - like that of the old actress Hermione Gingold or Dame Edith Evans as Lady Bracknell in 'The Importance of being Earnest'. I look round and see that the voice belongs to an eccentric-looking woman with a very large face and large nose - rather like a Leonardo caricature or the old film ans stage actor Roger Livesey. She wears a black dress with a lace collar almost like a ruff. She has tightly curled hair She is regaling her friends with her views. They seem to hold back from expressing an opinion. We leave the concert hall with everyone else, thoroughly disappointed with the evening.

I am in a big  ASDA store on the outskirts of Leeds.  I have gone there with my wife.   I am shopping for casual clothes and buy a lot, all in brown or cream colours.  While I am changing a man takes my new clothes and puts them in a plastic bag. I set of to find hm to thank him but cannot see him anywhere in the crowded store.  I find myself in a group of men taking about Christmas. I ask them if they have seen him or my clothes but they take no notice.  When I go back I find my bag of clothes has disappeared.  Then I can't find my way out of the store. I look for my phone to ring my wife but fail.   I look for her outside which is a vast grassy neglected wilderness . There are two old buildings in nearby, one seems to be a semi-derelict chapel, maybe a mausoleum, built of smooth blocks of stone in 18th century style.  Graffiti cover parts of the walls. It makes me sad that no-one cares for an historic building like this.  I am now lost...

I capture and arrest a suspected paedophile, a large man (larger than me), thick set. He is dressed in a brown suit and has short dark hair. He bears some resemblance to the actor David Morissey.  My late wife may be helping me.  I ask for help at a railways station to make sure he doesn't escape.

My late wife and I have bought a bigger flat and are in the process of redesigning it with a lot of expense.  It is part of an old mansion with a cobbled yard outside.  The main job is creating a huge lavishly equipped new bathroom in brown and cream.  Our old neighbours ,Jack and Edna, live in the adjoining flat and we seem to be competing with them in spending money and chasing perfection, though I feel embarrassed about this.  My wife stays at home while go to work and I come home to see the progress.  I am uneasy.  There seems to be some awkwardness between us.

I am wandering in a city. I don't know why. Am I looking for something or someone?  I come across the local BBC TV news presenter Roger Johnson speaking to camera amid squally and foggy weather.  A battle is taking place on film and he is explaining what is going on. I don't understand.

an image of a row of early 19th century terrace houses with flat roofs in Bermondsey, London. It appeared almost as if painted by the surrealist artist Chirico: clean in yellow grey London brick, and in an impossibly clean and empty street with no people. There were no other buildings around the terrace.

I need to give a Christmas card to old schoolmate Tony Wallis and set off walking from my second childhood home in London but suddenly find myself in Newcastle and in the offices where I started work after university.  But my little office is empty and all my possessions, including my large wall map,  have disappeared. I ask one of the the staff where I am supposed to work but he just shrugs.  So I try to find a working space in the large open office but get lost going from floor to floor in what is now a large complex of floors and escalators.

It is World War 2. I am trying to teach soldiers how to email their messages and calls for assistance. They don't understand what I am talking about. In fact most of them give up and don't bother to attend the classes. Eventually someone tries to blow the classroom up.

I am on holiday at the seaside with my late wife. A man has joined us: I don't know him but his friendship is innocent. We go for walks. We arrive at an area of the seashore with areas of wet sand around a kind of lagoon. The wet parts may be quicksand and we know to avoid them. There are ducks on the water and a man starts to shoot them with a double-barrelled shotgun. He is American. He is only intent on slaughter and goes for the ducks which have become stuck in the wet sand, shooting them at close range. We are angry and shout to try to stop him but he just grins at us. We run away.

I am in Mitcham Fair Green , walking to meet someone who will cash  money. I have to abide by 24 hour time. I get this wrong but will still get to give them a cheque, though I will have to wait for 24 hours to get the cash.  Meanwhile my Aunt Eva is trying to learn to count sheep and our shed is rotting.
I sensed that my late wife was lying in bed alongside me, followed immediately by the realisation, with acute disappointment, that she was not there and never would be.

I am in some kind of work situation with a bunch of women.  They are mocking me for my ambitions towards them. I leave as soon as I can but am then lost in the building and wander into an arts complex looking for my wife but never find her.  I am dazed and confused with a bruised ego.

My bicycle has broken - it refuses to move. I take it to be repaired.  But I hear nothing for a very long time. So in the end I call to find out if it has been fixed.  But a very stern and intimidating woman at the door refuses to let me in or tell me so I take the bike back. It has not been mended.  I don't know what to do.
There’s a group of us. We are making our way through huge drifts of snow. They look like a gigantic dessert of ice and sponge. Some of the snow is stained brownish.

There’s a group of us. We are children. We are walking over the ice round the corner at the gates of St Anne’s. I slide over the cobbles. It’s fun. As we reach the road, my sister Annette runs across, in front of a car but timing it just right. I follow but haven’t got enough time and have to wait in the middle as a car approaches. Does the car pass or does it wait for me to cross in front of it? I can’t remember but I make it to the other side in one piece. As I look back over my shoulder, my other sister Lizzie is shaking her head at me. There’s more. I think someone has a toy or a doll that we look at, but I can’t quite remember. I’m wearing an anorak.

I was listening to my son practise the organ. But we were in a church-like place, with heavy brown wood everywhere. It was early in the morning, very early and someone (a man) was leading the practice, or was it an audition? Then I was told to go back to bed and come back later, but I couldn’t sleep as the sun was rising. I was in an uncomfortable single bed and I had the impression people were near at hand and couldn’t relax, and thought I was missing something I should be there for. I think there was a woman there too. Both the people were older and might be some people I need to contact, both of whom are connected with the Church. Then I was helping my son fill out an online form. We were indoors but then suddenly I was outdoors looking at a big display screen about the size of a bus stop advert, which was self-populating with large blocks of colour to represent buildings in a space viewed from above. Then the blocks got labels and each one was labelled with the name of a country. the Philippines.   And then we were back indoors and I was filling in an online form on my laptop, only not for my son this time, who was doing the same thing but his father/my partner was helping him and he was looking over his father’s shoulder. We were in a bedroom, like a hotel room, and kind of sitting up on the bed, and I was wearing a top or T shirt and some knickers with my laptop on my lap. There were lamps on. The form was some kind of application and I was doing it for another boy, not my son, but it was hard because it was all in a language I don’t speak. There was a text box to fill in with a list of something and at the top of the box was a word meaning HOME or RESIDENCE, but then a tick box at the bottom, and when I ticked it the page reformatted to have two text boxes forming two columns, and one was HOME and one was WORK (both  in a language I don’t know) - the word for work was something like ERZATT. I thought the boy whose form it was should probably do the form filling for himself because it would require detail I didn’t know, or because it was looking like a large job I shouldn’t have to make time for, or was just a drag. And I wondered if my son’s form was needing the same level of detail and what should go in the boxes, and then I remembered for work he had some churches he’s played the organ for and they could go in there if we could remember them all.

I was talking to someone about their art studio. It seems it was based in a local GP surgery. In my mind’s eye I could see they were able to go swimming there as well. I wondered if it was my GP as it seemed familiar and then I remembered that I actually had been allowed to store a lot of the stuff from my studio in the basement at my GP’s. One of them had said I could and so I had, even though the rest of them probably didn’t approve. I realised that it must all still be there as I’d forgotten to retrieve it all when I moved in to my current, larger place. I wondered if it would still be there and if I should go there and sort it all out, but I wasn’t sure whether I should bother. The person I was talking to said I might be able to take their studio over. We looked for an ad about it in a local magazine, which actually has become defunct but she had the next couple of issues that would have been published if it had kept going. One wasn’t bound and the pages were just held together in an unglued bundle, and the other I’m not sure, but it was unfinished in some respect. There were articles about artists that would never be published, which seemed sad although I was secretly satisfied. I started to head over to my GP surgery, but instead went to her studio and the entrance seemed to be on the edge of a car park. It was dark as it was very much in shadow, whereas it had been sunny where I was before. I managed to scoot through the door as it was closing, but changed my mind at the last minute and scooted back out again.

I went to the doctor, who gave me a portable geiger counter. It seemed a perfectly normal thing to do at the time. I went home and showed the others. While we were talking, a stray cat miaowed outside the front door and I opened it and encouraged it in. It was small and tawny brown with white patches. I tried to pick it up and held it quite firmly as I didn’t want it to run off into the house and be hard to find. It looked a bit unkempt, as if it might have fleas. It didn’t want to be held and twisted its head to bite me on the hand. So I put it down back outside the front door and went back in. The house had changed and was huge and had big doorways and archways. There was a lot of wood panelling in a light, warm coloured wood, and drapery in plain warm colours - yellows and oranges mainly. My partner and I went into one of the rooms to check my radiation levels with the geiger counter. It registered a high reading and I thought I should tell the doctor when I took it back in to give back. Then I noticed that the bag of pink liquid attached to it had punctured and some had come out on my hand. It had the consistency of liquid soap. I wondered if it was toxic and kept checking my hand but nothing bad seemed to happen. I went looking for something and found myself on a large landing. The doors from my bedroom on to it were tall wooden double doors and I couldn’t get them to close properly behind me. I realised that the landing was actually a public place with entrances to restaurants and so on, and people were coming and going, so it was all the more important to get my doors to shut although I soon forgot about them as it felt like I was in Italy and I was pleased about that.

My son W had been off school, perhaps he’d had an appointment, and he had to go in late. I think he was feeling unwell or perhaps had been off so long it all felt unfamiliar, as he was a bit clingy and wanted me to go in with him. He was still primary age, and when I went in with him, I realised it was my old junior school, although much updated. R, my partner was there too. Was he a teacher? While I was there, I noticed one class, form 3, was without a teacher. They seemed to be short staffed. It turned out that their regular teacher was on a course on Thursdays. I offered to another teacher that I could keep an eye on them if she liked. I said I was there to keep an eye on my own son anyway, and so I could just bring in some work to do on Thursdays and do it there, so the class had someone to turn to if needed. She accepted and said they would pay me, but then asked if I was OK to be paid in Sainsbury’s coupons. I laughed and said no, because I don’t shop there, and she said that was OK. I said it would come in handy to top up the scholarship my son was applying for but then I said I shouldn’t count on that as he hadn’t won it yet. It seemed to be a kind of free class session, where the kids could do as they wanted within reason, but I said I would prepare a lesson session and people could listen and join in if it was interesting and amuse themselves quietly if they weren’t interested. I said next Thursday was the feast of the assumption and I would do a session about this and the children could chip in about festivals in their own religion and how they celebrate. I also remembered from my own time at the school that teachers were expected to read to the children while they ate their lunch and wondered whether I should continue with the book their regular teacher was reading them or whether they should have a different Thursday book. In the end I settled on a Thursday book but can’t remember what it was. I never did manage to get any work done, as the kids wanted to chat and ask questions, which I enjoyed. I had a huge wooden musical instrument case with me, and they wanted to look inside and try the instruments, which was OK. One girl, who I recognise from real life, was really musical and played everything one by one. One instrument was a gigantic type of saxophone and I told her that even though it was made of brass, it was a woodwind instrument, and I saw a parent, a black man, nodding approvingly out of the corner of my eye. He asked me when I began to sing, which I didn’t really and there had been no mention of, and I said I had a lot of different hats, and that I had worked in technical theatre when I first left school. I started to explain I am now a writer and artist, and was going to mention singing just so he didn’t feel embarrassed to have got it wrong, but he wasn’t really listening anymore so I stopped. I thought how true it is that people are not really interested in others. Eventually I packed my things up. The room was such a mess and the cleaners had come in and were waxing the floor. I asked if the kids should put their chairs on the tables, like in my day, but they said no, no one does that anymore. There were pencils and pens here, there and everywhere and I decided to bring a large biscuit tin in next week to gather them all into at the end of the session. I gathered as many in my hand as I could and put them on the front desk. We all gradually shuffled towards the exit and I saw my partner again. He said my son was outside the front of the building and I saw him, but then I remembered that I hadn’t gone to the front main room for assembly. It was very much as I remembered it but emptier and painted white. When I got there, I realised that I counted as a teacher now, not a pupil like last time I had been to assembly in that room, so I sat on one of the chairs on one side, instead of on the floor. I hoped we would sing some hymns but it was more of an informal gathering with announcements etc. I had teachers on either side of me and they were friendly.
