I explained I was just covering one day a week for form 3. I said I had been a pupil here myself. They asked if I had been there in Mrs B’s day and I said yes, I remembered her well. They said she is dead now, and I said yes, I know, I nearly went to her funeral but didn’t in the end because of something. One of them said I must have been born in the 70s and I said no, I’m older than I look, I was born in the 60s, but then I admitted she was very close as I was born right at the end of the 60s. She said she was born in the 30s and I laughed because she looked nowhere near that old, but she insisted it was true. She asked me which teachers I remembered, and I mentioned Mrs H and Mrs T, who had got cross because I marked her white jumper with pencil by accident once. She was very firm with me all the time and I disliked her, but I recognise now that it was because she saw my potential and wanted me to reach it. We started to file out of the room, I had loads of bags to carry and two jumpers, which kept falling out of my arms, which was annoying. On my way out, I went into form 2, which I remembered well, although it had changed a bit. There was still a huge plan chest in one corner, which had held big pictures of biblical scenes used for morning prayers, but when I looked they had been replaced with educational posters from the 1950s. I looked to see if the venetian windows were still there but they had been replaced with frosted glass. I realised it was time to go and went back through the cloakroom to the exit to find my son.

My partner R and I were on a journey in Scotland, which we broke to take some clothes shopping back for a refund. I had a skirt and R had a suit. At the door to the store, there were escalators going up to the shop floor. We realised that we had forgotten our masks but I thought it would be OK and they would probably still serve us. R said they wouldn’t. I said I’d go first and he should watch me and then copy. I took mine in. Inside there were lots of people without masks, so I could have got away with it but then I came up with the idea of pulling the polo neck of my jumper up over my nose. I queued at a counter. The girl who served me was Chinese or Thai. I asked for a refund for my skirt, saying it was too small. The girl asked me to repeat myself and I said, ‘I was going to say it’s too small, but actually it’s also too big.’ She offered me 10% of my money back, which I thought was cheeky, so I just said, ‘I’d like a refund’ again, but then I started wondering if I was actually entitled to one as there was nothing faulty about the skirt. But she agreed to a refund. When I got back out, R was nowhere to be seen. I saw a lot of men in a beer tent watching a screen where football was about to start. I pushed my way through the crowd to find him. He’d swapped his suit for a case of beer and he’d had it all and was drunk and slurring. He wasn’t wearing a mask, which was stupid and he hadn’t organised his refund. I told him we were leaving but it was hard work to get him to move as he was so drunk.

I went to a parents meeting at school for my youngest son. I was cross because my partner was supposed to be there too but he hadn’t turned up. It was cold, I think there was snow on the ground. We waited in a big hall with child sized seats set out in clusters. My son’s workbooks were there to look at but I didn’t because I was too angry with my partner to concentrate. I was waiting to see the headteacher, not the class teacher. She had someone else with her. I waited and waited and eventually my partner did turn up but we had to wait some more. Our appointment was 4.30 and eventually when it was 6.15, I could see that we would be next, but I wasn’t sure I had time to wait any longer.

I was having an interview for a gardening position. It was at a place where I have previously flunked an interview in real life. They asked me to entertain a group of small children with a puppet made out of twine and some bits and pieces. I wondered what it had to do with the gardening work. I saw myself as if in a mirror or on film and realised for the first time how incredibly fat I am, that my stomach looks as though I am still pregnant and it’s completely obvious that my breasts are different sizes, which I had thought was not that noticeable.

I was shopping in Waitrose. It was busy and only two checkouts were open so there were long queues. They were going to close soon and it was dim as half the lights had been turned off. I joined a queue and eventually was second in the queue. I didn’t want to get my stuff out of my basket yet because since coronavirus we aren’t meant to get too close to the person in front. Just as I started to, I remembered that my middle son wanted boursin cheese and I had forgotten it. I knew I would have to go back and lose my place in the queue. I said ‘Shit’ really loudly but did leave the queue and go to the cheese aisle, only to find it was almost completely destocked. There were a couple of things I didn’t want in one fridge but all the other fridges had coverings pulled down over them and were empty. I walked up and down to check the cheese wasn’t in a different place and found that the whole supermarket was being reorganised, which is why they were closing early and hassling people to leave. I realised I wouldn’t get my boursin now and that I’d left my place in the queue for nothing.

We were taken hostage by Nazis. We disguised ourselves by wearing their uniforms. There was one man in charge and I had to make sure my hands were hidden, as if he had seen them they would have given me away. I managed to do that successfully. We were hidden under the floorboards of an old building, possibly a church. I was handcuffed to a man who was dressed in the same uniform but I wasn’t sure if he was a real Nazi or one of us dressed as one. Because of all of this, the kids missed their piano lesson and I was worried their teacher would phone or text to check up on us, because if my phone made a noise it would give us away.

My youngest son T filled a hot tub with water in the corner of the living room and then turned on the jacuzzi feature so all the water bubbled up and spilled over the side and all over the carpet. It was coloured red, green and white, like the Italian flag. I shouted at him to turn it off and clean up the mess. Everybody acted like I was being completely unreasonable.

There’s a boy with some siblings, brothers. He is killing them with poisoned eyeglasses and chasing them through the sky. Eventually the chased ones die, and are left charred. The winning brother gets higher, stronger, faster. Gradually the siblings are replaced with other ones, one each from Germany, Spain and Italy. When they’re all dead too, he turns on me. I avoid him and gradually he gets weaker. When everybody is weak, it all begins again from the beginning.

I had a friend I was communicating with by email. But there was something about her that my partner didn't like or disapproved of. There was nothing sexual about it but it seems like there was an agreement emails would only be sent from an account that he also had access to. But for some reason I broke that agreement, again, not for any very awful reason but just because of some kind of practical issue, like I was at a computer other than my own and a different, simpler email address was what came to mind. I felt guilty and anxious about being caught, even though I hadn't really done anything wrong.  The light was very clear. It feels like there was snow on the ground.

there was a ballet dancer and the message was that it was ok not to do the reports (these seemed to be performance reports and something to do with Covid-19). My Mum was not pleased I was going to my Dads and there was this ongoing theme that it was ok not to do the reports.

I was with my sister and another woman at Loe Beach. The water was like a canal. The woman had lost something and I was trying to help her - I'm not sure if we were in the water.  My sister was in the background I think and wanting me to leave.

my work colleague and setting up a Microsoft team meeting online. I think my husband Simon was also in the dream and we were both trying to work out with Darren how to join an online meeting - I think I was feeling anxious
The image of a slice of bread with damson jam and cheese.
Going to bed with three other people. Wanting to stay close to my wife however.

I am going to an academic conference of some sort in Finland. Everything goes smoothly, including at one point travelling on an underground system which was clean and well-lit - even when the train goes through tunnels. The train can negotiate 90 degree bends somehow. We arrive at our destination and book into hotels etc as planned.

I am in London around Whitehall with some Quaker friends of mine. One - an elderly widower is looking for somewhere for his wife to spend time and be able to sit down.  Then I enter somewhere - a small chamber - in the House of Lords. Very ornate formal building with people standing on ceremony. I'm not sure what I am doing here so leave.

My brother in law is driving us from London (where we are living) to Scotland or Northumbria in a coal lorry. He and I have different views on the roads to take. I suggest a road up the west of the country and he wants to go up the East.

A hyper-real sort of filmic image of men. A little like from the film Brief Encounters so in 40's clothing - suits and perhaps hats. I do not know who they are but they are incredibly real. I'm aware that I'm half awake and watching

I am having sex with a young woman who I don't know. She has firm almost rubbery nipples which are both arousing and curious. I am watching a kind of competition in which contestants are kneeling in rows on the ground in front of buckets of water. They put their faces close to the water with dead fish in their mouths. I am on a train station somewhere in London. Possibly South London as it is an overground station. It's bleak. When the train arrives it has old fashioned carriages and passengers reach out of the windows to open the door as the train comes to a halt. They hesitate to get off until an announcement is made however. I get on and try to find a seat. I'm anxious that the carriages are crowded and it is almost pitch dark. I reach out at one point to see if a seat is empty and touch the fur of a dog. I move towards a lighter and less crowded carriage although it is probably first class and I won't be entitled to be in it.

A woman with the wrinkly face of an elephant's backside is guiding us around some kind of furniture store which believes it is an art gallery. It's kind of repulsive as she is to us (my wife and I). The woman guide is very forceful and confidently upper class. We don't want to be shown around but have to put up with it until we are released. We are in a London road like Piccadilly which we cross within the store through a flyover cum walkway.  Later we are eating in a very expensive restaurant/bar. Each dish is about £20 and the menu specifies that it will charge £2.05 for each dish to be brought to our table. Again we feel intimidated.

My wife has unusually had a drink of wine mid-morning. She has to take a phone call from her daughter's father in law - a conservative man from Northern Ireland. She is unable to form a coherent sentence or word even just making mm and ah noises. At first she is amused but then slightly distressed. I am ashamed and take the phone from her to speak to him. We are by the roadside perhaps by some kind of attraction. A grotto or cave?
I am in the city of London. Walking around buildings like the 'olde Cheshire Cheese'. Small rooms. Oak beams. Ornate stairways. Somewhat haunted feeling

There are toddlers in some kind of rebirth contraptions fitted between their mothers legs. They have to squeeze through a small aperture in a rubbery material. It's traumatic and they are crying. It feels bordering on the abusive. Later I see my son as a toddler running between his mother's legs as she stands up. She has no knickers on and his hair brushes against her vagina. She laughs.

I am going to a conference on green eco theme in London with a friend Alison. I've done this (been to this conference's sessions) before so I decide to leave early. She is a bit offended.   Donald Trump is at the conference acting like a fool and being abused and laughed at. He is angry. around his midriff is a yellow balloon which is inflating. Like penis - like his ego - like his self. He is opposite of fool who lets go of his self. He is trying to pretend to be grown us and serious.
there were giant earthwork sculptures, large enough to have houses on. One of these was a tortoise. Also, felt very sexual in dream, but never quite able to reach orgasm

It has a vintage 1950 feel. A group of women had been exposed to radiation, so we gathered to decontaminate. Some time was spent bin a large, but shabby pool. A group of feral cats turned up, and we adopted them, then a group of Japanese ladies in fabulous 1950 vintage dress turned up and explained social distancing to us with Christmas cards on a piece of string.
being very satisfied with the work my son had done cutting the grass near our local shop. Also talking to an old school friend who had recently moved into a nearby Flat and was sweeping the grass

I had found someone else's diary and started writing in it myself. I was alternatively in a luxury hotel or an old neighbour's house. Kept switching between the two locations with no reason to it. Was some quite erotic writing in book. Ended up sitting on the roof of the bus reading book and eating sauerkraut and chocolate ice cream

I appeared to be watching and simultaneously starring in a new version of Pirates of the Carribbean. Was driving around in a pink land rover with my dad and his wife. We were watching the film on DVD., as well as floating in a pool on flamingo inflatables. I almost stole someone's dog when it jumped in the car

I was with my parents, but I was an adult. We were alternatively on holiday in Cornwall, or in a department store shortly before Christmas. For some reason, I was security. There were good meals and friends were talking about their weddings

I had opened a woman's 70s themed bar where women only could go to be nostalgic and dance. it was going well, and was also being used to film an episode of murder she wrote,  where people were choaked by a slushie machine freezing their innards. It starred William shatner.  Inbetween this, I was trying to catch a train and buy my baby son check flannel pyjamas

I had gone to see my best friend and her family. I remember going for a meal, shopping in the Body shop, I was disappointed that they had such a small range now and didn't buy anything. I remember smelling scented candles. At some point I went to the shop with her daughter, they would not accept cards. Her husband went to complain. We were driving in a car, she told me she was thinking of having an affair. Suddenly in a house with open patio doors, full of her work colleagues. Waiting for her return. They didn't speak to me and I played with a dog. She returned and apologized to them. I went home and to bed

Working in a large department store type shop. Lots of staff meetings and area manager coming down. Not really achieving anything, but did lend area manager old shoes and phone. Worried that I had old boyfriends text on phone. While atmosphere was a weird mixture of steam punk  and chintz

I was in my bed and feeling. afraid. Was holding my hand to comfort myself, when I realized it was a third hand belonging to an unknown entity. meeting y best friend in a very hipster cafe, where the owner was too busy to serve food, was just giving us ridiculous drinks. I then seemed to be baby sitting for my friend and her husband in a very rundown basement flat. On their return I went home, but left my handbag and was too worried to return for it as my partner wouldn't believe I had left it by mistake. The child I sat for told takes about me

Being returned home from a war. Arriving on big coaches. Was very scenic, more like a coach holiday. Was supposed to be given walking repatriation tour, but missed it. Me and my son and another man lost in small seaside town in dark. He found a pub and said" hope never to see you two again". Was annoyed because I didn't want to spend time with him, and he obviously thought I did.

Living in a house, with my partner and son. My partner had a friend who I was talking to in our car about music and listening to a remix tape he had done. My partner was glaring at me and I was afraid because I knew he would be angry I was talking to other people without him. I was wondering embarrassed and annoyed. For some reason I was in my pyjamas and with no make-up on.
My partner was clearing rubbish out of the flat. I was stressed out about wasting good wood and throwing out collectables
There were bags that needed to be delivered somewhere by me. But then the 'format' of them changed.   I think I was in New York, and then I became aware that the bags contained explosives.

I was at work. My manger got sacked and she had to explain in front of myself and a load of other people what she's done. She was crying.  Then I was working on something else - maybe for the government or something, and some one, a Japanese girl, was revealed to be a Russian spy. In another team there was a Chinese spy. This was really bad.

I was, or was training to become a life coach or therapist or something. I met James. He came to me for some coaching/ therapy, and then we went out to a nightclub and slept together afterwards.   During another 'coaching session', an angry American woman came in and told me I was doing it wrong. Everyone kept using this acronym that I understood, yet didn't know.
aurochs

walking on a country path. There was a wooden fence with a right-angle-bend in it; the path went around the outside of the fence, and there were tall grasses on the other side of the path.

Weavers, weaving classes, trying to find new premises. Giving a boy age 8 a certificate on stage; he was dressed in traditional costume with a round flat-topped cap, heavy silver necklaces, and patterned weave tunic belted over trousers. Sharing a candy bar with my husband.

trying to figure out how the Japanese Islands rifted from the continent pulling segments of the Eurasian continent with them. This was visualization of how to draw the maps accurately and where to position things in the past.

I was trying to solve the relationship problem from the episode of the TV program "Rita". It had just been revealed she was sleeping with an old flame while in a new relationship. tried out several scenarios what might happen next.

sitting around a large wooden table in a meeting with people I didn't know. Then cleaning up afterwards and separating out the trash into recyclables. Something about pushing a pram through an autumn scene.

Vegetables were going off because I had cooked dinner with a bag of kale bought on sale that was still fresh 11 days later and I had made salad the previous day with tomatoes that were so ripe that the skins were slipping off.

I was getting together an archaeological crew for a dig and trying to order some work shirts online but couldn't find anything suitable. So my dissertation supervisor ordered me a red and black checked wool shirt, a small men's size. When it arrived it was absolutely voluminous, coming down to my knees and the sleeves were about 10 inches wide. He also needed to write me a reference for a grant because I had little fieldwork, but I had compiled a crew to compensate for this. Meanwhile, I learned of a geological expedition that was taking place nearby and really wanted to go on that instead.
We were house hunting, when we got a phone call from a friend that her partner had been knifed to death at a house on the axial street of my hometown.

My husband and I were travelling around Scotland trying to recreate the trip we took years ago with a couple of our friends. He insisted we flew to Lair, which was a coastal city on the map he showed me. I told him we drove. We stayed in a Scottish hotel with a renovated room without a staircase.
the survey for this study I completed before dinner. I noted that you did not ask me whether I took cream and sugar in my coffee.

We were going to a concert with friends of ours living in a nearby city whom we have not seen for many months. The concert was being held up north in the castle area. We had to get there by bus, and I quizzed my friend very carefully about the bus times coming and going. When we arrived, we went into this room in the castle estate that was wholly unsuitable for a concert: it had a large wooden barrier across the middle that blocked the view from either side (kind of like a Japanese public bath); the conductor sat on top of it, and chairs were aligned to face it on both sides. There were already some orchestra members sitting in the chairs with their instruments but otherwise they were dressed in everyday clothes. So I sat next to one of them but was quickly moved to the back row, where other musicians were also sitting. This row had a lounge chair where I could sit with my feet out. My friend and I had to visit the loo and dispose of some things; we were directed across a large room to a door. In the loo my sister held up her panties and asked if she should wear them again today.

A friend took me up into the college library where she had a key. It was out-of-hours and no one was supposed to be there. But in fact there were students everywhere studying, and also students camped out on the floor so that you could hardly walk by. No tents, but all the students had tarps laid out with all their craftgoods on them; some were flint knappers and their stone tools were laid out as if for sale. We finally made it to a back bedroom where another Chinese colleague from Chicago joined us. It was getting very late, like 2am, and I was very tired. My friend ran a bath and put her foot into it because she had a sore foot. I desperately wanted to get in, and hinted that I would like to stay overnight. But she didn't respond, and my colleague left. So I followed him out and learned a new way into the library down a narrow passage into a train station. There was a train waiting, only two cars long, more like a tram, but I didn't know where it was going, in a city I'd never been before. But I got on anyway to see where it would take me. I was conflicted whether to send my sister a text explaining that I was out overnight but didn't want to wake her. By this time it was 3am, and I was hungry. So I got out a cutting board and green onions from my shopping bag and proceeded to start making a salad, cutting up the green onions into 1 cm lengths. But then I realized I didn't have a bowl with me, so I got out a pack of radishes and just ate them onion pieces and radishes by hand. This was all on the tram with people around me as I stood in the center aisle. When the tram finally stopped I got out, and the sun was shining brightly, resting on the horizon. The all-night sun. There was a beach outside the station and it was filled with college-age students in wetsuits. They looked like seals. It was a beautiful scene, but I didn't know what to do next. lots of angst.

My dream involved going somewhere with a group of people, but especially with my sister. There were empty boxes that were perhaps leftover from moving, and I was making sandwiches from baguettes, cut cross-wise and put into sandwich bags and packed into the boxes. But the boxes were dirty and had cobwebs hanging from them. When that task was done we went shopping and I visited a store of an archaeologist where I found a pistol I liked and had to buy some bullets from the shop-keeper. He had a small target area where I could test the pistol, but I didn't take that opportunity. Somewhere in the background were buses and houses. Also there was some anxiety whether I could find my sister again having gone off shopping on my own.

I was part of a ballet production with people I had attended university with 10 years ago and some current work colleagues. The uni friends were people I met through clubs and societies, not coursemates. I remember feeling that they looked familiar but I couldn't remember all their names.  I was in some sort of backstage role. I was watching a rehearsal from the audience position. There was a lot of chaos and noise. One of the costumes was a giant bird with enormous wings and real feathers. The wings were as wide as the dancer was tall. The feathers were dark brown like stained wood with lighter brown mottled patches. The female dancers walked everywhere on pointe, which confused me.  One person didn't like their role and wanted a different role but was told no by the director. I didn't recognise the director. The spurned cast member lay her head down on a train track that appeared across the stage area running from the rear of the stage to the front of the stage near the audience seats. There was a tunnel in the wall and a train was coming.  The cast member who lay on the tracks was short and had brown hair which was cut in a bob and pinned back on one side with hair pins. She wore a brown skirt suit with beige piping and I thought she looked old-fashioned. It was her character's costume.  The train came and ran through the theatre and then vanished. The person got up and was fine and walked down the tunnel.  I followed. We ended up inside an attic space looking through a peephole in the door at a ballet rehearsal. The performance was related to the Disney movie Frozen. There was a character in white who represented Elsa. She danced on pointe. There were two men in brown suits as costumes. They were the male characters from the film. There were about 20 ensemble cast members dressed as villagers in brown and purple and green colours.  The room we were in had oak beams and wood planks on the walls. The rehearsal room looked like a dance studio with mirrored walls and a nice wooden floor. I knew we were not meant to be watching the rehearsal.

I was with my wife's family including her sister and brother, her parents, her aunts and uncles and cousins. There were 14 of us in total. It was Christmas time and there was a big long dining table that would have accommodated all of us. The location was not a familiar one to me but I accepted that it was a house belonging to somebody in the family. It had a feeling of a castle with stone walls and tapestries hung on the walls. It was gloomy because the only light was from the fire and candles on the walls. We had to make buttonhole arrangements before we could go out. I was told this was a family tradition. I asked why we were doing this when we haven't done it before. The family insisted we've always done this. There was a shout that we needed more holly. There was actually no holly on the table and there hadn't been any the whole time. My mother in law was fussing about how could we forget the holly. Some holly was brought in from the garden. My wife's youngest cousin brought me a finished buttonhole and said I had to be the first to wear it. I didn't want to and I packed my bags to leave. The cousin had a strange look in his eye that I didn't trust. Then, I was at an underground train station. My extended family were there with me: my mum, my aunt and my cousins. I was aware that my Nan was also there but I didn't see her. Everyone had a ridiculous amount of luggage with them. I was exasperated that my family had packed so much. Everyone had at least two large suitcases and another bag with them. We were running late for a train. We had to try and get all of us and our bags to the platform. The entry barriers reminded me of the ones in the London underground. They were narrow and it was a struggle to get everyone's bags through. Some porters appeared with trolleys for the bags. We were all running down a tunnel corridor to get to the platform. I kept trying to get my mum to give me some of her cases to lighten her load but she wouldn't let me. When we got to the platform, the train was there. It was very plush and it had two levels like European trains. There were lots of people trying to get on. The seats looked like they were covered with blue velvet. The outside of the train was brown. It reminded me of a fancy old-style steam train I saw at Carlisle station once. It only looked like a steam train - I was aware it wasn't really a steam train. It didn't look like there would be room for us all to get on with all the bags. I turned away and put my hand in my jacket pocket. I felt a phone there that wasn't mine. It was really bulky and could fold in half like a flip-phone but it didn't look like anything I've seen in real life. It had rubberised corners that made it feel unpleasant for me to touch. I knew it wasn't my phone. I opened the flip-phone and tried to work out who it belonged to. A girl I knew from school walked by asking if anyone had seen her phone. I yelled out "Laura! Laura!", Trying to get her attention. It was too noisy in the station with all the people around. I kept yelling and the girl turned around. When I saw her face, I remembered that her name was Lindsay not Laura. I gave her the phone with my arm outstretched over everyone's heads. I told her that it had ended up in my pocket but I didn't know how. She handed me another phone in exchange and said it had ended up in her pocket. It wasn't my phone I opened Facebook on the new phone to see if there were pictures of the owner. It belonged to Alex. I yelled Alex's name and she was in the crowd. We tried to exchange phones because she had my phone but someone in the crowd slipped their phone into Alex's hand so I now had my phone and her phone, and she had a phone that wasn't hers. I looked at the person who pulled the switch with the phones and it was an old woman who looked homeless. She tried to take Alex's phone from me.i yelled out to Alex that she had the wrong phone. The person was scrabbling at my hand trying to take Alex's phone. I managed to get Alex's phone back to her at the same moment as the homeless woman triumphantly held up a SIM card and said she'd taken it from Alex's phone.

I was laid in a double bed beside a former boyfriend of mine. We were both wearing clothes and I was making sure not to touch him. I did not want to be there.  It was dark. I was confused as to why I was there. I didn't know how to get out of the room.  Then, a person came into the room. The person looked like the character Percy Weasley from the Harry Potter films. I understood that this was the ex-boyfriend's older brother.  Percy Weasley was looking for the ex and was surprised to see me. I couldn't explain why I was there.  I had to try and pack a suitcase in the dark so I could leave without leaving my things behind. Things included clothes and stationery items like pens and pencils. I was confused by the pencils in my suitcase of clothes. They didn't seem to fit. I wondered if I had packed my own case.

I was in a large building that reminded me of a shopping centre as it had white walls and very high ceilings. I was with my wife and her mum and dad. The location was not familiar to me.  There was an enormous pyramid in the centre of the space. The pyramid appeared to be made of firm foam covered in vinyl. The vinyl was red on the sides of the pyramid and blue on the cap. The pyramid had four sides and the top was cut off to create a platform. It reminded me of children's soft play equipment.   To reach the top of the pyramid, it was necessary to climb many flights of stairs. There were two staircases - one on each side of the pyramid. I chose one staircase and my wife and her parents chose the other.   I felt annoyed that they had chosen not to come with me and worried that they were annoyed with me for not coming with them.   After climbing the many flights of stairs slowly because my lungs had a problem and I couldn't breathe well enough to go any faster, I got to the top and found myself looking down at the top of the pyramid. I was about 2 flights of stairs (one storey) higher than the top of the pyramid and I then had to descend in order to get to the top. My wife and her parents arrived at the top of the pyramid at the same time as I did but their staircase finished level with the pyramid top.  The reason I had chosen the staircase I did was because it went directly up whereas the one they chose went down first. They told me so at the top.  The top of the pyramid was very large. The floor was made of a foam-padded vinyl (blue) grid with white netting in between. We had to crawl on our bellies to safely move across it.  There were white square pillars reaching up to the ceiling. There were four of them in the centre of the pyramid top, where there was no netting. Behind each pillar was a man with a black machine gun. I was scared.

I was at a cadet camp as a cadet but I think I was actually as old as I am now. My detachment (troop of cadets) were an absolute shambles. Very scruffy and not performing well at the assessed tasks. I recognised some of the cadets as people I had attended cadets with when I was a teenager. They seemed to be the same age as me. I did not have the feeling of being younger again.  The camp was a competition between lots of different detachments. I was annoyed with my detachment that they were performing so badly. I had returned to help them with this camp - I wasn't a regular member of the group. We wore camo pattern trousers and green woollen jumpers. Everyone had a shoulder patch called a brassard that displayed the badges of rank and achievements they had earned. None of my detachment had any badges.  Initially, we were all in tents in a field. Then, we were called to assemble at a main drill square which was surrounded by portakabin classroom spaces. The drill square was made of a concrete style material, like old pavements. It was dark grey and had a rough surface.  There was another detachment there who were all excellent. They were neatly turned out and had pristine uniforms and lots of badges.  One of the cadets from the other detachment saw me and recognised me. She was tall and naturally bright blonde. Her hair was in a bun. I recognised her. She greeted me like an old friend and I explained I'd come back to the detachment. She said she left that detachment to join the one she was currently in because they were so much better. She asked me what star level I had. I said I hadn't progressed from 1 star when I had been with the detachment previously. She was a 4 star and proudly showed me her badge. I congratulated her but privately felt jealous.  I went back to my detachment and they asked me why I was talking to the girl. I said I had trained her at my detachment before she left. I told them that I taught her how to march and now she was a 4 star.  We were told that there would be an inspection of our detachment meeting place as part of the competition camp. We rushed to get back there and tidy it. The space was in a shared building. On the way in, we passed my old Brownie leader and my old Sunday School teacher coming out. I greeted the Brownie leader with "hi" and the Sunday School teacher with "hello, Mrs Addison". The boys in the detachment mocked me for this.  Our old cadet leader was at the meeting space. I found him very creepy. He had missing teeth and I couldn't stop looking at them. His teeth were brownish yellow from smoking  The meeting space was a mess. I started telling people what to do. I told some boys to take the rubbish bins out and some to sweep the room. We had to go and collect some mugs from a shared kitchen. There were two older women in there. I think they were connected to the Sunday school. They tutted about us and complained among themselves about our untidiness and general unpleasantness.  The cadet leader told me that as I am a girl, I must be able to sew. He asked me to sew a cover out of white bin bags for a toilet door to prevent the inspector from seeing that the door had been damaged at the top. The door was made of chipboard covered in pale grey plastic and a large chunk of it had been ripped off to reveal the jagged chipboard inner.   I rummaged in a Danish biscuits sewing tin (a round metal tin that used to contain biscuits and now contains sewing supplies) for some white thread but could only find black. The boys mocked me. Then I found some beige thread and took that. I sat on a chair in the space between the toilet cubicles and the sinks and tried to sew the bin bags. I was angry that I had been told to do this job just because I am female.

I was in a big park area with lots of lush, green grass. There were no other people around. The park area was one big expanse of lawn with bushes around the edge marking a boundary. There was a brown 5-bar gate behind me. Through the gate was another field area with some round stones that looked like wheels.  Some of the wheels were as tall as me and some were up to my knee. The wheels were stood on edge as if ready for use. They were solid stone with a square hole cut from the middle as though for an axle.  I pushed one of the wheels to see what would happen. It was a gentle push. Somehow this caused all of the wheels to start moving. At least 5 wheels (4 as large as me and one small one) rolled into the grassy park area and toppled over to lay on their sides. I was worried about this and about disturbing all of the wheels.  Suddenly, I was in a house that reminded me of the house I grew up in. I was in the room that we had used as a dining room and I was overhearing a conversation between two unknown voices of unknown gender about how someone had toppled over the wheels in the park and the grass was going to die. I felt guilty and panicky and I was wracking my brains for a way to move these very heavy stones to undo the damage I had caused but I knew I couldn't lift the big ones up.
a house, like ours at home, but i was alone, then on my bike in the streets. Our house was joined to another, there was loud music playing from the other part of the house.

I was in an office of some kind. Apparently I was part of a team who provided changes to the design of the office, like a change of set design in a film. Walking through this office, it had been transformed into a kind of sixties baroque wallpaper with stripes, curtains and fittings. As I walked through I asked one of the people at a desk if they liked it. They expressed approval, as if they were used to and expecting change, as if we did it regularly.  I was in a cinema, watching a film with others. It felt like part of an event, or a festival. The difference was that the audience provided the musical soundtrack to the dialogue of the film. So as we sat there we would sing ro whistle tunes that we thought went with the action. Groups of people in the cinema would come up with different themes. A man sitting next to me was in sync with me, we sang together. As time went on, I ran out of inspiration, and talked to him, telling him I couldn't think of anything for this bit. He seemed to have more ideas and carried on singing.  I was somewhere with two of my former work colleagues. We were setting up to film. I was checking previous recordings we had made, of the Clash and Morrissey. I was playing back the music. Then i started worrying about where the files for these tracks were, and started searching the SD cards for them, but couldn't find them.

In an erotic scene there was a naked young woman. I picked her up, telling her she was as light as a feather. I was very pleased with myself that I could pick her up with such ease. I laid her on the bed, ready to perform cunnilingus on her.  I was in a cinema, watching an animated abstract film, full of vivid blue shapes morphing and changing. There was quite a few people in the cinema, one man with a lot of curly hair and a tall hat, which was getting in the way.  I was in a building with large offices, laying cable around the edges of the ceilings. I did this in a few rooms.  I was attending class at somewhere like Goldsmith's University. A band had played, there was a table in the room with a few of us standing around, confused and irritated that there was no teacher. I leafed through the papers on the desk, they were meticulous transcriptions of the guitar parts the band had played, which intrigued me as it is very unusual to have such detailed music scores for a rock band. There was somebody else there, a man, who gave the impression that we were close buddies on the course, and he started to wipe the bare white walls with his hand - there seemed to be some apprehension that we hadn't performed a task of setting up the room with our work. As he wiped his hand over the wall, it produced some kind of virtual art - bright blue 3D plastic shapes, small structures entwined in chains, which he spread over the wall. These then became part of the paintings, framed, which he covered the walls with quickly. We were impressed at his speed. This room sloped down to the far end, where the next class had now gathered. They, with their teacher, started to walk round the room looking at the paintings. There was now a walkway around the room, with glass partitions enclosing them as they walked around. I joined them, it was very crowded.  I was in the street with someone, in the city. I pushed a nondescript door, flush with the wall, so that you may not have noticed it, and entered, encouraging him to come with me. I was a member and this was a side door we could use. We went into a room, full of stuff on the floor. There were people setting up an exhibition. They said it wasn't open yet, but we could go into the next room and have a look. We entered the next room, where there were art installations. These were like long tree branches, artifical, with bright multi-coloured leaves and flowers attached to them. My companion found at the end of a branch a pair of spectacles and deduced that the idea was to put them on and did so. He urged me to do the same. I grasped a branch, trying to work my way along its length, through the thick foliage with some difficulty. I could see the spectacles at the end but they were tantalisingly out of reach.  An old friend of mine, Allan, who i haven't seen for years, came down to stay, as he used to. We were walking down Baker St and passed what looked like a shopfront, but was the entrance to a club, It was covered in light bulbs. I remarked to him that I remembered going to this club with him. He didn't see it, so we circled around to find it again. We couldn't see it at all. I tried to remember what it was called, but could only think of one called Shoom, which I knew it wasn't. As we turned round the next corner, going now in the opposite direction, the street ahead of us opened up into a large canyon, buildings and normal shops in the near foreground, blending into a mountainous landscape in the distance. We walked down the street, we thought is was some kind of art installation. The 'mountain' was clearly an artificial construction, purple with green shades and some red. We were delighted at this novel site, and proceeded down a walkway into the mountain where there were trees and clearings we gazed down upon. We were delighted.

I was in a town street called Eastgate, in Inverness, my home town. I was with some sinister men, one in a brown hat. For some reason I was compelled to be with them, though I felt very uncomfortable with them. We were walking down the street. Then I was in a car, driving, with them. The most sinister of them, in the  brown hat, was in the passenger seat. I kept asking him where we were going, he refused to answer, but pounded the dashboard with his fist. It was raining and the wipers were on. I kept going. We were in a city that I didn't know. It was full of foreboding. Then I was in a German city, driving on my own. I didn't know any directions, but I had to go to Dusseldorf. This was something to do with Ross, a friend of mine, although he wasn't there. Although I didn't know the way, I came to a central large junction, just followed the majority of cars, went round a corner off the junction, narrowly missing a protruding iron rail. I then saw signs to Dusseldorf, so was on the right road. Beside the road in this city centre flowed a huge, very wide river, which was sparkling and full of small, choppy waves. I felt exhilarated, suddenly it was going right. Later, I was on the river, in some kind of boat, looking at the city from the water.  I was then in the car, with my mother, driving on a road on the outskirts of Inverness. I was overtaking a car which kept going faster, so I had to increase speed to overtake. But then a roundabout came up, I braked but was going too fast to stop, or the brakes weren't very good. As I entered the roundabout, I caused a car coming round to brake, skid and turn round 180 degrees, causing it to crash. We were unhurt and not involved in the crash. I pulled away from the roundabout, wondering if I should stop, but carried on, thinking I have got away with it.

I was with an old friend Raymond. We were in a gift shop, maybe at a gallery or similar kind of place. We were looking for something for a friend of his two boys. We were either going to see them or had been there. In this gift shop I was going to buy two T shirts I saw which were white with black lettering on them, like headlines. I couldn't see exactly what they said. However Raymond decided to get them so I was mildly irritated that he had taken 'my' present, so I was looking around for what else there was. There only seemed to be books, like art books, which were unsuitable for young boys. The shop was busy.  We were then in a car, Raymond was driving. He was telling me a story about something that had happened to him. It was something serious, a close escape or similar. I just knew it was a serious incident. We parked in Queensgate, Inverness, my home town, after searching for a parking space. I could see other cars clearly jockeying for space. They all seemed to large vintage cars. I asked where this incident took place. He said, "near Leonard Cohen's grave". We are both music fans.  in my kitchen, Raymond is waiting for me, we have to go out. I am going to take something with me, something to drink. I search through these plastic bottles on the counter. One is full of green liquid, but turns out to be old and mouldy. I pour it away. The sink is full. Elsewhere on the counter are other plastic bottles, in bits, one sliced in two. I try to tidy up this mess.

I was with a producer I work with. he was getting married. It was at the Barbican. There was a lot of confusion and he seemed uncharacteristically confused and not in control. We were wondering what to do and he assumed I could help, although i couldn't.  Then I was looking at the tube map. A friend of his, an actor was leaving his job. There was a lot of talk about who would replace him, and I realised I was losing any prospect of future work.

there was three of us, all men, in an enclosed, maze like space of corridors and rooms, like a down-and-out hostel or low rent hotel. Something had happened, I think someone had been killed, and one of us was responsible. There was a feeling of doom, that we would be apprehended, as we wound our way through these corridors and rooms, with random people, all hostile, in them. We then emerged at the top of a metal fire escape, looking down over the city at night, the lights stretching out into the distance, gangs roaming, danger in the air. We realise we have got away with it, or escaped from the immediate danger, and descended the steps to ground level. Once on the street, we agreed to stick together and I remember someone clearly saying (me?) that we should stick together because no one person could stay alert 24 hours or even most of the time, to danger or attack from unknown directions or assailants. We agreed. I noticed one of my companions was tall, mixed race, braided hair with a hat, almost like a guy out of a film. I thought he was ok, but wasn't sure. A maverick. The overall feeling was a kind of helplessness, forbidding and dangerous, with gangs marauding in a post-apocalyptic landscape.

I was in West London, then I was in a small flat. I was waiting for a visit from my former girlfriend, who was the best person I ever met. She was bringing her family. I was in a room when there was knocking on the door. Just then, I needed to pee. For an unknown reason, I tried to pee in a box or something, then decided that wasn't a good idea, so peed in the sink. Then I went to the door and let her in, along with one of her kids.

I was hanging out with a small group of people (20-somethings, male & female) in a dodgy area. We were standing around on a small clearing with some grass nearly. It was dark and but there was still a little light in the sky. It felt like summertime - i didn't feel cold.  The leader of the group looked like he was near enough in age to me, was white with short blond hair. He was good looking. We were there to hang out and to shoot heroin but when I saw the syringe, I started to get scared.  I slipped away without anyone noticing me and pegged it down the main the road. It was fully nighttime now but I ran into a brightly lit Spar newsagent where 3 people in Spar uniforms were working behind the tills - 2 men and a woman. I asked the smallest staff member - a young lad the same height as me if I could just hang out in the shop for 20 minutes. I didn't want the gang to find me and I was worried they were close by - I don't think I said this to the staff. I just felt this fear.   The guy was friendly and said sure no problem and told me he'd do me one better, he'd give me a job- he motioned me to follow him. I'm in a dark room but then I'm at the till area. It's just me there so I started just messing around at the till trying to look busy . I was wearing a plain white t-shirt with a black cropped vest underneath it from H&M.  A voice starts to panic a bit and makes nervous jokes about how I'm not wearing proper uniform.  I go to the wings of the till area [ it felt I was standing in the wing of a stage almost] and it was quite dark but with a little light. Someone hands me an "official" Spar longsleeve top - it's black and red and is themed after 'The Simpsons'. I think it had a big Bart Simpson on it. I thought it was kind of cool. There are two other Simpsons-themed Spar tshirts lying about one - one is white and another is red. I think my boyfriend, J, would like them. I think about nicking them.

it felt like I was in a VR video game world.  It was a mix of first-person view and third-person. Mostly first-person.  I was a prince climbing on a dragon's tail and was trying to reach the top of its head. The dragon is flying high above the ground and I can see nothing but clouds. It's a really beautiful sight - the light of the sun makes the clouds a primrose yellow colour and there are some small slashes of blue sky in between them. They're fluffy and pastel. I'm just focused on killing the dragon.  I make it to the top and I jump up with my sword in both hands to kill the dragon by driving it into the skull.   The jump feels like I'm making a combo move in a video game, time even feels like it slows down a little. The view has switched from first-person to third-person - I see myself a little bit. I'm young and I have dark black hair. I make the kill. It just felt like a task I had to complete - I knew it was something I had to do.

I felt like I was in a video game world. I'm in a royal court with a prince. It feels like a live action version of Fire Emblem : Three Houses. The prince reminds me of the yellow house prince, Clyde.  He's really pleased with himself as he's won a war. I can sense that the court is filled with royal officials etc but I don't see anyone's face. I just know they're there. The room is bright and it has wood floors. They bring out this fancy glass box holding their greatest war celebration treasure - this box is huge. Turns out it's a massive copy of the movie Basic Instinct starring Sharon Stone on VHS. I'm immediately horrified. I want to get out of there ASAP  - I don't want to watch porn with these people.  I know it's just movie sex scenes but I just equated it to porn because I didn't know any of these people in the room. It would be a huge room filled with people and I would have to watch these dodgy sex scenes with them.  It felt like that same awkward panic when you realise a film or tv sex scene comes on when you're watching something with your mum. You're not sure whether to turn it off and pretend it didn't happen or just pray it's over soon.  The thought just made me so uncomfortable and I just wanted to book it out of there.

I am still in the video game world. it is completely in first person. I don't see any part of my body but the game in front of me.   There is this weird pudgy pink/purple dog in a wicker basket on a purpley-pink sludgy river. The dog is ginormous, fat and lumpy. The basket is floating in the river. I figure out the controls of the game and move the dog creature along the river. The game is pretty simple - as the dog moves along this river, items are falling out of the sky. You have to catch the cartoon roasted turkeys and avoid the gross orange cartoon sludge. I eat too much of the sludge and I lose the game. The dog creature's face makes an  X___X  expression and turns into an orange puddle. Game over.

I was part of a team of doctors and nurses from my own hospital sent to cover the intensive care unit at Another hospital that i had previously worked in. The patients were all young people that Some looked like they could be vampires. Turned out the usual staff were all hiding behind a Fold out screen In a secret area of the unit as they were scared and they said they didn,t want to work nights. They were very friendly and pleased to see me.   The dream started off with my colleague and i doing a ward round. We were picking up a lot of really odd practices and correcting them while wondering what on earth was going on on the unit.   Suddenly one of the vampires bit the tongue off another patient. We put the vampire back to bed and dealt with the non vampire patient,s bleeding. Put that patient to bed.   We continued the ward round and the tongue bitten off person started changing into a vampire. The vampires started Getting together and plotting to eat the doctors. At this point when they got out of bed to chase us we ran off and left by steam train. A vampire was on the top of it.

I went travelling to paraguay. I was walking around the locale and people were trying to sell my baked local delicacies from stalls. I turned a corner and the scenery changed from a south american  village to looking like a european city. I was very disappointed. It looked like austria. Then i saw my parents. They had decided to also go on holiday to paraguay at the same time. They then started dictating my schedule and Walked off expected me to follow them.

I was working in a hospital that looked like a cross between a nursery and a posh cafe inside. My registrar had been on overnight and the nurses fed back that he had not been answering his phone for calls.   They left feedback on a white board using stick on red felt shapes. The more felt shapes the bigger a picture formed, the worse he had been at answering his phone.   There was a massive picture on the whiteboard.   I had to sit him down and tell him he had a duty to answer his phone and it was dangerous for him not to.   He denied that he hadn’t been answering his phone. I showed him the picture and explained what it meant.

I went to wagamamas for dinner with some friends. A few people i worked with also walked in. I waved, they sat elsewhere.   I was trying to find out the name of a trainee who i wanted to cover a short gap in our rota. I rang up the secretaryand she couldn’t tell me. As I put the phone down i shouted angrily and loudly “why the f&£#” do we even have these people when they’re so f&£*ing useless!”. The person in charge of this trainee walked in at this point and heard me say that. I was very embarrassed.   They sat down opposite me on the long table i was sat on to talk about ghis. I was trying to explain who this person was and wasn’t makibg sense so i had to facebook the oerson and show them a picture. They recognised her and said she was on leave in london due to stress. Being looked after by her family so no she couldn’t help.   Then my boyfriend came to say goodbye. He seemed like a nice person but he was red in the face, greasy hair, thick nhs glasses, columbo mac and worn down rotten teeth with gingivitis. He smiled and i was repulsed. He wanted to kiss me goodbye and i touched my cheek to his. I could see that the people opposite me were thinking why is she with him. I was embarrassed of him. I tgen knocked my glass of vwine over the people opposite.   I went to the loo and some people in tgere Were saying i could do better and asked why I was with him. I said i couldn’t get anyone better. Then i looked in the mirror and i had a completely bald head and when i stood under tge celing lights i became translucent.   Then it came to going home. I went to my hotel as now i was in london. Got my stuff and left for waterloo station. Realised when i got there i’d left two bags. I had to run back and luckily they were there. Tge cleaner was about to go in my room.   At waterloo there were two options for getting to tge pkatform. I wanted to go one way which was less treacherous. The otger was steep and had a very fast escalator. My friemds were getting annoyed with me as tgey wanted to go the otger way.

i was living with a friend In a really nice townhouse and she was having a celebration. She invited her dad to the celebration who was a small grey haired man. He was very jolly. Slices of cake were being passed around. I took a few and they were huge. So i took a small corner off with my hand then gave them to someone else. I was able to try all of the cakes but not eat too much.
There were lots of little presents wrapped in gold paper stacked up in the corner of the sofa.
I was cooking in a very tall, black metal chimney-like structure, outside. It had lots of different sized apertures where different dishes could be cooked at different temperatures.
I, and other people, were covering racing cars up with fabric covers.

I was on holiday with three other people. I had two light bags. It was an old fashioned hotel, we went up grand, carved wooden stairs to first floor. There was a lift - silver metal doors. Two friends were shown into the room next to mine, and the third friend and me into ours. It was over full of furniture - single beds, sofa beds, tables and chests of drawers. The previous occupants possessions were still there. The hotel worker said they'd be gone soon. The window had a burgundy coloured blind, and looked out onto a cobbled courtyard filled with pots of colourful flowers.

I was cooking for myself and others in a very cluttered, disorganised kitchen. One electric ring burner on the cooker was dislodged, but still working. I was frying chicken, and adding chili flakes, salt and pepper. The fridge door was open - sparse contents.
I was driving around, needing to get to locations, dictated by a computer programme. Some venues closed before I got there.
I was poked in the eye with a stick, again

I was asked by the parents to look after their children at their home for a couple of days. seemed to take place mainly in the kitchen, and garden. There was a lot of rubbish and clothing on the floor. I used a rake to gather it up. I put the clothes in the washing machine, after taking out the damp clothes inside - a pink towelling dressing gown, and a couple of other things. I hung these out on the washing line in the garden. The washing machine was in front of a tumble dryer that seemed not to have easy access.  I put all the rubbish into large plastic bags. I felt pleased I caould see clean floor underneath. There were several episodes of cooking. There was a very large refrigerator in the kitchen, with freezer drawers underneath. I was cooking large quantities of broccoli and other greens, and some kind of roast meat. On another occasion I was making a cheese sauce, and looking for pudding ingredients. I came accross a supply of pins and needles with multicoloured heads. I started to sort them into differenent compartments, but the quantities seemed to expand, and they were slipping through my fingers. The parents returned, and weren't happy that the washing was on the line. They were pleased that dinner was ready.
I was poked in the eye with a stick.
myself and several others were putting masks on. Full face, fabric, with eyeholes. No sense of concern.
There was a new concrete gully near my house.I opened the car door as I went past, to let some liquid drain out.

I was sitting in the kitchen with my partner, his teenage son and my partner's divorced wife. My partner was refitting a strap to his Fitbit. I should've been at work, but thought I wouldn't be missed if I was a bit late. I poured another cup of coffee, but before I could drink it, my partner emptied some orange juice and chopped walnuts into it as he was tidying up. I chided him. I was searching for a notebook I needed, and got a rucksack ready to take with me. I was on a bus, and realised after a while that I'd gone past my stop. I spoke to the driver who tried to persuade me that I needed a different bus, but I decided that I would just stay on and go round the circular route again until my stop appeared on the display board. A phone in my work bag started ringing, and I knew it would be work asking where I was. It was now very late - about 3pm - and I used to start work at 08.30...

I was working a night shift at a place I volunteer - using a telephone and computer screen. A fellow volunteer was having problems using the equipment. The third volunteer was explaining it to her. She was struggling to understand. She was holding some sort of handheld controls, and I was trying to make the explanation simpler for her by reinforcing she needed to to something with her right hand, and something else with her left. She was repeating these instructions to herself, and sat down at my work station to put the instructions into operation - I was concerned as I had an ongoing call on the screen. I left them to it, and went into the other room, where I remembered I hadn't checked my temperature with the remote, digital thermometer before starting work. The other volunteer aimed it at my forehead, and said with dismay it was raised. I wasn't feeling unwell, so I asked by how much. he didn't tell me, but was very concerned that we would need to close the shift. and all go home for two weeks to isolate. I kept repeating that I wanted to know my temperature, and was looking in the diary for the official advice as to what upper limit was acceptable, but I couldn't find it. A number of smartly dressed women started drifting in, as if ready for a night out together (it was half one in the morning by now).

I was visiting ? an old childhood home. Myself and ? my nieces and nephew did some grocery shopping. My parents returned. My mother was unwell and went to bed to rest. I returned there the next day. The dining room table was covered with gift bags full of unwarapped Christmas presents - it was only early September.. I felt sad. I was cooking lunch - chicken. Later that day I was looking out of a downstairs window that had one-way glass. A stranger, a man with a mustache, was looking at the house and windows and writing things down on a piece of paper. I told him to go away. He said not doing anything wrong. I went out to speak to him - he was now a young woman. She was selling double glazing, and tried to persuade me to have mahogony frames. I declined as current double glazing OK, and not my house.

I was in a pub. My female friend was dressed in orange. She was tired and laid her head on my lap. We were walking along the street  - there were lots of dark coloured fruit, like damsons, scattered on the ground.

I was asked to visit former partner's home, now seemingly abandoned. There was a sink full of unwashed dishes, and insects on the floor.Some electrical equipment was switched on. A neighbour came to complain the house was unsafe. I invited her in via the kitchen porch.I blew out a small fire in a piece of electric equipment. I looked in a wardrobe (downstairs) - it was full of fancy, unworn clothing (women's and children's) with many repeats of same patterns in different designs.

I am out with people, driving places in the dark. We reach a spot on the edge of town. we have to get on a bus. I'm one of the last people to get on, and find a seat near the front because there aren't many left. Next to me is a man. We both realise that we're on public transport and need to put masks on, which we do. I notice many passengers haven't got masks on.

I am standing near the top of a hill. It's sunny and clear. I am looking out over wheat fields that are ready for harvest. There's a village on the hill. I live here. I talk to the man next to me. Looking over the fields down the hill.

I am moving between houses, staying different places, trying to not be found or trying to make sure someone doesn't find something I have in my bag. I am with someone - it varies between my husband and a friend. I each room I stay in I unpack & repack my bag. There is an outer pocket where a bunch of papers are contained. Eventually I need to catch a train, so I'm driven to a carpark where there is a queue. The person driving me says they can drop me closer to the station but that they might as well drop me at the end of the queue. Then I'm in an auditorium, with lots of seated people. We are here to listen to some musicians - singers and band. Possibly a boy band because the audience seem very young. After a bit the crowd runs down the aisles to be at the front, but the crowd is thinner than I expected. My husband and I move towards the front. Then a compare asks people to go back to their desks. I sit next to my friend, not where we originally sit. I check I still have my bag. I see that there's a school exercise book on the desk in front of me. I wonder where the student is who was sitting at this desk earlier. I expect to be told to move back to my original seat by the student who sat here earlier. But no-one comes. I look through the exercise book and can see handwriting and pictures. The pictures are coloured in with various colour highlighter pens - yellow, pink, orange and green.
Work is progressing. We are measuring something purple. Graphs are being produced.

I am in a house. I am running some form of workshops. In fours rooms are is a pair of people. They are working together on a task, paper is on the tables in each room. The rooms aren't offices, they look like dining rooms and family rooms. To help them getting ready for the task although they haven't finished the current task, I go into each room and tell the people that the next task involved drawing a sketch of themselves. That I don't want the instructions to surprise them because I know people can be surprised by that kind of request, because I know that I am. I leave a few small yellow post-it notes on each table, these are what the sketches need to be on, so the people can practice on these. One man tells me he can't draw. I tell him I can't either, so when I did this all I did was not attempt to draw accurately, but I stuck to what I can draw. I can't tell him the trick of the task - that all they need to do is a stick-person or an emoji style face or similar - I'm not allowed to tell them. I leave all the people in the rooms to finish their tasks. I gather with some other people, to get ready to go for a walk.

work feel. I was in a large group of people, most of who I didn't recognise. A couple I did recognise where from my school days and who I have not seen for years. The city felt French and there was a Charbonnel drink. I cycled between offices, and stowed my bike upstairs at the office. My bike is stick-like and grey. Below the office there are people inside a glass fronted room, gathering around something I can't see. I feel I may need to be there but that I will be too late to see whatever it is. I go upstairs. The room is wood floored, with arm chairs and lights on low. I go for the centre section and tell this to the person I'm with but who I can't see. I relax a bit because I can stow the stick

I am at work and the team I am part of decide to go and get lunch. The people I am with are am ix of people I have previously worked with. We walk about a mile through streets that are not that full, not with cars and not with people. The weather is warm. I get the impression we are in a city where people don't walk much. We get to the shop and everyone except me gets a coffee. I don't drink coffee so I go further into the shop to find a can of cold drink. It takes me a while. Eventually I pay for it electronically, as the cashier tells me they aren't doing cash. There is a leather square where I need to swipe my bank card. I go outside of the shop but can't see my colleagues and I assume they've gone. I start to walk back but as I don't know the city I'm not sure of the way. On the plus side, it was a fairly straight route for most of it. Eventually I get to where I need to turn off the road the shop is on and I turn left. But it's not the turning, it turns out that I've accidentally turned into someone's drive and little yard. A man tells me I'm not allowed there. I leave

I am with some other people. I can't see who they are. We are going from room to room. Then we get to one room where we wait for permission and the time to go to another building. Then it's time to go and we walk outside. I'm carrying a black bag. We file outside and walk to a field. Here is a driver of a motorised tri-cycle type vehicle. I am to ride a a passnegr on this. The driver helps me on, takes my bag and stows it hebind me knees. He has to show me how to flip down some peddles where my feet need to go. The peddles are shiny steel. I place my feet on them. The driver (a man) tells me I use the peddles to keep the bag safe. I hav eto keep the bag safe, I know that this is important. The driver also reassures me that he can keep the bag safe. The others I am with are in the vehicles behind this tri-cycle. We head off, driving out of a car pack. The road is more like a tarmacked track, with a strip of grass down the middle. The driver says that this is his favourite type of track. I am on my way to do something important for the legal profession.

I am wearing some sort of uniform, although I can't see what it looks like. I am with others and we are working together to count items. My role is to take the item and stack them. We talk whilst we do this, to help track progress. We all feel as if we are working towards something important.

I am in a car, in the back seats, and am wearing a new blue suit. Next to me is another lady, also dressed in a suit. I haven't worked with her before. She has neat hair. Someone is driving us to a town. I notice a whit dusty patch on the knee of my the trousers of my new suit and I try to brush it off. It doesn't completely vanish but if looks less obvious. The lady I'm sitting next to says that we're lucky there is no traffic. It is passed the rush hour. I reply that it depends on what shifts the factories are doing as the traffic builds when the shifts change and that rush hour can happen outside normal hours. We get to a T junction and turn and then carry on down an empty road, with trees down the sides.

I am with my husband in a house. We are cooking something for a pudding. The oven has a glass panel in the door and I can see the pudding cooking. The pudding explodes and cake mixture is splashed all over the oven. I am concerned that the little bits of mixture will catch fire and then set the oven on fire. I ask for help and my husband takes the pudding tin out of the oven, walks into the garden and swears because what he is holding is hot. Then we are driving through a village. We have lived here before. I comment that we are driving down a road I had never been down and that it is dd because the village only has two roads. The road is down hill, lined with houses. The road then opens up onto a plain.

I am in Aberdeen, in an office. I'm surrounded by ex-colleagues as I used to work for the w=company they work for. However, I don't know anyone because I used to work for a different division. We are all in a room and there is a buffet on two of the tables . There is bread, strudel, Chinese spring rolls, fruit, pizza. I eat a spring roll because I'm hungry but I'm not enjoying it. I feel uncomfortable. Then we are told to sit down. There are seats near the two tables and down the sides of the room in a horseshoe shape. I sit near the back and try not to be noticed, as I no longer work at this company. Some people swap seats, including me. Then three people walk into the centre and slide open a cupbaord door to start a presentation. Behind the door is a large sheet of wide cardboard and there is a hand-drawn map of the USA on it, with some sketches and postcodes. Then it's finished. Someone behind me says to someone else that next time their team draws a map of the USA they need to remember to not use their UK postcodes. I move to leave but an ex-colleague I worked with stops me and we chat about her trying to find a book. I say there might be a copy in my old desk as I could never be bothered to go back and retrieve it when I left. Another woman approaches me an tells me she is Corrine in a way that suggests I should know her.

I am in a park. There is lots of grass, and a lake. There is something going on. I can see a celebrity wearing gold trousers and a t-shirt. I think they are being filmed. She smiling and look happy. She falls backwards into the lake, and there is another celebrity already floating on his back in the lake. They talk to each other but I can't hear what they say, but it makes me think that they are both Australian. Then I am cutting my hear, in front of a mirror at home. I'm using clippers to clip the undercut of my hairstyle. It's difficult to do and get neat. I'm able to do the sides, and start the back.

I am in a living room in a house. My husband is there too. We are tidying up things, moving around between rooms. I pick up a plastic thing. It's a dark, olive green, with a moulded shape. I must have made a comment because my husband tells me it's the new laundry basket. He picks up the old laundry basket- also a dark green. It's rectangular. He holds it on one of the shorter edges and I can see the longer edges are broken. The baskets twists as the longer edges can't hold the shape. I notice that the new baskets is square and has a kind of double/corrugated structure.

I am in a place like Texas, cowboy country. I have flown there. With a colleague I am driven to a set of sheds. Here we are to get a taxis - except that we then decide to get separate taxis. I have to get a taxi to collect my team. We are following a spying book. I find the taxi driver I need to use. He has a moustache. The car is on ramps whilst he finishes some work on it. It's a customised, fat car with a V10 engine. I'm aware that the driver may not be someone I can trust. I am joined by the rest of my team. There are four of us. We all get in the car, and because of teh driver, there are three of us on the back seat. There are some hot pies to eat, except that they get trodden on. I show one of my team the spy book. Although it's a story, the pages seem to have a lot of geological diagrams. We remark that this is odd. Some of the diagrams are in colour. We drive down empty roads. I expect them to be wide and straight (we are in the USA), but they are twisty and narrow country lanes, and look more like the UK. We head towards the airport.
someone eating children, or children eating someone.

I was on my own at a concert. I think it was for the band Elbow. There were chairs laid out in rows, except it wasn’t a music venue. It felt more like a large church hall as it was bright and airy. The chairs were clustered together in the centre of the room, far away from the stage and walls of the room. I think I thought how they weren’t socially distanced, but I kind of knew it didn’t matter as this was a dream. They had side tables and it looked like on each there was either an arrangement of a small white flower or a box of tissues that had a tissue all puffed out. There was a man who came to talk to me, he was tall and had expressive eyes. We chatted and sat down. He told me he had just come back from Vietnam. I let him talk for a bit. I said a couple of things that we both laughed at. Although when I laughed I didn’t recognise my laugh, it sounded too relaxed and joyful. I started to talk about my trip to Vietnam, but he seemed to lose interest in me then. He got up and went over to talk to someone else.

I was away, with work but my partner had come with me for a mini holiday before the work started. We were staying in a hotel room with two other people. One, a woman I work with. Two, a character from the Sopranos. My partner left to go back home, but left me with all the luggage to carry. I had a shower. I fondled my breasts. I got ready for the day ahead but couldn’t find what I needed in all the luggage. The woman I worked with had a shower. The Sopranos character, shouted at her that they were going to be late. I was frustrated at having so much luggage.

I was sat outside in my car, except it was open as if I was in a bar, reading. Two people I vaguely recognised walked past, then turned and looked at me to suggest I was doing something stupid. I then remember an old friend from university (c. 20 years ago) coming to sit next to me on a wall. Our feet dangled. She leant her shoulder against mine and started humming a soft/soothing tune. I started crying.

we were building a new house, but it included a massive waterside space that was almost warehouse sized like a furniture store on a retail estate. I felt apprehensive and confused as we’ve said we’re never going to live next to water again. Inside the building was lots of different seating areas, benches, sofas, round tables, booths. I couldn’t work out how to make the inside into a home, and felt very overwhelmed.

I was in Ethiopia where I used to live when I was a young child, and some men were holding up a root system of something. The structure was like a tree without leaves and someone was taking a photo. The men were friendly and relaxed. Then I was digging and I realised I was making a mountain and a valley. It seemed like a huge realisation.

I was looking out over a landscape of tree stumps, birch trees. I felt a fraud because I was trying to reassure someone this wasn't very serious in the face of global ecological problems, but I didn't actually know.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: Richard and his girlfriend invited Finn out for their engagement/birthday celebration. I was giving them a lift.

Me, Jeremy and Finn were meeting/treating Dad and Judy to a picnic lunch in the tmiddle of a medieval town, but it was next to a bakery and all Judy and me wanted was to ear fruitcake and barabrith, not the picnic.
