Next to the picnic table was a dog poo bin that we thought (there was some ambiguity though) was a bin of buried potatoes in earth. After that Jeremy and my dad were talking about directions for travelling on somewhere else and Dad was pointing bakc the way he'd come through Caernarfon, but Jeremy knew that that way was less direct and he was too impatient to indulge my dad the way I would, or my siblings might, yet he couldn't be bothered to explain either.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: A few people in the dream. I think Sophie and Steven were in it and their friend, a young woman who I was supposed to be counselling. She was being haunted. Then she pointed behind me (and she became my sister, Nic) and there was Pete. He was brimming with amusement, but silent. I put my hand out and he was solid, so I thought for a moment that he can't have died and that I'd misremembered. But then, I knew he had died and this was his ghost. I felt as though I was yearning for someone, or something. I realised that the ghost was my own mind creation and that made me think about memory and thinking. I wondered if having a vivid /photographic and eidetic memory would diminish the need to think and reason clearly and if you couldn't remember very well, whether that would make you exercise logic and reasoning more. And I was thinking that Finn has poor reasoning skills, yet  has a detailed memory. The older he's become, the less he remembers and the more he reasons.

We're going to Fife to go house-viewing, where K lives. Before we go, we're in our house in Essex and there are lots of people (family and friends) who I'm telling we've decided to move to Fife, but J isn't happy. He says we're not decided, and I think why are we going all that way then? Usual kind of argument, me wanting decision, him not wanting to commit. Ruth and Chris have brought their friend to see our house and I feel a bit anxious that it isn't tidy or clean or up to R & C's standards, but also slightly miffed that they're eager to jump in before we're definitely selling up. S is solicitous towards me when she sees J has put his foot down and I really appreciate his kindness--nice to have some empathy. We stop overnight at my dad's in Wales, where he is busy packing to go to London to see his mum. Dad has all his bags packed ready to go and I see there are lots of Easter eggs, and I wonder if he's got some for us. He's upstairs and we're downstairs with all the bags around the floor. Then I hear snoring and see a body laid out on a blanket box under a blanket asleep. I call to ask Dad what's going on and Dad and Chabbo just roll their eyes and laugh about a drunken Ethiopian friend of theirs. It reminds me that Dad has a 'Just William' streak in him and only a part of him is prudish, fundamentalist Christian. I'm wondering whether to call K to let her know we're coming. I worry that she might not hear anyway, and also that she might not understand.

I was travelling through London suburbs in a car, driven by someone else, and on foot. I was with a young woman and her child and my buddhist friend, A, who was being egocentric and grumpy. He stopped answering my questions abruptly when I asked about his 'wellbeing'. We passed through strangers' empty houses as the doors were unlocked, and helped ourselves to tea, but didn't stop. We were continually moving. A feeling/sense of mild excitement as though we were on our way to a concert in the city. One garden was a beaded floor or bed coverlet decorated with a garden and I sprawled across it, letting my fingers graze the thousands of tiny beads. I told the young woman I would have loved this as a child more than a proper flower garden because I hated the earth and dirty things back then. The young woman was studying the same 2 A levels as me--French and Psychology--and we swapped email addresses so we could talk coursework. We were sitting on the pavement, not much sign of nature.

Me and J and F were at a literary weekend in London. the house was victorian, but had steam punk decor. the hostess thanked us for coming and we were about to leave when a man came in in a long, smart cashmere coat and hat and took J off by the elbow to talk about J going somewhere to do an interview. J agreed and told me he'd be going with the man--who knew J either through Uni or through Carcanet. They were going to H & M's flat not far up the road. I had just been talking about maybe having a dog after all...J had always wanted one and I was feeling indulgent..thnking about a short curly haired spaniel or something. After J had gone, I only half remembered the name of the the road where H & M lived and we had never been inside their London flat, so I wasn't confident to find my way. I also had a heavy, overstuffed travel bag, but I put my purse buried deep inside the bag inside rolled up clothes..afraid of being pick-pocketed in London. Me and F caught a bus and I was nervous about where to get off and swore at F who was being sulky and passive aggressive, sliding off and almost gettting lost in the crowd in the bus. Just as we were about to step off the bus, a tall middle-eastern man came up and very charmingly said I should get a purse. I wasn't sure if he meant handbag or money purse. He seemed concerned for me and F that we should be safe. We got off at a stop and I clutched at F's hand as though he were a 3 year old boy intead of a 6 foot young man. He was smart in a cream Burberry raincoat with a trilby hat, very gangster like. I also had a new cropped hairdo and a trilby hat. I wondered if we looked poor, but just dressed up to look rich and that was why the man had felt sorry for us. I also remembered that F had unusual way of behaving and maybe he had been pulling a face or something. We were looking for maps to find the street, but so far two of the bus stops didn't have a street map on them. It was a busy road with lots of lanes and tall, dark green doored buildings, like a terrace. No, actually that was the place I had in my mind that we were looking for. The street we were walking down was more commercial, and building was going on...scafolding to dodge and skips. I was very uptight with F and swore at him again, which upset him so he was angry but silently fuming and trying to just resist being held onto. I was imagining H & M's flat, worrying I would't recognise it, then I remembered H had died, and I was imagining poor M rattling about in his flat empty of H--all alone and sorting through her papers. H died in July, not of Covid, but cancer, but it felt related to Covid because M held a small family funeral and sent us the programme aftewards.

I dreamed I was trying to get in touch with Mum. She was in Paris on a trip with her French friends and Robin, and being cared for because of her Alzheimers. She was staying in a hotel. I could see her empty room that I was trying to call her in, so could see why she wasn't answering the phone...they hadn't brought Mum home come yet from their day out. I was anticipating talking with her and, as usual, trying to think how to modify my speech not to overwhelm her or confuse her. I was yearning to hear her softness--not her 'soft voice' because there was this sense I had of her not really existing, even though I was imagining how sh'ed spent her day and wondering whether she's be able to find the phone when she heard it ringing. I was also designing a toy box for her, a few wooden crates that would stack and be stored in the corner of her room. While I was waiting for her to come back,  I tidied up her suite and it was like her 'Wallace' as she called her house extension...full of too much furniture, like a furniture showroom.

I think I was with Finn and we were in the back of someone's car..either Est, Anita or even Mum's. We arrived at our destination and helped unpack car. Then we were in a sort of church hall type of room and doing fitness exercises following Alex's lead, But all of a sudden we realised his cheer was fake and he was being sarcastic. He started tearing into me and Finn for not being good team players and being uncooperative towards him --and for some reason he was our stepfather. I was shocked and became immediately placatory and soothing towards him, even though he was out of order. I wasn't scared, but I just could see how hurt he was. Yet I had these doubts that he should be leading us: he's always overcompensating for something and doesn't have real inner confidence, like my brother.

Babajun died and I was preparing for his funeral. The woman living nextdoor was a farmer and a teacher. I watched her out of Babajun's bedroom window as she gathered fallen branches in her tractor and piled them up. Then I was facing Judy to explain why I had borrowed her socks. She was unhappy that I'd left my warm toe prints in them. Then another woman was not prepared to share her special stones with me either (that we were going to bury in the ground with Babajun). I felt spurned, but remarkably unbothered by this. I was just trying to bounce everyone along and nudge them out of their petty irritations with me.  I found a semi-precious rock in my own collection and I was prevaricating about whether to bury it instead, sort of mild shame in being pragmatic about which rock would match the appropriate value of my feelings about Babajun. I wasn't very upset that he'd died. I was also mixing him up with Abdul. Next, I was in a classroom, about to watch a projected film on a green dresser. The teaching assistant was being pedantic and excessively tidy as she set the dresser up ready for the film. She was a cross between Ruth and a violinist we know in the choir. The farmer/teacher, who had some kind of status and whom everyone was edging around came to sit down and I was in her chair. I moved over for her, feeling as though whatever I did was going to be clumsy and socially inept, but I didn't really care. I felt a bit belligerent and mildly amused by everyone's pettiness.

I was child minding a baby for a man (a stranger) who seemed to be in mourning, but I was not very organised about it, just drifting from one activity to another without any sense of time and I felt ashamed that I wasn't giving the baby my full attention. I also had Finn who was a toddler. I kept coming up with silly ideas for the baby and Finn to do, like eating weird things and singing weird songs. I was kind of desperate and really wanted to be alone. Then I saw the sun was shining, so I took them out in the garden. The house wasn't my house and the garden was all rocks and paths--pretty dangerous for a baby and toddler. But then I saw a woodcock and it was carrying its baby in its beak. I ran indoors to tell the mourning man to come out and see (I think he had his own baby again by this time), but he was sitting rigid at the table opposite his father and his father was weeping. The mourning man was angry with his father and clearly wanted me to leave them alone. They were planning a funeral (I think it was the mother/wife of the pair). I didn't clear off, but hovered, thinking about trying to act as a bridge between them. I think the father wanted a proper funeral and the son wanted no service, but just a burial without guests/words. I realised my experience and my father's of Mum's death and funeral had been similar and seeing the weeping father, I felt guilty about not letting my father come to the burial, which was only attended by me and my siblings.

There was a strong sense of place, but not somewhere I recognised. It had flagstone floors and felt semi indoor/outdoor. It was reminiscent of St Nicholas Market but prettier. There were tiny brass rectangles in the floor and the second time I noticed them, someone had added a label 'mouse trap'. a wedding reception. having to solve a puzzle to get to the floor below. my partner appeared and starting talking to me about converting the lower floors and how they suited pools. I then saw a decorative, rectangular pool with dark green water. Like a sunken pool in a reception area, not a swimming pool.

I was in a function room, lie a social club - I didn't recognise the venue. The activity seemed to be a sort of video/ karaoke/ lip synch and on a screen I could see different family groups playing with guitars which were part of kit that had been provided. I don't think they were toys or inflatable guitars but they were caricature/ pointy angular gutars. my aunt Susie in the venue presenting slides of some sort on the monitors.  2 per screen,  they were visually attractive. Someone told me it was important to make the information appealing else the intended audience wouldn't absorb the educational messages.
The main motif was a graph of some sort showing a mountain shaped peak in figures. It referred to something financial. It didn't feel like I was in an office.

I found myself chatting to some women I didn't know, in an unfamiliar and low budget office. They e planned about their fundraising plans which involved asking hotels for donations. A hotel had told them it was against their rules to donate to clients and I was saying that I didn't think that was the case and making suggestions. We walked while we talked, to a photocopier. In the next scene, I was in a high street talking to a young man with a cap on backwards. He was trying not to be recognised because he was an actor. An older man came up to him and they had a heated exchange and then came to some sort of agreement. As the second man moved down the street he picked up half a brick and threw it at the young man. I chased down the street and made a sort of citizens arrest. He was lying in a door way while I sat on him and shouted for someone to get the police. The door of the doorway opened as he was shouting at me. The entrance was bare concrete with some rubbishy looking junk mail.

I spent time with an old friend who now lives in The Netherlands and caught up about our mutual friends. Then I arrived at a shared house with a key on a rope. Someone else was supposed to have arrived before me but there was no sign of them and I explained this to another friend, Julie. Julie is a friend from different friendship group. She demonstrated a new eye makeup product that did eyelashes and eyebrows with one swish. I played with it and she said I could have it as she was just about to start a new one. Janelle, another old friend, from another earlier friendship group also made an appearance but I can't remember much about her context.

The setting was a recognisable version of my current home. I found myself in the midst of hosting a party for colleagues but I'm not sure which ones. My sense was of not being prepared. I was wearing my gardening jeans and I'd put my bicycle up on the dining room table. I felt that the guests weren't gelling well and I wasn't sure if I'd put music on.

I was frying portions of white fish - prepared, squarish fillets not fish shaped. Its not something I have ever done. That lead to another repetitive task and then that morphed into being house guests in someone else's house. It wasn't a familiar house but I felt awkward and tried to keep out of the way of the friends getting ready for work. Then our hosts became clear as friends Dave & Lou although it wasn't how their house looks in reality. Then the sense of waiting for them to go to work so we - my partner and I, could relax and get our stuff together changed. Some other friends I didn't know were also staying and the rolled up quilt we'd slept in went  ack under the sofa bed and some suggestion that the friends sleep quality would return because we'd finished with the bedding. Then my partner appeared wearing a too small for him, vintage style, peaked helmet and I said 'it suits you!'. He larked about with Dave and the matching child's ride in car which reminded me of Rupert the Bear.

I found myself in an unfamiliar, small galley kitchen with glossy white u its on both sides. A smartly dressed man was providing some sort of induction and he made a dry comment about looking in the 'womens fridge, when I said 'you're kidding' it turned out that he was. I then tried to help a woman with her drink  but I added too much elderflower cordial so I ended up making pitchers, with strands of fresh herbs, and carrying them to a lege and busy function room. I had more interaction with people I didn't know in that room and then left because it was hometime. As I walked towards the entrance with a woman,  I put my hand in my coat pocket and realised I had at least one key in there - a hotel key with a cold metal fob. I said 'oh shit' and explained to the woman about the key and how I'd checked out on Sunday - which was at least 3 days earlier.  As we wandered out of the building/hotel and through a  buzzy pedestrianised area I spotted my mother and so said goodbye to the unfamiliar woman from the venue. I greeted my mother who was with another woman who I didn't recognise.  They were dressed up,  my mother was wearing a lovely full length vintage dress in a black, jacquard print and a big hat and billowing veil. Her companion needed the loo and while we waited for her, my mother started to tell me an anecdote from the 60s about John Lennon and a groupie with a bath full of money.

I was talking to a young boy who I felt was my friend's son, although he is an adult now, and she was in the background. I was trying to entertain him and that involved taking my glove off and there was another glove underneath. Then I was in a room in an unfamiliar house, it was untidy and for some reason I believed I was staying in a house share with circus performers. I went to have a wash and the bath was full of bin bags of clutter and then the occupants came home. I also then spotted a group of small, old cats I hadn't spotted in the bathroom straight away. Then I was on a grassy common, not manicured and not far from town either. I was fretting about my cat running off, and the other groups of cats. A dog lay down near me and I told it to go away because of the cats but then I felt bad as it was a sweet dog and its owner seemed nice. At one point, a group of 3 or 4 cats all came and arranged themselves together on a frame which I admired. I was lying on my back trying to contain a small, furry creature - possibly a gerbil - in my hands and I asked someone if they could take it as I was worried about the cats spotting it.

I arrived in a large, contemporary roof terrace. It didn't seem domestic but apparently it was my godmothers and she had lent it to me and my mother. As we wandered around, we saw someone and asked who they were - we weren't expecting anyone else but it could have been a shared building. He said he was a fried of my godmother and that we'd met in the restaurant the previous evening. He described a few things including someone's hair colour. I didn't remember him he could have been TV presenter Lawrence Llewellyn Bowen. I thought he could have just seen us the restaurant. We asked him to call Victoria but he didn't. Then he became more like a pantomime villain and in a tongue in cheek way threatened to be my nemesis. The view from the terrace and tourist literature were for a beautiful but unfamiliar European city with great and quirky architecture.

I was walking up the stairs in a house that looked like it was a Victorian, British house that hadn't been done up well. Poor quality paintwork, bad patterned carpet, wood chip. I was there pre-holiday with a cat, it was somewhere safe we could spend the day/hours till our flight. Near the top stair, I felt something with my foot and I'd nearly tripped on a cat laid across the stairs. As I came on to the landing, there was an entrance to a room that had been done up perhaps for a teenager. It seemed like it might have a sauna which felt incongruous. I had a false memory of having had to go on holiday by myself earlier in the year too. Then the setting stayed the same but there was a big sample/jumble sales which kept me entertained.

I bumped into some unknown people and travelled with them to an area described as the east end. I didn't recognise it as London's east end but is was urban and brightly lit. I was aware that I didn't have the correct clothes or enough money.  I had some change which I could feel through a plastic bag. I didn't recognise anyone.  The setting morphed into a sort of hotel and it seemed like a work outing with some colleagues I recognised and someone I didn't recognise who I heard complain that our department had ordered something with a shiny surface which we didn't really need and would be dusty and difficult to clean. The rooms weren't really hotel rooms and there were lots of people coming and going and making provision for bringing their cats.

I came to the end of an urban street and I was looking in the dirty window of an empty shop fronted building - possibly Georgian. Some young women appeared from the back and asked what we thought of them renting it, they may have been students for the new term. The property was surrounded by litter and on a main road, some way along from the 'fashionable' bit we could see in the distance. I think we were supposed to be in Camden or Islington. Looking down the road in the other direction was a bridge. Next scene I was in an old-fashioned parlour sort of room with several people and there was something going on with a paper bag. There was some talk about the transfer of pet cats with reassurances that they'd be taken to a grassy common for exercise and I was protesting that it was a bad idea.

being in a room with a cat who I think was my former female cat Ella and a man maliciously throwing drugs on the carpeted floor and me trying to save her from eating tiny, lethal things which were the size of beads or hundreds and thousands. There was a sub story about a cat I didn't know 5sas in a bad way but I managed to intervene and achieve an improvement. The scene changed later and there was a little girl foisted on me in the early morning who complained about wishing she had a 'normal mummy'.

I was trying to save a cat that was found in my old house's garden, which was also somehow the garden of a large elementary/middle school. The cat was large, very fluffy and white, and very friendly, and it seemed in much better conditions than the high number of stray cats that lived in the area; hence I and a group of kids wanted to rescue it. My mum was opposed and didn't want to help because we already have three cats at home and she was concerned about bringing a potentially sick cat in; in the end I managed to convince the mother of one of the kids to take the cat in for one night, promising to go buy litter and food and everything it would need myself, and then take it to the vet the next morning. The plan was for the cat to live in the school after all of this, taken care of by the caretakers; I was scheming about how to ask the headmistress in a way that would force her to say yes.

I was starting to investigate a mysterious sacred object in a Cambridge chapel. I found someone I only know from Twitter replying to an earlier inquiry by an old uni classmate of mine in Italy and mentioning that she had been asked to eat it. Then I was going with my dad to pick up a package at an old workplace of his; he drove a small two-person car rather than his usual bike. I had to pee but wasn't sure we would be allowed to use the bathroom in the old office. The porter, a chatty middle-aged man who vaguely knew me from when I was a child, had opened the package, and I pointed out that was incredibly rude and kind of illegal, but then we found out the address was ambiguous and so he needed to open it. I had an exchange about how I don't play the clarinet in the local marching band any more and everyone who plays is now old; I said my mum also says the same every time she sees them. As we were leaving my dad mentioned an elderly family friend who used to be very proud of me for playing; he was alive and also playing in the band. A common trait of the two parts of the dream was that I needed to readjust "things" to be perfectly horizontal or something horrible would happen; this didn't actually seem to apply to anything in practice in the dream world, but I was mentally visualising lines that were slightly askew and straightening them so they were horizontal in my mind.

I had to do some translation work for my dad, but I then found out he actually wanted me to write the copy directly. I told him that was going to cost him more. I was also, however, on a trip to London with my friend Lena; we had to decide which two out of four exhibitions to visit. I was enjoying this but also stressed about the work that I needed to finish ASAP.

I was at an ancient Greek course for all levels. I'm very advanced, but my friend Lena who is a beginner was also there. I kept falling asleep in class briefly and having to apologise for that. Then Lena translated the beginning of a story and the professor corrected her very harshly on her syntax. Her translation actually sounded fine and very creative, so I got annoyed and challenged the professor in front of everyone, which he very much did not like. After I left the class, I ran into my high school Greek teacher. he looked fine, and he explained that he was on a new therapy that was really helping. I apologised for not keeping in touch with him and we hugged and it was all very happy.

I was on the last day of a conference and I had decided to get drunk for the evening. It was like, a positive project for myself? I drank some wine before we moved on to a pub, where I had some "kahlua", which was a thick chocolaty liquor. I was about to pick a fight with someone who was being obnoxious.

going through a haunted house/landscape. At first it was me and my family on a huge boat with wheels. We had taken the ferry to an island and were going to take it back at the end of the day. I went through a door and ended up in a swampy landscape with what looked like giant leeches; it turned out the landscape was the reign of Norse deity. The rest of the boat, which was now a house, was inhabited by creepy children that refused to answer our questions, and by furniture which grew human limbs. at some point I was in a chase with a girl who was taking care of some books and wanted to steal the books we had, and managed to both protect our books and actually convince her and her brothers to rebel against the deity that controlled them. In the end we all left on the boat, now having acquired two shepherd dogs, one of which was snuggling with her head under my armpit.

me driving down a country road, being very careful because it was late at night and also because, well, I can't drive. I could hear a truck coming up behind me, which was stressful until I realised that my right turn was just coming up and I could get out of the road. As I turned, however, the truck sped up and basically roared over me, pushing me into the ditch. I was okay but very scared. After this, I was at a function with other people from my university faculty. A specific professor for whom I'll be covering some teaching next academic year was presenting her pet project, a residential conference. Me and some other people pointed out that the conference was prohibitively expensive (she was sort of bragging about this) and would only contribute to excluding marginalised scholars. She got quite annoyed at these questions but sidestepped them. After the presentation there was a party, and when I had to drive back home (I had no car but could drive), this professor offered one of her cars to me, a huge green SUV. It was so unwieldy that it moved without me even being in the driver's seat; with the help of a couple of friends we managed to park it again in the same parking lot, after bumping into a couple other cars (with no visible damage). I came back to give the keys back to this professor (somehow a few hours had passed) and she was in a different parking lot nearby, furious because her SUV had scratched a few very expensive cars and trying to blame that on me. I defended myself by saying I had only moved the SUV in the other parking lot, and so any damage in this one could not be blamed on me (she had clearly done it but didn't want to admit it). I was trying to appear very sure, but I also remembered that we had bumped into a couple of cars in the other lot, so if those were damaged I would be responsible (and I definitely didn't have the money to pay any of that back). In the end she begrudgingly accepted my version of the facts but it was clear she was pissed at me and I had ruined my academic relationship with her.

I was somehow magically skilled and I was helped by some large creature that I used to draw power from, while I focused it with my skill. With this we managed to navigate a tricky landscape. Then we stopped at an inn (we was now my family), where we were fed meat. My mum was confused because her cut of meat seemed to have a very human-like spine. Using my magic I detected that we had all been eating human meat; we were appropriately horrified.

I was at the opera, nominally a Mozart opera even though it was mostly a mishmash of scenes that aren't actually in any existing opera I've seen -- the musical style was absolutely Mozart's, though. My ex partner was with me. We had in some way gotten back together. We were in a booth with at least another person, but my partner was still whispering and trying to cuddle me while I was very embarrassed. There were long unexplained gaps when the scenes changed, and part of the opera was performed by kids who were just learning to play an instrument; I remember trying to be very supportive of them. I also remember trying to figure out how to break up with my ex again, as I had just had a conversation with my best friend about how I need to stop getting into bad relationships. This worry mixed with the worry about how to get back home efficiently (we had to take a bus).

started inside the castle from before, as we were gathering some useful objects for an expedition into the building itself, which we knew was infested with monsters and hostile robots. The we in this case is a team of four including me, which was more or less my family (dad, mum, and brother), although this was not very salient or consistent anywhere in the dream. First we gathered some equipment but no weapons, which became a problem when I was locked in the same room we'd started in by a robot who was bashing the door in. I managed to solve that by escaping into an adjacent study with a sturdier door and finding a gun in a desk drawer, which I used to take the robot out. Then we proceeded towards the interior of the building; on occasion we encountered either skeleton-like people who had been chained and tortured, or the people who had tortured them, who were well-fed bureaucrat-like types dressed in suits. A group of the latter was descending towards a lower level, but we decided not to follow them; instead we found ourselves in a gallery overlooking said lower level, which seemed to be a sort of dystopian garden with weirdly-coloured, chemical-loking plants. The bureaucrats from before were making an announcement about a girl who was the reincarnation of someone who would destroy them; just as they did that a pair made of an older boy and a younger girl tried to fly above the lower level, but the boy fell while I managed to help the girl up. She revealed that she was the reincarnated person in question and needed our help, and "that's what Chadwick would have wanted".

I was following a dog who was chasing after a fox (with hostile intent). The fox was trying to reach a maze on the top of a hill, in which there was a secret house where she would find protection. I managed to also reach the house, in which lived an elderly couple with a lot of cats and at least another elderly fox. The dog also arrived there but was welcomed lovingly and was not hostile any more.

I was at a huge wedding party. Before the party, I had accidentally spilled my aunt's pill box; while I tried to recover all the pills, some still went missing (according to my aunt; I could reconstruct at least one version in which she was lying), and she wanted me to pay her back for them. As this was too much money, we decided we would play a card game after the party and if she won I would be her indentured servant for life. While at the start I was me and my aunt was my aunt, at this stage I was a tall young white man and she was a Norse deity; Loki was also going to play in this life-or-death card game. There was a long wedding reception scene in which people ate two meals (regretting the fact that I had not ordered the fish for the second meal, because the fish in the first one was disappointing, but then it turned out the second meal had been cooked by a different restaurant). Then everyone started getting drunk; in particular, my partner got so drunk she couldn't walk and completely forgot I had a freedom-or-servitude game coming up. I was heartbroken but sent her away. In the end, we played the card game; I lost two rounds so I was eliminated, but at the last minute Loki won over my aunt and released me. My friends drove me away. The final scene was stopping on the road and asking a restaurant if we could use their bathroom; the owner tried to refuse on grounds of possible COVID contamination, but I managed to get the upper hand in the argument by pointing out that she wore a facemask with a hole cut out for her mouth and therefore clearly didn't actually care.

I was in some sort of magical school. Three familiars, a white mouse, a pink grasshopper, and a blue snake, had escaped. They could all change their shapes, but these were the ones they preferred. I was trying to find them and also raise the alarm with others. Everyone was pretty chill because they knew the familiars couldn't leave a specific area of the building, but I was still pretty annoyed, especially when I found the mouse and the grasshopper in someone's breakfast porridge (ew). In the end, with the help of my mum, we found all three.

I was trying to clean my laptop of a bunch of malware/inappropriate programmes that had installed themselves after I downloaded something that I should have guessed wasn't safe. The programmes were mostly games or movies, and they kept popping up; I was trying to uninstall them via the regular uninstall procedure on Windows, but I was struggling because I couldn't hit the proper keys on my keyboard. I wasn't helped by the fact that there was a huge storm and the wind coming through the window kept rattling my laptop and threatening to sweep it out of my hands. My brother and father would laugh at me rather than help.

I was playing some kind of virtual reality game in which I was fully immersed, but also fully aware it was a game. I went around killing other characters to level up. One of these revealed itself to be under some kind of curse that turned him into a zombie that kept attacking me, and I didn't know how to kill him. In the end my brother, who was playing with me, killed him on my behalf and made good-humoured fun of me for not knowing what to do. Then a teenager appeared with a message for me that together with other information I had found earlier in the game was meant to expand the storyline for me. I killed him too, which seemed entirely okay with him. Another teenager appeared and asked for a peer support chat.

I was trying to escape a castle using my magical powers and also physically running through a tunnel, while someone I knew was running after me and trying to hold me back, often grabbing at my clothes. I ended up managing to hide in a bathroom from which I knew I could escape using magic.

I was trapped in a featureless cell, sometimes alone, sometimes with someone else who was teasing me and who I hated. I was sometimes myself and sometimes an elderly woman. I was periodically zapped by a floating sphere -- it felt like an electrical shock in my midriff and I lost consciousness. To escape I had to find a specific reference in a Dickens short story; I had been shown the passage reference but it only appeared for a limited time, and it was indexed using the complete works edition. I was also, at the same time, in my childhood bed, aware that the other story was a dream, but that I also had to do the work to escape from there; a giant centipede appeared in the bed but quickly dried up and died.

I was part of a force defending a fortress from a siege. The era was approximately 19th century, and it was very cold and snowing. I was on patrol with another soldier and we saw a group of kids; I was scared and instinctively raised my rifle to shoot. I didn't do that, but I was so scared about the possibility of shooting a kid that I had to lie down and cry.

This was a fantasy dream that kept changing structure and storyline. First I was in a castle and there was something about freeing a princess and a prince and having them meet and marry; the aesthetic was very steampunk rather than medieval, with technology and machinery. Then I was being expelled violently from the castle into a desert where people were fighting, and I was severely wounded. I managed to return into the castle grounds and I went to ask for help from an old friend who was an engineer; at this point I was accompanied by my ex-partner, who insisted that we were together and also insisted on kissing me and having sex. We found my old friend who thought I was dead and hugged me (I had a moment of in-dream COVID panic); he equipped us with high-speed vehicles (mine was a flying thing, my partner's was a bike), and we planned our way into the castle to free it from our enemies.

I was entering some kind of memorial with my family and a school; at first I thought it was a Holocaust memorial and was extremely sad, especially remembering a Holocaust survivor I knew and who has since passed. Then it turned out it was some Vatican Catholic thing. My dad pointed out that you could get your sins pardoned if you walked a certain distance from the monument. We left from a side door and met a couple of cats which we tried to pet. Later my dad and my brother were arguing because my brother needed help finishing his homework but he'd left it to the last minute and now my dad had to go out instead. The next day at school, a boy was putting up a play all by himself. He started monologuing about a girl in the class but both I and the teacher stopped him because she wasn't present that day and it was disrespectful. He got huffy but agreed. Then he tried to steal my jewellery box and the jewellery I was wearing. I got very upset because they were valuable items and some of them belonged to my mother. I cried and tried to bite and scratch him.

I am in a wilderness, adventuring with a group. There are different environments to explore. going through deep gulleys, down rivers and traversing cliff edges to reach high peaks. overlooking lush, green mountainous terrain, however there's an edge to the wilderness which has huge steel fencing bordering it. It appears the wilderness is more of a theme park experience and there's also cable cars running to each peak. I want to continue exploring on foot but others want to take the easy route of the cable car.

I am at a party with Em, my girlfriend, and my friends. It’s at a packed nightclub and there’s barely room to move between people. We’re having fun but we feel a bit overwhelmed by the amount of people and need some breathing space. We go into a private section of the club which seems to be a sort of spa. Covering most of the floor is a very shallow pool of mud which we take turns to lie down in and make amusing shapes with our bodies. As the mud is quite viscous our forms remain in the surface when we get up. There’s a shower in the corner of the room which I use to rinse the mud off.

I am swimming in a lake with Em, my girlfriend, playing with her parent’s dog, Mollie. I am throwing a ring frisbee for her to fetch and trying to capture footage on a waterproof camera. Suddenly a large creature emerges from the lake, breaking the surface. Em identifies it as a humpback whale and I try to film it excitedly. Then a killer whale starts trying to force the humpback whale to beach, running it aground at the shore. Em and I try to push it back into the water. We do so somehow, but it is wounded, bleeding profusely.

Emily, my girlfriend, and I are moving into a new house. The space is very small and there is confusion over which bits of garden space are ours. Em’s parents are with us helping us move.   I am in an attic space full of clutter trying to sort out boxes. It turns out my cousin’s cat uses the attic space as a sleeping area. It has cage with a bed and litter tray which is full of crap. My cousin, Emma, appears and she attempts to sort out the litter tray by first trying to remove the cat. The cat struggles and gets its own crap stuck in its fur. I feel disgusted and sorry for the cat as it doesn’t look too well.  I am with a work colleague, Andrew, who is making a transaction at a till with a customer. This is not taking place at work, but in the hall of the house I grew up in. The customer accuses Andrew of damaging his payment card. We both deny this is the case and I make rude comments about him behind his back while heading into the living room of the house. The customer is aware I have said something about him but I carry on walking away from him, at which point my mum arrives which I am pleased about. We then go to the kitchen for a family meal. Pizza is brought out, I sit next to my sister, Rosie, who exclaims she can’t eat the cheese on top. I say I’ll have it so it doesn’t go to waste, so she scrapes the cheese and toppings onto my plate. This leaves her with just the base. The kitchen is crammed full with family members and there lots of chatter which is lovely.

I am at work and it's Christmas time when we put on illuminations and other festive things for the public to enjoy. However, it's different due to the coronavirus situation. There's less we can put on for the public due to no money and I am working with my colleagues to try and find the best way to please people and avoid disappointment. However my colleagues are distracted by a new member of the team who appears to be Channing Tatum and they persuade him to do some routines from Magic Mike. He obliges and while I'm impressed by his talent I'm a bit annoyed that we're not really focusing on the task at hand.   I go outside to clear my head and inspect the areas we want to illuminate. However, the historic estate that I work at has turned into an industrial complex and there's a strange forboding atmosphere. It seems I've travelled through time and have appeared in the future. There's a huge screen displaying a speech from some leader. He is flanked by muscular men, one of which appears to be Channing Tatum in a crop top and looking thoroughly uncomfortable. The leader is explaining how they travelled through time to capture him and he's now his lover of sorts.

I am in university student accommodation and I am going for a shower. The shower rooms are very long and run parallel with the hall outside which leads to each student's room. I begin showering, wash myself then realise I don't have a towel with me and have misplaced my clothes. The hall outside is full of students. I try to hide my privates at first but this seems to make people stare more so I decide just to walk around normally and I don't feel ashamed or self-concious.   I reach my room, enter and get into bed. There are also a group of girls in the room too. One of the group gets into bed with me - it turns out to be Emily, my girlfriend. She is also naked and we begin to get intimate. It's like we're doing so for the first time.  It's now the next day and I am in my room hurrying to get swimming shorts to join my friends for a slip and slide. My good friend, Shannon, is with me also trying to find his swimming stuff. My other friends have already left without us and I am afraid of being left behind so leave without Shannon once I find my things. I get in my car to drive after my friends.  It turns out we have to trek up mountainous terrain to reach the slip and slide. My friends are already making their way up a steep section of hillside on foot and I try and catch them up. I reach them and they discuss a barbeque for when we arrive. I find some blocks to put the BBQ on out of concern of starting a wildfire and carry them with me.  We reach a section of hillside which consists of a cliff face above a busy beach. We have to climb down it to reach the beach. At this point Shannon catches up with us. He begins by finding an easy route down however my other friends attempt a more challenging route which we concede to doing as well despite misgivings. They speed ahead along this route which involves handholds and rock climbing. I am encumbered by the blocks I am holding and am frustrated at my slow pace. Shannon is also going slowly. I wonder whether I can throw the blocks down to my friends but I worry I may hit one of them or other beach goers. Shannon and I discuss going down the easier path but I stubbornly insist we carry on.   Shannon is getting impatient and worried about being left behind again. He decides to jump though it's far too high to do so. He says jokingly 'this might hurt a bit' and leaps off the cliff before I can protest. He plummets and begins to scream when he realises how far he is falling. Our friends look up in panic and attempt to break his fall. This isn't effective and he lands badly on his front. He lies there unresponsive and twitching. My friends call the emergency services while making their way up the cliff to me. I head back to the easy route down and am angry at my friends for not staying with Shannon as he seems to still be alive. I make my way to him as I don't want him to be alone if these are his last moments.

I am at a beach, I head into the sea to bodysurf. At first the waves are fairly small but I can catch them into the shire. As time goes by the swell gets bigger until the waves are enormous, which is exciting. I catch a huge wave in which takes me back to the beach. I begin walking down the beach and meet with Emily, my girlfriend, and her parents who are digging a hole through a rock to help a couple escape the tide as they are trapped on the other side of the rock. I dream about our current restructuring at work due to the effects of the coronavirus situation. I remember just retreading concerns I have in real life. One part I do remember is as follows:   There is a meeting with the heads of the organisation to explain the changes they are proposing. Those chairing the meeting are a mixture of actual work colleagues  and teachers from Hogwarts, the school from the Harry Potter series. I intend to go in to voice my concerns about the restructure but end up ranting about the way Hogwarts is run and how irresponsible the headmaster Dumbledore is. He is there and gets annoyed at me. He counters by asking whether I have even read the Harry Potter books. To which I reply that I read them as a child each time a book came out and have listened to the audiobooks multiple times. He still looks angry at me and the meeting continues.

I am at a party in a field with some friends. There are others from school there who I haven’t seen in a long time. While my friends know them well and are chatty with them I take a social backseat and just sort of tag along. We are drinking and as the night goes on the party seems to evolve into a festival with loud music, lights, stages and tents with music acts. I’m not really into it but keep tagging along, not really enjoying or paying attention to what’s going on around me as my friends have fun. I get separated from them and spend a while searching for them. I eventually do and by this point the night is winding down and we go to a tent of our own.   As the morning comes round we discuss the night before, one friend is disappointed he didn’t get the number of a girl he got off with. We all need the loo so head out to the toilets. The small field party has truly become a festival with surrounding fields filled with tents. We have to drive to the toilets because they are so far away. By the time we have gone to the toilet there are huge queues to use them.   We head back to the tent which has now become a stately building. Again we discuss the previous night in the drawing room of this big house. They ask me about my night. I cant recall much detail as I was drunk, though my friend says I appeared sober during the night. At this point I look out of the window as I see a flash of light that turns out to be a fireball, erupting like a mushroom cloud. The view from the window overlooks the fields and beyond, a bay with the Disney castle on an island in the sea. It is being attacked by dragons, torn apart and set ablaze. I tell my friends we need to get out of the building because, as it turns out, it is the White House and the dragons are clearly attacking important buildings. As I say this a fireball hurtles towards the building so I leap out of the window.  The fireball enters the building and engulfs everything inside including my friends, who are incinerated. Horrified and in a panic I rush to a bunker I know exists under the White House and enter it. I worry that I may be locked in and look for others who may have survived the blast. There is no one who can help. I enter the bunker alone to take a look around. It’s deserted. There’s windows looking out at the castle, the dragons have gone but it’s destroyed. I head further into the bunker and find a woman strapped to a table. At first she seems to be out cold but as I approach she opens her eyes and gives me a look of fear.

I am overlooking a section of garden of the White House in which Donald Trump is talking to a camera crew. I catch snippets of what he’s saying but can’t quite work out if he’s doing an interview or acting out a scene with the person he’s talking to. From what I can hear of what he’s saying, it seems he’s amping his rhetoric up to new levels of outrageousness to outright parody. He seems self-aware. I try to film it myself but they’re too far away to get any good footage. Trump leaves the crew to go back into the White House. It turns out he will be doing an interview inside now, the interviewer being my friend, Jake. A while later there is commotion and Jake is wheeled out on a stretcher. It seems his line of questioning provoked Trump into attacking him. Jake is not majorly injured; he was just punched in the face and seems quite amused by it. Trump himself has fled as other media people descend on the scene. I rush to Jake to congratulate him on finally tipping Trump over the edge to do something he cannot come back from.  I am watching the events that follow as if in a cinema. A manhunt ensues in order to find the President and bring him to justice. Trump is being moved around by a loyal team of agents in a convoy of big black SUVs – his vehicle stops and remains in hiding under a bridge. Another vehicle goes ahead down a hill and as it reaches the bottom a chain is brought taught across the road at windscreen height. The chain rips through the car, taking its top off and horribly injuring the driver who is thrown from the vehicle. The passenger managed to duck the chain but is dazed from the subsequent crash. The driver is on the ground having lost most of his limbs somehow. He pleads for help and is executed by a shadowy figure with a gun. The dazed passenger tries to get himself together, but the shadowy figure appears behind him and stuns him further. The shadowy figure turns out to be James Bond, but as he was when acted by Pierce Brosnan. Bond then proceeds to cut open the passengers back and climb inside his body as a form of disguise. It’s really fucking horrible.Trump is inside his vehicle, nervous about the disappearance of the car that went ahead. His driver reassures him as he sees the driver of the missing vehicle approach them. It’s Bond in his disguise and once he gets close the driver begins to become unsure, but it’s too late and Bond executes him – shooting him in the head which explodes. Trump is rattled as Bond gets in the car with him. Bond proceeds to talk to Trump and threaten him. It seems he needs to bring him in but is also weighing up whether to execute him too.  At this point the lights go up in the cinema and even though people begin to leave their seats I am certain the film hasn’t ended, it’s just an intermission so I don’t leave my seat. However, it seems everyone is leaving, even using emergency exits. I am disappointed and even though it may be an emergency, I remain seated.

I am playing Splinter Cell, taking out enemies. I am playing a level in an urban setting, hanging off buildings and grabbing people from below and hurling them to their deaths.  I am now playing Crash Team Racing, a kart racing game. I'm not doing very well. I keep losing to the computer.  I am now playing a sort of survival game. Again I'm not very good at this and I'm killed quite quickly. I then go to a restaurant with my friends. It's an all you can eat buffet rather than table service due to Covid restrictions, but it's a bit of a free for all with no social distancing. We then go to a water park or swimming pool where we enjoy time by ourselves until loads of kids and families join us. At this point my friends start playing Fall Guys which annoys me at first, then I reluctently give in to play too.

I am traveling in China with my girlfriend, Emily, boarding a bullet train to Shanghai. I am taking her on a journey I have not made before but feel as though I have; locations and routes are familiar despite not actually having seen them before in real life. Feels a bit like déjà vu. I know my way and lead Em around confidently. On the bullet train I excitedly explain to her how fast bullet trains travel and how smoothly they do despite this. I point out the speed we are travelling at on a readout. The train lurches around corners instead of smoothly like it is meant to which is slightly disconcerting. The train also has a lot of British tourists on board too. We have to disembark the train in a rural location to make a connection, I lead Em along the allegedly familiar route of the train station. I notice that the platform that we need to get our connecting train is seems to have been partly demolished with huge earthworks built up around and on top of it. In a state of panic I am separated from Em but she catches up. The station surrounding the platform seems to be partly converted into an art gallery and I note a deconstructed crochet bumblebee which I point out to Em. The art is accompanied by an explanation being pretentious and unnecessarily glum. Again the whole place seems familiar yet it has changed from what I remember, so I am confused and try to find aspects that haven’t changed. On a bridge overlooking the tracks I notice the rails have been removed and workers digging up the sleepers. The British tourists from the bullet train are still milling about and we begin to walk through the rural area to reach Shanghai.   I am playing a video game, enacting or living the game rather than playing it in the normal sense. The game involves stealing the eggs of flying creatures and takes place on rock spires and cliffs high above the sea. I am flying around, sometimes sailing, dodging the attacks of the flying creatures. It’s exciting but also frustrating.  I am working with a colleague, Sophie, who has been furloughed since the lockdown started in the UK and still is. She has returned to work and has too much work to catch up with and is flustered and exasperated; she is reprimanded for not being able to properly take care of things by a superior. I have tried to help but ended up breaking a piece of artwork she looking after because I have stored it somewhere inappropriate in her time away. I stored it on my grandma’s balcony with other art pieces. The weather is terrible with the wind and rain being the cause of the breakage. I am at my grandma’s but I am video calling her despite her seemingly being in the house, however she is having problems with technology and our conversation is lost. My focus being on this is the reason I have neglected the artwork and why it has broken. I feel upset at losing the connection with my grandma and guilty about my colleague who is clearly annoyed at me and may lose her job.   I am watching online footage of a footballer walking along a street who reprimands his teammate for using a homophobic slur against him. He insists that acceptance of peoples’ sexuality is part of being Catalan. To back this statement up he points out the stripes on his jersey, yellow and red as proof of this. This colour association doesn’t make sense to me. The other player disagrees and a scuffle ensues. All this time as they are walking down the street other bizarre interactions start happening like passers by groping the players, cars causing accidents and then the players are robbed. A person with me who seems like a detective pauses and rewinds the clip and tries to encourage me to work out the situation and who has committed what crimes. I am just confused and overwhelmed.

I arrive at work and I am in foul mood. I’ve got a gun, but I don’t want to use it so I bury it in some rubble in the staff car park. I head to the office where I start my day – various irritating situations happen and wind me up further. One particular person is making my life difficult and then it turns out my line manager is leaving and being replaced by this other individual. This sends me into a rage and I head for the car park with the intention of getting the gun. My ex-line manager pursues me to stop me from causing anyone harm. As I try to collect the gun from its hiding place she drives her car into the pile of rubble as I’m trying to retrieve it. This causes the gun to be crushed, however it went off in the process. I don’t think anyone is hit and I feel horrible for what I could’ve done had the gun not been destroyed.  Later, my girlfriend, is pregnant and about to go into labour. We are not in hospital but in our house from when we were students. There are medical people assisting her and preparing her for the birth. She seems very relaxed about it and not experiencing any pain, in contrast I am panicky and fretful but excited and expectant too. One of the medical team do an ultrasound and note the baby is not in the right position so Em shifts around to correct this, during which I worry. I want to reassure Em, even though she seem fine with the situation. I want to hold her hand but the medical team keep bustling about and I can’t get close to her and don’t want to get in the way. Eventually they leave and I’m left alone with Em who begins to go into labour but is still very chilled about it. This also worries me.
a red purse in a dark wood. the colours sharp against each other. a group ofvpeople.

I had to follow physical lines which kept diverging at right angles but never led anywhere. They were made of a thin metal which sometimes became heavy solid squared metal and was set in a cloudy world without floor, walls ceiling

I was stitching an improving moral maxim about the Bees on an openwork white canvas cover for a thermos flask. It was intended for Patrick C Smith So I had to stitch his signature in spidery black thread at the end. The maxim was written in a circle in thick yellow stitches  so it could go over the top of the thermos flask. I bent over the task, working assiduously: I was sitting – but on nothing, neither in or outside - a reclining pig. I was also walking around earlier looking for someone who had been stung to death by bees, and found someone lying there dead with the dead bee on them. But it was an enormous bee made out of some glistening golden metal in sharp planes, and very big, about the size of a retriever. It was embedded in his back. He looked as if he was from the ancient world, being dressed in a kilted garment of white linen.

I was walking behind a curvy young woman wearing a short tight fitting dress with a shirt flared skirt. She lifted it up to scratch her bottom and she was completely naked underneath. I noted this without any emotion or disparagement

We were on holiday travelling, PJ and I, and we had identified a little round room in a woodland setting (“very colourful” it said on the computer screen) and when we got there it was pretty nice – a thicket with a hole in it leading to a round central room with a selection of rooms leading off. There was a fireplace and a four-poster bed. The only misleading thing was the “very colourful” – through a doorway there was a brilliant yolkyellow room butand all the others and the minimal furniture were splashed with splashes of washy pink and purple as if someone had thrown a Paint pot at it. There was a particularly disappointing large ugly statue of a deer made of wood or wickerwork in the sitting room with a splash of lavender on its nose. But all in all  it was pretty good and I nipped outside with no clothes on to see what the strange clunk clunking was outside and it was a wide metal pot filled with water and weed and hiding among the weeds was one – then two, three sweet little green frogs swimming and croaking and bumping against the sides , and I looked up and there was a kitten – the teeny tiniest Calico kitten I have ever seen – the size of a mouse, slinking through the undergrowth above the frogs, under the kitchen window of the next house to mine. It was absolutely lovely.  I did wonder if anyone might see me naked, but comfortably assured myself that there was probably nobody about. Probably.  And then PJ called and asked me to help him get branches because it was about to rain and the thicket home tho pleasant was a bit low on roofing. So we went to the top of some steps and found two good-sized branches (I think I was magically clothed by this stage) but all the rest was bamboo because clearly other thicket home residents had got there first so I walked down the steps and found myself in a street market on one side of a steep stone street with windowless stone buildings along one side and a stone wall the other. Faded brown canopied stalls held various junk but I realised one was smack full of secondhand Chinese army winter jackets – aquamarine, downfilled and waterproof with hoods and I realised that if we couldn’t get enough wood for the roof these would keep us dry in the thicket. And there were probably trousers to match too. I was just about to ask “duo xiao qian?” when I woke. There was I realise an earlier part to this dream set in the Yorkshire Dales but all I can remember is the green fells and how it knit together with an old stone farmhouse and yard. I forget the rest and how we got from there to the thicket.

A troublesome dream about filling in this survey and not getting round to doing so - but it wasnt a chart but a little angular squarish iron blockish construction, with bits above, below, to each side, nothing regular, a bit like a block of flats built into a cliff and seen from an immense distance. Because it was small enough to be sitting on a small wooden table in the sunlight from an long open window with a net curtain blowing in the gentle breeze from the balcony beyond. “i must write about it NOW before I forget it, “ I thought, but I didn’t wake up in time to do so and as I procrastinated, it turned into a gold leaf imprint of the same strange shape on the inside of my arm, glittering in the sun

All the green things in the world are dying and I didn't want this to happen so I collected a bicycle basket of seeds of all sorts. I didn't collect them in the dream I just had them already.There were things like ash keys and avocado pits in as well as fruit and flower seeds Very dark  as if there was no daylight any more. I walked out and planted the seeds - I threw them into a big hole in the ground in a dark tangled forest of trunks and dead leaves underfoot.  They didn't grow.. I knew nothing would ever grow again. I was distraught.

We were a group of women in mid-Victorian dress sitting in a rough circle on some marble steps in the middle of rough green savannah. No buildings in sight.. I was part of the group but I was also an onlooker looking down on it from the air, and so can confirm we were all dressed in similar green and yellow striped sacques with tight black belts and we all were wearing modish  little black hats on one side of our heads. We were sitting in languishing poses on the ground as if waiting to be painted but it was a formal meeting and we were thrilled because it was going to solve the problem of Brides  - or possibly Widows, I can’t remember which. Not that we spoke but we had found the solution!

my dead brother. We were walking outside and someone needed visiting somewhere because they were ill - maybe my mother -  and I was  planning to visit her and was at the same time talking to Alec – he much as I remember him, tall and skinny blond curly haired and laughing and aged about 20 just before he became ill. We were joking around, he was going to travel with me. He was dressed in a Norwegian lusekofte (white and grey with red accents) and we were joshing around with a group of friends – unidentified - and there was some kind of accident of both our making: he jumped just as I pushed a button or something and he shot high in the air and crashed to ground half a mile away amongst trees and meadows on a little hill. I was startled and worried tho not unduly concerned and rushed through narrow cobbled city streets and squares to find him, being interrupted on the way by my very elderly friend Jean , lean and healthy and also dressed in a lusekofte who wanted to tell me about how she was retraining as a nurse and asking about my mother. I so didnt want to be impolite as I hadn't seen her for ages, so spent a while in chitchat lifting and admiring a little gold brooch on the hem of her lusekofte when I realised she was very uncomfortable with me handling it, because she had nothing but bare skin under it. Anyway we made our adieux and I ran on, on, on through head high scented white flowers like mignonette but much bigger and there was a crashed place where Alec had landed so I ran to a stone building with a three-door doorway like a church but which was the conveniently placed hospital and put my head inside and it was like a refugee camp, walls made of blankets and people lying everywhere and asked where a&e was and was pointed through a red blanket to where people were lying on camp beds like a war hospital. I asked “Has anyone been brought in just now and how badly is he hurt?” because at that moment I realised Alec could have broken his neck though I’d only been mildly exasperated till then and a busy middle-aged woman answered “The nice young man? Bless him, he's as right as rain. He’s only broken his” (here she mumbled s word, but I got the impression it was either shoulder blade or rib) “and it doesn’t even need setting, it will set by itself.” So I walked among the camp beds, and there was Alexander laughing and everything was ok

I spent the night in a friends' wetroom. It was the size of a Turkish baths with various rooms, and all white tiles. Both friends exist irl. I had gone in there to change for a party but then spent hours pursued by a spider the size and shape of a giant trilobite that squirted vivid green poison at me, and responded angrily with fangs the size and shape of a killer shark's when I tried to stamp on it. I still made strenuous efforts in the stamping direction. It didn't seen to have spidery legs, being built more like a bumper car , but it was a rich chocolate colour and changed size dramatically: at one point it was hiding in the wall behind the loo roll, another it was charging at my legs - the size of a child's car It also squirted a LOT of poisonous white froth. I wasn't asking for anyone else to help me. There was nobody else in the dream, tho I think my husband, peeped round the door merrily ar the end

I was walking outside  a friendly happy spirit with 3 woman friends. One friend took an unexpected phone call which was from a woman in despair . It was being broadcast live on a radio station somewhere else. We walked and she talked and we could hear the caller at the other end weep and expostulate and explain her plight and in the end one of the group  said, this isn’t a subject for the world to hear and we sat on  wooden seats around a round table in a place which became increasingly dark and gloomy and my friend tried to calm her but she gave louder and louder details: we were all in tears except for one woman who was a professional in this particular woe: she was surprisingly smiling broadly and unconcerned. I was startled and cross.  I pushed a piece of paper across  the table to my friend with five points she could ask/answer her caller. I can’t recall them but they were very sensible.

I was busy reciting a poem I already knew. I was very smug that I already knew it because I could write about it in this dream log with little trouble or difficulty and yet it would be a real dream. Sort of like cheating - but I could get away with it because it was true. It was the kind of poem you learn at school to remind you of something else and it appeared in thick black print in front of my eyes as I declaimed it. The strange thing was that it referred to two quite separate subjectsm something like Sheep and The Kings of England. I was all alone in a grey cloudy space without anything in it - just the lines of text.

There are three people in the meeting. I lie down uner my duvet with my head poking out. It is nice and warm. I get in a car and drive tp "Hawthornmere." to get my flight. I then segway back  to Rushcliffe park and their is a leather chair with an upholstered back.I write a sentance on the back of  it in biro and although it doesnt write with ink it leaves shiny marks which can be read. At work in a room I dont recognise with a 2 tables in it and two computers on the table. There are cards hidden in the officer we have to find. Got mine from under the table in the room I was in. In on an ope plan office floor. There is filing everywhere in cabinets and by desks. I exit to go down some internal emergency fire escape stairs and I see there is fiing here against the walls. Im looking into a a film set. Several fake walls that are half built (triangle shapes at 45 degrees with rough edges) and a women is walking through them. One of them says they can see abody at the steering wheel, as if it where a ghost..   From there I walk to the wall at the side of the building where I am told there is some fishing tackle available to borrow if I want to go fishing, as outside is the beach. I was accused of doing a terrible crime by police. I felt guilty but I couldnt remember exactly what I had done. Horrible.

I thought that the dream was about this man who was Chilean or South American. I went away then I came back and when I came back, P was together with him. And I remember thinking “but this can't be right.” We were both supposed to be with him. She was with him. They were together. I remember being surprised. Given that P is a lesbian, anyway there she was with this Chilean man. There was several of us, it was, a party, with a number of Chilean men Maybe it was an exhibition as well. We were nervous. At some point, there was a competition to make pots. And it turned out that the Chilean man was really really good at making pots. He made large pots on the wheel, and they sort of turned into flowers. That is a really good way of making money as well. I said to him, “Gosh, you could earn your living doing this.” I think he already knew that. So it was a dream about me yearning for this man who was together with my best friend. And also, P was writing poetry, we were all writing poetry, I think we had to write. And I'd suggested that I started it and she finished it. She had a really good way of finishing writing. And each of the rest of us in the group had to do a bit. I think D was also in the group. He had bare skin and it was white and fragile. There was something between me and the Chilean man. It was about to happen. But then it had to be hidden. I went away and came back and she was with him instead. It wasn't anything real, it was just feelings under the surface, I think.

Her friend, who had long brown hair with two plaits in the front, one on each side of her face, was very taalkative and I asked her if she would be able to give me lessons, I think of Spanish, and she told me that she was working at the Getty, she had been working there the whole summer, and she would go on holiday after SEptember. She was available on certain days that she told me, but either at 12 or late in the evening.

Cakes, children a woman who I knew, and a man. It was the woman’s birthday and he brought a cake for her, a cream cake and they were sitting round a Christmas tree although it was Easter. We went to the church, we went to several churches, and there were Easter decorations everywhere. It was the woman’s birthday the next day and she had lots of children, a boy and a girl. There weren’t enough cakes so I went to buy another cake, a small one and I chose a chocolate éclair with cream in choux pastry. When I came to pay I didn’t have any money but my friend C turned up in the queue and he paid for me, which was embarrassing. I found loads of change in the bottom of my bag so I was scrabbling about in the bag and trying to pay him back. And there was that awful feeling.   But we went back to the house where the woman was with all her children and we ate the cakes and had a discussion about pride and feeling good. We went somewhere else and the children did a performance/ presentation and they were all utterly brilliant and their mother was very proud of them and very happy.   At some point, and I can’t think how I went into a car to have sex with someone. And I remember thinking that the sex was purely biological. It was like a huge ritualistic opening up of a flower  - to receive, a huge taking in, a sucking up - to reproduce.    Earlier there had been a sheep or something, a sheep or a dog I had him on a lead. At some point he met a dog a male and there was a lot of interest in his/her bottom but we managed to get him away/ get her away before anything happened. the church and the Easter services. there was lots of sex going on in an Easter service.   There was a moment when the service took place and I was next to the person who was giving the service. There were lots of doubt and worries.

I was in a group of people that meet to sing. Some sort of singing. The flat that we were meeting in was interesting. It was a horseshoe shaped flat, modern and triangular, geometric and you walked round it. There was paint involved in it again. They were painting the walls with colours. The flat was empty of furniture. The idea was to sing or leading the singing. And so we all came together with something slightly different that we were going to sing to each other. Lots of people involved. Quite a variety of colourful, different people. Bright coloured clothes and walls, different coloured skins.   I had the feeling that I’d been to the house before. Meeting points for cultural activity. It reminds me of going somewhere. meeting somewhere. Finishing something. going along a track and around, a mapping. I’m try to describe something that happened ages ago, I can’t remember going somewhere and coming back, buses, buses that took you half the way, getting wrong buses.   the geometry of the place. The geography, patterns in movement, going round the horseshoe. Going somewhere and returning.

There was a bit where I was with a group of people, and I needed to go to the toilet. A few of us did And I went into this large concrete toilet, there were mostly cubicles without doors but I found one with a door, you had to go up steps to sit down on the toilet and It was dirty so I didn’t sit down. I did a poo by the side of the toilet. I was really tired and I wanted to just lie down after having done the poo. But I knew it would be revolting to lie down. I cleaned up the poo and came out. I'd noticed that P was there and we started chatting and somehow we ended up having a reconciliation. I said to her “When are you coming to Bristol? When are you coming to see me? I would so love it if you came and stayed with me. I really miss you.” and we had a big hug. So that was nice. And then we were back into this art gallery or museum, where there had been something going on to do with climate change and animal extinction. They'd done this thing where you listen to a recording as you go around the museum, so that you think about the animals. And I was trying to record the recording. But it turned out that it wasn't the whole recording, it was just a preview trailer. It was going to be released that evening at eight o'clock, so I only had a tiny bit of it. We were walking through the gallery and the person who was leading the group had long white stringy hair which she had dyed a pale yellow but you could see all her roots. I was with a group of people. And we were all very tired and we were lying down and telling stories to each other. I was lying next to a much younger man, a friend. I just remember, really enjoying lying next to him, I could feel the warmth of his body snuggled up against mine. He seemed to be really enjoying lying next to me too. We had to tell a story of an object that was important to us, that had been handed down through the family, something we would like to keep. And everybody was telling their story and it turned out that loads of them were aristocratic types. They were telling historical stories about valuable heirlooms, and I was trying to think of something. And then they said “oh now it's C's turn” but instead of saying C's turn they said “it's Rachel's turn.” And just as I started to speak P, who was lying on the other side of the man started to speak over me, she'd been to the toilet again I think and she just come back when they said, “It's Rachel turn” she started telling her story. So I didn't tell my story and then at the end of that everybody acted as if it was now time to have sandwiches. And I went, “Oh, but I haven't said my story,” and some people noticed and listened but other people started telling more stories. And it was frustrating trying to tell my story. I was feeling really frustrated. That was quite tricky. And I'm not quite sure which story I was going to say. I wanted to say something about my Nana being a seamstress and having been in service and my grandfather being an orphan. And some thing about both my parents being thieves, but they weren't really thieves. It's just that there are a few funny stories about them stealing things. Or that's how the family knew them but I'm trying to think now what on earth it could have been or whether it was just something I made up in the dream. For instance, my mother stole a plant when she was with me at the garden centre. We could choose one free plant to take with us, if we spent more than £20, so my mum made sure that we spent £20, then we went to choose the plant on the way out. And I couldn’t decide which plant to choose so she suddenly said, “Just take both” and then “Run!” So we did. That was the kind of thing that my mum used to do.
