There's various little stories like that in my family. And of course, the whole thing about what we did with my Dad's ashes which was completely illegal. We scattered my dad's ashes in Australia around a tree with the sound of the sea and you're not supposed to do that. So we did it very surreptitiously. And we liked that my Dad would really enjoy the fact that we did it secretly.

People from my artist studios. ice-cream. We were all doing different jobs in lockdown.  We were taking turns with the jobs: sometimes it was your turn to be organising the food and sometimes it was your turn to go and do some painting.    The painting was happening in two rooms and we could choose whereabouts in the rooms to sit. The rooms were nearly empty. No furniture or people, Just one or two belongings placed on the floor to reserve space.   I got really upset. I’d spent a while considering where I wanted to sit and one person objected to where I sat down. She picked a fight with me, she kept physically jumping on me. She had left her things nearby and she came back and grabbed me round the neck. I was saying: “Please take your hands off me. This is physical abuse. I will report it.”  - It was something to do with me sitting in the wrong place or too near to her paper.     It was M’s turn to do the ice-cream M and J  and he had to all sorts of complicated things like a report or say something and he had to eat the ice-creams and dish up the ice-cream for everyone else, like in a cafeteria The ice-cream had layers of chocolate bits and chocolate thin flat plane tablets, sticking out at angles from it and chocolate drops at the bottom.  M was arranging the chocolate in it and he was eating it. And a child went past and she was feeding him with a spoon and digging down to the bottom of the bowl to get at the small droplets of chocolate and feeding him. And he said: “I think when she grows up she’ll be having these lockdown fantasies of feeding people ice cream and chocolate. And instead of memories of what you can’t do in lockdown it will be memories of indulging in chocolate and ice-cream.”   Something to do with having to do these complicated reports and we are all getting into trouble for doing it wrong.  There were two rooms to do the making and painting in.   I was really upset because I couldn’t do any painting my paper was empty and everyone else was busy painting, being really productive.  I was very upset by the dream. By the not being able to do it and by everyone seeing I had an empty piece of paper.    And the woman who grabbed me and refusing to let go and I was saying really clearly to her “please take your arms of me. If you don’t take your arms off me I will report you. Just stop it. This is an assault.”   Ohh horrible, horrible I don’t know why she was dong that.   And someone else saying, it was M who came up to me and said: “I hear you haven’t been able to do any painting.” And that’s why he gave me the ice-cream.

I was in a cinema, seeing a film by an obscure film maker, who I was pretending to know more about than I did. I was sitting in the front row and the seat was too close to a wall and it was really uncomfortable. I was sitting next to my housemate Tom, unsure if we were on a date. Then another girl came along and sat next to him so I decided it wasn’t. Some other Girls’s came and sat next to me- I didn’t recognise their faces. It turned out I was supposed to be watching the film with them, I couldn’t remember who they were. We decided to change seats to more comfortable ones and as soon as I Stood up I couldn’t find them again the the crowd. Then I was in my deceased grandmas house, in her bedroom, she was there, my grandfather had just died. All his clothes where in a really elaborate wardrobe, his sweaters and his ties and his cotton stripe pjammas - all layed our like they were in a fancy clothes store. There was a toilet in the room too, and I tried to use it but it was too high to get on to. I flushed it and the sound was so loud I had to cover my ears

High school based dream, there was a never ending escher-esque staircase that was going the opposite direction to the one that I wanted to go in, a science lab with students sitting in rows in uniform. Several of the seats were empty and suddenly a bunch of Eaton type public school boys entered and took up the seats that were not meant for them. They kept saying - I got here first.   I could see the street out of the window of the lab, and Tina Turner (Simply the Best era) was outside making a music video - she looked amazing, she had on silver snake skin leggings and red patent stilettos    My mum and her friend Carol were outside smoking

I was with my classmates from university, we were set out in 3 rows of desks one behind the other, all facing the blackboard   The classroom was in a branch of Lloyds bank in Stoke Newington, I need your love by Laura Marling was playing in the background   There was no teacher and it was chaotic   The other students - one is which was an ostrich, has been on a camping trip without me and I got upset and did a big speech about being left out, and how they don’t like me

I was with my brother we were in the British countryside trying to get somewhere, we got stuck on obstacles including a humped back bridge that was too steep to climb up and a flower container that was huge inside. My brother had long claws on his hands and feet, they were bleeding, he was vulnerable and in pain

I am with Giorgio (my father), my son (Tito) and my only nephew (ERik), who is 3. His face is however different, he has a large face, quite plumpy, he is more similar to my half brother on my father side, who is ERik's father. ERik is standng on the sofa, Tito and I are at one end of the sofa, my father is at the other but none of us is sitting on the sofa. There is a small table i front of ERik with an old dial phone, He is playing with the phone, pretending to make call, turning the dial. Everytime he finishes to turn the dial, we heard the voice of my father's wife, saying something like, "Hello, ERik, how are you". Everytime the message is slightly different. After a coupla of times I ask myself if my father has a recorded message on his cell phone that he plays, as the old phone is clearly not working.

I am in a classroom together with my husband and some of our colleagues. MY husband is sitting at a desk on his own, on one side of the room. I am more or lesso in front of him, in a cluster of desk. Behind me there are other people from his department. I turn towards them and intervene in their discussion confirming that Tony  was indeed with us one night at a kind of a party which took place in a village. But while I say that the name Tony does not come easily to my mind, I have to pause slighlty to concentrate to remember it. I add some other details of that night that I have forgotten. I do not feel completely at ease. I see Tony nodding and the discussion is over.

Someone is telling me about the love story between a female and a male actors. THey show me the b/w photo of the man who wears late nineteenth-century clothes and long sideburns. And then all of a sudden I became the female ator. I am standing in large room like a living room, thre are people working in it, they are renovating it or perhaps they are setting the set, and tmy male counterpart arrives. I hug him and start kissing him and tell him that I want to make love with him right now, right there. He is a bit surprised and embarassed, so he says something like "I need to go in the other room to do something" to the people in the living room and we enter another room. He lays on a kind of a singe bed but on the short part of it, and I sit over him, but he slowly and intentionally slides with his back on the floor and I have to follow. Although I am determined in my intent, nothing is happening, I feel that there are too many layers of clothes between us plus he does not seem to be able to have an erection. And then my son enters the room, around 5/6 year old. And then my lover becomes my husband, my son  asks something to him, my son is very joyous and he does not find our position strange or he does not seem to suspect what his parents were doing. He receives the answer he needed and he leaves. I am surprised and think that this might be because he watches documentary on animals where they copulate in a different position/.

I look myself in a mirror or I am outside myself and I am using a kajal to make-up my eye. I am discussing with someone else how to use it. I already have some black kajal on my eyes and I try a green one.

I am in the bedroom of my flat in Mantua. I am sitting on the floor with my son, he seems a girl. We are doing something together when he sees something brown on one of my tights. He thinks it is a crumble and pick it up and puts it in his mouth, but it is in fact a knot of hair or textile and he spits it. I take it and throw it out of the window.
I was in bed sleeping and it was too hot and then I realised that I was dreaming

I am with someone, I think he is my husband. We are in a sort of hotel or bed and breakfast. The rooms are strange as they are very permeable. I am unable to explain why, in my memory the rooms have walls but perhaps they are not thick, I feel that the rooms were very permeable to noise and the oitside. The man who guides us, the owner of the place, too confirm this and takes us to our room, which he cals in a way that I have forgotten but the room has a name suggesting that it is a sort of capsule protected from the outside and more intimate, although in fact the upper part of the room is made of glass, not of wall, so everybody can see inside. We enter. At some point, we walk along some quite dark corridors, it is lte at night and there is someone, the owner of the place, still at work painting the walls of the corridor with withe and other bright colors and he is painting a pattern. I watch inside a house in what is clearly a holiday place. The owners, a couple over 65 who smiles at us (I am with other people but I am unsure who they are) let us visist their house which is typical of the place and they have mantained its typical fixtures, which means that the metal cupboards of the kitchen, the shape of which remember old fridges with their round forms, cupoards used to store food and things, have been left in their original position very high on the walls, where only with a long ladder someone can reach them. where they originally were. They have the bought a modern kitchen where everything is normaal and accessible, but they seemed very proud of having retained that touch of originality.

Fabrizio comes to visit us. I am at home with someone else who is not my husband, perhaps a cleaning lady. When Fabrizio comes closer to say helo and kiss me I do nt know how but we hug rathe tighlty and kiss on the lips. I am more responsible for this although it seems an error, the result of a misjudgement of distances. BUt then we kiss again, and I feel that I need to be careful as I am no alone at home. He is quite passive while I tentatively kiss his mouth. Then I apologise and he seems to be uncertain what to do and he says not to worry, that in his opinion it is a reaction to the enopause. Then we are outside. ONe moment we are in the street and we see someone dressed in a funny way, with a large hat, so Fabrizio takes me by my hand and we run after this man to look at him closely, and I see my image in a shop windomw and I am laughing, I seem happy, but I have very deep wrinkles especially around my mouth, in the lower part of my face, and I am surprised. THen I am with Fabrizio again in the garden of a modern house of just one floor, with the outside walls made of bricks and glass. I take him against the bricks and I kiss him again. I am driven by a strong desire but although he seems to reciprocate my interest, he is much more tepid. At a certain point we are inside a house, perhaps my house, and I lift in my arms a young girl, blond and with light blue eyes. She might be 3 years old. She tells me that her name is Gaia Luce and I feel a tenderness.

It s night adn I am going with my husband and my son to see my parents that I do not see since Chistmas because of Covid. I am in an urban environment, in the historical centre of a city. When I arrive at their house, I meet Silvia who has a yoga mattress on her shoulders. I do not remember if we had t do someting together but  notice that she has red cheeks and red eyes, she does not feel well. So I help her with something, I tell her that she is unwell so we cannot stay together. At that point I realise that my son too is unwell. My husband, who stands a bit far from us, tells me that our son too does not feel well and I check his tempretaure with my hand outside my parents' house. His forehead is hot. I am upset as I do not understand why my husband has not told me that our son was unwell earlier, so that we would not have been coming to my parents' house and now we cannot go and visit them. I cary my son into my arms, one arm under his armpits, the other under his knees, and I carry him all the way until our house. I walk ith him/her in my arms aong a large street that exist in my hometown and I am singing sotly to entertain him/her. I am alone and I meet a couple of people but I do not sop, one of them is Jovanotti who notice me singing, I hear him saying somethng about my singng to his friend but I am concentrate on arriving home as soon as possible and protecting my son..

There is someone who has fallen in a cellar, tere are debris eveywhere, and he is called for help with his mind, I see him in a part of the cellar but he is in fact in another part of it. I then see him being taken away with a strecher, he wears a gry gown with white pois and has the right arm bent on his body. I think it might have been the keeper of the place where I am going next. I enter a storage place which however resembles more the floor with all the cellars in the house where I used to live in Mantua. All the doors of the individual storages are made of woode planks painted in blue, and you can see through them as the planks are distant one from the others. THe walls are in concrete, grey and rough. I go to my own storage, the space has an L shape and it is very dusty. There is a kind of wardobe but still made of concrete and I open it to put something that I have brought with me in a large white plastic bag. I start to hang to some metal hangers old Italian postcards from the beginning of the twentieth century, they seems part of a philatelic collection rather than of personal importance. At a certain point I realised that they re too many for the number of hangers that I have and I take out of the bag a grey leather skirt.

I am with a group of friends among whom there are Francesco and Giovanna. We are supposed to do things together but there are often obstacles. The only one I remember clearly is the fact that we have planned to go somewhere and in fact Giovanna and someone else of the group say that they need to go to the Biblioteca Nazionale in Florence to pick up some books. So the entire group goes there, I do ot understand how we can go inside since a pass is needed in real life, but the process seems very easy, the people at the entrance leave the entrance open and we all can enter the library trough a very small metal door. Inside, there are two girls studying and talking together in one study room. Giovanna sits with one of her friends from the group at a table in a small space and I ask her where are the books that she needs to pick up but she says that they need time to do some research. At that point I am very upset because they haven't been straightforward and the rest of the group has come all the way to the library for nothing since there is no point in waiting for who  knows how long.

I went to the Getty museum to visit an exhibition, perhaps on Leonardo. THe place is ot like the real Getty but it is a place with different levels and there are escalators to go to te different evels. I arrive by car, a blue SUV, and I park it inside the covered parking. I then take one of the escalator and go to the exhibition, I amwith a group of people, not sure they are frinds, they are most art historians, they might be fellows at the Getty Reserahc Institute. I do not remember how the exibition was but I remember that after it I offered to take some of the people that where with me back to wherever we were going by car. THey were not the very same people that had come with me so I was wondering if it was the good thng to do but I did not want to wait the others and it had become dark meanwhile. So I asked the people that were with me if some of them wanted to come by car instead of taking the train, THey were deciding as they were 5 and I could only take 4 of them with me. THey did not know how to choose who was goign to come with me and at a certain point the word monarchist came out and I said that I id not want any monarchist in my car, half joking and half serious, and I realised that I have slightly offended the old man. I told my husband to tell the other people who hd come with me by car that I had left and I also tried to tell him the name of the only people that I knew that was coming with me know, but I could not remember it on the spot, so I told him instead the main article that she had wrtten and only after a while I was able to tell hm the full name. THen we went to the parking lot to take the car but I could ot find it. I tried to use the remote control of the key but I could not see it. And then I realised that part of the parking had been invaded by water so some cars were partially under water, olny up to half wheel, but still it was difficult to get in it. IT became progresivily difficult to not only find the car but move for one level of the parking to the other, people were giving me advice on how to find it. Someone who worked at the Getty told me that this happened often and there were people tat put a sort of localiser in their car to be able to retrieve it. Then I went out of the building of the parking lot and I had to go back but the stars or escalators where now full of people coming in the opposite direction and I could not go against them. I think that at the end I might have not been able to find the cr as the last thing I remember of this dream is travelling in perhaps a train with the people who should have come in my car. One of them was a person tha I know, she is an art historian. Her friend, who had long brown hair with two plaits in the front, one on each side of her face, was very taalkative and I asked her if she would be able to give me lessons, I think of Spanish, and she told me that she was working at the Getty, she had been working there the whole summer, and she would go on holiday after SEptember. She was available on certain days that she told me, but either at 12 or late in the evening.

I am walking along my street in North London and the front gardens have green and flowers. We notice a man with a strange black and elongated hat, like the beak of a duck, and my husband says he is the number 6. He is going out of a house. Then I find myself entering a house but I do not know the owner. Here the dream is confused. The first spaces that we go through are very nice and well mantained, with wood on the floors and they are quite empty as if the owner has just moved in. I show my husband the simple, linear wall skirt as they are how I would like them. However the wall skirts start changing, they become moulded and there is more than one, so they appear now confused and chaotic. Also the walls have different, bright colours, as if these spaces have not been decorated. At a certain point I find myself in a room in the back of the house, overlooking a garden. The walls are have been painted in a dark grey and there is a washing machine which is lifted on one side, as if there were bricks under the front side of it, a few white pieces of furniture and a sink, like a service room. It is large and behind the washing machine and the furniture I notice a single bed and I lay down and fall asleep. Then we are taken by a very welcoming woman to the second floor. Then I find myself on the second floor. I am not sure my husband is with me anymore. The woman I met before is sill there and she very kindly takes me around the second floor. Here there are some walls painted in very bright colours, and it is clear that some small children use this space. There is a sort of large space where doors open on other rooms, and its floor is made of soft rubber tiles very colourful and then a sheet of wrapping brown paper has been put on it to protect the tiles as there is a sink in this space and the child who uses it clearly sprays water everywhere. When I pass by one of this door, I can see the inside of the bathroom. It is a very large room and there is still a kind of trail/passage that has been built with boxes, toilet paper, towles nd othr objects that you might find in a bathroom, to guide the child who uses tha bathroom outside the room. It is a nice thing to see, I tell the woman that I have seen it, she says that the room is very untidy, but I say instead that it is nice and sweet. We see again te man with the black hat, he seems to live in this house, but I am uncertain about his role.

Tito is coming back home and when he enters he tells me that my dad in donwstairs, in the common TV room, to watch tv. I am surprised and I go downstars, where I find him and he behaves as ths was normal. I sit down with him and we chat while the tv is still on. The room is quite dark.   I am at home with my son (who is a young child now) and the cleaning lady. I realise that, although I assumed she is a woman, in fact is a man. He wears glasses, a scarf on an almost bold head and clothes with patterns. I ask him to clean the windows in the kitchen and the glass of the shower. He says something about this tsk, as if he does not want to do some of it, but I do not want him to clean only where I am. I tell him to clean only those windows that he wants. This discussion takes place while I realised that in the living room there are my son and Marco. Marco hugs me from behind, he smiles, he is very tender and wants to kiss me. I feel his erection. I am happy of having him there with mebut I realise that it might be a bit confusing for the cleaning man to see me with someone who is not my husband, so perhaps that is why I ask him to go and clean the windows. Also my father is around, but he does not seem to mind at all. He knows Marco and seems to be fine with te situation. On the contrary, Marco tries to hid when the cleaning man is around but I realise that I do not mind if he  is seen by the other people in the flat or not. Then Tito, Marco and I go out. Tito and I are on a kind of handcart that Marco pushes, we are trying to make Tito fall asleep. It is night and at distance a strange scenary appears, like the backdrop of a theater. I tell Tito to watch the skyline of the hillside landscape. It is all very dark but for some strong blades of pink and purple. Against this purple and pink I show him the smoke raising from several bonfires, creating a strange zig-zag pattern, and then I also notice and show him tro groups of people, they are agitated, they are buring of destroying things, and I tell Tito that they are revolting. Although the scenary is very dramatic, I seem not woried at all.  Then we keep going looking for a place where Tito can sleep, but it is clear that we are not in the right place as we are in a sort of urban environment and Marco makes a joke saying: "it is very strange that there is no place where you can leave your child to sleep in San Francisco". Tito is very at ease with Marco, he likes him, and I find myself thinking that Marco would be a marvellous dad. I start thnking what Tito will tell to my husband about this night and this man that he has met, but I am not worried. I also start thinking about how I can tell my husband about this night, how I can explin to him my feelings and what has happened. No matter how nice it is the time I am spendng with my ex-boyfriend, it is clar to me that my life is with my husband.   Then the three of us plus my dad are eating outside. It must be some sort of self-service as we all have plastic trays under our plates. A man who is around 70 and wears glasses approches our table and takes away my dad's tray under his nose, without saying a word.

I am with Guido and SCott. WE are discussing students' marks. SCott has a register with all the marks and they are discussing the marks of a student in particular. I do not remember exactly the problem now but she had clearly some very good marks and some others not so good. I am wondering if she is Alexandra POpa, a student I taught. I feel a bit guilty that she might not achieve a high mark because of my low mark. I try to look at SCott's register, there are many marks but in fact the numbers are too longo to be real marks. And I am unable to verify if my suspect is correct or not.

There is a danger, asniper or something like this, on a floor of a tall building. I am with other people, possibly policemen, and I enter the building. It is the sort of modern building with offices on each plan and glass walls. I found myself on one of these foors and from there I need to go further up. I decide to go through the tunnel of the elevator, I cannot use the elevator itself as I would be discovered. There are a couple of people with me, they are women. I force the doors of the elevator and enter the tunnel and I start climbing the pole at the centre of the tunnel to go up.

My mother-in-law asks me when the cleaning lady is coming to my house. I tell her on Wednesday morning. She seems surprised and asks me again if I am sure, if it is ok. Clearly there is something that upset her in this date but she does not want to say it to me directly. I realise this and thus reply to her in a slightly irritated way, that yes I am sure, she told me herself, WEdnesday morning. Then she finally tells me that she would prefer the cleaning lady to go to her house on Wednesday morning as she then needs to go somewhere. Can the cleaning lady go firts to her place and then to mine? But I have the same problem as I need to go somewhere for lunch. I am on my bicycle in Corso UMberto I and I am goign to meet someone, it is going to be a family reunion. At the end of the street I meet my grandfather, I recognise him for far away and I stop so that we can go together wherever we are supposed to go, which is no far away. Also my uncle, who is his son, arrives.

It s night and I am cycling with my red Holland old bicycle downhill in a place that could be the courtryside around Flrence. I am slightly worried because the brakes do nt seem to work properly. Other two people are on the road but they are not with me. I find a way to cycle safely even without good brakes. I arrive in a village, there is light now and I pass by a building and I notice that on ts side there is a corner coming out incongruosly. Someone at my back, I do not see him, says that he will take down the dress that someone has left hanging from the corner to dry, because it is not allowed or good to see. Then I arrive in font of a shop where someone is renovating the space. A person there who is wworking to renovating it explains to me that that corner is theresult of wrong renovation works.

I am with my husband and Luca. Luca is tall. I look at him while he is speaking and I find him very attractive. I think that we could have a story and perhaps I could try to seduce him, then I remember that he is married. After a while we separate and Luca comes closer and touch me and kisses me on the cheek and I find all this very inappropriate considering the current Covid situation.

I am in a car with people that I do not know well, nobody is familiar. The driver has a short beard and keeps making jokes, bt they seem not spontaneous to me. We then arrive to a house and there are other car with us. The driver of our white car and of a blue car get out of their cars, like aall of us, and start to climb the front staairs to enter the house. I realise they have left the engine running. I am not sure I am the one who says something to them or if it is aanother young woman who is wth me, but they have been asked why they leave the engine switched on, I say that engine idling is a punishable offence and ask them if they have never heard about the problem of global warming but they are clearly unimpressed. The other driver has curly white hair but he is not old. I then enter the house with the woman who was upset by the engine idling like me and anothe girl. We look for a toilet. Each of us goes to a dirrefent bathroom. They are clearly very large and new but the one where I am going seems the most luxurious one, with very sleek and design pieces. I enter it just to realise that in fact it has in fact a series of doors with matt glasses that close not so well. I close them but I never have the feeling that I am in a private and secure space to do what I need to do and so I proceed until I arrive in a large reception room, here many people have gathered. From one window there is a view of the large garden where there are men's clothes hanging from stilish structures built in the garden, like the stands that you find in clothes shops but more fancy. I say that I have done what I needed to do although it is not true, I want to leave this place.

I am with my husband but I see ourselves from outside and we are a couple of rather robust middle-age white people. WE wear clothes that we would never wear, all white with details in kaki. I am confused about the situation, I know that I am that woman there but I do not recognise myself. On the contrary, they seem very happy and with no problems at all.

I am in a social context, possibly at home during a party with my friend and husband. THere are also his three children from a former relationship. I have strong feelingss of love and tenderness for these children who are small, under 10. I am with them when their mother arrive. I know she has never met them and I show them to her although she does not seem interested at all. She is blonde with big blue eyes, but she is not pretty. Her eyes are very wide, she seems disturbed. I talk to her with calm, I ask her confimration that she has never seen them and then I tell her that her children are very good, but se is distracted. Then I do not know where she goes.  Next I find myself in a restaurant on top of hill along the sea. The place is rather crowded and I am arranging a lunch there with my friends. IT is a festive occasion, possibly my husband and I just got married. We agree on a fish menu and they set a table with glasses, plates and folded napkins. It is an oval table and there must be around 10 seats. At this point some time has passed and I do not see our friends around us anymore. I am worried beacuse I am not sure one of them likes fish and I would like to ask them before I confirm the menu. I try to call them with a cell phone, but I choose the ring number and I call Ida.    In the dream Ida is the mother of my husband's children, I dismiss her quickly saying that I have made the wrong call, but I feel bad as I hear from her tone that she needs to talk and her voice was that of Fernanda, so I feel guilty to cut her off but at the same time I feel that this woman is potentially instable and dangerous. Since I am unable to communicate withour friends over the phone, I leave the restaurant and look for them. I see them heading towards the beach, down the cliff, they are passing an area where the tide is going down. They all have large beach bags. I shout and they hear me. Sabina guides everybody back. I ask Sabina is a fish menu is fine for everybody, she say almost for everybody, she does not eat fish but it does not matter. She wants me not to worry and she dismisses the problem, walking briskly in front of me, but I am worried an try to suggest an alternatve for those in the group who do not eat fish.

I am planning to make a large order from an online website that is ethically and environmentally friendly. I carefully consider what to buy and the advantages of making this choice. I am doing this while I am in my bed, but I am kind of sleeping and I find this situation awkward.

I am caressing a plant. it is an herb. It is in a vase. And while I caress it I realised that I have dreamt of having herb instead of hair on my head and of someone saying something about how beautiful my hair are. The thought it is not disturbing at all.

I am in a room with many other people that I know. I am holding a book, Il sistema periodico by Primo Levi, which has beautiful, colourful, abstract illustrations. The pages are larger than usual and I realise that they easily come loose. The spne of the book is i bad shape. Someone else is doing the same with a luxury version of the same book, whic has even bigger and more elaborated illustrations and the paper of the pages is so thick that it seems paper for watercolours. I remeber being fascinated by the illustrations and disappointed and surprised when the pages come loose.

I am with a group of people that I do not seem to know. One of them, a man with curly blaack hair and black glasses, mentions Luca MOscon and says that Luca found living in New York very difficult, that it made him be anxious or violent the precise word that he used was important, and then he associated Luca's name with that of Evelyn Welch and I intervene asking with amused surprised what does Evelyn have to do with Luca. I am very sceptical that there is any connection between the two. The man starts answering but he has a very strange way to talk, he starts a sentence then he turns his head and talk about something else, just to come back to what he was saying before. It is a slightly annoying behaviour but it is clear that he doesn't do it on purpose, he just has a mind who does not proceed folowing a linear way of thinking.

I was playing and coaching junior hockey and we were using pears and oranges as balls. Needless to say, the pears disintegrated upon impact, but we persevered. The oranges held up for a little longer.

Early in the night, I was playing hockey. We were mostly running training drills, not a game. It was fun. I was quite happy.  Later in the night, I was with some one looking at these large photos of a woman in fancy lingerie. She had the photos taken to give to a friend, they were staged and sultry. I thought they were a bit bizarre and over the top. Later, I was trying on some of the lingerie, I pulled on a pair of knickers that can down to my knees, and seemed to be made from a wooden material. They were quite thick, more like a fancy pair of long johns.  I didn’t really see the point of them. They were warm but only came to the knee?

Mum was making dinner, we were in a house that is unknown to me. We were looking at a clothing catalogue, and I saw some items that I had been involved in working on. She liked one of them, but not the other. The fabric was colourful and quite beautiful. Dad had set the table with huge wine glasses, the size of large bowls. They could probably have held a whole bottle of wine. He had already poured a white wine into them, ready for our meal. I was already drinking a red. My partner was there too, but no other family members.

I was with a group of 4-6 female friends.  One of them was getting married, low key event, low stress. I suggested we get together for a quick drink to celebrate. Everyone was making suggestions, for times, venues. It came down to mine, Sunday afternoon. I thought I should put it in my diary, to remember. When I open the event in my calendar, I found some “templates” for “hens parties”, and thought that would be fun. When I clicked on it, I had inadvertently actioned a large event, for hundreds of people, run by a strange group / business, that ran sex parties for hen’s nights. In the accompanying videos, they showed guests lining up to be kissed, passionately by the “staff”! I thought this was a little over the top for our small, low key drinks, for 4-6 people. However, the event was underway. The next day, a man with a bulldozer came to clear some space in my back yard, he dozed down the fence, and cleared a space in a vacant lot next door. He did a good job mowing the lot, I was pleased with that. Thankfully, I didn’t get to experience the event. later one of my front teeth became wobbly, and fell out. I didn’t seem too worried, I thought, “oh well, I’ll have to get that put back in”...

I went to an animal shelter to get a second family dog. The dogs and animals you could get from this shelter were genetically modified. You could choose two breeds and the cells were combined to create your new dog. I felt pretty uncomfortable with this idea, but there was no other option. The women serving at the counter for “ dog orders” were quite pleasant and helpful. I could only think of one breed, an American Staffie, and could not decide on a second, for the mix, so the woman serving me said she would choose for me, and before I knew it, she had “mixed” two dogs in a test tube, and the process was started. I asked what she had chosen and it was some sort of pug dog, one of the breeds that have trouble breathing, and have been breed with existing respiratory problems. I said that I didn’t think this was a good choice for me, or a good mix. She was reluctant, but said we could throw it out and start again. I felt awful about this, it felt like a death, like an abortion in a test tube. I was left trying to make this decision, my inclination was to keep the new dog as is and whatever I got!

I was in a large yoga class, 40-50 people. A man pull out a hand gun and proceeded to shoot and kill all the participants.  He killed nearly everyone with a shot to the head. A handful of people survived. I went from observing the scene, to being in a wounded body. I was shot with a graze to the head, and in the abdomen. I was alive, but lay still for a long time, in fear and so I was not discovered and shot again. Even when help had come and nearly all the dead and wounded were moved, I still lay there until I was sure that it was safe. When I sat up, people were amazed that I was still alive! There was blood everywhere. There was another shooting later!   I was at a large public gathering, like an outdoor concert, in a grassy park, I had lost my shoes, a pair of thongs and a pair of sandals. I went to where I had last left them, but they were gone. There seemed to be abandoned shoes everywhere, but none were mine. I was a bit annoyed, with myself for losing them, with the person that took them. It was crowded, and I hate crowds, so I was grumpy.  I went to drop off a bag of clothes to a friend of my daughter, she had left them at our house. I’d travelled by bus. This friend was not the owner of the clothes, but I thought she would know to whom they belonged. She lived with an older brother and sister, her parent were deceased. Her brother was talking with friend’s at the front gate and welcomed me in. The front lawn was so steep, I had to crawl and climb clinging to trees and shrubs. I kept slipping back wards. While I was crawling up the lawn, the police came in to raid them for drugs. I finally got in, and my daughters friend let me know to whom the clothes belonged.  There was a plumber doing some work, in a house i was visiting. I was writing some sort of on-line review for him.

I was working back in the atoll country Tuvalu. I was flying in a plane over the island, but the island was much bigger than what it really is. I could see the water. When I was on the ground I was staying in like a Hotel
I was being driven to deliver something.

I had to look for a house to buy as well as wood chips for my garden. I looked at a few houses, with someone else. I looked at one house right on the beach. I was worried about the sand overtaking the house if dunes moved,over time. Then I was at the big hardware shop and found the type of wood chips I wanted, but they did not have enough. I also looked at a house in the forest, with no access road/driveway. I also looked at/stayed at a house in the regional town right next to my city. There was something in the middle of the dream that involved anxiety. There was a situation that I felt needed to be resolved, but it wasn't and I just left. it involved other people.

I was in a large plane and someone was doing a pilot's test, and doing a difficult tae off, down a side of a mountain, on a dirt runway. The brother of the pilot was also on the plane. He managed to successfully take off and we all clapped. I also was at an information desk at a university. A student came up and wanted to get home to her country quickly (with all of the travel restrictions currently in place). I referred them to student services, but she said they were no good so I started to help her to organise getting home.
I was in a car on a journey to deliver something to someone. There were some slight issues or hassles, or worry that I was not going to be able to deliver it.

I was travelling in my car, along a road near my house and suddenly everything went black, as though the streetlights and all electricity went out. Then there was like a flash of lightning. I could not see where I was driving and panicked, I put on the brakes, I don't think I smashed, but think somone smashed into the back of me.

I'm living at my family home again with my parents and sisters. My parents have been away for a period of time (days, weeks) and have just returned home. We're doing exercises on sexuality as a family, so we can all learn together. I try to borrow a book about sexuality from the library but it's a medical/ biomed science book and it's a medical library. I'm not allowed to borrow a book. Dr S contacts me to get the book because it's not available.   I'm with Steve, we step out a door and into a neighborhood street. The houses are double storey brick and they have palms on the front yard. There is a person in their front yard smiling and waving.   It looked like the street where I grew up in Perth. I felt like I was in Perth.   someone getting hair plugs to grow more hair. I feel like I should get hair plugs too.  There is a young girl who is dead on the street. There is a boy who is on love with her. She is there as a ghost with him.   I'm with a patient doing arm exercises to help them recover from a stroke.

I'm with a  young boy who is a prodigy and his mum,  in their house.  He wrote a book. He lives in a very wealthy neighborhood with lots of large houses. He is treated like a prince. I'm sitting with his father who is around 60 and has grey hair. I'm reading the boy's book, it looks like a children's book with pictures of castles. The pages are white with silver and pink illustrations. I think the book is quite good. His mum brings out a white cake that she made with icing piped into the words "Prince Daniel who had to give up his gardening", because he loves gardening and had to give it up to write the book.  I keep flipping through the book and realise there's more to it than I thought. There is a whole back section on marine sea life. I look down into my back pack and see sachets of Milo. I think of Steve and feel aroused.

I'm at a supermarket checkout. There is a display of mini travel shampoos and cosmetics on the checkout. They have really cute designs. I want to buy some for my sisters. I'm indecisive and picking up different bottles trying to decide how many to buy and which ones for which sister. I'm taking time to decide. I go through the checkout and the attendant scans my items. I feel like I've held up their time.  Then I'm at another supermarket checkout. They have a  give away where you can get gourmet biscuits if you have points. I'm looking at the biscuits, I want to get them all! The attendant offers to give me a collector's box that looks like a gingerbread train made of cardboard. I think "Gee their quality has improved ". The attendant says no other shops are doing this deal. I want to choose biscuits. At the checkout I realise it's my friend, Julie's, birthday. I haven't seen her for a long time. I want to get in touch with her and send a bottle of wine.   Still at a shop checkout, I find out my hot Latino boyfriend "Peter" is dead. I'm shocked. I found out by seeing his picture in a video magazine. He has long dark hair and he is an actor. His actor friends make a movie to commemorate him. They cast a young American actress with brown hair to be in the movie. I'm watching this woman and a young blonde man act out the same scene over and over again. They are watching something in the distance from a crowded bridge. She looks suddenly shocked, she turns to the man and he comforts her. Then someone yells "cut!" and they repeat .    I'm with Steve, my partner. We are angry about animal cruelty, especially against an ape that is locked up. Steve has a house set up and a pet dog. He wants me to join him. His sisters have given him a big box with house warming presents and baby clothes/ toys, hand me downs from their kids. I feel like I'm not joining him in this future. Steve and I are at my work, but it's not my work. Its a big clinical room with a kitchen. My manager Cynthia is there. I'm looking down into a sink or dirty dish water. Music by Queen is playing. They think why I can't be more like Steve. I look down, I've got bird poo on my left shoulder on my khaki colored t shirt. I'm disgusted. I think that clearly I've been standing around for too long. I need to change shirts for work.  I'm sitting on the floor with an old man. I think how I don't have the PPE to provide proper patient home visits for work. The lyrics "My island home is waiting for me" plays in my head.

I'm protesting in my mind, I can't see all the patients at work. There's too many, we're over capacity, we can't fit them in because we work from home half of the week, we're in COVID.  I'm in Steve's kitchen. Kylie passes me the tea towel. I feel like I'm having  the responsibility and onus of the team leader role passed down to me.  But the towel is scrunched, used and dirty, like I'm using it after her. I feel undervalued. Like I've been given the scraps and have to deal with the crap at work.

Matt and I are at the outdoor markets in the forest. We are buying trinkets and little soft toys. We are putting them on order to be delivered later. Matt is ignoring and dismissing me. I say to him "Do you just want to break up?". He agrees. I ask "Can we at least treat each other well in this process?". I feel sad but relieved. He is driving home to Ballarat but dropping my little sister off at home on the way. I'm near a lake with fountains, it is getting dark and rainy. I'm worried about my sister and whether Matt will take her home safely. I'm waiting for the things we ordered to be delivered. I'm still in the forest. People are coming from delivery trucks and delivering the things we bought. I'm waiting a while for them all to be delivered due to COVID. I'm feeling like I can't trust them to deliver everything and some things are not delivered. I'm mindful of keeping Matt's things separately, so I can give them to him later. I'm in the forest and it's raining. I feel under threat, like some natural disaster is imminent. I message my sister to see how she's going, whether she's home safe, what Matt is saying about me in the car.  different styles of work pants. Normal pants aren't available because of COVID.  I'm looking in a clothing catalogue. There are wide leg pants, straight leg pants.... but not the pants that I want.

I'm in the city (Melbourne) I'm going to the MCG to meet Steve. It feels like a routine day. I meet him at the stands in the MCG but it is really his work and he is busy working. There is activity and colour and other people around in the stands but I'm not interacting with them and I'm on my own. I walk around for a bit, feeling disorientated. Then the stands are my bed and I'm in bed waiting for Steve to finish work.  Then I'm in another building with my family. It feels like it's still in the MCG  but a different place and kind of like a concrete apartment. We're in an open kitchen/living area and we've all brought donuts. I'm trying to get Amy's attention but I feel like she's not seeing me and doesn't care. We're waiting for Steve so we can go to the city together. My mum is asking me what our future is. I look down, I'm not giving an answer, I feel like the relationship is over and I need to end it. Mum says "you looked so sad the other day, I thought it was over". I'm thinking my mum has a mother's intuition, in my mind I agree with what she is saying but I still don't say anything. I am saving donuts for Steve. I go into the city with my parents, sisters and brothers in law. We're in a city express style supermarket in the aisles. It is still stage 4 lockdown. But the supermarket is busy with people. Everyone is wearing winter jackets. No one is wearing a face mask, when this is mandatory. I feel angry and annoyed. But then I realise I'm not wearing my face mask and neither is anyone in my family. I feel worried and guilty. I pull the collar of my puffer jacket over my mouth and nose.       Then I'm alone in the city, it is getting darker. I want to walk down Lonsdale St to get to a clinic, I feel like it is the fertility clinic. There is a pharmacy at the start of the street. On the outside of the pharmacy building there are words saying "Early Supported Discharge Program" and a directional arrow pointing up the street, in the same direction where I want to walk. I start walking up this street but the road is all broken up, it is dusty, dirty, there are no people, there is scaffolding on the sides of the street, it is dark and deserted. I feel unsafe and turn in the other direction to get out. I feel like I'll have to get there another way , later, when COVID is over. I feel sad to see what COVID has done to my city.   Then it is afternoon again. I see Jonno and Sarah walking out of a grey/black stone building with a group of people , I feel it is their extended family but people I don't recognise. I'm not a guest and I'm watching from the other side of the road, removed from the situation. It is their wedding and they are celebrating. I'm confused because I know they got married in Dec 2019. Sarah is in a wedding dress, it is the dress she got married in last year but it looks like a different dress, she is pregnant. She is wearing a flower garland. I am still confused because I know they had a baby in real life in mid August. I think, they must be getting married again for their family because they're pregnant and want to get married before the baby arrives. But then there is a toddler girl there who is their daughter. They get into their car and I say congratulations. Then I'm watching Phantom of The Opera being performed in a theatre, but it's not Phantom of The Opera as I know it. They are performing parts of it but not as a whole. It is dramatic with elaborate props, make up and costumes. Then I'm in Stawell. I'm in a meeting with local council, community leaders and business. They're talking about hosting the One Night Stand concert, if the government supports it, otherwise they're ready to proceed. The building turns into a beautiful old Victorian, provincial style homestead. There are beige/grey rendered walls and black ornate features. It is a bed and breakfast accomodation. I'm with the owner who is a middle aged woman with blond hair. She talks about buying the building/business off her dad over a card game and turning it into an accommodation / continuing the business. I feel an urgency to book this accommodation so I can attend the One Night Stand concert. The council members are performing Phantom Of The Opera in the accommodation. The woman is in theatre make up with black feathers on her head and black hair cut short in a bob, 1920s style. There is deep blue, black, stars, fireworks. I want to watch the whole thing.  Then I am still in Stawell and still in the Victorian building but it has turned into a wedding. I feel like it is my wedding day but not. Aimee is there with some other women and it is a Hen's party.  They have penis straws. AImee is holding a straw, laughing, saying she doesn't really like the penis straws. I chuckle and say, "I don't mind them! If they're used in a decorative way or as a garden ornament" I indicate to a white paper crepe penis hanging in the breeze like bunting. There is a lot of off-white bunting, streamers and decorations swaying in the warm breeze, it feels like Spring.  We are still in Stawell, it is late afternoon, there is warm, soft light, the grass is yellow/grey and dry, like it is in Summer, it feels whimsical. We are being guided to walk down the road for the start of the wedding. There are more white decorations and art works. While I'm walking I'm thinking that we have to go back to the accommodation to get all our things when the wedding starts, hopefully it doesn't take too long to go back and we don't miss too much of the wedding. And I'm still waiting for Steve to arrive.

I'm in Singapore, I have no Singapore currency, only Australian currency. I'm worried that I don't have any money. I'm trying to make friends in Singapore. I walk down a long path outdoors through forest, under trees and vines and along narrow cliff tops. I come to a clearing where there is a group of Asian men who are socialising. I recognise some of them as old uni friends. They won't let me be a part of their group. I feel rejected and turn to leave and try to get home. I end up walking through a busy city florist.  Then it's my birthday. I'm with my mum, dad, sister Amy and brother in law Adam. We're at a shop and I'm walking the aisles looking for birthday cards. The shop keeps changing. They give me presents. I've bought them tiny rabbit socks . They say "what do I do with this??" . I'm slightly offended, I say "you can wear them on your fingers or use them as a make up applicator!". I get up and leave, then I'm walking in a city street within a crowd of random people. I've said something to offend a man next to me in the crowd. He looks like my old maths teacher. I'm in a clothing department store but it's my home. I can see a young man with dark hair. He's broken in. He's walking amongst the racks of clothes. I'm trying to stop him but he's not listening. I feel powerless and violated. He's running through the aisles, I'm running after him, shouting and swearing at him.  I'm at Steve's (my partner) house. But it's not his house. It feels like an old townhouse in England. Steve has ordered lingerie for me. He ordered lacy body suits. He said it is black and dark green and shows me the colours on a sample of Terry toweling. He chose green because he remembered it's my favorite colour. The lingerie arrives in  the mail but the lacy leggings are fluro green. I think "I can't wear this!! I'll have to return it". But I put it on and feel really sexy and aroused. I think "I need to buy more", I think I can use the money I collected from my colleagues. I feel guilty but I think "I'll work it out  , it'll be fair". I see 2 small flower arrangements in jars, the arrangements were made by my mum but the flowers are starting to die. I'm still in the bright green lacy lingerie leggings. I'm trying to cover it up so no one will see them in public. I go into a swimming pool in the leggings. I'm trying to find other lingerie leggings I can wear. I want to show Steve.  Kylie is at the front door. I think "Kylie has lots of lingerie , she'll help me". But she comes in and says she can't spend time with me.  A moment later I see her leaving in a new out fit, holding a fresh bunch of flowers. I feel upset that she couldn't spend time with me but had time to go out and be with others.

I had won a trip to the USA but when I got there, there was a massive explosion and everyone died. I feel like I knew it was going to happen. I was alive, looking on after the event, but I had died. I was wondering how it could've been prevented.  Steve and I were traveling home on a bus at the end of the day. It was a cloudy late afternoon/ early evening. We could see trees had fallen down everywhere, like in a storm.  We got out of the bus and tried to clean up the fallen trees. I felt sad and a sense of loss and wanted to save the environment. I was trying to teach the other people who were there, how to save the environment.  I'm getting in line to board a cruise ship/ bus for a work event. I'm waking through the aisles to check in and trying to sneak past my managers to sneak Steve on board. We all have luggage as though it's a holiday. In the mean time, as I'm walking down a path in the check in (but its like a street) I see Abe. I see him twice. The first time I want to say hi but don't because of the negative circumstances around how our relationship ended. When I see him the second time, I go up and say hi. He tells me he has 2 kids now, who are 4 and 8 years old. I think this doesn't make sense because we were in a relationship 3 years ago and he didn't have kids. He was holding a child and looked fatherly and then he changed to look more like a woman. I thought how much he had changed since I knew him. I felt angry and jealous that he had a family now but I didn't, especially when he made a big deal about not wanting kids yet when we were together.  I then come to being on a big boat in the ocean with Steve and my colleagues.  The boat staff take us out on smaller boats to our own small individual cruise boats where we'll spend the night. There is a beautiful sunset. The next day we come back to the main boat. Everyone was given two boxes of breakfast food, but I only got one and felt like I missed out. I opened the box and there was cereal. I ate the cereal and could taste it and feel the texture in my mouth. Then I had this massive bowl of pasta in front of me. I couldn't eat it all.  There was a huge buffet and so much food, I didn't know where to start. But we couldn't stay, I had to then get up and leave to get on the boat to go home. We're lining up to get on the boat but I feel really disoriented and lose the group. Steve gets on the boat before me. When I get to the boat, they don't let me on because the boat is full. A male colleague and I can't board the boat. I feel angry that they didn't consider us and no one counted that everyone in the group was there before boarding. I felt the managers should have done that but then I think "well,  we're all adults, not school kids". I'm angry that Steve wasn't meant to be there in the first place but he took my place on the boat home. I'm angry that they had capacity to bring us out here but not to take us all back. We try to book another boat back but the next one is on Wednesday which is 3 days away. We have to self fund our return ticket and it is expensive.I think "I hope this is tax deductible!". I go to get my credit card but I can only find old, expired credit cards in my wallet. I worry that Steve has taken all my things with him onto the boat and now I have no clothes or money. Then I find my credit card and I realise I have all that I need. I feel attracted to the male colleague with me. I feel hopeful that something romantic will happen between us. But I feel like he doesn't notice me. I feel like I need to stick with him so I'm not alone and don't accidentally miss the next boat. The colleague then turns into Adam. We walk through a gift shop at the boat terminal and I'm looking at note pads with funny faces on them and think if I should buy a souvinear for Steve. It turns out that we're on an island and we get into a taxi to take us to our rooms. The sun is setting on the beautiful landscape and trees on the island and I think " actually, I think I'm going to really enjoy these 3 days".

I was at home but at work at the same time. I think Kylie (my team leader and close friend) was there. I was not able to see patients due to COVID and I was explaining to patients that they would not be seen at home as usual due to the COVID restrictions. I felt a little sad that I was letting patients down. Then I was at Steve's (my partner) house, in the kitchen, standing at the stove top with the light on, looking down at the pan, cooking Lomo Saltado I was pushing the meat around the pan with the spatula and thinking about how I had done this the night before.

I'm spontaneously going on a trip to Europe. I feel anxious because I haven't planned anything. But then I realise that Steve and Kristy are coming too. We're in an area with mountains. Kristy is doing a separate tour. She is nervous because she has never been on a tour and is worried that some people on the tour don't like her. Steve and I are encouraging/reassuring her and telling her that she doesn't have to be friends with everyone to have a good time.   I'm watching 2 actors perform a scene in a small theatre. the set is a bedroom with just a bed, one actor is trying to leave and drops a candle lit lamp on the floor and it breaks. I'm the only person in the audience.   I'm looking down from the ceiling onto a row of women cheering and clapping. I'm in the row of women and I'm watching myself. Each woman is taking a turn to walk down the row of women, like a cat walk, but trying different styles of walking. The women cheer each other on.  It's an acting work shop and everyone is trying different ways of self expression. I feel nervous waiting for my turn but also confident. I feel like my confidence infront of others has improved and I'm more open.

I was in South East Asia, helping to work to prevent climate change. I was traveling from place to place and mindful that a threat was coming, like bad weather was on the horizon. I'm trying to be resourceful and make things from recycled and reused scrap materials. I'm trying to get to my sister but I can't go there because I'm not allowed and physically can't get to where she is. I'm making letters to send to  people, I'm putting round stickers with pictures to seal the letter but when I peel off the sticker my finger rubs off half the picture from the front of the sticker.

It's Julie's birthday. I'm with her and her high school friends. We're out in the bush, sitting along a long carriage that's driving up and down a rural road amongst trees and bushland. It is a sunny day. We're chatting, dancing, playing music and drinking cocktails. I'm trying to tell Julie about my boyfriend Michael. He has been abusing me. We are trying to plan a future together but he grabs a knife and stabs me several times in the left forearm. It's like I'm in both the past moment experiencing this attack and also with my friend in the present at the same time. I look down to my arm and I can see the wounds from the knife. I'm at my parent's house and trying to tell my parents about the attack.  They have mail for me. It is a home made card from my friend Markus in Austria. I open the card and it is colorful and glittery. Michael is there but I'm excluding him. I'm back at Julie's party. The party has continued into the city. We meet at a restaurant. I get there first and have a coffee on my own. When the others arrive we order food and drinks but we order too much for what we need.  We go indoor rock climbing on the wall but the hand holds are individual vertebrae. I think " I have to tell Julie about my boyfriend". The restaurant turns into her house but its not her real home. We're alone in her kitchen. I love her kitchen, it's quaint but modern. I feel at a loss, that she has a family and a family home but I don't have that. I feel like we're talking about my relationship without saying a word. I  think about how I want a kitchen like this once I have my family home.

It's Kristy's birthday. I've organised a card and a collection for a gift from random people who I don't know.  Kristy is standing there naked and she has a huge penis. I'm shocked and perplexed, thinking "that's not right!". Then I wonder how she and my brother in law have sex if she has a penis! Then I think they have a good sex life and I really need to be more sexual.  I'm in a foreign city walking the streets at night. I know I shouldn't be out after COVID curfew. I feel disoriented. I walk into someone's house but fear for my safety. I feel like I'm going to be attacked. I see coloured tiles on the ground and collectibles that were  taken from a woman who died.  Then I'm on holidays with Steve. We stop at a McDonalds because I have to go to the toilet. The staff say I can use the toilet. I walk through the door but I feel like I enter a hotel room that is still in use. There are someone's toiletry bags in the bathroom. There are 3 or 4 cleaners cleaning the room at the same time. I go to the toilet but feel exposed. I want to complain to the manager. But then the room turns into a self help group. There is a group facilitator who is a woman with big hair and make up. She sits next to me and I tell her that I want to leave my relationship. She tells me that I need to talk to Steve about it. I'm mindful that Steve is there. He comes and we leave together.

I'm a participant in the TV show 'Further Back In Time For Dinner'. We're in a warehouse /studio style building in groups, cooking chicken like they did in the  'old days'. I was mindful about dressing up in office style clothes ( cardigan and skirt) and heels. I arrived in the car park and saw my colleague stepping out of her car at the same time, I was surprised and happy to see her there and we walked into the studio together. one of the other participants in the show, who is a teenage girl, is dressing in lingerie and trying to seduce me. She wants to grow up and learn sex skills. I'm curious and intrigued but then I say no to her because she's only a teenager and I'm not a lesbian. I think about how I'm glad I'm past the stage of being a teenager who is inexperienced in sex and life. I think how "sex isn't that great anyway and it's not that big a deal!" .This teenage girl was disappointed and sulking.  I also remember being in a city toilet block and it was dirty and filthy, there were random men there, I was disgusted and left. I went to a hospital to have fertility treatment. I was standing at the service desk with a nurse on the other side. She was giving me medication scripts and I had to double check the names of all the drugs. I was thinking that it was a lot of pressure and this wasn't my job. Then she passed me multiple tablets and syringes containing medications. I had to take the tablets and administer the drugs via the injections. I felt lonely and sad that I had to do this and go through it by myself.

I'm at a funeral and looking at the coffin on the stand. It's the funeral for Matt. I am shocked/ saddened that he died but not surprised as I felt he didn't look after his health. A past neuroscience tutor of mine is leading the service.  I'm sorting through rubbish that I have collected in the boot of a car aswell as my own possessions. I'm trying to reduce litter and make sure rubbish is recycled and disposed of properly. I'm decluttering and getting rid of the things I don't use anymore. I pick up plastic bottles/ containers that I had found on the street and empty them. They are full of water and one is full of drugs of different shapes, colours  and sizes. The drugs are going everywhere and I'm trying to contain them and get them back in the container but they're going everywhere in the back of the car.

I was at work and I was working as the team leader. I was in an office on an island overlooking the sea. It was nighttime. There is a black snake in the room. It is curled up on top of my bag. It is flicking it's black fork tongue in and out. I'm worried it will bite me. I pick it up and it doesn't bite. It is crawling around the room but mainly stays curled up on my bag. I feel like it's my friend but it is also threatening.  There is a cruel medieval regime that has power. The environment looks like a set from Game of Thrones. I'm in a medieval city with the stone buildings and people wearing medieval clothes. They are taking people and murdering them in horrific ways just for doing the wrong thing. They have caught me and I'm scared about how I might die. They have also caught Kylie and her sister. I see them get killed. I worry about their mum who will now be alone. I'm killed but I don't know how, it is not as horrific so I feel I have some mercy. I see all the powerful leaders killed one by one. I feel relieved that this regime won't go on.   I'm back at work with my colleagues. My colleague Claire needs us to babysit her daughter. I'm surprised, I didn't know she had a daughter! Her daughter has blonde hair like her. She is about 4 or 5 and is wearing a little school back pack. Her daughter doesn't like school. She is very cheeky. Claire comes back to pick her up. She holds her and says "You don't like school, awww", she puts her in the back seat of the car and then drives away back home.

I'm trying to get a patient online access to be seen over telehealth due to the COVID restrictions. It's frustrating and stressful.   I'm moving into a new team at work. I'm trying to settle into new routines and understand who is seeing which patients and who is taking new referrals. I'm trying to refer patients to other people. I feel busy and stressed. A patient gives me a box of baklava as a gift. I eat a few. I see him in the waiting room with 3 other boxes of baklava, I give him my box.   I'm putting my work as a Physio on hold and decide to work as a clown visiting sick kids in the children's hospital. I have a list of kids to visit and I'm carrying helium balloons to take to each child. I'm dressed in a clown outfit. I'm going up and down the floors of the hospital and getting lost and disoriented and can't find the ward I need to go to. The patient's parents are getting angry at me for making mistakes and getting lost and not getting to the right ward in time.
I was sleeping in my bed and someone was breaking into my house through the bedroom window. They were wearing a black adidas tracksuit.

I had a friend I haven’t seen for many years round for dinner. She has just had a baby and the baby was there too but I had to look after it and it’s was newborn but it could talk. My friend was trying to teach me how to carve the ham she had brought over but I was really scared because I had a giant very sharp knife and I thought I would slip and cut myself. I couldn’t cut the ham well so my friend took Over. Then she got changed into a nurse uniform and cycle to work. The baby explained that my friend couldn’t miss a shift because she had been stood down and would have no work soon.

I went to the beach with my sister and a friend who I am actually going to see today. The beach was halfway between Sydney and Melbourne and in a fictional place that was known for having dirty beaches. We arrived at the beach and it was beautiful and we started kayaking and swimming. At first there was no one there but then lots and lots of people arrived and it became unpleasant. There was a man living in a giant kayak floating on the water and his toilet emptied into the ocean. He went to the toilet and flushed it where we were all swimming and the water became a bit murky and the air smelt like shit. I noticed an old colonial house on the cliff above the beach that was open as a museum. I swam to the shore and my sister and friend had already gone and changed out of their bathers. We were leaving as it was now unpleasant.

I’m in a war zone in the middle east in a hotel in a shopping mall crouched under a tarpaulin crawling round on dirt trying not to get shot. I’m with one other person, a male love interest. We are both trying not to die, we try to escape using the elevator which is huge and all glass but can’t work out how to get into it and it’s moving so fast we can’t get in it.  Now I’m at a big dinner with friends who are doing a university course together. Im not doing the course but they are celebrating end of semester. It’s a long banquet table and they are all going to Egypt for a university subject and they tell me how four of them paid $10,000 to buy one foreign coin and only one of them could keep it. They are embarrassed to have wasted so much money. They tease a woman who went to a ball and ate dinner but not dessert and vomited because she didn’t eat dessert. An old love interest of mine appears and I pretend not to be interested in him anymore. He had just finished the course my other friends are doing.

I was at a wedding with my family. It was the wedding of someone I used to live with’s brother. I haven’t seen her for 15 years. I walk around while things are being set up and take off my shoes and walk on the grass, pan flute music plays in the background. My mums friend is talking to me but I want to get away because the wedding is starting, her son whispers a joke in my ear. Now the wedding really is starting so I take a seat on my own behind my sister in law. Some of the bridesmaids are sick so some people had to stand in and this has caused fights within the bridal party and one woman gets told to sit back down even though she was a stand in bridesmaid. The bride comes out and she’s drawn a mono brow on her face. She is almost in recognizable. One bridesmaid is distraught because she is in love with the groom and everyone knows it. She is sobbing during the ceremony. I get into a conversation about dresses with my sister in law and some other people around is.
I was working at the medieval equivalent of the Australian open. Then it turned into a war. But we didn’t have enough money to fund the army. I was in the army. It was a medieval type army.
I was living with a group of people and we had to renegotiate the lease on our house. It was really hard and stressful.

I was staying in an apartment in a city in Europe, except the owner didn't know, so it was more like squatting. The owner was going to come back, so I had to get out of there quickly. I remember having a shower and trying to find a clean towel, and then suddenly my sister was there, in the midst of having a nervous breakdown.

I had got a new teaching job, and for some reason this involved sharing a house with a number of other new teachers in a narrow terraced house. The house had a name written above the door, but We had decided to change it. I got to know the other teachers, who were from all over the world. At one point, we visited a chemist to buy various things, including sanitary pads. When I got back to the house, I realised I had my period and was bleeding profusely, with drops all over the bathroom floor. I spent a long time cleaning the bathroom and myself, but luckily we had pads, so I was satisfied that no one would notice.

My husband was made the manager of his favourite football team. I couldn't believe it, because he wasn't in the same country as them, and was still employed in his regular job.  But I texted my parents to tell them and then thought maybe I should Google it to make sure.

I was on some kind of trip with a group of friends from work; it may have been a conference of some kind. The men in the group decided they would try to pick up women, take them back to their caravans  (our accommodation), while other friends (men and women) would hide and record the dates. It wasn't about filming them having sex; it was about seeing who had the smoothest moves and slickest lines. I was appalled and confused, not least because one of the men involved was gay, and another married. But everyone else thought it was a hilarious game. Then the action moved to my childhood home, and I was trying to order t-shirts for everyone. The conference was still happening. My boss had told me to order some new t-shirts before going on leave, but the operations assistant said I had to order a cheaper version, with less vivid colours. But I knew my boss wouldn't be happy about this. I was also organising all this while trying to have a shower and looking for the soap and shampoo, which we had run out of.

I was reliving an event from my past, but it was like watching a movie of it. It was the time I was 19 and travelled to another city to try and get a job in a theme park where a good friend worked. I was both reliving it and watching it happen, so although I knew I wouldn't get the job, there was still excitement. I was also very much feeling like the awkward 19 year old I was, and wishing I had more confidence and self-belief at the same time.

I took my friend to my hairdresser after she hadn't been for months because of lockdown. She hated hairdressers and didn't really want to get her hair cut but I insisted. My friend wanted the hairdresser to give her layers and a fringe, but the hairdresser was reluctant. In the end, I convinced the hairdresser to put in the layers, and I thought my friend looked great. But she still wasn't happy. Then she had to pay, and I suddenly felt really bad because I remembered my friend was unemployed and didn't have much money, and my hairdresser was very expensive. But my friend paid, using all the money she had. We left, and as we walked home, I spent the whole time trying to convince her that she looked good and it was money well spent.

I was taking a group of kids to the movies; they were part of a youth group from my father's church. It was a night time screening, but I had calculated that it wouldn't finish too late. We lined up for the tickets and were directed to a big theatre, but instead of a cinema screen, there were comedy performers taking part in a comedy festival. But we were told that the movie would start after the festival. We watched and waited. The comedy wasn't really child-appropriate and at one point it started to rain and we realised the roof was open. By this time it was close to midnight and the kids were falling asleep. I was also panicking because I thought the kids' parents would be worried and I felt I had let my father down. We decided to leave and ask for a refund on the tickets. When I got back to my car to take the kids home, only two were with me. I was told the rest had walked home! I started to drive the two kids home, but I got lost driving through unknown streets.

I was back at school and I was a new student. When I entered the classroom, I had to find a place to sit but all the chairs were impossibly small, like in a kindergarten. There were also a bunch of bitchy girls, who I was trying to avoid sitting too close to. When the teacher came in, he gave us writing work to do, which I thought was very easy. But I found that I couldn't write as neatly as I wanted to. I became very frustrated, because I had a crush on the teacher and wanted to impress him.
I was in an apartment. I was trying to find my cat, who I had let out but who hadn't come back. There were mice in the room where I was sleeping and I needed my cat to come home and get rid of them.

I dreamt that my daughter had been beaten to death while I sat working in my home office. The killer had crept into the house and I hadn't even noticed. When the police broke the news to me,  I screamed and screamed and screamed.

I was friends with the British royal family. They lived in a small village in what looked like the Alps or Austria. The dream jumped between two times - the present and the past.
