In the present some of staff that worked for the royal family were now tour guides and not talking to each other.   In the past I was staying with Kate and Wills and their children asked why they were so special. I said they were awesome just like their parents. I didn’t feel comfortable exposing to them they were princes/princesses.

I was at a different site to what I normally work at and I had to open the museum all by myself. I had not been trained in the alarm system or even remember where keys were kept. Some colleagues were quiet snippy that I didn’t know this information whilst others tried to show me. As we were trying to close the museum ready for me to open the next day a man came in to buy a gift and let lots of other visitors in. I kept trying to learn the new opening procedure whilst trying to help the visitors and get them out.
I was going around the zoo again. It was sunny and light and I saw lots of animals.

one was about starting university when I was 19 and meeting and getting enamored with a boy my age after only being on campus for about an hour. It was a cheerful funny blushing kind of dream! Then I had some strange complicated dream that seemed to involve prosthetic limbs dropping off...bit creepy. The main dream I remember is ...I imagined a sort of kinetic housing. Huge modular blocky modern apartments that people could customise. You could enclose your balcony with a big windowed hood...like a giant BBQ lid(!) You could change the shape of your living room and bedrooms by changing the angles of the boxes with your windows to follow or avoid the sun. I imagined the building changing shape as blocks were tilted and shifted to suit the inhabitants. I also imagined separate, safe walkways and stairs leading to each apartment. Low rise only two or three storeys...really organic with lots of places to for people to grow their own food on platforms near their front doors.

My Dad, step mother, step sister, niece and nephew were staying in a holiday house on a farm. At the start of the dream it was a holiday but by the end we all just permanently lived there. It was dark and very 80s decor.  I think I was younger, around 18 or 19 years old.  There was a shed with lots and lots of hay bails which I had to shovel. The hay had lots of rats and I was scared.  At some point my Dad and I went to the pub. It was a very Australian country pub, lots of wood in the decor, a bit dark. And it was next to a swampy river. My Dad and I had a great time drinking cocktails and got very very drunk. I didn't think I was that drunk so I drove home but later I felt really guilty and knew I should not have driven as I was drunk.  At some point some people I met in 2017 when I travelled to New Orleans were in the holiday home. My family were no longer there but the people from New Orleans were filming a reality tv show and creating conflict for the cameras.  Then I was back at the pub with my friends. Something happened here but I now can't remember what. I remember walking down a street I know in Bourke (NSW) and telling someone about another dream I had had this week, detailing it.

I won a scholarship for theatre directing and was sent to the UK. I met the Queen, Gillian Anderson and the actor who plays Princess Anne in The Crown. I then performed in a large arena like the Edinburgh Tattoo with a big projected monster. The monster was large dark shadows which eventually came to life and turned real. It then chased me. My Mum and dad needed to go to hospital. They told me whilst sitting in my Mums back garden and it was sunny. Not sure what was wrong with them. I knew it was going to be difficult to get them to the hospital. My little brother Joe and I had to take them on a bus. We lost my Dad on the way - I think he went to buy beers. We got mum to the hospital but we weren’t allowed in. We had to leave her there which was hard. We decided to go buy gifts for her.   Then I was part of Superheroes group trying to save the world. It was dark

I was marching and got caught in Black Lives Matter protest in New Orleans. A man drove through the protest.   Ftagbwieeens in there.  A murder happened being investigated by me, but no rights.  Back at my old job but my mum worked there. A new co-worker fought with me as I laughed at her for being dramatic/saying mean things to my mum.  On way to new subway restaurant a very fat toddler dressed in light blur rolled down a gutter into the road and his elderly male grandfather/carer didn’t seem to get to him in time or notice he was about to be run over. I ran and picked the fat toddler up and stopped him from being run over. I was panicked and worried as the elderly man and child looked disheveled. Child was safe but I was scared for them.   All the Stores were shutting down everywhere. Could not get lunch.

I was part of superheroes trying to save the world. We were in China and we were caught. One of my superhero colleague was burnt at a stake, the mutilated penis cut off and bled to death. A third survived. I saw their remains.   I was then desperate to get postage stamps to send all of the posts cards I had found in my suitcase. swapped to being in France in an airport searching for postage stamps. Then the airport was attacked. Lots of bombs and explosions.   We then Escaped on a private jet with a rockstar and had a party.   Went home to my Mum’s house who had family over. Joseph and his friend was there. Someone had died.

I was in Ru Paul's Drag Race competing. It felt very stressful. I remember being backstage waiting anxiously to hear the judges verdicts and not knowing what was happening or where I was supposed to be. It was dark backstage with a big purple satin ruffled dress. I was alone. I was anxious to know if I had made it through to the next round.
I felt very stressed and felt as if time was running out, that plans were not coming to fruition
I was in a competition. having to compete in something and feeling very stressed about it.

one was about starting university when I was 19 and meeting and getting enamored with a boy my age after only being on campus for about an hour. It was a cheerful funny blushing kind of dream! Then I had some strange complicated dream that seemed to involve prosthetic limbs dropping off...bit creepy. The main dream I remember is ...I imagined a sort of kinetic housing. Huge modular blocky modern apartments that people could customise. You could enclose your balcony with a big windowed hood...like a giant BBQ lid(!) You could change the shape of your living room and bedrooms by changing the angles of the boxes with your windows to follow or avoid the sun. I imagined the building changing shape as blocks were tilted and shifted to suit the inhabitants. I also imagined separate, safe walkways and stairs leading to each apartment. Low rise only two or three storeys...really organic with lots of places to for people to grow their own food on platforms near their front doors.

I went to meet friends at a street festival. The place was a bit like Hobart, the 'Salamanca' waterside area...lots of old heritage buildings arranged around a waterfront.   I walked up a flagstoned lane between sandstone warehouses with weather beaten wooden hatches and rusted iron stays. I headed alone towards the crowds around the festival site. There were different themed events in each building. An old stone pub was decked out as a pirate haven. One of the waterfront buildings had a 'haunted arctic' theme to it. I wandered around the venues trying to connect with my friends...weaving between crowds and the weirdly themed buildings. Each one was like a film set. I was becoming increasingly frustrated as I couldn't locate my friends and my mobile phone had developed a surreal bug where it was aging...the OS was crumbling and becoming Windows 7. Out of frustration I tried to go to or find a 'reception' area to get some help to locate my friends. I just couldn't find anyone to help...everything was surreal and unfathomable. No one could point me in the right direction or really help me. I wandered into a hotel in a 50's style, got lost in the stairways and weird empty lobbies twisting around a central atrium. I had to get out of the maze and finally exited and went to the next confusing space. This was the pirate themed bar...again I was searching for friends with no luck. I got tangled in a set of elevated stairways and planked walkways tied together with rough shipping ropes above the bar area. Then finally found my way back to ground level...I reached for my phone in another attempt to communicate.  My phone had such a bad 'aging virus' that it had, in fact, turned into a small leather bound book...a small Bible! Miraculously my youngest son appeared and I tried to get his help to 'fix my phone'. He took the book, curved it into a scroll... which flexed the edges of the pages...written along the edge of the pages was the 'key' a series of numbers and symbols which would 'unlock' my phone from it's ancient state and make it usable again. My son exclaimed that the hackers must have changed the code because (checking with this own mobile) he couldn't unlock my phone.   With that, he apologised and went to greet his own friends...leaving me feeling a bit lost in the crowd.

I am in a tense situation where  a problem must be solved, but I lack either the means or power to resolve the issue at ha hnd. the setting was my old boarding school nestled in the British countryside.  It was dark dauntingly overwhelmingly dark. The lights inside the main house glowed feebly. Frensham Heights is a grand old set of buildings...main house was where the girls dorms are. I came in through the main entrance with a sense of heavy trepidation...I think there had been a disappearance or crime of some sort and I felt compelled to try and help solve the mystery. I met with old staff members and tried to make sense of the unfortunate event...i was wandering the grounds in the dark. People with torches were searching around..I was just left with a heavy sense of foreboding and mystery...

I went to visit a friend at her house. It was the first time I'd been there. The house was very strange...not a single flat surface in an ancient stone building on the waterfront. I wandered in behind her as she headed to the kitchen. The floors were sloping and the whole kitchen leaned on an angle to the windows which opened right out to the ocean. I looked out the windows and the waves were breaking on big rocks right outside.   A couple of my friend's house mates joined us in the kitchen. I started to feel uneasy and wanted to call the visit to an end. No one was being unfriendly, they we just pottering around the kitchen making snacks and idle chit chat. I just felt uncomfortable in the topsy turvy house with the ocean lapping at the side! So, I made my excuses and made my way out.  I walked towards my car, got in and set off to drive home. I got lost, the streets seemed to have rearranged themselves. What had been familiar now seemed surreal, twisted and confusing. In the end I had to stop the car after going around in loops for a long time. I stopped because the street ahead had actually shrunk to the width of a skateboard...it had curved and curled around the base of a tree. I was left bewildered...staring at the strange shrunken road and marvelling at how odd it was.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: I was working as a researcher at an old fashioned business in the city of Sydney. I was grilling the staff with loads of questions about how they do their business and how they work with their customers. the business may have been a travel agents...the shop was old and in an antique looking mall like the Strand in Sydney. There was a clutter of suitcases on display and at least five or six staff. I was working with an old colleague from London who I haven't seen for over 20 years. Matt and I worked with the staff for days until they became a bit sick of us being around. I promised that 'today is the last day of our incessant questions! I promise'...so Matt and I went to the Queen Victoria Building and decided to get a nice gift for our helpful shop staff. We went to Haighs and bought them chocolate treats and then decided to stop for coffee next door.   Suddenly there was a panic of shouting and police sirens, vans and ambulances all screeching up to the QVB. All the customers had a sense of panic and imminent danger. Then there was a terrible, acrid smell. I think it made me physically gasp in my sleep. It was a hideous, sour, chemical smell. Then I overheard someone shouting that a 'meth lab' nearby had exploded. So we all grappled with our various bags, and fished out our masks to protect us from the toxic gas.

a dark cobbled street in an old town ...somewhere ancient and a bit Gothic. Prague perhaps. It was an oppressive dark...the street lights were dimmed and there was a beautiful, slim, lithe ballet dancer...alone, dancing on the cobbles. I fretted about her pointe shoes getting caught between the stones. I wondered if she might injure herself, sprain an ankle on the un even surface. I worried that she'd ruin her satin ballet shoes in the mud.

I was on a huge luxury yacht out in the ocean. There was an AI research team on board and they were experimenting with robotics. There were three of us women aboard...seemingly along for the ride, not part of the research team. The robot that interacted with us was so threatening and psychologically creepy it upset all of us (three women) I finally had enough of the behaviours but we set about to destroy the robot. I partially dismantled it and threw it overboard. The reaction of the researchers was understandably rather angry and disappointed. We had an angry debate about the nature of their work and the focus of their research. "that robot of yours was pernicious, it made all three of us cry"...we confronted them about their motives and their design objectives. There was a lot of tension and mistrust on board between us and the researchers....then My first boyfriend Jason appears and he is there speaking wth Jacob Collier about their research and design work in robotics. robots only go wrong or behave dangerously if they become 'jealous' or if someone gets between them and their maker...

8 members of my church came to my home to watch something in particular and also the ex vicar and his wife came.  She was wearing a beautiful of white coat with black lines/ squares on it and a belt. We all watched the programme then at the end the ex vicar and wife got up,  put their costs on and left.  they spoke to me and my husband but no-one else.  Then their was a programme about Gloucester cathedral choir

I was in a large red brick house, i lived  there and it was day time.  a man came and carried a tree from my house to his and i looked over a large lawn as he walked off with it.  i think my husband was with me.   I was then  upstairs in another building, old like a university building or manor house.  i think i was with my husband.  as i left a man I found attractive with dark hair and a short neat beard wearing a bright green emerald green coat kissed me and I kissed him back.   I wad then on  sea front top of the harbour I think it was Beer in Devon and I was with Sue Kinross and a young woman came to us and spoke in French and asked us if we were 20 and Sue repleid 'no sixty' in French and I said 'aussi'.
my husband was painting a fence in our back garden send that it was dark grey and he was painting light orange on it but big areas but not covering it completely.
some plans I had made were being put on hold because of unforeseen circumstances.

I was on my way to the airport to catch a flight to India, but had stopped at a shopping centre for an unspecified reason. I was with several people who were known to me. I was carrying a small shoulder bag like an evening bag containing my wallet, passport, credit cards etc. One of my companions commented that my bag fears not securely closed, and I informed her that it never closed properly. When I reached down to fiddle with the flap I noticed my bag was empty. the police station at which I reported the theft was the station at Atari. I was distressed trying to think how I could get access to funds when I would have to cancel all my cards before I left Australia and could not get new ones. I wasn’t worried about the loss of my passport, strangely.

I was trying to remember how to perform the Highland dance ‘Blue Bonnets’ and was having difficulty with one of the steps. I was in the dancing studio in Mackay where I first learnt Highland in my early 40s. I was alone, and it was afternoon. From there, it seems I abruptly transitioned I to worrying about whether I would complete my CPD requirements for my Pharmacist registration this year. I was speaking with someone, asking them how I could be expected to complete so many hours of professional development activity when I worked 6 days per week and commuted for another 12 hours each week. I was very upset and angry, and scared I was going to be deregistered if I didn’t complete the total hours.

Buckbeak Icecream sandwiches Christmas Jumpers Range Rovers Old dorms and houses Dan Oneill - old friend We had to get away from somewhere On different days we had to wear different jumpers There was someone trying to break into the complex

I was in a house with lots of friends from uni, we were doing a lot of cocaine together. I went downstairs at one point and there was a woman with a torch who was trying to get into the house - she had a knife and fork as weapons.  I had to call my friend to come downstairs because I became paralysed from the drugs and couldn't move my hands or do anything to stop the woman coming in.  My friend came down and restrained her

Was at some sort of festival - my friend and her housemate was there and my boyfriend too.  My friend Susie and my boyfriend were telling me that they didn't want to drink or do any drugs because they had worked hard to be in good shape and they didn't want to ruin that because they knew if they did then they would eat all of the crap food that we had brought with us.  It was really muddy and we had pitched tents on a muddy hill.  The girls of the group went on a boat trip - I remember saying it was Perth and that we were in the wrong part of the water to see what we'd come to see, but it didn't look like Perth. It was cold and hilly.

There was a hill with goats at the top. Poultry was going bad - we had to somehow pick the meat apart from the bones. This was a new job that was supposedly going to make everything ok. Bruce was there and I needed to find a way to talk to him. We were in a huge house - maybe Bruce's family house? Aaron, a cinematographer I have worked with before, was there - we were swapping things, both filming for a new tv show Everything was about getting the right angle Different animals as well as goats were on the hill - the hill was on the beach

being in a small boat with my boyfriend - or maybe he was in a separate small boat, but we were together. We had to cross some rivers and there being really tall bridges and hills around us, we were hiding from something.  My family from England were in the dream, and so was an old colleague. I'm a filmmaker and I think I was filming teh experience.  There was a guy who had killed many people and was morbidly obese that we were chasing.  my boyfriend shouting at me as I wasn't concentrating and water was getting into my boat as we were paddling.

a couple of my friends. It took place at a kind of cross between a school and a university, but it was definitely a campus environment. At a pool, I was telling kids why not being able to do a gap year wasn't the worst thing in the world to happen to them.  Maybe it was a sort of induction day. I was in a dance competition and also watching people perform A Midsummer Nights Dream. At one point I was running through the streets to get back to the campus, either with dogs or watching dogs, trying to get there on time.

My friend Chrissy and I are babysitting for a couple, Marcia and Rune, that we know through church. We get to their house and it’s like two separate houses. There’s one part of their house facing the street, on the right of that is another house, and on the right of that is the continuation of their house. So there’s a random house between the two bits of their houses. The two bits are connected by a corridor which runs along the back of the random middle house. We mainly spend time in the far right house. We greet Marcia and Rune and the baby is supposed to be asleep. but he comes out wearing only a nappy and is walking around with a kind of circular baby walker. Marcia and Rune go to the movies but at some point Chrissy and I are also at the movies, like we swapped places with them. Then suddenly we realise someone has set fire to the other part of the house, not the part we’re in. I know it’s arson but i don’t know who did it. There’s a great sense of sadness because apparently an old Greek lady live there and all her stuff is gone. It was a tiny room and her entire life had fit in there.

My friend Jen is telling me that her friend who I’m supposed to know if getting married. It’s in Germany in September and she wants me there to ‘give her away’ as she’s in her 50s and her parents have died. I find this very odd and say that I can’t get to Germany because of Covid. Jen says sure you can you’ll find a way. I say then what about quarantine on the way back? And she says I should just do it. It’s like she doesn’t think it’s a problem at all. We are having this conversation in another country already but I’m not sure which one. We’re all helping look after this foster child. My husband isn’t there and I wonder if i should go straight to Germany from here even though the wedding is in September which is 2 months away in the dream. The foster kid needs sneakers and Jen makes these shoes out of fold up cardboard.

I was at a Trump rally. Even though i’ve never been to a trump rally or even watched one on tv I knew it was a trump rally. I don’t know why I was there or who I was with. It was held indoors at a library with people sitting facing each other in rows on opposite sides of the wall and Trump in the middle. He started answering peoples questions but I couldn’t hear because people spoke quietly. Then he flipped out at someone and suddenly a kind of riot started and lots of people flocked to the middle. I caught sight of a guy I used to date who was a socialist. We made eye contact but didn’t speak. I was confused about why he was there. I was hanging out with a guy in a wheelchair and we were getting a plane to go to Armidale in NSW.

I’m at Downtown Abbey and I think I’m part of the staff. There’s an important guest arriving. Then it cuts to after the guest has arrived and we get a letter saying that we did a great job and everyone is chuffed about it. We’re on a train going somewhere when we get this letter. The train turns into a boat, like an old boat used in the early 20th century. Then I think I’m in Orange in NSW at a school and something has happened to the lawn of the school. Lava has bubbled up through it and there are burning hot coals across the whole lawn. It’s taking ages for it to cool down and there’s a sense of great sadness that the lawn will take ages to fix. I’m walking with an Asian teacher who doesn’t know that this has happened and she’s really shocked when we walk past.

My friend Lucy has just moved into a new apartment by herself and it’s in the city in a very fancy block. There’s marble everywhere in the reception area downstairs and a concierge, high ceilings, it’s like an old bank. There’s a restaurant for people who live there and they can bring guests so Lucy and I have a cup of tea there. I realise they don’t check if you’re a really a resident so I decide to come back another day bringing my friend J and we have lunch. We feel sneaky, like naughty children. Then the next time Lucy and I have lunch there someone tries to arrest me because I’ve broken the rules. It’s ridiculous and wrong and I start to run away. I’m escaping the building and there’s lots of complex tasks for me to do to get away. For example I have to explain to my dad how a particular device works and how I put down several books on the bed to turn the device on. I have to hide those books so other people don’t use the device. I don’t know what the device is for but I think it’s for communication. I tell my dad that one book I like to hide in the hallway. The other in my undies drawer and the other also in a personal drawer. I recommend that he does the same because he has to take over now.

A guy who was interested in me back in 2008 came back to Sydney and it seemed like wanted to kick things off again. I remember feeling confused that he was back because I thought he was happily married.

I was in a room with many children. I think it was an orphanage. We were trapped and the floor had turned into a bubbling swamp which was dangerous, possibility radioactive. I felt too lethargic to do anything. The kids were crying. It was relentless. I felt impotent . Eventually help came in 2 grown up Boy Scouts who packed everything up as if it was a camp and the swamp had gone.

I had revealed some secret misdeed or lie of an unspecified authority figure and was facing some punishment if I did not apologise. Egged only my daughter and a close friend I was in defiant mode and that felt good. Some apprehension that there would be consequences, withdrawal of privileges. Much of this was set in old workplace and also in the marine lake where I swim. Saw some young colleagues who ignored me and that was hurtful. Had to try on a new dress and it looked ridiculous.
My grown up daughter figured. Some entrapment. Lots of frustration and loose ends which could not be tied up.

I am in my bedroom and it is full of bags, boxes and other paraphernalia. My sister / daughter is with me. Outside  there are two big, shadowy men, they are mending the window, they came with three brown  horses and a cart. The horses were outside of my bedroom window. My mother came into the room and started to tidy up ,i asked her not to and showed her the pathways id made. One to the bed, one to the wardrobe, one to the door and one to the cupboard where i keep my cheque book. The other female with me told me to look at the horses but i was afraid and said 'No its unlucky to dream about horses'. I saw my father in the kitchen standing up but leaning over the table writing a cheque to pay the men. I grabbed my cheque book and ran into the kitchen saying "No no i must pay, its my house"...My father was pleased.

I was in bed in a large room. There was a family with many members of young ages. I was apprehensive, i thought they may think i am too middle class. The young men had suits on and they were going to wheel my bed somewhere. Someone yelled out 'The kids are outside!' I leapt out of bed and ran outside, there was a steep grassy bank and two children were running up and down on it , i asked them to come inside because their mummy was worried.They came in.I was back in bed,Two young women laughed at my bedside table which had lots of things on it ,i don't know what they were except a small bowl of dying flowers, i could see splash of yellow in the flowers, i thought they were Pansys. I said 'You shouldn't laugh at people' and then i shouted ' Social media is to blame and should be banned over the WHOLE WORLD ! ' The young people looked surprised. My brother in law stood in the doorway and told me off for  not seeing my sister, i walked through the door and went into a small white room with a narrow bed and a wooden bench in it, on the bench was a small posy of flowers in a bowl. My sister as in bed and i said sorry to her . She smiled her kind smile. Two of the young men were eating small pies which contained fish. They didnt like them and i smiled to myself.

I was sitting in a vehicle next to a man  i didnt know. We were talking about the orchards we had played in as children.He said he was waiting to see a man who was coming to the town we were in. I was excited because i knew the man and hadn't seen him for a long time. A car with 4 occupants parked in front of us, i could see the blond hair of the man we were waiting to see. I jumped out and he saw me and got out of the car  and said " Don't hug me i have swollen glands in my neck' I thought of Coronavirus and was afraid. I asked him to wave at the man who was in the vehicle with me but the man was cross and turned away. We went to a building which was once a bar but was now derelict. We leant against the counter 2 and stood  metres apart , we talked. I felt sad that we couldn't hug and frightened because he was ill. My mother cut my hair which took a long time to get right. We were happy. I went outside and saw my hairdresser with her babies. I said 'Hello' and was very happy to see her because i hadn't seen her for so long. She was cross with me because id let my mother cut my hair.

I was asleep and my ex partner came into the room and we started to argue. My daughter passed by the door and told us she needed to rest. My partner said she wasn't well.I felt deeply worried and started to shout at him ..'Why didnt you tell me?,why didnt you tell me?'I went and listened at her door but all was quiet.My ex said he had taken a blanket off of the bed, i started shouting 'But why when I'm too hot?'. I became ill and need an ambulance but had to walk a mile to find it. I walked through the village where i grew up and my legs felt strong. I got into the ambulance and everyone except my family stood by the church and waved,I felt very sad. At the top of the village an old lady got on the ambulance and i did up my seatbelt, she said 'I remember you at school' and i realised she looked familiar.I said 'But you are old' and she replied 'And so are you'..... She was very funny and told jokes and we laughed a lot. My dream was very colourful and the blanket was yellow.

I am in the kitchen with my grandson and when i look out of the window i see that the lawn has swollen massively and is flooded. I lean out of the open window and see a large metal shoot leading to an opening that i think of as a 'Sluice,' on the metal shoot are my fathers large string nets that he used to put hay in when we had a farm. I knew if they were washed into the sluice we would have a bad flood. I got into a van with my grandson and told him to stay in the van no matter what and i got out and stood on the shoot, i leaned over the sluice and saw the nets disappearing, being washed away.I was frightened because i was in danger of being washed away too but i managed to grab the end of the nets and pulled and pulled until i got them out. I heard he water rush away and knew the danger of flood had passed. I was exhausted and dragged myself onto the back seat of the van. My grandson was where i had left him and i told him what a good boy he is. I am at a family gathering and we are eating at a table. My mother said we need more wine and i said i would get it. Im standing with my sister and a child looking into a muddy hole. My sister says she wants meat, onions and chips to eat .... i wonder why i haven't thought about what id like to eat. My mother appears with two bottles of wine in a string bag. I think i'll buy more wine because she hasn't got enough, i tell her that i'll buy extra food as well. I ask what everyone would like but we just look at each other because no one knows the answer except my sister.

I was sitting in a room on a  chair with my cat. Opposite me was a very elderly  lady in  a bed, she was saying that when you become an old lady no one takes any notice of you at all, even when she told someone her spectacles had broken no one had believed her.....I had two thoughts, one was 'So i haven't been imagining it, I am being ignored, and people are waiting for me to die in order to inherit my money and thats the only reason they bother at all ! The other thought was how awful it must be for the old lady not to have her spectacles. I looked at my cat and realised part of his tail had been shaved. I started to shout "What has happened to my cat?" A man i knew as a boy at school appeared and said "Irina took him to the vets" .Irina came in. She was a care worker, and she looked at me with disdain and said in an Eastern European voice .Why are you bothered ? Just pay the bill" I was angry and shouted "He is MY cat' You should have told me" I looked at the bill and it was for ear drops which cost £7.

I was racing a car along a network of roads. I had a big metal box which was a telephone but the dial wouldn't work properly. I was very frustrated. I was looking for something that had been hidden away.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: I was watching the TV show 'the Bachelor' with one of the earlier contestants from the Australian Bachelor and she was talking about her favourite contestants and and who were the most like her. The previous contestant had a big social media following and was trying to find the next 'star'. She was encouraging me to participate in her planning but I wasn't really interested, but she seemed to want me to be.

my parents had told me about a young person who had climbed to the top of a building as a protest and had fallen down and died. I went with them to the building - it was a shopping centre and everyone was talking about how silly it was, whether he had fallen intentionally, etc. My mothers friend was there also but was supportive of the man.

I was with an old colleague from years ago on a train going to work. our train being picked up by some unknown force and moved to the last track. We were jumping carriages and the smell of garbage was very strong. Then we realised there was an art project underway- there was a photographer who was asking everyone to pick out some special pieces from the rubbish that he could photograph. I found a colourful felt badge the size of my hand which looked to be something that could be worn by an Indian woman in a sari and cleaned it so he could photograph it. He was obsessed with this badge and said it was probably the best piece of rubbish found yet while photographing it.
I was with a few colleagues from work and we were composting. They had some really good advice on composting techniques and different ratios and we were comparing our composts.

I was walking along a path with this girl that I vaguely know though a friend, we were heading somewhere. We came across a body that was covered in worms and half buried. It was actually the same girl like we were looking at her through another lens. She gave me some elaborate explanation about the worm and body break down process. I then realised we were heading to a fashion show being put on by this girls work and it was very prolific. When we arrived there was cameras and people everywhere and a lot of decorates and music. They gave me a fancy jacket to wear that had tassels and I was taken by her boss into the venue and given a really good seat to watch the show. I remember riding in an elevator to get to the show with her boss who was very stylish. The show ended up being like a circus it was very animated.

I was in some tropical holiday destination and Elton John was coming to visit, everyone was really excited. I spotted him heading toward me up a windy staircase and started taking photos. Then he said "why don't you get one of us together" or something and jumped in next to me. He had an entourage and it was holding everything up. Then Elton John and his entourage continued going up more stairs.

We were somewhere where it was heavily snowing and cold. My friend had organised a cart to travel somewhere and was loading our luggage onto it. She was encouraging me to put my things on it but for some reason we were held up. there was a big group leaving but I don't know where we were going.

I was with another old colleague from years ago and we were watching TV at an old fashioned looking bar. Her and her partner brought around cocktails to a group of us. Whatever we were watching was captivating everyone.
My partner and I were cooking falafels in my dream

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: A number of my work colleagues featured - mostly senior level people. We had just found out that the organisation was closing. The CEO didn't really seem bothered by it and was talking to me a lot about it in a really calm voice. A previous Executive who had been quite detrimental to the company and wasn't around any more had come back and she had something to do with it closing. She had tried to do something and it had such a negative impact that the organisation had to shut down. Her and I went out for lunch, we talked about her Canadian heritage a bit... mailing something important and I couldn't find a post box, I was running back and forth with the help of another colleague.

I was with a group of close girlfriends and we'd each just purchased large houses and were visiting each others houses. One house in particular was really interesting, it had rooms around the inside perimeter of the house and see through walls, with a big open space in the centre.  One of my girlfriends felt uncomfortable visiting me there because the house used to be owned by her ex-boyfriend. One of the girls made us all homemade jam but gave them to us without lids on them because she didn't have any. I was with my mother-in-law and sister-in-law at a shopping centre. They were convincing me I had to try this particular sandwich which we all ordered. They then went home to look after my niece who was staying with them with me, and I stayed out until the next morning. When I got home they wondered what I had been doing all that time. I was at my wedding  but it wasn't really my wedding- I didn't like anything about it, the dress, the vibe, the vowels, etc. I thought that when my real wedding came that it was going to be nothing like this. Noone had fun, including me and people were leaving early. My brother said he had to leave because his friend got hit by a car and he was worried about him. He took his girlfriend with him  and a number of my friends were heavily pregnant at the wedding and had to leave. The bar staff weren't doing a good job topping up peoples drinks and there was long queues at the bar.

I was walking around the house of a family that were missing or didn't live there any more, but was observing the poor conditions in which they lived. They were a multigenerational family and I remember looking a room and thinking that must have been where the grandfather slept. seeing blood maybe on the walls or bed and wondering what had gone on, maybe the family had been murdered. I think my brother was there for part of it, walking around with me. Some time later feeling locked in the house by someone on the outside. my brother being there trying to find a way out. It wasn't particularly scary, just annoying not to be able to get out.  I think it was in the same house that I found a friend from uni and we were dancing together, there were other people around. thinking she was a good dancer, but I never knew that. She had a fancy outfit on I think.  maybe outside this house I was talking to another friend who I'm not that close with who was sitting outside with a group of people and I remember feeling excluded from whatever they were doing. They were sitting around having a picnic or something. I started talking to her about recycling/composting and she had some good advice about this sort of stuff.  I was at the train station with a good friend of mine but didn't have the right type of ticket. She left me at the station because she had to go somewhere.

I was participating in an art project/competition in the UK. I remember lush wilderness and we were somewhere remote, maybe Scotland. The project was to prepare art for patients at a hospital. The judges had extremely high expectations and there was a lot of attention on the artists. I got a negative reaction to mine, and was somewhat shunned. The hospital seemed to so large that we had to catch a train through the hospital grounds to get around. I was at the airport getting a flight home and having some trouble checking in my luggage. Someone was with me. Suddenly Russian spies appeared and started asking us a lot of questions. They were demanding to see our artworks which were in our suitcases.
A friend told me she was 6 months pregnant because she could feel the baby kicking. We were at a swimming pool I think.

I was in the centre city at a weird time, in the night, sort of twilight, hardly any people around. The ground was wet like it had been raining. It was sort of like a scene from old England, but in current Melbourne. All misty and people walking briskly like they needed to get home rather than linger in city streets at this time of night. There was a spotlight on a hippy guy - beard, sloppy jeans, singing the most beautiful tune in a really sweet high soft voice, standing in a little crossroads of alleys singing. I stopped to listen and the song was about breath and oxygen and air, and how that's what songs are made of. It was incredibly sweet. A few of us were listening. I looked away and when I looked at him again he was wearing different clothes - a funny suit made out of terracotta coloured linen - and I didn't understand how he could have changed so quickly. Then I looked closer and it was a hologram of the guy, and I thought perhaps none of it was real, that it was all pre-recorded. Then I looked around and saw that the real guy was there, he had just turned on a hologram version to give himself a break from singing. He wasn't disguising that at all - he was standing in plain view with a remote control. Then he changed the hologram to a different version, a different outfit. Then he turned it off and kept singing himself, to the end of the song. The people all walked away on the paths in different directions.

I dreamt that I was having a meeting with Malotru and a Russian man. I was enabling a transaction between them. The Russian man took what he wanted, but Malotru didn't want the money and another object he was given in return. These objects were sitting awkwardly in the room we were in, which was wooden and completely bare, upstairs in a warehouse type building, but more of a house. Malotru was about to leave for good, and we were in the middle of sorting out what he was going to do with the money and the other object, when we heard people downstairs. But something was drowning out the sound, so we were all straining to hear what it was. I went down, and saw that it was three women, some of them I knew. I had to go down and distract them from the upstairs scene, but said I could only talk for a couple of minutes as we were moving out, and I didn't want to jeopardise the transaction. Then other people started arriving and the scene changed, and there were men arriving that I knew, and everyone seemed to belong to an organisation known by a set of letters - CBE etc - and I was always trying to work out what the letters meant, in order to know what the organisation was for. It seemed the men didn't know what the letters stood for either.

I was staying with Catherine here in Melbourne at her ex-husband's place. It would seem she had a lot of ex-husbands. This one was very nice, they got on very well. I was very happy to be staying there and was thinking about how in the past I always wanted to stay places by myself and found staying with others a compromise, whereas now it was the other way around. Here I had a place by myself and a place with her and other places, and I was moving around a lot and considering what all the options and differences were. There were postgraduate students from my old university there too. Everyone had lots of advice about various things. I was doing dishes at the ex-husband's place and decided I quite liked him. Then I thought about Catherine's many ex's and how great they all were, and how I knew a lot of them. There was lots of easy conversation with this one about my day, which seemed to entail working in various corporate or university type settings. We had some good eye contact and I decided that he was the 'one' for me. And then it turned into a really big house party and there were people everywhere. I came across the ex-husband later in the night, but now he looked different. Very thin. He was wearing a very distinctive green shirt. Lime green. Really a beautiful colour. I wanted to tell him I liked it but he started coming on to me, which I hadn't expected. He brushed his lips against mine and they were very thin but very soft and I told him so. Then I moved on to other parts of the party. Later there was a scene where he helped me with the dishes by chucking them all in a dishwasher in a really funny way. I was talking to Catherine about sending items from NZ to Australia, which everyone seemed to be doing, and how the price was really hard to work out, and the post took ages, and lots of people were finding that it would be quicker to wait and take the thing themselves. Then I was sneakily taking a little hair tie of hers. I chose a plain colour like grey and then tried it out, but as soon as I stretched it it turned into this big like twirly clown wig type hair tie, a big bunch of ribbons, and it changed colour, and then when I moved it changed colour again, all really bright fluorescent colours. And I felt bad because it was now so obvious that I took something from her - because if I wore it it was so noticeable and bright - but I I also really like it and found it really magical and thought that I might send it to my niece in Dunedin.

I kept hearing about a book by a person with a Russian sounding name, with an 'x' in it, that I couldn't pronounce, that people thought I would be interested in. My former PhD supervisor invited me to comment on it. I attended a gathering of academics, including one controversial former member of staff who I haven't seen for a long time, and Tony was standing at the front of the room with a whiteboard filled in with categories and questions for us to discuss. He started by throwing the first opportunity to me, to 'distinctly and clearly articulate the major arguments' of the Russian guy's book, and that I might also want to refer to one of our Department's academics work. I mumbled something about needing to re-read the old book, and not quite knowing the new book, or the new author, but was ready to make a summative comment about what I thought it was about - but before I could make this comment Tony talked over me and gave the opportunity to someone else, realising that he'd put me on the spot. I was then in a room with one of my PhD examiners and another woman. Everyone was wearing square big glasses, so none of us felt stupid because we all had the same style. The talk was still about the new book, and I was going to read it. Someone gave it to me, but it was all written in a bag of chips. As in, the book was a bag of chips, and each chip had text on it, on both sides. The problem was that it was all in order when I got the bag, but as soon as I opened it, of course the chips started to move around and it was impossible to keep them in order! I started pulling them out one by one and trying to read them, but realised it was futile, that there was no way I'd be able to make sense of the thing as a whole. I was very confused and couldn't understand why anyone would write a book in this format. I decided that I'd get myself a proper copy of an actual book, but knew that that would have to wait, or I'd have to pay a lot or something. But in the process of looking at the chips I realised what the book was about and thought of my brother and was going to tell him about it. It seemed the book was kind of a backwards story, in that the author wrote of having a fantasy childhood, like a fairytale, not real, and then growing into - and travelling into - a real world.

I was living with a gangster guy in a big glass mansion. There was an arrangement whereby he wanted to make a regular thing of an affair he was having. I'd be outside and he'd come out at 7.20 each evening. He'd have small packets of cosmetics that he'd brought from inside, which now seemed like a big department store. He'd take the tag thing off so that it wouldn't set the alarm off, and then he'd give them to the girl he was going to cheat with. She was tall and blond and elegant. There was a third party involved, a guy, who we ran through the exercise with a few times and then the husband checked that he would be able to do it every night, or every Friday, at 7.20. But all this was arranged without saying anything, just nods. Then the wife found out. She had someone helping her and it turned into a big action scene where they were trying to kill us. She was really plain. Short red hair and a red fleece top. I ducked under a hedge beside the house and wriggled backwards, but someone was following me in. But behind the hedge was just a big open space, so I got caught straight away. Then it was like we were in a TV show, a NZ one about Janet Frame and other famous people. It was like Close to Home, and I was thinking about how NZ is really good at making shows like that.

I discovered a new way of rating zoom calls, that could be applied to everything, and was trying to convince people of it. It was to do with visual clarity and it seemed very complex to me. It was to do with colours and three categories from poor to good to excellent. It seemed an important breakthrough for COVID but I kept having to tell different people in different scenarios to get them to understand how useful it would be. Green and red were two of the colours.

I arrived home and there was a note at the door, it was on a kind of form for visitors to leave a note if you weren't home, and it was from my Mum, and it said 'all of us'. I understand that to mean that all of them - my parents and my brother who lives with them - had come for dinner, but because we weren't home, they had left again. I was furious. They'd come all the way from New Zealand but hadn't bothered to ring first or let me know. As I moved around the house I realised that my brother was there. He was a bit shy about it and didn't say anything. I called my sister and had a rant to her about how they do this kind of thing - Mum particularly - that don't make any sense. And I guess I was sad that I had missed them. Then I started talking to my brother about it and he said 'Dad's here', and I thought, oh yeah, I thought I saw him. He was sitting in a little side room, at a table, with a plate of biscuits and loaf as he often does. I realised that I'd walked past that table several times, and taken a bit of loaf off it, eaten it, but hadn't noticed Dad. So I made some conversation about how I'd be terrible if I lived with Mum, because I'd eat little treats like that all the time if they were sitting around on a plate. But I was still really upset with Mum and didn't know what was going to be for dinner, and moved back through to the kitchen where my brother was, and started talking to him about Mum, but at the same time realised that she was there. I guess she'd been there all along. I couldn't understand how I didn't see her because she was all aflutter like she always is in the kitchen. Big pans of crumbed chicken and lots of other dishes on the go. She had her apron on and was totally into what she was doing. I went back into the side room and my brother was there now. There was a plate on that table - a different table to the one Dad was at - with a very strange looking cracker on it. The kind of square cracker you would usually put cheese on, but it was about an inch thick, with another centimetre layer on top of a darker yummy looking stuff. I picked it up and took a bite and it was very delicious, but very strange, and I thought perhaps healthy as well as delicious because it was very crumbly and a bit grainy. I was worried then that it was my brothers, and it was probably really expensive, and so I said to him that it was really yummy. He said 'oh yeah, it's got what they call animal icing on the top'. I was like, 'oh, it's a dog biscuit! Well, it's really yummy', and put it back on the plate.

Everything was mixed up and strange. Biology was bad, or dairy farming was bad, and I was some kind of consultant for these things. This also meant being a consultant of a rugby game, and my analysis showed that farming and business and rugby tactics were all intricately woven together. I wasn't sure if the audience were quite understanding my complicated explanation. I had a whiteboard and drew a diagram of a rugby formation that I thought made everything wonderfully clear. There were vertical lines on one row, and then once I got down to about the sixth row I felt that everthing made perfect sense and drew very vigorous horizontal line across the players, making a loud noise with the pen and drawing over and over the horizontal line, which got quite a bit of attention. I felt like surely they must be able to understand now, especially the rugby people. Another row of the drawing concerned a single tooth. As people were leaving I invited them all in to take a souvenir of some person we had been celebrating. There were the people and they formed an orderly line. I was standing beside an open closet, and handed them each something. This turned out to be an item of clothing, which all became the same - a gold/tan and black plaid jacket, which everyone was now wearing, even before I gave it to them.

I was in a mall with my niece and my phone rang and it looked like it was in regards to the job application I am waiting to hear about. I had all sorts of problems answering the phone and trying to call back and trying to find the home button on my phone. I ended up taking a phone off some little girls by accident and having to remove it. The mall was busy and noisy which added to my stress and we couldn't find a quiet place to sit. At one point we sat outside a supermarket and a peasant woman was handing out loaves of bread and telling everyone that they didn't know how lucky they were to have free loaves of bread. Eventually I found the girls and returned their phone.

I was with my Mum in Dunedin, but it was a very different house, and very like her parents house that we used to stay in a different part of New Zealand. I was organising to stay the night with her. The place was a real mess and I was trying to get things in order. There was stuff everywhere and dirty dishes and it seemed she needed food but there was a lot of stuff. She was happy though, and helping me to get organised, and I was thinking, this is great, I'll be able to come and stay here for a while next year and it will be a cheap way to live and we would be fine. And then I realised that Dad wasn't there, that he must have died and that's probably why I felt comfortable about going to live with her. But then I thought about how gross it would be to have to be there all the time, and to have to shower in that bathroom before going to work. But all the while I kept organising and making a shopping list for food. Mum was happy to have me organise dinner that night. She had some little bottles of McDuffs beer around the place, which used to be a favourite of mine when I lived in Dunedin. Then she bought all these books out - old slim volumes about walks and tramping around Dunedin. She suggested we work our way through all of them, doing all the walks. I thought it a great idea. There were heaps of them though, some slim but some quite big books. Maybe fifty books all together. I knew we could buy it now in one little volume, but I didn't want to disappoint her as she felt so good about having kept all the books all this time and that now we would make good use of them. She was very happy throughout the dream, quite energised and moving around. She told me to get dogfood. I was worried I would get the wrong sort, and kept meaning to ask her what kind to get, but then getting distracted. Then for a long time the dream was just about what I was going to cook for dinner. I just couldn't get it straight in my head. I couldn't get a single idea of what to cook that I could run through my head. Everything I thought of seemed too complicated and like I couldn't imagine it working out, and that it would take hours, and it was already after-work time and we needed something quick. It was weird because I cook a lot and I tried to think of things I make for me and Luke but those ideas were all confused and led to the same problem.

I noticed a little white pimple on my neck. I began to squeeze it and it started a big tube-like white substance about a centimetre diameter coming out of my neck. I knew that there was a build up of toxic stuff inside my neck and at the back of my ear and in my jaw, that needed to come out somehow. It was a thick white paste, and it just kept coming out. It wasn't painful but it was disturbing. But at the same time I was relieved that I was getting it out of my system. Then immediately from there I was in an elevator and it was night. I hesitated about getting into it because the lights didn't seem to be on and I thought that meant it might not be working, and I might get stuck. I hovered at the brink of stepping in for what seemed like a long time. Half stepping in and hoping that would be enough to make the lights come on, rather than having to step right in and then have it be too late to get out again before the door shut and I was stuck.

I walked down onto a beach with Luke. We were wandering along the beach and came to quite a narrow part, where the tide was in and almost trapping us in to the hill beside it. As we started to walk back to the more open part, news came in somehow that something really big had happened out in the world, something to do with the virus, that meant the world was going to change. Immediately the water started to recede, with each wave it drew further back, like a tsunami, but we knew it wasn't a tsunami, it was the virus having a ripple effect. But from then on it occurred like a tsunami - we became aware of a massive wave that was building up as the tide drew further back. We could see the wave, and then it was against a massively high cliff, maybe a kilometre up in the air. A straight cliff face with the wave drawing further and further up it. Luke is a very calm person but he started to almost panic as we realised we needed to get out of there. We were in the bottom of a basin, surrounded by hills, and not that far from the huge cliff. There were a few other people around, some were worried, others less so. No-one seemed quite sure what to do. No-one wanted to panic, and we were all a bit in awe of the wave. It was really beautiful. We had no idea when it might break, but it seemed logical that it would do so once it reached the top of the cliff. We started to rush and almost panic slightly, grabbing our things from the sand. I had my nice grey socks, and wasn't sure if there was time to put my shoes and socks on, but was worried about trying to make the steep climb up to safety in bare feet. I couldn't decide.

I was having dinner with a friend and we ordered small round items in a fancy restaurant. Then as we started eating I remembered that I had had something like dumplings there before. And ice-cream. Both of which I felt would go well with the meal we'd ordered. So I left the table and started wandering around talking to various staff about whether they had these items - the bar tender, the receptionist. They managed to find it and added it to my order. The waitress kept seeing me talking to people and wondering what I was doing. Meanwhile the ice-cream had been delivered and was starting to melt. I was also on the phone to some people about a yoga studio, that was going to be developed in a location that had just become available via inheritance, and a trust. My partner's friend, an artist, was involved and said it was all fine. But it turned out there was a problem with the title to the property, which at the beginning seemed just like a complexity, bu then turned out to be something that the artist was making trouble about. I kept leaving and returning to the dinner table. I also kept cutting to a scene where there was a massive standoff taking place between a huge Mongolian army and me and my forces. We were a much smaller army but the standoff was happening at a sharp bend in the road, so the very nasty leader of their forces couldn't actually see the extent of my army, even though he suspected it was very minor. It was very tense, every time I checked in with the scene. At one instant I would start to feel relieved as he admitted he was beaten on this occasion and started to retreat. Then it would always flick back to him hesitating, calling my bluff, and doing something horrible to my main guard as a way of getting him or me to reveal that our army was small and weak.

I was in the place near my childhood home. I was stuck in the valley between two hills, and actually needed to be on the other side to get to the mountain that I'm interested in. But I kept coming over the hills before, into the valley, and into the one social place in this very small place. I was confused and panicked as I felt that time was running out to express what I'd found out about the mountain in my research. I kept going through all my study papers, rummaging through looking for maps, trying to explain it to people, but nothing I said made sense. One guy in particular was nasty about it, pretending he understood and the taking me outside and being very mean and a bit threatening about it.
I had a flash back of being punched in the head.
Back in the town and I am sitting at a bus stop waiting for a bus. My bus didn’t come. I was then at a farm watching and helping pack potatoes into bags and help sell them

Dreamt about our Lions Club having to find somewhere else to meet as our meeting place is now a covid hotel.  Kept thinking about going to Cafe Squires and giving him a heads up that the committee will be coming to see him,

I had cancer in my back and chest and it was operated on by nursing staff from the past.  Even though I was recovering I was walking around and trying to nurse and give advice to people in my role as a nurse. Even went to a property not far away to help people.  Really weird.  Didn't like it

I was on a cruise ship with weird people who didn’t make sense. The boat although large went into small shallow places. Saw the white cliffs of Dover which had a shallow area in front of it and school girls in uniform playing in front of  My sister was on the boat but I didn’t see or meet her. My parents on the boat but same thing I don’t remember seeing them. I had my kids and at the end of the dream I had to settle the account and prove the life jackets were in the cabin but the person ignored me.

I was living in a house and my kids were in primary school. I was working night duty and at home. It was hot and I bought icy poles for them when they got home from school. The light bulb in the kitchen needs changing and one of my sisters came and didn’t know how to do it so I did it.  My dad came and got an icy pole. I tried to sleep but I kept thinking about my kids ability to cross the road from school to come home at lunch time to get icy pole.
There was a bank, Agatha Christie’s detective who was fussy about what we looked like and what we were wearing. There were people going to their Prom night. There was a cat

I was on a push bike in a mall I heard a boy band and the singer was great, so I stopped to hear it.  I gave some money and heard a large bang and a female had come off her bike and hit her head on a building wall. Had no helmet  on and was unconscious  I went to help and examine her  A single manned ambulance came and I had to go to help

I was in a party that had home away stars. I told the actors present that I didn’t watch the show as I don’t like it. Some got annoyed with me but kept drinking. They then went to a private club over the road to continue partying.  Next thing I am back in the ambulance opposite the party site with the same patient and ambulance driver. He called for back up of another driver.

I was in NZ and had my 2 kids with me. I had many problems to deal with. I also had to pack and catch a plane home. I didn’t know the people I was with and they were not helpful at all.  I was so anxious about not catching  plane on time. We should already have booked in and I was still packing and then we had to drive to the airport.

I had picked up  one of my sisters who was quite difficult to live with as a sibling.  I wanted to have a talk with her. We took a short cut in the car along a track to get to a town for a coffee. We ended up driving of a high cliff into the ocean.

Was at a Lions meeting but not my normal members,  People I didn't know.  Went to a house and talked and had a young guy trying to get onto to me.  I wasn't interested.  There was a Hungry Jacks directly opposite and we got coffee and chips from them.

In a small shopping mall and a friend and I wanted to buy some plums. The stall owner wouldn’t tell us if they were red or yellow inside. She gave us soiled ones to try. They had a chocolate covering and had raspberry inside them. We again asked for just plums. We asked the price   She said they were on special at $18 a kilo. We both said you must be joking. We were getting pretty pissed off

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: Sarah and I were together and she was a teenager. At a river and people were giving kids the chance to do things in the river. I was impatient as we had to be somewhere else.

I was in a room and one of my sisters and my ex dead husband were there also. He was being an arshole as he was. I was getting soup for tea and I couldn’t find the ladle and neither were helping. I missed my hair appointment because of them. Next I wanted to go bed as I had worked that night and was so tired. He started to argue

The kids and I were going on a holiday and changing schools. Had to find their school items which were packed in boxes.  Really hard to find them.  The kids had to get fitted for new uniforms.  Had crooks trying to get to me and I didn’t know why.  Went to a GP I didn’t know and I didn’t get to tell her what was wrong with me. The kids and I were going on a holiday, to a sunny island and I was trying to get everything organised before we went. It was busy and stressful.

I was in the bush and hiding/running away from people who wanted to hurt me.  We all had guns. The leader had a plan and a shed where he trained and planned his operation.   2 people and I managed to escape into the bush. I ended up on my own and went through streams and bush to escape. I ended up at a small building and ordered food to eat.

I was at the beach and talking to people. I also ended up being with the lifeguards. They had to rescue lots of people.  I also helped once the swimmers were bought to land. It was confusing, confronting and I didn’t know why I was there
I was in a bank and there were customers and it got held by people with guns. Very scary.

Volcanoes that had an explosion slightly once and I had to take paper work to other side of island, leaving my family behind. It then had a big explosion and I started to go back. Lots of people coming away from it and some going back. Had to deal with difficult terrain and red ants.
I was in a woody area and trying to explain covid restrictions to people who were not listening.
guns, rivers, death, police as a lady had killed someone  My daughter was in it vaguely, she was alright and not threatened  Also TV show criminal intent flashed into it slightly

I was attending a church service in a very large building with a nave that seemed to be as long as a mile or more stretching into the distance and full of people with a strange light. It seemed supernatural. I knew that this was a dream and recall wondering what I and all these thousands of people were there for. There didn't seem to be and focus or purpose to the congregation.

my mother was in bed and talking about doing an online course which meant that no one except her could access the internet for months. Then she was also in the nude reaching up for something on top of a cupboard.

I was walking through a house with my husband. It felt like it was my parents house but it didn't look like it. There were a lot of nude people lounging around on bean bags listening to low, chilled out music. My brother was one of them. They looked like they might be on drugs and having sex. I knew my husband was thinking he never wanted to come back to the house.

DD_problematicSR_why: 1st dream but SR apply to all dreams
Text: being back at the full time job I retired from 10 years ago and going through the deliberations of retiring - how, when wisdom of doing so. Astonishingly deciding to stay and being sacked and escorted from the office. I seemed to know this was untrue but I found it unsettling as many of the people were people I did not know.

I was staying at my mother in laws house and inexplicably we found ourselves unable to get out of the front door and the side gate. It was all locked. I recall climbing up a very high brick wall with difficulty and asking a neighbour who I did not recognise could he help. He was hostile abusive and refused. A while later the neighbour appeared at the front door with what I took to be a large rocket type. bazooka gun threatening me.
A vague, unspecific dream but with clear recollections of death, dying and a funeral in which improbably I featured as an undertaker. Nothing terrifying - a brief recollection.

meeting huge numbers of human like people in a big venue - light, airy, non threatening - who hall had animal heads. Somewhat fantastical, Gothic style heads with adornments and exaggerated features. I was not frightened just confused and bewildered. I had no idea why I was there or how I had got there.

I was in a dark auditorium, maybe holding about 400-500 people, as if I was in school again and we were watching something on a screen in front of a stage. I got pulled aside to go into a really bright room where there was a bathtub. My friend was sitting in there asking me questions and I got in the bath. She was asking me about Niagara Falls in Canada and whether I had visited and I said no I had never been to Canada. We were having a nonchalant conversation in this brightly lit room.
It was night time and I was running away from something. Then I was reunited with the guy I’m still in love with we looked at each other and we both felt safe again. it was starting to be a sex dream

I was meant to be going camping with friends on some hill/mountain top. The sky was pink and purple sunset. My friend was meant to drive me there but she said she was elsewhere so somehow I made it and found another friend there. We were talking about something but turns out we couldn’t camp that night because we didn’t have enough camping gear. I then ended up in a shopping centre and ran into two girls I’m no longer friends with and we were catching up. It was a bit awkward but we were friendly. Then my mum showed up and was shocked to see me and the girls were being friendly again and she told them off for how horrible they were to me. Then those girls left and I was getting ready to meet another group of friends at a cafe by the beach. I took the wrong bus and got lost and ended up at some beach shack coffee shop and ordered a coffee but the guy said it was $6.30 for a small coffee. I was reluctant to pay. Then another girl I’m not friends with anymore showed up and said I didn’t have to order it at all if I wasn’t ok with the price. She then invited me to a birthday party of another girl we both went to high school with. They were having cake and asked me to record them for Instagram while everyone - a big group of maybe 10 sitting along a long table - sang happy birthday. Somehow then the party was over and it was the day time and we were all dressed in black and white and we were at this other cafe by the beach again that looked familiar to the one in my hometown. They were doing an Oscars parody but real famous people were there. We were all bunched up around small tables and I went to grab a glass of water but then Michael B Jordan was there and said I shouldn’t drink it and gave me a bottle of water. Then this weird Oscars ‘game’ began and the whole cafe filled up with sand and there were cameras recording us do these weird tasks/challenges. Then somehow I was in the ocean and then ended up on shore again and went to these gross blue and white tiled public bathrooms trying to get all the sand off. Then I returned to the cafe and these people told me I ‘passed the game’.

I owned an apartment in Dublin but still lived in Australia but my friend who is Irish was living in it. He called to tell me that there was some fee he had to pay with the rent and I said I could claim it on tax and that he should send me anything else related that I could claim on tax. It was raining heavily and the conversation was happening on the phone. He then said he has around $1000 of things I could claim on tax but I said it was unlikely I could get all of it back to him. I think we had an argument or I felt pressured for some reason. I was at a supermarket, barefoot, looking to buy ice cream. I ran into people I used to work with who were asking about my roommate as he still works with them. I was trying to buy ice cream but was indecisive as to what flavour to get. When I got home I was looking for my roommate in a house. It was empty but then I found him in a room sitting on a brown leather chair and I was telling him I had to claim all these things for my friend who was living in an apartment I owned in Dublin and he was confused as to why I owned the apartment and how it hadn’t come up in conversation before.
I was filling in a Japanese crossword puzzle
I was volunteering in my role as a communications support officer, and had to try to find someone to volunteer for the afternoon shift that day. I called someone and it was done.

I was at a science-fiction convention and suddenly found I was going to be interviewing some of the celebrity guests, along with someone else I didn't know. It was in a big hall, with lots of relaxed people chatting amongst themselves. I was neither nervous nor excited, just took it in my stride. I sat down opposite one of my favourite actors and had a quick chat about what to do with the panel discussion.

I was at a warehouse with characters from the TV show, Sons of Anarchy. It was announced that the police were on their way so Tara and I got in a car. Some pieces of material were handed to Tara through the open window by Gemma. We sped off onto the motorway. I was viewing the chase from above and could see we were approaching traffic. We were apprehended by police officers. I don't remember getting to the station but we were there. An old man in a hospital gown on crutches was wandering around.

An old friend from primary school, Ruth, was having people over. I was growing house plants for a living and brought some with me. Most of them were potted in this weird jelly gravel that retained water. It was white and shiny. Ruth then told me a friend of ours, Nia, had died on her 40th birthday.

Myself and some friends were superheroes but some of our colleagues had been kidnapped so I made everyone visit my friend Nadine's house as even though she was my friend, she was also a supervillain and might help us. Nadine gave us all wine and jelly sweets but said she could not help us. There were also some scenes featuring a spaceship, an alley near the river and snow.

I was in the woods with lots of children. My friend Lucy was there holding an event about wildlife and nature but the children were running around everywhere and not listening. I wandered off whilst checking my phone. I was looking at paintings based on World of Warcraft that I think my brother had painted but my ex-boyfriend had posted on Facebook. I saw Michelle's son standing next to the river. He was scared to walk next to it so I held his hand and we walked together until the path turned up a hill and he felt safe. A woman and her daughter were running up and down the hill laughing and playing as we walked up and a man was following close behind us. It was very sunny but not too hot. At some point, someone was talking about growing carrots but I can't remember where it happened.

I was watching a film about a white Jewish man and a black Christian man who had fallen in love whilst trying to catch a glimpse of the filming of a new Superman film. All the older Jews were excited as the actor playing Superman had played Jesus in a recent film. The white man was wearing a huge black cloak that reminded me of Lady Gaga and the black man was worried that the older men would realise he was gay and shun him from their community. They were on a bus.

I was at my childhood home and my bedroom window was black with dirt so I was leaning out trying as best I could to clean it with a baby wipe. My parents were in the next room and my Dad was complaining about not being able to find shoes to fit him. I put loud music on and somehow managed to twist the window enough to clean it. I then put all the dirty wipes in the toilet and turned the music off.

It felt like I was watching a sitcom. A car stopped next to a couple who had been stranded after their car broke down and the men in the car believed the man to be a renowned Mexican writer. They took the couple to Mexico to show them. The man then dressed up in Aztec clothing and was selling books at the roadside.

I was in work listening to Dafydd telling Toni that she was a genius and he was going to hire her separately as his assistant. She came to me asking if she should do it and I said no. I told her that he was humouring her because he wanted to sleep with her. She got upset at the insinuation but I stood my ground and explained that she got so much wrong at work and she was not a genius so what else could it be? Kate overheard our conversation and joined us to tell Toni that if she took the job, she'd be taking a job from an underprivileged teenager who are usually hired for those assistant roles. I left to go home and ran down a spiral staircase to leave the floor I was on. I emerged in a library rather than the building reception.

I was pregnant but with Dan and during the scan, he was going on about how he was going to set up a trust for the baby but with special clauses that relied on us staying together. He went to work and I decided to have a termination. The letter was sent to my parents' house to keep it secret and I got ready there. I called in sick on the morning of my appointment and my boss was asking if it was stress but I maintained I had a stomach bug and I'd be fine. I then asked Mum where Dad was. She informed me he had gone to the hospital for an appointment of his own. I was panicking that I would not be able to get to my appointment in time. I called Dan and told him I had a check up but he refused to take me. I checked bus times and train times but had left it too late. I tried to call the number on the appointment letter but I kept mis-dialling.
