I started getting them all out and filling them with wine, until I realised I was doing the last thing first - I needed to get them to the event before I filled them. A colleague/someone from the conference came to help me transport them and we wondered together whether to pour out the wine or just try and move them (in a car, a long way) and keep the wine intact. It was a very international group of people - he was from Pakistan. Later, we were in Paris for a bit. I was riding a very nice bike down a winding road, and going past my old boss from a second hand bookshop. It repeated itself a few times, I went past her on my fast bike but didn't say hi. Then at some stage I had a mini crash, I veered up a hill on the side of the road and feel off my bike, and started to walk down the hill to get someone to help me with the bike and there was my old boss. She said she'd seen me, but I never stopped to say hello (she wasn't hostile, just curious, surprised). I said, I'm always going so fast on my bike, I always want to stop but then I've gone past! It wasn't 100% true, although there was an element of truth - I was slow to react on my bike, but it would have been easy to stop down the road and turn around but I always preferred to pretend I hadn't seen her, to avoid it.

It was another 'collective' time - like a conference, except it wasn't. there was a 'collective.' I was staying in this huge ramshackle house, the kind from a book like Lemony Snickett - rundown, multiple stories, like something that doesn't actually exist in real life. I was there with my family - my brothers, and my mum. There were others there too. There was a zoom meeting that had to be set up, a big book club happening on zoom. Someone living in the house with us who wasn't my family member had been running it - an older man. Somehow he asked me to set it up for him, and in the process, I became responsible for it, everyone in the group addressed me with their question because my name held the account that had created it. They switched over to having me as the responsible person with the matter of a change of account, although it had been going for months. And it was like the older man had known but he hadn't said, just quietly got me to do it for him while he did something else. I wasn't annoyed with him, more laughing at his cheek! I just sort of ignored the zoom group, I didn't care about their books, I let them discuss it amongst themselves and figure it out amongst themselves when they were getting no replies from me. Other things were happening in the house. A young woman who wasn't my family member was trying to drive a Rav 4 and we were watching out the window, because she couldn't do it. She bumped into a big ute going by. We were laughing but there was a sense of desperation to it too, she was desperate to be off in that Rav 4.

I had been in a house, staying in another city I think. An old housemate of mine was living there and there was a social buzz, people coming and going in the house. I approached her and we were cautious with each other, like we didn't know if it would go well between us or not. She was wearing a beautiful dress, black with 70s prints. I said how beautiful it was and there were other people there who echoed me, and there was a gentle truce between us. Then, I  went to the doctor's to do this study, to report my dreams and my thinking. I had got it wrong because you do it from your computer. They didn't know what I was there for, but were inclusive, welcoming, and so gave me a room in the practice to record what I needed to. I wrote it all down on a piece of paper and gave it back to the receptionist, who was a friend of my old housemate. As I handed it over, I realised I'd got it wrong, it was like the exercise of a crazy person, and the whole interaction between her and I was empty, it was for no reason at all, like it was a performance of something ordinarily necessary. I didn't say anything about it, I just went back to some class I was taking at a big high school. There were about eight of us (all adults) in the class, but I'm not sure what the class was. It was afterhours at the school but it was actually day time. It was taking place in these huge rooms that are usually used for sewing class, and as I entered I realised there were pins stuck into the ground and all over the surfaces. Lots of them, it was like the floor was lined with them although it was clearly accidental not on purpose. I felt relieved I had my boots on. I mentioned it to someone passing by and they just sighed and said yes, the year sevens had been making jumpers. I thought it was strange because that absolutlely did not seem to answer why there were SO many pins everywhere, surely they couldn't have done that by accident in one class. I also thought it funny that noone tried to clean it up, or to stop them while they were doing it. I said, no one take their shoes off then. Many of the others in my class had taken their lunch break to do something medical, and they came back with various medical patches or bandages on. There was one guy in the class who I found attractive, and I kept on accidentally calling him by my boyfriend's name. I was mortified, but then realised he didn't know the significance of the name, and my boyfriend would never know.

I was at a pub with one of my best friends. The scruffy, friendly sort. We were sitting in a booth chatting and having fun. Behind us there was a guy who I had been on a tinder date with two years ago. I had recognised him, but thought he hadn't seen me and carried on having fun with my friend. After a while he got up to leave and handed me a slip of paper - it had his contact details on it. My face had been in shade and when I looked up I thought he would recognise me and realise I wasn't a stranger, I was someone he hadn't liked, didn't want. Realise that he'd put his foot in it. There was an ambiguous look in his eyes, it could have been that I was right or that I was wrong. I felt bad about mysef and wanted to get a drink and drink it down. We went to the bar and ran into a friend of mine from uni who I've fallen out of contact with - normally she's a messy drinker, and I was excited to both see her and at the idea of a party, but then when I offered to get her a drink she was having these freshly squeezed smoothie juices instead of alcohol, she'd given it up. She was still having a great time, dancing and laughing and squealing. My friend who I'd come with doesn't drink much so she was excited about the smoothies and wanted one too. I reluctantly asked the bar maid for two smoothies, a bit disappointed that it wasn't going to be a party and still feeling that flightly nervous energy that had come with the guy from tinder.

I am zooming downhill on Beresford Avenue, which is the road going down from my parents' house to the railway station and main shopping area in Beresfield.  I am zooming because it has been raining and the roads are wet and slick - I am on a sled-type donut thing which allows me to zip across the water on the road.  My son Guy is with me, as a baby. He laughs as he splash thru a massive puddle, spraying water onto cars alongside us. At times we need to navigate around water-filled ditches, which we would get stuck in. Guy clings to my back when I jump out to clear one ditch - next to which a couple of blokes are building a fence    We quickly get to the newsagency next to the railway station (at the bottom of the hill). We call out to my brother, who is waiting for a train. He waves and throws us a bundle of money - he asks us to buy him the latest "RC Monthly" issue as there is a new car he wants to buy and to let Guy buy something for himself.  We thank him and  wave again.  In the newsagency we find RC MOnthly for my brother, the new issue of "GM" magazine for me, and Guy buys a Chupa Chup lollipop. He is happy as the newsagent tells him he can get 4 for $1 and so he chooses more to share with my brother and also my other son

I am walking through the University of Newcastle, from the main carpark around the Psych buildings and down to the Library. I am strutting along, listening to music (the soundtrack from Guardians of the Galaxy) and wearing a Star-Lord mask and jacket.  As I pass people they stop what they're doing and wave (one is juggling fire, another is fixing an old Mini Minor and there is a group watching a "protest play" featuring a white-clad woman strangling a skinny laughing Buddha).  I get to the Library steps and get out of my backpack the books I am returning (they are large, soft-cover textbooks, but I cannot see the titles or pictures)  I notice on the steps a couple of other textbooks, wedged between the steps themselves. They are soaking wet, it seems they were left out last night when it was pouring rain. Angry that someone had been so reckless with their borrowed books, I pick them up and take them to the After Hours "mailbox" and close it so all of the books are now safely ensconced in the Library.  On my way back down the steps I notice there are other things stuck between them. upon examinnig them I see that they are old comics which are also soaking wet. I pull them out and - like the old magic trick with the scarves - keep pulling out more and more comics. Some are old and wet, others are in mylar bags and so are dry, and others have been bound in bespoke "volumes"  Excited, I keep pulling out comics to see if they are ones I need to complete my collection(s) - and shout happily when I find some issues of Hellblazer, Avengers and a pristine copy of Amazing Spider-Man #3.

It's the zombie apocalypse ! It breaks out at the primary school I went to, which is across the road from a crematorium.  Zombies appear in the school itself, while skeletons erupt from the crematorium and race across to the school.  At first I am scared, but I realise that I am safe as long as I stay completely still. Inching very slowly thru the school playground as others are taken by the zombies (swelling their numbers) until I am close enough to jump the low fence. While waiting near the fence Jamie and his class go past. Jamie's teacher

Some friends from school - John, Ed and Brad - and I were travelling on a hovercraft train to New York. I was on the outside as the train was full, and it was exhilarating feeling the wind rushing past me. The others planned where they wanted to go in NY, I wasn't able to though I was really keen to visit a comic shop.  We left the train and as we started our wander thru NY we were attacked by the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and shredder. I fought them off by using a smoke bomb to hit Donatello from behind then ran off. While the others were taken by the turtles I was chased by Shredder and Raphael.  I managed to find a comic shop, on the corner of two very busy roads and jumped cars zooming past to get inside.  In there I saw my favourite comics writer and sometime e-mail chat friend Greg Rucka and an unknown artist. Sal and Greg told me the artist could help me, as his drawings were so realistic they affected the real world.  The artist drew a scene on which Raphael and Shredder fought on top of fast moving cars.  Looking outside we saw this scene playing out.  I bought a few graphic novels from Sal and Greg signed them for me before inviting my family yo have dinner with his. I ran into a local university to tell my wife of the invitation, and saw my boys flying a remote controlled Millennium Falcon. I realised I had to pee, and so spent a few minutes looking for a free toilet. It was whilst trying to find a toilet (by running up and down stairs and opening every door to find it) that I woke up.

Kings Park, Perth. It's the height of summer and families have flooded the park to play and have BBQs and walk around enjoying the trees and flowers. Sar, the boys and I are playing in the Dinosaur Park, the boys are climbing up the fort and sliding down the pole. Sar is coming back from Zamia Cafe with a latte for herself and a Vanilla Coke for me.  She drops these as a huge shadow covers the park. An enormous T-Rex with three eyes looms over the park, it's third eye blasting out a ray of pure force ! The T-Rex is a cartoon.  People scatter screaming as the T-Rex blasts down the DNA Tower and comes towards the Dinosaur Park.  Jamie and Guy spring into action - Guy uses his magic to awaken the dinosaurs of the park, while Jamie summons the Triceratons using the communicator the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles gave him last week.  Guy, riding on the brontosaurus crashes into TRex's legs while Jamie leads the Triceratons in a jet-pack powered frontal assault. Meanwhile, Sar and I guide panicked people into the Vietnam War memorial, where Aunty Nat has organised a birthday party for Guy. Everyone calms down as they eat chocolate cake, drink apple juice and watch the boys taking down the TRex.

In this dream I was acting as both the gamesmaster (GM) and a player character (PC) in a Call OF Cthulhu RPG game session. this game played out like a movie, with the players literally becoming their PCs and taking actions.  The game played out as follows:  Setting: Victorian London, a murder has taken place in a fancy hotel. I had travelled from Sydney to take part in a presentation on the recent Ackerman expedition to the South Pole. The murder was of a hotel maid and was unusual as she had drowned despite working in an upper level room.  The other investigators were an infamous "detective" whose reputation was much overestimated - he appeared to be a scruffy opium addict, a scientist from the expedition ( a woman, which was scandalous) and the hotel manager, an amateur astronomer/astrologer who had read an unusual horoscope on the night of the murder.  Lots of stuff happened, in cut-scenes (and at one point I was "interrupted" in the game by my son asking for toast  Scenes  % The detective and scientist argued about the idea that women on boats is bad luck, she punched him  % Manager disavowed any responsibility   % We decided to go to Auckland where the captain of the expedition's ship to interview him % The maid's ghost appeared and told me she was promised to a "monster"   As GM, I knew she had been killed a Deep One who loved her, he drowned her with a kiss which flooded her lungs with water   I woke up as the group went onto the ship, again as GM i knew what would happen. They would be attacked by a leviathan which shatters the ship's hull. The Deep One who killed the maid is following the ship and saves the group, taking them to an underwater city, probably R'Lyeh, where Great Cthulhu lies sleeping.

A cinema full of people are waiting for the movie to start, they are playing balloon tennis while they wait   A hugely fat nerd says something which spoils a major plot twist in the movie and he is pelted with popcorn, Jaffas and a full roast turkey  In the movie a masked man removes his domino mask. He is blonde haired with very blue eyes. Those in the room with him are shocked "Is he a Nazi ?"  Also in the movie the man runs thru a corridor, holding the hand of a West-Indian woman. They are both wearing maroon coloured robes and carrying domino masks   In the cinema I let fly with a big fart. Terribly, crap follows and my pants are filled. Embarrassed I sneak out of the cinema to clean myself up. I say out loud "Better wake up and hit the can, man"
Exams and lots of solving. Fish  Driving

I was teaching a class. There were only about a dozen kids. It was about year 5 or 6. It was a very English uniform. Grey with red stripy ties. The classroom was very cramped. They were doing an exam or test or something. The fire alarm went off. There were a lot of stairs to go down. But they were more like stairs in a castle or church tower. Stone. Lots of spirals and short cuts and obscure Directions. I don’t remember if I ever made it to the bottom.   I was in an underwater place. Everything was underwater. I remember splashing in and out of this pool, gasping for air and resisting, before I succumbed to living down there. Lots of pastel sea colours. Lots of creamy yellow sand and seaweed door curtains. There were quite a few people down there. There was a sense that everyone had to pack up and move. I didn’t understand why I had to move when I’d just got there. I didn’t know where we were going. There were just boxes everywhere. A very skinny guy came in. He was dressed in black with a leather jacket and was a bit cocky. I wasn’t intimidated by him though. He asked if he could borrow something and I obliged. He took a box of cleaning products. I followed him coz I didn’t say he could take the whole box. I ate all the hummus  Went to a talk in a theatre. 75% of people there were in blue dresses and there were also a lot of little people there. There were tens of thousands of people there. I was with my friends. They all got up and I asked where they were going. They said they needed a wee. I hadn’t even realised the talk had finished or that it was interval. I was too busy being confused and marvelling at how many people were there in blue dresses. Why? Had I missed th memo? None of my friends were in blue. We got up and went out to the foyer.

Julia Morris’ child had chicken pox  Cat eyes  I was back at school, as a student. I was told by Mr Thorton That he thought it might be best if I go to the year below. I was wore a hat to school and didn’t want to take it off. Everyone else was piling into the school hall. It had just been renovated. A school leader told me to take my hat off. This made me cross and anxious. I felt vulnerable. Everyone was lookin  at my short hair. Someone got up and everyone was told to get into their surgery groups. I didn’t know what was happening. The girl I was sitting next to was kind and explained that it’s the project they’re doing at the moment. They have a pretend doctors surgery and they had to research the history of doctors as well as conduct their own - hire all the people, work out how much to order the equipment and running the bookings ect. My school friend Cat was sitting at the next table. I realised it was a joint 5/6 project. I thought maybe I could manage this after all. Cat disappeared though and when she came back she looked more like when we were in year 12. I suddenly remembered that was was meant to be in yr12 and only go back one year but now I seemed to be in yr 5. Had everyone brainwashed me or was I so stupid I had to go back to yr5? Cat came back and was trying to study for her exam. Rachel was begging Cat for a drink of water. She had 2,1 litre bTitles sitting on her table. She didn’t want to share her bottle but Rachel kept begging. Cat was so determined to deny Rachel the water she poured it over herself, in the middle of the school hall. Then I was called over by a teacher to come and read to her in the corner. I was so embarrassed I had to go read to her. She had to ask me twice to come. I got up and walked over but just as I got to the table I dramatically yelled, ‘I can’t do this!’ And collapsed into the table in a ball of tears. Everyone just stared at me. I hid my head in my arms and cried.   I was in the backyard of a house I didn’t know. There were lots of steps up to the house - maybe two flights. The grass I was standing on was synthetic and there was a big open shed to the side... maybe more like a tim roof with a back and clear plastic sides, no front - it was huge. I was wondering around in my school dress on the grass. It didn’t fit me anymore. Margaret was there. she said she suddenly had to go home. I was confused and thought we already were home. I turned around and I could suddenly see her getting on a train on a platform way above the shed. The platform was built on a sandstone wall. It was just your average metro melb train but when they were green, not blue. I was sad she had to go so suddenly and wondered if anyone else was going to come home. I did strangely think Marg was just taking a train on a scenic route to the front door. I was sure to beat her home. Then I realised there were all the instruments laid out - violins, violas, clarinets, flutes and a piano. Just as I thought made I would have a play of the violin , it started to rain and I thought I better get the instruments out of the rain. So I was running with over filled arms with instruments to the uncover of the shed. Once I got all the instruments there I thought I better play the violin but it just wasn’t the same and I was cold and soaked through. So I took of all my clothes, left them in the shed and climbed the many stairs to the house. Everything was very white. I put on a white singlet, like a men’s under singlet and some white men’s undies. I turned around and Emily was standing there. I was so surprised she was there. She asked me, ‘what are you doing?!’ At the same time I asked her, ‘how long have you been here?!’ Marg walked in the front door. Everything went black.   I was wandering around a University campus. Some parts were extremely old, like Ancient Greece or Rome and other parts were modern, like maybe built in the 80s and everything in between. Big buildings and very tight pathways between. It felt like a maze I was unfamiliar with. I seemed to be on a teamed scavenger hunt but I somehow had been separated from my group. I was finding things for the scavenger hunt but I had no way to record them. I walked into this chapel but it was more like the crypt. It was very dark and closed in, rough stone walls and ceiling. There was soft spot lighting shining on the ceiling where there were faded drawings, mostly in a clay red. They were stunning. I kept marvelling at it, leaving the chapel, thinking I’d try a different direction and a different door but I kept finding myself back in this chapel staring at the ceiling. I found a few members of my group just outside the chapel and asked if they’d seen the drawings inside. They said they hadn’t and so I took them in to show them. They said it was amazing, jotted it down in their notes and left. I didn’t feel like they appreciated it as much as they should have.   I was standing in Emily and Mick’s entrance to their house. A small brown puppy came bouncing over to me. He stared barking at me and said hello and tried to calm him without touching him. He started growling at me and I was very wary but tried to pat him, which he let me but was still agitated. I asked him what was up and if I was missing something. He continued to growl at me impatiently. I suggested to Mick that I take him for a walk so he can see I’m a fun person so have around. Mick went o get his lead but the postman suddenly opened the front door unexpectedly. The dog ran out and I ran after him. He ran next door where they had this red round plastic tub they’re turned into a garden bed full of cacti. The dog did a huge wee and I realised he was just trying to tell me he was absolutely busting. Mick came over and was pleased I got the dog but said I needed to be careful in this garden bed. Last time he was here it was full of lizards and snakes. The dog was now sniffing round the grass. And when I looked back at the bed I realised all the snakes and lizards were hiding under the rocks fairly camouflage. I jumped back.

I was at some weird shopping centre. It was quite cramp space wise. It was difficult to social distance even with few people there. I went into Bakers Delight. Some girls from my high in a few year below me were serving. I was feeling stressed with how many people were in there and everyone being so relaxed. I knew the people being served inform of me too but I didn’t speak to them, I was feeling too stressed to say hello. They left and I walked up to the counter. The BD people said a snide comment about the people in front of me. I screamed at them that i knew them and they might like to hold their tongues in front of customers. They looked embarrassed. Then I next door to BD. Was another room that was being rearranged. There were lots of people all shuffling about. I realised they were going to have some kind of meeting or talk and so I joined in. Then without evening starting the packed all the chairs away. I stood in a corner watching abstract baffled. I swear they were setting up and now they’re packing up. I suddenly realised I was standing a bit cramped in this corner between this wooden desk like the teacher desk at school and a smaller desk like wooden student desk at school. Behind me were some curtains. I Opened them and realised There was a beautiful beach outside. I opened the glass door and realised to get to the sea was this sheer drop of a sand dune. It was huge. But everyone else seems to just be chilling and jogging around it like it was flat. I thought it mustn’t be as steep as it looks. I took one step out and got in the way of some joggers and cyclists. I jumped out of the way, lost balance and fell down the hill. I was clinging on for dear life. I’m not sure what I was clinging to but I daren’t move. It was gorgeous sunny day out the beach side but down I was facing the other way it was night time in the other direction. I looked up for help, which didn’t come but there was a castle on a distant mountain with fireworks. I suppose it looked a bit like the Disney castle. I was mesmerised by it and couldn’t believe no one else was turning around to look at the fireworks. Looking at the fireworks seemed to make me forget that I was terrified of clinging to the steep hill. I seemed to suddenly be able to run inside to tell people there was fireworks but by the time I got inside I didn’t get a chance to tell anyone because they were all rushing about packing their suitcases and saying ‘we have to go. We have to go now.’ I didn’t know what was happening but everyone seemed quite panicked. I found my suitcase, which was already packed. But I realised I kept forgetting bits. So my arms were laden with odd bits and pieces. Carter was there and said she couldn’t come. I didn’t understand why. I gave her a hug and told her I hoped to see her soon. She said hopefully she’d finish whatever she had to do and follow shortly. I ran out to the corridor and I seemed to be on the ground floor of my primary school. I ran to the exit and a few teachers from my high school were there i told them id forgotten my face masks. I hadn’t packed any face masks. I dropped all my things and ran back tot he room but couldn’t find any. I knew we had to go so I ran back to my luggage. One of the teachers had bought me a pack of ten. She said she knew it wasn’t enough for three weeks but it would get me through a few days. We walked out the door of school and appeared to be going into the London underground. But when we got to the bottom of the escalator we were in the tarmac of the airport. There was a plane waiting for us with a staircase attached. I got on and realised I’d forgotten my card game Spot It. I knew exactly where it was and ran of the plane. When I found the pack of cards I realised there were other students who were on the plane yet. I asked them what they were doing and they were too scared to come. We had to be fast and I told them we could fly to the plane. And we did. I don’t know how we flew like superhero’s but we did. One of the guys id found fell from the sky mid flight. I felt guilty but there was no time to see if he was ok. The plane was due to leave. The other and I made it too the plane and I could see the other guy was ok and now running for the plane. But suddenly I was surrounded by police. The people who had just boarded the plane With me were arrested, as was I. I didn’t know why I was being handcuffed. The guy who fell out of the sky saw all this happening and hid behind a bus. We we assorted away and taken to what looked like a prison camp.

Someone was trying to kill me.   Square KFC  Lots of sneaking about.   I was in a bedroom I didn’t know. Sitting on the bed looking out the window. A group of kids were having a surf lesson but the waves were getting bigger and bigger. A woman in a white bikini, separate from the surf lesson on the sand was just heading out for a swim. It looked very dark and cold for a bikini. She dove into a wave and then kind of became the wave or was inside the wave. She had her arms out and legs together like a cross. The wave was in slow motion. It lifted her up, her back to the bank. It slowly flipped her backwards with the cube of the wave and then when she was upside it sped up and slammed her into the ground. She was then just a floating body in the sea. The kids were screaming and ran of. I panicked I’d be blamed for her death and the kids would find me in this room I didn’t know, so I hid under the covers. No one came for me.   I walked past a toy shop. I knew I shouldn’t go in, restriction say we shouldn’t. It was a lovely old toy shop with antique toys. I asked the man at The desk if he’d mind me having a look around. He indulged me. It was a bit cramped but I loved looking at everything. I was just about to leave when I saw a toy rabbit I actually had as a child. I was so excited and told the man. He smiled but then quickly wasn’t smiling. Then I realised I’d knocked a whole stand of toys over. I offered to pick them all up for him and as I was doing so, I kept finding more and more toys I recognised from my childhood. I had to stand on a ladder to put some back in the shelf. I was in the back seat of a car. My friend Clara was in the passenger seat and her boyfriend was driving the car. We were driving on country roads in the US. It was such a long drive and I kept dozing because I was so tired. I suddenly realised, despite it being night time, that there was orange glowing in the distance getting closer and closer. Panic entered me. I know what orange glowing means in the middle of the night. I told the guy driving we have to stop and turn around, fire is ahead. He shrugged me off and it was too late anyway, there were flames on the side of the road. I could see emergency services blocking the road ahead. He pulled over. Clara seemed to wake and asked why we were pulled over. The guy said he’d hit a sign and had to stop. He got out and walked over to the police blocking the road. Clara said she was struggling to breathe and opened the door. I screamed at her to shut the door. The smoke was getting into the car. She seemed to have forgotten what bushfires are like. I didn’t know how we’d got to California. I thought we were in New York. Had we really been driving for that long?! I remember screaming at Clara, ‘why is no one Fucking concerned that Australia and California have had the biggest fires they’ve ever seen IN THE SAME YEAR?!?!?’. Clara and I seemed to suddenly be at a beach house. White 50s weatherboard beach house. She said we had to find the dogs. And I was thinking ‘when the fuck did you get dogs?’ We finally found them and I was thinking, ‘oh are we looking after Cat’s dogs?’. The house was slightly oddly configured but there seemed to be eski’s full of bottles of soft drink. Clara kept cussing that her boyfriend had drunk all the bottles she liked. I just remember hold a 1 litre coke bottle and there was only about 1cm left.

I found a dead body with its insides spilling out everywhere. I was terrified.   Ben  and I were on some kind of mission. We were sneaking around a Uni campus. It was quite modern. Someone stopped us and Ben referred the question to me. I had to lie but I wasn’t even sure what I was lying about. We seemed to get by. We found a pub and went in. It was bustling with people. I bumped into two school friends. They were pleased to see me and couldn’t believe I’d made it for whoever’s birthday it was. I didn’t really know what they were talking about  but pretended I did. I turned around there was a big easel with a poster in it. It was in blurred colours brown and gold. Then I realise Jason Crawford was signing autographs just over there. I completely melted inside. I was just plucking up the courage to go over there when Clara came rushing over, ‘it’s time you go. If you want to catch ???? You have to go now!’ And she pushed me out the door without saying goodbye to anyone. I was very annoyed she wouldn’t let me say goodbye to anyone and didn’t understand the rush. I went to the car and thought about texting people goodbye but when I got to the car I realised the drivers door wasn’t quite shut properly. I shrugged it off and thought it would have been Clara when she went to get something out of my car. But then my car wouldn’t start, telling me a door was still open. So I lent over to the passenger side door, opened and closed. I realised it too was ajar. I thought it was a bit weird but I shrugged it off thinking Clara must have had trouble finding it. The car still said there was a door open. So I lent over to the passenger side Back door and it too was ajar. I was a bit concerned now that someone has ransacked my car. I just wanted to go home though so the car finally started and I backed out of the space in the carpark. It was a small carpark with only about a dozen cars and a laneway to enter and exit. I backed out and suddenly realised my brakes didn’t work. I started rolling backwards down this lane way. A few people ran out of the pub  and were screaming at me to stop and keep calm. They were going crazy yelling. I was a little panicked but I was keeping calm. Just trying to concentrate on steering the car and hoot the horn to get everyone out of the way. Then it’s like I blacked out and woke up finding myself in a tangled mess on the ground just outside the lane. It was dark and I was crying. There was a man loitering. I wasn’t sure if he’d already raped me or was about to. I found my phone and rang my parents to ask if they could come pick me up. They didn’t sound very interested by reluctantly said they’d come. I put down the phone. The man grabbed me.

It was night time and everything was dark. My friend was having a party at a nightclub or bar. It was a secret though. I mean the location was a secret. It was in the top floor of a tall building. Like 5-10 storey building from a 1920s or 1950s detective Movie. The stair case was very run down and the lift looked dangerous and was the old style cage like thing with two fires you have to open and close one after the other. And there was an operator. We had to all meet out the front first and then we were divided up Into smaller groups so it was easier to sneak up undetected. Then there were a series of secret tunnels, hurdles and slides to go through. Some were easier than other. Some were dark and dirty. Some where a tight squeeze. Some went into the walls or ceiling. And sometimes we had to solve puzzles or riddles or clues to move on. Sometimes we got caught and it was like a computer game where we had to start again from the start. We finally made it too the top but these detective found us and then it really was game over. They arrested us and took us away to jail and charged us with hefty fines for breaking the law and leaving the house without valid reason and gathering illegally.

Being kept captive in a hospital. It was very pristine. Lot of long corridors. I was trying to escape. Ended up in this room. This voice came over a loud speaker and instructed me to give myself a mammogram. It was terrifying.  I was wandering around backstreets and alleyways with a friend. Clare found us. She was behaving slightly oddly but convinced us her apartment would be safe. So we followed her back. She told us to wait there, she had to go and pick up her daughter and get some food. I was a bit uncomfortable being there and felt hesitant to touch anything. The person I was with was much more relaxed and I remember snapping at them to not touch anything. Could we really trust Clare? Clare’s parents arrived. They told us they were there for the professional development course. I asked them why it interested them and they said they wanted to learn some dance moves for their music videos they make. I suddenly had food wrappers in my hand and I went to the kitchen to put them in the bin. I could only find the compost and the soft plastics bin. Luckily it was soft plastics I had but I did wonder where all the other bins were or if maybe there was just a general waste somewhere. I was very confused. I went back into the living room and things were happening there was lots of bustling. Everyone had to move now. Someone was coming. We could not be found. We ran quickly and quietly down the corridor. I could see and hear fireworks in the distance.

I was at my high school in the PE department. eggs. I think Mr Hogan was there. It was nighttime. I think I got on a tram. One of the green ones. I had a feeling of being lost and trying to find something.

I had a Facebook comment conversation with Rueben. It was a lucid dream. I kept thinking in the dream, remember it’s 2.15am, remember it’s 2.15am. When finally opened my eyes and looked at the clock it was 4.20am. I was in an upstairs apartment. It was like id just moved in. Boxes everywhere. I don’t remember much but I do remember feeling very tired, very lost and overwhelmed, very unsure And afraid. The stairs are significant. And there were lots of shadows. I was back at high school. I was at rowing training in the morning. Our warmup was a bit slow which made us come in late. I was worried about Lily. I couldn’t find her Once we’d come in. The coach told me I had to carry all this equipment back to school. So I walked back to school with all this equipment id never seen before. I suppose they were like oars but all different sizes and length and none of them useful. I had some with the girth bigger than you could use in a boat, difficult to carry. I also had a lots of tiny ones that I kept dropping. I finally got back to school and the corridors were very narrow. It was a challenge to walk down them with all the oars. I came through some double doors and the corridor smelt like a swimming pool and the walls and ceiling were this light pastel green colour. There was a huge crowd standing there, all looking at something. I was really struggling and I was dropping oars at all angles. I called out for some help but no one even turned. So I said to myself, ‘don’t worry [name], just put everything down, reorganise and go again.’ While I was reorganising the oars, someone came over and informed me that the crowd was the Aus netball competition and they weren’t happy we were late and packing up around them. I picked up the oars again and had to carry them through this crowd. I tried to be polite and crack a joke. The captain of the team, with arm crossed and in a very bitchy voice said, ‘good to see you’re studying hard.’ I got instantly mad and retorted, ‘oh would you like to help and carry these for me.’ She put her nose in the air and turned away. I had to wait briefly for the ball yo go out of bounds and the whistle gone to pause the game so I could run across it to the storage shed. I could feel the crowd livid with me. Once id got rid of the oars I went to the change rooms. There were a few people from my year level just chatting. The change rooms also seemed to be this green colour. I got to a big umm box thing. Huge. Built in. Like seamless with the floor but came up to about waist high and was about 1m wide and 2m long. It was some kind of bin and I put a few things in. I suddenly realised I was also carrying a small box. It was made of cardboard but looked nice. Like a gift box. It was pale pink. It had Barbara Streisand written in the top. I opened the box and it started to sing ‘ba ba ba, Barbara Ann, ba ba ba, Barbara Ann etc.’

Throwing balls  Rain. Lots of rain. My family being weird. One of my sister’s live IN the computer. Huge indoor plants with great big long leaves.   I was lost with a group of people. We wondered tunnels and caves and corridors. People slowly dropped off or disappeared the longer we were lost. Sometimes we’d get to a ‘room’ in the cave and there’d be something like a wedding or conference or something. Nothing helpful. I seemed to be standing on a bridge with a few others. Looking down there was lots of rushing water. Out of nowhere there appeared a robot that looked like Santa but a very square form of him. He somehow separated me and backed me into a cave room. He pressed a button and laughed an evil robot laugh. White rolled doors came down and shut us in. He announced he was going to kill me. He caused me around. I was terrified. I tripped over

Mum got a greyhound. I was stunning and confused.   Murder. There was lots of creeping about a dark house. I felt scared.   I was trying to meet up with someone. It was dark. And raining. It was on a farm. I had to climb many fences and walk through many paddocks to get there. I felt like I was going as fast as I could but not getting anywhere - going round in circles. It was very muddy. I couldn’t find them. I was annoyed. Google maps popped up in my head and kept trying to tell me ‘location not found’ and so I was having to use the map manually to work out where to go. I was suddenly in a car moving very fast on a freeway. High walls either side. I was terrified I was going to crash. I couldn’t slow down and I felt out of control. I still didn’t know where I was going and I was still trying to find this person at this mysterious location. Everything was moving so fast and I couldn’t read any of the exit signs. It was also still dark and raining. I suddenly realised I was going the wrong way and I should be going the opposite direction. I’m not sure if I was driving or not but the brakes slammed in and the car span out. It was terrifying. No time to recover though, the car quickly zoomed off again in the opposite direction.
Sex. Went on a date. I was wet and uncomfortable. I was on school camp. Wanted to go home. Tired of being told what to do and not being able to see my family.

I was meeting my old school friend Annalisa for a quick coffee before she got on a train back to England. We met in a t-shirt shop which I wanted to look around because, as I explained to her, whenever I was in there with my kids I never got to look for myself, but there were no t-shirts on the ground floor, and she was keen to go elsewhere. We were both wearing North Face jackets of similar but slightly different greeny-blue hue. We went to buy some gift cards in what looked like a museum or library gift shop. Later she sent me one of these cards explaining in grey felt tip, but illustrating in gooseberries, how well her 3 nieces had done in their exams. The rows of gooseberries indicated how many As and Bs they had got. I was also able to see each of these nieces posing for selfies in front of mirrors.

I was in a pub with members of my coastal rowing team. We were sitting around a round table. The man I was sitting next to was speaking but I didn't know him. My eye caught someone coming down the stairs at the back of the room. It was Richard. He came over to the table and stuck his hand out for me to shake. thinking that wasn't allowed, but shook it anyway. Then I stood up and moved next to him. He put his left arm around my waist and together we moved outside the pub, still with our arms around each other. It felt lovely.

I was in a big hotel with some of my female friends and family and lots of other women. There was some kind of warm-up entertainer who was going around and pointing at different women saying "You know someone called X". She pointed at a woman and said "You know a Scott McIntosh", and although she agreed that she did, my entire group of friends also stood up and said "We know Scott McIntosh!" which we thought was hilarious but then we felt a bit embarrassed. We were there for some kind of prize-giving for writing an essay but the prize wasn't going to be awarded until the morning so we had to sleep overnight in upright comfy chairs. Mine was the tatty orange one from our house. In the morning there was a decision to be made about when to shower, and would that mean you might miss the prize-giving?  I decided to go for it but the shower block was a long way away. As I walked along the (now very grand and large) corridors I realised that nearly everyone else was with me, but whereas I was only wrapped in a slightly too small dark green towel, they were all wearing lovely fluffy white towelling robes. Eventually we found ourselves in the centre of the hotel where the dining room was, but there was still no sign of any showers. Someone flagged down a hotel worker who, simultaneously to me seeing a sign pointing to showers on the floor below, indicated that we should meet her on the floor below. As we congregated around her, I realised that getting back to our room and clothes was going to be  tricky, and since I knew I would have a quicker shower than some of the others with their long hair, that my strategy would be to reverse the route we had just taken.

I was walking around a town in bright sunshine. The pavements had really tall curbs, the streets were cobbled. There was a big pond with geese and people pushing twin buggies around it. There was a nice looking bakery at the end of the square, but I turned my back on it and walked up the street opposite, with a friend and into a building with a group of other people, who were acquaintances rather than friends. I felt a bit uncomfortable around them but made a joke and felt better when everyone laughed. There was one boy in glasses sitting apart from the others who seemed to appreciate me more than the others. I started pruning an indoor bush next to the people, and went outside to get a black bag into which to put the clippings. When I got back inside the boy had tidied it all up for me already. I told him that was really really nice of him, and he seemed pleased. A woman then came up to me with a big bag of stuff from cleaning out her office. It was mainly junk but there were also bits of greenery and plants. I told her she could add the greenery to my bag, and held it open for her, but she blanked me and just walked away, leaving her full bag in the bin. So I started to remove the greenery from her stuff and add it to my bag. It was hard to separate the greenery from the rest of the rubbish, and tedious work.

I was walking towards the dual carriageway to the bus stop when I bumped in to my friend Marie who was dressed in short skirt, thin tights and smart boots. She was having wheelbarrow filled with chuckies and pushing it back to her house, which had a porch like an American house. I realised to my horror that it was decorated for Christmas, even though it wasn’t even Halloween yet. I said in an aside to my other friend Nicola ‘could she not have waited until it was at least the end of November?’ but out loud we both told her how great it looked. It really didn’t.

I was teaching my 13 year old daughter Claire to drive, or rather to park, our bright red Ford Focus. The parking space was very awkward, involving a really tight turn to the right and requiring the car to brush up against and through a bit of privet hedge before stopping in front of a metal bin. She managed it like a pro. I thought about how I should prune the bit of hedge you have to drive through since it was scraping the car unnecessarily.

My eldest daughter was having a violin lesson at home, her fairly useless violin teacher was accompanying her on the piano while my younger twin daughters were basically jumping around the room and getting in the way. I shouted at one of them to leave the room, and picked up the younger one and carried her outside, upside down. I realised that she had Downs syndrome. I laid her down head first on the ground and realised that I'd laid her head in a muddy patch.

I was in a cheap hotel room with some people, one of whom was Donald Trump. On the large TV screen there was footage of a fuel tanker truck sliding sideways on slick ice into a petrol station. Trump was watching this and throwing a strop because he didn't have his wellies. Next thing I knew I was on a bike cycling to a remote cottage inside of which were some of my friends, who grinned at me through the window when I cycled up to it. They were all drinking white wine. Inside the cottage the power was out and we were having trouble getting the lights to come on. I ended up in a big bed with Paul and Lee-Ann, a work colleague that I don't really like. I was only wearing my underwear, and Lee-Ann was jiggling my flabby belly and listening to the gurgling noises my stomach was making. Despite feeling really uncomfortable about this I found myself telling Lee-Ann that I liked her sense of humour, which was a lie. Paul told me that he was going to have to get up soon to catch a plane to the US, and Lee-Ann said she would be getting up to catch a plane to Canada an hour later. I didn't like the idea that I was going to be on my own. I looked at the windows and saw that there was a grubby looking man in a blue parka looking in. He had his hood up. I was scared and looked through my fingers as he moved along to the middle window and then the closest one. He turned away and I looked out the window to see that he had a really big belly. He went to his silver car, which turned out to be a large double decker bus with advertising on it for a blinds company. It was very important to me to remember the licence plate, but I could only hold 3 characters in my head, 2T3.

I didn't have a job any more but was maintaining the pretence of having one. I drove home to my home and as I was unpacking the boot someone came to visit. I left a big beige coat on the open flat-bed boot of my car as I let him in to the house.  The large house was decorated in a very old fashioned and mis-matched way. In the bathroom there were two toilet cubicles, which didn't match each other. One had a ridiculously large circular bowl with a narrow and uncomfortable looking seat. I realised I had stayed in this house many years ago with my dad when visiting friends of his in Oxford, but I could remember or work out what room I had slept in.  I went outside to do some work in the disastrous back garden. It looked like a bomb site. I was trying to find some pots to replant. Someone pointed out the one I was looking for inside a big concrete drainage pipe. As I went to retrieve it my left foot slipped into a muddy trench up to my knee. The soil was full of both worms and small pebbles. My leg was clarted in mud and I regretted wearing shorts.  On the right hand side of the garden there was a steep slope down to an outdoor area which had a large red carpet, lots of sofas and an ironing board. As I walked down to it I drew almost level with Donald Trump, who slid under the edge of the carpet until only his hair was visible. I thought this was hilarious and couldn't prevent myself laughing out loud. Then I walked over to the ironing board and started to iron white shirts, some of which belonged to Donald Trump.

I was at the beach with two friends, one of whom was my friend Sarah, the other unknown. I told them I was going to go for a jog, even though I was not wearing the right type of clothes or footwear. I ran across the soft sand to where the sand was firmer, holding my jacket across my chest, partly to keep it from flapping and also to provide support as I wasn't wearing a sports bra. My shoulder bag was flapping annoyingly at my hip. I looked down and realised I'd gone too close to the sea, and my maroon chelsea boots were splashing in the water. I felt annoyed that they would now be salt-stained. I turned inland to run on a path next to the coast because there was a rocky headland I couldn't run over. The path took me past a new house being constructed. It was an odd shape with what looked like an enormous garage-to-be but very little living space.  The dream ended with me in an underground car park watching the bad instructor from the Karate Kid flirting with and kissing a rather unattractive woman in a wheelchair. She wouldn't stop talking as he was trying to kiss her, and when he finally managed to kiss her she rated him afterwards as a 'better than I expected'.

I was observing a large extended family with at least one special needs child. They were trying to leave a museum and getting everyone ready to get in to their van. Two of the children needed to get special dental implants/retainers fitted before getting in the van. One of them, a boy, was fighting against the process. He needed to be draped in a disposable see-through plastic gown, have the retainer fitted, and be put in to the van so that he was facing a blank white wall. He was screaming that he was going to be sick. It was distressing to watch.

I was living with a group of people (my family plus others) in a large bungalow. The room that i slept in had a little secret window that looked out on to a lane and a little chicken coop, and a larger window that looked into a garden with trees and monkeys. My daughter Sarah had a really large bed fitted with purple sheets that she was finding difficult and fussy to change.  There was a room in which a selection of fishing rods and a violin had been arranged in some kind of Heath Robinson-esque construction and I watched it all fall apart and exclaimed angrily that I didn't know what they were playing at as there were literally hundred of clamps in Paul's garage that they could be using instead of violins. Paul admitted this was true, but then had a go at me for always being on a diet that affected the way the rest of the family had to eat, and yet I was always cheating and not losing any weight. He made fun of my swollen stomach and chest. I looked down at myself wearing my blue sleep t-shirt and it was all tight. I felt hurt but recognised that he was right. I stood up to stalk out of the room and found that I was now wearing my eldest daughters school shirt and cardigan. I left the room with poise and dignity.

I was in some insanely cheapy shop that I had never been in before and was selling loads of exciting stuff and also really cheap including vegan coconut biscuits which I was very excited about. I was there with my younger brother and the shop was quite chaotic and all the banners and signs were red in colour. There was a buy one get one half price offer and I went up to a sales assistant, she was an elderly woman and she was up a ladder down one of the aisles hanging a sign from the ceiling and I asked her if the buy one get one half price offer applied to all of the items in the entire store and she said that it did so I started going around the store trying to find the best deal available by getting something relatively expensive and then getting another expensive thing at half the price.

Dreamed about getting a Christmas card from my old childminder where she said she hoped we'd get in touch with her address on one side of the Christmas card. On the other side of the Christmas card she had a picture of 4 dogs that belonged to her and little stick drawings of the people now in her family. I was in my living room when I opened the card and my younger brother and my mum were present. I thought it was strange that she was sending a Christmas card after so long but I also felt excited and happy that she'd got in touch after so long and it was nice to hear about what was going on in her life and who was in her life now. I spoke to my brother about what I should say about him in my response to her and whether he wanted me to say he had changed his name due to being transgender, he said that he didn't want me to tell her. Then I thought about all the things I was going to tell her in my response like my A-level results and what I was studying at university now and this made me feel excited because I wanted to be able to share that stuff with her.

I was at my boyfriend's house and I found a plate of brownies on his table that I'd made a month ago that had hardly been eaten that I had made for his family. I then asked him why no one had eaten them and he said "Because they're yours" and I said, "but I made them for your family". I felt a bit insulted and upset that the brownies had been left for so long and it felt like his family were choosing not to eat them because I made them. I then took them upstairs to offer them to his brother and sister although in the dream, even though we were supposed to be in his house in the dream, in real life it is my house and although I was supposed to be giving the brownies to his brother and sister, in the dream I was going them to my brothers but it made sense in the dream. A few of the brownies were eaten because despite being a month old they still tasted fine. When I went back downstairs my boyfriend's mum wanted me to help put some icing that she'd made on top of the leftover brownies and so I started doing that. Then the dream morphed into them not being in it at all but I was still putting icing on top of something and talking to a family friend of mine about something. Later on in the same dream I started thinking about Christmas even though it was August and for some reason I'd already bought my boyfriend a Christmas card but I was thinking to myself that I couldn't only give him a Christmas card in August and not one actually at Christmas and then I found that I had two more Christmas cards to give him that I kept on top of my wardrobe.

falling asleep while working from home, lying down on the bench in my dining room. Throughout the dream I felt stressed and panicked.

Someone else I used to know in real life but still knew in the dream made a comment about how I'd almost got married to this guy but didn't and so I got upset and left the building and went in to someone's front garden which was actually quite big because they had like a mansion and a gate at the end of their driveway that led to their house, but they also had a front garden path which just opened out on the street and so I went onto their land knowing it was their property and found this little bench that was in front of a very small leafy tree and therefore obscured quite a bit and sat down. After a while, the person who had made the comment came to apologise about making the comment and said things would be okay and that he'd had his heartbroken quite a few times and wasn't trying to upset me with his comment. Then the police arrived through the gate from the person's house and told us we couldn't be sitting on the bench because it was private property and escorted us off the bench and started walking us back to the venue we'd been at and one of the police officers said he wanted to have a word with my mother at which point I said I was over 18 and didn't give him permission to talk to my mum, I got up really close in his face and tried to appear threatening and I felt quite smug for standing up to him like that. Once I got in to the venue I found my mum and told her to pretend she wasn't my mum because the police wanted to talk to her, the police officer came in and asked around then I went up to him and said he wasn't talking to my mum because I was over 18 and didn't give him permission to disclose any information about me at which point he shouted over me at the crowd, disclosing personal information about me, at which point I said "Okay, raise your hand if you heard me tell him not to share any personal information about me?" everyone raised their hands and I kicked the police officer out of the building because technically he was breaking the law. There was also a second police officer who hadn't been involved and had just watched amused from the sidelines who I pretended to kick out along with the other one when really we shared a nice, cheerful conversation about me standing up to him and we were both smiling at each other when I kicked the second one out. This was a happy feeling. Then I got a message from my boyfriend saying how he felt things were too weird between us after lockdown and all the reasons why we couldn't be together anymore...

I was out in my local town centre with my mum and my younger brother and we were going to go shopping and it was much busier than I was expecting it to be and I felt anxious and overwhelmed by how many people there were on the streets when there wasn't actually that much space to stay away from people. Then I realised to my horror that I wasn't wearing a mask and got really stressed and so tried to cover my mouth and nose with my hand but didn't know what to do now as I didn't have a mask with me and there were so many people around that I felt like I wasn't safe anymore.

I was part of a group of kids/young people and we were all on the run from something, but not actually running away, more like, escaping and we were taking boxes of stuff with us and we kept camping out in random abandoned buildings that we had to look around to make sure they were safe and sometimes they had like booby traps or trip wires. In one of the buildings which was quite small I was anxious of looking around because it was quite dusty and dirty and there were lots of cobwebs and I was frightened that there were going to be spiders. my boyfriend turned out to be cheating on me in some way.

I was in a room full of young children and some adults, like a special day at kindergarten.  There was a task where we were giving each other porcelain tea cups and matching saucers. I was seated at the breakfast bar in my home.  I was aware that I dont have many dreams set in my home and the breakfast bar is a new renovation, so very current.

I was hosting a party at my place, but it was a much bigger, rambling estate than my real house. Lots of people arrived and after what seemed like hours I thought the party was a dud and everyone had left, then I realised that all the party people were in the backyard in the pool and surrounding area having a great time.  The people inside were the boring old relatives and so i felt relieved that it was a good party and people were having fun.  I hooked up with Russ which was an inevitable kind of thing but not nearly as exciting as I thought.  I was pleased he didnt fuss about using a condom. Suddenly everyone started to gather around TV sets in a few parts of the house to watch the US Election results.  I didnt know what they were doing at first and then asked "Wait is this 2016 or 2020?  Becasue if its the 2016 results then I already know the outcome"  Someone said no its the 2020 election. Then the party was invaded by Trump security and there was a ceremonial parade with Trump and entourage walking through the party which no one was interested in.

set in my old high school, walking around the grounds and in various classrooms and the general hall.  I had two dresses I was trying on, one was mint colored 1950's design and the other was a more modern style, grey with black sleeves and a V-neck.  I liked the grey one.  Lisa M said she preferred the mint one.  Ginger from work was there too.  She was out of context and I dont really like or trust her so felt suspicious about her presence.  The whole thing felt a bit off, weird.

My sister and I were taking washing off the line and chatting, very low key, domestic ordinary vibe.  The washing line was in the dusty car park near the train station.  I saw a white van drive off and tried to listen to hear what music the person playing.  I thought it was a song I liked and hoped it was a song with a significant meaning or memory so it would be a good omen.  However it was disappointing to recognise it as a Justin Timberlake song which meant nothing to me.

There was a big warehouse type place and lots of people around.  There was a stocky good looking guy and David Bowie and others participating in an orgy type party.  There was a huge sheet of material covering everyone and a gym mat on the floor and myself and the stocky guy were getting into it.  David Bowie was keen on me too(!!) but I was getting it on with the other guy. It was very erotic and arousing.   I was aware that my teenage son was around and there was also a baby under the sheet with their parents, just laying there, nothing sexual but too close to the action. The journey to my place was convoluted and it took ages to get there, with lots of interruptions and distractions on the way. I'm walking down the street at night.  It is Chapman St where I grew up.  I'm walking alone and after a few minutes I feel very alone, aware of my isolation and vulnerability.  I realise I am not safe or comfortable walking alone and turn around to head back home. There is another part of town where all the cars and people are headed. There are lots of individuals in battered old Holden Kingswood cars.  The cars are full to the brim with what looks like junk but I realise its their belongings and they all live in their cars.  They all look a bit homeless or mildly zombie-ish.  There are no windows or windscreens in any of these cars.  The roads are chaotic and traffic is congested.  I realise things are pretty bad and pretty grim for many people.

In the loungeroom of my childhood home.  I notice that Phil has hung his washing up all over the room, draped over the couch, chairs, hanging from the mantlepiece.  I cant bear to see it like that and start re-hanging it using the actual clothes line which hangs from the ceiling near where he's draped his clothes.  I'm not as angry or annoyed as I would usually be if I saw this lack of common sense and just feel a bit bemused.  When I finish hanging it I feel pleased and then gently chide him some more as he sits at the dining table studying.  I lean in to him and say 'kiss my neck, c'mon' and he does and he hasnt done that for ages and it feels nice. I notice he has some tablets and ask if they are the same as panadol and he says yes.  I say 'are they exactly the same?'  Yes the same.  I ask what are they called and he says Metamuesil.  I crunch 1 & 1/2 tablets and he asks how many did you have.  I am not confident they are the same as panadol and think they are actually some kind of constipation medication but trust him anyway.

Phil (current partner) and I were with Mia (friend) at a country cottage like we had just stayed there for the weekend.  Mia got back from seeing a psychic/astrologer and said she had to tell me something.  She said the psychic told her this was the last time she was going to see us.  Meaning we were going to die soon, like on the way home from this trip. I started having a panic attack as I realised this was probably true.  I was remembering all the weird conversations of late, like when my son asked what would happen if he became an orphan. I was hyperventilating whilst Phil sat there offering rational explanations for everything and I felt annoyed that he didnt get it.   I was thinking about whether we should drive home, or stay longer to beat or trick our fate into living longer.  I was very scared as it seemed our fate was sealed.

Phil and I had to take a test, like a political general knowledge test for The Greens.  We both did well on it and were keen to compare scores.  I felt pleased, even smug. Later at a party, for the Greens I was meeting some new people at a table and then spilt my glass of wine and the glass smashed on the floor.  I felt ashamed and embarrassed and bewildered-thinking Gosh that the third time this week I've knocked over my wine glass. At the same party I was introduced to or meeting a new boss for the first time and commented that she really liked my grey cardigan. I say, yes its a good one-pure wool and show her the wool mark logo as proof.  Op shop bargain I tell her, only $2! Finally back at home after all this, there are 4-5 teenage boys having a sleepover, comfortably taking over the loungeroom with their sleeping bags and mattresses.  They have their phones and ipads etc and are all very comfortable, friendly and fun happy vibes.  It's like I havent seen them for ages and its nice.

Travelling around like a backpacker, staying in various places.  There were Indian kids hiding in the rooms, going through the bags and sleeping inside the empty backpacks at night.  I lost a lot of belongings but wasnt particularly worried, felt a annoyed with myself for not keeping things safer, but going with the flow.  There was an informal cooking class happening in the backpackers kitchen.  It was my teenage son telling everyone how to make meringues.  He admitted it was an unorthodox recipe and method but assured everyone it would work well.  The egg whites were in a bowl with some mashed avocado and he said we should take a mouthful of the egg whites and swish it around and then spit it back into the bowl and whisk away.  The meringues would stiffen and work beautifully due to the extra ingredient of saliva.   I thought it was a bit disgusting and went along with it, trusting the process.  What's the worst outcome hey?

Phil drives me and other friends, Narelle, Nada, Mia out to a movie and to get a pizza.  He is driving carelessly, a bit aggressively not sure why he's driving like that.  Taking corners recklessly in the car park and eventually, inevitably he crashed into an embankment and the car is wrecked.  Its my subaru and I wonder to myself-why wasnt I driving anyway?  This wouldnt have happened if I was driving.  I feel annoyed and embarrassed.  We have to wait for ages in the car park for the pizza and realsie we wont get to see the movie and after a while the car and Phil vanish.  Nada says to me that it's nice to watch me being kind to Mia.

I was with my partner and son but we were in an empty house which was my first share house 30 years ago.  I was wrapped in my son's furry plush blanket for safety because there were horrifying jumping psychotic Huntsmen spiders in the house.  Many, many of them but they jumped violently in every direction and I was terrified they were going to land in my face or on me.  I had to ask Phil to help.  I was very anxious and scared.  I couldnt believe how out of control the house was with these spiders.

walking down some stairs to a railway station. There was a fountain at the top of the stairs with several jets rather than a single jet. There was a barrier at the top of the stairs comprising what I think was a wooden trellis-type fence. I have the impression that the station was in Germany. I think I was outside the station and I have a memory of a grassy hill or bank at the back. At some point I felt I needed to go back but initially went to another station (there  were actually a number of stations on one long platform) but wanted to go back to the one with fountains. I recognised it by the wooden trellis, but I think the fountain wasn’t working.

I was driving down a country lane not far from my home, looking for something to photograph. The fields had recently been ploughed and were a beautiful dark brown, which contrasted with areas of green grass. There were a few trees dotted here and there, but I couldn’t see a suitable composition. My overall impression was of the rich deep brown of the fields which gave me a feeling of joy. At some point I was looking down from a balloon, and then I was on the ground trying to hold on to the balloon with a rope, but the rope slipped out of my hands and the balloon drifted away. I have the impression that I was Steve Coogan as a character in the film A Cock and Bull Story, based on an 18th century novel by Tristram Shandy, although I seemed to be both him and watching him at the same time. I managed to catch hold of the rope, which was now a length of string, but it was too short and not long enough to keep the balloon from floating away, so as the string started to slip out of my hands again, someone else, a woman I think, tied the string to some thick rope.

I was observing, or involved in, the filming of a stage play. They wanted to illustrate a scene or a theme of the play and I suggested photographing overlapping pages of newspapers. The stills photographer disappeared so I started to tear out pages of some newspapers and arranging them in different ways - in a circular pattern and then in a linear pattern. I seem to remember someone gave me a camera so I started photographing what I'd done. Suddenly I was in a different part of the area they were filming in and I continued photographing arrangements of newspapers. I started walking back to where I was before and passed someone with what looked like a microphone boom. He was complaining about something, possibly people getting in the way.

I was at a swimming baths and meeting some friends, or maybe work colleagues. We were in the dressing room but for some reason we were not able to get undressed. I found myself in another part of the building on my own and trying to find my way back to the pool. I found  that there was more than one pool in the building and went into one. There were  number of people in the pool and they appeared to be standing up. I think they were all adults. I couldn’t see my friends so I went to another pool. The building seemed to be in the shape of the letter H, with a pool at each end of the legs. I went from one pool to another and people seem to be being instructed in something but not swimming. I think I found my friends but they were not ready so I went into the pool myself. On the way out of the building I smelled the sleeve of my coat and decided it needed washing.

There's a big house/convention centre where people were setting up an art/design exhibition and then also later it was an Airbnb I was staying in. There was a lot of history to this place and we talked to the owners about things that had happened, including maybe some films that were made there? We took a long time to decide what DVD to watch and never ended up doing it. I think I was there because my boyfriend had some kind of involvement. It's possible one of our dads used to live there and people who knew him were talking us through some memories.

I was looking for a sunken boat and found myself walking across a snow-covered field at night wearing a head-torch so that I could see the way. I saw a line of people coming towards me. They were all in 18th century dress but with modern head-torches. I told them I thought they looked strange. I found myself inside what I think was the sunken boat. I was walking along a corridor with wooden doors on either side, but everything was dry, as if I was walking through the corridors of a hotel. I was returning later by air, looking for the location of the sunken boat and saw a large ship below us. I had the impression that it was like a pirate radio ship from the 60s. We set down in the water but the people on the ship told us it was not the right location so we were in the air again.

I was in a large room, and I was aware of a few other people at the other side of the room. There was a large wrapped bundle on a bench-type table immediately in front of me. I unwrapped the bundle which contained some large white sheets of what I understood to be photographic printing paper, but they were made of cloth with a heavy embossed pattern, similar to embossed wallpaper. I picked one up and held it up to look at it. I said the embossing was very heavy and I couldn’t see how a photograph would look on it as the undulations would break up the image. It appeared they belonged to a photographer I follow on YouTube. He said he needed something to reduce the impact of his very large television, at which point we seemed to be in his living room where he was showing me his television. I said I only have a small television.

I was in a local specialist camera shop buying a photography accessory. It appeared to be made of plastic, round and slightly hollow. For some reason I had to go back for it later. I asked how much it was. The assistant had previously said he would give me a discount as a special offer but couldn’t remember what he’d said. He asked me if I could remember and I said I think he’d said it was an offer until Isaac Asimov’s visit to the town which seemed to be in February. He consulted with a colleague and agreed to give me the discount.

I was looking at a what might have been a web-page, or it could have been a sheet of white paper. There was a link to a job or a project so I clicked on it to express an interest. I was with a female Indonesian friend who I had trained with as a Careers Adviser 30 years ago. She showed me a form she wanted to complete which was a response to the link I accessed earlier. It was a small sheet of paper folded over like a small leaflet. When I looked at it I told her it didn’t look like the job or project I’d expressed an interest in so I agreed to check it out. I was in a room in a house discussing the situation with someone who I think resembled someone I trained with as a teacher 50 years ago. We talked about my relationship with my Indonesian friend. He said I should forget it but my feelings for her were more than just friendship and I didn’t want to let her down. I went to meet her in what appeared to be either a park or a pub garden. I sat down next to her at a bench-type table but said I had to leave and went to my car which was next to the table we were sitting at. I saw her go over to to another table to talk to some friends. I think they were talking about exam results.

I was in what appeared to be a classroom, but it might have been an office. I was with two people, a man and a woman, both fairly young, who appeared to be people I’d worked with in the past but they didn’t resemble anyone I knew. They were showing me how to make a drink in a glass and explaining what ingredients to use. I think it was a frothy drink, but I don’t think it was alcoholic. I went to taste it, but instead I was eating a fish, which I think was cod. It was just the white flesh of the fish, with no skin and it was very tender. I explained that I often baked fish myself using breadcrumbs, because what you can buy in a supermarket doesn’t taste as good. I explained what ingredients I used, which included breadcrumbs, water and flour, but I seemed to get them mixed up when I was explaining it.

I was talking to an older man (maybe in a pub). We were laughing about something and he suggested my bathroom needed tiling and he could do it for me. He resembled an electrician who had fitted a new extractor fan in my bathroom about three weeks ago. I felt relieved and grateful that someone had offered to do it for me and I imagined what it would look like.

I was trying to find a flat I used to live in in Hull, in Humberside, more than forty years ago. I walked past a house with the number 60 in large red letters, but I wasn't sure if that was the right number. It was in a row of Victorian terraced houses and it looked like the right one as there was an alleyway at the side. I walked to the end of the row and decided it must have been the right house so I walked back. I walked up the alleyway and turned into a much narrower alleyway as I remembered that if it was the right house it would lead to the back of the houses. I saw a fire escape at the back of the house, which I remembered from living there, so I knew it was the right one.  Then I seemed to be in a different house and someone showed me to a room which I was going to stay in. The room was quite small. I found myself downstairs sitting nest to a woman who I appeared to own the house. She was either showing me something or we were discussing the rent. I leaned towards her and put my fingers in her vagina. She enjoyed it so I continued until she had an orgasm.  I was then trying to get home and waited for a bus to take me to the station or the airport. I knew I had to get a number 2  bus.
