Several buses came together, one of which was a number 622, but none were a number 2. I decided to drive to the station or airport and some friends gave me lft to my flat to collect my things. They dropped me off at the corner of a street. I could see the street sign with the name of the street but I couldn't make out the name clearly. I was in a communal kitchen making a cup of tea, but I remarked that it was bigger and more modern than I remembered it. I found myself walking up some stairs to my room, which I hadn't used. The room was on the corner of a landing at the top of some stairs. A cleaner saw me and asked me who I was. I said I lived there.I tried to open the door to the room but the key wouldn't fit. Then I realized that it was the key to my home. I had several keys and found the right one, which was silver. Once inside I heard voices outside and someone knocked on my door. It was the cleaner asking for the rent.  I was driving home and decided to get some petrol as I had a long drive. I thought I would have enough petrol to get me home but I thought it would be safer to fill up anyway. I pulled into a large car park with a lot of empty bays. I had to swerve around some cars to get to the bays, but the only one which had a petrol pump was at the end, in the direction I'd just come from, so I had to turn around to get to it. There was a car already in the bay, but there was enough room for aother car, so I pulled in next to it. When I got out of my car I saw that the other car was a taxi - it had a red sign on top. A man was leaning out of the rear window of the taxi on the left hand side as I walked round to the front of it to get to the petrol pump. I had to stretch the hose in front of the taxi as I didn't want to damage the car. I found the filler cap on my car was low down at the front rather than at the back. This made it easier to put the hose in but I thought it was a bit strange as I had seen that on car before. Then I remembered that I'd changed my car. This one was white.   When I went to the kiosk to pay I said the petrol pump was number 1. The man in the kiosk said no it wasn't, implying  that there wasn't a pump with that number. Then I remembered it was number 4. He asked me something and showed me a printed card. I told him I didn't understand what he said so he gave me the card. It was an advertisement for something so I gave it back to him and said I wasn't interested. I paid with a credit card but he had to use tone of he old embossing machines. We talked about the new automatic system where you swiped your card, and I told him about someone I knew who said it was much easier and quicker so you could process more people in the same amount of time.  I wanted to get some CDs out of my bags so I could play some music on the drive home but I couldn't remember which bag they were in so I rummaged through all of them until I found them in a rack. I was then driving back, but instead of using the motorway I decided to take the scenic rout and go through York.

There were a lot of videos of my previous adventures with friends in my 20s that appeared online, based somewhat on reality but more involved - some sexual, some about this acting/charades game we used to play. It was great to see the videos but also a bit embarrassing. We were in the alps or new zealand and joined some kind of dance class, or art exhibition. Or it might have been a party I was going with my mum where she'd chosen to wear huge shiny red platforms and I'd chosen to wear comfortable 'mum shoes'. She was definitely doing it to appear younger but it made going down the stairs very hard. At one point I was going to stay at an airbnb before realizing that it was someone's messy house where I would be sleeping on the floor all in one room with the whole family - this had been described in the ad but I missed it. I also joined a class and the class was full of children except for me. It started as learning to draw but moved onto learning how to program a sort of device like a modem except you could change the configuration of the lights and lines inside to make a character walk. This was a puzzle to solve, and I knew my friend Sam was also trying to solve it so I gave him a call while on the way to his house (the same airbnb house from before but it had changed into his house apparently) and tried to describe it, and it turned out the solution also had something to do with perspective drawing and that rule where something in the mirror is exactly half it's size in real life? It was raining heavily when I arrived at the house and it turned out it was actually Mitch I was coming to see.

I had moved back to a house I'd previously lived in and had been spending time Tom who lived in this house, then a day came where a number of people died (eg. My aunties parents) and I wanted a friend to hang out with and instead he'd brought his girlfriend (they were back together) and some people back to the house to party. I tried some other friends (current and old) but nobody was available, but eventually my best friend who I usually live with was available. I was trying to wash my hair in the shower for a long time and there were times when Tom came to talk to me naked in the shower as if that was normal. I felt like nobody cared about me and that I'd made a big mistake by moving into this house when my old house was better. a concert/protest that was going to happen.

I was working at a big music festival, mainly from a tent in the back corner of the precinct but also sometimes elsewhere. At one stage there was a video we were shooting that was quite simple but other people were making it feel complex - too many cooks. There was also a religious element, the video was something to do with a church rather than the music festival, although some of the music festival people were involved. At one point later on one of my team members Anna brought me a stack of paper squares containing instructions about how the sequence of shots were to be put together. I tried to help her take one big photo of these squares laid out but wasn't able to.  Anna got quite sick, like almost having blank seizures, and it was while trying to call an ambulance for her that all the bits got out of order. Ruairidh was bouncing on a trampoline in full snowboard get-up, as if training for a x-games competition. There was a younger guy also working with me who previously had been at Beech Forest, he also had a kind of ownership of this house which was a but unsettling but didn't cause any issues. Em at some point during the festival poo-ed in her pants and had to change. Other people also changed their outfits. At one point someone else was doing my job and I tried to make it easier for her by telling her/our boss that she had to find someone else to help - she couldn't do two jobs at once. Things happened at a rapid pace but there was also some time where we just hung around waiting for stuff to happen and shot the breeze.

I was buying an apartment but the catch was that they would pay me to shoot porn in the bedroom once a month. This turned out ok except that I had to keep the apartment clean. At one point my colleage Lena went and joined in the shoot. When I was in the process of buying the apartment the broker/agent was a condescending unhelpful jerk. There was also a bushland location, there was a boat that someone had half constructed some time ago floating in the creek and I considered building it as a project but it sunk. The person who built the boat was trying to hide from the police using some kind of invisibility sheets near the boat, it wasn't scary, more like an administrative crime rather than something serious. At the same location it was very windy and a couple of people were going around trying to stop branches and trees falling down, one of them explained to me in depth a technique where you make a system of intricate channels in the tree bark to carry the wind, to prevent it falling. A group of us were waiting to take a test at this same location, the person appeared on a screen that moved around because of covid reasons - allowing her to work from home. I remember being impressed that she was able to speak to one of the other peoole in their own language (not English) to explain the process. In the apartment where my mum and dad and others were staying I had poo-ed in the shower for some reason, by mistake, and didn't get around to cleaning it so had to prevent others from using the shower without them knowing why.

I was taking part in a simulation of an old transport network, but using modern transport along an old route through a town. I found myself walking past a service which appeared to be commemorating the holocaust. I was walking along a raised glass bridge or balcony with a church below. There was a man just below the balcony kneeling down and he appeared to be praying. The balcony led to an indoor shopping centre. I walked through it and out the other side into an open street which looked like the town centre in a small market town not far from where I live. I saw an ex-girlfriend from 30 years ago in the crowd, who had lived in the town. She didn’t see me and walked on by. I felt sad and realized that I had missed my chance and was on my own.  I found myself in a car with some men who appeared to be escorting me out of the town. I looked back and there was a bright white flash that I realised was a nuclear explosion and I couldn’t see anything. I wanted to go back but found myself hoisted into the air by two men holding me under my arms, possibly suspended from a helicopter, although I couldn’t see it.  I was in a room watching all this unfold on the television, but I remembered there was a programme I wanted to watch on another channel. I switched channels and looked in a TV guide to see when the one I had been watching finished. It said it lasted 2 hours and was based on a story by Isaac Asimov.

I was in a newsagents near where I grew up. I recognised the counter from when I was a teenager and had a paper round from there. They kept my trousers on racks, along with other trousers, either for sale or belonging to someone else.I couldn’t find my trousers and the shop assistant said they’d moved them to the other side of the shop.I looked through the trousers on the rack and found what I thought were mine and took them off the rack. They looked to be the right colour but when I took them to the counter the part below the knee was black so I knew they weren’t mine. I put them back on the rack and kept looking but my trousers were not there. I told the shop assistant that my trousers were missing - there should have been at least four pairs, with two black ones. I felt angry that my trousers were missing and frustrated that the shop assistant didn’t appear to be listening.

I was walking in an area near the centre of my home town of Coventry and walked past a building which no longer exists but used to be a temporary museum or art gallery but was now a restaurant. It was in the process of being demolished and there was a large crane or mechanical digger and what appeared to be scaffolding. I was annoyed that they were destroying part of my city. I found myself inside the building where there was large bolt protruding from the medieval sandstone wall, secured by a large hexagonal nut. Some people, possibly engineers, allowed me to unscrew the hexagonal nut with an automatic device which fit over the nut. The device was yellow. I began unscrewing the nut until it came away from the wall. I remarked to the engineers how satisfying it was and how much easier it was with the automatic device. I think there was someone further along the wall unscrewing another bolt with a manual device.

I got out of bed and pulled back the duvet to find there was large wet patch on the green sheet and realised I’d wet the bed during the night, although I didn’t feel any dampness around my legs or on my pyjamas. I was in the large back bedroom of the house my grandparents lived in and which I grew up in until the age of 18. I decided I needed to go to the toilet but instead of going to the right out of the bedroom to go to the bathroom, which was at the top of the stairs, I went to the left and started to open the door of the large front bedroom where my grandparents used to sleep. The room was dark, but I remembered that Cormoran Strike and Robin Ellacott were sleeping in there, so I quietly closed the door and turned back to the bathroom. I hadn’t closed the door properly and I heard someone outside about to push open the door. I turned around and realised that it was Robin Ellacott. I sensed that she was naked although I didn’t see her apart from a glimpse of her leg. I quickly closed the door and finished urinating. I found myself in the front bedroom where Robin was on her own in pyjamas and appeared to be about to get out of bed. I asked her if it was ok if I lay down in the bed because I was tired, or maybe not feeling well. She said it was ok. She suddenly started having a panic attack, so I gave her a hug and said everything was ok and no-one was going to hurt her.

It was on a holding in a Nordic country and lots of adventures were had. There was a car we drove and crashed but didn't get hurt. There was a small group of us. We had to go into the men's bathroom to look for someone and pretended to be health inspectors, using a mousepad we'd bought as a souvenir as ID. There was an incredible hippy commune slash restaurant/event place that was made of stone and had lots of different places to explore. There were some crowds of people and it had an adventure-like quality but in the fun way I would get into scrapes on a holiday, not in a scary way. I think two teenage boys were part of my group, I can't remember the details of who exactly was there.

A sniper was wandering through the countryside picking off people one at a time. Originally he was part of a large group of people I was with when he started shooting. Early on we were forced to cross a river. I was strugglig to get a grip on the bottom as I had something on my feet which was impeding my progress and the water was up to my chest. I managed to get across by forcing my body forwards. There were other people around me and behind me and seemed to be urging me on.  We were in a busy town centre and I was aware of people being shot but there was no soud of gunfire. Someone with knowledge of the town layout said there was somewhere ahead where he might be waiting for people to go past. I heard someone say that the gunman would be there for maybe two minutes at the most and would then move on, and there seemed to be a worry that people were going to be picked off as they walked past him. There was a large crowd of people behind and in front of us.  Some aspects of the town centre, particularly the shop where the gunman was holed up, resembled the shopping centre in Coventry where I grew up and where my brother still lives. I had a feeling of panic because I couldn't escape, but just before I woke up, I seemed to be with a group of people where someone was suggesting how to outwit the gunman.

I was  driving a car behind a white van. It had double doors at the back. I think they were a group of musicians or performing artists and I was supposed to follow on behind them, but I don’t know in what capacity. The van stopped and I bumped into it, but because I wasn’t going very fast it didn’t harm either vehicle. I made a mark on the back of van with a marker pen, but someone said I should make the mark in a less obtrusive place, which I think I did when it happened again later. I had a slight sinking feeling, not because I'd bumped into the van, but because I hadn't put the mark in the right place.  We had arrived at a venue and I was in a room where there was an elderly woman lying on what was either a bed or a sofa of some kind, but it was covered with a large pink canopy like a tent. She seemed to be a singer or an actress and I think I was supposed to tell her when she had to go on stage. However I had fallen asleep and she scolded me for not telling her when to go. I had a feeling of panic or apprehension because she was angry with me.

I had finally completed a university course but didn't complete the submission correctly, didn't upload it in time. I was trying to be social at the same time, there was lots of festivities taking place. Something happened bad, I wasn't able to graduate after all that work.

I was in a kitchen with some other people. I got the impression the kitchen belonged to me, and the other people were intruders. We were trying to make a cup of tea but the kettle either wasn’t working or needed cleaning. When I looked around the kitchen was in a mess. There were things piled up all over the place although what they were was not clear. I looked at the floor and it was filthy and I said it needed cleaning. I remember thinking that I usually clean it regularly and now they had made a mess of it and I said this to them.

I had a bad boss and was working with someone else. He became more and more specific about the things we were and weren't allowed to do. There was a book of lists that we had to find items in, and they had to be sorted a particular way. One of us went on a business trip and could only wear our different dresses with the waist left to hang down rather than belted at the waist. Someone spilled water on someone else. I kicked up more and more of a stink and eventually left.

I spent a long time on a train platform looking for my bags, while the train was about to leave. I made it in time but it was very stressful. Afterwards, I went to New York with some girlfriends and had booked two different hotels and they weren't happy with what I'd booked. This was also stressful and made me really angry and I sulked while on holiday. I was overlooking the ocean and exploring different parts of the city and landscape.

someone being physically sick, perhaps in a hospital. I think it was a woman. After some time someone said everyone had to leave the building and then they were all outside on what appeared to be a grass verge. The whole building had to be evacuated. The woman who had been sick was given a small grey funnel to be sick in. I think there was suggestion that some poison was involved.
Something about health foods and making my own recipe of a product. My colleague  and his wife were in the dream - they also run a health food business

I was shopping with Mikael, my partner, and we went tminto a miscellaneous store - it had random items, it was cramped, and there was loud punk music playing. It was late at night. Mikael said he was going to go home,l. When he left I purchased a record I thought he might like and two big yellow earrings for me - I think my earring holes were closing and I needed to buy something that would keep them open. As I was making my way to the exit, a woman stopped me. She and her friends were drinking and partying in the part of the store next to the records. Somehow she started talking to me and showing me different t-shirts, all with slogans on them related to lesbian sex acts. I politely declined but she started following me, telling me I shouldn't be afraid and that lots of women were secretly lesbian. I kept declining and telling her no, thank you, I'm okay but she kept following me. She was drunk. The roads were busy as I started to walk home but she wouldn't leave me alone, even as I tried to dodge her and lose her and hide. All of her friends joined her and I tried to hide in the group to confuse her so she didn't know where I was or what direction I was going in. St one point I hid behind a bluestone wall as her group walked past. They then decided to turn around, back to the shop (all of them were loud, rambunctious and drunk). As each person walked past me, hiding against the wall, I kept thinking she would be next but she wasn't. Eventually I decided to make my escape, only to find she was on the other side of the wall waiting for me. I restrained her and tied her into a knot on a tree branch, before running away as fast as I could. I started cycling. I still had the record and the t-shirts and I was cycling erratically to get as far away as possible from her. By the time I got home, it was 11 am and I was so tired after being awake all night. I go to open the door quickly and bring my bike inside. As I lock the door behind me, I notice someone on the other side of the door. I panic. I think it's the woman and she's found me. I have my hand on the locked door handle to check she can't get in, and then peer through the door viewer. It's not the woman, it's Baddie Winkie, the famous Instagram star that's in her 90s and always posing in sensual pictures. I speak through the door and ask her what she wants. She returns that she saw one-off the t-shirts I was carrying with the slogan and thought it was good. She wanted to take a picture with it on for her Instagram and she was worth 3.5 million dollars. Reluctantly, I agree to help her quickly, even though I'm tired. As I open the door I tell her we'll take the picture in the laneway. I leave my front door open as we start walking, until I realise my two cats might try to escape. I'm right. Both are outside, near the front door. I quickly return and chase them in, one manages to run back but the other one is tricky and I end up handling her in a mean way. I feel guilty for doing it but I'm frustrated that all these obstacles are stopping me from getting into bed. I return to Baddie and she is finishing a cigarette. She throws it down, but it lands in a pole of dry sticks in my neighbours yard. I panic, watching the embers, and jump into his garden and start using my hands to scoop ash and dirt on to the pile to stop it from catching alight. After a few minutes Baddie gets impatient and I have to leave it as is, hoping that it doesn't catch fire and my efforts worked. Baddie has found an old taxable and she puts it in front of a corregated iron fence. She's wearing the white top and tight skinny jean trousers with a full face of make up and her midriff showing. She asks me to take photos on my Samsung. I do it, although I feel guilty because I would prefer to use my professional camera inside the house, but just want to get this over with quickly. The light is hard to fix She, because there's a lot of white and it's snowing. She poses alone for close ups, and with younger women. All of a sudden there are two men in the laneway catcalls us both. Baddie tells them off and they get angry and start threatening us, moving towards us. Baddie hops on to the neighbours fence and I make a run for it inside my house. As I do, one of the cats tries to escape and I get so frustrated. I try so hard to close my door - it's like the wind is pushing against it and making it hard to close - before I eventually manage it using the wine rack near the door to leverage my weight and force the door closed, all while I try to keep the cats from escaping. As I close the door I think about the value of the wine and an app shows up on my screen/in my view, rating each wine and telling me which ones have made it into the awards round that year. It even asks if I would like to add a vote for those that are in the running. I think the app is cool, and remark on how many wines I have are award quality.

We're at a beautiful farm property in Gippsland. It's supposed be my parents-in-laws'. I'm there with my Mum and a few other friends and I'm nervous because it's Stage 3 lockdown and I'm worried the neighbour is going to call the police on us. Our host tells us that we're having a gathering the next night and we spend all day preparing. Oddly the house then becomes a house owned by my Aunt, she's not there, but she's in the process of building next to the home and a wall is completely missing. Beyond the wall is the construction of her new home - it's no more than a meter away. After setting up for the gathering, I go to find the shower and as I hunt for a towel (I open up a drawer and there's odd towels, pieces of cloth, and damp towels. I don't want to pick one towel that looks like a towel already hanging up on the rail - I think that towel is mt unclea and I'm repulsed in case he comes back and uses my towel accidentally. As I go towards the shower, I realise the shower has a direct view of the open wall and construction men can see in to. I'm frustrated that my Aunt could be so careless and start looking around for an option. I find another shower on the other side of the hallway that has some privacy, but it's clearly not one they often use so I need to go back to the other shower and grab shampoo and conditioner. By this time, I had already undressed and I'm wrapped in my towel as I cross the hall. I'm very self conscious that the construction men can see me. As I'm getting the products, out of the corner of my eye I see one of the other male guests start to head my way. I quickly return to the other shower and find that he's also trying to use the same shower. I manage to beat him to it and he's frustrated because he needs to shower too. I tell him I'll take two minutes, and rush through. When I turn off the shower, and as I'm about to grab my towel, he pushes aside the curtain and catches me naked. I'm really self conscious and angry. As I grab my towel, he oddly uses the opportunity to encourage me to shower with him. Although he is very handsome, and the thought flickers across my mind, I say no because I love my partner and It's something we do together. I also don't trust this man.  As I leave the shower I realise I need to use the toilet and can't find one - there's not a single toilet in the house. I'm confused and frustrated at my Aunt - wondering where on earth she pees?? The dream skips to the gathering, and we're all dressed up and ready for it. Again I'm nervous because we're not supposed to have people over and the neighbour might dob us in. All of a sudden the whole town is there - it's packed - and it turns into a house party. I start to get really worried about Coronavirus, and that I might catch it from someone who's supposed to he self isolating. I tell one of my friends this and a guest overhears. He jokes that he's supposed to be self isolating. Even though he's joking I don't believe him - this is thr first gathering in months and everyone wants to be here. There's photographers and videographers and lots of food and wine. I decide to try and escape to one of the bedrooms, even though the party is still raging on. I jump into the bed - it's just the bed and some odd, purple doors that I hate, and take down my hair - it's been in three buns and it's really wavy. I feel like myself again as I do it - I didn't like the hairstyle and I'm uncomfortable in all the make-up. My friend comes in to check in me, and I'm explaining how I feel as a male guest aslo leans against the doors to listen. The dream jumps to the wedding of the friend that was in my doorway - she's about to marry the guy that walked in on me in the shower on a landing outside, extended out of the beach- almost like a pier. Again there are so many guests here and I'm worried that people on the beach will see us and call the police. I'm also unhappy because I don't like her future husband - he only cares about himself. She's in a beautiful dress, with cut outs and tan/white elements and I'm watching the wedding from her perspective. As she walks down the isle, her husband tells the musicians to stop playing. It's awkward but she makes it to the stand okay. He then tells every guest to sign s book - they can't hug her - but it's to prove that they were witnesses. She stands alone to the side of a table as each of her friends in pairs come up to the table. She can see they're happy for her, but they can't express it by touching or hugging her. At one point another male guest stares at her hard, and she realises that he can see her nipper through one of the cut out sections of the dress - it's moved during the ceremony. She's uncomfortable. It's then time for her Grannie to come to the table. She's 96 and she's trying to get to the table but my Mum refuses to help her. Grannie is upset she's not being helped, but she's muttering in South Korean. My Mum sits there stonyfaced. It turns out that Grabboe is not her Grannie, but her good friend's mother. We call her Auntie. Auntie is the mother of the bride, but very selfish. Auntie goes into help and they walk up to the table together. I'm standing to the side, where the bride was, and I'm accompanied by the male guest from the party fhe night before - the one that listened as I worried about Coronavirus. We've become close, but we're not partners. Grannie asks Auntie for her gift. Everyone gets angry because they think Aubtie hasn't got a gift for her own family's wedding. My Mum says it's typical - every time Mum has given Auntie a necklace or piece of jewelry - a priceless piece - Auntie has sold it for her own purposes. For drinking, houses, games. Auntie says it's not true and leaves Grannie to go and get a gift. She returns with two ancestral South Korean earrings. They're bright blue circles with beads hanging from the centre circle. She puts one of my companions ear, and gives the other to me. The wedding party is speechless. My Mum moves to stand and walks out a door without a word. Upset, I follow her. As I opened the same door that she and my Auntie had used, it turns into a beautiful hallway with necklaces and jewelry hanging from hooks on the wall. The hallway is so long. I catch up to my Mother and she tells me (she is a famous jewelry maker and businesswomen) that Aubtie stole the earrings from her collection. She points to where. She then picks out two items - one is a purple pattern and the other is red. She turns them into a fabric that dresses this huge group of people, who are supposed to be her army/dolls. It's magical.

There's some link to a colleague I ran an event with today, he walks inside a big cafe/restaurant after seeing me and he's nervous about a new client meeting he has. The dream starts as a small class I'm in, and the teacher tells us that we have an assignment on memory recall. To do the assignment, we have to neet her at this Cafe. I'm the first one, and as I try to walk into the cafe there's something wrong with my feet - they're really heavy, and I'm painfully shuffling to the right where a small table has been set up with my teacher and her colleague. The table is tiny and I remember being frustrated that I couldn't walk up to the table properly and in front of them, and that when I sat down, it felt tight - we were crammed into this corner with a tiny round table and a few papers on it. My teacher's colleague asked me if I had flat feet. I was surprised he asked and said I didn't think so. And he then said he did, it's okay. They then pulled off my rainbow- I was embarrassed because my feet might have been smelly. When I got the boot back on, they were asking me these odd personal questions about my life. I felt uncomfortable and wondered if it was part of the assignment. When my classmate walks in to the cafe for his turn - he's a big, older man - I stand up, guide him, and give him my seat. He almost ignores me and starts talking about his time in Indonesia. I try to join in and share that I was also in Indonesia but he doesn't look at me or acknowledge me. I walk out of the cafe and feel aimless. I sit down outside - there are people around and different types of seats - the kind you see in parks, made of stone or wood. I walk to the edge of the courtyard and pick a chair with a back. I'm tired and I just want to sit down and scroll on my phone. I'm sitting very close to the road, which is uncomfortable but I care about sitting in that seat more. When I sit down, a girl joins me in a seat slightly to the front of me. She's very close and I get worried about Coronavirus. I drop my pen, I'm rummaging in my bag for something, and she picks it up. I let her keep it. I'm worried I'll catch Coronavirus. I get up and that's when I see my colleague from the cafe. The fream changes, and that's when the repeat part of the dream starts. I am watching a mad man wreck havoc in the same cafe. He's smashing glass, throwing it at people, hurting people. It's uncomfortable and I'm afraid but weirdly people see him as this demi-God. Like what he's doing is okay because he represents something or someone. When he leaves/I leave the cafe, his girlfriend joins the dream thread. She's the cafe owners' daughter. I don't think she should be his girlfriend, but over the course of the dream I realise why it's okay. They're both crazy. She is an artist - she sketches - and her sketches are very upsetting. The repeat part of the dream ends here. I walk into a public toilet, the stall is very long. I sit down to wee, it's hard, when the stallholder next to me starts talking to me. I'm frustrated and curious at the same time and they tell mr about themselves and a video I need to watch of them. They start playing the video and ask me, can I see it? I lie that I can. The girlfriend then walks in and I'm worried. She wants to take a picture of her boyfriend - the crazy guy from the cafe. I help her get a picture with a good background. The rest of the dream is me watching their crazy life - how they got together, how the relationship turns sour and how they hurt people, how he dies and how she died afterwards. It's painful and upsetting to watch, and I'm frustrated that their behaviour is acceptable - that people don't try to challenge them. I wake up in a final scene, after he and her had been on a carpet ride (he had died somehow after this, I think she is to blame). She is on a 4x4 on his property - it's like the desert - and starts going crazy. She's restrained by someone and I'm relieved. And then it cuts to a scene where she's helping young kids - she is in dark blue with platform heels, and after she helps this little boy she steps inside a Jean material backpack and the little boy and his Mum think it's so cool but I know it's malicious and I'm frustrated that everyone thinks she's okay.

I was catching up on work emails but I was sat outside in a garden and had to hang the emails onto a washing line.  I had family and friends over to stay and we were all sleeping on the living room floor.  Rylan Clark-Neal was in the kitchen with me and my mum and he was presenting a cooking show on TV while we were there too trying to cook a roast chicken but the chicken was taking a long time to cook and I couldn't work out why.

I was working my usual university administration job and was at work, in the main building but it looked different to how it does in real life. I was in charge of a team and we were preparing the university to get ready for when the students were due to return .  this included clearing up old and dead leaves and cleaning and tidying the spaces. I was demonstrating to my team how to run reports on a system and cleaning the toilets!

I was with my husband Mike and a couple of friends that we had seen the day before.  we were watching cartoons on television and pausing or fast forwarding the cartoons when we went off to do house chores such as tidying and cleaning up after dinner and putting on he dishwasher.  As a group we then went into London but it was suddenly like we were in the victorian era as there were people dressed up underground and on the tube, dressed in Victorian-era clothing.  There were pickpockets and children about in the underground like in the film Oliver.  Then we were getting ready to go to another friend's wedding but we were all running late so were going to miss the wedding.  We tried to get ready quickly but we turned up at the wedding and it had already finished so we had to go back home again.

I was in a house with lots of dogs of all sizes - maybe a dog adoption centre? I was trying to look after some of them but it was hard to do so as they were crawling around everywhere and I'm not overly confident with dogs anyway.  In another part of this house my friend Clare was in it and was trying to sleep but she couldn't because a dog kept crawling into the bed and the room only had really thin curtains so she said she kept getting woken up early by the sun rising.  I felt a bit guilty about this for some reason as I couldn't really help; perhaps it was suddenly my house?

I was trying to work out how to use Zoom to teach people about Covid and social distancing.  I was also moving home so was tidying up my basement so was trying to make it Covid safe and clean. I was due to be working but I went in to the office and not just working from home and using Zoom but I ended up speaking to an older couple about mental health nursing programme so I had to miss an appointment/meeting.  The old man thanked me for my help and guidance but shook my hand and I remember feeling uncomfortable about this and immediately having to find some hand sanitiser.

I was at work and remember having to communicate with my colleagues and team through Zoom and Microsoft Teams to sort out a problem that had come up.  I think it was linked to another part of my dream where I was trying to make some brownies but I couldn't get hold of all the ingredients.  I was also trying to babysit a 1 year old baby boy but he was very advanced for his age and had the mentality and ability of a 5 year old so he kept walking around and getting lost so I had to keep looking for him and putting him back in his cot.

I was with my husband and some friends/colleagues and we were walking around  the local streets and commented on the state of the gardens we walked past.  It seemed they all looked neglected as there was a lockdown so we decided to set about creating a plan to clear them up. We scooped up fallen dead leave and noted that we needed to clear up the dead leaves from the plants and bushes that were hanging over onto the pathway from the gardens. We went about dead heading the roses and flowers as well.

I was logging my dreams in an online system but it was a system similar to a database I use at work.  I was sat doing this task on a sofa in a cozy lounge area of a grand stately home.  However, the "dream" I was logging were actually activities that are closely associated to my real-life university admin job and I was logging students' university progress with their course and placements, and not my own dreams.  Meanwhile, while I was on the sofa I was watching a Sunday church service which was being held in the garden of this property by a black male reverend who was holding a microphone that looked like a harmonica, and he was joined by the Chinese president. At the end of their service they were joined by Boris Johnson who went on to sing the British National Anthem in a comedic falsetto voice which I remember thinking was funny and cringey but also I remember feeling embarrassed for him.  I was joined inside by my chinese male neighbour and a female friend and we were commenting on Boris' singing

At my parents house that I lived in as a child.  I saw a man, who looked like British actor Steven Merchant appear at the back of the house and walk across the garden and jumped over the fence separating their garden from the adjoining neighbours' garden. This wasn't the first time I had seen him do this so I went out and caught him mid-hop over the fence, to ask him why he was doing this.  I was polite but also a little sarcastic in my questioning and direct as I felt it was wrong for him to go across the lawn and hop over.    He said he thought it was a "known cut through" but I explained it is clearly a private property which limited access to the public as he would have had to break into my parents garden and driveway, through locked gates, to be able to get into the garden!  He did apologise but I remember feeling a slight sense of pride that I'd rumbled him and stopped it happening!

Lin came to me and Mike to ask us for our dessert options.  She said there was 1 slice of apple pie, a whole cake (jam sponge cake with marbled icing) which is Mike's favourite, or a bag of peanut M&Ms.  I didn't particularly fancy any of them but I chose to eat the M&Ms.  My husband smashed his whole face into the cake to eat it from the centre!  IT ruined the cake but me and Lin found it very funny!

I was trapped inside a dome around a world, a bit like in the Hunger Games films and The Truman Show.  Inside this dome was a world of forests and rivers.  I was on a rollercoaster which travelled around this dome and up high so we could have full view.  It seemed I was one of the people in charge of this dome world and was being driven round the track on the rollercoaster with some of managerial colleagues and then the driver was there.  We had reports that there was a crazy lady/monster inside the dome but we'd lost sight of her and didn't know where she was or whether she was going to attack us.  I was in charge so had to make the decision for everyone on what to do and how to handle it but I didn't know what the best thing might be.  I had my head in my hands looking downwards as the driver sped up and we were travelling round and round on the rollercoaster so everything was swimming and blurring past my eyes while I tried to focus on the decision to make.  I woke up at this point and remember not liking it and visualising the spinning blurring world

I was at a large open field area with some students from the university I work at. There were barns in this field and we entered one of them to go and get our haircut.  I found an ex-colleague/manager in the barn and she was running a mini pop-up cafe in the barn-cum-hairdressers.  My colleague was moaning about the struggle of finding a job due to Covid-19 especially when she has children. We went outside the barn, my hair was now shorter; and sat down to watch a cricket match that was being played outside in the field. My dad was playing in the match and some cricket balls were hit in my direction so I managed to catch them.  My dad signalled for me to throw them back to him but when I threw one of them it fell very short so he shouted out to say I should have rolled the ball to him like he taught me to do when we were playing cricket when I was younger.  So I did. I then heard some chicken and rooster noises and moaned to the students I was with that these are like the noises my husband and I wake up to every morning at home as our neighbour has chickens.

I was visiting a house with some other people and someone was trying to sell some artwork painting they had done.  having to remember to maintain social distance from everyone that was there. The artist was a youngish male student.  someone commented on being a bit ill; that they had a runny nose.  Someone was concerned that this person might have Covid-19 so wanted to stay away from them but a doctor appeared and asked the ill person about their symptoms as he specifically said that Covid-19 is a respiratory disease so it was a sore throat and cough that was the key to have.

I was on a work outing with some colleagues but also some of my school friends so it was a mixed gang of people.  We were in an old warehouse building waiting for my friend Anna to perform for us.  She is a singer and ad her guitar with her.  She gave it to me to try and play but I realised I was holding it upside down and couldn't play it!  ME and a colleague Amie were in the warehouse to try and find a vaccination for TB and to get given this before returning to work as we'd be in an office and seeing students regularly so need to protect ourselves!  The vaccination was expensive so Amie had it but I didn't, I couldn't afford it.  My mum was nagging me to get it though so I was speaking to a science colleague to see if they knew where else I could get it.  The warehouse was pretty abandoned and dirty.  We tried to find the toilets and they were old, green tiled, dirty and full of water which was very unpleasant.  There was a seating booth in the warehouse where we were all sat but it was shaped like an old car, so there were padded car seats as the seats and the table was the car axis and bonnet.   We were eating sweets.

I was on holiday and on a boat cruise with my parents-in-law and sister-in-law. I hadn't prepared very well and hadn't packed very much so had only one outfit with me which frustrated me as I'd run out of time to pack properly. I was in a large open ballroom hall space on the ship dancing to Be Our Guest, the song from Beauty and the beast. My mother-in-law was singing and my sister-in-law was dancing with me and we were hopping and skipping and leaping around the room. I was in my work office clothes so in a tightish skirt which meant I couldn't leap as high as I wanted which was annoying and restrictive. Along with the frustrations of not packing clothes to take it meant I wasn't prepared for any changes in weather if the boat got wet or cold. I was panicking that if there was a fire drill in the night then I would likely be wearing underwear as I didn't have pyjamas with me and I would have to go outside in my underwear or naked!

I was holding 1:1 meetings at work with my direct reports and I was trying to communicate with a new member of my team who looked like Jo Gosling but I couldn't get through to her as she was the other side of a field of large thick dry grasses covered in thick crunchy peanut butter.  I was trying to wade through these thick peanut butter grasses and tried to bounce over as well as if it was a trampoline but it was a struggle.  Another colleague was trying to meet with me too and this was less distance to travel but she was behind a fence and again, although I knew it was close, I couldn't get over the fence because it kept getting taller, the more I tried to climb and the peanut butter go thicker in the grasses and up the fence when i tried to get across.  I tried to play a game with these colleagues, like tennis, hitting items over the fence to them.  Outside the world was a little post-apocalyptic as it was fairly empty, barren and run down.  Lots of rubble in the streets.  While I Was walking in the streets I saw a large man running after another, smaller guy so I chose to keep out of the way down a different street so I didn't get caught up in the chase.  I kept safe in the toilet of a nearby building and saw the larger guy walk past looking for the smaller one (his brother) and the larger guy was  holding a large machine gun.  deciding it was best to stay hidden as I was afraid I'd get attacked by being in the wrong place at the wrong time.

I was having to isolate as per new guidance from the government.  However it as very confusing as some people had to isolate when others didn't.  I remember telling someone off for not isolating at home but this person responded by reeling off a list of reasons why they shouldn't have to but these reasons were very odd and seemed trivial.  For example, because they owned pets and because they had crunchy leaves in their garden!  A friend was being punished by some godlike being and was forced to go an clean underground tunnels/poles/shafts and they had to dress up like a WW2 soldier  to do this, wearing a gas mask and full PPE as well.  But I remember knowing in my dream that this was all due to Covid-19 and in an attempt to "clear out the world."

I had a new job and as celebrating with new colleagues by eating cake.  In my new job I was having to look through how Health and Safety and risk assessment documents were working and needing updating due to Covid-19.  I met the CEO of this company but it turns out it was a very sakes orientated job in a pyramid-scheme style business which I didn't like.  I really didn't want the job but because they'd already given me some of the "secret files" I couldn't turn it down or quit!  While with the colleagues and CEO I was getting chased by youtube stars who wanted an online fight or battle because they thought I was someone else.  I remember panicking and trying to get away and explain it wasn't me involved in the "diss battle" so they should stop hounding me.  I felt very threatened though.  Also in the job I had to look at booking a skiing trip and I bought a skiing truck to take as well as a fridge to go on the skiing trip!

I was playing card games with some comedians and celebrities in a hut/bunker somewhere.  These included Eamonn Holmes and Jason Manford. There were wildfires reported in the forest and camp we had been near so we were all running away from these to try and collect our belongings and move to safety before the fires caught up however I couldn't remember the route to our campsite and the people in my group were following me so I got us lost.  I was panicking and rushing around and felt guilty for getting the others lost.  In the end we found the safe cabin where were all holed up playing cards and waiting until the fires cleared.  In this cabin some of my friends were practising dances for a show that was coming up so they were performing for us all.

I saw my friends Tim and Ella and I went out for dinner in London with them, where they live.  It was a pizza restaurant but it seemed quite normal.  It wasn't busy but there wasn't too much distancing between people.  they then came back to my house but house was suddenly very large and rundown and we were redoing the garden.  They were staying in a spare bedroom which happened to be underground and in a gross, wet abandoned room accessed from our garden.  I felt embarrassed asking them to stay there as it was so uninhabitable.  They helped us with redoing/renovating our garden.  We were trying to stop a waterfall that was running from the top of our garden and to dredge it out by putting in a new drainage system.

I was at my mum and dad's house.  They had new neighbours and I noticed that the new neighbours had 2 cars parked outside on the road which meant they were parked outside my parents house as there isn't much space.  For some reason it really annoyed me as they'd been doing this for ages so I went outside to ask them to move but they weren't very happy as they said there was no space for all their cars so what else could they do.  I got quite angry that they didn't seem to care or apologise that they'd done anything wrong and they responded quite angrily which in turn made me very angry and I remember raising my voice!

In a large old castle, thick stone walls. With a lot of people I seemed to know who were in separate groups. Waiting for someone? My father was there briefly. Then seemed to be in France. Looking for somewhere for the large group to stay. Looking down from above, eventually became a map. Went inside a large holiday home. Trying to find out the cost for one night. Then seemed to be in Brighton. looking across at cliffs. Large display done in fireworks - fireworks spell out instruction about social distancing.
I was in some sort of tourist attraction with a lot of people from my choir, including V We were all happy and joking together.

In France, travelling, looking for somewhere to stay. I had to get back to the UK because I was due to start at university in Manchester. Trying to pack what I needed to take with me - a strange random selection of objects. I was in a place I don't recognise. I was in a rush - I had to catch a morning train because I had something I had to do when I got there in the afternoon

A dark green spray bottle - I was maybe on a plane but not sure - I had to spray everything around me with the bottle. This image kept recurring over and over. Then in a town, terraced houses, with some people from my choir A young man was there - son of K who I didn't know existed. Tall with dark hair, nice face, in his 20s. He had built a massive timber structure - we were in some sort of hall - it was to be used as a stage. It had three sides, hinged to open out like a stage. I told him it was amazing. He asked if I knew the two people who K had always fancied - he pointed to two people - E & me. He lay down and I lay beside him. He had a small polythene bag with something like glass in it - I asked what it was - he said crystal meth. I felt sad and motherly towards him.

In a house or a very old castle. looking after a baby girl, not mine but in some way close to me, about 8 mths old. A happy smiling baby. We explored the building. Had tea and cake in a cafe, we were now in a high street somewhere, an old town. I somehow knew that my old friend N was missing and that she had become a fish. A large group of volunteers were out searching a river for her, diving in with their clothes on. Then I was back in the old house/castle. I realised my friend N the fish was stuck inside an old hollow door. We broke the door down and prised the two sides apart. We found her inside, she was still a fish and had a little newborn baby fish with her.

I was staying in a weatherboard shack on stilts, like an old Queenslander. I was housesharing with friends from uni I think. We were playing a sort of hide and seek game. Everyone went into different rooms and closed their eyes and counted to 100, while one person hid multiple stacks of cash around the house.  Someone else had hidden the cash and I was searching through the linen cupboard and laundry. I found four wads of cash in the cupboard and I had to go write it down on in a logbook.  Suddenly more people were involved in the game and they were hiding the cash in a big high school campus instead of just the house. Other people were finding it instead of my friends and I. I overheard someone saying he hid some in the Year 12 study hall So I ran up there and looked through all papers on the tables. My sister was there studying maths and she said people had already looked through everything and I was too late. I suddenly had this realisation that I was really really behind on my maths work, and I should stay and study. But I was so behind I didn’t know where to start. So I decided to ignore that and keep playing the game.  Then I was back at the shack and being chased by a bad man. My friend and I made a distraction and snuck away out the back door. We ran around the patio to the front, and he was at the bottom of the steps waiting. So we ran back and inside again, and there was a lady calling us to come, saying it was ok. We got closer and it was the man with a wig And lipstick on.

I was away with friends in Queensland for a week and I had a really good time. Then I was going back to my family home and was meant to have the house to myself for a night or 2 because my family was all away together in Queensland also. I was really happy to have the house to myself and I had plans for getting take away dinner and relaxing. I spent a while trying to get to the house and first I parked the car in a car park quite a while away, then remembered that no other cars were at home so I could park closer. Then I parked down the street from the house, then remembered Again that no cars were in the driveway so I could park at the house. So I drove again and parked at the house.  When I got there my sister was out the front and I asked her why. Then I saw my cousin and my mum too. I asked my sister again why were they all here. I was annoyed. She was pretty cryptic in her response and didn’t want to say much but it was something about An issue With my other sister’s partner. I wasn’t sure if her partner’s mum had died or her partner’s neighbour’s dog had died. I was frustrated because it sounded like a made up reason for the whole family to end the holiday early.  Then I went inside And my other sister was vacuuming and cleaning. She vacuumed my room but missed most of the dirt so I pointed out a spot for her to go over. I could hear my grandma taking to mum down the hall.

At first I was sending a text message to my ex boyfriend Denis. I was writing something silly and wasn’t planning to send it, but I accidentally did. I tried to recall the message and it didn’t work, and I accidentally deleted his phone number. So I sent him a message on Messenger saying ‘I know this sounds like a lie, but I didn’t mean to send that message’.  Then he rang and we had a long chat while I wandered around a shopping centre. There were lots of long comfortable pauses. All I remember about the conversation is I tried to explain the accidental message, and he told me he was in Korea at the moment.  Then I had a few missed calls from my friend Georgia. I called her back and she asked me could I pick up a sandwich for her tomorrow from the shop near my house and bring it for her lunch. We were going to uni together the next day so I said yes. I remembered I had already organised to get a sandwich for someone else too so I told Georgia it was no trouble as I would already be at the shop. We hung up and I thought I will have to ask Georgia to text me her order as I had already forgotten the type of sandwich she asked for.  Then I went to the supermarket in the shopping centre and talked to.  He was having trouble balancing the tills because the coin counter didn’t recognise Some of the coins. He said he was sick of it and it had to change. I told him the staff all agreed. I said ‘I have already talked to Keith about it but he doesn’t listen to us. Why don’t you talk to him about it?’  He said ok he would.  Then my grandma approached and I had a quick chat to her. I organised to meet her for lunch.  Then I was on the phone to my dad.  We had a really pleasant conversation. He was studying something at uni. He was travelling to lots of different places for uni and work. I was wandering around as I talked on the phone, and eventually I was standing in front of him. He was lying upside down while we finished the chat. I said ‘ok bye dad’ and he got up for a hug. He said ‘bye mum’ and I thought oh I must have told him I am pregnant so I said ‘not mum yet’.  I said I had to go have lunch with grandma. He asked do I always have lunch with grandma at the shopping centre and I said ‘no she just happens to be here today’.  At some point I also spoke to someone else about growing vegetables. He said we needed a central location to grow them. I said I have an empty vege patch in my front yard with no veges and he could grow them there and collect them whenever he wants to.

I was working at a store and I collected some things from the discount section. I found the nicest things I could for a girl and for a boy. It was a pencil case each and a couple of other things. I took them to the public bathroom and displayed them on the bench. The manager saw and was annoyed and asked ‘who has taken things form the store and put them in the bathroom’ and I explained that last time I did it they sold really well. I pointed to an empty bench In the bathroom and said ‘see, they’re all gone’ Then my manager was really happy and congratulated me.   I was on a train and had to change to another service, but there were trains going all over the place and not really stopping. To get on the one I needed I had to go through a small window as the train was moving, just when it passed by the train I needed, and into the window of the other train. As I did it I went back in time to a train from years ago, then back into another future train, to get on the one I needed. I was nervous to do it and it felt a bit weird.

I was working from some sort of holiday park where I was staying in a caravan. Some friends from work were staying there too.  I think I was trying to finish things up before going on leave so I was working really hard. I started work before 8am and got heaps of stuff done. I told my boss where I was up to and she didn’t pay any attention. I asked her if she still wanted my team to do an interview with (a lady).  She said she had already got someone else to organise that and it was happening this morning.  I was really annoyed that she got someone else to do it because I felt undermined and I would have done it given a bit more time.  I went to my friends in the caravan and told them about it and why I was annoyed, and they agreed.  Then We started talking about my friend Georgia’s birthday present. We were taking her to look at caravans of her own. Tash had organised to go look at that that afternoon after work. Georgia was really excited. I was too and I was really keen to go. Then I realised I would have to work late to finish everything so I probably wouldn’t be able to, and I was disappointed.  Later I was packing all my things To leave and checking I hadn’t left anything in the caravan. I think I was doing it in secret without my boss knowing. My boss brought me a glass of water with two aspirins in it and told me to have that because I have a migraine. I told her I don’t have a migraine, that’s not why I am upset. I refused to say any more and she walked away.

I was dating my high school boyfriend again. His name is Brad. We were hanging out together in his room in a massive house. I left The room to get ready to go out for the day, my mum was there as I was getting ready. I was in a Big laundry in the same house brushing my teeth and I needed to leave soon. I decided to go and say goodbye to Brad before I left.  I went to his room and he was curled up in bed still. There was furniture in the way between the door and his bed, like he had blocked himself in. I realised he was depressed, and that I had been noticing this for some time. I went over and hugged him and asked what is going on with him, he seems sad. He started to cry. He said didn’t know what to do with himself. We were having this conversation via Zoom as well as having it face to face. Suddenly another voice joined in from Zoom and asked Hey Brad what’s going on? I saw it was a male friend of his, and passed him the phone. Brad became animated and had a good chat with his friend. I was really happy that the call Has perked him up. I hadn’t met that friend before and I said he seemed nice.  He arranged to go to his friend’s house and I was happy he had plans for the day.  I have him a hug and said have fun at (male friend) house and he said ‘oh no I am going to see (female friend)’. He explained that she is his best friend and when he is depressed she is the only one who can cheer him up. I was confused and a bit jealous And sad that she could cheer him up but I could not. But I wanted to be supportive and I understood how important it was that he do whatever he needed to do to feel better. Brad and I dancing around the foyer of this big house and leaning against a marble column to kiss.

I had a cyst/ pimple on my tongue. I squeezed it and lots of puss came out. It started to make a crater/ hole in my tongue. A little branch appeared in the hole with little dead brown leaves. I was really scared and panicking. I kept squeezing it to try to make it come out. My mum and her partner got a new house and it was a massive mansion. I kept getting lost in there and couldn’t find the front door or the room I was looking for. It had a huge shed out the back too. The house was brand new and perfectly clean.  Mum was out so I invited friends over. One of them was upset so I was making her a cup of tea and some toast. Then someone said ‘oh quick we should finish the half finished drinks’ so we all ran down a hallway to a linen cupboard that had heaps of glasses Half filled with tequila and bottles of tequila All stacked really clumsily. Someone else had left them there and it was a game for us to finish them. I handed them all out to people and the pile in the cupboard was spilling and breaking everywhere. Suddenly we were all drunk and laughing and having fun but spilling things everywhere and making a huge mess. People were spilling things all over the floor in mums room and the kitchen.  I had fun while we were partying but suddenly I was sober again and I realised we were wrecking the place and I felt really guilty and panicked. I told everyone we had to clean up the mess and they didn’t care about it at all, they didn’t want to help. They just said they were leaving. I was really disappointed my friends would do that. So I just started cleaning myself. Then one of my friends talked the others into helping and grudgingly they did. It felt like our progress was so slow and I was still panicking. I went out to the shed to get the vacuum and one friend was still really drunk. He ran into the shed singing that he felt sick And he did diarrhoea All over the vacuum. I was so annoyed at him and I couldn’t use the vacuum.  Back inside I told his wife to Take him home and she was really annoyed at him too. I saw them out the front leaving and they were taking the dirty vacuum Home with Them to clean.  My other friend returned mum’s room to the state it was before we spilled on the carpet and actually mum had stuff all over the floor so you couldn’t see the spills anyway. I would have preferred to clean up the spills but I didn’t think mum would notice because there was so much Stuff on the floor Anyway.  All my friends said the cleaning was done and they had to go and all started leaving. I looked around and it was still so dirty and messy. I was upset with them. They left and I needed some cloths to clean up a mess in the carpet. The house was so big I couldn’t find the laundry to find cleaning cloths. Finally I found it and finished the cleaning. Then I got a text message and it was to say my pizza delivery was on its way. I was confused because I didn’t order pizza. I got a voice message from my friend Justin saying he ordered me pizza as an apology for not helping clean.

I was with a group of people and we were trying to escape from a group of bad people. We kept going back in time slightly and had the chance to try again. We were in this messy little weatherboard house at the end of a really long driveway in the country. We new the bad people were going to come to the door and it would be too late. We had a whiteboard and we wrote down the instructions or what to do so everyone would understand and remember. Before the bad people knocked at the door, we had to rush and pack bags, and I think get weapons.  When they arrived at the door there was a specific order of things we had to do to stop time or something and escape. We had to make it to the rest of our group who were somewhere else.  At one point I ended Up with the bad lady who was eccentric, like a comical evil character. She wanted a white dinner setting. I was her prisoner and as I was with her I was thinking about how to escape. We walked past a Kmart and she wanted to go in there to look for the dinner setting. The staff said there were none left, but she saw one set displayed on a table. It was the last set. She looked at it and said she loved it. It had text on Each plate that was something about ‘tell the kids to Be quite while I eat’. The staff asked her if she had kids, and she got angry because she realised she shouldn’t get that set because she didn’t have kids.  She took me back to the house and I tried to think about how I would escape. Suddenly she was in the house with other bad guys holding my group hostage, and I was outside looking in the window trying to think of a plan to rescue them. Then I was in an adjoining bedroom to where they were being held. I hid under the doona and created some sort of bomb with a microphone attached that would freeze time so I could get them out. I think I was going to blow up the whole place, then rush back and reset the timeline and come and prepare them before the bad lady arrived. So I set the bomb off, then went through the front door back to the other location but something had gone wrong with the bomb and I was in a waste land on my own. I realised I had messed something up.  There was another part where I was at the end of the long driveway to the house where my group was, trying to sneak in. A security guard saw me but didn’t recognise me. He asked what I was doing there and I looked around for an excuse. I saw there was a giant Rubber hard boiled egg, cut in half lying on its side. So like looking at the yolk and white of a person sized rubber hard boiled egg. I told the security guard I wanted to see the egg and he said ‘oh there is one here, you can touch it’ so I pretended to be interested in this giant egg.

There were three short clips of the dream. In the first, I had just had a bath and the water was draining away. The water contained a lot of soil and vegetation and I watched it go down the plughole wondering how all that stuff had come from my body and hair. The second was I was walking through a house with my husband. It felt like it was my parents house but it didn't look like it. There were a lot of nude people lounging around on bean bags listening to low, chilled out music. My brother was one of them. They looked like they might be on drugs and having sex. I knew my husband was thinking he never wanted to come back to the house. The third was my mother was in bed and talking about doing an online course which meant that no one except her could access the internet for months. Then she was also in the nude reaching up for something on top of a cupboard.

We were in a park somewhere with our regular fitness instructor. There were about 20 of us, I didn't recognise anyone except our instructor. One person next to me kept going out of sequence in the exercise routines. At one point instead of joining everyone in a line, he ran towards a wooded area. At one point, I was running alongside our instructor, I felt he wanted me to keep up with him as he increased his speed. I wanted to show him how fit I was and suddenly I felt a type of electricity through my body that allowed me to run faster. I felt fantastic in this moment.

I was writing cards and putting them in brightly coloured envelopes. I had written a lot of cards and was worried that they might not be delivered in time. My husband wrote one word "INTELLECTUALS" in beautiful capital script on an envelope. I can picture the writing now, it stretched from one side of the envelope to the other. It was a thank you card for the teachers of a remedial class in a school unknown to us. Next, I was walking barefoot in a park. It was covered in round gravel. I picked up a piece of gravel and ate it. It was cereal, I think called "oaties", that we used to have as children. The park was full of people sitting around in the sun, on their lunch break. I went to get an ice cream. The person selling ice cream was loading too many scoops onto the cone, and some scoops were falling off. The ice cream was covered in a fine grey hair-like filament mould. I walked around the park trying to find somewhere to sit. The people were all getting up now and going back to work.

I was at a big dinner occasion, perhaps a conference dinner. I was wearing a bright pink jacket. My old boss was opposite me. Another older man was talking about an old model of the tongue. I knew all the details, the name of the researcher and author "Thesbo". He or she had previously constructed a mechanical model of the tongue and a series of algorithms to make it move in a realistic way. I was talking about these details to everyone at the table. Then my boss cut in and said Thesbo had died in 1996. From that moment, I felt everyone attributed all the details that I had given about Thesbo to my boss. I felt cross and humiliated. Then another senior person stood up and thanked me as a "business associate". In turned to my friend and colleague Janet Fletcher who was sitting next to me and said "I'm an academic for fuck's sake!".

I was looking in the boot of a car, which was in the golf course car park. There was a man in the boot. I think he was dead. Then I was looking at some chickens that were roosting on a wooden box. I was standing in the box, which was filthy. In it were a couple of very thick paper bags. I could see there was something moving inside one of the bags. I opened it and I could see the rubbish moving around, so there was definitely something alive in the bag, and then a black animal, like a big rat or cat, jumped out.

I was on a cruise ship, or a ferry, and at first it was leaving and I had a very vivid image of how it was moving and almost spinning around. Then it was back on the quayside and I left it and went to an art exhibition, which had an incredible spectacular display of tall paintings. I was really enjoying the exhibition. But suddenly I realised that the ship was leaving and looking at my watch I would miss it. I started to run thinking it was possible to catch it, but knew it had gone without me. I could picture it in my mind sailing off out of the harbour. I tried to figure out how I could get back onto the ship. I thought about getting a flight to the next destination port, but then realised I had nothing with me, and no passport. I was so upset with myself for being so stupid. I could think of no way to get to the ship.

I was watering plants that were growing on the outside of a large, old square tower. The brick was a lovely pale ochre colour and the weather was warm. The plants were beautiful, great ferns and plants with huge leaves. They seemed to be growing out of the tower. I was then at the bottom of the tower and I looked up to the top of the tower. There was a man at the top calling down to me. I couldn't understand what he was saying, so asked him twice to repeat it. Then he was sitting next to me at the bottom of the tower. We were both sitting on a wall and I was looking at him. I didn't know him. He was young, he looked arabian or egyptian. He was trying to speak, but he could not get the words out. It was like he had a really bad stammer, blocking the words. I knew though that he was trying to express his love for me. I felt overwhelming compassion for him.

The whole dream took place in a hotel room. I was on my own, dressed and frantically packing my bag. It was morning and I was due to catch a long haul flight which left at 10.00. It was a London hotel, close to the airport, but I knew I had to get a train to the airport. I was travelling with my boss so it was a work trip, but he had the tickets and I was due to meet him in the the hotel lobby or at the airport. I was struggling to pack my bags, I seemed to have a lot to pack. The bed was piled high with duvets and cushions. I kept looking at my watch, it was 9.15. I felt incredibly anxious, I couldn't find my passport. I may still have time to get the flight, but I could get everything in the bag.

I was walking down a very steep scree slope. It was so steep, I turned back. At the top I had a camper van, or caravan, and I lay down on a bed to rest. Suddenly there was a man, unknown to me, and he was injecting me with a substance into my thigh. He was blowing on my skin. It was frightening, and I was thinking "Why am I being sedated?" "Was I going to be raped?", or something else?

I dreamt about The Block last night. It was exactly like I was just watching an episode. But I didn't feel like I was sitting in my own living room or in front of a TV. It was like I was there, but still looking through a camera. The people in the show didn't know I was watching. They were the same contestants who are currently on the show, and the scenes were exactly like they would be on the show. There was nothing out of the ordinary. They were up to kitchen week, which they aren't in the actual show right now. One of the couples was standing at their island bench and looking at plans or something laid out over it. The rest of the kitchen was in the background. It was the typical sort of kitchen you see on the show. Lots of dark overhead cabinets, stone benchtops. integrated appliances.There were a few different scenes that sort of flashed around, as it would if you were watching the show.
sitting at my computer and working on the stuff that I was actually working on. I was creating tables and adding colours to flag the status of different actions.

I was downstairs in my own actual house in the kitchen with my brother-in-law.  He was cooking something, or cleaning, I wasn't sure which. He was dressed as normal and looked a bit younger and with a beard. He was standing in front of the sink, or bench and was either washing dishes or preparing food and had a tea towel slung over the shoulder facing me. He was side on to where I entered the kitchen.  I knew I had come downstairs to ask him something but it wasn't anything urgent, more like I was curious about something, or just wanted to have a chat.  It all felt very normal and domestic.  Nothing struck me as unusual about him being there, I asked him a question about something and he turned to me to respond.

I was dreaming about cars, and helping someone to buy one. It was a guy who used to work with us last year but who suddenly left at Christmas. I was asking him how much he wanted to spend, and when he said $6000, I was telling him that he could get something way better than what he'd been thinking of getting. It's all a bit foggy now but I remember something about a Holden Commodore, and that he would have to get a pretty old one for that much, and that he should look at something newer, and smaller. We were sitting at what looked like an office or boardroom table. With a plain white laminate top. There were other people sitting around it too. It was rectangular. Marc and I were on one of the long edges with a big glass window at our backs. It was like I was sitting opposite, looking at the 2 of us talking. There was someone beside me but I wasn't paying attention to them. It seemed like maybe we were all waiting for a meeting to start and people were slowly filtering in and taking seats around the table.

I was in public. It seemed like a shopping centre but there weren't many people around. I was in a bed or on a couch and was covered by a sheet or blanket so no-one could see what I was doing. I had my hand down my pants and was otherwise fully dressed. I was trying to hurry though in case someone noticed but then I realised that because I was hurrying, the covering over me was jiggling, so I thought I better slow down or stop, as that would potentially draw attention. I was on the edge of coming when my 14 year old son suddenly appeared close by and walked over to me, so I had to quickly stop and pretend nothing was going on.  I talked to him for a bit.  He didn't seem suspicious that I was lying under a covering but I uncovered myself and sat up anyway. We spoke for a bit and then he walked off.  I was thinking about where else I could go to finish and then found myself in a car, in a car park, and thought to myself that I could probably do it there.  It was a typical concrete, multilevel car park, but I was parked on the ground floor.  There weren't many other cars parked near me, and there weren't any people walking around although it was daylight and I somehow knew that the shops were open. So I stuck my hand down my pants and took up from where I had left off.  This time I was wetter and was really on the verge of coming. I fantasized about getting someone to perform oral sex on me while I'm being penetrated. I continued to masturbate in my dream while knowing that it was a dream. I consciously moved my dream hand and how I was positioned in the seat of the car to try to get it to happen, but it didn't.

I was in a meeting at work.  There were several people sitting around a table. I recognised several of them.  I could tell that they all knew each other better than I did, they were a group who had been meeting regularly with each other.
