I knew that they were a group that had formed in response to the Coronavirus. I had been invited because I was about to join the group. I was already sitting at the table. It was quite a large group, so quite a large oval table.  It seemed to be an internal room.  It was pretty similar to many of the meeting rooms I've been in before.  There was a large TV screen at one end for using for presentations or video conferencing, but it was off, so just black.  Everything else was just as it would normally be in a meeting.  People were dressed for work.  The meeting proceeded as most meetings do.  I listened to others speak, and asked questions a couple of times. I could tell the meeting was about to finish, and I knew there was something I wanted to clarify before it did, so I asked a question of the group about my own position. I was expecting to join them in a couple of weeks and said I was looking forward to it, but then the person obviously in charge of the meeting/a senior executive said that actually, they wanted me to start straight away.  On hearing this I started to feel anxious about what my current manager would say, and how would I manage all the work that I had planned to finish in the next 2 weeks?  So then the next thing I knew I was in another meeting, this time I knew it was about me, and my position, and how soon I would need to start. I was already sitting at the table again and then someone I used to work with walked in and was walking behind my seat and I turned to say hello. I said how it had been ages since I'd seen him. For some reason there was then this awkward moment when I thought he was leaning down to give me a kiss on the cheek, so I started to reach up to do the same to him, but then I had a moment of concern that we were going to touch each other, because I knew that there was still an issue with Coronavirus and that we should be physically distancing, which then made me think about the fact that we were having a meeting in the first place in person, and that we were all putting ourselves at risk even being in the same room with one another. At the same time I was thinking we shouldn't be touching, I was also realising that he wasn't in fact about to kiss me on the cheek, he was just leaning a bit closer to say something, so then I was embarrassed that I'd misread his intentions, but at the same time relieved that we weren't going to touch. I was just about to say something to everyone about how we shouldn't be meeting in person.

I was eating whitebait.  Little tiny fish that had been dipped in flour and then deep fried.  I was at some sort of function, a dinner party or something where we were sitting at tables and eating.  lots of people sitting around drinking and talking.  It seemed like I was the only one eating the fish.  There was a basket or bowl of them on the table.  I took one, and it felt a little limp - not crispy like something deep fried should be, like it had got a bit of steam on it or something.  I put it in m mouth and realised the head was still on it, so I tried to bite just the head off and leave the rest in my mouth.  But it was too chewy and I couldn't get the head to separate from the body, and I was becoming self-conscious that the people near me would notice that I was doing something gross with my mouth as I had my fingers  sort of half in my mouth trying to pull the head out.  I gave up, thinking, well it's only tiny, I'll just swallow it, and I did.  Then I took a second fish.  It was only a couple of centimetres long, and very thin. This one felt crispier and I braced myself for what it would feel like to bite down on it, half expecting it to not be very nice. I crunched down on the head quite deliberately this time and was relieved that nothing gooey came out of it.  It was just like a crispy piece of prawn shell and was quite tasty with the flavour of the oil and fried flour coating it. I chewed up the rest of the fish and swallowed it.  I was thinking it wasn't bad after all and was almost going to reach for another one.

I had another ocean dream, which are dreams I've been having since I was a kid. but rather than being in the ocean myself it was like I was watching a documentary or video. I was looking down at a spit of yellowy/white sand. It looked like a beach at first, with waves breaking on one side. The sky was blue, it was clear, and not windy. It felt quite pleasant and I was thinking it might be nice to go for a swim in the water. But then I noticed that there was water also on the other side of the beach, so it was a narrow spit of sand. As the 2 lots of water started to mix with each other, the waves getting bigger and swirling around from the 2 different directions, I found myself actually in the water, but I wasn't getting wet. The waves were white and frothy and it all still seemed like I was watching a moving rather than being there myself. After initially feeling anxious that I was going to have to struggle to swim against the multiple currents and stop myself from getting swamped by the waves, I realised that I was actually just floating in the water. The waves were still moving around me, but I was protected from the currents somehow. Just as I was not getting wet, I was also not feeling cold like I thought I should. And I started trying to work out what was stopping me from actually being in the water - I wasn't in a vehicle, I wasn't in a bubble or force shield, I was just separate from the water somehow. I was almost starting to enjoy it, the sun was shining, the water was a lovely blue/green, but tinged with a concern that maybe I was out in the middle of the ocean, and if I was, then how would I get back to shore? Then I noticed a child, a young girl with long blonde hair was also in the water with me. she was wearing like an old fashioned nightdress of white cotton that was swirling around her like she was in the water, but she didn't look wet either. I easily floated over to her and we both reached out our hands to one another. We both floated up above the water and I started explaining to her how the waves had come in and covered the spit of sand that had been there, and how I would normally be frightened by waves coming from 2 different directions and that I often have dreams about that exact thing happening (at the same time I mentioned this to the girl my dream self actually had flashbacks to past dreams I have had about waves coming from unexpected directions and being caught between 2 bodies of water) but that for some reason this time was different and I wasn't scared. The girl didn't say anything but just held on to my hand and I continued to talk to her but then things started to feel distant and foggy.

I was needing to sort something out.  there was something I needed to find, or someone I needed to talk to.  I woke up and remembered having a dream that had reminded me that I needed to find this thing out.  I was lying on my bed, which was more like a mattress on the floor.  I was there alone. I sort of rolled off the mattress to get up.  It was daylight, I was in a bedroom with bright light shining in the window and I was trying to remember the dream so I could get more details about what it was I needed to find out.  In the dream I had been having I'd been sorting things into lists and I had discovered that something was missing and I needed to find it out before I could continue.  The next thing I know, it's getting dark and I'm outside in a street that looked like many of the inner suburban streets around here, lots of Victorian era workers cottages side by side, some blue stone cobblestones in the gutters or along the edge of the footpath.  I was with a couple of people now, and I knew that I had asked them to help me find out whatever it was that I needed to find out. I don't know who they were.  It was like someone had just put us together in a team to go find this thing.  The next thing I know, we're all in some sort of contraption that's like a buggy, but it wasn't being pulled by a horse. It seemed like a big trike, and someone was peddling in front, and I was siting in the back with someone.  I realised that we needed to hurry, because it was now completely dark, which meant that it might have been after curfew.  I started to worry that we would be seen and get into trouble.  I said something to the others on the trike about needing to hurry, or to get inside where we couldn't be seen.  We now seemed to know where it was we needed to go to find the thing we were looking for and were heading there purposefully - travelling through the dark, mostly deserted streets of Carlton, near Melb Uni.  So we're riding through the streets.  It was like it had just rained, the streets seemed wet, with the street lights reflecting off the glistening blue stone, and bitumen on the road.   Then I turned to look at the person sitting next me and suddenly realised that it was Jenny, my old boss from several years ago. she looked pretty much the same as she used to, her hair was longer, and her face seemed a bit more lined, so older.  I exclaimed "Hey, Jen!" "I didn't realise it was you". "How are you?, What have you been up to?".  She looked at me with something of a forlorn look and said "He tried to make me have another one".  I said "another one?  Another one of what?".  She then started just speaking. It was like she had been keeping all this stuff locked up inside her and hadn't been able to tell anyone. She didn't seem particularly upset though. She was just talking, almost in a monotone, and I was feeling very confused.  I was trying to follow what she was saying.  Eventually, I realised she was talking about having another baby.  And then I felt shocked. I'm pretty sure she's a few years older than me, and I'm 51!  So I was even more confused.  I said "What??! How is that even possible?  You must be in your 50s aren't you?  How could you possibly have a baby?".  She looked at me sadly, and also a bit condescendingly and said something like, 'if you have enough money, anything is possible'. It didn't seem like she was thrilled with idea.  I knew she already had 2 kids. One of them is about the same age as my younger son, and her older child would be in uni now. I asked her how she felt about it, did she want to have another one?  She said "I'm not sure I have a choice", "It's what he wants". The strange thing was, I couldn't tell if she meant, this was something that was happening now, that he wanted her to have a baby, or that it had already happened, and she did have another baby.  And then my attention was drawn back to the fact that we were sitting in this trike, riding through the streets and that we still needed to find that damn thing that I needed to find.  I felt bad that I couldn't spend longer talking to her and comforting her, but we needed to get inside and the place we'd been heading to was just around the corner.  I needed to tell the person steering where to go.  Which I did, and then we pulled up in front of this house. It was all dark.  There was a small front yard, with lots of dense bushes. I couldn't see what sort because it was very dark now. The house was a typical Victorian or maybe Federation building, not a plain as most of the cottages around it because it had tuck-pointed brickwork, and some different coloured bricks around the window at the front. It was single fronted, and had a big dark wooden door with a leadlight above it.  It was dark inside, the street was very quiet. None of the neighbouring houses seemed to have lights on either. It seemed way too dark for the time of night I thought it was.   I tried the door.  It opened slowly and silently. I started to feel optimistic. We had managed to get here without getting in trouble for breaking curfew.  Some of us might have even been further than the 5km from home we're allowed to travel.  I didn't need to worry about that. I knew that my mum's place was within my 5kms, and this place was closer to that.  I started to wonder where I needed to look for this thing.  I think it was something digital, so I was going to need to find a computer.  I opened the first door I came to in the corridor that the front door had opened onto.  It was a very typical hallway for the type of house this was. I walked into the room off the corridor.  It was facing the street and the curtains were pulled apart a bit so I could see out into the street. I saw Jenny standing out on the footpath looking around like she was in a bit of a daze. I felt sorry for her, and a bit outraged that her husband had tried to get her to have another baby at her age. But I had to remind myself that she was a strong woman and that if she really hadn't wanted to go along with it, then I was sure she could have handled herself and said no.  So I turned back to the room and saw a computer sitting on a desk.  It was a big wooden desk, and the computer looked old.  With a CRT monitor rather than the modern LED ones. so it had that big back on it like they used to.  I went over and turned on the computer and sat down at the desk and once the screen came to life I started hunting around for what it was that I had been looking for.  I think I found an excel spreadsheet and was trying to work out if this was the thing that I'd been looking for. sorting things into lists in an effort to find something in particular - that I was needing to remind myself of something, remember how to do something so that when it came time to do it again, I'd know how to.  telling myself to remember what I'd just been dreaming about so I could write it in this diary.

It was something out of a sci fi movie.  I was literally pulling another skin over my own skin.  This was so that I could impersonate someone, or pretend that I wasn't who I actually am. I felt apprehensive that I would be caught out.  The skin wasn't fitting me very well and someone was helping me pull it on - I don't remember anything about them.  I remember someone talking to me about what I would need to do once I had the skin on.  There was obviously something underhanded going on that I was central to. The situation seemed to become more urgent. I was in something like an office building. Just bland decor, not really set up with desks or anything, more open space but I was in a room with at least one other person trying to get the skin on me  It was like an internal office or meeting room with no external windows but glass that you could see through to the rest of the floor, which looked to be in a high rise building of some sort.  It was bordering on a nightmare just because I was getting a bit frantic about getting the skin on.

I was fulfilling a data request for someone.  I don't know who had asked for it, but it was data about children and young people that my department collects, or has. I was sitting at a desk looking at a computer screen that had lots of information on it.  Spreadsheets, and websites and documents that I was sorting through trying to find the information I needed for the data request.  I was making phone calls and talking to people about what I was looking at on the screen, trying to work out how to get what the person who had asked for the data needed. It seems more like a proper office than my home although most of what I could see was just the screen in front of me and not much else. I was really fixated on the screen, and with getting the data request right.  It seemed like the dream was almost in a bit of a loop and I kept sort of waking up but then going back in to the same thing happening again, I was getting frustrated that I wasn't getting anywhere with the request.  There was either too much to find, or I just couldn't find it, I'm not sure which.  I just knew I had to keep going.  I was talking to myself in my dream, telling myself where to look and giving myself suggestions about what to do next.  Then I'd be on the phone having a similar conversation about where to look or what to do with what I had found. I think I talked to my boss at one stage, and the person who had asked for the data just to get some more guidance on what they wanted.  And from my boss, what I was allowed to give them.

I was at a beach. not one that I recognised. I had been walking along the sand with someone, I'm not sure who, but they were a friend. There were fairly high cliffs of stone and then sand down to the ocean, which was fairly calm, with just small waves. It was late afternoon and my friend and I were just strolling along talking. As often happens in my dreams, we realised after some time had passed that the tide had come in, and we were unable to return back the way we had come. Usually when this happens in my dreams I start feeling very anxious and scared about how I"m going to get back but this time I wasn't. I just said to my friend, we're going to have to go up into the streets and walk back that way. They agreed. I can't even remember if it was a man or a woman. I think it was probably a woman. The cliffs must have ended because there was a gentle slope up off the beach now and we headed that way. So we left the beach and then we're suddenly in quite a busy street, with lots of street stalls and traffic and it was now night, so cars had their headlights on and the street lights and shops were all lit up. It had an Asian feeling to it but I didn't notice that there were particularly many Asian people around. So my friend and I were walking along and talking about what we were seeing, when suddenly I noticed my husband and he was talking to a woman iwith long shiny dark hair and I thought I recognised her as someone he works with. They were inside a building with big glass windows and well lit inside so I could see them clearly even though there were other people inside and outside the building milling around. Some people got in my way and so I couldn't keep my eyes on my husband. Once the scene cleared again, the woman was gone and he had started to walk away. For some reason I felt suspicious about what he had been doing with her, why were they talking to each other, what was she doing in the same street/city as us, as I felt we had come on a trip to be here. I ran to catch up to him, and started asked him about the woman he'd been talking to. He seemed genuinely confused about what I was talking about. He said that he hadn't been talking to anyone from his work. I started feeling confused and tried to get him to just think about the last few minutes, who had he bumped into, did he talk to any woman at all? We were discussing it rationally, really trying to work out what I had seen. I don't remember feeling angry or anything, just curious to work out what I'd seen, and what had happened. I started feeling more confused about how I was feeling and what I remembered seeing as he kept saying that he hadn't talked to anyone.

I was in a house that I didn't recognise.  It had a large verandah wrapped around the outside and was weatherboard, and there were lots of rooms and windows out to a fairly dense garden but with some patches of well manicured lawn. I was in the house and I heard something running on the wooden boards of the verandah.  I looked out to see what it was and there was an animal that looked like a fox shooting past. I say it looked like a fox, but it was slightly different.  It was sort of yellowy and not quite as big as a fox should be but it did have a bushy tail.  It tried to come into the open doorway I was approaching, but I shooed it on and it stayed outside.  Then I heard voices outside.  They sounded like they were urging a dog to chase the fox saying things like 'go on', 'go on, get it!'.  Then this huge dog rounded the corner of the verandah going in the same direction as the fox. it scrabbled on the boards, trying to find purchase and then came running towards me, sniffing furiously.  I told it the fox had gone along the side of the house and pointed that way, and the dog looked at me, it had a big head and sleek coat, like a mastiff or something, maybe a St Bernard but with short hair.  It took off after the fox and then I woke up.  I was momentarily frightened that the dog was going to jump on me, and I was a little bit frightened that the dog would actually catch the fox and harm it as it ran after it.

I was in a play with friends from high school who I have not seen in many years. My friend was the main character, who had to sing, and I was in a supporting role. I remember running around backstage changing costumes (both of the costumes were ball gowns, one yellow and green, and one blue) and thinking I would have liked more costume changes than the one. It felt like the play was a version of Hamilton, but with a woman in the starring role? I was happy to see my friends, but didn't have a chance to talk more as we were all busy in the play.

I was swimming in a big pool at the back of my aunt's house. I was in my hometown. My friends were also swimming in the pool with me - people I haven't seen in years, but that I grew up with. I was talking to them and catching up, and then I looked down in the water and realised I had my period, and there was blood in the water. I tried to hide it by getting out of the pool, but one of my friends drew attention to it and began laughing at me.

I was at my family home with my parents and my younger sister. The house and garden had flooded, and the water was chest deep. I was concerned about the water levels, and I could see all sorts of fish swimming in the water. The fish weren't dangerous, but I was worried about the house being damaged. My mother told me it would be fine, and the water would recede. Slowly, after an hour or so, the water began to go down in the house and the yard, and didn't leave any damage to either.

I was with two friends - a man and a woman - who have recently split up after 20 years together. We were in London near Chelsea bridge. I was pointing out where the harbour is and Sloane Square. We were on a balcony. Inside on a sideboard were two clear Perspex torsos. The kind you see in shops to display jewellery or fashion items.

The UK govt dissolved parliament for good, creating an autocracy. All opposition MPs and party leaders were arrested. Anyone who has ever tweeted negative comments about Brexit or signed a petition taking the govt to task were told they would have their property confiscated and risked arrest. My husband turned to and said “I cannot live in this country any more under this govt and would rather die. I am going to kill myself.”

out with a close girlfriend and others unknown - Limited time, hurrying to get back to meet a deadline - I saw the perfect pair of boots in a shop window but due to time pressure couldn’t enter the shop - felt angry and resentful that I couldn’t do as I pleased
Two very pale blonde ice skaters - one man and a woman. Going round and round an ice rink!
Worrying about the house being burgled. Thought I heard burglars.

I was on a high street, nowhere specific, and stopped by a greengrocer's shop to look at the fruit displayed outside.  I picked up a large melon but decided not to buy it.  Then I found myself in a posh clothes shop, the sort that might call itself a "gentleman's outfitter".  I was looking a several pairs of chinos and felt the quality of them.

I had started a new job and I was sitting at the corner of a table with one of my new colleagues. We were both doing some kind of task which seemed to involve logging information about sticks. Then we found ourselves watching a snooker match on TV and we both noticed that one of the players was left-handed. The dream then came back to the table but I knew that this was a couple of days later. Now I was getting along better with my new colleague and she also remarked on this and I said something to the effect that it takes a while to get used to someone who has replaced a former colleague. The sticks were still in evidence. Then I told her that the left-handed snooker player had won the tournament and then on TV there was a clip showing him as a young teenager appearing in a TV soap.

I was on the council estate in Essex where I had lived for two years around sixty years ago. It was a bit different now: instead of houses there were mainly flats and I was looking at some flats with a view to buying one. Then I spoke to the saleswoman and she said that there was one house being built but I might not like it because it didn't have any natural daylight. She showed me the plans and it was actually built underneath a couple of blocks of flats. It was, though, very spacious and smart and I said that I would think about it. I went back outside and looked at the way that the homes were placed on a hillside and I was pleasantly surprised that I remembered the layout of the road where I had lived.

I was with my late wife and we were surrounded by cats.  It was a lovely feeling.  Then we homed in on one of them who turned out to be one of our own cats from many years ago, a lovely, gentle, affectionate cat called Orion who lived to a ripe old age.  We spent some time playing with him and then another cat came along who was just like him, except that this cat was wearing a coat.  Now, this wasn't a little coat which slips on, rather it was a complete covering of fur which went over the top of this cat's own coat and made his colour a shade of light brown.  This cat, too, was very friendly and affectionate.

I was in a bank.  It was an informal set-up with just an open counter between the staff and me.  There were two staff members, one a young woman and a young man who was dealing with me.  the young man made a jokey remark about trousers.  I joked back showing him my own trousers and both he and his colleague laughed and he said that he had been talking about himself.  I acknowledged that and thanked them both for making me smile and then left the bank.

I was actually in my bed.  My mum came into the room and there was a light associated with her.  She told me that she had just seen a ghost and then she sat down on the edge of the bed.  I said that I couldn't see the ghost but then I felt a pressure on my ribs, not at the front but around my right side.  I then said that I could feel it.  Then gradually the pressure eased and then my mum and I agreed that the ghost had gone and I felt a strong sense of relief.  My mum then got up from the edge of my bed and went back to her room.

I was in Marks and Spencer's food hall. I was shopping for a visit by people, it wasn't clear who, in the near future. I looked at meat on the meat counter and saw something I thought I would buy and pointed it out. I was very surprised when it turned out that this piece of meat was actually a small chicken but I decided that I would buy it anyway. As I thought about it as I was leaving the store I decided that I was quite happy with my purchase.

I was with a colleague at the college in Cornwall where I taught Psychology between thirty and twenty years ago.  We were dividing up students for our respective classes from a long list and I let him choose those he wanted because he had a sense that many of them did not like him.  Once that task was done my colleague left the room and I followed shortly afterwards.  I then spoke in a friendly way with two students who were sitting in the corridor and then I noticed that a couple of desks on the other side of the corridor were messy and so I cleaned them up.  I then began preparing to take an exam in Psychology feeling comfortable that I had plenty of time to do so but then saw that the clock seemed to have been racing and that it was almost 2.00 and thus time for me to go into the exam room.  I remembered that I needed to have some lunch so I picked up a tub of apple puree and ate some of that and then washed it down with a mouthful of single cream from another tub and then went into the exam room.

The setting was an office.  I seemed to have the role of an observer in some kind of official capacity but that was never made clear.  Also, I think that the office was in a bank but it was a back office so no actual banking activities were observed.  There were two other people in the office, a middle-aged woman and a young man.  Then it was time for us to go and we all went out of the office and made our way to the door, which was a large, wide one, a bit like you would find in a stately home.  We went through the doors and down a few steps to somewhere like a courtyard and then on to the gates which led on to the street.  I was about to start talking to the woman when she was called back and I felt disappointed that I hadn't been able to talk to her.  The young man seemed to have disappeared and I went out of the gates, turned right and walked down a hill.

I was with a long-term friend called Philip and another woman whom I did not know but she seemed to be a friend of Philip.  We were in a hilly and rocky area, something like the Peak District.  Then I spotted on top of a footpath a woman called Jenny who was a colleague at the college where I had worked in Cornwall but whom I haven't seen for around twenty years.  She walked down the steep path to meet us.  She made a joke about how strange it was to meet up here and with our friends and I replied, "Why not?  We are all really nice people."  Jenny made a comment about my colourful polo shirt and then fingered its collar and said "You would be wearing that" and I said that I had several including one which was the same shade of bright red as her jumper, which I could see underneath the white mac she was wearing.  Philip then said that we needed to be getting back as he needed an early night.

I am watching a comedy.  It's not on TV or on stage but I am watching and at the same time a part of it.  There is a woman who is proud of her settee and says that it dates from 1830.  Then there is a lot of laughter, apparently from an audience although I can't see one, and then I see what they are laughing at which is a set of labels on the cushions of the settee saying that they come from Boot's.  The mood suddenly changes and it is reported that a young girl is missing from the home but somehow I don't feel a sense of threat, that everything will soon be fine.  Someone then advises the people of the house to redecorate their home and the missing girl arrives back.  They have a new front door which is very smart and also a brand-new wide filing cabinet which has a glossy finish.  The family have also acquired a new pet pig.

I was behind the scenes in an art museum which was probably in The Netherlands, although that was never made explicit, because there was a focus on the Dutch art of the 17th century. I was with someone who had been guiding me through the establishment and then he went off and left me with two young women. I was explaining to them why I really like the art of this period and mentioned that in a book I had read the writer drew parallels between the art and Dutch football in the 1970s. All three of us got talking about the wonderful football played by Ajax and by the Dutch national team in the 1974 World Cup. Then one of the women said that sadly Dutch football isn't like that any more.

I was at an airport.  I was watching a string of planes landing and was impressed with this.  I have a fear of flying so it was meaningful to me to see so many planes land safely.  I turned round from my vantage point and found that several people were there from the college where I had worked around twenty years ago.  I then found myself marking some work and talking with one particular colleague.  As well as the paper-based assignments, we were looking at and assessing, but not listening to, a set of oversized CDs.  I then felt a sense of relief when I had finished my own marking and I talked with a couple of colleagues who were just finishing theirs.

A meeting that was between me, and the other brothers of a fraternity i was a part of. We were discussing something important about the start of term, and it was quite heated. We were meeting on a grass square in the town where I grew up, and there was a huge stage like at Glastonbury. The head of the meeting was a guy I used to fence with at university, freddie, and he was being very hostile towards me. The other members of the meeting were David Lloyd George, but he looked like albert einstein, William Barr the US attorney general, and some other members.The focus of the meeting shifted quite quickly to the acceptance of gay members of the fraternity, and freddie decided to fully call me out for being 'closeted'. He refused to go further in the meeting until I announced to the world I was gay. After this I quickly left the meeting, where I bumped into my friend at a nearby University, Pietro, and we had to take David Lloyd George home on the london underground, where we went back to my mums home.

I found myself wearing an orange hi-vis vest.  Then it transpired that I was in front of a group of about twenty people who were all commending me for having arrested someone and I inferred that I was some kind of police officer although no one was in uniform.  But suddenly it was announced that there were more criminals to be apprehended and so I set off although this time wearing a light blue hi-vis vest.  I was running through empty streets.

I was walking uphill along a road in Cornwall. On the way I passed a colleague from my college.  She was a rather quietand withdrawn; she just acknowledged me and walked on.  Then I came to a huge spider's web strung across the road and there were several people on the other side of it.  I broke though it and the people were very pleased that I had done this and were congratulating me. There was no sign of any spider.

the premise of the dream focused around needing to find my grandmother, as I had to deliver a pair of glass ornamental slippers. In order to find where she lived we had to break into houses and try and find her. We broke into one house and decided to use it as our base, so we left all our stuff there and would come back to it to pick stuff up. After the last house we searched, we couldn’t find my grandmother. So we decided to go back to our base house and collect our stuff and leave. As we got to the front door of the house we noticed there was music coming out of it so whoever lived there must be in. So I snuck in and quickly grabbed all of the stuff we’d left there in the living room. As I was leaving i noticed whoever was in the house was in the kitchen and had heard my packing up. In the process of packing up I’d smashed the glass slippers by accident. As i go to leave the house, I hear the owner come rushing out. I manage to make it outside and pretend to be just walking around, but I’m carrying loads of bags so i look suspicious. The owner comes charging over to me silently, with a scary look on his face.

I was in a city in the north of England.  It wasn't a city I recognised.  I was with a group of people but there was no one I actually recognised, it was just a feeling that they were people I knew.  We were on a bus and looking to get off at a particular place.  The streets were very busy, lots of pedestrians around.  I thought that we had arrived an told my companions and we all got off the bus.  Then we realised that it was the wrong place and we needed to get another bus but we didn't know where to catch it.  feeling frustrated and a little anxious.  Then I remembered where we should go and we walked quickly to the right place and a bus appeared immediately.  I felt a sense of relief.

I was re-taking my A Level History exam, I have no idea why. I desperately wanted to get an A grade.  After exactly an hour and twenty minutes of the exam I needed to go to the toilet.  I left the exam hall but couldn't find a toilet so I just kept walking for what seemed like an age and then I became very concerned that I was now a long way away from the exam hall and actually out in the street where it was dark and deserted.  So then I started running but my legs wouldn't respond and then I just gave up on the exam, feeling despondent that, although I knew that I had done enough to pass, I could not possibly get an A grade.

I was in a department store with my wife.  Then I lost track of her but I spoke with a sales assistant, a very pleasant woman, who assured me that all would be well and I would find my wife very soon.

I was at a football match but it was very quiet.  Someone mentioned that it was a shame that Stoke City got relegated from the Premier League.  One season they're playing Liverpool, Manchester City, Chelsea and Arsenal the next they're playing Wycombe Wanderers.  Then I said that it is much worse when a team gets relegated from the Football League and they end up playing Harrogate Town, Havant and Waterlooville and Braintree Town.

I was talking to an ex colleague from and old work, Daniel. We were standing under a small tree, it was a sunny day. I cannot remember what we talked about. There were other people, an old man, a few children around. Then the place flooded, but it went down very quickly, it was some sort of a strange tide. But the people and my Daniel seemed to be fine with it. Daniel told me it was very normal. Then we were looking at some random people working out inside a gym, but they had all the windows open. Out of nowhere my husband turns out with a pet tiger. He was walking the tiger on a leash down the road. I went to ask him é where he got it, he then said that someone has given it to us. My husband carried on with his pet and walked right under the litte tree me and Daniel were talking before.

I was with some close family friends and old friends, I haven't seen these people in almost 15 years. We were catching up with life. My godfather then declared that he had hidden son... People were angry and some tried to run away. We were all in what it look like an enclosure. Then I jump to another scene in a middle of a crowd again, we were in a square in my home town, people dressed and behave very strangely, it look like we went back in time sometime in the 1930, more random chatting to people took place. There was a couple that fall in love by sending each other letters but the father of the woman didn't approved. I couldn't recognise the people. Then I jumped again to another scene where I saw people from my previous works, again all gathering in some sort of closed building. A lady who used to work as a cleaner came to greet me and she was very happy to see me, she explained why we were all together but I cannot remember. There were buses bringing more people in and got pretty crowded.

I was in an open field, there was a party with white tents. At the party I saw some of my high school classmates. I went down to a river to talk to some friends who are a couple. I can't remember what we talked about but they asked for my husband. Then I walked back to one of tents and found another ex classmate. We were having a nice conversation then I walked across to another tent where I found an ex boyfriend and a good friend of mine chatting. My friend Dayana was a bit scared but I told her that I didn't mind if she wanted to be with Chicho, coz I never really liked him. The 3 of us were talking for a while then I started to rain. My grandfather came on a car to take me home. He was wearing his usual clothes, baggy fabric brown trousers, brown ancor boots and a white embroidered shirt. Dayana came to ask if we could give her a ride. I agreed. My grandfather complained about one of the lights of the car not working properly, it was dark and missed the road to my friend house. It was a dirt road, he abruptly turned around and drop Dayana near her home. We carried on driving, it looked like a hill then my grandad complained again about the lights a d not being to see much, so I offered to drive. We changed places and I drove. There was a gap in the dream, not sure, then I was at my grandparents house with my uncles and mother, they told me about my grandfather death. I didn't believe them coz I saw him the night before, so I run down the road to another house. That house belongs to a lady who is close friends with the family. Her house was a bungalow, white with terracotta roof tiles. She had flowers hanging from the porch. There were also other people sitting in white chairs, my grandmother's sister and the lady owner of the house. They were chatting and told me that my cousin was waiting for me inside. I walked into a room, my cousin was laying on a bed, when she saw me she got up. I told her that I didn't believe my grandad was death, she told me that we just hurried him and I started crying. Then I handed her a manuscript, I told her that I have written a story and that I wanted her to make it into a movie.

Me and approximately 5 other people were searching through old boxes of books for a school report for someone called 'Val'.  'Val' was an older woman and was a friend who had mysteriously disappeared and no-one knew what had happened. For reasons unknown, the school report was the key to the mystery.  'Val' liked horses and the boxes of books also contained lots of pictures of horses and books about horses.

I was at a music festival with a group of people I have been friends with for more than 20 years.  One of those friends was an agent for bands including the Libertines and introduced us to Pete Doherty in the backstage area.  Additionally, instead of using the normal festival portaloos, we were allowed to use the VIP bathrooms which were very large rooms decorated to an excessively high standard and included an area with sofas to relax in.

I was somewhere cold near the sea , the landscape was quite mountainous and bare. Buildings were wooden and there were large boats moored in a harbour type area. I was sitting watching the boats and not thinking of anything.

I was in a very large vintage style car with someone else. The car was very high up - similar height to a tractor - and had steps on the side to climb up. the length and width dimensions were proportional to the height. The car was topless and a teal colour. We were driving down the Main Street of the village in which I grew up past the village shop in the direction of my home.

I was walking back from the airport with a small red wheely case. It was a long way and I took a short cut through a small garden centre where I fell when climbing over the back fence, even though the fence was only about 1 metre high. I was uninjured but I made a hole in the right knee of my jeans.

I was in a zoo but there were no animals. I was trapped in a sort of walkway. there was another person with me they were male and in their 30s. The grounds was bare earth from overuse wearing the grass away.

There was an electricity outage in my flat.  The lights worked in the bedroom and living room but not in the kitchen, hallway and bathroom. I spent a long time trying to find out what was wrong. The torch I was using worked only intermittently so it was difficult to see in the electrical box.  The circuit breaker labelled 'Scotland renewable' was down - I moved it back into its up position and the electricity came back on again. Now I could see,  I noticed that the freezer in the hallway had moved and someone had put a water fountain in its place (it was a metal one like the ones they have in America but the spout part was not fitted so it was just the basin).  There was a woman in my living room that I was friends with. She had red hair and said the water fountain was her brother-in-law's and could I look after it until he came round to collect it. I had a memory of meeting her brother-in-law at a family even by a river.  I asked how she got in given that I hadn't let her in or noticed her entering the flat. She said she was able to fiddle the lock and remove the chain from the outside of the door to get in. She asked if I would leave the door unlocked so her brother-in-law could get in when he needs to collect the water fountain.  I thought this was unnecessary as I am working from home and be in but agreed anyway, saying I needed to know which day this would be because I couldn't leave the door unlocked every day.

I was living in and running a hostel. There were 20-30 people in the communal area - this was a large communal area with a sofa and some chairs to the right of the door and a table and chairs ahead of the door (I was stood in the doorway) a group of people were round the table getting ready to go out for a day trip. They split hand sanitiser (it smelt of tequila) on my table and it stripped the varnish so I was quite annoyed about this and started shouting at everyone to take more care with things as well as not waste hand sanitiser

I was in my childhood living room, decorated as it was over a decade ago when my parents still lived there.  I was getting ready for my zoom yoga class that I have this morning - instead of my laptop I was using a large-ish television (approx 32") as the screen on the dining table but I couldn't use the floor space by the dining table for yoga because there was a 4' non-decorated Christmas tree (Nordmann fir) in the middle of the space.  This was a bit annoying (and odd) because it is only October and there is no current need for a Christmas tree (also it will lose its needles by December).  I moved to the space in front of the fireplace and started and trying to balance the television on an armchair.   My sister arrived - I asked her if she wanted to join and told her I have a spare yoga mat - it is standing up against the back wall of my living room, she went next door to get it*. I asked her about the Christmas tree - she said it was our younger sister** who put it there and it was best just to let her get on with it.  I realised I was 15mins late for the yoga class. The whole story of the dream had a 'Little Women' type of feeling to it.

Someone I knew was missing a cat called Shelby. The cat was black and white (mostly white but black over one eye and some small black patches elsewhere) and walked with a crutch so the owner was especially worried. the cat was not found
A friend had 3 pills to treat anxiety in a small plastic bag. The pills were approx 1cm diameter and dark red in colour. He decided to take just one.

I met my sister for lunch in a quite upmarket cafe/restaurant and she’d brought 2 friends with her. The friends were cast members of Made in Chelsea - I can’t remember which 2. The 2 friends talked about themselves constantly which I found both boring and annoying. I left the lunch which annoyed my sister.
I was in prison playing cards with a guard. I was both the prisoner and the guard. Prisoner me held 2 cards - one was a spade.

I was in a living room with my two cousins, Nicola and Lisa. On the sofa, there was a couple laid down. They were Lisa's in-laws and the man was asleep. I said it was time for me to go so I gave everyone a hug and a kiss before leaving even though I don't really know her in-laws.
I was running for a bus with my friend, Emma. I had my shoes in my hand. We got on the bus and it was packed with people. We had to go sit upstairs and there was loads of children.

I had turned up at a bar, it was really busy. I was looking around for a seat when I noticed my crush behind the bar and realised it was his. He had his hands full so I took something off of him and ended up helping out in the bar.  Next thing, I was in the bar kitchen doing some washing up when he snuck up behind me and breathed into the back of my neck "boo".

I was in a school and people were preparing for rugby and football matches. In the changing room, there were rugby coats with players names and numbers on the back. One of the players told me I could have his coat. I put it on, struggling to zip it as I couldn't see the bottom of the zip the coat was so big! Everyone was staring and thought it looked cool, so I kept it on. I was walking around the pitches, and I came to a rugby pitch. Playing in the game was my crush. He saw me and smiled. Loud noises filled the air and I looked up to see two metal triangles flying in the air, like spaceships, and a plane flew by too. People were staring up at them amazed. In the background I could hear an old song playing, think it's called I'll Be Home Soon. The main line it was focusing on was, "Promise me you'll wait for me."

I was living back in Barkisland and holding a kids party. A guy was there helping me out (he was my boyfriend). Another guy turned up declaring his love for me and bringing gifts, saying how much he'd missed me. I was confused as to who I should be with, but told the second guy to leave as I wanted to stay with the guy that was supporting me and not the one buying me gifts and not been around.

I was living in a huge mansion that had been turned into apartments. My daughter, Chloe, came home with some neighbours she had met on her way up to our apartment. They were three guys, late teens early twenties, wearing black clothes and leather jackets. The main guy wanted to date Chloe. I didn't trust them. The guys kept popping by, insisting I let them in. I didn't want to but my two girls couldn't see what was wrong with them. I would let them in. One day, it was only two of them and when I asked where the other one was they laughed about never having to  see him again. I knew they had killed him.  Next time, the other guy had gone missing too. The main guy said he was moving in and took over my bedroom. He wanted me to share my bed with him, but I laid on the floor, in front of the bedroom door, so I would know if he tried to leave.  One day he was sleeping and I took the girls and escaped to my parents.

I was working in a school as a Teaching Assistant. The school very much resembled an old building I used to work at which was a respite home for adults with disabilities.  the head teacher was a past head I'd worked for previously.  I was walking passed a classroom, when I could hear commotion inside. I opened the door and demanded the troublemaker left the classroom. As we were walking down the hall he tried to leave me, but I persevered and kept him nearby. I got him to the reception where I asked them to phone his parents and I turned to leave. Looking back, I saw him steal something and quickly put it in his pocket. I went to go find the head and inform her so she could have him expelled, but when I found her, she was awful to me and started shouting about me interrupting her. I was annoyed I told her she could go fuck herself as I was only looking out for her and the school.

I was back in our old home in Barkisland. I was in the back garden when I saw my neighbour come out. she was old, but wearing 60s clothes. She had a blouse, mini skirt and knee boots on. Her hair was tightly curled. I went to speak to her and she turned her back on me. I came in front of her to say hello and she told me she didn't want to talk to me. She said I hadn't been to see her. I told her I was sorry and her eyes filled up and she said, "I've been looking at your photo."  A lovely young women came by, didn't speak a word, just stood there and smiled at me, with her hand on my shoulder. She had long black hair, a pretty face and a lovely, white smile. I told her how Sandra was upset with me and I felt guilty. The woman wrapped her arms around me and hugged me while stroking my hair.

I was a student in school and had a sore throat. I walked to the front of the class to tell the teacher that I didn't feel well and I was going to go home. As I was talking to him, my voice was croaky and I started to cough. The teacher covered his mouth with his hand and said, "Why are you telling me, you're just infecting everyone, just go!"

I was with the parents of a friend who had died. It was some sort of accident and i had written a letter which sparked a campaign Kier Starmer wanted to meet me to be his spokesperson.The dream moved from being on a pebble beach to a hostel at night. I was trying to be admitted as Kier was working a night shift there. However he couldnt let me in and there was a commotion at the doir as residents were trying to get in,i was trying to speak to Kier. He then led me away in the rain,although it wasnt the Kier Starmer but someone else,to talk in an open area,with large aircraft hangar type buildings around and it was now daylight

I was with some people who culd have been siblings. My mother was at one moment ailingcand the next dying from cancer,the tumour maing herceye  socket and cheek swollen and yellow.then there was s brief moment where i seemed to seperate from my wife and i was in a type of outdoor project making objects from pieces of tree,a sort of environmental project.Two of the women in the proect either fancied me or i was attracted to them,it wasnt clear and then i was in a seperate building,somehow i can tell its upstairs and there was a vague sensecthatvthexwoman there wanted sexual relations and i was both intrigued but distracted with other things i needed to do

i was a social worker and arrived at what seemed to be a 1930s or 50's building.i was in a corridor and there were tables of female nurses talking, the atmosphere was animated.A male doctor of indeterminate age with  a noticeable pointed white beard appeared agitated by his conversation with the nurses regarding the care plan for his patients and was insistent on engaging me, returning to try and shake my hand and seek my re -assurance that everything would be overseen There was hill of old buildings/wards behind us of wood and glass and peeling apint.one of the nurses, heavy set in black shirt and jeans got me to sit with her whilst she talked.She moved my arm from the chair behind her to the inner thigh which was laddered and it was evident she had sexual intent but though i was aroused i wasn't interested I was then walking through one of the doors with another nurse who had some time ago  it seemed persuaded me that  we could have sex and that it would not contravene my marriage vows.However as we moved through the room which  were arranged around a large corridor, they were teaming with  older people with all their belongings arranged in haphazard homes or living areas and there was again a sense of great activity and happiness.We ended  at the top where, over a balcony we watched a type of vaudeville show, an old man, one of the patients, riding on a bile with a long triangular frame around it, throwing crockery ans gazing to me to be approved.Another old man on the stage appeared to be performing pathos and similarly seemed beseeching in his manner  (there seemed a need to write this in the 'voice' of the person i was in the dream, a sort of victorian reflection on bedlam or similar)

I arrived  in Denmark,a country i'd never been to before. I realises i didnt have any euros. I was walking along a strram in the city. There was an older couple there too who seemed to be both hrlping and observing me but also needing to leave. There were small marine animals underfoot including small orange crabs and water slugs but i didnt know if i could eat them.  I was then in a market in narrow streets and there were all type of small shops or stalls,mostly selling fish based foods but i couldnt pronounce them or communicate and i had no money I was then decending steep improvised steps,down the outside of a building past thrown together stalls with refugees trying to sell goods I was with a group of younger people and we were students or similar. As we moved away from the shops there was a grand vista of valleys and trees lined hills,in the distance miniarettes and the sea. We couldnt reach it and my companions were despondent bu ii guessed there must be a cable car station. We foind it in a featureless soviet block type concrete building We ascended several stairs to a plain hatch in the wall . We summoned one of the staff who we couldnt understand due to language difficulties but made it clear there were no more cable cars that day. We were then in a large old house and shared accommodation.It was a typical student flat with belongings oddly placed. One of the males was clearly the 'leader', ie he had a sepwrate room,seemed to live there with his girlfriend. The other all seemed to have singlecrooms but mainly live in the main room ..there were stereos hapgazardlyvarranged and when i asked if there was a microwave i could heat some foid in it took time to locate it in another room under a chair

I was in a Scout hut with one of my daughters, C. I was reprimanded by one of the leaders for both being late and for talking.We were each handed a blank piece of white A$ paper and asked to draw a duck  and fold it into 3-D model I now was with my other daughter N who had already worked out a way to draw the outline and a way to fold it, so i began to copy her drawing We were then outside and planning a walk. it was wet and C was less than enthusiastic. As we looked at the map, i noticed the path traced through woodland, down a steep slope and up again but that, at the other side was a path that led to where i had parked the car as we walked along this path we met four older young women who were all, in some way related to us

I saw a man fall down and hit his head on a driveway. I wentvovercto check he was ok and sit with him but hecran off across thecroad and began to try and hide down another lane.  Somehow i persuaded him to return as we were both sat again on the drive. A small white car began to reverse almostvibto it andvi tgrew a stone hard. It dented the bumper but the car didnt stop. There was something about the mans presentation that made me ask if he'd ever had a diagnosis of Autism and that he shoild see his GP the next day to discuss this. I then became aware that his newly wedded wife and his father had been viewing a house behind us. He was then on the driveway of the house next door and i was invited in to have lunch. As i satcat the table i began to ask or think that i was asking if he had ever been diagnosed with autism . However i was  now focussed on putting out place mats of two different sizes which began to confuse me as the meal,possibly soup, was served

I was onholiday with my wife. We visited a place nearby which offered cheaper accommodation. Within a day i realised thatbit operated as a hostel for homeless people. We went into town and decided we needed amap. The shopwe went into was newly set up and was run by C,our local oub landlord. This seemed odd as he has no interestin hiking /walking and the shop was full of maps and walikg /outdoir guides. I wa also now trying to fix the handle of an upright vacuum cleaner and hoping C would help out. We went into the basement which was grey stone,part of one wall netly plastered where a fire place had been and the walls partly painted in bright yellow We had now returned to the hostel . There was a eceptionist who i was on the phone to he assumed i was someone else and began giving me a detailed account of a legal case she thought i was involved in until i told her she had the wrong person. I was then trying to take a shower and convinced we needed to leave . However i couldnt find my room, had taken aflannel from someone wash bag the same colour of mine by mistake whichbi returned,the occupant of the room never waking. . I returned to the hostel and the ssme secretery / receptionist was now detailing a xalm she had taken from a woman whos account she doubted. She had no idea that the womans ex husband was sat in the room eating with his back to her. I went into a back office. At some point the owners fad persuaded me to manage the property. I raised my concernthat confidential information was willi gly being given out with no insight into the ilklegality. The manager dismissed the concrns,tgat the secretary was well known and had worked there for 17 years. A second male tried to re assure me that nothing was untowrd about it I then found myself on a sloping roof,overlookig a medieval or eastern european town,at dusk, attempting to enter and leave when the owner/ foe confronted me with a long bladed piece of metal

I was looking at a white book with an inset on the cover on which appeared to be black rock, massed at the base but crumbling at the top so that the white background became visible. As i reached out for it, more with my mind than with my hand, , i was propelled backwards along a narrow dirt track, the book now in the distance, the road curving.i felt anxiious and scared and reached out again only to be propelled further backwards I was now in a busy market town, like India or morocco.My old friend PM was with me and thers was a sense of urgency about..there was a 21.00 curfew and everyone needed to be off the streets..someone said watch out for the grils in disguised in petticoats....im in a busy shop, there are queues and everyone is trying to buy blankets or other warm clothing...i find myself at a stall with two women trying on afghan coats...the one i choose is too large and drapes the floor but i realise might be helpful if i have to sleep out all night...there are vampires stalking the streets..i'm in the street which is now almost empty..i have no accommodation...I find one place which has two vacancies..i hesitate as PM isn't here, i can see him somehow but not talk to him..i enter the building..I am now in a bustling bar..it feels festive,like christmas and I am walking purposefuly through with someone else, they might or might not be the women from the shop...as I begin to clear the crowd i see my old girlfriend laughing with people and we momentarily catch each others eye..I feel compromised and uncertain how to erspond...i am now walking up a domestic staircase and note a small parcel on the turn of the stair..it is a christmas ornament, a tradition we used to give each other every year.I am suddenly aware that i have forgotten my sons birthday which is new years day, he is two or three, i cant recall his name..he is in the flat and with another person we begin to take down the small christmas tree and pack it away when I become aware that SB is coming back, that she will not have wanted us to put these things away, I cant recall my son's name or properly or connect with him, i realise i had forgotten to visit him since he was born him , i feel guilt and uncertainty.

I was walkind down a lane but noticed that the hedge,three fields across,was made of wooden oblongs,such that you looked at them end on and they seemed to be attached so the hedge moved like a child wooden snake toy. Then i was reading an uncharacteristically long letter from my friend Jon when i realised half way through it was from his wife jane and i was struggling at the same time to write and frame a response

We had an event to put on but couldnt find a single marqueee big enough. We had a collection of 5 or 6...onexwas canvass butvtoo long and narrow,another was squarish but made of white silk,another was flimsy,another msde of black plastic. We had to acandon one location as it was too muddy. The next one we put up was muddy too and then a foitball match stsrted. There were then repkays of a remarkable goal from the cotner spot where a new player ran into the box from outside the box to head in...the kickbfrom the right hand side of the pitch/field was taken by a left footed player which made the kick even more unlikely and on the third replay i realsed he was kicking a sleeping duck,not a ball which made me concerned for the head of the player scoring the goal

it was vague and less distinct i had to meet a service user but their was something sexualised about the encounter and i was distinctly uncomfortable about it then i was cutting a hedge, it had no colour and was black against a white background, we couldn't agree how to cut it and I was just cutting the larger branches but they seemed to remain, leaving an uneven silhouette against the sky

I was an observer. There was a thin white and anxious woman,with scars on her face...she was being told by a chinese female surgeon,who also had a set of deep cuts and scars on her face, that they would dolve her problems once and for all,or words to that effect. As if to maje the point that she was unhinged,she pushed the wide bladed scalpel into an area of grey mass at the side of her eye to clean it or scratch an itch but no blood emerged. Their intention was to surgicaly implant the woman into the body of an alligator type creature...the woman was obviously terrified but unable to move or get away...i then found myself trying to imagine how the surgery would turn out...would you see the womans face as the alligator opened its mouth...would her fingers be stitched to the inside of its claws...and i was in a room with an old girlfriend of minexwho was working on an art installation...id adked to use her toilet but it was blocked and overflowing with clear water..i asked if she had a plunger but the one she had as half rotted away..the sideof the cupboard next to the bath fel away to reveal boxes of tools and memorabilia but no lplunger.. it wasnt a happy or welcoming meet up and there was a tension in the air..

It was some form of funeral for a member of admin staff i had little knowledge of.I was waiting for CS to arrive..the church was a huge modern brick block of a building-CS is now retired and frustrated at being called out.There is another person there, a relative of the deceased, alarge heavy set male who we know is a violent offender and mentally unwell and has no clothing on his top half..then CS and i are sat in the church and CS has a bag of individually wrapped chocolats which are some sort of gift from the deceased we aren't supposed to be eating, or it seems that way and he drops one to me...then we are in some sort of vessel on a fast flowing serpentine river which feels more like a flume and dangerous..i am in the boat with another relative who is kate Bush but doesn't look like her and there is a KB song in my head 'night of the swallow'..there is some sense that there has been sexual intimacy between us in the past but i have little recollection and am not interested in her advances,,,CS is anxiiuos at the boats speed and then we are at the back of the church,..i have found the key but the door is unlocked...it is an impsoing but bland large brick building and we climb a back stairs into the church again and again i am sharing a pew with CS and he has the bag of chocolates.

I was at some sort if outdoir event,primarily with two women one of whom seemed loosely based on an old female friend who is a circus performer,the other on my partner. We were preparing for some type of festival or outdoir event. I made some sampmes of foid in small ramekins,one based on carrots one based on cous cous but when i oresentedcthem i was berated as people were expecting a full meal and children were hungry.there was a vague sense of being caught between the two women and making difderent asurances to them each,i was attracted to them both and they to me but the details are lost

I was stood out in the countryside with my wife and there was a sense of their being other people with us. We needed to get back to tbe village but the fields were filling up with flood water,the patb back becoming lost. Sian seemed relaxed about it all but i was becoming anxious She set off alo g the linecof a fence and was lost after a short while behind a small group of bushes. I tried to set off after her but the,waters had risen further and it was difficult to navigate. I stopped near a sink holexas Sian made way back to me Then we were in a large house,part party part refuge,with loads ofcfriends and i was trying to sort and put away all the cutlery and pans which had been washed a d piled haphazzardly but was getting frustrated that no one else seemed to be helping

A sense of loss at a relationhip ending, sat in a featureless unlit box room watching actv set at an angle facing away whilst an ex partner is moving out, Writi g notes,phoni g said ex but knowi g it is pointless; seeing a framesd letter on a wall thanking staff for the care of my daughter and realising one of my girls has recovered from a serious illness i knew nothing about; a young black goalkeeper left out of celebrations with other plyers as he has let six goals in

My daughter came home having got into an argument or trouble. It wasnt where e live now. A male i was with said she had been with the local traveller children and he wouldnt let his kids play with them...then we were with the local travellers, riding their horses, playing daredevil games
I was vacuuming a resort hotel and the vacuum cleaner opened up and there was no bag inside.

I am pregnant and go to a medieval type building. There are other houses in a U shape provided by the main house.  It is like a gated community. I am from the main house. I insist another women wears a belt strapped under her belly to protect her pregnancy also.

I walk up to the top of a water slide. I am told I can't go down the slide as it is a special place for Buddhist monks. I decide to go into the water and join a monk in the water on a ledge. I now realize I am completely saturated and I need to find some dry clothes. I search a market place to find something to wear. It is very hard to find suitable dry clothes. I am now chatting to my old boyfriend, Noel. I am very happy to see him but I then race after my husband and feel very young and athletic. In fact I fly up to him and around him.

I am at home. Dawn is with us. I am quite surprised but she stays the night and does not go home. She sleeps in my sister's bed in my old farmhouse where I lived as a child. I see her as she breast feeds my little brother aged around 3 years. In the morning Dawn says she can stay and work until 5 pm. It seems she does not want to go home. I am quite surprised as we no longer have little kids in our house for her to take care of.

I was in a place such as the Bahamas. My family were there but not with me. I seem to be having breakfast watching the foreshore from a car. Suddenly the car is swamped in water and I desperately get out into the waves. The car floats away. I get to the shore and am very distressed. My daughter comes to get me but decides to leave me there about 8 kilometres from the hotel. She goes back. My eldest sister turns up and watches me. I start the long trek back to the hotel. Dream 2 I am in a bus full of young people. My brother in law who is a financial adviser is at the back of the bus. I am towards the front. On our right, as we head into a very dark tunnel, Tesla is building a tall building with a massive air conditioning unit on the side. We go into the tunnel and it is pitch black. Two lights head towards us and we all believe it is a train and we are going to die. I duck my head down and say to myself well this is it. The lights pass through and we keep going into the dark tunnel. I look back at my brother in law and he shrugs his shoulders like and seems to be indicating, well we better keep going. We are now outside a week later and we are going to enter the tunnel again. We are all shocked how quickly the building has grown in one week since we were here. The building is very tall full of boxes with files and stationary. The air conditioning unit on the size is massive.

I am the assistant of Virginia Trioli we go to a school to interview teachers. Virginia is very short with the staff. We are made to wait and she is annoyed. I have ridden a horse, Eddie, that we own. I am told to take him to another room next door to the staffroom. He decides to pee and it splashes over me, the floor, the walls everywhere!! I am completely covered in horse piss! A teacher arrives who also used to be a colleague of Virginia's. She is not happy we are there. I am now looking at a large group of buildings, on of which is housing an elephant. Suddenly the building starts to collapse, like a a set of cards or dominoes. I rush over to save the elephant in the room. A woman in reception tells me to take it through the glass doors. I am now outside. Virginia is in a cab to the airport. I get into a pink looking Cadillac with a section of the elephant in the back. Suddenly the car turns into a small plane and takes of vertically flown by a woman pilot. She says it will cost $1800 to get to the airport and I worry I don't have the money. Suddenly a man and a woman both very athletic grab on to the plane as it takes off and try to get in. We are flying low over highways and bridges. I look behind and the elephant is gone.

I was in a work setting, though not a place I knew from reality, but I've been there in my dreams before. I was meant to be at a meeting about employment services to hearing impaired people, but I didn't think I was needed as there were many others there both junior and senior to myself. Then things got muddled and I found myself in some sort of medical setting with family members and work colleagues who were having part of their brains removed and replaced with music players. I was very frightened for myself and for them - all women. Then I realised that the "captors" wouldn't be interested in me as I'm post menopausal - the others were younger and prettier than me. I left the room and looked for an escape. A table and mirror in an alcove seemed to be an illusion which I could walk through, so I did and found myself outside the building. There were other people around but they couldn't see me. I seemed to have taken the form of a large black cat and blended into the darkness.

I am with people I know from my children's pony club. We are in a supermarket. They seem surprised but happy to see me ... but they do hesitate. Now the same people are riding horses outside amongst some hills. I am not riding as I can't anymore They are riding freely as in no helmets and galloping around. I do worry they don't have helmets on but think they are young. Now I am at a conference for mental health. I sit at a table with a very agitated man in his 50s.He is very slight andno one I recognize. I am able to help him calm down after a conversation. The room is now full and packed with so many people all there looking for answers to their mental health problems. The facilitator asks if anyone has anything to say. The man jumps up and points to me and says I am a miracle worker and he even has kept a green circular cardboard shape I have given him to help him cope. I shyly stand up and feel monk like in a room of unrest and agitated people. I feel very calm. I am now back at the horse property. Everyone has dismounted and sits in a circle. There are lots of young people. The facilitator moves around the room and selects people in which to point a mirror upon. They point the mirror at my nephew sitting next to me, then me and then my youngest daughter sitting next to me in the circle.

My friend from Uni days came to stay with me. She brought her younger brother Barry with her. I was very welcoming. I got them some towels but they were old looking. Barry decided he was leaving to stay with other friends. Then Wendy decided to leave. I said but you were going to stay for a few days. She indicated that was never the case. I suggested we go to a little nearby town for coffee but then realized we couldn't because we are in lockdown. I get the feeling my house is not good enough for them to stay in. I now go outside my house and go for a walk around a large oval. I realize I have never been here before yet the park is within 5 km radius of my house. I suddenly realize I don't have a mask on and try to find one in my pocket but only pull out large rubber bands and tissues. I try to make a mask but then realize many people are walking past me with without masks on. I feel unsafe. I try to climb a man made triangle structure. It has a narrow edge. I start up but feel to unsafe and come down. A small child whizzes down past me from the top of the tall black triangle. Young people are going up and down the triangle. They don't seem to care.

My family and I are camping not far from our property. I go up to the edge of our block and lit a fire for everyone. A few people are gathered around but suddenly there are little fires everywhere and they are out of control. I am blamed especially by my husband's female cousin. I then go down a long road barefoot to our house where my husband is. I am aware that there is a snake in the grass nearby. My husband is in a very low level bathroom. It is a similar bathroom to our first weekend away in a cottage 30 years ago!  We start to make love when we are interrupted by someone arriving. a horse competition. I'm on an old horse of ours and I get in the way of a child jumping their horse. The horse stops and I am blamed by the onlookers as their accusing looks say I was in the way. I express that I didn't know where to go. Just as it is my turn to jump, the little mare I am on collapses and lies down. She is too old and tired to move. I gather her up in my arms and take her somewhere safe.

I am having dinner with 5 or 6 people at a long medieval type of table in a stone castle by the sea. It is night time. We look out to sea and see a large black square of material across the ocean. There are people standing up on paddle boards on each corner monitoring the black square. Anne runs out into the ocean. She is dressed in a hessian like hood and cape. She is determined to go out into the ocean to meet God? Something is drawing her to the black material in the sea. She does not care if she drowns. She is totally one eyed. My husband rushes out to her and enters the water. There are large waves. He saves her and brings her back to shore. She tries to go back in again. I am worried Mark might drown but I know he has done the right thing in pulling her away from the draw of the ocean and the black square. It is like Anne is hypnotized and drawn into the ocean at whatever cost. She had lost her will. The feeling of the dream was not so much negative but I was fearful.

I am walking up a step dirt track. I drop my handbag over the side and then realise I too am slipping and maybe I will die. But somehow I don't. I am now at a funeral and am dressed for a funeral. I sit next to a woman who knows the dead person.  There are three other people sitting there on chairs. But I don't know them so they look at me like why are you here? I am now looking for a toilet and find myself in a toilet where the floor is inches deep in water and urine. I am hating it.

I am in a car with my husband, Mark, my daughter and my sister-in-law. We pull over in a housing estate and I realise it is quite nice because there are trees and birds are singing. My husband then decides we are all going back in another direction to where we initially intended to go. I am furious. I am so so angry. I get out of the car and go back towards a shopping center and enter it. I am completely lost in there and can't find where I parked the car. I don't seem to have my phone but I desperately need to contact my husband to find where we parked the car. So now I am angry at him because I really need him in order to find a way out of the labyrinth.

I am at a horse stable. My husband is given a new horse by a woman named Robyn. She also gives him a young mare who is a lot of trouble. She stays close by to make sure the horse doesn't break out of the stall. I'm very cross that we have another useless horse! I am in the stable yard and am so angry as I shovel together piles and piles  of horse poo.
I saw a large black wolf. I wasn't scared. I said to my husband he won't eat the chickens and he distinctly said Yeah! Right!

I’ve been at a conference, or possibly one element of a series of events, and am leaving.
