I recognise Gavin, who has never been my boss but is a relatively senior exec known to me, and he is striding off to reception with his suitcase, in a “beat the rush” kind of way.  I am making my way there more casually, and I meet Steve as we get there together.  The hotel reception looks more like a hybrid bank branch/train station ticket hall, with perhaps half a dozen agents behind cast-iron grate arches handling the requests.  It’s busy but not in a massive way.  Gavin is already near the front of the queue for one of the agents - although he doesn’t look my way or acknowledge me.  Steve is saying that he is going to skip the queues here and head outside to the airport shuttle buses, as he can get a ticket at the airport for the next leg of the trip, and he will get there earlier anyway.  He mentions Dulles, so I deduce we must be in Washington.  I counter that I am going to join one of the queues because, even if it takes a while, once I have my ticket, it doesn’t matter so much how long the airport shuttle takes, as I’ll know I have my seat, whereas Steve will be at risk of a shuttle bus delay and getting to the airport too late for anything.

As a family, we were staying at someone else’s house - it was a fairly large/tall town house type with many rooms.  it was important for me to find a particular toy for the kids to play with, and so I was sorting through some kind of dustin-shaped grey container.  I found the toys, which were small, grey insect-like domes.  I was very pleased with this and went off to find the kids to tell them.

I was in a room with three older women.  I didn’t recognise them.  It didn’t feel like a house so may have been some kind of public building, but the room was quite small. We were discussing leather coats, and how a long one looks good, wears well and is versatile.  One of the women was talking about a brown coat that she had, and I mentioned that I too had had a brown leather coat when younger, and really liked it - and the trenchcoat style that it had.  As I looked down, I saw that I was wearing the coat!  However, it was now looking very worn, with bare patches towards the bottom, through which one could see the lining...  it was basically falling apart.

I am somewhere in an office building making plans to go and visit my customer. As I pack up my stuff, I hear a loudspeaker announcing that there will be a very significant Banking Branch meeting very soon. l recognise the voice of Anona, who used to be my manager when I worked in that Branch before coming to my current role. As I am leaving, I pass a large number of ex-colleagues who are filing into an auditorium, and I realise that this is where Anona’s announcement is taking place. Thinking that they won’t mind if I join in, and it probably won’t take long, I decide to turn around and maybe stand at the back. As I enter, I find that it is a big hall sloping down to a stage on the left, with the entrance in the middle. I therefore turn right and climb the stairs to the back corner. Most seats are taken already, but there are a couple of benches right at back, where the hall flattens out again, so I sit there. I think I will get out my laptop and maybe do some email but when I open my briefcase it's not in there. I have a pretty good view of the stage but also realise that the flat area behind me includes a bed, and there’s someone under the covers who may be looking at me. I turn back to the stage as the speaker starts but when I hear that Matt Hancock is about to make an announcement, I realise that it must be Radio 4 news breaking through into my dream.

I was part of a large gathering - outside but in some sort of stadium / grandstand which may have been cast iron.  I was sort-of with people I knew but decided to sit at the back on the left, rather than nearer the front/middle, where they were gathered.  However, once one of my colleagues noticed this, he said that i couldn’t do that, and that I needed to be upstairs - either because I had some kind of special role in the event, or because of who else was gathering “upstairs”.  I wasn’t particularly happy about this, or sure that I had enough time to find a new seat upstairs, but decided I had no choice.  However, given the open-air nature of things, although I could see a tier of the stand overhead, it was far from clear how to get up there...  I couldn’t see any stairs, for a start.  I decided to walk back to the front along the left hand side, where I found I could go further down a hill... Hoping that this would give me some distance and perspective to see how to get back and “up”.  Once headed down, though, things just seemed to get more crowded and convoluted, and not only could I not see how to reach my target, I had lost where I had come from as well.  I was also now surrounded by strangers who seemed to have know involvement in or knowledge of where I thought I was going.

I am at a train station, and have just bought my ticket.  Within seconds, the train doors have shut and I therefore miss my train. A short while later, the next train to my destination arrives, so I get on and we start moving.  However, a ticket inspector then comes along asking to see my ticket.  I realise that not only do I no longer have it, but that the one I *did* have (briefly) would not be enough as it was valid only for the train that left without me.  I try and explain all this to the inspector, but he unconvinced.  Realising that I cannot show him even the invalid ticket, I can see why he might mistake me for someone trying to get the train without buying any kind of ticket first.  Trying to stay in my usual “polite but firm” mode I resist buying another ticket (and paying the penalty fare) while attempting to think of some evidence I can present.  I start looking at my mobile, thinking that the earlier ticket purchase may be registered in my Apple Wallet, but I can’t tell whether it is there or not - and can’t remember how I paid...

Having retired at 60, after a couple of months I was bought back part-time by my company as some sort of technical consultant. I have now converted full-time into being a salesman and this is my first day.  Many of the people in the office are well-known colleagues from the old days, including some who retired even before me.  The office is incredibly full and busy - and untidy.  Everything seems to be paper-based rather than run via the IT systems I remember and there are multiple bin-bags of documents just inside the door, which also seems to be a major crossroads for people coming in and out.  I often seem to be standing by the bags to let someone in or out as me, my new boss and my closest colleague co-ordinate how I will spend the day and what precisely are my responsibilities.  There is a vague discussion about me capitalising on my customer relationships from the old days but no-one seems to know how realistic this is.  The boss also doesn’t seem particularly pleased to have me there and at one point says “I don’t see why I’m paying so much more for you than for her when I don’t know what you’re going to do”.  I reply that I fully understand that I need to add value to a level commensurate with my pay, otherwise I’ll “just piss off back home”.  This seems to cheer him up considerably.

I was at an ATM drawing some cash.  However, when I got to the shop and got out my wallet to pay, I realised immediately that the money was not in there, as it was too thin (not bulked up when there is a lot of notes).  As I had come straight to the shop from the ATM I really couldn’t work out where the money might have gone in between the two. The shop however was pushing me to pay and getting impatient, so I thought “no problem, I’ll use my debit card instead, then head back to the ATM and see if I can track down the cash”... At this point, I realised that my debit card was missing too - and even worse, my main credit card also.  The shop was of course getting even more impatient but I had stopped caring about whatever it was I was trying to buy and was really worrying about how I was going to sort this out - since the credit card was definitely not involved in the failed ATM visit, and I therefore had had two separate disasters.
set in Iceland and having the image of the landscape around me.
Dream about Oliver Twist, the Charles Dickens book. I remember being in Dickens era London, with everyone dressed for the winter.

being in my house and having to do some cleaning while listening to a talk being broadcast from the computer. I have a big bowl of water and cloth that I am going to use to clean up and for some reason I decide to put my phone in it to clean it. It starts to get hot and make sparks and I need to try and fish it out to switch it off.

based in some kind of big shopping centre or supermarket. I was with my partner and we were walking around doing our food shopping. He needed to go and get some other things, so I had to get ice cream and spent ages in front of a huge standing freezer full of different options. Then I was going to buy a magazine and was standing at the huge display of books and magazines trying to work out what to get. I didn’t recognise any of the books and magazines. They were all in English, but they were all about really strange things. There was a small display of children’s books right in front of me that had a selection of strange books too - I picked up one illustrated book with dinosaurs trying to explain climate change.  A lady came up next to me to look at the books and magazines too. She started talking to me a lot, even though I had never seen her before, and was telling me lots of personal things - like the fact that she was going to the pharmacy to get some cream for her vagina as she had managed to injure herself somehow! She was talking to me all the way around the rest of the shop until I met my partner again. Apparently she was someone who had newly started at my work, though I had never seen her before.

I remember needing to greet someone that I had just met in the street and, because of coronavirus, we weren’t really sure how to do it. We ended up doing a strange dance of some kind. Then I went to get on a big train, which wasn’t particularly busy, but I had to go a really strange way to get to my seat - like climbing in through the window. My friend Pablo (who actually lives in the USA) was there and he came to sit with me. We were sad about something so he was holding my hand and we were just sitting quietly. The train actually ran along the road, with all the car traffic. Sometimes we would have to stop where there was congestion or an accident. I was then still on the train and walking around when I found a room with David Bowie in it dressed as his Goblin King character from the movie ‘the Labyrinth’. He was singing one of the songs and doing the dance that he does in the movie and I wasn’t sure what to do so I just stood and watched. He started to get undressed, but then realised that it was impossible, as the film had only ever captured him in his costume and so there was no way that he could be without it.

It was a big house with a garden out back and front, which was supposed to belong to my friends Angela and Tibor.   I was trying to get my raincoat ready for the rain as it was supposed to be a really wet day. I was dressed in a lot of layers with a big yellow raincoat on top. At this point my parents were there and we were very slowly trying to get ready to go outside.  We needed to clear everything up from the garden before the rain and my mum had left her jackets and boots piled up to air so we needed to collect them up. Someone had left a big handbag outside and I couldn’t work out whose it was and was worried to leave it there.  next we had bought a new hoover for the house and were trying to work out how to put it together. My ex-partner was mostly trying to do this. In the next room, someone who was supposed to be a student of mine (who I didn’t recognise) had set up what was supposed to be a whisky still. It was a very high tech looking thing, with pipes all over, that sat on top of the stove, taking up a lot of the kitchen space.   In the next scene I was tidying the yard at the front of the house, which was also some kind of space for selling secondhand furniture. Some of my possessions were sitting out there alongside my bike, which I had brought with me and which I needed to bring in to the house. I realised that a piece of furniture had gone missing and was worried that it had been sold by the owner of the store. It was a small, white chest of drawers, one that my partner is currently trying to sell.  In the last scene, my student decides to do a small comedy sketch. In the sketch he decides to switch on the hoover, which has not yet been fixed, and part of it starts to hover and zoom around the room so that we all have to take shelter and wait for the battery to run down enough until it finally drops out of the air.

I was in a big venue, where a party was going on. I was there with my friends and family and we were just dancing around and having fun. Although the venue was very formal, the toilets were strangely dirty - I needed to go to the bathroom and walked in to a really run down bathroom, with lots of damage and graffiti and water all over the floor. All of the toilets were squat toilets and I was trying to very carefully manoeuvre over one without stepping in the big puddles on the flooded floor. I was also wearing a really long and heavy dress, which I had to pick up and bunch all around me so that it didn't soak up all of the water. Then I had to try not to pee all over my dress and shoes!

I remember being in a small town somewhere, trying to work out what to do for a last night in the city with my partner and some friends. I think we were supposed to be in Sweden.  I can remember walking around some quiet streets with a small group of people as we tried to decide where to go.  At the l same time I guess I was supposed to be packing my bag, because occasionally I would find my things in some completely different place, like in the gift bag we had given one of our friends.  We eventually went to someone’s house and had a small party there. I remember clearing up and trying to work out which things were ours, to be packed and brought with me. A taxi driver was there, waiting patiently in the background.   We kept realising we had done odd things, like accidentally take two big African wax print fabric cushions from a restaurant.  Everyone was sad that I would be leaving and I wasn’t sure exactly when I would see any one of them again.

I was travelling somewhere - I think I was on the Eurostar then on one of the big SNCF trains in France. I remember it being quiet, with a few people only sitting in the carriages. The inspector started walking through the train and I was rummaging to find my ticket. Then I was on some other kind of transport, like a mix between a boat and a plane. Finally I arrived in this deserted terminal building and had to find the group that I was looking for at the end of the journey. We were supposed to be on some kind of field class and were all gathering to set off out in to the countryside. Everyone had tough outdoor clothing on and big boots and getting impatient as they wanted to get out of the terminal and on the road as soon as possible.

I was in a forest, where apparently I lived with my family. I remember looking around the pale green deciduous forest. Looking up and seeing a network of interconnected vines strung between the trees quite a long way over my head. We were supposed to be eating and it was my job to make the dinner, which I think we were cooking outside and serving at a long table.

Me and a large group of friends were staying in a big town on the coast. it was very busy with a huge tourist infrastructure, all lit up in bright lights at night. We were supposed to be there for some kind of field trip, like a college trip, although we all looked far too old to be at college! We were wandering around the town trying to find something to do and we ended up walking a long way, to this strange venue where a sort of magic / cabaret stage show was happening. We were watching a kind of burlesque escapology act, where several people were tied to large wooden boards standing up on the stage (like then they do knife throwing at the circus). In the finale of the show, something went wrong because one of the boards fell backwards straight on to one of the other performers. She was fine, but the accident triggered some sort of riot, which quickly descended in to chaos. The police arrived and were chasing people and we were trying to work out what to do. It was a really long way to walk back in the dark, especially through all the chaos, and one of my friends, Julia, from school appeared and said she would give me a lift in her car. A small group of us started walking to the car, then I remembered that I had promised Julia (who was apparently two people at this point!) that I would get a lift back with her. Everyone got confused and a bit annoyed about disruption to the plans, as I decided that I needed to go back and find the 'other' Julia.   We managed to get back and we were at our accommodation and I was tying to prepare for an online class that I needed to give some of my own students. As I was setting everything up, a big cat with thick, grey fur, like a lynx, but with a very long tail jumped over the wall. It was very persistently coming towards me and it wanted me to touch its face and hold its front paws. I was a little bit scared that it would attack me if it did, but it didn't. One of my colleagues came out and saw the cat and tried to put it on her lap to sit down. It stayed calm for a few seconds, then dug all of its claws in to her shoulders and legs. We had to wrestle it off of her and put it back over the wall, although all the way through this process it didn't actually struggle or resist.

I was in a bit city of some kind. London. My partner and I spent a lot of time trying to work out how to get somewhere on the underground which was quite busy and which I didn’t recognise the lines of. No one was wearing a mask or anything.  Finally we got to where we were staying, which was in a slightly scary part of town with lots of people hanging around on the street and lots of stuff going on. Groups of guys were cycling around everywhere and making loads of noise. We had to cut through a library complex to get to the house which was in quite a large block of apartments.
needing to organise something - I think a dinner - and really struggling to do so because there were lots of surreal arrangements in place because of COVID.
my friend who has a sewerage problem in her backyard. went onto clients I work with and my kids looking for accommodation.
police informants. I had visions of everyday people walking around with children. Strangely enough I did not have a feeling of danger but watchfulness.  a man with a child's toy.
I was helping a refugee client of mine get food from a foodshare centre. my niece who I had visited the day before and who has post natal depression.
#NAME?

I was visiting a Covid-19 test Clinic, where people were being infected with Covid-19 for tests. They were, or I thought they were, there voluntarily. It was in a basement. Most people were living there in a tight space to get infected through being close to each other. But there were some, including Charlie, who were being made ill purposefully through eating their own, and others, feces. Just when I was about to leave after my visit, I was suddenly pulled by Charlie and forced into this small room where I had to eat feces by someone covid infected and then my own.

It is Christmas, and me and my boyfriend Jason are at my cousins house, it is very nice. My aunt is sitting on the sofa and Jason is trying to put up a bunting. It is too heavy though, I try to help him but it somewhere else, but unsuccessfully. My cousins are coming down and another girl, not family, visits. I however know that girl from my childhood, and she is very happy to talk to me and catch up. She is very cute and sweet, about 12 years old. I ask her a few questions, but at some point she has to leave. We then ‘begin’ Christmas. I leave the house with my boyfriend, who suddenly is Tobi. We walk through this pretty but small town and talk about whether it is okay for a girl in a relationship to be making money going on dates. We end up near a pub and an ice rink, as well as a river. My boyfriend “Tobi” goes to get drinks, I give him a ‘Christmas kiss’, but in that moment I realise I do really not love him. He goes and I start rolling a joint near three girls who I seem to remember having met earlier. I wanted to meet them again and hang out with them. A fourth girl comes and one of the other girls goes in a towel to swim in the ice cold river.

I was together with a lot of my family members, I remember my cousin Jennifer. My immediate family however was a different one than my real family. we were all Jewish and made to leave/being separated by age. I can’t remember what exactly but at some point as I was saying goodbye to my mum, which felt very dramatic, I gifted her a necklace which turned out she was allergic to. But liked it anyways. I then remember someone from my family, I think a great aunt, randomly marrying/celebrating a wedding in what looked like school corridors. The bride was throwing her bouquet intending very much to get it to that certain person. It still ended up with someone else. I then remember being split up, which felt sad. I, with a few members of my family in the same age group, had to leave to ‘camps’. I remember being with people in like a school reception where I arrived and got myself a bad coffee. Then together with a few other people we were looking for a sleeping spot/some mattresses. I remember we found some and tried to get the best/largest one. They were very dirty though and I remember thinking to myself I will use my cloth towel as a bed sheet. I didn’t know how to submit my weekly column I was writing.

me being in Kyiv and holding the Kyiv Jewish Forum, which I am currently organising at work. Instead of the online conference with political leaders, it, however, was small in a school like stage room with not many people. The room was full however, the President of the organization seemed content regardless. After that my boyfriend and me went out on the street and ended up in Moscow at a farewell party for Silver Apples. The party was cool decorated and many cool persons were there as well as quite a few of my old uni friends. It was a sad atmosphere although more in a club like setting. I told people that Silver Apples was supposed to play at mine and my boyfriends wedding. Just before me and my boyfriend left the party, he told me that one of the bartenders was really mean to him and kind of pushed him. Once me and my boyfriend left the 'party' we ended up in supermarket and the bartender followed us first pretending casual before hitting and punching my boyfriend. I was very protective and punched and pushed back.   Next thing me and my boyfriends friends are in a soft play area for adults. We are doing drugs, and I am telling my boyfriend to dress warmer. At some point one of his friends, asks me to go to a certain area of the play area and we together run there. My muscles and legs feel very funny and it makes me worry a little bit. We climbed down a laaarge wooden ladder and I put my new phone in my jeans' back pocket, and I worried it would fall out when climbing down the lader.

- A firework show was going on nearby but people I was currently with did not want to go so I ended up going on my own. Arriving at the show, it was outside and several seating rows where there, I passed my grandma and a friend in a row, as well as next to them the parents of my best friend Valerie - I sat further in the front of the show - there was a carrousel ship on the 'stage' - after the firework went on the carrousel started going playing bad taste carnival music with lots of people on the boat, I remember covid safety going through my mind  - I anyways joined people on the boat but accidentally fell down at some point, slipped out of the boat and when trying to get back on I managed to end up under the boat and as the boat was moving up and down slowly I was about to being crushed although I tried to escape - the emergency button was hit when I got tight and I was safe, but also very embarrassed - walking around a lot being with different friends in different flats and locations - I sent a text to my friend Eva from my hometown on Instagram thanking her for the wine, It was sent in accident however and was meant for my old school friend Amelie - At some point then I remember living again with my 'ex' step brother Daniel and he suddenly got lost so I was looking for him everywhere and my best friend Valerie and her sister Carina helped me - At some point we found him at a train station eating a whole plastic bag of spaghetti bolognese, it was very disturbing and gross, he also had more food next to him - I took the plastic bag away from him, took a little bit spaghetti out of it and left it for him - I then went back to valerie to her flat, she was sitting in the bathtub and i was talking to her about her dating partner and how it is going and she answered very pessimistically that it wont be ending anywhere serious, he is away in Manchester now anyways - I was asking whether they were still talking and whether they would see once he would come back and she said yes so I struggled to understand why she is negative about it as I was telling her I am sure it is all still good

I had a brother. he died and somehow, we inherited some of his royalties or similar  - there were clashes in spreading the royalties among family members and arguments occurred - at some point suddenly I was outside on my own behind a school in the dark - I was aware of me having had my hair dyed just recently, blue highlights - being outside there, I got raped. However, this was not a painful or traumatic or something that felt like actually in the moment of happening - a little later Jason, my boyfriend, and me were out on that same street in the dark behind the school - We wanted to head home - the quickest way was through the school, entering from the back entry - however after having walked through the school, they didnt let us exit through the front door due to a covid one way system - I remember being angry and thinking to myself that this causes a 20 min diversion in the dark in an area where I got raped which leaves many people exposed to danger in an attempt to create safety against covid - I was thinking like I often do: Are these consequences worth it? Whats more dangerous, not having a one way system or girls being sent 20 mins through the dark where I have been raped - my boyfriend and me try and find our way through the streets, I flipped out and ran panickly ahead trying to find the way - The next thing I can remember is us crossing a football field where some young boys are playing and then I suddenly was at my old flat where I lived with my mum after my parents divorced - However, my grandparents lived there and they have given me photos of me as a young child looking like a Russian doll which made me feel proud of my Russian-German family history and background - I then suddenly arrived at a school like building and was there with Amelie, an old school friend - It was a sort of teacher telling students the grades day and we tried to find our French teacher - we couldnt find the teacher and at some point just sat around - Monique, a close friend of mine who I know since I am a baby, was suddenly there and I drifted into an imagination where we both were lying naked at the beach being taken photos of  - looking through the pictrues afterwards and picked the one where my breasts looked the least tiniest, not as super tiny as on all others, and intended it to my boyfriend - being at the hairdressers where I got my blue highlights redone and remember me saying " Blue highlights attract rape"
people with horse’s heads.
I was trying to help a friend transport a vehicle back to the UK but people who were supposed to be assisting kept going missing.

I recall I was kind of dating a friends son - who must now be in his mid 20s. I’m not too sure if I was dating him or more taking care of him . He occupied a corner room in some shared student housing which had triangular prism windows looking out onto ancient mounds of stones which were illuminated of an evening.  I recall feeling he was extremely unhappy. That he needed love & support.  We left the room and were walking outside. Indeterminable place. Lots of young people around us.  He just collapsed to the floor. As though he’d allowed and even willed all life to be taken from him.

I was pregnant and close to giving birth. But I could not have a natural birth. I have no idea why. So I had to visit a clinic where the doctor was not present. I had to discuss the procedure with the receptionist. It transpired I would be giving birth within hours. My partner was not present. I found my parents. They didn’t seem too happy I was pregnant. I realised I had nothing prepared for the baby. I knew it was a girl. I remember thinking I needed a papoose and that a buggy could wait. Even though my partner was absent he informed me the baby must be named Holly. Which I found odd as this is not a type / style of name he would ordinarily choose. I was alone starting to go into an induced labour. I was being fearful of the pain and the future.

It was my daughter’s birthday. She was working in a city. I arrived with a mass of helium filled balloons. Her boss, a woman in her late 40s, requested I pay her £18 in order to display the balloons. I spent a long & embarrassing time counting through change in my purse. In my head I begrudged the boss and her request but kept quiet so as not to upset my daughter on her birthday. I then remembered I had some £10 notes slotted away in another compartment of my purse - which I gave to hear.  As I left and was walking down the street I was harassed by a guy wearing brown polyester slacks and a plastic chimpanzee full head mask.
A girl aged about 5

I was part of a rebel group in the forest. It seemed like an exercise but it turned into a real situation with people getting shot. Military caught us eventually on the roads next to the woods. I was concerned that we had to get a specific type of seed - reebeck instead of rudbeckia. We also let someone go earlier in the dream who we had caught.
Loads of numbers and calculations I couldn't quite get my head around
Lots of talking around me but I couldn't quite hear what was being said.

There was a hurricane and lots of panic about the people out in a long golf buggy type vehicle. One person had to be put in a concrete cupboard and was told to stay there. I was there but it felt like i was doing something not quite right as I was always not where I should be. I was fine but never quite in the thick of it. Everyone in the dream was known to me.

I was in my father's old sheltered housing complex but his bungalow had changed. My dad was not there but we needed top get to Mass. I went to the bathroom but he had made that into a shower room only with no toilet. I went into a cupboard and instantly saw a huge bath taking up most of the room. I was quite taklen aback by this but there was a toilet jammed up against the bath so I was able to go to the toilet. Second dream involved two teenage boys in a swimming pool in a huge old disused place. I think I was one of the teenage boys - I knew where I was going. I told the other to swim right to the bottom of the pool and follow me as I knew where I was going and what specifically we were looking for. We swam down and through a long corridor and came up in a tiny bedroom with a huge supply of spinach and I knew there was other vegetables in other places. I was very excited about this. The small bedroom also had clothes and a dishevelled bed so it definitely belonged to someone else. The other boy was exhausted; there was something about a drop of water which was very significant. He had to fall asleep as he was exhausted. Next scene I was with an odd group of people at night-time taking them to a big hall to eat. It felt like a celebration. Again I was the one showing the way and checking we had everyone together including the guy in the wheelchair and a small child. I was excited but also slightly apprehensive. Looked for teenage friend but he had disappeared. Hoped he had set up the food - spinach.

Huge rain. Children had to wear plastic bubble suits to keep dry and I was worried they would suffocate. Eventuyally I was allowed to partly unzip one so some air could get in but that was no good either as the air was polluted. I felt very helpless
A washing machine had broken down. There was soap and water everywhere.
Throughout the night dreamt about Dennis Nielsen murders.
A wedding where things go wrong.
I was doing something mundane/ real-life - like. Suddenly, a wall of lava approaches me - the wall of a room suddenly closes in on me, only the wall is made of lava.
very random. There were a lot of people - old and new friends, and faces I didn't recognise, I did a lot of things.

I was at a big gathering/ party with family and friends. We were all outside in a big garden, with the older generation on one table and the younger on another - I was in the latter. Were eating and drinking and catching up, when suddenly someone tells me my ex is coming. I went to the gate, which was at the end of a long stretch of road, to let in him and we awkwardly drove down in his car to where everyone else was. I was drinking a lot and started smoking and, after two cigarettes, began coughing. This freaked me out because I remembered smoking always messes up my throat and, especially, during Covid I shouldn't do that to my lungs. Then, I realised that there were at least 50 people at the party and that there is a rule of 6 at the moment. I ignored that and pretended I was fine and carried on talking to everyone on my table.

one of my friends saying that I'm always late to things and I said that I'm not, it's just that a lot of my other friends are never on time so I've stopped trying to be on time, too. She responded that that still isn't an excuse for being late when meeting her because she's always on time and I said that I've only been late to meeting her once and that wasn't even my fault, but because I had to wait for some of our other friends. We were supposed to meet later that evening and she said that we'll see if I make it on time then. In the evening, I started getting ready but had a long shower, then my hair took forever to dry because it was cold and my contact lenses wouldn't stay in. My parents reminded me that I'll be late but I said that I need to finish getting ready. Finally, I was ready when, again, one of contacts fell out and so I had to find new ones and put them in. I was aware that everyone else was already there and I was the only one running late. I was going to walk to the restaurant we were meeting at but, since I was already so late, my mum offered to drive me. We left our house

I was with people in a castle at a party (the setting was modern times, we had just been invited to a party at a castle). I had made some new friends, especially with one girl, and the two of us decided to go into the town to get some beer. However, when I left to head down, she was gone, so I went on my own. There were a lot of people and a huge crowd trying to leave the castle to go into town, as well, so I had to wait a while. It was quite stuffy and uncomfortable, especially because everyone around me was with friends and I couldn't find anyone I know. Finally, I went into the town and ran into my friend John. He was drunk and got playful; he's also quite tall and I'm not, and I got scared he'll knock me over by accident. We danced around a well for a while.

I was at home, with my parents and sister, and someone knocked on the door. I felt suspicious toward them but it was daytime and I opened the door. The man burst in and started stealing things. I went outside and saw that he had a partner, who also came in and began to steal our belongings. My family was in shock but just stood there watching. I tried to shout at the burglars and tell them to leave, they ignored and continued. I tried dialling 911 but forgot the number. Eventually, I dialled 999 but an automated response answered the phone and couldn't understand what I needed. I called a couple of times and still the communication failed. Meanwhile, the burglars continue to take things out of the house and into the vehicle. I begged them to at least leave my laptop and they did. So, I called the local police. A friend from uni suddenly turned up and started speaking in a friendly way to the burglars. I tried to secretly warn her against them but then she walked away. By the time the police arrived, the men had left.  Later that day, I went to my friend's house. Her dad had just collapsed so I called 911 and this time a person answered straight away. A female paramedic arrived without a mask, but I was too worried to say anything. She checked up on my friend's dad and said he had simply fainted. Then, she left.

I had moved into my new flat and started my new job. I got ready for work, put on my mask and walked to the underground station. I was running late, so I was rushing. When I arrive at the station, there were a lot of people and everyone is wearing a mask. We all take the stairs down to the platform for the underground train and suddenly people aren't wearing a mask. Suddenly, I realise that I'm not going to work but for an interview. I bump into someone (who I had a crush on) from my degree, which I just completed, and we talk for a bit. Then, a few people get into a fight and I move away, and the person from my degree moves in the other direction and our interaction ends. I felt anxious when I got down to the platform due to people's failure to wear masks and when the fight broke out, I experienced even further fearful feelings.

I was at/ around my university in London. At first, I was with a friend called Emily and we went to see some outside theatre performances, which were pretty bad and in which the main character was played by a girl from my old school who I dislike. In the audience, I saw at old crush and when Emily asked me about him I told her his first name. She really wanted to know his last name but I blanked and said I think it begins with O. We then headed towards the main uni building and I got really hungry so decided to get some food. Emily said she'll do the same and opted for a uni cafe because it's cheaper. This annoyed me and I said I would go to another place because I wanted something nicer. Emily sat outside of the cafe to wait for me and I walked off, and started to be quite angry with how hungry I was. I remembered that I don't have my hand sanitiser because I'd lent it to my sister and didn't ask for it back and got annoyed. I thankfully bumped into another friend and complained to her about how Emily again would only get food from cheap places and I told her I forgot my hand sanitiser. She lent me hers and went with me to buy food.

My future flatmate realised that her earnings were less than what she thought. Our rent is split up so that she pays slightly more and I pay slightly less, to account for different earnings. she told me that she had calculated her income wrong, which means that we would have to split the rent evenly. My pay doesn't allow me to cover half of the rent while also having enough money left for other things, so I was mad and told her so. I also told her that her constant flakiness was really bothering me. Then, I felt guilty about my reactions and told her that I was sorry that I had gotten angry. She forgave me and we patched things up.

I was at my university, giving a tour to some family members along with another girl doing the same. We hung out in one of the common rooms for a bit. Then, I was in a play at uni and was trying to sneak into someone's dressing room because I felt they were hiding/ lying about something. I managed to sneak in but didn't find anything. Finally, we were at my house and a big group of us was hanging out. We were dancing and kept on knocking vases over and I kept on moving them so they don't get knocked over. I also struggled to understand the dance that the whole group was doing.
I ran into a girl from my old school and we got into an argument. I remember telling her what I don't like about her and how she is so fake etc.
I was in Fast and Furious with my sister.

I was back at Citibank talking to a few colleagues. Everyone was wearing black or grey. Kelly's husband Frank came in wearing a black turtle neck, asking where Kelly was. He was handsome and charismatic as I'd been told he was but when he smiled he had crooked teeth with big gaps.  That was a real surprise. I went to look for Kelly and she was around the corner talking with Kevin my old colleague at Beneficial Finance back in 1990! She had changed the colour of her hair from blonde to brown/red and it was longer. Apart from that she looked exactly the same as she did 17 years ago.

I was in England with a group of people and there was something supernatural going on. There were bits of paper falling from the sky like snowflakes and it made sense to all of us because of all the strange things that were going on around us. I think my two young sons were there too. We were all living/hiding in a little house tucked in underneath in a bigger house. Then I was walking in the red light district in Amsterdam. Still part of the same strange supernatural nature experience (there was something with water as well) but as we walked past the clubs I noticed the doors were very colourful and childlike, almost like they were made from lego bricks  and there were two doors on each club. I noticed that the doors on the left all had my name on them and some phrase to encourage me to enter. I had no desire to enter a sex club and just saw it as annoying marketing. I had a mission to get on with and kept walking.

I had a lucid dream. It was a dark afternoon with very cloudy skies, almost like twilight but it was only 2.53pm. I was working in my office and had my youngest son at home. I knew I had to leave at 3pm to pick up my eldest son from school. I fell into that panicky lucid dream state where you know you're asleep but you can't open your eyes. I could see a dark shadow fall across my closed eyelids and heave male breathing to my left. I asked the presence if it was death. I decided that I didn't have time to be scared because I had to do school pick up. I told it to go away and fought it with strong energetic intent. I could then open my eyes and it was gone but it had re-arranged the house a bit including changing the sliding doors to the living room and making a new manhole in the ceiling that was letting in sunlight.  I could see paintings up there like in an old-fashioned attic you see in American movies. I got really annoyed that the presence had done that because I had to get to school. In an instant the changes were reverted back to normal and I walked out the door. It was already dark outside and raining. I was standing in a big car park. I was getting in my car when I heard a man speak loudly on a mobile phone. I turned around and realised it was James' brother Robert. He must be here to visit James who was asleep in bed. I got in the car and started driving. Traffic was terrible and I realised it was already 3.23 so Ethan would probably have been taken to after school care. I was worried that he would be really upset and worried that I hadn't picked him up yet. I started driving into the busy traffic and could see a Coles truck at the lights.

I was on holidays with my boyfriend James. We were staying at a resort that was built out of timber, very ramshackle and on a very steep hill, like a mountain. There were lots of little stairs and people moving and sitting around. It was quit hard to get around and I was very mindful of social distancing and not wanting to be judged by others to be too close. It felt really stressful. James was still in our room and I was out trying to find a nice spot for us to have sundowners. I felt pressured to get things right. I had to move past people on my way down the stairs and finally found two nice outdoor chairs amongst some greenery for us to sit at. When I called James to tell him, thinking that I'd done well, he was upset with me because we had to hurry up and find some art exhibitions or other cultural events to go to because we weren't getting any cultural exposure or growth since Covid. He sounded quite annoyed with me which made me feel even unhappier and stressed because I hadn't gotten it right (again).

I was with my sons. It was in a busy city with lots of traffic and people. We were leaving somewhere and for some reason my youngest son travelled in an another car with strangers. My eldest son and I got out of our car at a traffic light at a busy crossroads. My eldest son said he saw the car my youngest son was in and that he was getting dropped off at the tech shop about 500 metres away. We pressed the button to cross the busy intersection in order to go to where my youngest son was. I was holding a newspaper with an interesting op ed piece on perfume review. We were walking past a very bright shop like those make up and perfume shops at the airport. I decided to quickly pop into that shop on our way to finding my youngest son. The ladies were very welcoming but didn't really know what I was asking and I felt myself getting more and more anxious and feeling guilty for being in a shop while I should be getting my young son. They put me in a chair and put a horrible ugly blonde wig on me and started cutting it. Nothing to do with my 'quick' perfume sample question I walked in with. I wanted to leave but didn't want to upset them at the same time. I felt myself getting really anxious.

In London for an event with my mum. Walking through London to get to an event, we were late so my mum goes on ahead and I get there later. I am wearing a long blue dress and there is a steep staircase in the building. There are other people there
a new person starting my job and training them. data protection and the GDPR.

My sister is heavily pregnant and my mum and I are in a room with her. The baby is early as the due date is not for another 2 weeks. We are waiting for my brother in law to arrive. The room is somewhere I don't recognise but there is a midwife who comes to check if my sister is ready to go into labour.

I was working in a dark room. I had one large monitor and it was very bright. I was reading an email from someone and one of my work colleagues came into the room. We spoke briefly, it was amusing and she left. I went back to what I was working on.
I was a student on a University campus with other students and it was before the pandemic. Can't remember where the campus was.
lush landscape like in Tasmania.

I dreamt of the names of places in the city which were whirly blown wheels which moved across a flat surface silently on their own an sometimes moved from me slightly touched with my finger, I guess, which wasn’t very obvious. I could have blown them.

food, meeting my new boss and we talked about how I am progressing and I wondered whether she had contacted the client and talked about how he is finding the classes with me. people living in small rooms in cafes using the bathrooms and shower facilities of the cafe. I thought this to be convenient as you would get to know people easily, but I also realized that due to the pandemic it could be now a lovely tranquil place to live in.

Somewhere in rural Spain. I am traveling with another friend. We travel with public transport, a Bus, and we end up in a small hotel. A woman is showing us the dark room with two separate beds. She asks us to collect the hair that we are losing every day in a paper bag and fill in a form for each of it. Because it’s for a good cause, I do it. On the first day I fill the form in, on the second, i only collect the hair and on the third day, just before the time that we have to leave, I remember that i still have to fill in the form for today, the third day and yesterday. However, when I look at the form it seems too much work and I finally decide that I won’t fill it in and that the first one will have to do. We are waiting for the owner before we can leave and I am worried, because it’s already in the afternoon . How  would we get to our next destination which is many kilometers away. There is no train station here and if there was a bus, it would probably leave to our new destination  only once per week and it would surely leave in the morning rather than in the afternoon. Should we ask the young fellows who pick us up to drive us to the station to drive us the couple of hundred kilometers to our next destination? But that would be too far. We could not really ask them to do so and how could we ask them and would that bring us in danger? There is still some waiting time left before we meet the landlady and I have to go to the bathroom. She is there in one of the cubicles, but I can’t really recognize her. She looks completely different. She looks young, thin, black hair. However, she recognizes me. She apologizes for the bad condition that the bathroom is in, inexplicable to her how it had happened, because a wall between two  cubicles has disappeared as well as the doors of these. As the other cubicles  have closed doors, I am prepared to use one of the toilets openly visible to everyone, even in sight of the two young guys who hang around at a table to wait to drop us off later at the station. They chat with each other and don’t pay attention anyway. So I pull down my pants and have a quick wee. I go back to the room and my fellow female traveler has already packed her super heavy and bulky bag. I am wondering why her luggage is so heavy. She is proud she has packed it already and so timely. This would speed up our departure. I am starting to pack mine, I am traveling light with s small rucksack, and think about the purpose of the hair collection. I continue to worry about how to get to the destination. I have heard it’s a nice small city and it is conveniently located to reach other destinations from there, probably by bus and train. It will make our lives easy to continue the next part of the trip. But how would we, if we got there at all, find a place to stay? We would surely arrive there after dark...

I was entering a very old theatre. I went there because I was singing in a choir concert. The theatre hall was empty when I entered it from the top. I walked down the stairs on the left side towards the seats for the audience. I remembered now that I had been here before performing in another concert and I remember that it had been difficult or that I had felt unsafe leaving my belongings at a supposedly safe place.  I had not trusted for them to be locked away somewhere far away from the stage. While I am contemplating where I could hide my belongings  before getting changed into my black clothes some other choir members appear and sit down randomly in seats many in a distance to others. When I feel it is time to find the change room, I decide to put the dog that I brought into a cardboard box not too far away from the stage but in a different room to be safe as I couldn’t bring it anywhere without complaints by others for the inappropriateness of having brought him in the first place. I know he will be fine in the box and I can retrieve him after the concert. When getting changed somewhere in the labyrinth of the theatre, I realized, I had forgotten to bring a black top. I only brought annoyingly a very white one. I know I would stand out in the choir which would be unacceptable.  I am finding other jackets in boxes which seemed to be abandoned, some suitable some not. I find a smoking jacket which I quite like. When I enter the change room I hear the rumor that the conductor had lost his smoking somewhere in the theatre. I check my box and can see the conductor stick in there and realize it must be his box. He had already dressed in a tight dark violet suit and is quite happy with the solution. I still pass  the smoking to an assistant which he takes, saying thanks but the conductor being still very happy with the way he looks will probably not use his smoking jacket.  I eventually decide to keep on my black winter jacket which unfortunately has some fur attached to the hood and will most definitely be way too hot on stage. But I think this must do. I am hurrying  back to the hall and the audience had arrived and the concert was just about to start. I was pushing myself through the audience with my handbag looking still for a safe place for it but time was running out. I rush embarrassed with my inappropriate look to my spot to sing. We strangely sang with the back to the audience.  At the end of he concert when most people had disappeared I went on the search for the dog in the box. But I couldn’t remember where it was. It wasn’t where I had thought I had left it behind. I open many boxes even in rooms where I was pretty sure I hadn’t entered before but I can’t find him anywhere. I feel so bad because a friend had entrusted the dog in my care. I try anxiously to find the dog, trying to hear a sound, a scratch or a bark but then the dog had probably fallen asleep with the lack of oxygen inside the box. I am thinking of giving up and in to the disaster that this day had been...

I was living in my childhood home. The sky was grey. I was talking to my best friend T her mother had passed away. I also talked to her father. Then I was on some kind of art school trip. I was wearing my old school uniform and I was with my two school friends Nat and Manny. Manny, Nat and I bought tickets to an exhibition in the Gallery we were visiting. The gallery was in a large garden that looked a lot like Wisley Garden. We met the art teachers and they told us that they wanted us to paint. We painted for a bit then snuck off to the exhibit. His museum was about chemistry. There was one room which had dark walls and a kind of red skylight. The room had an empty bathtub. I noticed at this point that I didn't look like myself, I looked like the character Elanor from the Good Place, played by Kirsten Bell. My museum was a pyramid with a giant statue of me on top. There was a TV on one side on a small metal and glass stand and there were a lot of chairs facing the TV. getting a coffee. It was a cold brew coffee and the woman serving me had a head scarf.
