In hospital, having tests, canulas in my arms, ECG wires on chest arms and legs, blood samples taken, and X Ray's taken. Its sunset outside the hospital window, and the screen curtains around the bed are white, with blue and green sea waves on them as a repeated pattern. When I'm back from the X Ray's, the doctor visits my bed and tells me I have cancer. The feelings I have are worry of the unknown, and fear before the diagnosis, and after the diagnosis great dread, devastation and fear.

driving to a place where it was like I would have to work but it also felt like a holiday destination. There were familiar people whose faces I didn't see. I felt like they were students, colleges and friends. I felt like I was torn between helping my students and making the adults happy.
I was at a place that felt like school. My colleague Cathy was trying to give me something like a cake or dessert. there was some drama over it.

I remember walking down the stairs and a student ran towards a sandpit, I ran after him. It turned out it was a student I taught 16 years ago.   My dream jumped to me still on holidays. I had the feeling that I was with people from work.  We had little devices we had to answer and communicate using these devices. I was out walking on the streets,  I remember there was a small child in a tree that would hop from tree to tree. Somehow I was at a beach, I could feel people around me. I put my feet in the water and it was lovely and warm. A youngish man who I felt like was my dad came to put his feet in the water too. He jumped the wave the water makes as it hits the shore. I laughed and asked why he jumped such a small wave. He walked further into the water and jumped again, this time he went under. We were back on the shore and he was soaking wet. We were all going out and because he was soaked I worried he wouldn't be able to come and I felt annoyed by what he'd done. My husband who I didn't see but felt was there said he had spare clothes. They both left and when they came back my dad had dry clothes. We started walking, I felt people leaving me. I looked at my device and the options I had. I was then sitting in a room with my husband. I couldn't see him but I knew he was there. We talked about tattoos. Then he drew a picture and we decided to tattoo it on me. He started tattooing. I fell asleep. I was out looking for something to do. I wanted to go to a beach dance party/ rave but didn't know if I should go. When I looked at my device I saw the tattoo. It was a bit bloody and very light. I thought it looked odd. I felt the presence of some people from work who were trying to figure out what they were going to go. I felt that some were going to go to the rave. My device showed me there were different types of raves available. I couldn't decide. I was alone again, people had left. I looked up and it was if I was lying on the ground. A man's face appeared and I felt it was my husband. The man had curly hair, the sun was filtering through the tree behind him. It felt like it was a beautiful day. I remember thinking to myself, I've missed your curls as I ran my hands through his hair. I was alone again, but it was still sunny. I felt guilty because I knew my real life husband never had curly hair. I was worried he'd find out that I still thought of another man. It was afternoon again and I still couldn't decide where I wanted to go. Apart from the part where it was sunny, the weather was overcast.

I was using an app that would pair me up with a Spanish speaking person who could teach me Spanish close by. I found a guy who lived on the next corner. On my way home I saw a car broken down on the side of the motorway. The car belonged to the person who lived next corner. As I drove past I asked if someone was coming to help. It was actually another neighbour. He called out he was ok and that he'd see me for our date later.  I remember having difficulty getting to the location I was meant to meet this person. When I finally got there, the person I thought was going to teach me Spanish was actually my neighbour who had broken down. He asked me if PQ was ok with me dating other people. very confused because as I was only there to learn Spanish. When I figured out what was going on, I asked if his partner knew he was seeing other people. staying around for a few drinks.

I was at an obstacle course / water party thing with my fiancé where we did a race on rubber rings, down a slide, surrounded by loads of people in the water. feeling happy with how my body looked in a bikini.  Went to meet a new contact about a job. Turned out he was running multiple companies . He wanted my help with marketing. I had to go into a big office space to meet him . feeling good in my work clothes. He agreed for me to work for them but we hadn’t discussed terms.   I then invited him round for a cup of tea and my grandparents were there. My grandad discussed work with this man and we ate porridge and pastries.   Then I was in New York on a boat but couldn’t go on land. I was saying how much I’ve always wanted to see New York. The boat was going to Greece so next I was on a Greek island with old school friends in a place with beautiful blue water. I kept wanting to eat lots of food. There were some sexual elements when I was with men. Then I was in an underground labyrinth of caves on a Greek island and suddenly in a film about tracking down criminals who were using the caves for bad purposes.

I was on holiday in Iceland or somewhere Scandinavian and there was lots of interesting geothermal activity. Then I was swimming around with strangers and then there was a big tidal wave we had to hold our breath for. I shouted to hold your breath and then went under. I was ok and managed to hold my breath for long enough. Afterwards I was swimming around looking for family or friends and I felt distressed. Then I was swimming around a big indoor room filled with fish tanks and I was swimming around to see if the fish were ok. Then I was back at school/uni and my classmates weren’t engaging with me and we were meant to be helping each other do the work - it was related to poetry. Then I was having tea with a student and their dad and eating chocolate, while we worked through the exercises.

I was part of a group endurance run event where we had to run 5 miles at a time, with a break between and do it five times. So a marathon effectively.  I hadn’t done any training and I felt really unprepared, I couldn’t find my headphones, my phone wasn’t charged, I was late to the starting line and I wasn’t wearing the right clothes. I kept getting distracted by things when I was meant to be getting dressed and ready to take part and line up with everyone else. I then was in a film watching the main character (I wasn’t physically in the film, it was like I was a ghost or presence hovering next to the character during the film). At one point she was writing things down but I can’t remember what she was writing now and I can’t remember what was happening in the film

Was with lots of people. Was out partying with old school friends, going to pubs and bars. I ended up talking to one friend who had been through a traumatic event in childhood and I told her I had too and that I understood. She then ran away and I started to run after her but couldn’t catch up because of my shoes. I felt sad and was alone. I went into a pub even though I was supposed to be making my way to the nightclub which was a fair walk away. I made friends with people in the pub and time was going by quickly. The pub had its own climbing wall and some guys were showing me that I had to do it before I left. It was nearly 2am and I still hadn’t got to meet my university friends in the nightclub. I looked at my phone and I had lots of voicemails and I started crying because I couldn’t get to see my friends. Then it turned out my boyfriend was in the pub I was in, looking for me, he just hadn’t seen me. The feelings I had throughout this dream were ones of pure enjoyment and freedom - to be having a good time with friends - and at times, despair and sadness that I had missed out and got left behind. It was like I had actually gone back in time 10 years to when I was at university, and young and carefree.

I was in a big mansion in a sunny exotic place abroad with my university friends. We had been there a week and it was at the end of the week we were going to have a party so we ordered shopping but then we had too much food and drink to eat.  At one point I looked out the window and there was a beautiful swimming pool and swim up bar below but I couldn’t go to it because it was too far.

I was in a massive hotel/haunted house with my mum and there were giant lions about to attack us so we climbed out the window and tried to escape. I remember trying to throw stuff at the lions so they would leave. Then I was on a tropical island walking around with a guy, I was in a bikini but I felt body confident. We were walking along a very long beach which went round in a loop and we were trying to get back to the start but there was loads of distractions. We decided to try and swim across the bay to get back to the start but the shoreline was full of rubbish and things in the sea.

my fiancé’s cousin had committed suicide. We had been told by his dad. I recall that before we received the news, I was at home and my house was in a terrible mess. There was clutter everywhere in every room. I remember crying and feeling devastated by the news and trying to analyse why he had committed suicide. I tried to comfort my fiancé‘s sister but she didn’t want to be hugged. I recall questioning if I was dreaming in the dream - “This must be a dream, it can’t be real”

I missed a flight to Corfu because I had to go to my fiancé’s grandparents house  - Was flying - I argued with and fell out with my mother in law because I was being blunt about death - i said “if it happens it happens”. She was upset because she thought you can control things like that  - getting to Corfu/or an Italian island and running around sobbing because I felt alone, I wasn’t together with my fiancé - Met up with an old colleague who was waxing lyrical about being given two amazing job choices, I felt happy for her but internally I felt jealous of her success because I wasn’t having any  - Saw a couple of dogs fight, couldn’t stop it, wasn’t nice

At my friends parents place. I am staying with them with another large group of people including my friend. At one point I am in their kitchen, making food? Or packing the dishwasher? It is evening There is a woman in my room with her daughter who I know to be working for me. In the dream she is from another country and is very shy. She does not join our party. I can see her through a window with her daughter. The don’t see the party or other people but just know that the party happened and other people were there. I can see a tray of margaritas and know that everyone was drinking a lot at the party. It is morning. There is snow just outside the door, lots of thick bright white snow. I can see a large mountain covered in snow right next to the house. I am looking outside the kitchen door. I feel excited. Someone gets up late and I tell them that they have missed the snow. I can see the mountain outside and the snow is now patchy and melting. I tell them to hurry if they want to see it. I have to get a plane home. I cannot fit all my clothes in my suitcase and have to decide what to leave behind. I decide to give my friend my clothes and leave them in a pile. I let the woman who has been working for me know she can select any items so wants before I give them to my friend. She seems too shy to do this and I try to encourage her. She says she won’t be able to wear them at home and they will be wasted on her but I can see she would like them. I give her some pencils for her daughter. At the same time I am aware that I have to catch my flight soon and need be there 3 hours beforehand. I don’t remember what time my flight is and I keep thinking I need to check my ticket to find out but I don’t do this and feel stressed that I don’t know the time of the flight.

I am at the house of my parents in law. I am at the shops with my friend. We are trying to find jackets for our daughters. I am looking at the sizes and asking my friend what would fit. I pick up a few different jackets, her daughter is suddenly there and tries on the jacket, it fits, she is no longer in the dream. I then go to find a jacket for my daughter and look at different colours. I find one in her size. I am driving into the driveway of my house. I am reversing. I have the jacket in a bag. I am on the back veranda. It is dusk and I am looking over the back garden. My husband arrives. He has brought home a new wife. I am unhappy, it is a surprise to me but in the dream I know that I have agreed to this arrangement. I love my husband so I want it to work. I am in the kitchen it is my in laws house again. My mother in law is preparing a meal, I am on the other side of the bench to her. My husbands new wife is there helping to prepare the meal. She looks like someone I know and dislike in real life. Someone else is also there but they are a vague blur and I can’t remember them. I feel threatened and sense that my mother in law is uncomfortable with the situation. My mother in law says she wants to put the salad in the red bowl. She says the red bowl is in the dishwasher. The dishes in the dishwasher are dirty. I know that my mother in law would not ask me for that bowl if she knew it was dirty as she wouldn’t would to trouble me. I wash the red bowl quickly so she doesn’t see as I want her to have the bowl she wants. there is a greasy film on the bowl. I am in the bedroom I am packing my things. My husband comes in and rubs my back. I tell him that I am leaving and can’t continue with our agreement. My husband is upset and tries to convince me to stay in the relationship. I tell him that I love him but I don’t like his new wife and didn’t realise how hard it would be. I am at a sports carnival with my bag I took from the house. Inside is the jacket I bought for my daughter. The sports carnival is in the primary school that I went to as a child. My children are around somewhere. I speak to another parent but I am distracted. I am looking for someone or trying to do something but I am not sure what. I am at my parents. I feel relieved and comfortable.

I’m in my house that I rent from my father. In the front garden some workers have dug large holes and are in the process of installing hot water systems in the holes. My father has not told me this was planned. I feel annoyed and go outside to see what is happening. I speak to my father and the worker in charge. A young male worker walks up to to a young female worker and demands she does something. He is rude, contemptuous and aggressive. I tell the young worker he should apologies and ask politely. The worker storms off the site without saying anything. The senior worker and my father are annoyed with me for disrupting the work. I am then in my house and the work outside has not been completed. I feel anxious. I have gone to my colleagues house who has just had a baby. Someone is at her house and lets me in to wait. When my colleague arrives she is hot and tired and with two friends who are concerned about her and suggests she rests and eats grapes. She is pregnant and it is before she has had the baby. I want to ask my colleague if I did the right thing telling the worker to be polite to the girl. I can’t ask her because she is so tired. My colleague wonders why I am at her house before her and who let me in.  I am later at work and in an office environment. My colleague is in a cubicle a few places over. A man comes and asks me where she is. I direct her. I then hear shouting and look over. My colleague is shouting at him for asking her questions and telling him this is not the appropriate way to approach her. She said she would answer the questions but only if they were by the proper channels. She thinks he might be scamming her.  It is later and I am reading a magazine. I see an article featuring the same man. He is a CEO of the company we work for. It’s a feature article about successful workers who also have children. I think my colleague has missed out on an opportunity to be in the article because she didn’t give the man an opportunity to speak with her. I laugh because this is typical of her. I show my colleagues who also laugh because this is typical.

I am with my best friend K. We are in a jewellery store and an older woman with grey hair is helping me. There is a shiny glass and gold jewellery case between us. I ask to have my engagement ring remade as it doesn’t fit well. The woman takes my ring into a back room. She returns with three rings. Only one fits me it’s thick gold and has green and red stones in it. I try it on and don’t like it. I ask her if she can remake it. She is annoyed and says in an irritated way that she still has my original ring out the back, she didn’t remake it she just used an old one she already had. I take my old ring and we leave. We are outside the shop there are old stone buildings and it looks like European streets. I ask my friend why the woman was annoyed with me and she says I was arrogant. I feel bewildered.

I am at work, though it doesn’t look like my work. My student has behaved unprofessionally and my colleagues are annoyed with her. They complain to me. I feel bad that my student has been unprofessional and also feel bad for her. I have to speak to her about it. My student then merges into another colleague (they are two people at the same time so my colleague is my student). I am not in the scene but I am somehow watching my student without being there. She is on the computer which has a tropical island screen background. She is reading emails from her partner. Her partner has broken up with her and her whole world feels like it is falling apart. We are also somehow in Holland. In my dream this explains why she behaved unprofessionally.
There were some planes. An airport. The planes were quite small. There was some shouting.
Diane was going down on me. There was an orange chair and raffel tickets. Diane won a trip on the orange chair and I wanted to win it. She said there is enough room for both of us.

I was walking along a path which is where I used to live on a boat. I saw an old friend and neighbour called A. I wanted to avoid him. I saw him on the escalators inside a big shop. He did not see me. But I was conscious if he did what I would look like. I was wearing a big baggy bomber jacket and my hair was tied back. Walking away I reached a bridge with big queues. People were calling out with impatience. I remember thinking how strange that the old bridge had been opened and there was no queue. I went to the entrance and even though lots of people started shouting at me I continued along the bridge. Inside there was a big mall. Tiger had a big sale on. I rushed around thinking about presents I could buy then decided otherwise. I exited the mall and passed an old lady. We stood in an ancient walled section. Some flowers and bird song was around. The old lady was struggling with her stick. She was wearing beige colours. I asked if she needed help she said yes. So I tried to help her along. Another woman....I don't know who she is popped up and said she would help the old lady. I was going the other way. And neither of them said thank you. I felt disappointed and continued on my way. The other lady was much better at helping the lady though.

in a huge opulent mansion. I was wearing an expensive dress. It was my aunties mansion and I was with my Irish family. I needed to go to the toilet so I ran off. I went the wrong way but eventually found a bathroom. I couldn't lock the door...the silver bolt was broken so I went to the loo. As I was peeing I heard sounds and worried someone would come in I got up to try and lock the door. I got urine on my dress as I hobbled over. I realised no one was coming so I went back to finish but it happened again. There were some other smaller locks but because I was panicking I couldn't use them. When I fi ished I looked in the mirror and ghought I looked beautiful. My hair was bright blonde and cut short. It suited me. Then I heard sounds and rushing out met two young people in the kitchen. Hello I said to them smiling. The girl was shy the guy was friendly. They said they were my uncle Motorbikes cousins and I sad I was my aunt motorbikes cousin...I said does that make us cousins? The girl was finishing her sandwich and got up to empty her plate and said no I don't think so. I was smiling and said twice removed?

Villanelle was walking around a party looking for trouble. It was a BBC event and there were so many staff on shift. Lots of people behind the bar not doing anything. Katie (my colleague) said how after lockdown she wouldn't come back to work immediately because it was too much. Lockdown was beginning the next day. Villanelle was walking around. She got to a point where she was strutting around in her knickers with a gun pouch in front of her crotch. Someone decided to lure her down and confront her....I felt scared and ran away. I ran home and hid in my bedroom which was filled with glass windows. The curtains open in late evening I began to close them all immediately. There was a silver tin beer van selling drinks outside. For a brief moment I was a black man on a balcony with a plate of food trying to do his homework. There is a cabin outside...washing hanging up to dry in there. I think its a good idea to dry clothes there. Then there's a knock at the door. I lock myself in my room and turn the lights off. I hear my friend is also in the house. I quickly go out and get her to come and hide In my room. I lock the door and try and bolt it but the top lock is broken but there is a silver one that I pull across. We hear activity and we are scared but all we both talk about is the lock.

I was sat on the floor of a cathedral, up in the triphorium. I had to use a large kitchen knife to scrape the coating off of a hammer, or large mallet. It needed to be put back into the pipe organ so the organist could play and record that evening. One of my assistants was there and one or two other people I couldn't really see.

Queuing in a supermarket at the tobacco counter part. Instead of cigarettes they had laundry detergents all lined up on the shelves behind. I almost bought some blue lenor but decided against it - i wanted to get something that was eco-friendly but I couldn't find what I was looking for. There may have been cigarettes at some point I'd leant my wedding dress to someone, possibly my younger sister and then was waiting in a cafe, maybe for her to finish with it. My other sister reminded me about a family zoom, or online game we were going to play and i was supposed to send a link to my cousin before it started. I realised it was 7.30 already and I hadn't done it.

at an army/ training boot camp, wandering around. maybe someone had hung themselves? lots of people shouting, decided to leave. There was a boy - teenager? - there who wanted to leave as well. walked through the mens' bathroom to leave, put hands against eyes as blinkers so i didn't see anyone was in a local park or graveyard where teenagers hung out decided to visit my sister. had a friend with me in a car and drove past my eldest sister. I was happy to see her, signalling to eachother, asking where she was going. she mimed going for a swim and that we should join her it was a nice sunny day thought about some woods near by sister's house and that i'd never been in a long queue at Aldi, where i used to work. wanted to pay for an ice lolly i was already eating. can remember the man's name who was on the til but he was having trouble with finding the right codes to enter. was happy i didn't work there anymore

in  bed with a friend. we lived together but were't exactly a couple. the house was big and modern, lots of warm pine colours, a bit scandinavian. i decided i needed to leave in order to have more boyfriends, rather than stay with her. i was more interested in men than women. the words did't come out exatly as i wanted them too our house keeper was arrested for trying to poison us with some fresh pumpkin juice she had laced. she poured it out of a hollowed out pumpkin into a jug into the sink. then i was part of a late victorian/edwardian family. we wore long dresses and white caps and aprons. we drove to a neighbour's house, with fields all around, and my sister was married off on one of the boys. i ran down a paved lane thinking i might be past it but i'm sure i'll find something

In either a hotel room or a students dorm room looking out the window. The sea was a bright turquoise. Swimming in the sea with a few other people, we were fundraising to save it/clean it up. I was lifted out by someone and this made me the star of what we were doing, then it was someone else's turn. Back in the room, i was waiting for someone to come in. Think we were going to have sex, I felt turned on. Driving down a road in a village, the neighbourhood was poor but had been saved recently by a vegan deli that had opened and turned things around. Think it was the village near where my mum grew up.

In a town square which was fairly empty. there was a huge Sycamore tree with lots of carvings in it and the trunk had grown into figures. Like a living totem pole . Sense of foreboding/ominous.  The tree stood over a book shop. I went in with commander Chakotay (from Voyager) they made him pay to get in as he couldn't get in for free as a veteran - they did not accept a gas bill as proof of ID. the receptionist reminded us to out on our face masks.The book shop was huge. we split up to hunt for something. lots of old fashioned books, modern old and occult, which i think was what he was looking for. I found a section labelled 'Philip Green' then left.  I was in an outdoor shopping precinct with Mila we headed towards a vintage tea room style cafe I had been to before. Mila starting dancing wildly with a stranger when we went in and I felt awkward. We were told to put on our face masks again . the cafe was big and spread over three floors or so. We went up but then I was on my own. I knew that my two other companions were up on the roof. The King of Ghana arrived and sat at a table, I knew he was after my two friends. I needed to get to the roof without him realising. i went into one of many toilets but couldn't close the door. He helped me figure out the weird spring loaded lock and was really friendly.  Then I was in another stall struggling to take off my coat whilst trying not to drop my hat and gloves. I was sat on the toilet surrounded by parents and two of my sisters who were all keeping the door closed for me. it was hard to balance on the loo because it was really thin.

i was sitting in a large lecture hall.  brightly lit with grey fold down chairs. I was a student at an american style college. it was very busy. lots of people in big groups and wandering around, there were some cheerleaders walking through. there was general air of excitement and some people had toy guns and were trying to control the crowd. i had a toy gun in my hand at one point, there were two safety catches that i struggled with. i was sitting near a man and we were chatting and flirting a little bit. we asked each other how old we were - we were both mature students as everyone else was about 18. we were both in our 30's, though he looked much older. when the lecture finished it was understood that we would go on a date.

In a bedroom. I woke up and had lots of spots all over my forehead and some on left cheek. I felt strange and took my temperature - I had a fever of 37.1° I didn't know whether to go to work or not, meanwhile M. Was getting ready to go to his work. Took my temp again and fever was worse. By now I was running very late.had a text from my assistant asking where I was, I told him I was ill. I had a bottle of half drunk advocaat with a message to the venue (where I was supposed to be working) from my assistant. I was annoyed he had over stepped the mark. Then I was an old glamorous lady with her teenage granddaughter walking through busy town centre, we were half real, half characters on a soap opera who had run out of money. Some people came up to us and asked me if I'd pull out granddaughters eye lash for £120, while they filmed.We agreed. Stood out side a pub waiting to do more filming, there was a bad smell from somewhere.

I was walking down a road and i went past some local shops which has wine bottles outside, advertising their wine and it's price. An inner monologue/ voice over told me it's how the shop keepers decide on competitive pricing. i walked over a pedestrian bridge across a busy road, it twisted and turned a bit so i was a bit confused when i eventually came out on the pavement again.  eventually i recognised where i was just as a man asked me if i knew where i was going. i checked my bag - i was carrying fresh muffins which were getting crumpled. Chris (an old friend from school, don't really talk to him anymore)- the person i was meeting appeared and took them off me. he was with Lauren (an old best friend, we fell out some years ago) and someone from schools younger brother I think. we were staying at Chris' house for the night. Lauren said something snarky to me - i see you haven't bothered to dress up/ you've not made any effort as usual. I told her to shut up and pointed out that she wasn't wearing makeup either. I stood up to her and felt a bit jittery but proud. i felt left out because everyone had been hanging out for a few days already we were at Chris' house. i hoovered some bits off the rug and wiped up a spillage. we sat around chatting. i realised we were breaking the socialising rules though no one seemed bothered. Chris' mum told his younger sister that one their pet bees had died, she cried in a really hammed up and over dramatic kind of way. i saw her face in a close up. i was at their back door looking at their garden which was a bit wild and backed onto fields. a fox/dog came down looking at me. I knew it was a guardian of sorts, like Sirius Black from Harry Potter. I imagined meeting him later. then i imagined being in my old attic bedroom and he was an Owl this time who would knock on the roof with its beak so i knew to let him in. I liked having an animal friend/guide and felt connected with something. another dog showed up which looked injured. i called Chris' parents to come and help it.

I was in a typical school hall - parquet floor, a stage, chairs etc. I was with a group of others and we were starting a competition/ game. We had to follow clues like following small arrows and switching switches, running through corridors and stairwells until we made it back to the hall. We were told that we hadn't discovered a huge underground part of the place and had done stuff wrong, which meant Zombies were going to attack. We barricaded and waited.there was footfall sounds and banging on some of the doors, I looked underneath to see feet heading my way. I bolted the door. I turned to a man who was muscular and had a weapon and suggested we break off and try to survive. We ran out side around houses and through gardens, I collected an apple and some tomatoes. We ran in a circle, back to the place. People were lining up, waiting to commit suicide. A man was explaining to everyone from a podium how to hold the gun. I suggested we go back to mine - lockable gate, first floor and I'd just done a food shop. I later changed my mind and decided I lived in a house with big garden. We ran holding hands, he was a bit grumpy and not talkative.

Night time. Someone, possibly builders were trying to saw through the board which covers one of the windows downstairs. i was afraid it was people trying to break in, i ran upstairs and shut the door which has a lock and tried to call the police.  I was downstairs again, this time i was with Martin and we crept out side onto the driveway and around a large white van. the van started to move and follow us around the drive without it's headlights on. we ran back inside and i struggled to close the front door in time.

walking down a quiet residential street in Oxford with my youngest sister. I'd forgotten to put trousers on and hoped no one would notice. we managed to find a seat on the busy seat. it was opposite a chinese student who was coughing and sneezing so much that it made vomit, she rushed off to the bathroom. that made my sister be sick and she pujed over the girls luggage, her and her friend hurried away, my sister finished being sick into a paper bag. it switched to a plastic bag and i tied it up and put it in the bin. i had some sick in my mouth and spat it out.  then i was on a train with people from college, we were discussing our graduation night and how we all got drunk at a friends house. i fell asleep while watching a film. there were alerts lights on the train how you would have in an aeroplane, we were supposed to see to them when they went off.  my friend Charlotte was cooking me breakfast. she fried an egg in its cardboard box, just balanced on the hob

Saw L on the internet or something in a performance. Robert Pattinson was in it too, everyone in the small cast was laughing and joking together at the end and posing for photographs. I felt very jealous and disappointed with myself because she had done something with her life and I hadn't. There was something about a road.

At Hogwarts type of school. Alone in room getting ready for event. I wore a long sky blue skirt. In a big room lit by candles and fire light. I poured milk on my friends for a laugh and immediately regretted it. I think someone filmed it. Then I was in a different room, in what felt like an empty or abandoned building. I was sitting around a table with loads of people from university, we were about to have a dinner. We were waiting for Lorraine who had gone to the loo and not come back, we heard there was trouble in France where she was from and were a bit worried. Then I was getting on a bus from my old bus stop at home. School buses went past. I was with Daddy. Got on the bus and I took ages to pay, eventually driver let me on because it turned out my dad was famous and possibly now called Jason. Then I was scampering across rocks like in the peak District. they had been carved with lots of short lines. There were dogs running around off their lead I was a bit apprehensive but they minded their own business. I thought about my nephew who is terrified of dogs. One of the dogs started sniffing/licking horse or badger poo. I thought it was a bit gross.

I was in a room with a few other people and we were looking at flat A4-sized packages that had labels on them. On the labels were names and disabilities/deformations of the people who's names it were. The packages were the people in some kind of deep-frozen dehydrated form and there were exaggerated depictions of the people on the cover of the packages. A woman explained that this is a human trafficking institutions and people come in and choose the 'package/person' they want and this person then gets transformed into a live state again and is sold to whoever chose them.
I was with a group of people in a snowy forest. We had horses/other animals and were hiding from another group of people.
I was starting uni but registration and everything was closed because of Covid.

My sister was held in a room by my mother and I was in the room too. Then we were in a supermarket looking for lunch. I wanted to go for tomato soup but then remembered that I prefer edeka soup over Lidl tomato soup. I said I wanted to go to that supermarket.

my mum and I were worried about her mum and tried to find her, but we couldn't. Instead we took a walk with my dad's mum in a an outdoor area with many lovely meadows. We came to a café that was situated next to a river and we had to cross the river to get to the cafe. The staff of the case were just preparing the birthday celebration of someone.  I met with two separate friends and was walking through Glasgow with them individually and explained the project to them. It felt like I was talking about a superpower that I have. They were highly intrigued.  I was in the White House talking to its chief of staff, Sam Seaborne.

I was a clownfish working in a theatre company. There wasn't a part for me on the upcoming play, so the director and I decided that I would take a new member of our company (also a clownfish) to receive training. We went into a water container that would be transported by someone/thing else. Somehow, this container itself was surrounded by water itself...I think we might have been in the ocean.   At some point we managed to leave the container and we find the shore near a small town. The moment we left the water we turned into humans. We went into a shop with lots of animals and my protégée picked up a small snake with which he chased me. I have a phobia of snakes so I freaked out and ran. No matter how often I told him to stop, he didn't and thought it was funny. The snake grew more and more in size the longer he chased me.  I left him them to his own devices as I was deeply disappointed in him. I tried to find my way back to the water. The rest of the theatre company caught up with me and had my protégée with them. They told him to apologise.

I was back in school, in German class. Our teacher returned a test to us and I had a 1 (=A, very good). However, she then made everyone who had very good results stand up and threatened to have us fail the class. She wanted to give an example of how racism works, choosing a group of people by an arbitrary characteristic and then treat them differently because of it. I went out of the room after class with my friends and I was very upset by it all. Not because she threatened to fail us but by the fact that this is how people in the world sometimes treat each other. I started crying and my friends alerted our teacher who then came over and talked to me.
I got home to my flat and caught two people in it who had broken in m they didn't flee but waited with me until I caught the police.
there was a secret land and someone sneaked me in twice. I wasn't supposed to be there and had to pretend I belong and fit in.

I was living in a boarding school that was in a big old castle. I was in the toilets in a cubicle and when I opened the door there were 4 guys threatening me. I somehow managed to escape them and then afterwards my best friend got upset with me because she cared for one of the guys and apparently I had hurt him.
